The fasciculus gracilis is wedge-shaped on transverse section and lies next the posterior median septum, its base being at the surface of the medulla spinalis, and its apex directed toward the posterior gray commissure. It increases in size from below upward, and consists of long thin fibers that are derived from the posterior nerve roots, and ascend as far as the medulla oblongata, where they end in the nucleus gracilis. The tract of Goll was named after Swiss neuroanatomist Friedrich Goll[WP].

name: obsolete regional part of superior olive
blood feather
description: A developing feather

name: manual digit 2 epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a manual digit 2.

name: obsolete regional part of caudate nucleus
right thymus lobe
description: A thymus lobe that is in the right side of a thymus.

name: nucleus raphe obscurus
description: The raphe obscurus projects to the cerebellar lobes VI and VII and to crus II along with the nucleus raphe pontis . This so called obscure nucleus has also been implicated in the modulation of the hypoglossal nerve. It has been observed that the ablation of this nucleus causes a change in the firing pattern in the XII nerve . In addition, the raphe obscurus mediates expiration via the inhibitory effect of serotonin and depresses periodic synaptic potentials . It has also been shown that this nucleus stimulates gastrointestinal motor function; microinjections of 5-HT into the n.r. obscurus increase gastric movement . [WP,unvetted].

name: glomerular capillary
description: the small branching blood vessels in the kidney glomerulus that receives blood from the kidney afferent arterioles; these capillaries are under high pressure for filtering within the glomerulus

name: olfactory apparatus chamber
description: An anatomical chamber that is part of the olfactory apparatus, consisting of cavity walls (nasal epithelium and mucosal layers) and the space bounded anteriorly by the nares and posteriorly by the choanae, when these structures are present.

name: obsolete retinal cone cell inner segment
description: The retinal cone cell region which contains the machinery of the cell (mitochondria, golgi, endoplasmic reticulum, etc) and where opsin molecules are assembled and passed to be part of the outer segment region

name: marginal zone of spleen
description: the zone between the red and white pulp of the spleen containing numerous macrophages and lymphocytes, and a rich plexus of sinusoids supplied by white pulp arterioles carrying blood-borne antigens

name: parietal operculum
description: The parietal operculum, forming the superior bank of the sylvian fissure, as studied in the cat, contains the secondary somatosensory representation, 'S-II', and a second somatotopic representation (parietal ventral, or PV). Anatomically, primate S-II receives inputs from area 3 and area 1, and projects to PV and area 7. PV has projections to area 5 and premotor areas. [WP,unvetted].

name: bony vertebral centrum
description: Ossified form of a vertebral centrum, a skeletal element that functionally replaces the notochord[VSAP,modified].

name: anteroventral plate
description: Dermal bone that is part of the scapular complex in placoderms.

name: medullary reticular formation
description: The reticular formation is a series of brain nuclei located in the medulla oblongata

name: crista dorsalis humeri
description: Small hooked process on the dorsal aspect of the humeral shaft; it does not extend on to the glenoid head. The m subscapularis is inserted on it.

name: lateral recess
description: A part of the inferior cavity of the olfactory organ, found in anurans.

name: right uterine tube
description: A fallopian tube that is part of a right side of organism [Automatically generated definition].

name: caudal fin upper lobe
description: Surface structure that is the dorsal portion of the caudal fin.

name: nauplius stage
description: The free-swimming first stage of the larva of certain crustaceans, having an unsegmented body with three pairs of appendages and a single median eye. The eye is known for that reason as the 'naupliar eye', and is often absent in later developmental stages, although it is retained into the adult form in some groups, such as the Notostraca.

name: thyrohyoid cartilage
description: This small finger of cartilage completes the connection between the thyrohyoid bone and the thyroid cartilage (rostral cornu)

name: serratus dorsalis superior muscle
description: The serratus dorsalis superior is a thin, quadrilateral muscle, situated at the upper and back part of the thorax. It arises by a thin and broad aponeurosis from the lower part of the ligamentum nuchae, from the spinous processes of the seventh cervical and upper two or three thoracic vertebr√¶ and from the supraspinal ligament. Inclining downward and lateralward it becomes muscular, and is inserted, by four fleshy digitations, into the upper borders of the second, third, fourth, and fifth ribs, a little beyond their angles. [WP,unvetted].

name: principal sulcus
description: Sulcus in the frontal lobe of the macaque. (Brain Info)

name: inferior mesenteric nerve plexus
description: The inferior mesenteric plexus is derived chiefly from the aortic plexus. It surrounds the inferior mesenteric artery, and divides into a number of secondary plexuses, which are distributed to all the parts supplied by the artery, viz. , the left colic and sigmoid plexuses, which supply the descending and sigmoid parts of the colon; and the superior hemorrhoidal plexus, which supplies the rectum and joins in the pelvis with branches from the pelvic plexuses.

name: adductor crest
description: A bony crest on venteral side of femur that is the attachment site for the adductor muscles. [AD]

name: posterior nuchal plate
description: Paired nuchal plate that is part of dorsal fin proximal radial 2 and usually in contact with the middle nuchal plate.

name: accessory optic system
description: Subdivision of visual system that processes movements of images across retina and regulates the movement of eyes to keep the image stable.

name: carina distalis
description: In a zygapophysis that has ridges and sulci, the distal ridge.

name: anterior lateral line system
description: The anterior lateral line system develops from cranial ectodermal placodes, situated between the eye and the ear, that give rise to both the neuromasts and the anterior lateral line sensory nerves that innervate the neuromasts. The anterior lateral line system consists of small sensory patches (neuromasts) located superficially on the skin or just under the skin in fluid-filled canals on the head of all fishes and most amphibians and are innervated by several lateral line nerves, which project to the hindbrain. The anterior lateral line system is stimulated by local water displacements and vibrations, and detects propulsion of the fish through the water, as well as facilitating shoaling, prey capture, and predator and obstacle avoidance.

name: cerebellum vermis culmen
description: The culmen is the portion of the anterior vermis adjacent to the primary fissure of cerebellum. The culmen and the anterior parts of the quadrangular lobules form the lobus culminis[WP].

name: anterior lingual gland
description: the small glands located near the apex of the tongue on either side of the frenulum

name: ceratobranchial 4 cartilage
description: Ceratobranchial cartilage that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with epibranchial 4 cartilage or bone.

name: white matter of hindbrain
description: A white matter that is part of the hindbrain.

name: pedal digit 4 metatarsal endochondral element
description: A pedal digit 4 metatarsal bone or its cartilage or pre-cartilage precursor.

name: spinal cord gray commissure
description: the band of grey substance spanning the midline of the spinal cord that surrounds the central canal

name: rhombomere
description: A segment of the developing hindbrain[ZFA]. In the vertebrate embryo, a rhombomere is a transiently divided segment of the developing neural tube, within the hindbrain region (a neuromere) in the area that will eventually become the rhombencephalon. The rhombomeres appear as a series of slightly constricted swellings in the neural tube, caudal to the cephalic flexure.[WP].

name: pectineal ligament
description: an extension of the lacunar ligament that runs on the pectineal line of the pubic bone.

name: mesenchyme of sublingual gland
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a developing sublingual gland [Automatically generated definition].

name: muscle layer of spongiose part of urethra
description: A muscular coat that is part of a spongiose part of urethra.

name: interdigital region between manual digits 2 and 3
description: An interdigital region that adjacent_to a manual digit 2 and adjacent_to a manual digit 3.

name: epithelium of mammary gland
description: the epithelial layer of the luminal surfaces of the mammary gland

name: neuron projection bundle connecting eye with brain
description: A neuron projection bundle that connects the retina or its analog in the eye with the brain. This includes the vertebrate optic nerve (not truly a nerve) as well as analogous structures such as the Bolwig nerve in Drosophila

name: posterior inferior cerebellar artery
description: The posterior inferior cerebellar artery (PICA), the largest branch of the vertebral, is one of the three main arterial blood supplies for the cerebellum.

name: chordamesoderm
description: The central region of trunk mesoderm. This tissue forms the notochord

name: axial mesoderm
description: The axial mesoderm includes the prechordal mesoderm and the chordamesoderm. It gives rise to the prechordal plate and to the notochord.

name: amphibian larval stage
description: Amphibian larvae, sometimes called pollywogs or tadpoles, hatch from eggs and begin to grow limbs and other adult physical features at various times, depending on the species, before they metamorphose into the adult form.

name: larva
description: A distinct juvenile form many animals undergo before metamorphosis into adults. Animals with indirect development such as insects, amphibians, or cnidarians typically have a larval phase of their life cycle.

name: tadpole
description: An an organism at the tadpole stage

name: tadpole stage
description: wholly aquatic larval stage in the life cycle of an amphibian, particularly of a frog or toad[WP]. XAO: The stages from feeding to the end of metamorphosis. Encompasses Weisz's first-form tadpole (equivalent to NF stages 45 to 49), second-form tadpole (NF 49 to 56) and third-form tadpole (NF 56 to 60-plus) stages.

name: tegmentum
description: The ventral topographic division of the midbrain; the dorsal topographic division is the tectum. Meckel (1817; see English translation, 1832, vol. 2, p. 467) apparently introduced the term and roughly its definition here for macrodissected adult humans, except he excluded the cerebral peduncle (Tarin, 1753), a white matter tract at the base of the midbrain, which is still common today but is included here. As defined here, tegmentum refers to the whole of the midbrain (Baer, 1837) excluding the tectum but including the pretectal region (Scalia, 1972); see Swanson (2000, pp. 522, 526). Usage of this term is very complex, inconsistent, and illogical; see for example Crosby et al. (1962, pp. 221, 260, 262), Carpenter (1976, p. 367 ff.).

name: midbrain tegmentum
description: Ventral part of the midbrain, separated from the hindbrain by the isthmus[ISBN:0471888893]. Subdivision of the midbrain lying anterior to the tectum and posterior to the substantia nigra and cerebral peduncle[FMA] The part of the midbrain extending from the substantia nigra to the cerebral aqueduct in a horizontal section of the midbrain. It forms the floor of the midbrain that surrounds the cerebral aqueduct[WP].

name: olecranon fossa
description: A deep evacuation in the bone, into which the anconeal process of the ulna passes when the elbow joint is extended.

name: posterior chamber of eyeball
description: the ring-like space, filled with aqueous humor, between the iris/pupil anteriorly and the lens and ciliary body posteriorly

name: fasciculus aberans
description: The fasciulus aberrans is a distinct bundle of fibers at the dorsal aspect of the anterior commisure. These fibers travel in the internal capsule between the putamen and caudate nuclei, and cross the midline to connect the dorsal neocortex of the two hemispheres. When the fasciculus aberrans is absent, the fibers connecting the neocortex of the two hemispheres takes a diffderent route through the external capsule[Johnson et al., (1982a, 1982b, 1994)]

name: pharyngeal arch artery 2
description: The vessels formed within the second pair of branchial arches in embryogenesis

name: lacrimal lake
description: A small cistern-like area of the conjunctiva at the medial angle of the eye, in which the tears collect after bathing the front surface of the eyeball and the conjunctival sac.

name: tarsal gland
description: A modified lobulated sebaceous gland at the rim of an eyelid, responsible for the supply of meibum.

name: somite 15
description: Undifferentiated mesodermal component of early trunk or tail segment or metamere, derived from paraxial mesoderm; forms the myotome, sclerotome and perhaps dermatome. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: carcass
description: A body of a multi-cellular organism that is no longer living.

name: discoid placenta
description: A placenta in which part of the chorion remains smooth, while the other part interacts with the endometrium to form the placenta. The maternal blood cells are in direct contact with the fetal chorion.

name: obsolete lateral nucleus of ventral telencephalon
description: Peripheral nucleus of the ventral telencephalon that has migrated to the periphery of the brain. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

name: upper primary incisor tooth
description: A primary incisor tooth that is part of a upper jaw region.

name: periamygdaloid cortex
description: Is located ventral to the basal nucleus and has three subdivisions: the periamygdaloid cortex, the medial division, and the sulcal division.

name: parenchyma of quadrate lobe of liver
description: A liver parenchyma that is part of a quadrate lobe of liver.

name: tetrapod frontal bone
description: the bone forming the forehead and roof of the eye orbit

name: antler
description: Antlers are the usually large, branching bony appendages on the heads of most deer species.

name: pectoral fin proximal radial bone 3
description: pectoral fin proximal radial 3 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: arthropod optic lobe
description: A region of the adult brain that processes the visual information from the compound eyes.

name: dorsal artery of clitoris
description: The dorsal artery of clitoris is a branch of the internal pudendal artery.

name: somite 17
description: Undifferentiated mesodermal component of early trunk or tail segment or metamere, derived from paraxial mesoderm; forms the myotome, sclerotome and perhaps dermatome. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: vagus X ganglion
description: the group of sensory neuron cell bodies associated with the vagus nerve

name: autonomic nerve
description: The autonomic nerve is a small nerve which carries postganglionic sympathetic and parasympathetic neurons from the zygomaticotemporal nerve; a branch of the maxillary nerve, to the lacrimal nerve; a branch of the ophthalmic nerve. These neurons derive from the superior cervical ganglion and the pterygopalatine ganglion respectively. They will travel to the lacrimal gland via the lacrimal nerve. Parasympathetic will induce lacrimation and vice versa.

name: surface groove
description: A furrow or an incomplete tube.

name: mesometrium
description: A mesentery that is part of a uterus [Automatically generated definition].

name: spinocerebellar tract
description: This tract conveys interoceptive, proprioceptive, and exteroceptive information from the body's internal organs, and from the trunk, extremities, and neck region to the Cerebellum.

name: obsolete regional part of supraoptic nucleus
raphe nuclei
description: The raphe nuclei are thin plates of cells in and immediately adjacent to the sagittal plane.

name: lamina of spiral limbus
description: The osseous spiral lamina consists of two plates of bone, and between these are the canals for the transmission of the filaments of the acoustic nerve. On the upper plate of that part of the lamina which is outside the vestibular membrane, the periosteum is thickened to form the limbus spiralis (or limbus lamin√¶ spiralis), this ends externally in a concavity, the sulcus spiralis internus, which represents, on section, the form of the letter C. [WP,unvetted].

name: ganglion part of peripheral nervous system
description: A spatially aggregated collection of nerve cell bodies in the PNS, consisting of one or more subpopulations that share cell type, chemical phenotype, and connections. (CUMBO)

name: biliary ductule
description: One of the fine terminal elements of the bile duct system, leaving the portal canal, and pursuing a course at the periphery of a lobule of the liver[BTO]. the excretory ducts of the liver that connect the interlobular ductules to the right or left hepatic duct[MP]

name: collection of hair on forehead
description: A collection of hairs that grows on the forehead.

name: musculus rectus abdominis profundus
description: A component of the rectus abdominal muscle that is some taxa (see comment) forms a disctinct and separate muscle.

name: sternum
description: A midventral endochondral skeletal element which represents the origin site of the pectoral muscles[PHENOSCAPE:ad].

name: greater trochanter
description: The greater trochanter (great trochanter) of the femur is a large, irregular, quadrilateral eminence and a part of the skeletal system. It is directed a little lateralward and backward, and, in the adult, is about 1 cm lower than the head. Because the pelvic outlet in the female is larger than in the male, there is a greater distance between the greater trochanters in the female. It has two surfaces and four borders. [WP,unvetted].

name: lower rhombic lip
description: Posterior portion of the rhombic lip contained within rhombomeres 2-8. Gives rise to several brainstem nuclei and choroid plexus.

name: supraoccipital cartilage element
description: A cartilaginous condensation that has the potential to develop into a supraoccipital bone.

name: basiventral
description: Basiventrals are bilaterally paired cartilages lateral to the notochord which are replaced by ossified parapophyses or hemal arches.

name: os basale
description: A bone that forms both the floor of the braincase and the posterior part of the skull.

name: chromaffin paraganglion
description: Small bodies containing chromaffin cells occurring outside of the adrenal medulla, most commonly near the sympathetic ganglia and in organs such as the kidney, liver, heart and gonads.

name: m. intertransversarius capitis inferior
description: Involved in the movement of the head.

name: root of vagus nerve
description: A root of cranial nerve that is part of a vagus nerve.

name: stomodeal lumen
description: An anatomical cavity that surrounded_by a stomodeum.

name: epiotic
description: Endochondral bone that borders that medial edge of the posttemporal fossa. The epiotics are sutured to parietals and supraoccipital dorsally, the exoccipitals ventrally and the pterotics laterally. The epiotic is a paired bone.

name: mesenchyme of submandibular gland primordium
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a submandibular gland primordium.

name: primary auditory cortex
description: The part of the auditory cortex that is located on the superior temporal gyrus in the temporal lobe and receives point-to-point input from the ventral division of the medial geniculate complex.

name: hypobranchial 2 bone
description: Hypobranchial bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates with a median skeletal element medially and with a ceratobranchial 2 element laterally. Develops in hypobranchial 2 cartilage.

name: posterior cranial fossa
description: The infratentorial compartment that contains the CEREBELLUM and BRAIN STEM. It is formed by the posterior third of the superior surface of the body of the sphenoid (SPHENOID BONE), by the occipital, the petrous, and mastoid portions of the TEMPORAL BONE, and the posterior inferior angle of the PARIETAL BONE.

name: bony part of pharyngotympanic tube
description: The bony part of pharyngotympanic tube is about 12 mm. in length. It begins in the carotid wall of the tympanic cavity, below the septum canalis musculotubarii, and, gradually narrowing, ends at the angle of junction of the squama and the petrous portion of the temporal bone, its extremity presenting a jagged margin which serves for the attachment of the cartilaginous portion.

name: epiphysis of fourth metacarpal bone
description: An epiphysis that is part of a metacarpal bone of digit 4 [Automatically generated definition].

name: inferior gemellus muscle
description: Gemellus muscle that arises from the upper part of the tuberosity of the ischium, immediately below the groove for the Obturator internus tendon. It blends with the lower part of the tendon of the Obturator internus, and is inserted with it into the medial surface of the greater trochanter.

name: palmar pad
description: An autopod pad that is in the metacarpal region

name: lumbar vertebra 5
description: The fifth lumbar vertebra counting from the top down. Note that members of this class are not necessarily homologous[ncit,modified].

name: diaphysis of tibia
description: A diaphysis that is part of a tibia.

name: postcoracoid
description: The posterior of the two coracoid elements found in basal tetrapods. Corresponds directly to the 'coracoid' of synapsids. [AD]

name: proximal epiphysis of proximal phalanx of manual digit 1
description: A proximal epiphysis that is part of a proximal phalanx of manual digit 1 [Automatically generated definition].

name: maxillary vein
description: A vein that consists of a short trunk which accompanies the first part of the internal maxillary artery. It is formed by a confluence of the veins of the pterygoid plexus, and passes backward between the sphenomandibular ligament and the neck of the mandible, and unites with the superficial temporal vein to form the retromandibular vein. [WP,unvetted].

name: anatomical line along groove
description: Anatomical line that delineates a furrow or depression in an organ or tissue.

name: upper arm connective tissue
description: A portion of connective tissue that is part of a forelimb stylopod [Automatically generated definition].

name: articular capsule
description: An articular capsule (or joint capsule) is an envelope surrounding a synovial joint. [WP,unvetted].

name: flocculonodular lobe
description: The flocculonodular lobe is a lobe of the cerebellum consisting of the nodule and the flocculus. It is closely associated with the vestibulocerebellum. [WP,unvetted].

name: fornix of vagina
description: The deepest portions of the vagina, extending into the recesses created by the vaginal portion of cervix[WP,unvetted].

name: eyelid
description: A fold of skin that covers and protects part of the eyeball. Examples: upper eyelid, lower eyelid, nictitating membrane

name: tibial vein
description: One of the veins of the lower leg; empty into the popliteal vein

name: vertebral artery
description: the first branch of the left and right subclavian arteries that merge to form the single midline basilar artery; branches of the vertebral arteries supply the musculature of the neck

name: hepatic portal system
description: A portal system that begins in capillaries in the wall of the digestive tract and and runs as the hepatic portal vein to the liver.

name: frontal sulcus
description: A sulcus of brain that is part of a frontal cortex.

name: acinus of areolar gland
description: An acinus that is part of a areolar gland.

name: cerebrospinal fluid
description: A clear, colorless, bodily fluid, that occupies the subarachnoid space and the ventricular system around and inside the brain and spinal cord.

name: lung vasculature
description: The lung vasculature is composed of the tubule structures that carry blood or lymph in the lungs[GO].

name: hindlimb intermedium bone
description: A proximal tarsal bone that articulates with the fibula.

name: intermedium
description: Endochondral carpal bone articulating with the ulnare and the radiale.

name: nasal tentacle
description: A fleshy appendage ringing the snout of a Star-nosed mole.

name: tricuspid valve leaflet
description: A valve leaflet that is part of a tricuspid valve.

name: sublaminar layer S2
description: A retinal neural layer that is immediately adjacent to the S1 and S3 layers and comprises 20 percent of the inner plexiform layer of retina.

name: retinal tapetum lucidum
description: A tapetum lucidum that is part of the retina, within the cytoplasm of the retinal epithelium

name: neural arch 1
description: Neural arch that is the anteriormost neural arch.

name: plantaris
description: Plantaris is a vestigial structure and one of the superficial muscles of the posterior crural compartment of the leg. It is innervated by the tibial nerve (S1, S2) . It is composed of a thin muscle belly and a long thin tendon. It is approximately 2-4 inches long, and is absent in 7 - 10% of the human population. It is one of the plantar flexors in the superior compartment of the leg along with the gastrocnemius, and soleus. The plantaris is considered an unimportant muscle, it mainly acts with gastrocnemius[WP].

name: autopalatine
description: Endochondral bone that is part of the antero-lateral region of the palate. Commonly, it articulates with the maxilla anterolaterally and with the ethmoidal region medially. It may also articulate with the dermopalatine ventro-laterally and with the entopterygoid posteriorly. The autopalatine is paired.

name: palatine bone
description: A paired dermal bone situated in the mid-palate[Palaeos].

name: outer epithelial layer of tympanic membrane
description: A portion of the external acoustic meatus epithelium which makes up the outer (cuticular) layer of the tympanic membrane

name: subchondral region of epiphysis
description: The bone region of the epiphysis that provides underlying mechanical and physiological support for the cartilage of joint articular surfaces.

name: anal fin proximal radial bone
description: anal fin proximal radial element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: articular fossa of opercle
description: Fossa of opercle that articulates with hyomandibular condyle for opercle.

name: tunica media of pulmonary trunk
description: Tunica media of artery which is continuous with the myocardium of right ventricle.[FMA]

name: levator labii superioris alaeque nasi
description: The levator labii superioris alaeque nasi muscle is, translated from Latin, the 'lifter of the upper lip and of the wing of the nose'. It has the longest name of any muscle in an animal.

name: intertarsal-type crurotarsal joint
description: An ankle joint that passes between the astragalus and calcaneum.

name: intertarsal joint
description: Intertarsal articulations are the joints of the tarsus. The specific intertarsal articulations are: Talocalcaneal articulation Talocalcaneonavicular articulation Calcaneocuboid articulation Cuneonavicular articulation Cuboideonavicular articulation Intercuneiform articulation Cuneocuboid articulation

name: crurotarsal joint
description: A joint that connects the bones of the crus to the proximal tarsal bones

name: lacteal
description: a lymphatic capillary that absorbs dietary fats in the villi of the small intestine.

name: metanephric loop of Henle
description: The metanephric loop of Henle is a metanephric nephron tubule that connects the proximal convoluted tubule to the distal convoluted tubule in the metanephros[GO].

name: stroma of pancreas
description: A stroma that is part of a pancreas.

name: aponeurosis
description: A sheet of extracellular matrix.

name: hypodermis
description: Lowermost layer of the integumentary system in vertebrates. Types of cells that are found in the hypodermis are fibroblasts, adipose cells, and macrophages. It is derived from the mesoderm, but unlike the dermis, it is not derived from the dermatome region of the mesoderm. The hypodermis is used mainly for fat storage[WP].

name: metatarsal bone of digit 4
description: A metatarsal bone that distally_connected_to a proximal phalanx of pedal digit 4.

name: glutamatergic system
description: any molecule, protein, cell, tissue or organ that is related to glutamate (when in the role of a neurotransmitter).

name: distal carpal bone 5 cartilage
description: A distal carpal bone 5 endochondral element that is composed primarily of cartilage tissue.

name: vein of upper lip
description: The inferior labial vein is the vein receiving blood from the upper lip.

name: mucosa of left ureter
description: A mucosa that is part of a left ureter [Automatically generated definition].

name: lamina
description: Any thin layer or plate.

name: anterior auricular muscle
description: The anterior auricular muscle, the smallest of the three auriculares muscles, is thin and fan-shaped, and its fibers are pale and indistinct. It arises from the lateral edge of the galea aponeurotica, and its fibers converge to be inserted into a projection on the front of the helix.

name: intrahepatic bile duct
description: Passages within the liver for the conveyance of bile. Includes right and left hepatic ducts even though these may join outside the liver to form the common hepatic duct.

name: horizontal limb of the diagonal band
tail hair
description: A strand of hair that is part of a tail.

name: thyroid follicle epithelium
description: A epithelium that is part of a thyroid follicle.

name: brain gray matter
description: A gray matter that is part of a brain [Automatically generated definition].

name: frontal artery
description: The supratrochlear artery (or frontal artery), one of the terminal branches of the ophthalmic artery, branches off where the ophthalmic travels posterior to the trochlea.

name: cervical nerve plexus
description: An arrangement of nerve fibers, running from the spine that travels to the head and neck where it innervates skin and muscle.

name: hindlimb pre-cartilage condensation
description: A pre-cartilage condensation that has the potential to develop into a hindlimb bone.

name: pedal digit 2
description: 2nd digit of the hind autopod.

name: ureteric bud trunk
description: ureteric bud cells that elongate to form a rigid structure (stalk) consisting of polarized epithelial cells without branching; the stalks differentiate into the collecting system of the mature kidney, while the tip cells interact with the adjacent cells of the metanephric mesenchyme, inducing their conversion into nephrons.

name: phallodeum
description: Eversible phalloid portion of the cloaca that is inserted in the female's vent during copulation. Found in male Caecillians.

name: salpingopharyngeus muscle
description: The salpingopharyngeus muscle arises from the inferior part of the cartilage of the pharyngotympanic tube (Eustachian tube) in the nasal cavity; it passes downward and blends with the posterior fasciculus of the palatopharyngeus muscle. The salpingopharyngeus is known to raise the pharynx and larynx during deglutition (swallowing) and laterally draws the pharyngeal walls up. In addition, it opens the pharyngeal orifice of the pharyngotympanic tube during swallowing. This allows for the equalization of pressure between the auditory canal and the pharynx. The salpingopharyngeus is innervated by the vagus nerve (CN X) via the pharyngeal plexus.

name: pharyngeal pouch 2
description: A pharyngeal puch that is between the pharyngeal arches 2 and 3.

name: pulmonary myocardium
description: The pulmonary myocardium is the myocardial tissue present in the pulmonary vein

name: transverse muscle of auricle
description: The transverse muscle of auricle is placed on the cranial surface of the pinna. It consists of scattered fibers, partly tendinous and partly muscular, extending from the eminentia conchae to the prominence corresponding with the scapha.

name: sex skin
description: An area of skin adjacent to the female external genitals of various lower primates that undergo marked alteration in turgidity and often in color during estrus.

name: manual digit 3 epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a manual digit 3.

name: interilial region
description: Area of convergence of the ilial shafts. When the preacetabular ilium is narrow, the interilial configuration is V-shaped or narrowly rounded, whereas when the interilial region is broadly expanded the interilial configuration is U-shaped.

name: white matter lamina of cerebral hemisphere
fifth lumbar dorsal root ganglion
description: The group of nerve cell bodies located on the dorsal spinal roots within the vertebral column at the level of the fifth lumbar vertebra

name: obsolete retinal cone cell outer segment
description: The retinal cone cell region in which the visual pigment rhodopsin is in invaginations of the cell membrane

name: adventitia of ureter
description: An adventitia that is part of a ureter.

name: marginal sulcus
description: The marginal sulcus is the portion of the cingulate sulcus adjacent to the paracentral lobule and the precuneus. It is sometimes known as the 'marginal part of the cingulate sulcus'. [WP,unvetted].

name: neural spine
description: A extension of a neural arches dorsal to the neural canal[TAO,modified].

name: lateral nuclear group of thalamus
description: The lateral nuclear group is a collection of nuclei on the lateral side of the thalamus. According to MeSH, it consists of the following: lateral dorsal nucleus lateral posterior nucleus pulvinar [WP,unvetted].

name: interolateral plate
description: Dermal bone that is part of the scapular complex in placoderms.

name: zonal area
description: All those parts of the pectoral girdle ventral and medial to the glenoid fossa.

name: right auditory cortex
description: An auditory cortex that is in the left side of a brain.

name: left uterine tube
description: A fallopian tube that is part of a left side of organism [Automatically generated definition].

name: caudal fin lower lobe
description: Surface structure that is the ventral portion of the caudal fin.

name: thyrohyoid bone
description: Is a laterally bowed, sagittally compressed, slender element that extends from dorsocaudally from the lateral parts of the basihyoid. It connects the basiohyoid with the rostral corner of the thyroid cartlilage of the larynx.

name: serratus dorsalis inferior muscle
description: A muscle that originates from the vertebrae and inserts in the ribs.

name: internal rim of coracoid foramen
description: The internal part of the rim denoting the coracoid foramen.

name: notochord posterior region
description: Portion of tissue that is part of the caudal fin.

name: parasagittal processes
description: Paired, posteriorly directed process at the posterior margin of each neural arch lamina.

name: polar trophectoderm
description: Trophectoderm that surrounds the inner cell mass (ICM).

name: anterior superior alveolar nerve
description: The anterior superior alveolar branch (anterior superior dental branch), of considerable size, is given off from the maxillary nerve just before its exit from the infraorbital foramen; it descends in a canal in the anterior wall of the maxillary sinus, and divides into branches which supply the incisor and canine teeth. It communicates with the middle superior alveolar branch, and gives off a nasal branch, which passes through a minute canal in the lateral wall of the inferior meatus, and supplies the mucous membrane of the anterior part of the inferior meatus and the floor of the nasal cavity, communicating with the nasal branches from the sphenopalatine ganglion.

name: paramedian reticular nucleus
description: A medullary nucleus that sends its connections to the spinal cord in a mostly ipsilateral manner.

name: brainstem nucleus
description: A nucleus of brain that is part of a brainstem.

name: hippocampus alveus
description: Regional part of fornix consisting of a thin layer of white matter on the surface of the hippocampal formation, bordering the wall of the lateral ventricle and composed of white, myelinated fibers. The alveus arises from cell bodies in the subiculum and hippocampus, and eventually merges with the fimbria of the hippocampus. The fimbria goes on to become the fornix (MM: 2006-10-26).

name: gastrointestinal system mesentery
description: A mesentery that is part of a digestive system [Automatically generated definition].

name: pedal digit 5 metatarsal endochondral element
description: A pedal digit 5 metatarsal bone or its cartilage or pre-cartilage precursor.

name: apex of spinal cord dorsal horn
telencephalon
description: Part of the forebrain consisting of paired olfactory bulbs and cerebral hemispheres.

name: iridocorneal angle
description: Acute angle occurring between the iris and the cornea at the periphery of the anterior chamber of the eye[MP].

name: mesenchyme of vomeronasal organ
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a developing vomeronasal organ [Automatically generated definition].

name: patella cartilage element
description: A cartilaginous condensation that has the potential to develop into a patella.

name: frontal cortex
description: Anterior portion of the neocortex, lying anterior to the central sulcus in humans. It is bounded by the parietal cortex posteriorly and the temporal cortex laterally[NIFSTD,modified].

name: frontal lobe
description: Frontal lobe is the anterior-most of five lobes of the cerebral hemisphere. It is bounded by the central sulcus on its posterior border and by the longitudinal cerebral fissure on its medial border.

name: obsolete Kolmer-Agduhr neuron
description: Kolmer-Agduhr neurons are ciliated GABAergic neurons that contact the central canal of the spinal cord and have ipsilateral ascending axons.

name: wall of crypt of Lieberkuhn
description: The lateral parts of an intestinal crypt, continuous distally with the base and proximally with the intestinal villus epithelium.

name: major vestibular gland
description: the paired glands located slightly posterior and to the left and right of the opening of the vagina in the superficial perineal pouch in females; they secrete mucus to lubricate the vagina and are homologous to bulbourethral (Cowper's) glands in males

name: articulation
description: Anatomical cluster that connects two or more adjacent skeletal elements or hardened body parts.

name: obsolete predominantly white regional part of globus pallidus
immature gonad
description: Immature reproductive tissue that has not undergone final maturation into either testis or ovary. During gonadal development, the gonad may be transiently intersexual where there is a parallel presence of both oocytes and spermatocytes.

name: otic placode
description: A cranial placode which, once specified, invaginates to form an otic cup, which eventually separates from the surface ectoderm to form the otic vesicle or otocyst, a rounded structure without appar- ent polarity. As the otic placode invaginates into a cup neuroblasts delaminate from the anterior ventral aspect of the otic epithelium to give rise to neurons of the vestibulocochlear (statoacoustic) ganglion of cranial nerve VIII[NBK]

name: nematode larval stage
description: Nematode larval development begins with the newly hatched first-stage larva (L1) and ends with the end of the last larval stage (for example the fourth larval stage (L4) in C. elegans). Each stage of nematode larval development is characterized by proliferation of specific cell lineages and an increase in body size without alteration of the basic body plan. Nematode larval stages are separated by molts in which each stage-specific exoskeleton, or cuticle, is shed and replaced anew.

name: pretectal region
description: Nuclear complex between dorsal thalamus and optic tectum whose nuclei receive afferents primarily from the retina and the optic tectum and are involved in modulating motor behavior in response to visual input.

name: centrale
description: Endochondral bone located between the proximal and distal rows of carpals or tarsals and thus representing the central carpals or tarsals[PHENOSCAPE].

name: uvea
description: the pigmented middle of the three concentric layers that make up an eye, consisting of the iris, ciliary body and choroid[WP,edited].

name: facial nerve root
description: A nerve root that extends_fibers_into a facial nerve.

name: primary posterior lateral line primordium
description: Primordium that forms the first neuromasts of the posterior lateral line. This primordium travels at 1.5-1.7 somites/hour and deposits neuromast that are polarized along the antero-posterior axis.

name: koniocellular layer of dorsal nucleus of lateral geniculate body
lacrimal papilla
description: A small conical elevation at the basal angle of the lacrimal lake.

name: limb epidermis
description: The limb epidermis is the outer epithelial layer of the limb, it is a complex stratified squamous epithelium.

name: olfactory bulb main glomerular layer
description: The glomerular layer of the main olfactory bulb, lying deep to the olfactory nerve layer. It contains the glomeruli, neuropil rich spheroid structures surrounded by a distinctive shell of small neuros and glial cells (Paxinos, the Rat Nervous System, 2nd ed., Academic Press, 1995).

name: opercular cavity
description: Anatomical space which is located beneath the operculum and external to the gills.

name: anus
description: Orifice at the opposite end of an animal's digestive tract from the mouth. Its function is to expel feces, unwanted semi-solid matter produced during digestion, which, depending on the type of animal, may be one or more of: matter which the animal cannot digest, such as bones; food material after all the nutrients have been extracted, for example cellulose or lignin; ingested matter which would be toxic if it remained in the digestive tract; and dead or excess gut bacteria and other endosymbionts.

name: cloaca
description: Common chamber into which the intestines and excretory system opens. Arises during development in all vertebrates, but in many it becomes subdivided, lost or incorporated into other structures

name: anal canal
description: The terminal part of the large intestine, continuous proximally with the rectum and distally terminates with the anus.

name: adrenal gland X zone
description: A transient cortical layer juxtaposed to the medulla and the zona reticularis; in males, this zone rapidly involutes at the onset of puberty whereas this zone persists in females until the first pregnancy or later in adulthood in non-pregnant females

name: palpebral fissure
description: Orifice separating upper and lower eyelids. In the human adult this measures about 10mm vertically and 30 mm horizontally. It can be reduced in size in fetal alcohol syndrome. In Trisomy 9 the palpebral fissures can be upslanting. [WP,modified].

name: vesicular gland
description: The vesicular gland is part of the male reproductive system. The vesicular gland contributes fluids, energy substrates, and buffers to semen. It can be found near the Coagulating gland, which also belongs to the reproductive system.

name: somite 18
description: Undifferentiated mesodermal component of early trunk or tail segment or metamere, derived from paraxial mesoderm; forms the myotome, sclerotome and perhaps dermatome. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: entorhinal cortex layer 5
description: Layer of entorhinal cortex lying superficial to layer 6 and deep to layer 4 characterized by large pyramidal neurons that are darkly stained in Nissl preparations (Adapted from Paxinos, G. The rat central nervous system, 2nd ed, Academic Press, San Diego, 1995, pg. 474)

name: M. sartorius
description: Originates on the ventral pelvic rim, the pubic region, and the ventral surface of the adductor longus. The insertion bifurcates distally; the ventral portion attaches to the aponeurosis of the cruralis and the dorsal part attaches to the distal attachment of the gracilis major, the semitendinosus, and to the aponeurosis of the cruralis.

name: nephridium
description: An exceretory tubule that usually opens to the exterior by a nephridiopore. The inner end of the tubule may be blind, ending in flame cells (protonephridium) or may open into the coelom through a ciliated funnel (metanephridium).

name: pectoral fin proximal radial bone 4
description: pectoral fin proximal radial 4 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: cephalopod optic lobe
description: Large lobes of the brain associated with the eyes. In octopods and some squids the optic lobes may be separated from the rest of the brain by an optic stalk of varying length. In Octopus the optic lobes contain 92 million cells compared with only 42 million in the main central mass of the brain (J. Young, 1963) .

name: erectile tissue
description: with numerous vascular spaces that may become engorged with blood

name: somite 2
description: Undifferentiated mesodermal component of early trunk or tail segment or metamere, derived from paraxial mesoderm; forms the myotome, sclerotome and perhaps dermatome. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: inferior vagus X ganglion
description: the large group of sensory neuron cell bodies, anterior to the jugular vein, associated with the vagus nerve (tenth cranial nerve)

name: cerebellar commissure
description: A nervous system commissure that connects a left hemisphere of cerebellum and connects a right hemisphere of cerebellum.

name: future coelemic cavity lumen
description: An anatomical cavity that has the potential to develop into a coelemic cavity lumen.

name: zone of polarizing activity
description: An area of mesenchymal cells that contains signals which instruct the developing limb or fin bud to form along the anterior/posterior axis.

name: ethmoid sinus
description: the evaginations of the mucous membrane of the nasal cavity into the ethmoidal bony labyrinth, forming multiple small paranasal sinuses

name: processus frontalis of maxilla
description: Anterio portion of the maxilla that may contact the nasal and take part in the formation of a groove for the nasolacrimal duct.

name: spiral sulcus
description: A concavity in the floor of the cochlear duct, formed by either the overhanging vestibular lip (inner spiral sulcus) or the spiral prominence and the spiral organ (outer spiral sulcus).

name: nervous system commissure
description: Axon tract that crosses the midline of the central nervous system[NIF, modified]. In the context of Drosophila refers to a broad band of axons connecting equivalent neuropils each side of the brain[FBbt].

name: forehead protuberance
description: A bulge, knob, or swelling that protrudes from the forehead.

name: reproductive gland
description: Any of the organized aggregations of cells that function as secretory or excretory organs and are associated with reproduction.

name: m. ypsiloideus anterior
description: Hypaxial muscle in which contraction elevates the ypsiloid cartilage; originates from the anterior edge of the lateral process of the ypsiloid cartilage and insert on the anteriorly adjacent inscription.

name: humerus
description: Paired endochondral long bone that extends between the pectoral girdle and the skeletal parts of the forelimb. [PHENOSCAPE:mah]

name: lesser trochanter
description: The lesser trochanter (small trochanter) of the femur is a conical eminence, which varies in size in different subjects [WP,unvetted].

name: intervertebral space
description: Space formed by the anterior and posterior intervertebral notches. The intervertebral spaces accommodate the spinal nerves as they emerge from the spinal canal.

name: upper rhombic lip
description: Anterior-most region of dorsal hindbrain within rhombomere 1, adjacent the midbrain-hindbrain boundary.

name: corticomedial nuclear complex
description: These structures are referred to as nuclei but have a layered cortical like structure. These areas include the anterior amygdaloid area, posterior amygdaloid area, the periamygdaloid cortex, and the bed nucleus of the accessory olfactory tract.

name: supraoccipital pre-cartilage condensation
description: A pre-cartilage condensation that has the potential to develop into a supraoccipital bone.

name: notochord
description: A flexible rod-shaped body found in embryos of all chordates. It is composed of cells derived from the mesoderm and defines the primitive axis of the embryo. In some chordates, it persists throughout life as the main axial support of the body, while in most vertebrates it becomes the nucleus pulposus of the intervertebral disc. The notochord is found ventral to the neural tube.

name: obsolete regional part of enteric nervous system
collagenous dermal stroma
description: A layer of collagen fibrils present in the imature integument in an acellular subepidermal space. At first, the fibrils are all oriented in the same direction, later they form the complex plywood-like structure that is characteristic of the dermal deep region. Le Guellec et al, 2004.

name: ramules cutaneous
description: Many branches of the maxillary ramus that terminate in the integument of the maxillary region.

name: nucleus of midbrain tectum
description: A neural nucleus that is part of a midbrain tectum.

name: cupular organ
description: Epithelial sense organ containing the cupula housing a gelatinous material elongated from the basement of the organ toward the atrial cavity. The basement of the cupular organ consists of two cell types: sensory cells and support cell

name: ceratobranchial 1 bone
description: Ceratobranchial bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with epibranchial 1 cartilage or bone.

name: dilated medial process of metacarpal IV
cranial fossa
description: Any of the three large depressions in the posterior, middle, and anterior aspects of the floor of the cranial cavity

name: digit 2
description: A digit that is part of a digit 2 plus metapodial segment.

name: obsolete non-terminally differentiated odontoblast
description: Odontoblast that non-terminally differentiated, located in the odontogenic papilla and dentine tissue, and transforms from a odontoblast cell.

name: crop
description: A pouched enlargement of the gullet of many birds that serves as a receptacle for food and for its preliminary maceration.

name: systemic arterial system
description: The part of the arterial system which carries oxygenated blood away from the heart to the body, and returns deoxygenated blood back to the heart.

name: right hemisphere of cerebellum
description: A cerebellar hemisphere that is in_the_right_side_of a cerebellum.

name: epiphysis of first metatarsal bone
description: An epiphysis that is part of a metatarsal bone of digit 1 [Automatically generated definition].

name: superior gemellus muscle
description: The smaller of the two gemellus muscles that arises from the outer surface of the spine of the ischium, blends with the upper part of the tendon of the Obturator internus, and is inserted with it into the medial surface of the greater trochanter[WP].

name: pharyngeal slit
description: An organ formed from the perforation between the point of contact between ectoderm and endoderm in the pharynx. The slits assist in filtering food particles from the water.

name: pharyngeal cleft
description: An external pocketing of pharyngeal ectoderm that contacts a region of endoderm (a pharyngeal pouch) and interdigitates in the anterior and posterior directions by the pharyngeal arches.

name: transient cartilaginous element
description: Chondrogenic element that is composed of cartilage during development and has the potential to become replaced by another tissue.

name: posterior dorsal fin
description: Dorsal fin located posterior to the anterior dorsal fin. [WD]

name: epiphysis of phalanx
description: An epiphysis that is part of a phalanx [Automatically generated definition].

name: deep temporal vein
description: The blood vessels at the vertex and on either side of the head that drain deoxygenated blood into the pterygoid venous plexus.

name: crus of diaphragm
description: The domain of the diaphragm that is located dorsally and attaches to the vertebrae and surrounds the esophagus and aorta.

name: knee joint
description: The knee joint joins the thigh with the leg and consists of two articulations: one between the femur and tibia, and one between the femur and patella. It is the largest and most complicated joint in the human body. The knee is a mobile trocho-ginglymus (i.e. a pivotal hinge joint), which permits flexion and extension as well as a slight medial and lateral rotation[WP,unvetted].

name: alar central lobule
description: The lobulus centralis is a small square lobule, situated in the anterior cerebellar notch. It overlaps the lingula, from which it is separated by the precentral fissure; laterally, it extends along the upper and anterior part of each hemisphere, where it forms a wing-like prolongation, the alar central lobule. [WP,unvetted].

name: anterior nucleus of hypothalamus anterior part
fornix of brain
description: A C-shaped bundle of fibres (axons) in the brain, and carries signals from the hippocampus to the mammillary bodies and septal nuclei. It is typically divided into the columns (crus), body, commissure and the pre-commissural and post-commissural fornix (MM).

name: inferior temporal sulcus
description: The inferior surface of the temporal lobe is concave, and is continuous posteriorly with the tentorial surface of the occipital lobe. It is traversed by the inferior temporal sulcus, which extends from near the occipital pole behind, to within a short distance of the temporal pole in front, but is frequently subdivided by bridging gyri.

name: ecto-epithelium
description: Epithelium composed of cells that develops from the ectoderm[FMA,modified].

name: left common carotid artery plus branches
description: The leftmost of the two common carotid arteries, originating from the aortic arch in the thorax.

name: pelvic fin ray
description: Soft ray that is part of the pelvic fin.

name: renal portal system
description: A portal system that transports blood returning from capillary beds within tail or hindlimbs through paired renal portal veins that empty into capillaries within the kidneys.

name: obsolete life cycle stage boundary
description: Instant starting or ending a life cycle stage. These can be arbitrary/fiat.

name: proximal tarsal bone
description: A tarsal bone that connected_to a hindlimb zeugopod skeleton.

name: entepicondylar foramen
description: A canal through the medial epicondyle at the distal end of the vertebrate humerus, usually traversed by the median nerve and brachial artery.

name: primary nodular lymphoid tissue
description: A lymphoid follicle containing naive B cells

name: CA1 stratum oriens
description: Part of stratum oriens lying in area CA1, superficial to the alveus of CA1 and deep to the pyramidal cell layer of CA1. It is continuous with the stratum oriens of CA2 and bounded by the subiculum

name: sublaminar layer S3
description: A retinal neural layer that is immediately adjacent to the S2 and S4 layers and comprises 20 percent of the inner plexiform layer of retina.

name: choroidal guanine tapetum
description: A choroid tapetum lucidum that is made of a palisade of cells containing stacks of flat hexagonal crystals of guanine

name: rib of vertebra 2
description: Rib that articulates with the parapophysis of the second centrum.

name: suborbital foramen
description: Foramen located below the orbit and forming a passageway for nerves (eg fifth cranial nerve)

name: metanephric ureteric bud
description: The portion of the ureteric bud tube that contributes to the morphogenesis of the metanephros[GO].

name: frontomaxillary suture
description: A suture between the frontal bone and the frontal process of the maxilla

name: sesamoid bone of manus
description: A sesamoid bone that is part of a manus.

name: epioccipital posterior process
description: Process of the epioccipital that extends posteriorly, is laminar in form and is usually attached to Weberian apparatus.

name: superficial palmar arch
description: The superficial palmar arch is formed predominantly by the ulnar artery, with a contribution from the superficial palmar branch of the radial artery. However, in some individuals the contribution from the radial artery might be absent, and instead anastomoses with either the princeps pollicis artery, the radialis indicis artery, or the median artery, the former two of which are branches from the radial artery. Alternative names for this arterial arch are: superficial volar arch, superficial ulnar arch, arcus palmaris superficialis, or arcus volaris superficialis. The arch passes across the palm in a curve with its convexity downward. If one were to fully extend the thumb, the superficial palmar arch would lie approximately at the level of a line drawn from the distal border of the thumb across the palm. The superficial palmar arch is more distal than the deep palmar arch. Three common palmar digital arteries arise from the arch, proceeding down on the second, third, and fourth lumbrical muscles, respectively. They each receive a contribution from a palmar metacarpal artery. Near the level of the metacarpophalangeal joints, each common palmar digital artery divides into two proper palmar digital arteries.

name: ovarian fossa
description: A shallow depression on the lateral wall of the pelvis, wherein the ovary lies. This fossa has the following boundaries: superiorly: by the external iliac vessels anteriorly and inferiorly: by the broad ligament of the uterus posteriorly: by the ureter and internal iliac vessels

name: ligament of hip joint
description: A skeletal ligament that is part of a hip joint.

name: capsule of pancreas
description: A capsule that divides the parenchyma of the pancreas into lobes and lobules

name: upper lobe of right lung
description: The lobe of the right lung that is closest to the head.

name: venous sinus
description: A large vein or channel for the circulation of venous blood

name: thoracic segment muscle
description: Any muscle organ that is part of a thorax [Automatically generated definition].

name: metatarsal bone of digit 5
description: A metatarsal bone that distally_connected_to a proximal phalanx of pedal digit 5.

name: serotonergic system
description: any molecule, protein, cell, tissue or organ that is related to serotonin.

name: distal carpal bone 5 pre-cartilage condensation
description: A distal carpal bone 5 endochondral element that is composed primarily of a pre-cartilage condensation.

name: vein of lower lip
description: The inferior labial vein is the vein receiving blood from the lower lip.

name: mucosa of renal pelvis
description: A mucosa that is part of a renal pelvis [Automatically generated definition].

name: fontanelle
description: Anatomical structure that is a membranous gap between bones of the skull[TAO]. In humans: Fontanelles are soft spots on a baby's head which, during birth, enable the bony plates of the skull to flex, allowing the child's head to pass through the birth canal. The ossification of the bones of the skull cause the fontanelles to close over by a child's second birthday. The closures eventually form the sutures of the neurocranium. Although there are the two anterior and posterior fontanelles, there are two more fontanelles of interest, the mastoid fontanelle, and the sphenoidal fontanelle[WP].

name: cuneate nucleus
description: One of the dorsal column nuclei, the cuneate nucleus is a wedge-shaped nucleus in the closed part of the medulla oblongata. It contains cells that give rise to the cuneate tubercle, visible on the posterior aspect of the medulla. It lies laterally to the gracile nucleus and medial to the spinal trigeminal nucleus in the medulla. [WP,unvetted].

name: Meckel's diverticulum
description: A small bulge in the small intestine present at birth. It is a vestigial remnant of the omphalomesenteric duct

name: egg chorion
description: A protective, noncellular membrane that surrounds the eggs of various animals including insects and fish [GO].

name: chorion
description: the outermost extraembryonic membrane

name: ventral hair
description: A strand of hair that is part of a ventrum.

name: colloid of thyroid follicle
description: portion of substance contained within the thyroid follicle lumen. Contains prohormone thyroglobulin.

name: respiratory system lymphatic vessel endothelium
description: An lymphatic vessel endothelium that is part of a respiratory system [Automatically generated definition].

name: obsolete predominantly white regional part of cerebellar cortex
tragus
description: A small pointed eminence of the external ear, situated in front of the concha, and projecting backward over the meatus.

name: crista subnasalis
description: Ventral crest of the paries nasi.

name: urinary bladder vasculature
description: network of tubes that carries blood through the distensible musculomembranous organ that serves to collect and store urine excreted by the kidneys[MP]

name: auricular blood vessel
description: A blood vessel that supplies or drains an ear.

name: coelomic epithelium
description: The epithelial lining of the surface of the coelom.

name: pectoral appendage blood vessel
description: A blood vessel that is part of a pectoral appendage.

name: visual association cortex
description: Part of cortex considered to function in higher level visual functions

name: pharyngeal pouch 3
description: A pharyngeal pouch that between pharyngeal arches 3 and 4.

name: anterior ectodermal midgut
description: portions of the midgut that are derived from ectoderm.

name: oblique muscle of auricle
description: The oblique muscle of auricle, on the cranial surface, consists of a few fibers extending from the upper and back part of the concha to the convexity immediately above it.

name: ischial callosity
description: An area of hardened, leathery skin on either side of the base of the tail on the rump.

name: manual digit 4 epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a manual digit 4.

name: angular gyrus
description: Part of inferior parietal lobule formed by the cortex surrounding the upturned end of the superior temporal sulcus (Nolte, The Human Brain, 6th ed, 2009, pg 659)

name: recessus coccygealis
description: Area dorsal to the pelvic girdle symphysis, between the dorsal portions of the ilial corpora, where lies the posterior terminus of the urostyle.

name: upper leg nerve
description: A nerve that is part of a hindlimb stylopod [Automatically generated definition].

name: long ciliary nerve
description: A branch of the nasociliary nerve that innervates the ciliary muscles, the iris, and the cornea.

name: obsolete regional part of paraventricular nucleus of hypothalamus
medullary lamina of thalamus
description: Medullary laminae of thalamus are layers of myelinated fibres that appear on cross sections of the thalamus. They also are commonly referred to as laminae medullares thalami or medullary layers of thalamus. The specific layers are: Lamina medullaris lateralis (external medullary lamina) - separates ventral and lateral thalamus from the subthalamus and thalamic reticular nucleus; Lamina medullaris medialis (internal medullary lamina) - positioned between the dorsomedial and ventral nuclei of thalamus, encloses the intralaminar nuclei (centromedian nucleus, paracentral, and central lateral)

name: obsolete retinal rod cell inner segment
description: The retinal rod cell region which contains the machinery of the cell (mitochondria, golgi, endoplasmic reticulum, etc) and where opsin molecules are assembled and passed to be part of the outer segment region

name: lamina propria of ureter
description: A lamina propria that is part of a ureter [Automatically generated definition].

name: intraparietal sulcus
description: The intraparietal sulcus (IPS) is located on the lateral surface of the parietal lobe, and consists of an oblique and a horizontal portion. The IPS contains a series of functionally distinct subregions that have been intensively investigated using both single cell neurophysiology in primates and human functional neuroimaging. Its principal functions are related to perceptual-motor coordination (for directing eye movements and reaching) and visual attention. The IPS is also thought to play a role in other functions, including processing symbolic numerical information, visuospatial working memory and interpreting the intent of others. [WP,unvetted].

name: transverse process of vertebra
description: The transverse or costal processes of a vertebra, two in number, project one at either side from the point where the lamina joins the pedicle, between the superior and inferior articular processes. They serve for the attachment of muscles and ligaments. [WP,unvetted].

name: postparietal shield
description: Dermal bones (postparietals, supratemporals, intertemporals, extrascapulars) posterior to the intracranial joint. Forey 1997.

name: foramen perforans tarsi
description: Small opening between the centrale and fibulare that allows the perforans tarsi artery to pass from the ventral to the dorsal side of the ankle.

name: gyrus rectus
description: The portion of the frontal lobe medial to the medial orbital gyrus is named the gyrus rectus (or straight gyrus), and is continuous with the superior frontal gyrus on the medial surface. A specific function for the gyrus rectus has not yet been elucidated.

name: spinal plate
description: Dermal bone that is part of the scapular complex in placoderms.

name: left auditory cortex
description: An auditory cortex that is in the right side of a brain.

name: germinal epithelium of ovary
description: layer of simple cuboidal cells covering surface of ovary[WP].

name: sternocleidomastoid
description: A paired muscle in the superficial layers of the anterior portion of the neck. It acts to flex and rotate the head. It also acts as an accessory muscle of inspiration, along with the scalene muscles of the neck. [WP,unvetted].

name: external rim of the coracoid foramen
epibranchial 3 bone uncinate process
description: Epibranchial uncinate process that is part of epibranchial 3 bone.

name: circular nucleus of antherior hypothalamic nucleus
description: A group of cells located in the central part of the anterior hypothalamic nucleus in the anterior hypothalamic region of the rat ( Swanson-2004 ) and the mouse ( Paxinos-2001 ). Functionally it belongs to the magnocellular neuroendocrine cell groups of the subcortical motor system ( Swanson-2004 )

name: accessory articulation
description: Paired, additional vertebral articulations located medial to the intervertebral space, adjacent to the vertebral centrum.

name: humeral diverticulum of clavicular air sac
epigonal organ
description: An elongate paired tissue ventral to the kidneys and partialy enveloping the anterior gonads in Elasmobranchii. Apparently important to the immune system

name: posterior auricular nerve
description: A branch of the facial nerve that innervates the posterior auricular and intrinsic muscles of the auricle and, through its occipital branch, innervates the occipital belly of the occipitofrontal muscle.

name: mucosa of ureter
description: A mucosa that is part of a ureter [Automatically generated definition].

name: granular insular cortex
description: Granular region of the insular cortex

name: ciliated columnar oviduct epithelium
description: A ciliated columnar epithelium that is part of a oviduct.

name: primitive nephron
description: An epithelial tube that is fated to become a nephron.

name: nasal capsule
description: An embryonic cartilaginous frame, the nasal capsule, an evolutionary-conserved structure composed of ventral and dorsal components: the mesethmoid and ectethmoid cartilages, respectively.[PMID].

name: pelvic appendage bud ectoderm
description: An unilaminar epithelium that surrounds a pelvic appendage bud.

name: skin of forehead
description: A zone of skin that is part of a forehead.

name: manual digit metacarpus endochondral element
description: A manual digit metacarpus bone or its cartilage or pre-cartilage precursor.

name: embryonic imaginal precursor
description: Embryonic structure that will proliferate during larval development into a larval imaginal disc. During early embryogenesis the precursor is part of the epithelial sheet before segregating from the epithelial sheet by late embryogenesis (Bate and Martinez Arias, 1991).

name: dentate gyrus molecular layer
description: The molecular layer of the dentate gyrus that is bounded by the pial surface superficially and the dentate gyrus granule cell layer deep. It is divided into 2 or more sublayers.

name: diencephalon
description: The division of the forebrain that develops from the foremost primary cerebral vesicle.

name: aortico-pulmonary spiral septum
description: The spiral septum that separates the truncus arteriosus into a ventral pulmonary trunk and the dorsal aorta[MP]. The aorticopulmonary septum is developmentally formed from neural crest, specifically the cardiac neural crest, and actively separates the aorta and pulmonary arteries and fuses with the interventricular septum within the heart during development. The actual mechanism of septation of the outflow tract is poorly understood, but is recognized as a dynamic process with contributions from contractile, hemodynamic, and extracellular matrix interactions.

name: mesenchyme of umbilical cord
description: A gelatinous substance within the umbilical cord, largely made up of mucopolysaccharides (hyaluronic acid and chondroitin sulfate). It also contains some fibroblasts and macrophages. It is derived from Extra Embryonic Mesoderm[WP]

name: patella pre-cartilage condensation
description: A pre-cartilage condensation that has the potential to develop into a patella.

name: lobe of cerebral hemisphere
description: Subdivision of telencephalon which is one of a number of subdivisions of each hemisphere separated by both real landmarks (sulci and fissures) and arbitrary boundaries[FMA,modified].

name: base of crypt of Lieberkuhn of large intestine
description: A base of crypt of Lieberkuhn that is part of a large intestine.

name: epithelium of endolymphatic sac
description: An epithelium that is part of a endolymphatic sac [Automatically generated definition].

name: minor vestibular gland
description: Small mucous glands opening upon the vestibular mucous membrane between the urethral and the vaginal orifice.

name: paraurethral gland
description: the numerous mucous-secreting glands found in several female mammalian species (including rodents and humans) on the anterior wall of the vagina, around the lower end of the urethra, and possessing a common paraurethral duct which opens (on each side) near the external urethral orifice; they are homologous with the prostate gland in males, have highly variable anatomy, and are believed to be the source of the female ejaculate, a lubricating fluid with a similar consistency to male prostatic fluid that is expelled through the urethra during sexual stimulation; like the male prostate, these glands are susceptible to infection (skenitis), cyst development, and cancer

name: ectodermal part of digestive tract
description: A portion of the gut that is derived from ectoderm.

name: obsolete predominantly gray regional part of Preoptic area
pectoral fin distal radial bone 3
description: pectoral fin distal radial 3 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: cranium
description: Upper portion of the skull that excludes the mandible (when present in the organism).

name: superior colliculus
description: Part of the midbrain tecturm consisting of paired bodies that sit caudal to the thalamus and surround the pineal gland in the mesencephalon of vertebrate brains. It comprises the rostral aspect of the midbrain, posterior to the periaqueductal gray and adjacent superior the inferior colliculus. The inferior and superior colliculi are known collectively as the corpora quadrigemina (Latin, quadruplet bodies). It consists of several identified cellular layers and also comprises the brachium of the superior colliculus and commissure of supeior colliculus from Wikipedia.org and Neuronames (MM).

name: intercuneiform joint
description: The intercuneiform articulations are articulations among the cuneiform bones[WP,unverified].

name: anterior uvea
description: Front (ventral) portion of the vascular, pigmentary, or middle coat of the eye, including the ciliary body and the iris.

name: iris
description: the adjustable membrane, composed of the stroma and pigmented epithelium, located just in front of the crystalline lens within the eye

name: obsolete regional part of cervical spinal cord white matter
secondary posterior lateral line primordium
description: Second lateral line primordium. These primordia moves at 0.2 somites/hour and deposite neromasts that are polarized in a dorso-ventral direction.

name: colic flexure
description: A sharp bend between consecutive segments of the colon.

name: nephric duct
description: A nephric duct is a tube that drains a primitive kidney[GO].

name: obsolete telencephalon of primate
description: The telencephalon of the primate

name: gastroepiploic artery
description: One of two (right and left) arteries along the greater curvature of the stomach that supply blood to the greater omentum and stomach.

name: psoas muscle
description: A powerful flexor of the thigh at the hip joint (psoas major) and a weak flexor of the trunk and lumbar spinal column (psoas minor). Psoas is derived from the Greek 'psoa', the plural meaning 'muscles of the loin'. It is a common site of infection manifesting as abscess (PSOAS ABSCESS). The psoas muscles and their fibers are also used frequently in experiments in muscle physiology.

name: anterior perforated substance
description: Regional part of telencephalon lying on the basal surface and bounded by the olfactory trigone rostrally, the diagonal band medially and caudally and the prepiriform cortex laterally. It is characterized by many perforations caused by small blood vessels entering the gray matter (Meyer et al., J. Comp. Neurol 284: 405, 1989).

name: somite 21
description: Undifferentiated mesodermal component of early trunk or tail segment or metamere, derived from paraxial mesoderm; forms the myotome, sclerotome and perhaps dermatome. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: mollusc venom
description: Venoms from mollusks, including the Conus and Octopus species. The venoms contain proteins, enzymes, choline derivatives, slow-reacting substances, and several characterized polypeptide toxins that affect the nervous system. Mollusk venoms include cephalotoxin, venerup in, maculotoxin, surugatoxin, conotoxins, and murexine.

name: molecular layer of dorsal cochlear nucleus
obsolete hair cell anterior macula
description: Specialized neuronal receptor cells of the lateral line and acoustico-vestibular systems. Kimmel et al, 1995. (Also see Anatomical Atlas entry for hair cells by T. Whitfield.)

name: parenchyma of caudate lobe of liver
description: A liver parenchyma that is part of a caudate lobe of liver.

name: upper central primary incisor tooth
description: A upper primary canine tooth that is in_the_central_side_of a dentition.

name: protonephridium
description: A network of dead-end tubules lacking internal openings found in the Phylums Platyhelminthes, kinorhyncha and Rotifera.

name: lumen of hemipenial sheath
description: A anatomical space that is enclosed by a hemipenal sheath.

name: epaxial region somite 3
description: Somite-derived body wall muscle present dorsal to the horizontal myoseptum. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: superior vagus X ganglion
description: the upper ganglion of the vagus nerve located at the jugular foramen

name: intraembryonic coelom
description: The part of the coelom in the embryo between the somatopleuric and splanchnopleuric mesoderm; the principal body cavities of the trunk (thoracic, abdominal, and pelvic) arise from this embryonic part of the coelom

name: zone of polarizing activity of pectoral appendage
description: A zone of polarizing activity that is part of a pectoral appendage bud mesenchyme.

name: body of caudate nucleus
description: Part of caudate nucleus lying just dorsal to the thalamus

name: dorsal metacarpal artery
description: Aanastomosis of dorsal carpal branch of the radial artery and the dorsal carpal branch of the ulnar artery near the back of the wrist. It is made up of the dorsal carpal branches of both the ulnar and radial arteries. It also anastomoses with the anterior interosseous artery and the posterior interosseous artery. The arch gives off three dorsal metacarpal arteries.

name: lamina anterior of maxilla
description: Most anterior part of the maxilla, which is in contact with the premaxilla.

name: perilymphatic space
description: The fluid-filled space separating the membranous from the osseous labyrinth.

name: nerve
description: An enclosed, cable-like bundle of axons in the peripheral nervous system originating in a nerve root in the central nervous system (or a condensed nervous structure) connecting with peripheral structures.

name: latissimus dorsi process
description: A bony process on the dorsal side of the proximal region of the humerus which corresponds to the insertion site of the Latissimus dorsi muscle.

name: sensory dissociation area
description: The area of the parietal lobe that integrates tactile and visual stimuli

name: left part of face
description: Subdivision of the head consisting of the left half of the face, vertically divided.

name: oral ramule
description: Medial branch of the ramus mandibularis externus. This ramule innervates the oral and angular lines of neuromasts.

name: pleura
description: The invaginated serous membrane that surrounds the lungs (the visceral portion) and lines the walls of the pleural cavity (parietal portion).

name: spiral modiolar artery
description: The artery which parallels the spiral ganglion in the root of the spiral lamina of the modiolus, serving the ganglion and the cochlear duct and its contents.

name: glandular acinus
description: The many-lobed berry cluster of cells that is the terminous of a gland where the secretion is produced is acinar in form.

name: neurocranium bone
description: A bone that is part of a neurocranium [Automatically generated definition].

name: somite
description: Somites are spheres of epithelial cells that form sequentially along the anterior-posterior axis of the embryo through mesenchymal to epithelial transition of the presomitic mesoderm.

name: obsolete predominantly gray regional part of basal part of pons
neural complex of Weberian apparatus
description: Anatomical cluster that consists of supraneural 2 bone and supraneural 3 bone and their extensions, and which is part of the Weberian apparatus.

name: ampulla of uterine tube
