description: The gastric glands in the pyloric region of the stomach; the pyloric glands secrete mucin, which coats the stomach and protects it, and hormones such as gastrin and enkephalin[MP].

name: respiratory system venous smooth muscle
description: A smooth muscle tissue that is part of a respiratory system venous blood vessel.

name: ophthalmic plexus
description: An autonomic plexus, entering the orbit in company with the ophthalmic artery, derived from the internal carotid plexus.

name: inferolateral surface of prostate
description: The aspect of the prostate facing the pelvic diaphragm and pubis.

name: intervertebral disk of cervical vertebra
description: An intervertebral disk that is part of a cervical region of vertebral column. A cervical intervertebral disk connects at least one cervical vertebra, either to another cervical vertebra, or at one point on the vertebral colummn, to a thoracic vertebra

name: heart rudiment
description: A cone-like structure that is formed when myocardial progenitor cells of the heart field fuse at the midline. The heart rudiment is the first structure of the heart tube.

name: mammillothalamic tract of hypothalamus
description: Part of mammillothalamic tract contained within the hypothalamus

name: pharyngeal vasculature
description: A vasculature that is part of a chordate pharynx.

name: pharyngeal pouch 6
description: A pharyngeal pouch between pharyngeal arches 6 and 7.

name: proneural cluster
description: An equivalence group of the neurectoderm where all cells can, although only one will, become a neural progenitor cell.

name: semimembranosus muscle
description: The semimembranosus is a muscle in the back of the thigh. It is the most medial of the three hamstring muscles. [WP,unvetted].

name: gracile fasciculus of spinal cord
description: A gracile fasciculus that is part of a spinal cord.

name: distal phalanx of digit 3
description: A distal phalanx that is part of a digit 3. In odd-toes ungulates (Perissodactyla e.g. horses) this is called the coffin bone. In even-toed ungulates (Artiodactyla e.g cattle) this is associated with the medial claw.

name: pedal digit 2 plus metapodial segment
description: A subdivision of the autopod consisting of pedal digit 2 plus the region incorporating a single metapodial element. These segments are typically repeated along the pre-axiom to post-axial axis.

name: caecum
description: A pouch in the digestive tract that connects the ileum with the ascending colon of the large intestine. It is separated from the ileum by the ileocecal valve, and is the beginning of the large intestine. It is also separated from the colon by the cecocolic junction.

name: accessory nasal sac
description: Accessory nasal sacs are found in a variety of teleosts (Webb, 1993) and likely assist in ventilating the olfactory epithelium by transmitting pressure Ô¨Çuctuations associated with gill irrigation from theoral cavity to the nasal (or sensory) sac (Jakubowski,1975; Webb, 1993; Belanger et al., 2003). [def from Eastman, J. T. and Lannoo, M. J. (2004)]

name: supraoptic crest
description: one of the circumventricular organs of the brain. The OVLT is outside the blood brain barrier, and so neurons in this region can respond to factors that are present in the systemic circulation.

name: ypsiloid cartilage
description: Y-shaped cartilage lying in the middle line, anterior to the pubo-ischium with which it articulates. It lies dorsal to the rectus abdominis muscle with which it articulates.

name: carapacial ridge ectoderm
description: A epithelium that is part of a carapacial ridge.

name: upper arm nerve
description: A nerve that is part of a forelimb stylopod [Automatically generated definition].

name: future hindbrain meninx
description: A multi-tissue structure that has the potential to develop into a meninx of hindbrain.

name: wall of urinary bladder
description: An anatomical wall that lines the insider of a urinary bladder.

name: central sulcus
description: The central sulcus is a fold in the cerebral cortex of brains in vertebrates. Also called the central fissure, it was originally called the fissure of Rolando or the Rolandic fissure, after Luigi Rolando. The central sulcus is a prominent landmark of the brain, separating the parietal lobe from the frontal lobe and the primary motor cortex from the primary somatosensory cortex. [WP,unvetted].

name: styloid process of ulna
description: The styloid process of the ulna projects from the medial and back part of the bone; it descends a little lower than the head, and its rounded end affords attachment to the ulnar collateral ligament of the wrist[WP,unvetted].

name: ventral ridge system
description: A collection of attached ridges on the ventrl surface of the femur consisting of the internal and fourth trochanters plus the adductor blade and crest. Most notible in early amniotes (based on Romer 1956)

name: tectum orbitale
description: The dorsal portion of the endocranium that covers the orbital region. Hanken and Hall (1993)

name: inter-premaxillary joint
description: Joint that articulates the left and right premaxillary bones. Inter-premaxillary joint is unpaired.

name: composite part spanning multiple base regional parts of brain
capsule of ovary
description: A capsule that surrounds a female gonad.

name: tympanohyoid cartilage
description: The terminal segment in the chain of skeletal elements of the hyoid apparatus. One of a pair of rods of cartilage that connect the hyoid bone to the styloid process of the petrous part of the temporal bone

name: submandibular region
description: The region between the mandible and the hyoid bone that contains the submandibular and sublingual glands, suprahyoid muscles, submandibular ganglion, and lingual artery.

name: urohyal lateral process
description: Process that is part of the urohyal; it is the posterolaterally directed process located on the ventrolateral margin of urohyal. Urohyal lateral process is paired.

name: profundal part of trigeminal ganglion complex
superficial feature part of the cerebellum
spiral valve of cystic duct
description: A series of crescentic folds of mucous membrane somewhat spirally arranged on the interior of the gallbladder and continuing into the cystic duct

name: basihyal tooth
description: Tooth that is attached to the basihyal tooth plate.

name: early prosencephalic vesicle
description: future brain vesicle that gives rise to telencephalic ventricle/lateral ventricles and 3rd ventricle

name: left adrenal gland medulla
description: the adrenal gland medulla that is in the left side of the abdomen

name: periovarian fat pad
description: The encapsulated adipose tissue associated with the ovaries.

name: mucosa of vagina
description: A mucosa that is part of a vagina [Automatically generated definition].

name: nauplius eye
description: An eye that consists of a cluster of three or four median eyes that form a single structural unit but are separated from one another by pigment layers

name: dorsal thoracic disc
description: Imaginal disc that is a precursor of dorsal thoracic structures of the adult.

name: forebrain pia mater
description: A pia mater that is part of a forebrain [Automatically generated definition].

name: chorionic ectoderm
description: A extraembryonic structure that develops_from a ectoderm and is part of a chorion.

name: minor alar cartilage
description: The part which forms the lateral wall is curved to correspond with the ala of the nose; it is oval and flattened, narrow behind, where it is connected with the frontal process of the maxilla by a tough fibrous membrane, in which are found three or four small cartilaginous plates, the lesser alar cartilages.

name: apex of cochlea
description: The cupula is a structure in the vestibular system, sensing proprioception. The cupula is located within the ampullae of each of the three semicircular canals. As fluid rushes by the cupula, hair cells within it sense rotational acceleration, and transmit the corresponding signal to the brain through the vestibulocochlear nerve (CN VIII) In their natural orientation within the head, the cupulae are located on the medial aspect of the semicircular canals. In this orientation, the kinocilia rest on the posterior aspect of the cupula. [WP,unvetted].

name: liver stroma
description: A stroma that is part of a liver.

name: paraventricular nucleus of the hypothalamus descending division - forniceal part
cerebral cortex neuropil
description: A neuropil that is part of a cerebral cortex [Automatically generated definition].

name: neck cartilage
description: A cartilage that is part of a neck [Automatically generated definition].

name: manual digit 3 metacarpus endochondral element
description: A manual digit 3 metacarpus bone or its cartilage or pre-cartilage precursor.

name: dorsal plus ventral thalamus
description: Subcortical brain region consisting of paired gray matter bodies in the dorsal diencephalon and forming part of the lateral wall of the third ventricle of the brain. The thalamus represents the major portion of the diencephalon and is commonly divided into cellular aggregates known as nuclear groups.(MeSH). The dorsal topographic division of the interbrain. The macrodissected adult human thalamus was clearly illustrated by Vesalius in 1543 and the term as defined here was introduced by His in 1893. It includes the traditional epithalamus, dorsal thalamus, and ventral thalamus of Herrick (1910, pp. 494, 498). Also see Kuhlenbeck (1927, Ch. 9) and Jones (1985, p. 87).

name: renal lymph node
description: A lymph node that is located in a kidney [Automatically generated definition].

name: lumen of secondary bronchus
description: An anatomical cavity that is part of a lobar bronchus.

name: cortex of cerebral lobe
description: Grey matter neocortex region of a lobe of the cerebral hemisphere.

name: wall of crypt of Lieberkuhn of small intestine
description: The lateral parts of an intestinal crypt that is located in the small intestine, continuous distally with the base and proximally with the intestinal villus epithelium.

name: epithelium of otic placode
description: An epithelium that is part of a otic placode [Automatically generated definition].

name: anatomical space
description: Non-material anatomical entity of three dimensions, that is generated by morphogenetic or other physiologic processes; is surrounded by one or more anatomical structures; contains one or more organism substances or anatomical structures.

name: epithelium of gonad
description: An epithelium surrounding a gonad.

name: bulbus arteriosus inner layer
description: Composed of subendothelium with longitudinally oriented collagen, reticular fibrils, elastic fibers, and smooth muscle cells bound by a thin endothelial layer. Hu et al. 2001.

name: deep anterior cervical lymph node
description: The deep anterior cervical lymph nodes are found near the middle cricothyroid ligament and the trachea.

name: regional part of spinal cord
description: A multi-tissue structure that is part of a spinal cord.

name: prepollex
description: A rudimentary additional digit-like structure on the preaxial side of the thumb of certain amphibians and mammals[dictionary.com].

name: somite 6
description: Undifferentiated mesodermal component of early trunk or tail segment or metamere, derived from paraxial mesoderm; forms the myotome, sclerotome and perhaps dermatome. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: barbel primordium
description: A surface structure that will eventually grow to form a barbel. The primordium is rich in taste buds. The final location for taste buds present in the primordium is the distal tip of the mature barbel.

name: upper secondary molar tooth
description: A secondary molar tooth that is part of a upper jaw region.

name: nerve ending
description: Specialized terminations of peripheral neurons. Nerve endings include NEUROEFFECTOR JUNCTION(s) by which neurons activate target organs and sensory receptors (see RECEPTORS, SENSORY) which transduce information from the various sensory modalities and send it centrally in the nervous system. Presynaptic nerve endings are PRESYNAPTIC TERMINALS.

name: nucleus of pudendal nerve
description: A nucleus in the ventral part of the anterior horn of the sacral region of the spinal cord that is the origin of the pudendal nerve.

name: medial nasal process mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a medial nasal prominence.

name: ischial tuberosity
description: A horizontal thickening onto which the muscles of the femur, such as the quadriceps and hamstring, attach.

name: obsolete telencephalon of rodent
description: The telencephalon of a rodent

name: obsolete palatine
description: Compound endochdondral and dermal bone that results from the fusion of the dermal dermopalatine and the endochondral autopalatine and forms the antero-lateral region of the palate. Commonly, it articulates with the maxilla antero-laterally and with the ethmoidal region medially. The palatine is paired.

name: obsolete palatine
description: Sliver of bone that invest part of or all the posterior aspect of each antorbital plane.

name: piriform aperture
description: A pear-shaped bony inlet comprising the most anterior and narrowest bony portion of the nasal airway.

name: rectus capitis anterior
description: A muscle situated immediately behind the upper part of the Longus capitis that arises from the anterior surface of the lateral mass of the atlas, and from the root of its transverse process that inserts into the inferior surface of the basilar part of the occipital bone immediately in front of the foramen magnum.

name: pectoral fin proximal radial element 1
description: Pectoral fin proximal radial element that is the most anterior or dorsal pectoral fin radial element.

name: piriform cortex layer 3
description: Deepest of 3 cytoarchitecturally defined layers of the piriform cortex characterized by a moderately high density of pyramidal cells and large numbers of basal dendrites descending from pyramidal cells in layer 2.

name: somite 4
description: Undifferentiated mesodermal component of early trunk or tail segment or metamere, derived from paraxial mesoderm; forms the myotome, sclerotome and perhaps dermatome. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: hyaloid vessel
description: A blood vessel that is associated with the lens. In mammals, this is transient and normally nourishes the retina, immature lens and primary vitreous of the developing eye.

name: entorhinal cortex layer 6
description: Layer of entorhinal cortex lying superficial to the cerebral white matter and deep to layer 5 characterized by cells of various shapes and sizes (Adapted from Paxinos, G. The rat central nervous system, 2nd ed, Academic Press, San Diego, 1995, pg. 474)

name: lower lateral primary incisor tooth
description: A lower primary incisor tooth that is in_the_lateral_side_of a dentition.

name: pelvic complex
description: Appendage girdle complex that when present, encompasses the pelvic appendicular skeleton and the pelvic girdle.

name: peptonephridium
description: Organs opening into the buccal cavity of pharynx (supposedly modified nephridia) of invertebrates.

name: skin bony tubercle
description: A bony structure embedded in skin, roughly equivalent to osteoderms.

name: motor system
description: The part of the central nervous system that is involved with movement.

name: premolar tooth 4
description: The premolar tooth of the upper or lower jaw that is phylogenetically number 4

name: midnasal cavity
description: An anatomical cavity that is the combination of the cavity between the nares and the choanae[HP,modified].

name: intermaxillary suture
description: A cranial suture in the midline of the skull that connects the left and right maxilla bones

name: obsolete predominantly gray regional part of ventral posteromedial nucleus
crista tibiofibularis
description: Tuberosity on the posterior surface of the lateral femoral condyle

name: hindlimb bud
description: A limb bud that develops into a hindlimb.

name: motor nucleus of trigeminal nerve
description: Nucleus located in the pontine tegmentum containing cells that give rise to motor innervation of the jaw through the trigeminal nerve. It receives both crossed and uncrossed fibers from the cerebral cortex (Heimer, L. The Human Brain and Spinal Cord, 2nd ed., 1996, pg 248).

name: margo vertebralis
description: Medial margin of the suprascapula, which lies dorsal to the vertebral column.

name: epithelium of pancreatic duct
description: An epithelium that is part of a pancreatic duct.

name: renal cortex artery
description: An artery that supplies the renal cortex.

name: cremaster muscle
description: A thin layer of skeletal muscle that envelops the spermatic cord and testis of most male mammals in a series of loops; it is a continuation of the obliquus internus, arising from the inguinal ligament and inserting into the crest of the pubis and into the sheath of the rectus abdominis; it is innervated by the genital branch of the genitofemoral nerve and functions to draw the testis up toward the superficial inguinal ring in response to cold or to stimulation of the nerve;

name: intersomitic artery
description: The small branching sprouts of the dorsal aorta that grow across the medial surface of the somite, turn right angles to grow over that surface and then fuse with other sprouts and form the vertebral arteries adjacent to the neural tube; the intersomitic arteries supply the body wall and persist in the adult as the posterior intercostal, subcostal and the lumbar arteries

name: pars jugalis
description: Anterior part of the quadratojugal that is in contact with the processus posterior of the maxilla.

name: submucosa of stomach
description: the fibrous connective tissue layer beneath the stomach mucosa

name: obsolete neurite
description: One of the processes or extensions of a neuron, axon or dendrite or cell body fiber. // Cell appendage of the neuron which includes the axon and the dendrite.

name: median extrascapular
description: The medial of the the paired series of extrascapular bones which carries the extrascapular or supratemporal canal.

name: m. ypsiloideus posterior
description: Contraction depresses the ypsiloid cartilage; arises from the anterodorsal edge of the pubis deep to the m. rectus abdominis profundus and spreads anteriorly in a fan shape to insert on the lateral edges of the shaft and the posterior edges of the lateral processes of the ypsiloid cartilage .

name: dermosphenotic
description: Infraorbital that is the last bone of the infraorbital series, carrying the infraorbital canal, and sometimes also the supraorbital, temporal, and/or preopercular canals. The dermosphenotic is sometimes sutured or fused completely to the skull, e.g. to the autosphenotic.

name: celiac lymph node
description: the visceral glands that are associated with the branches of the celiac artery, including the gastric, hepatic, and pancreaticolienal (splenic) lymph nodes

name: inferior hypophysial artery
description: The inferior hypophysial artery is an artery supplying the pituitary gland. It is a branch of the cavernous carotid artery (internal carotid artery).

name: urogenital sinus mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that surrounds primitive urogenital sinus.

name: septomaxilla bone
description: Paired, intramembranous bones located within the nasal capsules and embedded in the nasal cartilages; it is pierced by the ductus nasolacrimalis.

name: pelvic radial 1 cartilage
description: Small cartilage that forms at the posterior and lateral edge of the basipterygium.

name: embryonic cloacal lumen
description: An anatomical space that surrounded_by a embryonic cloaca.

name: spinalis cervicis muscle
description: Origin: spinous processes of seventh cervical and sometimes two upper thoracic vertebrae; insertion: spinous processes of axis and sometimes of second to fourth cervical vertebrae; innervation: branches of cervical; action: extends vertebral column.

name: pelvic fin distal radial bone 1
description: pelvic fin distal radial 1 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: adult mesothoracic segment
description: Any mesothoracic segment (UBERON:6000018) that is part of some adult thorax (UBERON:6003018).

name: digit 5
description: A digit that is part of a digit 5 plus metapodial segment.

name: thyroid primordium
description: The initial thyroid precursor, the thyroid primordium, starts as a simple midline thickening and develops to form the thyroid diverticulum. This structure is initially hollow, although it later solidifies and becomes bilobed. The 2 lobes are located on either side of the midline and are connected via an isthmus.

name: outer plexiform layer of retina
description: The layer within the retina where the bipolar cells synapse with the photoreceptor cells[ZFA]. Between the inner and outer nuclear layers, the outer plexiform layer (OPL) contains connections between the photoreceptors and bipolar and horizontal cells[GO].

name: epiphysis of fifth metatarsal bone
description: An epiphysis that is part of a metatarsal bone of digit 5 [Automatically generated definition].

name: chorioretinal region
description: The part of the eye that consists of both the retina and the optic choroid

name: compact bone of long bone
description: A compact bone tissue that is part of a bone tissue of long bone.

name: prepupa
description: An organism at the prepupal stage. The prepupal stage is a life stage interposed between the larval and the pupal stages in insects that undergo a complete metamorphosis. The start of the pre-pupal stage is marked by pupariation, and the end is marked by pupation

name: respiratory tract epithelium
description: the pseudostratified ciliated epithelium that lines much of the conducting portion of the airway, including part of the nasal cavity and larynx, the trachea, and bronchi

name: thoracic vertebra 1
description: The first thoracic vertebra counting from the top down. Note that members of this class are not necessarily homologous[ncit,modified].

name: triceps surae
description: The triceps surae is a pair of muscles located at the calf - the gastrocnemius and the soleus. These muscles both insert into the calcaneus, the bone of the heel of the human foot, and form the major part of the muscle of the back part of the lower leg, commonly known as the calf muscle. The triceps surae is connected to the foot through the Achilles tendon, and has 3 heads deriving from the 2 major masses of muscle. The superficial portion (the gastrocnemius) gives off 2 heads attaching to the base of the femur directly above the knee. The deep (profundis) mass of muscle (the soleus) forms the remaining head which attaches to the superior posterior area of the tibia. The triceps surae is innervated by the tibial nerve, specifically, nerve roots L5-S2. [WP,unvetted].

name: palpebral vein
description: A blood vessel that drains from from an eyelid.

name: manus joint
description: A skeletal joint that is part of a manus (hand) [Automatically generated definition].

name: substantia innominata
description: A predominantly gray matter structure of the basal telencephalon defined on the basis of Nissl stain. Caudal to the anterior commissure it lies deep to the globus pallidus and dorsal to the amygdala. Rostral to the anterior commissure it lies deep to the striatum. The more rostral portion contains the basal forebrain nucleus ( Anthoney-1994 ). In the late twentieth century the region containing the substantia innominata was resegmented on the basis of neurochemistry and connectivity to constitute the striatopallidal system ( Heimer-1995 ). In this scheme the caudal portion of substantia innominata is located largely in the ventral pallidum and the rostral portion in the ventral striatum. (from Brain Info)

name: scale circulus
description: Fine ridge on surface of scale, often parallel to the circumference of scale.

name: pedal digit 5 metatarsal pre-cartilage condensation
description: A pedal digit metatarsal pre-cartilage condensation that is part of a pedal digit 5 mesenchyme.

name: ureter
description: Muscular duct that propels urine from the kidneys to the urinary bladder, or related organs.

name: secondary palate
description: The part of the palate formed from the fusion of the two palatine shelves, extensions of the maxillary prominences.

name: roof of mouth
description: A multi-tissue structure consisting of bone and soft tissue that forms a part of the roof of the oral cavity. In mammals this is the combination of the primary palate (premaxilla) and the secondary palate. In early tetrapods it consists of the vomer, pterygoid, parasphenoid, palatine and ectopterygoid bones.

name: bona-fide anatomical boundary
description: An anatomical boundary that corresponds to some physical discontinuity.

name: epibranchial series
description: Anatomical cluster that consists of the epibranchial elements within an individual.

name: cleavage stage
description: The first few specialized divisions of an activated animal egg; Stage consisting of division of cells in the early embryo. The zygotes of many species undergo rapid cell cycles with no significant growth, producing a cluster of cells the same size as the original zygote. The different cells derived from cleavage are called blastomeres and form a compact mass called the morula. Cleavage ends with the formation of the blastula.

name: oropharyngeal choana
description: opening/conduit between the nasal cavity and the oropharynx via the roof of the mouth.

name: myotome somite 11
description: Portion of the somite giving rise to body wall muscle masses. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: sublaminar layers S2 or S3
description: One of sublaminar layers S2 or S3.

name: breast feather tract
description: A feather tract that is part of a the upper ventral region of an animal's torso.

name: esophagus squamous epithelium
description: A squamous epithelium that is part of a esophagus.

name: suprameatal foramen
description: Foramen in the temporal bone, adjacent to the base of the zygomatic process.

name: hypothalamic nucleus
description: A nucleus of brain that is part of a hypothalamus.

name: mammary placode
description: The mammary placode is a transient lens shaped structure that will give rise to the mammary bud proper[GO].

name: entire extraembryonic component
description: The part of the conceptus that may be lost before birth or will be discarded at birth, or when the embryo becomes an independent organism.

name: ethmoid foramen
description: An bone foramen in the ethmoid bone.

name: metanephric glomerular epithelium
description: A metanephric glomerular visceral epithelial cell is a specialized epithelial cell that contains 'feet' that interdigitate with the 'feet' of other glomerular epithelial cells in the metanephros[GO].

name: conducting system of heart
description: The cardiac conduction system consists of specialized cardiomyocytes that regulate the frequency of heart beat[GO]

name: rhombomere boundary
description: A boundary delimiting a rhombomere.

name: pancreatic fat pad
description: A fat pad that is part of a pancreas.

name: middle lobe of lung
description: A lobe of the lung that is situated somewhere between an upper lobe and lower lobe.

name: middle lobe of right lung
description: In the human, the right lung is divided into three lobes (as opposed to two lobes on the left), superior, middle, and inferior, by two interlobular fissures: [WP,unvetted].

name: thoracic segment blood vessel
description: A blood vessel that is part of a thorax [Automatically generated definition].

name: fetal tooth
description: Type of deciduous dentition found in foetuses and altricial juveniles of some caecilians.

name: hip muscle
description: Any muscle organ that is part of a hip [Automatically generated definition].

name: visceral pleura
description: The inner serous membrane of the pulmonary pleural. The visceral pleura lines the lungs.

name: perilymphatic channel
description: A channel containing perilymph passing through the temporal bone, connecting the scala tympani of the cochlea to the subarachnoid space.

name: optic choroid
description: vascular layer containing connective tissue, of the eye lying between the retina and the sclera. The choroid provides oxygen and nourishment to the outer layers of the retina. Along with the ciliary body and iris, the choroid forms the uveal tract[WP].

name: costal arch
description: The costal margin, sometimes referred to as the costal arch, is the medial margin formed by the false ribs, which in humans is from the eighth rib to the tenth rib.

name: respiratory system basement membrane
description: A basement membrane of epithelium that is part of a respiratory system.

name: vasculature
description: An interconnected tubular multi-tissue structure contains fluid that is actively transported around the organism[ZFA]. Examples: vasculature of lung, vasculature of face.

name: M. ulnocarpalis
description: Originates along distal third of the ulna and inserts on the ulnare.

name: circle of Willis
description: A circle of arteries that supply blood to the brain. The Circle of Willis comprises the following arteries: Anterior cerebral artery (left and right); Anterior communicating artery; Internal carotid artery (left and right); Posterior cerebral artery (left and right); Posterior communicating artery (left and right).The basilar artery and middle cerebral arteries, supplying the brain, are also considered part of the circle

name: ectoderm
description: Primary germ layer that is the outer of the embryo's three germ layers and gives rise to epidermis and neural tissue.

name: circular muscle layer of muscular coat
description: The inner layer of the muscular coat.

name: pila preoptica
description: A strut of cartilage  extending dorsally from the basal plate and with other similar cartilages forming the sides of the brain case. Posterior to the pila preoptica is the pila antoptica between these two cartilages emerges the optic and trochlear nerves.

name: humeroradial joint
description: A hinge joint between the head of the radius and the capitulum of the humerus.

name: non-transverse process-bearing vertebra
description: A vertebra that does not have a transverse process.

name: stomach smooth muscle inner oblique layer
description: The innermost layer of the muscularis; it is not present in all sections of the stomach but is clearly seen in the fundus and near the lesser curvature of the corpus; the oblique fibers disappear distally (towards the pyloric antrum); the oblique layer is responsible for creating the motion that churns and physically breaks down the food

name: taenia coli
description: The taeniae coli (also teniae coli) are three separate longitudinal ribbons of smooth muscle on the outside of the ascending, transverse, descending and sigmoid colons. They are visible, and can be seen just below the serosa or fibrosa. They are the Mesocolic, Free and Omental Coli. The teniae coli contracts length wise to produce the haustra, the bulges in the colon. The bands converge at the root of the vermiform appendix and the rectum. These bands correspond to the outer layer of the muscularis externa, in other portions of the digestive tract.

name: cardiac skeleton
description: Dense connective tissue that separates the atria from the ventricles and provides physical support for the heart.

name: obsolete precementoblast
description: Skeletogenic cell that has the potential to develop into a cementoblast.

name: appendage vasculature
description: A vasculature that is part of a limb/fin.

name: prepelvic clasper
description: A supplemental clasper in Holocephali, in front of the pelvic fin

name: glomeral mesenchyme
description: Portion of tissue that consists of the precursors of the pronephric glomus or glomerulus; derived from the medial portion of the pronephric intermediate mesoderm.

name: orbitofrontal cortex
description: The region of the cerebral cortex covering the basal surface of the frontal lobes; this region normally controls emotion and decision making

name: pectineus muscle
description: An adductor muscle that attaches to the pelvic bone and the femur. In humans, The pectineus muscle is a flat, quadrangular muscle, situated at the anterior part of the upper and medial aspect of the thigh. It can be classified in the medial compartment of thigh (when the function is emphasized) or the anterior compartment of thigh (when the nerve is emphasized). [WP,generalized].

name: distal phalanx of digit 4
description: A distal phalanx that is part of a digit 4 [Automatically generated definition].

name: pedal digit 3 plus metapodial segment
description: A subdivision of the autopod consisting of pedal digit 3 plus the region incorporating a single metapodial element. These segments are typically repeated along the pre-axiom to post-axial axis.

name: pedal digit 3
description: 3rd digit of the hind autopod.

name: caudal part of spinal trigeminal nucleus
Sharpey's fiber
description: Sharpey's fibres (bone fibres, or perforating fibres) are a matrix of connective tissue consisting of bundles of strong collagenous fibres connecting periosteum to bone. They are part of the outer fibrous layer of periosteum, entering into the outer circumferential and interstitial lamellae of bone tissue.

name: parapharyngeal space
description: The portion of the peripharyngeal space limited by the lateral wall of the pharynx, the cervical vertebrae and medial pterygoid muscle.

name: periodontal ligament
description: The fibrous connective tissue that surrounds the root of a tooth, separating it from and attaching it to the alveolar bone. It extends from the base of the gingival mucosa to the fundus of the bony socket, and its main function is to hold the tooth in its socket[BTO].

name: lower leg nerve
description: A nerve that is part of a lower leg [Automatically generated definition].

name: future metencephalon
description: A developing anatomical structure that has the potential to develop into a metencephalon.

name: trigone of urinary bladder
description: the smooth triangular region of the wall of the urinary bladder formed by the two ureteral orifices and the internal urethral orifice; it is an area in which the muscle fibers are closely adherent to the mucosa

name: processual entity
description: An occurrent [span:Occurrent] that exists in time by occurring or happening, has temporal parts and always involves and depends on some entity.

name: obsolete regional part of inferior colliculus
description: A regional part of brain that is part of a inferior colliculus [Automatically generated definition].

name: supraorbital ridge
description: the superior half of the orbital rim, which constitutes the curved superior border of the orbital opening, formed by the frontal bone.

name: medial octavolateralis nucleus
description: Lateral line sensory nucleus located in the cerebellum that processes sensory input from the lateral line.

name: obsolete accessory nasal sac
description: Structures that communicate with the main olfactory chamber and may be located posterior, ventral, or dorsal to it. [De Pinna, 1996]

name: skin flap
description: Surface structure that is a portion of skin that projects or hangs from the body.

name: postzonal element
description: All those parts of the pectoral girdle that lies posterior to the zonal area.

name: posterior ventrolateral plate
description: Dermal bone that is part of the scapular complex in placoderms.

name: seminal fluid
description: A substance formed from the secretion of one or more glands of the male genital tract in which sperm cells are suspended.

name: seminal vesicle fluid
description: A bodily secretion that is produced by a seminal vesicle.

name: dermal papilla
description: A mesodermal signaling center of the hair follicle consisting of closely packed specialized mesenchymal fibroblasts. Framed by the enlarged bulb matrix in anagen.

name: feather bud, dermal component
description: The part of the feather bud formed by a proliferation of dermal cells

name: external iliac artery
description: The external iliac artery is a large artery in the pelvic region that carries blood to the lower limb. The external iliac artery is a paired artery, meaning there is one on each side of the body: a right external iliac artery and left external iliac artery. The external iliac artery is accompanied by the external iliac vein, which is located posterior to the artery. [WP,unvetted].

name: obsolete hemisphere parts of cerebral cortex
cerebral hemisphere
description: One of two bilateral, largely symmetrical organ subdivisions within the telencephalon which contain the cerebral cortex and cerebral white matter.[FMA]

name: orbital part of frontal bone
description: A zone of the frontal bone that consists of two thin triangular plates, the orbital plates, which form the vaults of the orbits, and are separated from one another by a median gap, the ethmoidal notch.

name: accessory ciliary ganglion
description: A parasympathetic ganglion located on the short ciliary nerve differentiated from the main ciliary ganglion by virtue of the fact that it had no root derived directly from the inferior trunk of the oculomotor nerve and it never attaches to this nerve

name: urohyal median process
description: Process that is part of the urohyal; it is the posterodorsally directed and median process located on the dorsal margin of the urohyal.

name: spiral valve of conus arteriosus
description: The spiral valve alternately blocks & unblocks the entrances to the left and right pulmonary arches (sending unoxygenated blood to the skin & lungs).

name: pubic pre-cartilage condensation
description: A pubic endochondral element that is composed primarily of a pre-cartilage condensation.

name: right adrenal gland cortex
description: the thick outer layer of the adrenal gland that is in the right side of the abdomen

name: tail fat pad
description: Encapsulated adipose tissue that is part of a tail.

name: mucosa of seminal vesicle
description: A mucosa that is part of a seminal vesicle [Automatically generated definition].

name: uterine spiral artery
description: A corkscrew-like artery in premenstrual or progestational endometrium; uterine spiral arteries play a vital role in supplying nutrients to the placenta and fetus, and are thus remodeled into highly dilated inelastic vessels by the action of invading trophoblast (physiological change)

name: obsolete unspecified
description: Annotation with this anatomy term indicates that a structure was not specified by the author.

name: midbrain pia mater
description: A pia mater that is part of a midbrain [Automatically generated definition].

name: caudal middle frontal gyrus
description: Component of the middle frontal gyrus. The rostral boundary of the middle frontal gyrus was the rostral extent of the middle frontal gyrus whereas the caudal boundary was the precentral gyrus. The medial and lateral boundaries were designated as the superior frontal sulcus and the inferior frontal sulcus respectively (Christine Fennema-Notestine).

name: capsule of liver
description: A collagenous capsule covering the external surface of the liver.

name: brain endothelium
description: Vascular endothelium found in blood vessels of the blood-brain-barrier.

name: ventral nasal meatus
description: The ventral nasal meatus is found between the ventral nasal concha and the dorsal surface of the hard palate.It connects the nasal vestibule with the nasopharynx. Rostrally it is narrow at the nasal vestibule and widens caudally towards the nasopharyngeal meatus. The ventral nasal meatus is the main passage for air. Apart from olfaction, the nasal cavity functions to warm the inhaled air as it passes through the meatuses over the vascular beds of the mucosa. The air is humidified by the vaporization of tears and serous nasal secretion. The air is cleaned throughout the scattered mucous glands. These glands secrete mucous through the nasal cavity and the mucous serves to trap the large particles that come into contact with it. PPP Clinically in the horse the ventral nasal meatus is the main passage through which a stomach tube can be passed to the pharynx and oesophagus and then to the stomach. This kind of a tube is commonly used when drenching a horse for colic, as well as having many other veterinary applications. The tube has to pass through the ventral nasal meatus to the nasopharyngeal meatus and the caudal nares to reach the pharynx and oesophagus. If the tube is accidentally passed into the dorsal or middle nasal meatuses it would pass to the ethmotubinates and cause massive haemorrhage.

name: eye gland
description: A gland that is part of a eye. The eye is a compound unit which depending on the species may consist of an eyeballs plus associated ducts and integumentary structures. Eye glands therefore include the various types of lacrimal gland, the various types of apocrine and sebaceous glands associated with the eyelid.

name: obsolete regional part of basal amygdaloid nucleus
manual digit 4 metacarpus endochondral element
description: A manual digit 4 metacarpus bone or its cartilage or pre-cartilage precursor.

name: manual major digit (Aves)
description: A manual digit found in Aves that is morphologically similar to digit 2 in the standard tetrapod configuration and develops from embryonic digit 3.

name: hypothalamus
description: A specialized brain region of the ventral diencephalon arising near the end of the segmentation period; the embryonic hypothalamic region will give rise to the posterior pituitary gland as well as a number of brain nuclei. [ZFA]. One of the most important functions of the hypothalamus is to link the nervous system to the endocrine system via the pituitary gland (hypophysis).[Wikipedia].

name: manual digit 1
description: 1st (preaxial) digit of the manus[Wikipedia].

name: dermis adipose tissue
description: An adipose tissue that is part of a dermis [Automatically generated definition].

name: lumen of tertiary bronchus
description: An anatomical cavity that is part of a segmental bronchus.

name: sagittal suture
description: the dense, fibrous connective tissue joint between the tetrapod parietal bones

name: inter-parietal joint
description: Fibrous joint connecting the parietal bones.

name: zona intermedia of adrenal gland
description: A zone of the adrenal cortex located between the zona glomerulosa and the zona fasciculata.

name: material anatomical entity
description: Anatomical entity that has mass.

name: body marking
description: Surface structure that is a visible mark on the body resulting from pigmentation.

name: gingival epithelium
description: A stratified squamous epithelium consisting of a basal layer; it is keratinized or parakeratinized[BTO].

name: odontode scale
description: Multi-tissue structure composed of enameloid, dentine surrounding a pulp cavity, and bone of attachment anchoring the element into the dermis[VSAO].

name: somite 9
description: Undifferentiated mesodermal component of early trunk or tail segment or metamere, derived from paraxial mesoderm; forms the myotome, sclerotome and perhaps dermatome. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: wall of left ventricle
description: Wall of ventricle which is continuous with the wall of aorta.

name: strand of hair on external ear
lateral nasal process mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a lateral nasal prominence.

name: nerve to quadratus femoris
description: The nerve to quadratus femoris is a nerve that provides innervation to the quadratus femoris and gemellus inferior muscles.

name: obsolete brain of rodent
description: The brain of a rodent

name: caudal basal fulcrum
description: Basal fulcrum that precedes a caudal fin lobe. Arratia, G. 2009. Identifying patterns of diversity of the actinopterygian fulcra. Acta Zoologica (Stockholm) 90 (Suppl. 1): 220-235.

name: rectus capitis posterior major
description: A muscle that arises by a pointed tendon from the spinous process of the axis and inserts into the lateral part of the inferior nuchal line of the occipital bone and the surface of the bone immediately below the line.

name: pectoral fin proximal radial element 2
description: Pectoral fin proximal radial element that is the second most anterior or dorsal pectoral fin radial element.

name: somite 8
description: Undifferentiated mesodermal component of early trunk or tail segment or metamere, derived from paraxial mesoderm; forms the myotome, sclerotome and perhaps dermatome. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: obsolete nematocyst
description: A cnida that is harpoon-like in structure and is capable of penetrating prey.

name: hyoid muscle
description: One of a group of muscles used in mastication and swallowing. These muscles are attached to the hyoid bone, which is suspended in the neck and forms the base of the tongue and larynx. The muscles are divided into suprahyoid (superior) or infrahyoid (inferior) groups relative to the bone[WP, generalized].

name: sexually immature organism
description: A multicellular organism that is at the juvenile stage.

name: upper primary canine tooth
description: A primary canine tooth that is part of a upper jaw region.

name: neural tube ventricular layer
description: The layer of undifferentiated, proliferating cells that line the neural tube lumen that is the immediate transformation of the germinal neuroepithelium

name: hindbrain venous system
description: A venous system that is part of a hindbrain.

name: dorsal cloacal gland
description: Cloacal gland in female salamanders that secrete into the dorsal walls of the cloaca, anterior and / or posterior to the spermathecae or near the spermathecal common tube

name: gastric lymph node
description: A lymph node along the left gastric artery or greater omentum.

name: hippocampus molecular layer
description: The most superficial stratum in the hippocampus. Here the perforant path fibers form synapses onto the distal, apical dendrites of pyramidal cells.

name: commissure of superior colliculus
description: A commissure that is part of a superior colliculus [Automatically generated definition].

name: incisura coracoidea
description: Notch that separates the cartilaginous regions of the procoracoid and coracoid.

name: anatomical conduit
description: Any tube, opening or passage that connects two distinct anatomical spaces.

name: sciatic notch
description: Either of two notches on the dorsal border of the hip bone on each side that when closed off by ligaments form the corresponding sciatic foramina.

name: body of pancreas
description: The body of the pancreas is a subsection of the pancreas organ in the human body. It is somewhat prismatic in shape, and has three surfaces: anterior, posterior, and inferior. It is at the same level as the transpyloric plane. [WP,unvetted].

name: right frontal lobe
description: A frontal cortex that is part of a right cerebral hemisphere.

name: diphycercal tail
description: An internally and externally symmetrical tail (caudal) fin

name: pectoral fin bud
description: A paired fin bud that develops into a pectoral fin.

name: pectoral appendage bud
description: A limb bud that develops into a forelimb or pectoral fin.

name: spina acromioidea
description: Small process of the lamina recurvata that extends laterally toward the scapular-suprascapular articulation.

name: anterior nucleus of hypothalamus
description: a loose heterogeneous collection of cells in the anterior hypothalamus, continuous rostrally with the medial and lateral preoptic areas and caudally with the tuber cinereum

name: principal gastric gland
description: one of the gastric glands that secretes the hydrochloric acid of the gastric juice[Stedman's].

name: gastric gland
description: The branched tubular glands found in the mucosa of the fundus and body of the stomach which contain parietal cells that secrete hydrochloric acid and zymogenic cells that produce pepsin.

name: spinal artery
description: Arteries that supply the spinal cord.

name: processus dorsalis of lamella alaris
description: Dorsal process of the lamella alaris located at the anterior end of the margo orbitalis; a narrow ligament that runs from the frontoparietal is attached to it.

name: obsolete regional part of tuberomammillary nucleus
serosa of stomach
description: the outermost layer of the stomach wall, consisting of layers of connective tissue continuous with the peritoneum

name: obsolete predominantly white regional part of thalamus
obsolete synapse
description: The structural contact that is the site of transmission between neurons, identified by a presynaptic ribbon and synaptic vesicles as the input element and one or (usually) more postsynaptic elements with various specializations (membrane densities, cisternae, etc.).

name: metacarpal extensor pit
description: Pits located on the proximodorsal part of metacarpals denoting the attachemnt sites for ligaments.

name: ramulus suprabranchialis anterior
description: Ramulus that innervates the suprabranchial line of neuromasts.

name: infant stage
description: Nursing stage that follows the neonate stage in mammals and ends at weaning.

name: mesothoracic tergum
description: The dorsal sclerites (tergites) of the mesothorax.

name: mesenteric lymph node
description: The lymph nodes located in the mesentery, of which there are 3 classes: ileocolic, juxtaintestinal mesenteric, and central superior group.

name: embryonic cloacal epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a embryonic cloaca.

name: cloacal epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a cloaca.

name: postfrontal bone
description: A bone behind and above the orbit of which it commonly forms part of the border that is present in many vertebrates and corresponds to the postorbital process of the frontal bone of various birds and mammals

name: longissimus lumborum muscle
description: Lumbar muscle that extends and rotates the vertebral column.

name: anterior surface of kidney
description: The aspect of the kidney facing the abdominal cavity.

name: fluid-based anatomical entity
description: Fluid anatomical entity containing cells.

name: dorsal fin ray
description: Soft ray that is part of the dorsal fin.

name: obsolete dorsal fin lepidotrichium
description: Lepidotrichium which is part of the dorsal fin.

name: ultimobranchial body
description: An outpocketing of one of the caudal pharyngeal pouches that is comprised on calcitonin-producing parafollicular cells.

name: anterior longitudinal ligament
description: A ligament running the length of the anterior surface of the spinal column and thereby interconnects all the vertebral bodies.

name: palatoquadrate cartilage
description: The dorsal component of the mandibular arch

name: inner nuclear layer of retina
description: Cytoarchitectural layer of retina containing closely packed cell bodies, the majority of which are bipolar cells (adapted from Wikipedia).

name: pectoral fin ray 1
description: Pectoral fin lepidotrichium 1 is the leading or marginal ray of the fin and articulates with the scapula. Lepidotrichium 1 is commonly segmented but unbranched but occasionally may be a massive strong unsegmented element (e.g., spine).

name: Brodmann (1909) area 36
description: Ectorhinal area 36 is a subdivision of the cytoarchitecturally defined temporal region of cerebral cortex. With its medial boundary corresponding approximately to the rhinal sulcus it is located primarily in the fusiform gyrus. Cytoarchitecturally it is bounded laterally and caudally by the inferior temporal area 20, medially by the perirhinal area 35 and rostrally by the temporopolar area 38 (H) (Brodmann-1909). Together with Brodmann area 35, it comprises the perirhinal cortex.

name: somatic muscle
description: A muscle structure of invertebrates whose origin and insertion sites are in basal side of the epidermis or structures derived from it. The simplest somatic muscles consist of a single cell and associated extracellular structures.

name: fibularis tertius
description: A muscle located in the lower limb that arises from the lower third of the anterior surface of the fibula; from the lower part of the interosseous membrane; and from an intermuscular septum between it and the peroneus brevis and inserted into the dorsal surface of the base of the metatarsal bone of the 5th digit. It is innervated by the deep fibular nerve. Its action is that of weak dorsiflexion of the ankle joint and to evert the foot at the ankle joint.

name: anterior pole of lens
description: the central point on the anterior surface of the lens.

name: compact bone of diaphysis
description: A compact bone tissue that is part of a diaphysis.

name: pupa
description: An organism at the pupal stage. A life cycle stage of holometabolous insects in which the organism is a pupa and starts with the larval-pupal apolysis and ends with pupal-adult apolysis.

name: penis epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a penis [Automatically generated definition].

name: sylvian point
description: The Sylvian point is the point on the human skull nearest the Sylvian fissure and is located about 30 millimeters behind the Zygomatic process of frontal bone.

name: thoracic vertebra 2
description: The second thoracic vertebra counting from the top down. Note that members of this class are not necessarily homologous[ncit,modified].

name: posterior semicircular canal
description: The posterior semicircular canal is a part of the vestibular system and detects rotations of the head in the sagittal plane.

name: posterior semicircular duct
description: The semicircular canals are three half-circular, interconnected tubes located inside each ear. The three canals are the horizontal semicircular canal (also known as the lateral semicircular canal), superior semicircular canal (also known as the anterior semicircular canal), and the posterior semicircular canal. The canals are aligned approximately orthogonally to one another. The horizontal canal is aligned roughly horizontally in the head. The superior and anterior canals are aligned roughly at a 45 degree angle to a vertical plane drawn from the nose to the back of the skull. Thus, the horizontal canal detects horizontal head movements (such as when doing a pirouette), while the superior and posterior canals detect vertical head movements. Each canal is filled with a fluid called endolymph and contains a motion sensor with little hairs whose ends are embedded in a gelatinous structure called the cupula. As the skull twists in any direction, the endolymph is thrown into different sections of the canals. The cilia detect when the endolymph rushes past, and a signal is then sent to the brain. The semicircular canals are a component of the Labyrinth. Among species of mammals, the size of the semicircular canals is correlated with their type of locomotion. Specifically, species that are agile and have fast, jerky locomotion have larger canals relative to their body size than those that move more cautiously.

name: flexor digitorum longus
description: The Flexor digitorum longus is situated on the tibial side of the leg. At its origin it is thin and pointed, but it gradually increases in size as it descends. This muscle serves to curl the second, third, fourth, and fifth toes (flexion of phalanges II-V). [WP,unvetted].

name: dorsal fin proximal radial cartilage 3
description: dorsal fin proximal radial 3 element that is composed of cartilage tissue.

name: infraorbital sinus
description: An air-filled recess in the head of birds which lies lateral to the nasal cavity into which it opens

name: concurrent branch afferent branchial artery
description: The branch of the afferent branchial artery that continues posteriodorsally. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: anal pterya
description: One of two rows of feathers encircling the cloaca

name: parvicellular part of ventral posteromedial nucleus
prootic depression
description: Shallow area that exists on the prootic.

name: urethra
description: the fibromuscular tubular canal through which urine is discharged from the bladder to the exterior via the external urinary meatus; in males, the urethra is joined by the ejaculatory ducts and serves as a passageway for semen during ejaculation, as well as a canal for urine during voiding; in females, the urethra is shorter and emerges above the vaginal opening

name: spinal nucleus of trigeminal nerve
description: Nucleus extending from the upper spinal cord through the pontine tegmentum that receives sensory inputs from the trigeminal nerve. It is continuous caudally with the dorsal gray matter of the spinal cord.

name: obsolete musculus rectus inferior
description: Cranial nerve III innervated; ventral in the rectus group.

name: epaxial region somite 8
description: Somite-derived body wall muscle present dorsal to the horizontal myoseptum. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: ceratobranchial series
description: Anatomical cluster that consists of the ceratobranchial elements within an individual.

name: blastula stage
description: An early stage of embryonic development in animals. It is produced by cleavage of a fertilized ovum and consists of a spherical layer of around 128 cells surrounding a central fluid-filled cavity called the blastocoel. The blastula follows the morula and precedes the gastrula in the developmental sequence.

name: lenticular fasciculus
description: The lenticular fasciculus is a tract connecting the globus pallidus to the Thalamic fasciculus. The thalamic fasciculus (composed of the lenticular fasciculus and ansa lenticularis) runs into the Thalamus. It connects the globus pallidus to the thalamus.

name: secondary auditory cortex
description: The part of the auditory cortex that receive more diffuse input from the belt areas of the medial geniculate complex.

name: endostyle
description: An endostyle is a longitudinal ciliated groove on the ventral wall of the pharynx which produces mucus to gather food particles. It is found in urochordates and cephalochordates, and in the larvae of lampreys. It aids in transporting food to the esophagus. It is also called the hypopharyngeal groove. The endostyle in larval lampreys (ammocetes) metamorphoses into the thyroid gland in adults, and is regarded as being homologous to the thyroid gland in vertebrates. However, Dumont, et al. question whether the endostyle in ammocetes is homologous with that of the urochordates and cephalochordates. Since the endostyle is found in the three branches of chordates, it is presumed to have arisen in the common ancestor of these taxa, along with a shift to internal feeding for extracting suspended food from the water.

name: ciliary processes
description: The ciliary processes are formed by the inward folding of the various layers of the choroid, i.e. , the choroid proper and the lamina basalis, and are received between corresponding foldings of the suspensory ligament of the lens.

name: myotome somite 15
description: Portion of the somite giving rise to body wall muscle masses. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: cerebellum vasculature
description: A vasculature that is part of a cerebellum.

name: sublaminar layers S4 or S5
description: One of sublaminar layers S4 or S5.

name: atrium cardiac jelly
description: A cardiac jelly that is part of an atrium [Automatically generated definition].

name: stomach squamous epithelium
description: A squamous epithelium that is part of a stomach.

name: supratemporal process
description: Process of the parietal

name: ectodermal placode
description: An ectodermal placode is a thickening of the ectoderm that is the primordium of many structures derived from the ectoderm[GO]

name: styloid process of temporal bone
description: slender needle-like pointed projection that runs downward and slightly forward from the base of the inferior surface of the petrous portion of the temporal bone where it joins the tympanic portion; it gives attachment to the styloglossus, stylohyoid, and stylopharyngeus muscles and the stylohyoid and stylomandibular ligaments

name: diencephalic nucleus
description: A nucleus of brain that is part of a diencephalon.

name: pyramid of medulla oblongata
description: The anterior or ventral portion of the medulla oblongata is named the pyramid and lies between the anterior median fissure and the antero-lateral sulcus. Its upper end is slightly constricted, and between it and the pons the fibers of the abducent nerve emerge; a little below the pons it becomes enlarged and prominent, and finally tapers into the anterior funiculus of the medulla spinalis, with which, at first sight, it appears to be directly continuous[WP].

name: transitional anatomical structure
description: An embryonic anatomical entity that will turn into one or more other anatomical entities, perhaps with other anatomical entities, later in development.

name: metanephric glomerular endothelium
description: The metanephric glomerular endothelium is an epithelial tissue that covers the internal surfaces of the glomerulus of the metanephros[GO].

name: sinoatrial node
description: The part of the cardiac conduction system that controls the timing of heart muscle contraction. It relays electrical signals to the AV node[GO]. Subdivision of conducting system of heart at the junction of the right atrium and the superior vena cava, around the sinoatrial nodal branch of right coronary artery and is continuous with the internodal tract[FMA].

name: intermediolateral nucleus
description: The intermediolateral nucleus is a region of gray matter found in Rexed lamina VII of the spinal column. Rexed Lamina VII contains several well defined nuclei including the nucleus dorsalis, the intermediolateral cell column (lateral gray horn), and the sacral autonomic nucleus. It extends from the first thoracic through the third lumbar segment, and contains the autonomic motor neurons that give rise to the preganglionic fibers of the sympathetic system. [WP,unvetted].

name: abdominal segment blood vessel
description: A blood vessel that is part of an abdominal segment of trunk [Automatically generated definition].

name: muscularis mucosae of duodenum
description: A muscularis mucosa that is part of a duodenum.

name: m. opercularis
description: Muscle which arises from the dorsal m. levator scapulae and extends between the operculum and suprascapula.

name: pedal digit muscle
description: Any muscle organ that is part of a toe [Automatically generated definition].

name: pleural cavity
description: The fluid-filled cavity that lies between the visceral and parietal pleurae.

name: chest wall
description: Subdivision of thorax which includes all structures from the skin to the costal pleura. Examples: There is only one chest wall.

name: basilar membrane of cochlea
description: A stiff structural element that separates two liquid-filled tubes that run along the coil of the cochlea, the scala media and the scala tympani[WP].

name: pastern region of limb
description: A part of the leg of a horse between the fetlock and the top of the hoof. It incorporates the long pastern bone (proximal phalanx) and the short pastern bone (middle phalanx), which are held together by two sets of paired ligaments to form the pastern joint (proximal interphalangeal joint)

name: endoderm
description: Primary germ layer that lies remote from the surface of the embryo and gives rise to internal tissues such as gut.

name: longitudinal muscle layer of muscular coat
description: The outer layer of the muscular coat.

name: tibiofibular joint
description: A joint that connects the tibia and the fibula.

name: hindbrain neural plate
description: A neural plate that develops_from a presumptive hindbrain.

name: anatomical plane
description: A flat anatomical 2D surface that bisects an anatomical structure or an anatomical space.

name: stomach smooth muscle outer longitudinal layer
description: The most superficial layer of the muscularis; it has two sections, a longitudinal layer that is common with the esophagus and ends in the corpus, and a longitudinal layer that originates in the corpus and spreads into the duodenum

name: lacrimal bone
description: the irregularly thin plate that forms part of the medial wall of the orbit behind the frontal process of the maxilla

name: intervertebral disk of thoracic vertebra
description: An intervertebral disk that is part of a thoracic region of vertebral column. A thoracic intervertebral disk connects at least one thoracic vertebra, either to another thoracic vertebra, or at one point on the vertebral colummn, to a lumbar vertebra

name: parasympathetic nerve
description: A nerve that is part of a parasympathetic nervous system [Automatically generated definition].

name: outflow part of right ventricle
description: Anteriosuperior, smooth-walled portion of the cavity of the right ventricle, beginning at the supraventricular crest and terminating in the pulmonary trunk

name: conus arteriosus
description: A conical pouch formed from the upper and left angle of the right ventricle in the chordate heart, from which the pulmonary artery arises[WP]. the anteriosuperior, smooth-walled portion of the cavity of the right ventricle, beginning at the supraventricular crest and terminates in the pulmonary trunk[MP].

name: glomerular basement membrane
description: the layer of extracellular matrix that lies between the endothelium of the glomerular capillaries and the podocytes of the inner or visceral layer of the Bowman capsule; it is a fusion of the endothelial cell and podocyte basal laminas and acts as a physical barrier and an ion-selective filter

name: paratenial nucleus
description: One of the median nuclei of the thalamus, situated ventral and medial to the stria medullaris.

name: obsolete prechondroblast
description: Skeletogenic cell that has the potential to develop into a chondroblast; and arises from neural crest, meseosdermal and notochordal and connective tissue cells.

name: striated muscle tissue of prostate
description: A portion of striated muscle tissue that is part of a prostate gland [Automatically generated definition].

name: pseudoclasper
description: one or more pairs of stiff ossified lobes or prongs found in the tip of the intromittent organ of Bythitoidei

name: cardinal vein
description: Any of the four veins in the developing vertebrate embryo which run along each side of the vertebral column

name: muscle of leg
description: A muscle that is part of the region of the hindlimb between the pelvis and ankle.

name: distal phalanx of digit 5
description: A distal phalanx that is part of a digit 5 [Automatically generated definition].

name: pedal digit 4 plus metapodial segment
description: A subdivision of the autopod consisting of pedal digit 4 plus the region incorporating a single metapodial element. These segments are typically repeated along the pre-axiom to post-axial axis.

name: pedal digit 4
description: 4th digit of the hind autopod.

name: nictitans gland
description: A gland producing tears in a third eyelid in the corner of each eye.

name: lingual artery
description: The lingual artery arises from the external carotid between the superior thyroid and facial artery[WP].

name: procurrent spur
description: A ventrally projecting spur on the posteriormost ventral procurrent caudal ray overlapping ventrally the preceding ray in various percomorphs (Johnson, 1975).

name: urethra smooth muscle layer
description: A portion of smooth muscle tissue that is part of a urethra [Automatically generated definition].

name: skeletal system
description: Anatomical system that is a multi-element, multi-tissue anatomical cluster that consists of the skeleton and the articular system.

name: subdivision of spinal cord central canal
description: A subdivision of the central canal of the spinal cord along its anterior-posterior axis. This is typically subdivided into cervical, thoracic, lumbar and sacral segments

name: neck of urinary bladder
description: The constricted portion of the urinary bladder, formed by the meeting of its inferolateral surfaces proximal to the opening of the urethra[MP].

name: medial parabrachial nucleus
description: The Medial parabrachial nucleus is a nucleus of the pons which constitutes part of the pneumotaxic center. It gets its name from its location relative to the superior cerebellar peduncles, which is also known as the 'brachia conjunctiva'. [WP,unvetted].

name: flexural organ
description: A portion of tissue that is the most anterior portion of the notochord. The flexural organ secretes Reissner's fiber-related proteins, including F-spondin.

name: palato-maxillary ligament
description: Ligament between the palatine and maxilla. [Stiassny 1986]

name: dentary tooth row
description: Tooth row that is on the dentary.

name: dermal neck joint
description: Dermal articulation between skull and shoulder girdle localized to paired dermal neck-joint between anterior dorsolateral plate (ADL) and paranuchal (PNu) plates in placoderms.

name: feather bud, epidermal component
description: An epithelial bud that is part of a feather bud.

name: internal iliac artery
description: The internal iliac artery (formerly known as the hypogastric artery) is the main artery of the pelvis. [WP,unvetted].

name: obsolete anal fin skeleton
description: Median fin skeleton that is located posterior to the anus.

name: premaxillary-maxillary ligament
description: Ligament that connects the premaxilla to the maxilla.

name: spiracle (sensu Vertebrata)
description: A small hole behind each eye that opens to the mouth in some fish. In the primitive jawless fish the first gill opening immediately behind the mouth is essentially similar to the other gill openings.

name: spiracle
description: Opening of the tracheal system on the surface of the body.

name: radius cartilage element
description: A cartilaginous condensation that has the potential to develop into a radius bone.

name: right adrenal gland medulla
description: the adrenal gland medulla that is in the right side of the abdomen

name: beak
description: The avian beak is an external anatomical structure, in the head region, that is adapted for feeding self and young, catching prey, probing, etc. It encompasses, but is not restricted to, the maxilla, mandible, maxillary ramaphotheca, mandibular ramaphotheca, nostril, nasal fossa, nasal bones, egg tooth and rictus[GO]. The beak, bill or rostrum is an external anatomical structure of birds which is used for eating and for grooming, manipulating objects, killing prey, probing for food, courtship and feeding young. .

name: monotreme bill
description: An elongated snout found in monotremes.

name: mucosa of ejaculatory duct
description: A mucosa that is part of a ejaculatory duct [Automatically generated definition].

name: endometrial blood vessel
description: A blood vessel that is part of a endometrium.

name: wing disc
description: Dorsal imaginal disc of the mesothorax. Precursor of dorsal mesothoracic structures of the adult including the postnotum, scutum, scutellum, wing, wing hinge and part of the notal pleura.

name: distal early tubule
description: Portion of the renal tubule which is just posterior to the proximal straight tubule.

name: telencephalon pia mater
description: A pia mater that is part of a telencephalon [Automatically generated definition].

name: obsolete predominantly white regional part of anterior commissure
colon endothelium
description: Vascular endothelium found in colon blood vessels.

name: dorsal nasal meatus
description: The dosal nasal meatus is a narrow passage bounded dorsally by the roof of the nasal cavity and ventrally by the dorsal concha. It terminates caudally at the junction of the inner plate of the frontal bone with the cribiform plate and lateral mass of the ethmoid bone. It is the shortest and shallowest of the three meatuses.

name: lower respiratory tract cartilage
description: A cartilage that is part of a lower respiratory tract [Automatically generated definition].

name: manual digit 5 metacarpus endochondral element
description: A manual digit 5 metacarpus bone or its cartilage or pre-cartilage precursor.

name: manual minor digit (Aves)
description: A manual digit found in Aves that is morphologically similar to digit 3 in the standard tetrapod configuration and develops from embryonic digit 4.

name: abdominal fat pad
description: The encapsulated adipose tissue in the abdomen.

name: suspensory ligament of duodenum
description: A thin muscle connecting the junction between the duodenum, jejunum, and duodenojejunal flexure to connective tissue surrounding the superior mesenteric artery and coeliac artery

name: lumen of parabronchus
description: An anatomical cavity that is part of a parabronchus.

name: obsolete animal blastomere
description: Pigmented, smaller blastomere of the animal (upper) hemisphere of the cleaving embryo.

name: obsolete regeneration fibroblast
description: Is a fibroblast that differentiates from the de-differentiated cells of the blastema.

name: basibranchial element
description: Endochondral element that is ventral, median, and associated with a single pharyngeal arch in the pharyngeal arch 3-7 skeleton.

name: immaterial anatomical entity
description: Anatomical entity that has no mass.

name: ureteral valve
description: A valve that is part of a ureter.

name: cycloid scale
description: Scale that is smooth-edged, round or oval and composed of acellular dermal bone lacking small spines on the posterior exposed edge. (from http://www.briancoad.com/Dictionary/introduction.htm).

name: anterior maxillary process
description: Process that extends anteriorly from the planum triangulare and invests the medial face of the pars facialis of the maxilla.

name: wall of right ventricle
description: Wall of ventricle which is continuous with the wall of pulmonary trunk.

name: lateral nasal process surface ectoderm
description: An ectoderm that is part of a lateral nasal prominence.

name: rectus capitis posterior minor
description: A muscle that arise from the tubercle on the posterior arch of the and is inserted into the medial part of the inferior nuchal line of the occipital bone and the surface between it and the foramen magnum, and also takes some attachment to the spinal dura.

name: pectoral fin proximal radial element 3
description: Pectoral fin proximal radial element that is the third most anterior or dorsal pectoral fin radial element.

name: greater omentum mesothelium
description: A mesothelium that is part of a greater omentum.

name: obsolete spirocyst
description: A cnida that is adhesive and lasso-like in structure and is capable of being projected at and wrapping around prey.

name: lower primary canine tooth
description: A primary canine tooth that is part of a lower jaw region.

name: neural tube mantle layer
description: The layer of glia and differentiating neurons that forms as a second layer around the germinal neuroepithium; as this develops it comes to lie between the ventricular and marginal layers and includes the basal and alar plates. Develops into neurons and glia forming a gray matter layer.

name: pronephric mesoderm
description: A mesoderm that has the potential to develop into a pronephros.

name: flexor digitorum brevis muscle
description: The flexor digitorum brevis lies in the middle of the sole of the foot, immediately above the central part of the plantar aponeurosis, with which it is firmly united. Its deep surface is separated from the lateral plantar vessels and nerves by a thin layer of fascia.

name: ventral corticospinal tract
description: Part of pyramidal tract (corticospinal tract) containing uncrossed fibers and traveling in the ventral funiculus of the spinal cord.

name: obsolete regional part of vestibular nuclear complex
description: A regional part of brain that is part of a vestibular nuclear complex [Automatically generated definition].

name: tail of pancreas
description: The tail of the pancreas, located anatomically left near the hilum of the spleen, is not simply an anatomical distinction. The tail is the only part of the pancreas which contains Pancreatic Polypeptide (PP) cells, which are responsible for secreting pancreatic polypeptide to coordinate exocrine and islet enzyme release. PP cells are found in the tail's periphery. Beta cells and delta cells are found in the central part of the tail as with the rest of the pancreas. The cells described above are located exclusively in the islet cells; their secretions reach exocrine portions of the pancreas via the capillary network surrounding the islet cell populations. [WP,unvetted].

name: surface of bone
description: An anatomical surface that is part of a bone

name: left frontal lobe
description: A frontal cortex that is part of a left cerebral hemisphere.

name: heterocercal tail
description: Type of tail (caudal) fin in which the vertebral column turns upwards into the upper lobe which is longer than the lower. Asymmetrical externally as well as internally.

name: embryonic segment
description: Any segment that is part of some embryo.

name: cuticle
description: tough but flexible, non-mineral outer coverings of an organism, or parts of an organism, that provide protection. Cuticles are non-homologous, differing in their origin, structure and chemical composition[WP].

name: obsolete regional part of midbrain tegmentum
description: A multi-tissue structure that is part of a midbrain tegmentum.

name: anterior lamina recurvata
description: Portion of the anterior ramus of the cleithrum that invest the anterior margin of the suprascapula, extending onto its dorsal surface.

name: ureteropelvic junction
description: The junction between the ureter and the renal pelvis of the kidney

name: inferior palpebral vein
description: A blood vessel that drains from from an lower eyelid.

name: processus posterodorsalis of lamella alaris
description: Posterior process of the lamella alaris.

name: pyloric sphincter
description: A strong ring of smooth muscle at the end of the pyloric canal which lets food pass from the stomach to the duodenum. It receives sympathetic innervation from the celiac ganglion[WP].

name: obsolete motor nerve
description: A motor nerve is an efferent nerve that exclusively contains the axons of somatic and branchial motoneurons, which innervate skeletal muscles (that ensure locomotion) and branchial muscles (that motorize the face and neck)[WP].

name: nerve foramen
description: Opening and/or passageway for nerve(s) in bone.

name: ramulus suprabranchialis posterior
description: Ramulus innervating the suprabranchial line of neuromasts.

name: digit 7
description: A digit that is part of a digit 7 plus metapodial segment.

name: pharyngeal raphe
description: The Pharyngeal raphe is a raphe that serves as the origin and insertion for several of the pharyngeal constrictors.

name: caudal principal ray 8
description: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 7.

name: pleurapophysis
description: Paired processes that represent the rib attachments to the vertebra plus the ribs.

name: prostate field
description: A specific region of the urogenital sinus epithelium into the area in which the prostate gland will develop.

name: obsolete hemispheric parts of the cerebellar cortex
postorbital bone
description: The postorbital is one of the bones in vertebrate skulls which forms a portion of the dermal skull roof and, sometimes, a ring about the orbit.
