description: The bulb region adjacent to the dermal papilla that contains rapidly proliferating matrix cells that give rise to the various cell lineages of the hair shaft and inner root sheath

name: pelvic appendage muscle
description: Any muscle organ that is part of a pelvic appendage (hindlimb or pelvic fin).

name: obsolete predominantly gray regional part of medial geniculate body
posterior part of anterior commissure
description: The major forebrain commissure that connects the two temporal lobes of the cortex.

name: adult mammalian kidney
description: A kidney at the most advanced stage of development in a mammal.

name: oral pontine reticular nucleus
description: The oral pontine reticular nucleus is delineated from its caudal brother, with which it shares its first three names. This nucleus tapers into the lower mesencephalic reticular formation and contains sporadic giant cells. Different populations of the pontis oralis have displayed discharge patterns which coordinate with phasic movements to and from paradoxical sleep. From this information it has been implied that the n.r. pontis oralis is involved in the mediation of changing to and from REM sleep. [WP,unvetted].

name: alveolar process of maxilla
description: The thickened ridge of bone that contains the tooth sockets on the maxilla.

name: epiglottic cartilage
description: The most superior of the laryngeal cartilages, which is found at the root of the tongue and folds back over the entrance to the larynx during swallowing.

name: cricothyroid muscle
description: Intrinsic muscle of the larynx, innervated by the external division of the laryngeal nerve, a branch of the vagus nerve. It attaches to the anterolateral surface of the cricoid cartilage and the external surface of the thyroid cartilage.

name: obsolete predominantly gray part of solitary nucleus
genital papilla of vulva
description: The genital papilla is a part of female external genitalia not present in humans, which appears as a small, fleshy flab of tissue. The papilla covers the opening of the vagina.

name: mental artery
description: The mental branch of inferior alveolar artery escapes with the nerve at the mental foramen, supplies the chin, and anastomoses with the submental and inferior labial arteries. [WP,unvetted].

name: lingula of left lung
description: Anterioinferior portion of left upper lung lobe

name: obsolete regional part of stratum radiatum
space in vertebral column
description: Any anatomical space that is part of a vertebral column.

name: vibrissa hair bulb
description: A bulb of hair follicle that is part of a vibrissa unit.

name: posterior dentation of dorsal fin spine 2
description: Process that is tooth or thorn-like and arising from the posteriorly-facing margin of the abducted dorsal-fin spine 2.

name: obsolete early digestive tract associated mesenchyme
ceratobranchial 4 bone proximal cartilage
description: Pharyngeal cartilage that is part of and at the proximal end of ceratobranchial 4 bone, and that usually articulates with basibranchial 4 element. Ceratobranchial 4 proximal cartilage is paired.

name: gubernacular cord
description: The cranial, thin portion of the gubernaculum.

name: intermuscular bone
description: Axial bone which is a segmental ossification that forms in the myoseptum.

name: dorsal tegmental nucleus pars dorsalis
description: Part of dorsal tegmental nucleus characterized by round, small cells that are lightly stained in Nissl preparations.

name: pelvic spur
description: Pelvic spurs are the externally visible portion of the vestigial remnants of legs found on each side of the vent in primitive snakes, such as boas and pythons. The remnants of a pelvis and femur, which have no connection with the spine, simply 'float' in the muscle mass. The femur protrudes from the snake's body and is covered by a corneal spur, which resembles a claw. Males' spurs are generally longer and more pointed than females', and are used for clasping and tickling during courtship and mating, as well as combat with other males in some species

name: anterior root of zygomatic arch
description: The anterior or rostral end of the zygomatic arch, which includes the temporal process of the zygomatic bone, but also including some of the body of the zygomatic bone. It may also include the zygomatico-temporal suture and the most rostral portion of the zygomatic process of the temporal bone.

name: proper hepatic artery
description: The hepatic artery proper (also proper hepatic artery), arises from the common hepatic artery and runs alongside the portal vein and the common bile duct to form the portal triad. The hepatic artery proper gives off a small supraduodenal artery to the duodenal bulb. Then the right gastric artery comes off and runs to the left along the lesser curvature of the stomach to meet the left gastric artery, which is a branch of the celiac trunk. It subsequently gives off the cystic artery, which feeds the gallbladder, before bifurcating into the right and left hepatic arteries. Of note, the right and left hepatic arteries may demonstrate variant anatomy. A replaced right hepatic artery may arise from the superior mesenteric artery (SMA) and a replaced left hepatic artery may arise from the left gastric artery.

name: adventitia of epididymis
description: An adventitia that is part of a epididymis.

name: hindlimb mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a developing hindlimb [Automatically generated definition].

name: C1 segment of cervical spinal cord
description: The segment of the spinal cord that corresponds to the first cervical vertebra in most mammals.

name: abdominal cavity
description: The part of the ventral body cavity that is within the abdomen proper (excluding the pelvic cavity).

name: Leydig cell region of testis
description: The male gonad containing two functional parts: the SEMINIFEROUS TUBULES for the production and transport of male germ cells (SPERMATOGENESIS) and the interstitial compartment containing LEYDIG CELLS that produce ANDROGENS..

name: cuboid facet of calcaneum
description: Facet on the anterior surface of the calcaneus (as called calcaneum) for the articulation of the cuboid bone

name: mucosa of main bronchus
description: A mucosa that is part of a main bronchus [Automatically generated definition].

name: iliocostalis muscle
description: The iliocostalis is the muscle immediately lateral to the longissimus that is the nearest to the furrow that separates the epaxial muscles from the hypaxial. It lies very deep to the fleshy portion of the serratus ventralis (serratus anterior). [WP,unvetted].

name: choroid plexus epithelium
description: The epithelial component of the choroid plexus. Consists of cuboidal epithelial cells surrounding a core of capillaries and loose connective tissue.

name: viscus
description: An organ that is located within the body cavity (or in its extension, in the scrotum); it consists of organ parts that are embryologically derived from endoderm, splanchnic mesoderm or intermediate mesoderm; together with other organs, the viscus constitutes the respiratory, gastrointestinal, urinary, reproductive and immune systems, or is the central organ of the cardiovascular system. Examples: heart, lung, esophagus, kidney, ovary, spleen.

name: gracilis
description: The most superficial muscle on the medial side of the thigh. It is thin and flattened, broad above, narrow and tapering below. It arises by a thin aponeurosis from the anterior margins of the lower half of the symphysis pubis and the upper half of the pubic arch.

name: somite boundary epithelium
description: Epithelium located in the intersomitic region.

name: hindbrain arachnoid mater
description: An arachnoid mater that is part of a hindbrain [Automatically generated definition].

name: myocardium of atrium
description: the atrial part of middle layer of the heart, comprised of involuntary muscle

name: dorsal fin distal radial bone 7
description: dorsal fin distal radial 7 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: muscle of Aristotle's lantern
description: Any muscle organ that is part of a Aristotle's lantern.

name: solitary tract nuclear complex
description: The solitary tract and nucleus are structures in the brainstem that carry and receive visceral sensation and taste from the facial (VII), glossopharyngeal (IX) and vagus (X) cranial nerves. [WP,unvetted].

name: nasopremaxilla
description: A compound bone consisting of premaxilla, nasal and sometimes septomaxilla in adult members of Caeciliidae and Typhlonectidae.

name: obsolete regional part of spinal nerve
dorsal scute
description: Scute that is a bony plate that forms in dorsal midline of body margin between the skull and dorsal fin.

name: equine hindlimb splint bone
description: A splint bone in the metatarsal region

name: flexor pollicis brevis muscle
description: The flexor pollicis brevis is a muscle in the hand that flexes the thumb. It is one of three thenar muscles. It has both a superficial part and a deep part.

name: ventral abdominal vein
description: A vein formed by the combination of veins in the pelvic region which collects blood from the liver, stomach, intestines, and gall bladder.

name: rhamphotheca
description: thin keratinized layer of epidermis projecting from outer surface of beak[WP].

name: naris epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a naris [Automatically generated definition].

name: inferior epigastric vein
description: The blood vessel carrying deoxygenated blood that arises from the superior epigastric vein and empties into the external iliac vein.

name: pharyngeal arch system
description: A transient embryonic complex that comprises the pharyngeal arches, bulges of tissues of mesoderm and neural crest derivation through which pass nerves and pharyngeal arch arteries. The arches are separated internally by pharyngeal pouches, evaginations of foregut endoderm, and externally by pharyngeal clefts, invaginations of surface ectoderm. The development of the system ends when the stucture it contributes to are forming, which may include (depending on species) the thymus, thyroid, parathyroids, maxilla, mandible, aortic arch, cardiac outflow tract, external and middle ear[GO,modified].

name: loop of Henle ascending limb thin segment
description: A sub-portion of the loop of Henle in the nephron of the kidney that is permeable to ions but not to water

name: sacral spinal cord ventral column
description: A subdivision of spinal cord ventral column that is part of a sacral spinal cord.

name: mineralized avascular GAG-rich matrix
description: Avascular GAG-rich matrix that is mineralized.

name: caecum mesentery
description: A mesentery that is part of a caecum.

name: proximal epiphysis of phalanx of manual digit 4
description: A proximal epiphysis that is part of a manual digit 4 phalanx [Automatically generated definition].

name: duct of male reproductive system
description: Any of the ducts that are part of a male reproductive system.

name: medial nasal prominence
description: The central area of the two limbs of a horseshoe-shaped mesenchymal swelling that lie medial to the olfactory placode or pit in the future nasal region of the embryo; it joins with the ipsilateral maxillary prominence in the formation of half of the upper jaw, and the nasal tip and philtrum of the upper lip develop from it

name: bile canaliculus
description: An intercellular channel that takes up bile from hepatocytes, transporting it to the bile ducts.

name: lingual gyrus
description: Component of the occipital lobe. The rostral boundary of the lingual gyrus was the posterior extent of the parahippocampal gyrus whereas the caudal boundary was the most posterior coronal slice where the gyrus could be visualized. The medial and lateral boundaries were the medial portion of the temporal and occipital cortices and the medial bank of the collateral sulcus respectively (Christine Fennema-Notestine).

name: mesenchyme derived from neural crest
description: Mesenchyme that develops_from the neural crest[Automatically generated definition].

name: forelimb wing bud
description: A wing bud that develops into a wing

name: skin of knee
description: A zone of skin that is part of a knee [Automatically generated definition].

name: cervical spinal cord white matter
description: A white matter of spinal cord that is part of a cervical spinal cord.

name: endoderm-derived structure
description: An anatomical structure that develops (entirely or partially) from the endoderm.

name: female urethra
description: A urethra that is part of a female reproductive system.

name: superior pubic ramus
description: The superior pubic ramus is a part of the pubic bone which forms a portion of the obturator foramen. It extends from the body to the median plane where it articulates with its fellow of the opposite side. It is conveniently described in two portions, viz. , a medial flattened part and a narrow lateral prismoid portion.

name: diapophysis of neural arch
description: Paired processes that arise near the midpoint of the neural arch lamina, for the attachment of the tuberculum of two-headed ribs. Also called transverse processes. In anurans, the term diapophysis is used in reference to the modified transverse processes of the sacral vertebra elaborated for support of the pelvic girdle.

name: descending colon
description: The portion of the colon between the left colic flexure and the sigmoid colon at the pelvic brim; the portion of the descending colon lying in the left iliac fossa is sometimes called the iliac colon.

name: obsolete regional part of temporal lobe
posterolateral fissure of cerebellum
description: Fissure between cerebellar lobules IX and X.

name: caudal vertebra 1
description: Caudal vertebra that is the anteriormost element of the series.

name: postcleithrum 1
description: Postcleithrum that anteriorly articulates with the supracleithrum and/or the cleithrum of the pectoral girdle; most dorsal element in a series of postcleithra.

name: crista radii
description: Small ridge on the lateral aspect of the radial shaft, located at the level of the collum antibrachii.

name: condyle
description: An articular prominence of a bone, typically present in pairs, resembling a pair of knuckles. Examples: Condyle of humerus, condyle of femur.

name: mesethmoid-premaxillary joint
description: Joint that articulates the mesethmoid and premaxilla. Mesethmoid-premaxillary joint is paired.

name: serosa of large intestine
description: A serous membrane that is part of a large intestine [Automatically generated definition].

name: pubococcygeus muscle
description: The pubococcygeus muscle or PC muscle is a hammock-like muscle, found in both sexes, that stretches from the pubic bone to the coccyx (tail bone) forming the floor of the pelvic cavity and supporting the pelvic organs. It is part of the levator ani group of muscles.

name: coccygeus muscle
description: The Coccygeus is a muscle of the pelvic wall (i.e. peripheral to the pelvic floor), situated behind the levator ani and in front of the sacrospinous ligament. It is a triangular plane of muscular and tendinous fibers, arising by its apex from the spine of the ischium and sacrospinous ligament, and inserted by its base into the margin of the coccyx and into the side of the lowest piece of the sacrum. It assists the Levator ani and Piriformis in closing in the back part of the outlet of the pelvis. [WP,unvetted].

name: ascitic fluid
description: The serous fluid which accumulates in the peritoneal cavity in ascites.

name: caudal principal ray 15
description: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 14.

name: pelvic fin middle radial element
description: Pelvic fin radial element in the middle of the pelvic fin.

name: dense regular connective tissue
description: Connective tissue that is dominated by collagen fibres organized into a definitive pattern (e.g., parallel to one another), with comparatively fewer cells (mostly fibroblasts).

name: spiral prominence of cochlear duct
description: a projecting portion of the spiral ligament of the cochlea, bounding the lower edge of the stria vascularis and containing within it a blood vessel, the vas prominens.

name: hilum
description: An anatomical cavity, depression or pit where structures are attached.

name: trabecula carnea cardiac muscle tissue
description: A portion of cardiac muscle tissue that is part of a trabecula carnea [Automatically generated definition].

name: line connecting laterally paired nipples
description: Line across midline connecting a left and right nipples.

name: obsolete skeleton of embryo
description: A skeletal system that is part of a embryo [Automatically generated definition].

name: solid compound organ
description: Compound organ that does not contain macroscopic anatomical spaces.

name: submucosa of pyloric antrum
description: A submucosa that is part of a pyloric antrum [Automatically generated definition].

name: Hadjikhani et al. (1998) visuotopic area V3A
larval segment
description: Any segment that is part of some larva.

name: serosa of esophagus
description: A serous membrane that is part of a esophagus [Automatically generated definition].

name: leg blood vessel
description: A blood vessel that is part of a leg [Automatically generated definition].

name: vitreous chamber of eyeball
description: The chamber in the eyeball enclosing the vitreous humor, bounded anteriorly by the lens and ciliary body and posteriorly by the posterior wall of the eyeball[BTO,modified].

name: mesenchyme of forearm
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a developing lower arm [Automatically generated definition].

name: buccal nerve
description: The buccal nerve (also called the long buccal nerve) is a nerve in the face. It is a branch of the mandibular nerve (which is itself a branch of the trigeminal nerve) and transmits sensory information from skin over the buccal membrane (in general, the cheek) and from the second and third molar teeth.

name: propatagium
description: In bats and pterosaurs, thin web of skin that extends from the shoulder to the wrist anterior to the upper arm and forearm, and is fixed on the neck or skull.

name: flexor muscle
description: a skeletal muscle whose contraction bends a joint.

name: climbing fiber
description: Portion of tissue that consists of afferent axons from the inferior olive and synapsing with Purkinje cells within the molecular layer of the valvula cerebelli and corpus cerebelli.

name: pedal digit phalanx cartilage element
description: A cartilage element that is part of a pedal digit mesenchyme.

name: obsolete regional part of limbic lobe
subdivision of skeleton
description: Anatomical cluster consisting of the skeletal elements (i.e. bone elements, cartilage elements, cartilage condensations) that are part of an individual subdivision of the organism. Excludes joints.

name: outer layer of endometrium
description: The layer of endometrial epithelium adjacent to the myometrium.

name: dermal annular fold
description: A dermal fold surrounding the body reflecting body segmentation. Found in Caecilians.

name: viscerocranial mucosa
description: Nonparenchymatous organ which consists of mucosae of the nose, mouth, pharyngotympanic tube, pharynx and larynx. Examples: There is only one viscerocranial mucosa.

name: epicardium
description: a region of the serous membrane that forms the innermost layer of the pericardium and the outer surface of the heart.

name: rhombomere 2 floor plate
description: A rhombomere floor plate that is part of a rhombomere 2.

name: anteroventral lateral line nerve (AVLLN)
description: Sensory nerve of the anterior lateral line component. It develops from preotic anteroventral placode. AVLLN innervates lower jaw lines of neuromasts.

name: heart vasculature
description: An interconnected tubular multi-tissue structure that contains fluid that is actively transported around the heart.

name: cortical layer V
description: Layer of neocortex lying deep to the internal granule cell layer (layer 4) defined cytoarchitecturally by the predominance of large pyramidal cell bodies

name: pars plana of ciliary body
description: Flattened posterior region of ciliary body

name: decidua parietalis
description: The part of the decidua in the pregnant human female lining the uterus.

name: rhomboid
description: A rhombus-shaped muscle associated with the scapula and chiefly responsible for its retraction. There are two rhomboid muscles.

name: piriform cortex layer 2
description: Middle of three cytoarchitecturally defined layers of the piriform cortex characterized by a compact layer of cell bodies. It can be divided into a superficial part and a more densely packed deep part

name: segment of pes
description: A segment of autopod that is part of a pes.

name: medial longitudinal fasciculus of midbrain
description: A medial longitudinal fasciculus that is part of a midbrain [Automatically generated definition].

name: ventral wall of dorsal aorta
description: Region where blood progenitor markers are expressed. Probable site of definitive hematopoiesis between 36hpf and 4dpf.

name: dense regular elastic tissue
description: Regular connective tissue, which consists of fibroblasts and of intercellular matrix, which contains elastic fiber bundles oriented predominantly in definable directions.

name: muscle layer of urinary bladder
description: A muscular coat that is part of a urinary bladder.

name: renal cortex vein
description: Artery that receives blood from the renal cortex[MP, modified]

name: bone marrow cavity
description: the medullary cavities of the bones where bone marrow is stored

name: golgi tendon organ
description: The sensory organ in muscle that is involved in regulating muscle tension

name: glandular columnar epithelium
description: Simple columnar epithelium that constitutes the secretory part of a gland. Examples: epithelium of stomach, luminal epithelium of lactiferous duct.[FMA]

name: hypopharynx
description: Bottom part of the pharynx that connects to the esophagus.

name: tibial facet of astragalus
description: Facet for the articulation of the tibia on the astragalus (talus).

name: peripheral lymph node
description: The lymph nodes located outside the thoracic and abdominal cavities, such as the submandibular, prescapular, axillary, inguinal and popliteal lymph nodes

name: transverse process of atlas
description: A transverse process of vertebra that is part of a vertebral bone 1.

name: gill
description: Anatomical surface structure found in many aquatic organisms. It is a respiration organ whose function is the extraction of oxygen from water and the excretion of carbon dioxide. The microscopic structure of a gill is such that it presents a very large surface area to the external environment. Gills usually consist of thin filaments of tissue, branches, or slender tufted processes which have a highly folded surface to increase surface area. A high surface area is crucial to the gas exchange of aquatic organisms as water contains only 1/20 parts dissolved Oxygen compared to air. With the exception of some aquatic insects, the filaments and lamellae (folds) contain blood or coelomic fluid, from which gases are exchanged through the thin walls. Oxygen is carried by the blood to other parts of the body. Carbon dioxide passes from the blood through the thin gill tissue into the water. Gills or gill-like organs, located in different parts of the body, are found in various groups of aquatic animals, including mollusks, crustaceans, insects, fish, and amphibians.

name: fibrous pericardium
description: Membrane organ which is attached to the pericardial sac proper and the central tendon of diaphragm and is continuous with the pretracheal fascia.[FMA]

name: cartilage of main bronchus
description: A cartilage that is part of a main bronchus [Automatically generated definition].

name: parapophysis 2
description: Parapophysis that is lateral projection from the second centrum, absent in Siluriformes (Fink and Fink, 1996).

name: obsolete postbranchial lamina
description: Medial facing projection or surface on the anterior ( cranial) region of the cleithrum that is often textured or denticled. This process has two primary functions: 1) its shape enhances the vertical strength of the cleithrum and 2) it forms the edge of the gill chamber and helps to direct water after it has passed over the gills (modified from Clack 2012).

name: obsolete superficial feature part of medulla oblongata
m. serratus inferior
description: Muscle which originates as a posterior and anterior head. The posterior head originates from the transverse process and cartilaginous epiphysis of presacral vertebra IV. The anterior head originates on the same parts of presacral vertebrae III. Both insert on the medial surface of the suprascapula near its postero-ventral edge.

name: infra-orbital canal of maxilla
description: A canal through the maxilla that is connects the infra-orbital groove and foramen and is the conduit for the passage of the infraorbital nerve and artery.

name: caudal vein
description: Vein in the tail returning blood from the trunk and tail to the heart, leads directly into the posterial cardinal vein in the posterior trunk. Kimmel et al, 1995.[ZFIN]

name: lagenar capsule
description: Anatomical cluster that consists of a bulla formed by the exoccipital and basioccipital bones, and surrounds the lagena.

name: tail fold of embryonic disc
description: The crescent-shaped, ventrally located fold of the embryonic disc at the future caudal end of the developing embryo

name: urogenital diaphragm
description: muscular components of the deep perineal pouch.

name: banks of superior temporal sulcus
description: Component of the temporal lobe, lateral aspect. The rostral boundary is the superior temporal gyrus and the caudal boundary the middle temporal gyrus. Within the FreeSurfer definition, this reflects primarily the posterior aspect of the superior temporal sulcus (Christine Fennema-Notestine).

name: extensor digiti minimi muscle
description: The extensor minimi digiti (extensor digiti quinti proprius) is a slender muscle of the forearm, placed on the ulnar side of the Extensor digitorum communis, with which it is generally connected. It arises from the common Extensor tendon by a thin tendinous slip, from the intermuscular septa between it and the adjacent muscles. Its tendon runs through a compartment of the dorsal carpal ligament behind the distal radio-ulnar joint, then divides into two as it crosses the manus, and finally joins the expansion of the Extensor digitorum communis tendon on the dorsum of the first phalanx of the little finger[WP].

name: dorsal fin lepidotrichium
description: Lepidotrichium that is part of the dorsal fin skeleton.

name: basioccipital bone
description: One of the bones of the occiput, the part of the skull which articulates with the spine. The basioccipital is located (if present) ventral to the foramen magnum. It often rests on or articulates with the basisphenoid, as well as meeting the exoccipitals. The basioccipital usually forms most (sometimes all) of the occipital condyle(s) and the ventral margin of the foramen magnum.

name: muscularis mucosa of fundus of urinary bladder
description: A muscularis mucosa that is part of a fundus of urinary bladder.

name: hair follicle isthmus
description: The middle part of the hair follicle that extends from the sebaceous duct to the bulge

name: metanephric mesenchyme
description: one of the two embryological structures that give rise to the kidney (the other is the ureteric bud). The metanephric blastema mostly develops into nephrons, but can also form parts of the collecting duct system.[WP]. Metanephric mesenchyme is the tissue made up of loosely connected mesenchymal cells in the metanephros[GO]

name: common tendinous ring
description: A ring of fibrous tissue surrounding the optic nerve at its entrance at the apex of the orbit.

name: uncinate fasciculus
description: Pathway arising from the fastigial nucleus to the vestibular nuclei, reticular formation, motor neurons of brainstem and cervical spinal cord (Butler and Hodos, Comparative Vertebrate Neuroanatomy, 2nd ed., 2005, pg 261).

name: bone fossa
description: A depression or hollow in a bone[WP].

name: mesonephric tubule
description: A mesonephric tubule is an epithelial tube that is part of the mesonephros[GO]. Genital ridge that is next to the mesonephros[WP].

name: alveolar ridge of mandible
description: The thickened ridge of bone that contains the tooth sockets on the mandible.

name: ligament of larynx
description: A ligament that is part of a larynx and connexts the cartilages of the larynx

name: vastus intermedius
description: The Vastus intermedius (Cruraeus) arises from the front and lateral surfaces of the body of the femur in its upper two-thirds, sitting under Rectus Femoris and from the lower part of the lateral intermuscular septum. Its fibers end in a superficial aponeurosis, which forms the deep part of the Quadriceps femoris tendon. The Vastus medialis and Vastus intermedius appear to be inseparably united, but when the Rectus femoris has been reflected a narrow interval will be observed extending upward from the medial border of the patella between the two muscles, and the separation may be continued as far as the lower part of the intertrochanteric line, where, however, the two muscles are frequently continuous.

name: cheek
description: A fleshy subdivision of one side of the face bounded by an eye, ear and the nose.

name: breast
description: The upper ventral region of the torso of an organism.

name: subthalamic fasciculus
description: The subthalamic fasciculus is a tract which connects the subthalamic nucleus and the globus pallidus. It is a bidirectional connection between the GP and the subthalamic nucleus, including (1) fibers running from the GPe to the subthalamic nucleus, and (2) fibers running from the STN back to the GP.

name: buccal artery
description: The buccal artery (buccinator artery) is small and runs obliquely forward, between the Pterygoideus internus and the insertion of the Temporalis, to the outer surface of the Buccinator, to which it is distributed, anastomosing with branches of the external maxillary and with the infraorbital. [WP,unvetted].

name: mesocardium
description: The part of the embryonic mesentery which connects the embryonic heart with the body wall in front and the foregut behind.

name: nasociliary nerve
description: A branch of the ophthalmic nerve that serves to supply the mucous membrane of the nose, the tip of the nose, and the conjunctiva.

name: vibrissa root sheath
description: A hair root sheath that is part of a vibrissa unit.

name: branchiostegal ray
description: Dermal bone that is a flattened element that supports the branchiostegal membrane. Branchiostegal rays are generally present in a series articulating ventrally or ventro-medially with the anterior and posterior ceratobranchials whereas the most posterior ray articulates with the subopercle. The branchiostegal ray is paired.

name: anterior dentation of dorsal fin spine 2
description: Process that is tooth- or thorn-like and arising from the anteriorly-facing margin of the abducted dorsal-fin spine 2.

name: chemoreceptor
description: A sensory receptor that detects chemical stimulus within the body.

name: submucosa
description: A layer of dense irregular connective tissue that lines organs and supports the mucosa, as well as joins the mucosa to the bulk of underlying smooth muscle. [WP,unvetted].

name: long bone epiphyseal plate proliferative zone
description: germinal layer of the epiphyseal plate where cells are actively dividing as well as producing extracellular matrix[MP].

name: limb bud mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a limb bud.

name: presumptive endoderm
description: Presumptive structure of the blastula that will develop into endoderm.

name: pharyngobranchial bone
description: Endochondral bone of the branchial arches located medial to the epibranchials.

name: multi cell part structure
description: A structure consisting of multiple cell components but which is not itself a cell and does not have (complete) cells as a part.

name: proximal epiphysis of ulna
description: The head of ulna presents an articular surface, part of which, of an oval or semilunar form, is directed downward, and articulates with the upper surface of the triangular articular disk which separates it from the wrist-joint; the remaining portion, directed lateralward, is narrow, convex, and received into the ulnar notch of the radius.

name: third phalanx
description: The third phalangeal bone in a digit ray.

name: left hepatic artery
description: A hepatic artery that is part of a left lobe of liver.

name: muscle layer of epididymis
description: A muscle layer that is part of a epididymis.

name: neural arch
description: posterior part of a vertebra that consists of a pair of pedicles and a pair of laminae, and supports seven processes: four articular processes, two transverse processes one spinous process[WP]. ZFA: A neural arch encloses the neural canal and typically meets its partner to form a neural spine. .

name: cranial suture
description: Fibrous joint in which the articulating bones or cartilages of the skull are connected by sutural ligaments (scant amount of collagenous dense connective tissue). Examples: sagittal suture, frontal suture.

name: outer renal medulla interstitium
description: A portion of interstitial tissue that is part of a outer medulla of kidney [Automatically generated definition].

name: paraventricular nucleus of the hypothalamus magnocellular division - posterior magnocellular part medial zone
dorsal osteoderm
description: Osteoderm found on the dorsal surface of an organisms.

name: mucosa of lobar bronchus
description: A mucosa that is part of a lobar bronchus [Automatically generated definition].

name: splenius
description: A superficial postvertebral muscle innervated by the posterior ramus of the cervical spinal nerve with origins in the upper thoracic and lower cervical spinous processes whose actions are to extend and ipsilaterally rotate the head and neck. Examples: splenius capitis, splenius cervicis

name: chitinous tooth
description: tooth-like structure composed of chitin.

name: cuticle of hair
description: smooth and glossy outer protective cell layer of hair shaft

name: rotator muscle of the vertebral column
description: Any of a number of short transversospinal muscles chiefly developed in cervical, lumbar, and thoracic regions, arising from the transverse process of one vertebra and inserted into the root of the spinous process of the next two or three vertebrae above, with nerve supply from the dorsal branches of the spinal nerve, and whose actions rotate the vertebral column.

name: obsolete regional part of red nucleus
juxtaglomerular apparatus
description: An anatomical structure which consists of juxtaglomerular cells, extraglomerular mesangial cells and the macula densa. The juxtaglomerular apparatus lies adjacent to the glomerulus and regulates kidney function by maintaining the blood flow to the kidney and the filtration rate[GO]. a microscopic structure in the kidney, which regulates the function of each nephron. The juxtaglomerular apparatus is named for its proximity to the glomerulus: it is found between the vascular pole of the renal corpuscle and the returning distal convoluted tubule of the same nephron. This location is critical to its function in regulating renal blood flow and glomerular filtration rate. The three cellular components of the apparatus are the macula densa, extraglomerular mesangial cells, and juxtaglomerular cells (also known as granular cells)[WP].

name: processus posterior of maxilla
description: Posterior, toothless portion of the maxilla by which it usually comes in contact with the quadratojugal.

name: paraventricular nucleus of the hypothalamus magnocellular division - medial magnocellular part
hypophyseal cartilage
description: forms around the developing pituitary, and together with prechordal cartilages creates body of sphenoid bone

name: dorsal fin distal radial bone 8
description: dorsal fin distal radial 8 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: inferior olivary complex
description: largest nucleus situated in the olivary body, part of the medulla oblongata. It is closely associated with the cerebellum, but its specific function is voluntary body movements.

name: inferior olivary nucleus
description: The inferior olivary nucleus is the largest nucleus situated in the olivary body, part of the medulla oblongata.

name: dorsal nerve root of sacral spinal cord
obsolete cloacal spur
description: retained pelvic vestiges found in birds. They are generally used in courtship and are more pronounced in males than females.

name: infraclavicular lymph node
description: A lymph node located in the area below the clavicle.

name: presumptive endocardium
description: A presumptive structure that has the potential to develop into a endocardium.

name: sclerotome somite 10
description: Medial ventral region of the somite that will form vertebral cartilages. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: procerus
description: The Procerus is a small pyramidal slip of muscle deep to the superior orbital nerve, artery and vein.

name: elasmoid scale
description: Multi-tissue integumentary element composed dentine, elasmodine, and hypermineralized tissue.

name: basal zone of heart
description: The superior portion of the heart located opposite to the apical portion. It is formed mainly by the left atrium.

name: maxillary rhamphotheca
description: A rhamphotheca that is part of a upper beak.

name: developing mesenchymal structure
description: A mesenchyme-derived anatomical entity undergoing a transtion to become another structure.

name: superior epigastric vein
description: A vein that drains into the internal thoracic vein, anastomosing with the inferior epigastric vein at the level of the umbilicus and drains the anterior part of the abdominal wall and some of the diaphragm. Along its course, it is accompanied by a similarly named artery, the superior epigastric artery.

name: anterior limiting lamina of cornea
description: A transparent homogeneous acellular layer, 6 to 9 um thick, lying between the basal lamina of the outer layer of stratified epithelium and the substantia propria of the cornea; it is considered to be a basement membrane.

name: Reichert's membrane
description: An nonvascular extraembryonic basement membrane that forms on the inner surface of the trophectoderm during placenta morphogenesis and is secreted by the distal parietal endoderm; required for the maternofetal exchange of nutrients and is important for the postgastrulation development[MP]. a thick multilayered basement membrane between the parietal endoderm cells and the trophoblast cells

name: long nephron
description: Long nephrons are associated with juxtamedullary glomeruli and extend to the inner medulla

name: cervical spinal cord ventral column
description: A subdivision of spinal cord ventral column that is part of a cervical spinal cord.

name: right lung cranial lobe segmental bronchus
description: A segmental bronchus that is part of a upper lobe of right lung.

name: proximal epiphysis of phalanx of manual digit 5
description: A proximal epiphysis that is part of a manual digit 5 phalanx [Automatically generated definition].

name: isthmus
description: The fleshy throat region of a fish which extends forward from the ventral part of the chest and narrows anteriorly, and externally separating the two gill chambers; that narrowed portion of the breast which lies between the gill chambers and separates them.

name: dorsal pallium
description: Subdivision of pallium that is located dorsally.

name: oviduct smooth muscle
description: A portion of smooth muscle tissue that is part of a fallopian tube [Automatically generated definition].

name: insect labrum
description: A mouthpart of insects.

name: accessory olfactory bulb
description: The forebrain region that coordinates sensory signaling arising from the vomeronasal organ; it is located on the dorsal-posterior portion of the main olfactory bulb, and the axons that leave the accessory olfactory bulb project to targets in the amygdala and hypothalamus

name: renal column
description: A column of tissue that is histologically identical to tissue found in the renal cortex, but which is located in the medulla between the renal pyramids.

name: pectoral appendage field
description: A limb/fin field that has the potential to develop into a pectoral appendage bud mesenchyme.

name: spinothalamic tract
description: A tract that originates from neurons in the spinal central gray and projects to various somatosensory nuclei of the thalamus. It is formed in the medulla by merger of the anterior spinothalamic tract and lateral spinothalamic tract (adapted from Braininfo.org)

name: spinothalamic tract of medulla
description: Part of spinothalamic tract that is in the medulla

name: kidney collecting duct epithelium
description: The simple cuboidal epithelium lining the lumen of kidney collecting ducts.

name: obsolete hyperphalangy of manus
description:
Increase the number of phalanges per digit beyond their ancestral digital
formulas. Modified from Cooper and Dawson 2009

name: forelimb wing bud mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a forelimb wing bud.

name: vestibulospinal tract
description: A long process of a CNS neuron, that carries efferent (outgoing) action potentials from the cell body in the vestibular nucleus of the pons towards target cells in the spinal cord[GO].

name: basale commune (carpal)
description: Amalgamation of distal carpals 1 and 2.

name: circuit part of central nervous system
description: A collection of neuronal components interacting in a functional circuit. A neural circuit is bounded by the nervous sytem regions in which its participating neuronal components are contained (BB).

name: skin of leg
description: A zone of skin that is part of a leg [Automatically generated definition].

name: accessory nerve root
description: A nerve root that is part of a accessory XI nerve.

name: duct of lesser vestibular gland
description: A duct that is part of a minor vestibular gland.

name: prostatic urethra
description: the widest and most dilatable part of the male urethra canal which runs almost vertically through the prostate from its base to its apex, lying nearer its anterior than its posterior surface; this portion of the urethral canal is spindle-shaped, being wider in the middle than at either extremity, and narrowest below, where it joins the membranous portion; it is lined by transitional epithelium and contains in its posterior wall, or floor, the orifices of the prostatic utricle, ejaculatory ducts, and prostatic ducts, collectively known as the seminal colliculus (aka verumontanum)

name: inferior pubic ramus
description: The inferior pubic ramus is thin and flattened. It passes lateralward and downward from the medial end of the superior ramus; it becomes narrower as it descends and joins with the inferior ramus of the ischium below the obturator foramen.

name: sigmoid colon
description: The part of the large intestine that is closest to the rectum and anus. It forms a loop that averages about 40 cm. in length, and normally lies within the pelvis, but on account of its freedom of movement it is liable to be displaced into the abdominal cavity.

name: superior parietal sulcus
description: A superficial feature of the parietal lobe that extends from the dorsal surface of the superior parietal lobule across the margin of the parietal lobe into the precuneus (Ono-90). (NN)

name: superior parietal cortex
description: Copmonent of the parietal lobe. The rostral and caudal boundaries of the superior parietal cortex were the precentral gyrus and lateral occipital cortex respectively. The medial and lateral boundaries were the precuneus and/or cuneus cortex and the infererior parietal cortex respectively (Christine Fennema-Notestine).

name: ventral limb of posttemporal
description: Zone of bone organ that is the ventral extension of the posttemporal.

name: postcleithrum 2
description: Postcleithrum that articulates dorsally with postcleithrum 1, ventrally with postcleithrum 3, and anteriorly with cleithrum.

name: 1st arch maxillary mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a 1st arch maxillary component.

name: mesethmoid-nasal joint
description: Joint that articulates the mesethmoid and nasal. Mesethmoid-nasal joint is paired.

name: accessory olfactory bulb granule cell layer
epibranchial element
description: Skeletal element that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with ceratobranchial element.

name: caudal principal ray 16
description: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 15.

name: metatarsus
description: The first of the tarsal segments of the adult leg. It is located between the tibia and the second tarsal segment and is longer than the other tarsal segments. It has 8 longitudinal rows of bristles around the circumference.

name: lung hilus
description: A depression on the surface of the lung where the bronchus, blood vessels and nerves enter.

name: embryonic brain
description: Brain of the embryo.

name: future brain
description: The embryonic precursor of the brain.

name: left nipple
description: A nipple that is in_the_left_side_of a body proper.

name: skeleton of upper jaw
description: A subdivision of the skeleton that corresponds to the upper part of the mouth. The lower jaw skeleton includes the following elements, when present: upper jaw teeth, the maxilla and other lower jaw bones.

name: gray matter
description: A nervous system structure composed primarily of nerve cell bodies (somas). May also include dendrites and the initial unmyelinated portion of axons.

name: submucosa of pylorus
description: A submucosa that is part of a pylorus [Automatically generated definition].

name: Hadjikhani et al. (1998) visuotopic area VP
Bidder's organ
description: Anatomical structure which forms from an enlargement of the anterior portion of each gonad in all male bufonid larvae and consists of ovarian tissues.

name: epithelium of esophagus
description: the epithelial layer that lines the luminal space of the esophagus

name: respiratory system blood vessel
description: A blood vessel that is part of a respiratory system [Automatically generated definition].

name: mesenchyme of footplate
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a footplate.

name: lateral pterygoid nerve
description: A nerve that innervates the lateral pterygoid muscle.

name: dactylopatagium
description: An interdigital region that is part of a patagium.

name: manual digit phalanx cartilage element
description: A cartilage element that is part of a manual digit mesenchyme.

name: two-pass circulatory system
description: A closed circulatory system in which blood passes twice through the heart to supply the body once.

name: vertebral element
description: Skeletal element that forms around the notochord and is part of the vertebral column.

name: obsolete pronephric podocyte
description: Podocyte that is part of the pronephros.

name: distal tarsal bone 4
description: Endochondral tarsal bone articulating with centralia and metatarsal 4.

name: dorsal fin distal radial bone
description: dorsal fin distal radial element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: rhombomere 2 lateral wall
description: A rhombomere lateral wall that is part of a rhombomere 2.

name: pelvic splanchnic nerve
description: A splanchnic nerves that arises from sacral spinal nerves S2, S3, S4 to provide parasympathetic innervation to the hindgut.

name: cortical layer VI
description: Innermost layer of neocortex lying deep to the internal pyramidal cell layer defined cytoarchitecturally by cells of varying size.

name: auditory radiation
description: The acoustic radiations or auditory radiations are structures found in the brain, in the ventral cochlear pathway, a part of the auditory system. Lesions to the auditory radiations could be a cause of cortical deafness.

name: fibular crest
description: A bony projection on the lateral side of the tibia, allowing contact between the later and the fibula.

name: embryonic abdominal segment 8
description: Any abdominal segment 8 (UBERON:6000029) that is part of some embryonic abdomen (UBERON:6000171).

name: foramen rotundum
description: The foramen rotundum is a circular hole in the sphenoid bone that connects the middle cranial fossa and the pterygopalatine fossa.

name: prevertebral muscle
description: One of the muscles deep to the prevertebral fascia on the anterior surface of the cervical and superior three thoracic vertebrae, symmetrically placed on each side of the median plane, including the longus colli, longus capitis, rectus capitis anterior, and rectus capitis lateralis muscles. innervated by anterior rami of cervical spinal nerves.

name: superior frontal gyrus
description: Component of the frontal lobe, lateral aspect. The rostral boundary is the first appearance of the superior frontal sulcus whereas the caudal boundary is the midpoint of the paracentral sulcus on the "inflated" surface. The medial and lateral boundaries are the medial aspect of the frontal lobe and the superior frontal sulcus respectively (Christine Fennema-Notestine).

name: prostate duct
description: The minute canals that pass the prostatic secretions to the urethra.

name: egg cylinder
description: The transient cup-like structure of the epiblast that consists of a single layer of embryonic cells

name: rectum
description: the terminal portion of the intestinal tube, terminating with the anus

name: trochanteric shelf
description: Anatomical projection on the anterolateral region of the proximal end of the femur.

name: sternocephalicus muscle
description: The sternocephalicus is a flat muscle and its caudal border is adjacent to the ventral border of the brachiocephalicus. The lateral aspect of this muscle is crossed obliquely by the external jugular vein. It originates as a unit on the first sternebrae. The cranial portion of the muscle divides into two separate sections with different insertion points. These are the sternomastoideus and the sterno-occipitalis. The ventral portion, the sternomastiodeus is the stronger and main continuation of the sternocephalicus, which inserts on the mastoid part of the temporal bone. The thin but wide dorsal segment, the sterno-occipitalis attaches to the dorsal nuchal crest by a thin aponeurosis. The main action provided by the sternocephalicus is movement of the head and neck to the side. Ventral branches of the cervical nerves are attached to this muscle.

name: arthropod sensillum
description: Sense organ embedded in the integument and consisting of one or a cluster of sensory neurons and associated sensory structures, support cells and glial cells forming a single organised unit with a largely bona-fide boundary.[FBbt]

name: inferior parathyroid epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a inferior parathyroid gland.

name: epithelium of appendix
description: A epithelium that is part of a vermiform appendix.

name: diaphragm
description: A thin musculomebranous barrier that separates the abdominal and thoracic cavities. Often used for breathing control

name: neural arch 3
description: Neural arch 3 is expanded and fused to supraneural 3 as part of a neural complex roofing and protecting the neural canal.

name: infraglenoid buttress
description: An anatomical projection ventral to the glenoid fossa on the scapulocoracoid that abuts on the cliethrum (if present).

name: cephalic neural fold
description: The elevated margins of the neural groove that are located in the future cephalic region of the embryo

name: obsolete segment of white matter of spinal cord
regenerating fin/limb
description: Fin or limb undergoing the process of regeneration.

name: basihyal bone
description: Replacement bone that is median and is the anterior-most bone of the ventral hyoid arch.

name: prostate gland ventral lobe
description: Prostate gland lobe that in the mouse has the following characteristics: grossly, clear, gelatinous, and leaf-like; originates ventrally and wraps incompletely around the urethra dorsally, bilaterally. Simple columnar epithelium with the least amount of infolding. Secretory cells are oval and have slightly foamy cytoplasm; nuclei and basal nucleoli are inconspicuous. The secretion is pale and homogeneous. The stroma is thin

name: respiratory system skeletal muscle
description: A portion of skeletal muscle tissue that is part of a respiratory system [Automatically generated definition].

name: temporal process of zygomatic bone
description: The temporal process of the zygomatic bone, directed backward and medialward, is concave, presenting medially a rough, triangular area, for articulation with the maxilla, and laterally a smooth, concave surface, the upper part of which forms the anterior boundary of the temporal fossa, the lower a part of the infratemporal fossa. Near the center of this surface is the zygomaticotemporal foramen for the transmission of the zygomaticotemporal nerve.

name: musculature of larynx
description: The collection of muscles that are part of the larynx.

name: exoccipital bone
description: Paired cartilage bone that bears a large foramen (lateral occipital foramen). Contacts the supraoccipital dorsally, the epiotic laterally and the basioccipital ventrally. Forms the posterior hind margin of the cranium and borders the lateral and posterior margins of the forum (foramen) magnum.

name: muscularis mucosae of fundus of stomach
description: A muscularis mucosa that is part of a fundus of stomach.

name: metoptic pillar
description: The posterior border of the optic nerve foramen.

name: phalanx
description: Endochondral bones that are often elongate and arranged in rows of articulating elements, and form the visible part of the digits.

name: hypobranchial group muscle
description: A jaw muscle that arises from trunk somites and is innervated by spinal nerves.

name: dorsal longitudinal fasciculus
description: A fiber bundle containing fibers from nuclei of the hypothalamus that project to the dorsal tegmental nucleus and other regions of the midbrain and the pons, as well as fibers originating in the pontine reticular formation and the medullary reticular formation that project to the thalamus and other regions of the forebrain (Carpenter-83). In NeuroNames it is a composite structure consisting of the dorsal longitudinal fasciculus of hypothalamus, the dorsal longitudinal fasciculus of midbrain, the dorsal longitudinal fasciculus of pons and the dorsal longitudinal fasciculus of medulla. (NeuroNames)

name: fenestra
description: An opening in the skull or other bones[WP].

name: paraventricular nucleus of thalamus
description: The nucleus paraventricularis anterior thalami and nuclues paraventricularis posterior thalami, two of the nuclei mediani thalami; they are situated on the dorsomedial wall of the thalamus, juxtaposed to the third ventricle.

name: ureteric bud
description: An epithelial swelling on the Wolffian duct that elongates to invade the adjacent metanephric mesenchyme[MP]

name: anatomical projection
description: A projection or outgrowth of tissue from a larger body or organ.

name: papilla
description: Surface structure that is a small, fleshy protuberance.

name: lymphoid tissue
description: Portion of connective tissue with various types of white blood cells enmeshed in it, most numerous being the lymphocytes[WP].

name: monkey lips dorsal bursa complex
description: A structure consisting of a pair of anterior and posterior dorsal bursae in which a pair of phonic lips are embedded, along with the bursal cartilage and a blowhole ligament

name: muscle of larynx
description: The muscles associated with the larynx.

name: extensor muscle
description: a skeletal muscle whose contraction extends or stretches a body part.

name: scalene muscle
description: Any of the three pairs of muscles in the lateral neck, namely the scalenus anterior, scalenus medius, and scalenus posterior. They are innervated by the spinal nerves C4-C8[WP].

name: caudal appendage
description: Multi-tissue structure that is region of the body posterior to the last anal-fin ray.

name: ischial spine
description: A bony process projecting backward and medialward from the posterior border of the ischium.

name: future glans penis
description: A future glans that is part of a male genital tubercle.

name: ophthalmic artery
description: The ophthalmic artery is a branch of the internal carotid artery which supplies branches to supply the eye and other structures in the orbit. It enters the orbit together with the Optic nerve through the Optic foramen/canal. [WP,modified].

name: involucrum
description: A layer of new bone growth outside existing bone seen in pyogenic osteomyelitis. It results from the stripping off of the periosteum by the accumulation of pus within the bone, and new bone growing from the periosteum.

name: vibrissa inner root sheath
description: A hair inner root sheath that is part of a vibrissa unit.

name: canal plate
description: Dermal bone that is ventral to the preopercle and bears a portion of the preopercular sensory canal.

name: arterial baroreceptor
description: Arterial baroreceptors are stretch receptors that are stimulated by distortion of the arterial wall when pressure changes.

name: periosteal dura mater
description: The outermost of the two layers of the cranial dura mater which normally always adheres to the periosteum of the bones of the cranial vault

name: long bone epiphyseal plate hypertrophic zone
description: The layer of the epiphyseal plate of a long bone where chondrocytes mature and enlarge[MP].

name: paired limb/fin bud mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a limb/fin bud.

name: internal cerebral vein
description: The internal cerebral veins (veins of Galen; deep cerebral veins) drain the deep parts of the hemisphere and are two in number; each is formed near the interventricular foramen by the union of the terminal and choroid veins. They run backward parallel with one another, between the layers of the tela chorioidea of the third ventricle, and beneath the splenium of the corpus callosum, where they unite to form a short trunk, the great cerebral vein; just before their union each receives the corresponding basal vein.

name: basal ganglia of rodent
description: The basal ganglia of the rodent

name: developing neuroepithelium
description: An embryonic or larval epithelium that is committed to form part of the nervous system.

name: atlantal spinal nerve foramen
description: Foramen housing the root of the spinal nerve seen in the neural arch of the first vertebrae (atlas). (see Edwards 1976)

name: right hepatic artery
description: A hepatic artery that is part of a right lobe of liver.

name: adventitia of ductus deferens
description: An adventitia that is part of a vas deferens.

name: pedal digit 4 phalanx
description: A phalanx that is part of a foot digit 4 [Automatically generated definition].

name: tooth socket
description: Dental alveolus (plural, alveoli) are sockets in the jaws in which the roots of teeth are held in the alveolar process of maxilla with the periodontal ligament. The lay term for dental alveoli is tooth sockets. A joint that connect the roots of the teeth and the alveolus are called gomphosis (plural gomphoses). In mammals, tooth sockets are found in the maxilla and the mandible. [WP,unvetted].

name: inner renal medulla interstitium
description: A portion of interstitial tissue that is part of a inner medulla of kidney [Automatically generated definition].

name: entocarotid fossa
description: A depression on the lateral surface of the braincase posterior to the Vidian canal (Conrad 2008)

name: mucosa of segmental bronchus
description: A mucosa that is part of a segmental bronchus [Automatically generated definition].

name: mesenchyme of interdigital region between pedal digits 1 and 2
description: An interdigital region mesenchyme that is part of a interdigital region between pedal digits 1 and 2.

name: tooth-like structure
description: hard bony, calcareous, or chitinous organ found in the mouth or pharynx of an animal and used in procuring or masticating food.

name: cortex of hair
description: A cortex that is part of a hair [Automatically generated definition].

name: layer of dentate gyrus
description: One of the three layers of the dentate gyrus of the hippocampal formation.

name: ansa lenticularis
description: The ansa lenticularis (ansa lentiformis in older texts) is a part of the brain, making up the superior layer of the substantia innominata of Meynert. Its fibers, derived from the medullary lamina of the lentiform nucleus, pass medially to end in the thalamus and subthalamic region, while others are said to end in the tegmentum and red nucleus. It is classified by NeuroNames as part of the subthalamus.

name: superior olivary complex
description: A a collection of brainstem nuclei that functions in multiple aspects of hearing and is an important component of the ascending and descending auditory pathways of the auditory system.

name: podotheca
description: A horny sheath covering the lower leg of some birds.

name: obsolete anal fin
description: Median fin that is located posterior to the anus.

name: spinalis capitis muscle
description: Origin: spines of upper thoracic and lower cervical vertebrae; insertion: occipital bone; innervation: spinal nerves; action, extends head.

name: presumptive midbrain hindbrain boundary
description: Embryonic structure that gives rise to the midbrain hindbrain boundary.

name: pectinate muscle
description: The prominent ridges of atrial myocardium located on the inner surface of most of the right atrium and both the right and left auricular regions[MP].

name: sclerotome somite 13
description: Medial ventral region of the somite that will form vertebral cartilages. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: Jacobson's vein
description: Either of a pair of veins which receives many small vesicles from the kidney and collects blood from the oviducal vein.

name: depressor septi nasi
description: The depressor septi (Depressor alE nasi) arises from the incisive fossa of the maxilla. Its fibers ascend to be inserted into the nasal septum and back part of the alar part of nasalis muscle. It lies between the mucous membrane and muscular structure of the lip.

name: mandibular rhamphotheca
description: A rhamphotheca that is part of a lower beak.

name: carpal tunnel
description: The fibro-osseous passageway on the palmar side of the wrist that connects the distal forearm to the middle compartment of the deep plane of the palm.

name: salivary gland primordium
description: A primordium that has the potential to develop into a saliva-secreting gland.

name: inferior thyroid vein
description: The inferior thyroid veins two, frequently three or four, in number, arise in the venous plexus on the thyroid gland, communicating with the middle and superior thyroid veins. They form a plexus in front of the trachea, behind the Sternothyreoidei. From this plexus, a left vein descends and joins the left innominate trunk, and a right vein passes obliquely downward and to the right across the innominate artery to open into the right innominate vein, just at its junction with the superior vena cava; sometimes the right and left veins open by a common trunk in the latter situation. These veins receive esophageal tracheal, and inferior laryngeal veins, and are provided with valves at their terminations in the innominate veins.

name: embryonic head
description: A head that is part of a embryo.

name: left gastric vein
description: The Left gastric vein (or coronary vein) carries blood low in Oxygen, tributaries derived from both surfaces of the stomach; it runs from right to left along the lesser curvature of the stomach, between the two layers of the lesser omentum, to the esophageal opening of the stomach, where it receives some esophageal veins. It then turns backward and passes from left to right behind the omental bursa and drains into the portal vein. Esophageal and paraesophageal varices are primarily supplied by the left gastric vein and typically drain into the azygos/hemiazygos venous system.

name: short nephron
description: Short nephrons are associated with mid-cortical glomeruli, and have no short ascending limb, so the limb is situated in the outer medulla

name: lumbar spinal cord ventral column
description: A subdivision of spinal cord ventral column that is part of a lumbar spinal cord.

name: acellular bone tissue
description: Mineralized bone tissue that has terminally differentiated osteoblasts but lacks osteocytes.

name: right lung caudal lobe segmental bronchus
description: A segmental bronchus that is part of a lower lobe of right lung.

name: olfactory cortex
description: Aggregate brain region defined as those areas of cerebral cortex receiving direct synaptic input from the olfactory bulb (Price, 1973). It usually includes the piriform cortex and sometimes other areas.

name: proximal epiphysis of first metacarpal bone
description: A proximal epiphysis that is part of a metacarpal bone of digit 1 [Automatically generated definition].

name: posterior sclerotic cartilage
description: Sclerotic cartilage that is located posterior to the eye.

name: lateral pallium
description: Subdivision of pallium that is located laterally.

name: outflow tract smooth muscle
description: A portion of smooth muscle tissue that is part of a outflow tract [Automatically generated definition].

name: elbow
description: The elbow is the region surrounding the elbow-joint-the ginglymus or hinge joint in the middle of the arm. Three bones form the elbow joint: the humerus of the upper arm, and the paired radius and ulna of the forearm. The bony prominence at the very tip of the elbow is the olecranon process of the ulna, and the inner aspect of the elbow is called the antecubital fossa. [WP,unvetted,human-specific].

name: serous sac
description: Organ with organ cavity, which has as parts a serous membrane and a serous cavity . Examples: pleural sac, pericardial sac, tendon sheath, bursa.[FMA]

name: nephron
description: The basic functional unit of the kidney. its chief function is to regulate the concentration of water and soluble substances like sodium salts by filtering the blood, reabsorbing what is needed and excreting the rest as urine. A nephron eliminates wastes from the body, regulates blood volume and blood pressure, controls levels of electrolytes and metabolites, and regulates blood pH. Its functions are vital to life and are regulated by the endocrine system by hormones such as antidiuretic hormone, aldosterone, and parathyroid hormone.[WP]

name: ventral posteromedial nucleus of thalamus
description: The ventral posteromedial nucleus is a nucleus of the thalamus. [WP,unvetted].

name: gustatory papilla of tongue
description: A papilla that contain taste buds, including the fungiform, foliate, and circumvallate papillae.

name: penicillar arteriole
description: One of the small straight arteries of the red pulp of the spleen; a branch of the spleen central artery that supplies the red pulp[WP,modified]

name: superior temporal gyrus
description: Component of the temporal lobe, lateral aspect. The rostral boundary is the rostral extent of the ssuperior temporal sulcus. The caudal boundary is the cauday portion of the superior temporal gyrus (posterior to becoming continuous with the supramarginal gyrus). The medial boundary is the lateral fissure (and when present the supramarginal gyrus), and the lateral boundary is the superior temporal suclus (Christine Fennema-Notestine).

name: angulosplenial
description: Dermal bone of anuran lower jaw investing lingual and ventral surfaces of Meckel's cartilage; forming coronoid process and articulating with palatoquadrate posteriorly.

name: skin of ankle
description: A zone of skin that is part of an ankle [Automatically generated definition].

name: strand of hair of face
description: A strand of hair that is part of a face.

name: duct of vestibular gland
description: A duct that is part of a vestibular gland.

name: membranous urethra of male or female
anal fin radial element
description: Anal fin radial elements are internal skeletal supports of the anal fin.

name: postcleithrum 3
description: Postcleithrum that articulates dorsally with postcleithrum 2 and, sometimes, anteriorly with cleithrum.

name: entire pharyngeal arch associated mesenchyme
description: The sum total of mesenchymal tissue in the pharyngeal arch region. Pharyngeal mesenchyme is undifferentiated, loose connective tissue derived mostly from mesoderm, and also contains ectodermally derived neural crest cells.

name: mesethmoid-frontal joint
description: Joint that articulates the mesethmoid and frontal. Mesethmoid-frontal joint is paired.

name: caudal principal ray 17
description: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 16.

name: ureteric bud tip
description: The terminal end of the ureteric tree; the ureteric tip cells are proliferating immature cells located at the branching points that induce the adjacent cap mesenchyme to undergo nephrogenesis.

name: lobule of mammary gland
description: Organ component of the mammary gland which consists of an aggregate of mammary alveoli that communicate with a lobular lactiferous duct.[FMA]

name: left lung hilus
description: A lung hilus that is part of the left lung.

name: future central tendon
description: A tendon that has the potential to develop into a central tendon.

name: Peyer's patch
description: the protruding lymphoid tissue located on the mucosa of the intestine that is composed of densely packed B cell follicles

name: small intestine Peyer's patch
description: nodular lymphoid structures on the serosal surface of the small intestine.

name: intestinal mucosal muscle
description: A thin layer of smooth muscle immediately beneath the base of the villi which permits the intestinal mucosa to dynamically move and fold.

name: right nipple
description: A nipple that is in_the_right_side_of a body proper.

name: skeleton of lower jaw
description: A subdivision of the skeleton that corresponds to the lower part of the mouth. The lower jaw skeleton includes the following elements, when present: lower jaw teeth, the mandible and other lower jaw bones, and Meckel's cartilage.

name: occipital lobe
description: Posterior part of the cerebral hemisphere (MSH)

name: submucosa of biliary tree
description: A submucosa that is part of a biliary tree [Automatically generated definition].

name: Hadjikhani et al. (1998) visuotopic area V4v
anterior internodal tract
description: Internodal tract which consists of the atrial and atrial septal branches.

name: blood serum
description: The portion of blood plasma that excludes clotting factors.

name: trachea blood vessel
description: A blood vessel that is part of a trachea.

name: obsolete regional part of cerebellar white matter
obsolete regional part of cerebellar white matter
obsolete gill ionocyte
description: Ionocyte located in the gills

name: submucosa of anal canal
description: A submucosa that is part of an anal canal [Automatically generated definition].

name: obsolete regional part of hippocampal formation
masseteric artery
description: The masseteric artery is small and passes laterally through the mandibular notch to the deep surface of the masseter muscle, which it supplies. It anastomoses with the masseteric branches of the external maxillary artery and with the transverse facial artery.

name: dactylopatagium brevis
description: A dactylopatagium that is connected_to a manual digit 1 and connected_to a manual digit 2.

name: adductor brevis
description: The adductor brevis is a muscle in the thigh situated immediately behind the pectineus and adductor longus. It is somewhat triangular in form, and arises by a narrow origin from the outer surfaces of the superior and inferior rami of the pubis, between the gracilis and obturator externus. Its fibers, passing backward, lateralward, and downward, are inserted, by an aponeurosis, into the line leading from the lesser trochanter to the linea aspera and into the upper part of the linea aspera, immediately behind the pectineus and upper part of the adductor longus.[WP].

name: one-pass circulatory system
description: A closed circulatory system in which blood passes once through the heart to supply the body once.

name: pericalcarine cortex
description: Component of the parietal lobe. The rostral boundary of the pericalcarine cortex was the first appearance of the calcarine sulcus whereas the caudal boundary was the most posterior coronal slice where the calcarine sulcus was visualized. The medial and lateral boundaries were the medial portion of the temporal and occipital cortices and the inferomedial end of the calcarine sulcus respectively (Christine Fennema-Notestine).

name: placenta blood vessel
description: A blood vessel of the placenta.

name: distal tarsal bone 5
description: Endochondral tarsal bone articulating with centralia and metatarsal 5.

name: hypaxial region somite 13
description: Somite-derived body wall muscle present ventral to the horizontal myoseptum. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: rhombomere 2 roof plate
description: A rhombomere roof plate that is part of a rhombomere 2.

name: primary circulatory organ
description: A hollow, muscular organ, which, by contracting rhythmically, keeps up the circulation of the blood or analogs[GO,modified].

name: renal nerve plexus
description: The renal plexus is formed by filaments from the celiac plexus, the aorticorenal ganglion, and the aortic plexus . It is joined also by the least splanchnic nerve. The nerves from these sources, fifteen or twenty in number, have a few ganglia developed upon them. They accompany the branches of the renal artery into the kidney; some filaments are distributed to the spermatic plexus and, on the right side, to the inferior vena cava.

name: carotid artery segment
description: One of: the common carotid artery, or its branches, the external and internal carotid arteries.

name: mucocartilage tissue
description: A temporary avascular cartilage found in the heads of ammocoete larvae and surrounded by perichondrium. Contains a few fibroblasts scattered throughout ECM containing elastic-like microfibrils.

name: palatoquadrate arch
description: The dorsal portion of the first pharyngeal arch, comprising the upper jaw[ZFIN,VHOG].

name: distal tubular epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a distal tubule.

name: semi-lunar valve
description: the valves that gate the flow of blood from the ventricles into the aorta and pulmonary trunk

name: middle pharyngeal constrictor
description: The middle pharyngeal constrictor is a fanshaped muscle, smaller than the Inferior pharyngeal constrictor muscle.

name: hypocleideum
description: Zone of bone organ located on the flat ventral side of the distal region of the furcula, serving as attachment region for pectoral muscles.

name: embryonic abdominal segment 9
description: Any abdominal segment 9 (UBERON:6000030) that is part of some embryonic abdomen (UBERON:6000171).

name: epithelium of duct of salivary gland
description: A epithelium that is part of a duct of salivary gland.

name: carina of trachea
description: A cartilaginous ridge within the trachea that runs anteroposteriorly between the two primary bronchi at the site of the tracheal bifurcation at the lower end of the trachea.

name: glottis
description: the vocal apparatus of the larynx, which includes the vocal cords and the opening between them

name: sinus nervi hypoglossi
description: Depression that houses the hypoglossus nerve and is located between the anterolateral process and the proximal part of the hyale.

name: labium minora
description: One of the folds of skin which form the inner lips on both sides of the vaginal opening

name: arthropod neurohemal organ
description: A system of neurons that has the specialized function to produce and secrete hormones, and that constitutes, in whole or in part, an endocrine organ or system.

name: tuber
description: Eminence or swelling on anatomical surface.

name: circular sulcus of insula
description: A marginal sulcus that is part of a insula [Automatically generated definition].

name: hermaphrodite gonad
description: A gonad with both testicular and ovarian aspects[WP].

name: superior parathyroid epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a superior parathyroid gland.

name: anterior jugular vein
description: The anterior jugular vein begins near the hyoid bone by the confluence of several superficial veins from the submaxillary region. It descends between the median line and the anterior border of the Sternocleidomastoideus, and, at the lower part of the neck, passes beneath that muscle to open into the termination of the external jugular, or, in some instances, into the subclavian vein. It varies considerably in size, bearing usually an inverse proportion to the external jugular; most frequently there are two anterior jugulars, a right and left; but sometimes only one. Its tributaries are some laryngeal veins, and occasionally a small thyroid vein. Just above the sternum the two anterior jugular veins communicate by a transverse trunk, the venous jugular arch, which receive tributaries from the inferior thyroid veins; each also communicates with the internal jugular. There are no valves in this vein. [WP,unvetted].

name: neural arch 4
description: Neural arch 4 is expanded and fused to supraneural 3 as part of the neural complex. A reduced neural spine projects from the posterior margin of the neural complex.

name: transverse pelvic ridge
description: The transverse pelvic ridge is a short crest directly anterior to, and not extending posterior to, the prominent supra-acetabular buttress  from Pawley and Warren 2006.

name: nucleus praetectalis profundus
description: A neural nucleus of the pretectal region that lies lateral to the posterior commissure and gives rise to widespread projections.

name: odontode
description: Multi-tissue structure composed of enameloid and dentine surrounding a pulp cavity, and found either attached to dermal bone or freely in the skin.

name: limb mesenchyme
description: The primordial embryonic connective tissue of the developing limbs, autopods and digits, consisting of mesenchymal cells supported in interlaminar jelly, that derive mostly from the mesoderm and contribute to limb connective tissue, bone and musculature in conjunction with myotome cells.

name: pharate adult
description: The developing adult after pupal-adult apolysis, i.e. from stage P8 (when yellow eye color first becomes visible through the pupal case), to eclosion.

name: fundus of gallbladder
description: The fundus of gallbladder is the portion of the gallbladder which lies the farthest from the cystic duct. It is covered with peritoneum. A traditional cholecystectomy is most commonly performed from the infundibulum to the fundus. It's at the same level as the transpyloric plane.

name: metacarpophalangeal joint of manual digit 3
