description: The internal carotid plexus (carotid plexus) is situated on the lateral side of the internal carotid artery, and in the plexus there occasionally exists a small gangliform swelling, the carotid ganglion, on the under surface of the artery. Postganglionic sympathetic fibres ascend from the superior cervical ganglion, along the walls of the internal carotid artery, to enter the internal carotid plexus. These fibres then distribute to deep structures, which include the levator palpebrae superioris and pupillary dilator muscles. Some of the fibres from the internal carotid plexus converge to form the deep petrosal nerve. The internal carotid plexus communicates with the semilunar ganglion, the abducent nerve, and the sphenopalatine ganglion; it distributes filaments to the wall of the carotid artery, and also communicates with the tympanic branch of the glossopharyngeal nerve. [WP,unvetted].

name: navicular bursa of pes
description: A navicular bursa that is part of a pes.

name: pedal digit blood vessel
description: A blood vessel that is part of a toe [Automatically generated definition].

name: buccal fat pad
description: The Buccal fat pad is one of several encapsulated fat masses in the cheek. It is a deep fat pad located on either side of the face between the buccinator muscle and several more superficial muscles. It should not be confused with the malar fat pad, which is directly below the skin of the cheek. It should also not be confused with jowl fat pads. It is implicated in the formation of hollow cheeks and the nasolabial fold, but not in the formation of jowls.

name: obsolete vH ionocyte
description: Integument ionocyte rich in vacuolar-type H+ ATPase and carbonic anhydrase

name: dactylopatagium major
description: A dactylopatagium that is connected_to a manual digit 4 and connected_to a manual digit 5.

name: pelvic girdle skeleton
description: Skeletal subdivision consisting of a set of bones linking the axial series to the hindlimb zeugopodium and offering anchoring areas for hindlimb and caudal musculature.

name: lateral plantar nerve
description: A plantar nerve that supplies the lateral side of the plantar part of the foot, including pedal digit 5.

name: stylohyoid muscle
description: The stylohyoid is a pharyngeal arch II muscle that participates in oral/pharygeal behaviors and is innervated by the stylohoid branch of the facial nerve and attaches to the stylohyal and the non-stylohyal part of the hyoid apparatus.

name: superficial feature part of occipital lobe
rhombomere 3 roof plate
description: A rhombomere roof plate that is part of a rhombomere 3.

name: dorsal acoustic stria
description: white matter structure containing fibers arising from the cochlear nuclear complex

name: ramus recurrens
description: Branch of the vagus nerve that separates from the vagus well postcranially, then continues anteriorly to innervate the larynx.

name: thoracic splanchnic nerve
description: Thoracic splanchnic nerves are splanchnic nerves that arise from the sympathetic trunk in the thorax and travel inferiorly to provide sympathetic innervation to the abdomen. The nerves contain preganglionic sympathetic and general visceral afferent fibers.

name: male reproductive gland
description: A sex gland that is part of a male reproductive system.

name: outflow tract septum
description: The outflow tract septum is a partition in the outflow tract

name: infratemporal fenestra
description: An infratemporal fenestra, also called the lateral temporal fenestra is an opening in the skull behind the orbit in some animals.

name: paraventricular nucleus of the hypothalamus parvicellular division
ventral mesogastrium
description: Portion of ventral mesentery closest to the stomach.

name: preaxial centrale
description: Centrale in the preaxial side of the mesopodium.

name: perichordal bone
description: Bone element that is adjacent to the notochord.

name: pubo-ischium
description: Composite element formed by the fusion of the ischium and pubis.

name: coronal suture
description: the dense, fibrous connective tissue joint between the tetrapod parietal bones and the frontal bone

name: collecting duct of renal tubule
description: The collecting duct is a portion of the nephron through which water flows, moving passively down its concentration gradient

name: corpus cardiacum
description: One of a pair of neurohemal organs located on the walls of the aorta just behind the brain. The corpora cardiaca release their store of PTTH only after they receive a signal from neurosecretory cells in the brain.

name: puboischiadic bar
description: A transverse flattened or cylindrical plate in the posterior body wall opposite the anterior ends of the pelvic fins, in front of the vent and at the posterior end of the body cavity, that supports a few anterior pelvic radials and a basal cartilage, the basipterygium.  from  Leonard J. V. Compagno. 2001. Sharks of the World: An Annotated and Illustrated Catalogue of Shark Species Known to Date. Volume 2.

name: collateral sulcus
description: The collateral fissure (or sulcus) is on the tentorial surface of the hemisphere and extends from near the occipital pole to within a short distance of the temporal pole. Behind, it lies below and lateral to the calcarine fissure, from which it is separated by the lingual gyrus; in front, it is situated between the hippocampal gyrus and the anterior part of the fusiform gyrus. [WP,unvetted].

name: skin of prepuce of clitoris
description: A zone of skin that is part of a prepuce of clitoris.

name: apical ectodermal ridge dorsal fin
description: Apical ectodermal ridge that is part of the dorsal fin.

name: urodermal bone
description: Paired, thin dermal bones at the rear of the caudal fin skeleton, derived from scales.

name: rib of vertebra 6
description: Rib that articulates with the parapophysis of the sixth centrum.

name: metapodium region
description: Intermediate segment of the autopod, between the mesopodial region and and acropodial region. Examples: metacarpal region, metatarsal region

name: obsolete regional part of inferior parietal cortex
prostatic utricle
description: A small indentation located in the prostatic urethra, at the apex of the urethral crest, on the seminal colliculus (verumontanum), laterally flanked by openings of the ejaculatory ducts.

name: fourth lumbar dorsal root ganglion
description: The group of nerve cell bodies located on the dorsal spinal roots within the vertebral column at the level of the fourth lumbar vertebra

name: gingiva of lower jaw
description: A gingiva that is part of a lower jaw region.

name: sternohyoid muscle
description: The sternohyoid muscle is a thin, narrow muscle attaching the hyoid bone to the sternum, one of the paired strap muscles of the infrahyoid muscles serving to depress the hyoid bone. It is innervated by the ansa cervicalis. The muscle arises from the posterior border of the medial end of the clavicle, the posterior sternoclavicular ligament, and the upper and posterior part of the manubrium sterni. Passing upward and medially, it is inserted by short tendinous fibers into the lower border of the body of the hyoid bone. [WP,unvetted].

name: quadrate-hyomandibula joint
description: Joint that articulates quadrate and hyomandibula bones. Quadrate-hyomandibula joint is paired.

name: caroticotympanic artery
description: The caroticotympanic branch (tympanic branch) is small; it enters the tympanic cavity through a minute foramen in the carotid canal, and anastomoses with the anterior tympanic branch of the internal maxillary, and with the stylomastoid artery.

name: alveus of CA2 field
description: Part of alveus lying within hippocampal sector CA2

name: metacarpophalangeal joint of manual digit 4
description: A skeletal joint that connects a metacarpal bone and connects a proximal phalanx of manual digit 4.

name: gall bladder serosa
description: A serous membrane that is part of a gallbladder [Automatically generated definition].

name: chamber of eyeball
description: A segment of the eyeball that is filled with refractive media

name: neurovascular bundle
description: A body structure consisting of nerves traveling together with arteries, veins, and/or lymphatics.

name: myelinated nerve fiber
description: Axons of neurons encased in a lipoproteinaceous material called myelin. (MeSH)

name: epithelium of mucosa
description: A layer of epithelial cells on the surface of the mucosa.

name: hepatic duct smooth muscle
description: Smooth muscle tissue in all or part of a hepatic duct.

name: abdominal fascia
description: A fascia that is part of a abdomen.

name: forelimb endochondral element
description: A forelimb bone or its cartilage or pre-cartilage precursor.

name: caudate nucleus
description: Subcortical nucleus of telecephalic origin consisting of an elongated gray mass lying lateral to and bordering the lateral ventricle. It is divided into a head, body and tail in some species.

name: Mullerian tubercle
description: An elevation on the wall of the embryonic urogenital sinus where the M√ºllerian ducts enter.

name: dartos muscle of labia majora
description: A dartos muscle that is part of a female reproductive system.

name: trabecula
description: A small, often microscopic, tissue element in the form of a small beam, strut or rod, generally having a mechanical function, and usually but not necessarily composed of dense collagenous tissue. On histological section, a trabecula can look like a septum, but in three dimensions they are topologically distinct, with trabeculae being roughly rod or pillar-shaped and septa being sheet-like. Trabeculae are usually composed of dense fibrous tissue, i.e. mainly of collagen, and in most cases provide mechanical strengthening or stiffening to a soft solid organ, such as the spleen. They can be composed of other materials, such as bone or muscle[WP].

name: optic artery
description: The artery that carries blood to the eye. It branches from the internal carotid artery and enters the eye ventrally through the optic fissure. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: Brodmann (1909) area 13
description: Brodmann area 13 is a subdivision of the cerebral cortex as defined on the guenon monkey and on the basis of cytoarchitecture. Brodmann area 13 is found in humans, however it seems to act as a bridge between the lateral and medial layers of the brain. Thus it is sometimes misidentified as not being a Brodmann area.

name: collagen and cuticulin-based cuticle
description: A type of cuticle composed of highly cross-linked collagens and specialised insoluble proteins known as cuticlins, together with glycoproteins and lipids[WP].

name: pelvic appendage
description: Paired appendage that consists of the posterior appendicular skeleton and associated soft and hard tissues, but excludes the pelvic girdle and its associated soft and hard tissues.

name: paracentral nucleus
description: one of the intralaminar nuclei of the thalamus, located medial to the central lateral nucleus.

name: fringing fulcrum
description: Fulcrum that is a small, paired dermal structure associated with the marginal, leading rays of paired and/or unpaired fins. Arratia, G. 2009. Identifying patterns of diversity of the actinopterygian fulcra. Acta Zoologica (Stockholm) 90 (Suppl. 1): 220-235.

name: pedal digit 4 phalanx pre-cartilage condensation
description: A pre-cartilage condensation that is part of a pedal digit 4 mesenchyme.

name: trophoblast
description: the mesectodermal cell layer arising from the trophectoderm that erodes the uterine mucosa and contributes to the formation of the placenta

name: diastema
description: A space or gap between two consecutive teeth.

name: capsule of parathyroid gland
description: The dense and irregular connective tissue capsule surrounding a parathyroid gland.

name: obsolete regional part of septal nuclear complex
embryonic cisterna chyli
description: An embryonic lymph sac that is dorsal to the retroperitoneal lymph sac, at the level of the adrenal glands.

name: taenia tecti medialis
description: Cartilaginous connection between the taenia tecti transversalis to the tectum synoticum, and subdividing the parietal fenestra into left and right fenestrae. Often persist from larva to adult.

name: subarachnoid space
description: The space between the arachnoid and pia mater.

name: ventral thalamic fasciculus
description: The thalamic fasciculus is a component of the subthalamus. It is sometimes considered synonymous with 'field H1 of Forel'. Nerve fibres forming a composite bundle containing cerebellothalamic (crossed) and pallidothalamic (uncrossed) fibres that is insinuated between the thalamus and zona incerta. The thalamic fasciculus consists of the joint fibers of the ansa lenticularis and the lenticular fasciculus, coming from different portions of the medial globus pallidus, before they jointly enter the ventral lateral nucleus of the thalamus.

name: sclerotome somite 22
description: Medial ventral region of the somite that will form vertebral cartilages. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: Aristotle's lantern
description: Within the mouth of a sea urchin is an elaborate five-sided jaw structure called Aristotles lantern that can be partially extruded from the mouth. It is able to grind up calcareous exoskeletons of plants and animals.

name: dorsal mesentery
description: The mesentery that originates from the dorsal side of the peritoneal cavity[ZFA].

name: pit organ
description: Mechanoreceptive organ of the lateral line, smaller than neuromasts, they are located on the surface of the epidermis. These receptors receive afferent and efferent innervation.

name: entopterygoid
description: Dermal bone that forms the ventro-medial part of the palate and the antero-ventral and ventral wall of the orbit. The entopterygoid is a paired bone.

name: extraembryonic tissue
description: Portion of tissue that is contiguous with the embryo and is comprised of portions of tissue or cells that will not contribute to the embryo.

name: outer dental epithelium
description: Outer layer of cells of the dental organ.

name: medial cartilage of palatine
description: Pharyngeal cartilage that caps the medial margin of the palatine at the autopalatine-lateral ethmoid joint.

name: pulmonary baroreceptor
description: A baroreceptor that located_in a pulmonary vascular system.

name: strand of pelage hair
description: A strand of hair that is part of a coat of hair.

name: annular epiphysis
description: secondary growth centers occurring as rings at the periphery of the superior and inferior surfaces of the vertebral body.

name: fourth ventricle median aperture
description: The large midline opening of the posterior inferior part of the roof of the fourth ventricle that connects the fourth ventricle to the posterior cerebromedullary cistern and the spinal cord

name: inner chondrogenic layer of perichondrium
description: The perichondrium consists of two separate layers: an outer fibrous layer and inner chondrogenic layer. The chondrogenic layer remains undifferentiated and can form chondroblasts or chondrocytes.

name: cortical plate
description: The outer neural tube region in which post-mitotic neuroblasts migrate along radial glia to form the adult cortical layers[MP].

name: papillary duct
description: The terminal portions of the medullary collecting ducts are the papillary ducts, which end at the renal papilla and empty into a minor calyx.

name: rectus abdominis muscle
description: The rectus abdominis muscle is a paired muscle running vertically on each side of the anterior wall of the abdomen. There are two parallel sets of muscles, separated by a midline band of connective tissue called the linea alba (white line). It extends from the pubic symphysis/pubic crest inferiorly to the xiphisternum/xiphoid process and lower costal cartilages (5-7) superiorly. It is contained in the Rectus sheath. The rectus is usually crossed by three fibrous bands licked by the tendinous inscriptions. [WP,modified].

name: middle phalanx of pes
description: A middle phalanx that is part of a toe [Automatically generated definition].

name: diencephalon subarachnoid space
description: A subarachnoid space that is part of a diencephalon [Automatically generated definition].

name: pars tuberalis of adenohypophysis
description: The pars tuberalis is part of the anterior lobe of the pituitary gland, and wraps the pituitary stalk in a highly vascularized sheath. [WP,unvetted].

name: right pelvic girdle region
description: A pelvic girdle region that is in the right side of a multicellular organism.

name: ventral horn of spinal cord
description: The ventral grey column of the spinal cord[MP]. The neurons of the ventral region of the mature spinal cord participate in motor output[GO].

name: postnasal wall
description: Paired, anteriorly concave structures that form the posterior limit of nasal capsule. It consists of two parts: a ventral piece, the lamina orbitonasalis, and a dorsal plate that is part of the tectum nasi.

name: vas deferens
description: A secretory duct that transports sperm from the testis. In mammals this is a continuation of the epididymis and ends in the prostatic urethra where it terminates to form ejaculatory duct

name: arthropod fat body
description: An insect gland dorsal to the insect gut, with a function analogous to that of the vertebrate liver. It is a storage organ for fats, glycogen and protein and is a major site of intermediary metabolism.

name: cerebral cortex
description: The thin layer of gray matter on the surface of the cerebral hemisphere that develops from the telencephalon. It consists of the neocortex (6 layered cortex or isocortex), the hippocampal formation and the olfactory cortex.

name: upper urinary tract
description: Subdivision of urinary system which consists of the kidney and the ureters.

name: nucleus of brain
description: A neural nucleus that is part of the brain.

name: processus pterygoideus of maxilla
description: Posterior end of the pars palatina of the maxilla that is in contact with the anterior ramus of the pterygoid.

name: ampullary gland
description: A paired accessory, glandular, androgen-dependent outpouchings of the proximal ductus deferens, one on each side, that produce and secrete lipids and glycogen, components of the seminal fluid; they open into the ampullae at the level of the colliculus seminalis, are lined by simple columnar epithelium with large, oval nuclei, and may be distinguished from those of the prostate as they are surrounded by a characteristic, dense, fibromuscular stroma

name: manual digit 5 digitopodial skeleton
description: A subdivision of the skeleton of the autopod consisting of the phalanges of manual digit 5 plus the associated metapodial element.

name: oblique cartilage
description: Semi-circular cartilaginous sheet that lies lateral to the side of the septum nasi.

name: pharyngeal gill precursor
description: A primordium or bud that develops into a gill.

name: pharyngobranchial series
description: Anatomical cluster that consists of the pharyngobranchial elements within an individual.

name: presumptive paraxial mesoderm
description: The part of the blastula that has the potential to develop into a paraxial mesoderm.

name: subendocardium layer
description: The layer of loose fibrous tissue located between the endocardium and myocardium which contains the nerves and the impulse-conducting system (Purkinje fibers) of the heart

name: obsolete set of proper plantar digital arteries
inferior orbital fissure
description: The orbital fissure that is situated inferiorly between the greater wing of the sphenoid bone and the maxilla

name: bone of free limb or fin
description: A bone that is part of an appendage [Automatically generated definition].

name: pericardiacophrenic vein
description: Vena comitans of the pericardiacophrenic arteries.

name: posterior auricular artery
description: The posterior auricular artery is a small artery and arises from the external carotid artery, above the Digastric muscle and Stylohyoid muscle, opposite the apex of the styloid process. It ascends posteriorly beneath the parotid gland, along the styloid process of the temporal bone, between the cartilage of the ear and the mastoid process of the temporal bone along the lateral side of the head. The posterior auricular artery supplies blood to the scalp posterior to the auricle and to the auricle itself.

name: S-shaped body
description: The S-shaped body is the successor of the comma-shaped body that contributes to the morphogenesis of the nephron

name: rib 2
description: The second rib of the rib cage

name: chiasmatic cistern
description: the region of the subarachnoid space that is located below and anterior to the optic chiasm

name: proximal epiphysis of fifth metacarpal bone
description: A proximal epiphysis that is part of a metacarpal bone of digit 5 [Automatically generated definition].

name: transverse sinus
description: one of the dural venous sinuses and drains the superior sagittal sinus the occipital sinus and the straight sinus, and empties into the sigmoid sinus which in turn reaches the jugular bulb.

name: neural spine 6
description: Neural spine that is associated with the sixth vertebra.

name: articular capsule of glenohumeral joint
description: An articular capsule that is part of the glenohumeral joint.

name: knee
description: A segment of the hindlimb that corresponds to the joint connecting a hindlimb stylopod and zeugopod.

name: dorsal tegmental nucleus pars ventralis
description: Cytoarchitectural part of the dorsal tegmental nucleus based on cell size. The pars ventralis is characterized by medium sized oval or triangular cells that stain darkly in NIssl stains.

name: feather shaft
description: The combination of the rachis and the calamus.

name: tectospinal tract
description: A long process of a CNS neuron, that carries efferent (outgoing) action potentials from the cell body in the superior colliculus of the midbrain towards target cells in the ventral spinal cord[GO].

name: rib of vertebra 7
description: Rib that articulates with the parapophysis of the seventh centrum.

name: vein of lip
description: A vein that drains a lip.

name: centrum 1
description: Centrum that is part of vertebra 1.

name: abdominal aorta
description: Abdominal part of aorta: the distal part of the descending aorta, which is the continuation of the thoracic part and gives rise to the inferior phrenic, lumbar, median sacral, superior and inferior mesenteric, middle suprarenal, renal, and testicular or ovarian arteries, and celiac trunk[BTO]. The abdominal aorta is the largest artery in the abdominal cavity. As part of the aorta, it is a direct continuation of descending aorta(of the thorax). [WP,unvetted].

name: nutrient foramen vein
description: A vein or veins draining a bone and emerging from a nutrient foramen.

name: entoplastron
description: A median bone at the anterior margin of the plastron.

name: epidermis suprabasal layer
description: Any layer of the epidermis that is superior to the stratum basale

name: neuromast
description: Volcano-shaped lateral line sensory organ located in characteristic positions within the skin epithelium and containing hair cells and their support elements.

name: suprapharyngobranchial
description: A pharyngobranchial bone that articulates with the neurocranium dorsally and epibranchial 1 and pharyngobranchial 2 ventrally; lies dorsal to other elements of the dorsal portions of the branchial arches.

name: C7 segment of cervical spinal cord
description: The segment of the spinal cord that corresponds to the seventh cervical vertebra in most mammals.

name: anterior lateral line nerve
description: Cranial nerve which enters the brain between cranial nerves VI and VII; contains afferents and sensory efferents to the anterior lateral line ganglia.

name: midbody melanophore spot
description: distinct colored area on the midbody region of an organism, similar in shape to a spot, i.e. circular.

name: pharyngobranchial element
description: Skeletal element of the branchial arches located medial to the epibranchials.

name: kidney vasculature
description: A vasculature that is part of a kidney.

name: larynx connective tissue
description: A portion of connective tissue that is part of a larynx [Automatically generated definition].

name: metanephric pyramid
description: Metanephric pyramids are the conical masses that constitute the renal medulla in a metanephros; they contain the loops of Henle and the medullary collecting ducts[GO].

name: levator auris longus muscle
description: Muscle organ located on the dorsal surface of the head innervated by the facial nerve

name: superior cerebellar peduncle
description: A composite structure of the brain stem, which in NeuroNames is subdivided into the superior cerebellar peduncle of pons, the decussation of superior cerebellar peduncle and the superior cerebellar peduncle of midbrain (MM).

name: fenestra prechoanalis
description: Large opening of the nasal floor anterior to the fenestra endochoanalis.

name: proximal carpal endochondral element
description: A proximal mesopodial endochondral element that is part of a forelimb.

name: anal fold
description: A slight elevation flanking the cloacal membrane and derived from a cloacal fold; anal folds form the border of the anus.

name: neck bone
description: A bone that is part of a neck [Automatically generated definition].

name: vasculature of trunk
description: A vasculature that is part of a trunk [Automatically generated definition].

name: skin of palm of manus
description: A zone of skin that is part of a palmar part of manus.

name: forelimb epitrochlearis muscle
description: The superficial-most muscle of the anterior surface of the arm is the epitrochlearis. It has no homolog in humans.

name: CA2 stratum oriens
description: Part of stratum oriens lying in area CA2 deep to the CA2 pyramidal cell layer and continuous with stratum oriens of area CA2 and bounded by the dentate gyrus hilus[Modified from NIFSTD by CJM].

name: stratum basale of epidermis
description: the deepest layer of the epidermis, which is composed of dividing stem cells and anchoring cells

name: epicardial fat
description: Visceral intrapericardial fat contiguous with the myocardial surface.

name: holocrine gland
description: any exocrine gland whose secretion consists of its own disintegrated secretory cells along with its secretory product; holocrine secretions are produced in the cytoplasm of the cell and released by the rupture of the plasma membrane, which destroys the cell and results in the secretion of the product into the lumen.

name: median pars intermedia
description: Region of the adenohypophysis which secretes melanophore-stimulating hormone, affecting the integumentary chromatophores.

name: arterial blood vessel
description: A blood vessel that is part of the arterial system. Includes artery, arteriole and aorta.

name: umbilical cord blood
description: blood that remains in the placenta and in the attached umbilical cord after childbirth[WP].

name: plagiopatagium
description: A flight membrane running between the body and the limb or digits.

name: medial plantar nerve
description: A plantar nerve that supplies the medial side of the plantar part of the foot, including pedal digit 1.

name: pectoral girdle and thoracic body wall skeletal muscle
quadratus femoris
description: The quadratus femoris is, as its name implies, a flat, quadrilateral skeletal muscle. Located on the posterior side of the hip joint, it is a strong lateral rotator and adductor of the thigh, but also acts to stabilize the femoral head in the Acetabulum.

name: rhombomere 4 floor plate
description: A rhombomere floor plate that is part of a rhombomere 4.

name: obsolete regional part of telencephalon
description: A regional part of brain that is part of a telencephalon [Automatically generated definition].

name: proximal deep inguinal lymph node
description: One of the deep inguinal lymph nodes located in or adjacent to the femoral canal; sometimes mistaken for a femoral hernia when enlarged.

name: obsolete ptychocyst
description: A cnida that is glutinous and is capable of sticking to prey. Found on burrowing (tube) anemones, which help create the tube in which the animal lives.

name: superior mesenteric artery
description: Mesenteric artery that supplies the whole length of the small intestine except the superior part of the duodenum. It also supplies the cecum and the ascending part of the colon and about half the transverse part of the colon. It arises from the anterior surface of the aorta below the celiac artery at the level of the first lumbar vertebra.

name: obsolete glenoid head of scapula
description: The scapula's contribution to the glenoid fossa.

name: processus confluens
description: Strip of cartilage that forms the lateral margin of the foramen nervi hypoglossi.

name: right adrenal gland
description: An adrenal gland that is in the right side of the abdomen

name: corpus allatum
description: One of a pair of separate or fused bodies in many insects that are sometimes closely associated with the corpora cardiaca and that secrete hormones (as juvenile hormone)[BTO].

name: triphycercal tail
description: A caudal fin with three lobes.

name: rostral interstitial nucleus of medial longitudinal fasciculus
description: The rostral interstitial nucleus of medial longitudinal fasciculus (riMLF) is a portion of the medial longitudinal fasciculus which controls vertical gaze. They project to the vestibular nuclei. [WP,unvetted].

name: foramen of skull
description: Anatomical space that is an opening in a bone of the skull.

name: left gastroepiploic artery
description: Artery that runs from left to right along the greater curvature of the stomach, between the layers of the greater omentum, and anastomoses with the right gastroepiploic.

name: iliothoracic muscle
description: The iliothoracic group is made up of the abdominal wall muscles: rectus abdominis, external abdominal oblique, internal abdominal obliquus, and the transversus abdominis

name: scale pocket
description: A continuous flap of skin with scales implanted in pockets or invaginations. [Baldwin, CC and Johnson GD. 1996. Interrelationships of Aulopiformes. Pages 355-404 in MLJ Stiassny, LR Parenti, and DG Johnson, (eds.), Interrelationships of fishes. Academic Press, San Diego, CA.]

name: rib of vertebra 5
description: Rib that articulates with the parapophysis of the fifth centrum.

name: mesopodial skeleton
description: The collection of all skeletal elements in a mesopodium. Examples: the tarsal skeleton, the carpal skeleton

name: coronoid tooth
description: Tooth that is attached to a coronoid bone.

name: omohyoid muscle
description: The omohyoid muscle is a muscle at the front of the neck that consists of two bellies separated by an intermediate tendon. It belongs to the group of infrahyoid muscles. [WP,unvetted].

name: prothoracic leg
description: Leg of the prothoracic segment.

name: male genital tubercle
description: A differentiated genital tubercle that is part of a male reproductive system.

name: extrapyramidal tract system
description: A neural network located in the brain that is part of the motor system involved in the coordination of movement that is distinct from the pyramidal tract.

name: lamina IX of gray matter of spinal cord
heart ventricle wall
description: An anatomical wall that is part of a cardiac ventricle [Automatically generated definition].

name: ocular refractive media
description: Body substance in a liquid or semi-solid state in the eyeball which serves to refract light.

name: actinopterygian frontal-parietal joint
description: Fibrous joint connecting the actinopterygian frontal bone to the actinopterygian parietal bone.

name: pharyngeal epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a pharynx [Automatically generated definition].

name: extrahepatic duct
description: Bile duct that collects from the intrahepatic ducts and feeds into the common bile duct.

name: lens nucleus
description: The core of the crystalline lens, surrounded by the cortex.

name: epididymis smooth muscle
description: A portion of smooth muscle tissue that is part of a epididymis [Automatically generated definition].

name: keratin-coated spine
description: A modified strand of hair covered in a keratin coat, as found in porcupines and hedgehogs.

name: hindlimb endochondral element
description: A hindlimb bone or its cartilage or pre-cartilage precursor.

name: putamen
description: Subcortical nucleus of telencephalic , which together with the caudate nucleus, forms the striatum. The putamen lies lateral to the internal capsule and medial to the external medullary lamina, and is separated from the caudate nucleus by the fibers of the internal capsule for most of its length, except at its anterior portion.

name: foramen ovale of skull
description: one of the larger of the several holes at the base of the skull that transmit nerves through the skull. The foramen ovale is situated in the anterior part of the sphenoid bone, posteriolateral to the foramen rotundum..

name: deep inguinal ring
description: The entrance to the inguinal canal.

name: M. pulmonum proprius
description: Originates along the connective tissue covering the dorsal surface of the lung and inserts on the dorsal surface of the femur. Muscle found only in Pipa.

name: Brodmann (1909) area 14
description: Brodmann Area 14 is one of Brodmann's subdivisions of the cerebral cortex in the brain. It was defined by Brodmann in the guenon monkey. No equivalent structure exists in humans.

name: premaxillary-maxillary joint
description: Joint that articulates the premaxilla and maxilla. Premaxillary-maxillary joint is paired.

name: supraglenoid tubercle
description: The supraglenoid tubercle is a region of the scapula to which the long head of the biceps brachii muscle attaches.

name: ventral lateral nucleus of thalamus
description: The ventral lateral nucleus (VL) is a nucleus of the thalamus. [WP,unvetted].

name: uroneural 1
description: Uroneural that is the anteriormost element of the uroneural series.

name: pleurostyle
description: Postero-dorsal process of preural vertebra 1 or postero-dorsal process of the compound terminal centrum. The pleurostyle is a paired membrane bone.

name: patella
description: A large sesamoid bone found in the distal femur/proximal tibial region of the hindlimb of tetrapods. The patella is the attachment site for proximal hindlimb tendons.[PHENOSCAPE:ad]

name: pedal digit 5 phalanx pre-cartilage condensation
description: A pre-cartilage condensation that is part of a pedal digit 5 mesenchyme.

name: ingested food
description: A substance that is consumed by the organism for food.

name: parenchyma of parathyroid gland
description: A parenchyma that is part of a parathyroid gland [Automatically generated definition].

name: accessory lymph sac
description: An extracoelomic lateral abdominal space that accumulates body fluid.

name: cervical mucus
description: A substance produced by the cervix and endocervical glands[BTO]. Thick acidic mucus that blocks the cervical os after mestruation[WP]. This 'infertile' mucus blocks spermatozoa from entering the uterus.

name: digit 6
description: A digit that is part of a digit 6 plus metapodial segment.

name: femorotibial joint
description: One of the two primary bendings of a typical leg, pertains to the femur and the tibia.

name: scapular blade
description: Enlarged and broad extension of the scapula distal to the glenoid region that conforms to the contour of the ribs. Origin for the major shoulder muscles including the deltoid group.

name: lumbar vertebral foramen
description: A vertebral foramen that is part of a lumbar vertebra.

name: sclerotome somite 25
description: Medial ventral region of the somite that will form vertebral cartilages. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: styliform cartilage
description: A styloform element in a cartilaginous state.

name: epibranchial bone
description: Dorsal branchial arch bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with ceratobranchial cartilage or bone and medially with pharyngobranchial cartilage or bone.

name: cerebellum lobe
description: A major subdivision of the cerebellum: anterior, posterior and flocculonodular

name: ejaculatory duct epithelium
description: The ejaculatory duct epithelium is composed of cuboidal to columnar cells between or through which project the terminal parts of the ducts of the unicellular prostate glands.

name: posterior superior alveolar artery
description: The posterior superior alveolar artery (posterior dental artery) is given off from the maxillary, frequently in conjunction with the infraorbital just as the trunk of the vessel is passing into the pterygopalatine fossa.

name: tectal plate
description: embryologic structure that is formed by two longitudinal eminences, one on each alar plate of the midbrain. These eminences become the superior colliculus and inferior colliculus ( Carpenter-1983 )]

name: fourth ventricle lateral aperture
description: One of the two lateral openings of the fourth ventricle into the subarachnoid space at the cerebellopontine angle[MP].

name: outer fibrous layer of perichondrium
description: The perichondrium consists of two separate layers: an outer fibrous layer and inner chondrogenic layer. The fibrous layer contains fibroblasts, which produce collagenous fibers.

name: peritoneal vaginal process
description: A peritoneal diverticulum in the embryonic lower anterior abdominal wall that traverses the inguinal canal. In the male it forms the tunica vaginalis testis and normally loses its connection with the peritoneal cavity; a persistent processus vaginalis in the female is known as the canal of Nuck[MP].

name: renal interlobular vein
description: Any of the veins that parallel the interlobular arteries, receiving blood from the peritubular capillary plexus and empty into the arcuate veins

name: supraspinatus muscle
description: The supraspinatus is a relatively small muscle of the upper limb that takes its name from its origin from the supraspinous fossa superior to the spine of the scapula. It is one of the four rotator cuff muscles and also abducts the arm at the shoulder. The spine of the scapula separates the supraspinatus muscle from the infraspinatus muscle, which originates below the spine. [WP,unvetted].

name: trabecula carnea of atrium
description: The supporting bundles of muscular fibers lining the walls of the atria[MP].

name: distal phalanx of pes
description: A distal phalanx that is part of a pedal digit [Automatically generated definition].

name: cochlear nuclear complex
description: The cochlear nuclei consist of: (a) the dorsal cochlear nucleus, corresponding to the tuberculum acusticum on the dorso-lateral surface of the inferior peduncle; and (b) the ventral or accessory cochlear nucleus, placed between the two divisions of the nerve, on the ventral aspect of the inferior peduncle. [WP,unvetted].

name: hindbrain subarachnoid space
description: A subarachnoid space that is part of a hindbrain [Automatically generated definition].

name: pituitary stalk
description: the apical portion of the tubular structure extending from the hypothalamus to the posterior lobe of the pituitary gland

name: left anterior cardinal vein
description: A anterior cardinal vein that is in_the_left_side_of a multicellular organism.

name: left pelvic girdle region
description: A pelvic girdle region that is in the left side of a multicellular organism.

name: dorsal funiculus of spinal cord
description: the white substance of the spinal cord lying on either side between the posterior median sulcus and the dorsal root.

name: chitin-based cuticle
description: A cuticular covering that is composed primarily of chitin. The main structural component of arthropod cuticle is a polysaccharide, chitin, composed of N-acetylglucosamine units, together with proteins and lipids[WP].

name: kidney mesenchyme
description: Kidney mesenchyme is the tissue made up of loosely connected mesenchymal cells in the kidney[GO].

name: granular cell layer of dorsal cochlear nucleus
medial longitudinal fasciculus
description: The medial longitudinal fasciculus (MLF) is a pair of crossed fiber tracts, one on each side of the brainstem. These bundles of axons are situated near the midline of the brainstem and are composed of both ascending and descending fibers that arise from a number of sources and terminate in different areas. [WP,unvetted].

name: lumbar sympathetic nerve trunk
description: A sympathetic nerve trunk that is part of a lower back.

name: splanchnocranium
description: Subdivision of endoskeleton derived from pharyngeal arches

name: anterior mediastinal lymph node
description: A lymph node located in the superior mediastinum that collects lymph from the thymus, the pericardium, and the right side of the heart.

name: basibranchial series
description: Anatomical cluster that consists of the basibranchial elements within an individual.

name: infraclavicular region
description: The region below the clavicle.

name: presumptive floor plate
description: A presumptive structure that has the potential to develop into a floor plate.

name: paraventricular nucleus of the hypothalamus descending division - lateral parvicellular part
parasternal lymph node
description: Any of the lymph nodes of the breast located under the ribcage, near the sternum.

name: obsolete prezygapophyses
description: Anteriorly projecting processes allowing de facto contact between consecutive vertebrae (some soft tissues are also present) via articular facets. [PHENOSCAPE:NI]

name: digital artery
description: An artery that is part of a digit [Automatically generated definition].

name: distal epiphysis of distal phalanx of pedal digit 1
description: A distal epiphysis that is part of a distal phalanx of pedal digit 1.

name: fin bone
description: A bone that is part of a fin [Automatically generated definition].

name: thymic vein
description: A vein that drains blood from the thymus.

name: deep auricular artery
description: The deep auricular artery often arises in common with the anterior tympanic artery. It ascends in the substance of the parotid gland, behind the temporomandibular articulation, pierces the cartilaginous or bony wall of the external acoustic meatus, and supplies its cuticular lining and the outer surface of the tympanic membrane. It gives a branch to the temporomandibular joint.

name: rib 3
description: The third rib counting from the top of the rib cage down. Note that members of this class are not necessarily homologous[ncit,modified].

name: remnnant of ductus deferens
description: remnant in a female of the portion of the embryonic mesonephric duct that develops into the ductus deferens in males.

name: hippocampal sulcus
description: The hippocampal sulcus, also known as the hippocampal fissure, is a sulcus that separates the dentate gyrus from the subiculum and the CA1 field in the hippocampus. [WP,unvetted].

name: proximal epiphysis of first metatarsal bone
description: A proximal epiphysis that is part of a metatarsal bone of digit 1 [Automatically generated definition].

name: superior sagittal sinus
description: The superior sagittal sinus (also known as the superior longitudinal sinus), within a human cranium, is an area above/behind the brain, which allows blood veins to span the area, from the top of the head towards the back. It is believed that the cerebrospinal fluid drains through the arachnoid granulations into the dural venous sinuses of the superior sagittal sinus. [WP,unvetted].

name: neural spine 7
description: Neural spine that is associated with the seventh vertebra.

name: articular capsule of hip joint
description: An articular capsule that is part of the hip joint.

name: pedal digit
description: A digit that is part of a pes (foot).

name: head
description: The head is the anterior-most division of the body [GO].

name: rib of vertebra 8
description: Rib that articulates with the parapophysis of the eighth centrum.

name: external pudendal artery
description: Either the superficial or deep external pudendal arteries

name: centrum 2
description: Centrum that is part of vertebra 2.

name: skin of elbow
description: A zone of skin that is part of a elbow [Automatically generated definition].

name: nutrient foramen artery
description: The medullary or nutrient artery, usually accompanied by one or two veins, sends branches upward and downward to the bone marrow, which ramify in the medullary membrane, and give twigs to the adjoining canals.

name: nucleus lateralis valvulae
description: Hindbrain nucleus in the tegmental region of rhombomere 1. The cells of the nucleus are granular and lie at the ventral border of the cerebellum and brain stem.

name: anal fin actinotrichium
description: Actinotrichium that is part of the anal fin skeleton.

name: postcingulum
description: A shelf like ridge on the posterior (distal) outside edge of the upper molariform teeth. (modified from http://animaldiversity.ummz.umich.edu/collections/mammal_anatomy/cheek_teeth_structure/)

name: central tendon of diaphragm
description: the three-lobed cloverleaf-shaped aponeurosis situated at the center of the diaphragm; the central tendon is fused with the fibrous pericardium that provides attachment for the muscle fibers

name: future cardiac atrium
description: Multi-tissue structure that is part of the heart tube and will become the cardiac atrium.

name: pharyngobranchial 1 tooth plate
description: Pharyngeal tooth plate that lies ventral to pharyngobranchial 1 bone.

name: nasal process of premaxilla
description: A bony projection of the premaxilla that extends cadually and separates the nasal bones.

name: neural groove
description: The median dorsal longitudinal groove formed in the embryo by the neural plate after the appearance of the neural folds.

name: alisphenoid bone
description: either of the broad curved wing like expanses on each side of the sphenoid bone in adults; may exist independently in the young

name: mammary gland connective tissue
description: The fibrous supportive tissue of the mammary gland.

name: chemoarchitectural part of brain
description: Regional part of an anatomical region that is revealed by the use of a stain that reveals chemoarchitecture.

name: vermilion
description: The zone of the skin that surrounds a lip and is colored red due to thin epithelium and presence of eleidin

name: proximal carpal cartilage
description: A proximal carpal endochondral element that is composed primarily of cartilage tissue.

name: navicular fossa of spongiose part of urethra
description: The dilated terminal portion of the male spongy urethra located in the glans penis right before the external urethral orifice, also referred to as the most distal pendulous urethra; it is lined by stratified squamous, non-keratinizing epithelium; during development, the glans of the penis is initially solid but cannulates to give rise to the navicular fossa.

name: chest bone
description: A bone that is part of a chest [Automatically generated definition].

name: submucosa of trachea
description: A submucosa that is part of a trachea.

name: preopercle vertical limb-hyomandibula joint
description: Joint that articulates the anterior edge of the preopercle vertical limb and the hyomandibula.

name: skin of sole of pes
description: A zone of skin that is part of a skin of pes.

name: stratum spinosum of epidermis
description: the layer of polyhedral cells in the epidermis found between the stratum granulosum and stratum basale; shrinkage and adhesion of these cells gives a spiny or prickly appearance

name: basidorsal
description: Basidorsals are bilaterally paired cartilages on the dorsolateral side of the notochord which are replaced by ossified neural arches or dorsal arcocentra. In otophysan fishes, basidorsal 1, bd2, bd3, and bd4 give rise to parts of the Weberian apparatus.

name: uropropatagium
description: The membrane that is stretches between the legs of bats, used for flight, and in the case of insect-eating bats, for catching prey.

name: intrinsic muscle
description: Any of the muscles that are entirely within the body part or segment moved by them.

name: lateral vestibular nucleus
description: One of the nuclei comprising the vestibular nuclear complex. In some mammals, e.g., primates, it is further subdivided into subnuclei. It therefore differs in appearance and topology in different mammals.

name: caudal part of nephrogenic cord
description: The metanephros develops from the most caudal part of the nephrogenic cord that is itself derived from the intermediate plate mesoderm.

name: mineralized extracellular matrix
description: Extracellular matrix that is mineralized.

name: rhombomere 4 lateral wall
description: A rhombomere lateral wall that is part of a rhombomere 4.

name: vitelline duct
description: A long narrow tube that joins the yolk-sac to the midgut lumen of the developing fetus.

name: middle phalanx of manual digit 2
description: A middle phalanx that is part of a hand digit 2 [Automatically generated definition].

name: cardiac ganglion
description: Any of the parasympathetic ganglia of the cardiac plexus between the arch of the aorta and the bifurcation of the pulmonary artery.

name: inferior mesenteric artery
description: Mesenteric artery that supplies the large intestine from the left colic (or splenic) flexure to the upper part of the rectum, which includes the descending colon, the sigmoid colon, and part of the rectum. Proximally, its territory of distribution overlaps (forms a watershed) with the middle colic artery, and therefore the superior mesenteric artery. The SMA and IMA anastomose via the marginal artery (artery of Drummond). The territory of distribution of the IMA is more or less equivalent to the embryonic hindgut. [WP,unvetted].

name: ileal artery
description: The ileal arteries feed oxygenated blood into the ileum, a portion of the small intestine in mammals, reptiles, and birds. They are branches of the superior mesenteric artery.

name: iliac neck
description: A constricted region of the ilium which is dorsal to the acetabulular region. Prior to the expansion of the iliac blade.

name: lateral septal nucleus
description: Regional part of the septal nuclei, lying dorsal and slightly lateral to the medial septal nucleus. The lateral septum receives the bulk of projections of areas projecting to the septal nuclei (Adapted from Brodal, 1981).

name: common palmar digital artery
description: Three common palmar digital arteries arise from the convexity of the superficial palmar arch and proceed distally on the second, third, and fourth lumbricales muscles.

name: prominentia apicalis dorsalis
description: Anterior end of the arytenoid cartilage.

name: baroreceptor
description: The sensory nerve endings in the wall of the atria of the heart, vena cava, aortic arch and carotid sinus that are sensitive to changes in blood pressure

name: left adrenal gland
description: An adrenal gland that is in the left side of the abdomen

name: mushroom body
description: Prominent lobed neuropils found in annelids and all arthropods except crustaceans. They are thought to be involved in olfactory associative learning and memory[MESH] Mushroom body neuropils are divided into calyces, pedunculus, and its subsequent lobes. In Drosophila these are the alpha, beta, and gamma lobes.

name: solitary tract
description: The solitary tract is a compact fiber bundle that extends longitudinally through the posterolateral region of the medulla. The solitary tract is surrounded by the nucleus of the solitary tract, and descends to the upper cervical segments of the spinal cord. [WP,unvetted].

name: spatium intertarsale
description: Separation of the tibiale and fibulare along their longitudinal axia.

name: femorothoracic muscle
description: The femorospinal group is made up of the psoas major and iliacus muscles

name: aphakic space
description: The space in the pupil, which is not occupied by the lens. A rostral aphakic space may enhance the forward binocular field of vision.

name: pre-narial cartilage
description: The pre-narial cartilage is a cartilage that is located anterior to the anterior naris.

name: tarsal skeleton
description: Subdivision of skeleton that consists of endochondral elements distal to the zeugopodial skeletal elements which constitute the proximal region of the posterior autopod skeleton[PHENOSCAPE:ad].

name: carina of sternum
description: An extension of the sternum (breastbone) which runs axially along the midline of the sternum and extends outward, perpendicular to the plane of the ribs[WP].

name: keel
description: Ridge shaped projection, similar to the keel of a boat

name: sternothyroid muscle
description: The Sternothyreoideus (or Sternothyroid muscle) is shorter and wider than the Sternohyoideus, beneath which it is situated. It arises from the posterior surface of the manubrium sterni, below the origin of the Sternohyoideus, and from the edge of the cartilage of the first rib, and sometimes that of the second rib, it is inserted into the oblique line on the lamina of the thyroid cartilage. This muscle is in close contact with its fellow at the lower part of the neck, but diverges somewhat as it ascends; it is occasionally traversed by a transverse or oblique tendinous inscription. [WP,unvetted].

name: capillary plexus
description: A network of capillaries.

name: obsolete superficial feature part of hypophysis
quadrate-metapterygoid joint
description: Joint that articulates quadrate and metapterygoid bones. Quadrate-metapterygoid joint is paired.

name: malleus pre-cartilage condensation
description: A malleus endochondral element that is composed primarily of a pre-cartilage condensation.

name: future mouth
description: The primordial mouth region of the developing head.

name: obsolete regional part of trapezoid nuclear complex
stria medullaris
description: The major afferent track to the habenula from the telencephalon (particularly in the septal side) in all vertebrates[Butler and Hodos].

name: periallocortex
description: Agranular cortical structures located next to the allocortex.

name: respiratory system mucosa
description: the mucous membrane lining the respiratory tract

name: matrix part of tail of caudate nucleus
description: Matrix compartment located in the tail of the caudate nucleus

name: proper palmar digital artery
description: The proper palmar digital arteries travel along the sides of the phalanges (along the contiguous sides of the index, middle, ring, and little fingers), each artery lying just below its corresponding digital nerve. Alternative names for these arteries are: proper volar digital arteries, collateral digital arteries, arteriae digitales palmares propriae, or aa. digitales volares propriae. They anastomose freely in the subcutaneous tissue of the finger tips and by smaller branches near the interphalangeal joints. Each also gives off a couple of dorsal branches which anastomose with the dorsal digital arteries, and supply the soft parts on the back of the second and third phalanges, including the matrix of the fingernail. The proper palmar digital artery for the medial side of the little finger arises directly from the ulnar artery deep to the palmaris brevis muscle, but the rest arise from the common palmar digital arteries.

name: epithelium of midgut
description: An epithelium that is part of a midgut.

name: nerve ending of of corpus cavernosum maxillaris
leptomeninx
description: pia mater or arachnoid mater.

name: Tootell and Hadjikhani (2001) LOC/LOP complex
description: Cortical parcel in occipital cortex of human according to Tootell and Hadjikhani 2001 that is activated preferentially by more peripheral stimuli compared to the adjacent lateral occipital central parcel

name: barbed keratin-coated spine
description: A keratin-coated spine that is tipped with a barb.

name: phalanx endochondral element
description: A phalanx bone or its cartilage or pre-cartilage precursor.

name: globus pallidus
description: Subcortical nucleus, functionally part of the basal ganglia, which consists of two segments the external (or lateral) and internal (or medial) separated by the medial medullary lamina in primates. In rodents, The globus pallidus lateral is separated from the medial segment by the fibers of the internal capsule/cerebral peduncle.

name: skin of forearm
description: A zone of skin that is part of a lower arm [Automatically generated definition].

name: sensory root of facial nerve
description: The nervus intermedius, or intermediate nerve, is the part of the facial nerve (cranial nerve VII) located between the motor component of the facial nerve and the vestibulocochlear nerve (cranial nerve VIII). It contains the sensory and parasympathetic fibers of the facial nerve. Upon reaching the facial canal, it joins with the motor root of the facial nerve at the geniculate ganglion. [WP,unvetted].

name: right testicular vein
description: A vein that drains the left pampiniform plexus and empties into the left renal vein.

name: Brodmann (1909) area 15
description: Brodmann Area 15 is one of Brodmann's subdivisions of the cerebral cortex in the brain. Area 15 was defined by Brodmann in the guenon monkey, but he found no equivalent structure in humans. However, functional imaging experiments have found structures that may be homologous.

name: lateral geniculate body
description: the group of neurons that serve as the primary processor of visual information received from the retina via the optic tract and send processed information to the visual cortex of the occipital lobe

name: ural centrum
description: A vertebral centrum that is posterior to preural vertebra 1 and consequently the most posterior vertebral centra. Ural centrum is a unpaired median bone.

name: pedal digit phalanx pre-cartilage condensation
description: A pre-cartilage condensation that is part of a pedal digit mesenchyme.

name: bolus of food
description: Ingested food has been chewed at the point of swallowing.

name: obsolete natural killer cell
description: A lymphocyte that can spontaneously kill a variety of target cells without prior antigenic activation via germline encoded activation receptors and also regulate immune responses via cytokine release and direct contact with other cells.

name: sclerotome somite 29
description: Medial ventral region of the somite that will form vertebral cartilages. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: uterine ligament
description: Any of the eight ligaments pertaining to the uterus including the anterior, posterior, lateral, sacro-uterine and round ligaments.

name: colonic mucosa
description: Mucosa that is part of a colon. The mucosa of the colon is lined by a simple columnar epithelium with a thin brush border and numerous goblet cells.

name: embryonic lymph heart
description: A lymph heart that is part of an embryo

name: deep inguinal lymph node
description: One of several small inconstant lymph nodes, proximal, intermediate and distal deep to the fascia lata and medial to the femoral vein; they receive lymph from the deep structures of the lower limb, from the glans penis and from superficial inguinal nodes; efferents pass to the external iliac nodes.

name: sacral foramen
description: A vertebral foramen that is part of a sacral vertebra.

name: sclerotome somite 28
description: Medial ventral region of the somite that will form vertebral cartilages. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: right clavicle
description: A clavicle that is in the right side of a entire appendicular skeleton.

name: gonadal ridge
description: the elevation of thickened mesothelium and underlying mesenchyme found on the ventromedial border of the embryonic mesonephros in which the primordial germ cells become embedded, establishing it as the primordium of the testis or ovary

name: mammary gland myoepithelium
description: the outer cell layer of the mammary gland epithelium bilayer which is located basal to the luminal (secretory) cells and adjacent to the basement membrane.

name: interventricular foramen of CNS
description: The paired channels that connect the lateral and third ventricles and allows cerebrospinal fluid produced in the lateral ventricles to flow into the third ventricles

name: incisor dental lamina
description: A dental lamina that is part of a incisor tooth.

name: cerebellum vermis lobule VIIA
description: The folium vermis is a short, narrow, concealed band at the posterior extremity of the vermis, consisting apparently of a single folium, but in reality marked on its upper and under surfaces by secondary fissures. Laterally, it expands in either hemisphere into a considerable lobule, the superior semilunar lobule (lobulus semilunaris superior; postero-superior lobules), which occupies the posterior third of the upper surface of the hemisphere, and is bounded below by the horizontal sulcus. The superior semilunar lobules and the folium vermis form the lobus semilunaris.

name: temporal operculum
description: Part of temporal lobe overlaying the insular cortex

name: interstitial tissue
description: connective tissue between the cellular elements of a structure.

name: connective tissue
description: Tissue with cells that deposit non-polarized extracellular matrix including connective tissue fibers and ground substance.

name: sulcus dentalis of maxilla
description: Groove located between the pars dentalis and the bases of the maxillary teeth.

name: remnant of left anterior vena cava
obsolete predominantly gray regional part of orbital gyri complex
sural nerve
description: The sural nerve (short saphenous nerve), formed by the junction of the medial sural cutaneous with the peroneal anastomotic branch of the lateral sural cutaneous nerve, passes downward near the lateral margin of the tendo calcaneus, lying close to the small saphenous vein, to the interval between the lateral malleolus and the calcaneus. It runs forward below the lateral malleolus, and is continued as the lateral dorsal cutaneous nerve along the lateral side of the foot and little toe (via a dorsal digital nerve), communicating on the dorsum of the foot with the intermediate dorsal cutaneous nerve, a branch of the superficial peroneal. In the leg, its branches communicate with those of the posterior femoral cutaneous.

name: antitrochanter
description: Raised surface at the posterior portion of the acetabulum (see Nesbitt, 2011). [NI]

name: proximal phalanx of pes
description: A proximal phalanx that is part of a pedal digit [Automatically generated definition].

name: obsolete predominantly white regional part of red nucleus
dorsal trunk
description: The part of the trunk that is in the dorsum[cjm].

name: striatum
description: A region of the forebrain consisting of the caudate nucleus, putamen and fundus striati.[GO].

name: dorsal striatum
description: Dorsal components of the striatum comprising the caudate nucleus and the putamen, in species that have distinct nuclei; the caudoputamen in species which don't.

name: right anterior cardinal vein
description: A anterior cardinal vein that is in_the_right_side_of a multicellular organism.

name: vertebra cartilage element
description: The cartilaginous form of a vertebral element, a skeletal element that forms around the notochord and is part of the vertebral column.

name: corpora quadrigemina
description: Either of the two pairs of colliculi on the dorsal surface of the midbrain composed of white matter externally and gray matter within, the superior pair containing correlation centers for optic reflexes and the inferior pair containing correlation centers for auditory reflexes[BTO].

name: mesenchyme of interdigital region between digits 1 and 2
description: An interdigital region mesenchyme that is part of a interdigital region between digits 1 and 2.

name: masseteric nerve
description: A muscular branch of the mandibular nerve passing to the medial surface of the masseter muscle, which it innervates.

name: ocular segment
description: Head segment derived from the second embryonic segment (between the labral and antennal segments). In the larva, this segment includes Bolwig's organ.

name: medulla of organ
description: Middle part of an organ, surrounded by the cortex.

name: adductor muscle
description: A muscle capable of adduction. Adduction is a movement which brings a part of the anatomy closer to the middle sagittal plane of the body. It is opposed to abduction.

name: ceratobranchial 1 cartilage
description: Ceratobranchial cartilage that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with epibranchial 1 cartilage or bone.

name: tympanic membrane epithelium
description: One of the two epithelia which make up the tympanic membrane (along with the fibrous layer)

name: post-hyoid pharyngeal arch
description: A pharyngeal arch that is posterior to the hyoid arch. i.e. any pharyngeal arch with a number 3 or higher.

name: vertebral element 2
description: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 1.

name: great cerebral vein
description: The great cerebral vein is one of the large blood vessels in the skull draining the cerebrum (brain)[WP,unvetted]

name: presumptive bulbus arteriosus
description: A presumptive structure that has the potential to develop into a bulbus arteriosus.

name: pectoral fin radial cartilage
description: pectoral fin radial element that is composed of cartilage tissue.

name: ventral thalamus
description: Anterior part of the diencephalon that lies between the dorsal thalamus, hypothalamus, and tegmentum of the mesencephalon, including subthalamic nucleus, zona incerta, the fields of Forel, and the nucleus of ansa lenticularis[GO, modified].

name: left branch of atrioventricular bundle
description: The left branch of the atrioventricular bundle that separates at the bundle of His, descends the septal wall of the left ventricle and connects to the terminal Purkinje fiber[MP].

name: thagomizer
description: The distinctive arrangement of four to ten spikes on the tails of stegosaurid dinosaurs. These spikes are believed to have been a defensive measure against predators.

name: forelimb digital artery
description: A digital artery that is part of a forelimb [Automatically generated definition].

name: dentate nucleus
description: the largest and most lateral of the deep cerebellum nuclei; it receives axons of Purkinje cells in the lateral cerebellar hemisphere (neocerebellum) and receives its afferents from the premotor cortex and the supplementary motor cortex through the pontocerebellar system, and its efferents project through the superior cerebellar peduncle and is a major source of its fibers

name: distal epiphysis of distal phalanx of pedal digit 2
description: A distal epiphysis that is part of a distal phalanx of pedal digit 2.

name: distal metaphysis
description: A metaphysis that is in the distal side of a diaphysis.

name: bronchial vein
description: The bronchial veins are small vessels that return blood from the larger bronchi and structures at the roots of the lungs. The right side drains into the azygos vein, while the left side drains into the left superior intercostal vein or the accessory hemiazygos vein. The bronchial veins are counterparts to the bronchial arteries. The veins, however, do not return all of the blood supplied by the arteries; much of the blood that is carried in the bronchial arteries is returned to the heart via the pulmonary veins. [WP,unvetted].

name: infrapatellar fat pad
description: The infrapatellar fat pad, also known as Hoffa's fat pad, is a cylindrical piece of fat that is situated under and behind the patella bone within the knee.

name: pharyngeal arch artery 3
description: The vessels formed within the third pair of branchial arches in embryogenesis

name: anterior choroidal artery
description: The anterior choroidal artery originates from the internal carotid artery, though it also rarely arises from the middle cerebral artery.

name: mammillary body
description: One of two hemispherical bulges on the base of the posterior hypothalamus (Butler and Hodos, Comparative Vertebrate Neuroanatomy, 2nd ed., 2005, pg 455).

name: rib 4
description: The fourth rib counting from the top of the rib cage down. Note that members of this class are not necessarily homologous[ncit,modified].

name: proximal epiphysis of second metatarsal bone
description: A proximal epiphysis that is part of a metatarsal bone of digit 2 [Automatically generated definition].

name: oculomotor nerve
description: Cranial nerve which connects the midbrain to the extra-ocular and intra-ocular muscles.

name: buccopharyngeal complex
description: Anatomical cluster that is located in the oral cavity and consists of modifications to the skin on the roof of the mouth into three primary skin folds. In addition to these longitudinally oriented folds, secondary folds are present in some taxa.[PHENOSCAPE:WD]

name: transverse tarsal joint
description: The transverse tarsal joint is formed by the articulation of the calcaneus with the cuboid, and the articulation of the talus with the navicular. The movement which takes place in this joint is more extensive than that in the other tarsal joints, and consists of a sort of rotation by means of which the foot may be slightly flexed or extended, the sole being at the same time carried medially (inverted) or laterally.

name: shoulder
description: A subdivision of the pectoral complex consisting of the structures in the region of the shoulder joint (which connects the humerus, scapula and clavicle).

name: actinopterygian frontal bone
description: Dermal bone that bears part of the supraorbital canal and usually covers a large area of the neurocranium occupying part of the ethmoidal, orbitosphenoid, and otic regions. Commonly, the frontal bone articulates with its antimere medially, with lateral ethmoid, orbitosphenoid and pterosphenoid ventrolaterally, with supraorbital bone(s), autosphenotic and pterotic laterally, and with parietal posteriorly.[TAO].

name: tetrapod parietal bone
description: In humans: bone forming side and roof of cranium. Each bone is irregularly quadrilateral in form, and has two surfaces, four borders, and four angles.

name: coronary ligament of liver
description: The coronary ligament of the liver refers to parts of the peritoneal reflections that hold the liver to the inferior surface of the diaphragm.

name: centrum 3
description: Centrum that is part of vertebra 3.

name: skin of wrist
description: A zone of skin that is part of a wrist [Automatically generated definition].

name: infraorbital
description: Dermal bone that is located anterior, ventral or posterior to the eye. Infraorbital bones may or may not contain the infraorbital sensory canal. Infraorbital bones are numbered starting with the anteriormost element of the series.

name: lateral ventricle subependymal layer
description: A cell layer below the ependyma in the lateral ventricles of the brain. This region contains adult neural stem cells which have the potential to generate new neurons and glial cells via neurogenesis. It is an adult version of the embryonic forebrain germinal zone

name: posteroloph
description: A shelf like ridge on the outside of the upper molariform teeth. (modified from http://animaldiversity.ummz.umich.edu/collections/mammal_anatomy/cheek_teeth_structure/)

name: orbital fat pad
description: A fat pad that is part of a orbital region.

name: lateral line nerve
description: Cranial nerves that carry afferent and efferent fibers for the lateral line system.

name: ruminal fluid
description: A portion of organism substance that is produced a rumen.

name: valvula cerebelli
description: Brain structure which is caudally attached to the rostral medulla oblongata and extends into the tectal ventricle. The valvula cerebelli consists of a granular and a molecular layer along with aggregations of large Purkinje and eurydendroid cells and is uniquely present in ray-finned fishes. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

name: nuchal hump
description: Dorsal swelling on the head. Found in cichlid fish. Often only in males and during breeding season, but not exclusively so.

name: neural fold
description: One of the two elevated edges of the neural groove[GO,MP].

name: manubrium of malleus
description: The handle of the malleus; the portion that extends downward, inward, and backward from the neck of the malleus; it is embedded throughout its length in the tympanic membrane.

name: dermis connective tissue
description: A portion of connective tissue that is part of a dermis [Automatically generated definition].

name: obsolete predominantly gray regional part of neurohypophysis
accessory olfactory bulb mitral cell layer
middle cerebellar peduncle
description: Regional part of medullary white matter (according to Neuronames) primarily found at the level of the pons, consisting of a very large bundle of fibers originating in the pontine nuclei projecting to the cerebellum (MM).

name: hepatogastric ligament
description: Ligament extending between the liver and stomach

name: manual digit 2 phalanx
description: A phalanx that is part of a hand digit 2 [Automatically generated definition].

name: Gu√©rin's valve
description: An inconstant fold or valve of mucous membrane sometimes found in the root or upper wall of the navicular fossa of the urethra

name: frontomarginal sulcus
description: A superficial feature of the human frontal lobe; it is located at the rostral margin of the orbital surface of the lobe (Ono-90). (NN)

name: obsolete predominantly gray lateral regional part of thalamus
vasculature of eye
description: Vasculature that is part of the eye region.

name: enteric circular muscle
description: Smooth muscle of the enteric muscle system in which the cells are aligned perpendicular to the lumen of the gut.

name: coronoid process of ulna
description: A a triangular eminence projecting forward from the proximal epiphysis of the ulna[WP,modified].

name: stratum corneum of epidermis
description: the outer layer of the epidermis, consisting of several layers of flat keratinized non-nucleated cells

name: pes
description: distal portion of the hind limb, including tarsal region, metatarsal region and digits.

name: obsolete predominantly gray regional part of lateral hypothalamic region
calcar
description: A spur of cartilage arising from inner side of ankle and running along part of outer interfemoral membrane in bats

name: plantar pad
description: An autopod pad that is in the metatarsal region

name: central part of mediodorsal nucleus of the thalamus
dorsal fin distal radial element
description: Rod-like internal median skeletal support elements of the dorsal fin, which articulate with the lepidotrichia distally.

name: tympanic membrane
description: A thin membrane that separates the external ear from the middle ear, consisting of two epithelia (one part of the the external accoustic meatus epithelium, the other part of the tympanic cavity epithelium) with a fibrous layer between them. Its function is to transmit sound from the air to the ossicles inside the middle ear. The malleus bone bridges the gap between the eardrum and the other ossicles. Rupture or perforation of the eardrum can lead to conductive hearing loss. [WP,unvetted].

name: lower leg connective tissue
description: A portion of connective tissue that is part of a lower leg [Automatically generated definition].

name: muscle tissue of prostate
description: A muscle tissue that is part of a prostate gland.

name: rostral part of nephrogenic cord
description: The initial renal anlage that develops from the most rostral part of the nephrogenic cord is termed the pronephros.

name: obsolete proteinaceous extracellular matrix
description: A layer consisting mainly of proteins (especially collagen) and glycosaminoglycans (mostly as proteoglycans) that forms a sheet underlying or overlying cells such as endothelial and epithelial cells. The proteins are secreted by cells in the vicinity. An example of this component is found in Mus musculus. [GOC:mtg_sensu, ISBN:0198547684].

name: rhombomere 4 roof plate
description: A rhombomere roof plate that is part of a rhombomere 4.

name: dorsal longitudinal fasciculus of pons
description: Part of dorsal longitudinal fasciculus located within the pons

name: chorionic villus
description: One of the minute vascular projections of the fetal chorion that combines with maternal uterine tissue to form the placenta.

name: middle phalanx of manual digit 3
description: A middle phalanx that is part of a hand digit 3 [Automatically generated definition].

name: pectoral fin ray 6
description: Pectoral fin lepidotrichium that, in a linear sequence, is the sixth most anterior pectoral ray that it is usually branched and segmented.

name: occipital gyrus
description: A gyrus that is part of a occipital lobe.

name: outflow tract
description: The outflow tract is the portion of the heart through which blood flows into the arteries

name: deep circumflex iliac vein
description: A vein that corresponds to the deep circumflex iliac artery and empties near or in a common trunk with the inferior epigastric vein into the external iliac vein; deep circumflex iliac vein.

name: dorsal aorta
description: The dorsal aorta is a blood vessel in a single-pass circulatory system that carries oxygenated blood from the gills to the rest of the body. In a single-pass circulatory system blood passes once through the heart to supply the body once.

name: incisive process of premaxilla
description: A small protuberence on the lingual surface of the premaxilla, immediately posterior to the teeth.

name: renal fat pad
description: Encapsulated adipose tissue associated with the kidney

name: renal artery
description: One of two laterally paired arteries that supplies the kidneys. These are large arteries that branch from the dorsal aorta in primitive vertebrates.

name: vascular plexus
description: A vascular network formed by frequent anastomoses between the blood vessels (arteries or veins) of a part.

name: iliac peduncle
description: Bony projection that is part of the dorsal surface of the ischim, where it articulates with the ilium.

name: oculomotor nerve root
description: Initial segment of the occulomotor nerve as it leaves the midbrain.

name: epileon
description: Dorsal extremity of the ilial shaft, which remains cartilaginous.

name: basilic vein
description: A superficial vein of the upper limb that drain parts of manus and forearm.

name: intermediate layer of tympanic membrane
description: The intermediate fibrous layer of the tympanic membrane.

name: prominentia apicalis ventralis
description: Posterior (cardiac) end of the arytenoid cartilage.

name: adrenal cortex
description: the thick outer layer of the adrenal gland that produces and secretes steroid hormones such as corticosterone, estrone and aldosterone

name: pars intercerebralis
description: A neurosecretory center of the insect brain, located along the anterior midline[wiktionary]. A medial cleft or depression dividing the left and right protocerebrum and containing numerous large and small somata of neurosecretory and neuromodulatory neurons[FBbt].

name: spino-olivary tract
