description: A vertebrate nasal chemosensory system that is responsible for detecting intraspecific pheromonal cues as well as environmental odorants

name: nail of manual digit 4
description: A nail that is part of a manual digit 4.

name: accessory nerve fiber bundle
description: Fibers of the accessory nerve (11th cranial nerve) contained within the medulla

name: pharyngobranchial 2 tooth
description: Tooth that is attached to the pharyngobranchial 2 tooth plate.

name: pleural sac
description: A serous sac that has the pleura and the pleural cavity as parts.

name: sublingual dorsal ossification
description: Sublingual that is the dorsal element paired with the sublingual ventral ossification.

name: renal system
description: The renal system in an anatomical system that maintains fluid balance and contributes to electrolyte balance, acid/base balance, and disposal of nitrogenous waste products..

name: fibular nerve
description: Any nerve that innervates the fibularis. Includes the common fibular nerve, and its branches

name: osphradium
description: The osphradium is the olfactory organ in certain molluscs, linked with the respiration organ. The main function of this is to test incoming water for silt and other possible food particles. It is used by all members of the Genus Conus.

name: hypobranchial 3 cartilage
description: Hypobranchial cartilage that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with ceratobranchial 3 cartilage or bone.

name: hindlimb zeugopod
description: The middle limb segment of the pelvic free limb, between the autopod and stylopod segments. Includes as parts the hindlimb zeugopodial skeleton, which includes as parts the tibia and fibula, or their cartilage precursors, or evolutionary variants.

name: lateral nasal cartilage
description: The lateral cartilage (upper lateral cartilage) is situated below the inferior margin of the nasal bone, and is flattened, and triangular in shape.[WP].

name: future meninx
description: A developing mesenchymal capsule that covers the developing brain and spinal cord and is the precursor of the meningeal cluster. In mammals this gives rise to the arachnoid mater, pia mater and dura mater. In cyclostomes and fishes, the future meninx gives rise to a single meningeal layer, the primitive meninx.

name: bulbo-ventricular groove
description: depression at base of developing heart that contains a population of cardiomyocytes that migrate and contribute to the interventricular septum

name: adult tagma
description: Any tagma (UBERON:6000002) that is part of some adult (UBERON:6003004).

name: white matter of parietal lobe
description: A white matter of cerebral lobe that is part of a parietal lobe.

name: epithelium of female gonad
description: An epithelium surrounding an ovary.

name: neural plate
description: A region of embryonic ectodermal cells that lie directly above the notochord. During neurulation, they change shape and produce an infolding of the neural plate (the neural fold) that then seals to form the neural tube[XAO]. The earliest recognizable dorsal ectodermal primordium of the central nervous system present near the end of gastrulation before infolding to form the neural keel; consists of a thickened pseudostratified epithelium[ZFA]

name: archenteron
description: The cavity of a gastrula forming a primitive gut.

name: neocortex
description: An area of cerebral cortex defined on the basis of cytoarchitecture that have six layers. Starting from the cortical surface the layers are: molecular layer (I), external granular layer (II), external pyramidal layer (III), internal granular layer (IV), internal pyramidal layer (V), and multiform layer (VI). Neocortex is most prominent in the frontal lobe, the parietal lobe, the temporal lobe and the occipital lobe, less so in the cingulate gyrus, the parahippocampal gyrus and the insula. It is composed of two subdivisions: true isocortex and proisocortex (Carpenter-83)(NN)

name: dorsal fin proximal radial cartilage 2
description: dorsal fin proximal radial 2 element that is composed of cartilage tissue.

name: skeletal muscle of trunk
description: A skeletal muscle organ that is part of the trunk region.

name: roof plate of metencephalon
description: A roof plate that is part of a metencephalon [Automatically generated definition].

name: temporalis muscle
description: Pharyngeal arch 1 muscle that is innervated by the deep temporal branches of the trigeminal nerve and attaches to the wall of the braincase (including the cranial vault) and mandible.

name: periodontium
description: The tissues that invest or help to invest and support the teeth, including the periodontal ligament, gingivae, cementum, and alveolar and supporting bone[BTO].

name: lower secondary molar tooth
description: A secondary molar tooth that is part of a lower jaw region.

name: trachea
description: The trachea is the portion of the airway that attaches to the bronchi as it branches [GO:dph].

name: throat
description: In anatomy, the throat is the anterior part of the neck, in front of the vertebral column. It consists of the pharynx and larynx. An important feature of the throat is the epiglottis, a flap which separates the esophagus from the trachea and prevents inhalation of food or drink. The throat contains various blood vessels, various pharyngeal muscles, the trachea (windpipe) and the esophagus. The hyoid bone and the clavicle are the only bones located in the throat of mammals. It is sometimes considered a synonym for fauces. [WP,unvetted].

name: epithelium of crypt of Lieberkuhn of small intestine
pterygomaxillary fissure
description: The pterygomaxillary fissure is a fissure of the human skull. It is vertical, and descends at right angles from the medial end of the inferior orbital fissure; it is a triangular interval, formed by the divergence of the maxilla from the pterygoid process of the sphenoid. It connects the infratemporal with the pterygopalatine fossa, and transmits the terminal part of the maxillary artery. Alveolar branches of the maxillary nerve go from the pterygopalatine fossa to the infratemporal region via this fissure. In older texts, the pterygomaxillary fissure is sometimes called the pterygopalatine fissure.

name: ural centrum 3
description: A vertebral centrum that is located immediately posterior to ural centrum 2 (polyural terminology). Ural centrum 3 articulates with hypural 3 ventrally. Ural centrum 3 is an unpaired median bone.

name: mouth
description: The proximal portion of the digestive tract, containing the oral cavity and bounded by the oral opening. In vertebrates, this extends to the pharynx and includes gums, lips, tongue and parts of the palate. Typically also includes the teeth, except where these occur elsewhere (e.g. pharyngeal jaws) or protrude from the mouth (tusks).

name: left pulmonary vein
description: Vein that drains left lung and returns blood to the heart.

name: paranasal sinus
description: the paired air-filled cavities surrounded by the bones of the face that are lined by mucous membranes and are continuous with the nasal cavity

name: glossopharyngeal nerve
description: Cranial nerve that branches into the ramus communicans (to the skin), the pretrematic (to the walls of the pharynx and mouth, viscero-sensory fibers), and the larval post-trematic branch (lost in the adult).

name: hindlimb stylopod
description: The part of the hindlimb between pelvis and the knee, corresponding to the femur.

name: epitheliochorial placenta
description: A placenta in which all three maternal layers are retained.

name: obsolete superficial feature part of parietal cortex
wrist joint
description: A joint connecting the forelimb zeugopod skeleton with the carpal skeleton.

name: radio-carpal joint
description: A skeletal joint that connects a radius bone and connects a carpal skeleton.

name: pelvic fin skeleton
description: Paired fin skeleton located in the abdominal position that consists of supporting endochondral radialsB and dermal fin rays or lepidotrichia.

name: pedal digit 6 plus metapodial segment
description: A subdivision of the autopod consisting of pedal digit 6 plus the region incorporating a single metapodial element. These segments are typically repeated along the pre-axiom to post-axial axis.

name: primitive metanephric nephron
description: A primitive nephron that is part of a metanephros.

name: infrahyoid muscle
description: The infrahyoid muscles are a group of four pairs of muscles in the anterior part of the neck. (The term infrahyoid refers to the region below to the hyoid bone in the neck. ) Collectively, they are referred to as the strap muscles, because the muscles are long and flat much like a strap.

name: pharyngeal arch mesenchyme from neural crest
description: Mesenchyme that develops_from a neural crest and is part of a entire pharyngeal arch associated mesenchyme.

name: preural vertebra
description: Caudal vertebra that is one of the last caudal vertebrae anterior to the ural vertebrae that with its neural and haemal spines supports the procurrent caudal fin rays or lepidotrichia. The numbering of preural vertebrae is from caudal to rostral direction.

name: posterior macula
description: Patches of thickened, pseudostratified epithelium of the inner ear, consisting of regular arrays of sensory hair cells interspersed with supporting cells. Each patch has its own charcteristic shape and polarity pattern. (See Anatomical Atlas entry for sensory patches of the ear by T. Whitfield.)

name: ethmoidal artery
description: One of: anterior or posterior ethmoidal arteries.

name: pectoral fin distal radial cartilage 1
description: pectoral fin distal radial 1 element that is composed of cartilage tissue.

name: oviduct albumen gland
description: A gland in the glandular region of the oviduct that secretes albumen over the ovum. In birds there are two regions of the oviduct, the first secretes a thin chalaziferous albumen layer, the second secretes a thicker albumen layer.

name: renal cortex tubule
description: A region of nephron tubule that is part of a cortex of kidney.

name: resorption pit
description: A pit formed in an existing functional tooth, causing resorption of the surrounding dentine and periodontal tissues. (modified from LeBlanc and Reisz 2013, see figures 8, 10 for more details)

name: surface of epithelium
description: An anatomical boundary that adjacent_to a epithelium.

name: pelvic fin bud
description: A paired fin bud that develops into a pelvic fin.

name: pelvic appendage bud
description: A limb bud that develops into a hindlimb or pelvic fin.

name: lobar bronchus of right lung cranial lobe
head mesenchyme from mesoderm
description: A head mesenchyme that develops_from a mesoderm.

name: neural rod
description: A solid rod of neurectoderm derived from the neural keel. The neural rod is roughly circular in cross section. Neural rod formation occurs during primary neurulation in teleosts[GO]. An intermediate stage in the development of the central nervous system present during the segmentation period; the neural rod is roughly cylindrical in shape, forms from the neural keel, and is not yet hollowed out into the neural tube[ZFIN].

name: nail matrix
description: Portion of tissue (or germinal matrix) upon which the nail rests, the part of the nail bed that extends beneath the nail root and contains nerves, lymph and blood vessels. The matrix is responsible for the production of the cells that become the nail plate. The width and thickness of the nail plate is determined by the size, length, and thickness of the matrix, while the shape of the fingertip itself determines if the nail plate is flat, arched, or hooked. The matrix will continue to grow as long as it receives nutrition and remains in a healthy condition. As new nail plate cells are incubated, they emerge from the matrix round and white to push older nail plate cells forward; and in this way yet older cells become compressed, flat, and translucent, making the pink colour of the capillaries in the nail bed below visible[WP].

name: nose vertex
description: The extreme point of curvature of the external nose.

name: skeletal joint
description: Anatomical cluster that consists of two or more adjacent skeletal structures, which may be interconnected by various types of tissue[VSAO].

name: anterior fontanel
description: In humans, the anterior fontanelle (bregmatic fontanelle, frontal fontanelle) is the largest, and is placed at the junction of the sagittal suture, coronal suture, and frontal suture; it is lozenge-shaped, and measures about 4 cm in its antero-posterior and 2.5 cm in its transverse diameter. The fontanelle allows the skull to deform during birth to ease its passage through the birth canal and for expansion of the brain after birth. While the posterior and lateral fontanelles are obliterated by about six months after birth, the anterior is not completely closed until about the middle of the second year. Full ossification starts in the late twenties and finishes before the age of 50 . [WP,unvetted].

name: metanephric glomerular mesangium
description: The metanephric glomerular mesangium is the thin membrane connective tissue composed of mesangial cells in the metanephros, which helps to support the capillary loops in a renal glomerulus[GO].

name: submandibular duct
description: the duct of the submadibular gland that opens at the sublingual papilla near the frenulum of the tongue

name: nasal fin
description: The nasal fin is an epithelial seam that develops by fusion between the epithelial linings of the medial and lateral nasal swellings. Shortly after its formation the nasal fin regresses and is replaced by mesenchyme, with exception of its most posterior portion which remains as the bucconasal membrane.

name: principal inferior olivary nucleus
description: The inferior olivary nucleus that consists of the major laminar structure.

name: supraneural 3 bone
description: Supraneural bone that is located dorsal to vertebrae 3 and 4.

name: dorsal part of neck
description: The posterior region of the neck, including the suboccipital region.

name: mastoid process of temporal bone
description: The mastoid process is a conical prominence projecting from the undersurface of the mastoid portion of the temporal bone. It is located just behind the external acoustic meatus, and lateral to the styloid process. Its size and form vary somewhat; it is larger in the male than in the female. This process serves for the attachment of the posterior belly of the digastric, sternocleidomastoid, splenius capitis, and longissimus capitis muscles. The word is derived from the Greek 'masto-', alluding to its resemblance to the breast.

name: cutaneus artery
description: Artery which supplies blood to the thymus and parotoid region.

name: fibrous joint
description: Nonsynovial joint in which the articulating bones or cartilages are connected by ligaments. Examples: sagittal suture, inferior tibiofibular syndesmosis, gomphosis.[FMA]

name: pars interna plectri
description: Plate-like structure that lies in the fenestra ovalis. It arises within the membrana opercularis in the posterior part of the fenestra.

name: epibranchial 1 bone
description: Epibranchial bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with ceratobranchial 1 cartilage or bone and medially with pharyngobranchial cartilage or bone.

name: M. coracoradialis
description: Muscle which originates from the omosternum and epicoracoid cartilage and inserts on the proximal radioulna.

name: hippocampal commissure
description: the triangular subcallosal plate of commissural fibers resulting from the converging of the right and left fornix bundles which exchange numerous fibers and which curve back in the contralateral fornix to end in the hippocampus of the opposite side

name: ventral posterior nucleus of thalamus
description: Part of thalamus receiving primary somatic sensory information via the medial lemniscal pathway that projects to the primary somatosensory cortex (adapted from Paxinos, The Rat Nervous System, 2nd Ed, Academic Press, 1995).

name: presumptive embryonic/larval system
description: The sum of all the developing presumptive components of a specific embryonic/larval system in an embryo.

name: pericardial visceral mesothelium
description: A visceral mesothelium that is part of a pericardium.

name: skeletal ligament
description: Dense regular connective tissue connecting two or more adjacent skeletal elements[VSAO,modified].

name: urogenital papilla
description: A protuberance in front of the gential pore and behind the vent. Mature females have a well developed urogenital papillae whilst in mature males it is poorly developed. Brion et al, 2004.

name: nucleus of pontine reticular formation
description: A nucleus of brain that is part of a pontine reticular formation.

name: diastema between incisors
description: A space or gap any two incisors. This may be a midline diastema between central incisors, or a diastema located entirely in a single jaw quadrant between lateral incisors.

name: raphe of scrotum
description: A ridge of tissue that extends along the midline of the scrotum.

name: carpal region
description: A mesopodium that is part of a manus. Includes as parts the carpal skeleton and associated tissues[cjm]. The anatomical region surrounding the carpus including the distal parts of the bones of the forearm and the proximal parts of the metacarpus or five metacarpal bones and the series of joints between these bones, thus referred to as wrist joints. This region also includes the carpal tunnel, the anatomical snuff box, the flexor retinaculum, and the extensor retinaculum[WP,unvetted]

name: fourth ventricle choroid plexus epithelium
description: A choroid plexus epithelium that is part of a fourth ventricle [Automatically generated definition].

name: paraventricular nucleus of the hypothalamus descending division - medial parvicellular part, ventral zone
skeletal muscle tissue of digastric
description: A portion of skeletal muscle tissue that is part of a digastric [Automatically generated definition].

name: right lateral ventricle
description: A telencephalic ventricle that is in_the_right_side_of a telencephalon.

name: middle phalanx of pedal digit 5
description: A middle phalanx that is part of a pedal digit 5 [Automatically generated definition].

name: inguinal lymph node
description: the lymph nodes located in the groin area

name: nucleus K of ventral tegmentum
description: A nucleus present in the ventral tegmentum of skates.

name: aorta collagen fibril
description: The connective tissue bundles in the extracellular matrix of aorta tissue that are composed of collagen, and play a role in tissue strength and elasticity

name: parietal peritoneum
description: The outer layer of peritoneum that is attached to the abdominal and pelvic walls.

name: preorbitalis muscle
description: A jaw muscle arises near the orbit and tapers as it passes posteriorly to its insertion on the adductor mandibulae. Found in sharks.

name: ossicone
description: Ossicones are horn-like protuberances on the heads of giraffes, male okapis, and their extinct relatives, such as Sivatherium, and the climacoceratids, such as Climacoceras. Only giraffids have true ossicones (as opposed to horns or antlers). The base that a deer's antlers grow from is very similar to ossicones. Ossicones are similar to the horns of antelopes and cattle, save that they are derived from ossified cartilage, and that the ossicones remain covered in skin and fur, rather than horn. Antlers (such as on deer) are derived from bone tissue: when mature, the skin and fur covering of the antlers, termed 'velvet,' is sloughed and scraped off to expose the bone of the antlers.

name: lingual region
description: The region of an anatomical structure (such as a tooth or jaw bone) facing the tongue. [PHENOSCAPE:WD]

name: 1st arch mandibular mesenchyme from neural crest
description: Mesenchyme that develops_from a neural crest and is part of a 1st arch mandibular mesenchyme.

name: accessory neural arch
description: Neural arch that is located posterior to the neurocranium and anterior to neural arch 1. The accessory neural arch is not associated with a vertebral centrum.

name: skin of neck
description: A zone of skin that is part of a neck [Automatically generated definition].

name: network of trabecular spaces in bone tissue
description: Tissue cavity consisting of intercommunicating trabecular spaces in the cancellous bone.

name: extraembryonic epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a extraembryonic structure.

name: oral disk
description: Lip that is expanded to form a broad, rounded cup around the mouth.

name: trabecula carnea of right ventricle
description: A trabecula carnea that is part of a heart right ventricle.

name: future dorsal motor nucleus of vagus
description: A gray matter that has the potential to develop into a dorsal motor nucleus of vagus nerve.

name: prime adult stage
description: A life cycle stage that starts at completion of development and growth of the sexually mature adult animal, and ends before senescence.

name: pancreas left lobe
description: A pancreatic lobule that is in_the_left_side_of a exocrine pancreas.

name: eyelid muscle
description: A muscle that attaches to an eyelid.

name: eye sebaceous gland
description: A sebaceous gland that is part of a camera-type eye. Example: a tarsal gland.

name: mucosa of left uterine tube
description: A mucosa that is part of a left uterine tube [Automatically generated definition].

name: right renal pelvis
description: A renal pelvis that is part of a right ureter.

name: epithelium of bronchiole
description: An epithelium that is part of a bronchiole [Automatically generated definition].

name: brachiocephalic vein
description: The left and right brachiocephalic veins in the upper chest are formed by the union of each corresponding internal jugular vein and subclavian vein. This is at the level of the sternoclavicular joint. These great vessels merge to form the superior vena cava. The brachiocephalic veins are the major veins returning blood to the superior vena cava.

name: Ongur, Price, and Ferry (2003) area Iai
conjunctival space
description: A anatomical space that is enclosed by a conjunctiva.

name: vagus X nerve trunk
description: A nerve trunk that is part of a vagus nerve.

name: superior intercostal vein
description: The superior intercostal veins are two veins that drain the 2nd, 3rd, and 4th intercostal spaces, one vein for each side of the body.

name: epithelium of submandibular gland
description: An epithelium that is part of a submandibular gland [Automatically generated definition].

name: forelimb
description: A (free) limb that is connected to a pectoral girdle. The extent of this structure includes autopod, stylopod and zeugopod regions when present, but excludes the pectoral girdle and its parts.

name: anatomical line between inner canthi
description: An anatomical line of the face that connects the two inner (medial) canthi of the eye. The length of this line is known as the inter canthal distance.

name: median external naris
description: Am unpaired external naris that lies in the midline of the head.

name: cartilage tissue of sternum
description: Any portion of cartilage tissue that is part of the sternum

name: urodeum
description: Cloacal compartment into which the urogenital system empties[Kardong]

name: esophagus mucosa
description: A mucosa that is part of a esophagus [Automatically generated definition].

name: obsolete superficial feature part of pons
silk
description: A protein fiber composed mainly of fibroin and produced by certain arthropods[WP,modified].

name: manual major digit (Aves) plus metapodial segment
description: A subdivision of the autopod consisting of manual major digit (Aves) plus the region incorporating a single metapodial element. These segments are typically repeated along the pre-axiom to post-axial axis.

name: posterior digastric muscle
description: The posterior digastric is a pharyngeal arch II muscle that participates in oral pharyngeal behavior, is innervated by the digastric branch of facial nerve and attaches to the posterior cranial base and the hyoid apparatus. It is found superficial to the mylohyoid muscle.

name: obsolete pigment cell
description: Cell type that contains a deposition of coloring matter.

name: sagittal sulcus
description: A sulcus that lies within the longitudinal fissure.

name: pelvic fin distal radial bone
description: Pelvic fin radial that develops from the pelvic fin endoskeletal disc. Pelvic fin distal radials are paired.

name: webbed interdigital region between manual digits
description: A webbed interdigital region that is part of a manus.

name: upper jaw molar epithelium
description: A dental epithelium that is part of a upper jaw molar.

name: stomach fundus epithelium
description: A simple columnar epithelium that is part of a fundus of stomach.

name: cardiogenic splanchnic mesoderm
description: The splanchnic mesoderm in the cardiogenic region where the heart develops; it gives rise to endocardial heart tubes that fuse to form the primordial cardiac tube, the heart primordium[web]. Two migratory heart primordia that move ventrally during the course of neurulation, and then fuse[XAO].

name: large intestine smooth muscle
description: A portion of smooth muscle tissue that is part of a large intestine [Automatically generated definition].

name: liver blood vessel
description: A blood vessel that is part of a liver.

name: anterior visceral endoderm
description: The extraembryonic tissue that is responsible for the proper orientation of the anterior-posterior axis of the embryo and for appropriate patterning of adjacent embryonic tissue

name: secondary palatal shelf mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a developing secondary palatal shelf.

name: myocardium of ventricle
description: Muscular layer of the cardiac ventricle composed of a compact myocardial layer surrounding the trabecular layer.

name: basal forebrain
description: A region of the brain consisting of ventral and rostral subcortical regions of the telencephalon, including among others, the basal ganglia, septal nuclei, amygdala, ventral pallidum, substantia innominata, and basal nucleus of Meynert.

name: upper left incisor tooth
description: A upper jaw incisor that is in_the_left_side_of a dentition.

name: basal part of pons
description: Ventral subdivision of the pons which consists of the massive pontine pertuberance on pontine ventral surface.

name: umbilical artery
description: The umbilical artery is a paired artery (with one for each half of the body) that is found in the abdominal and pelvic regions. In the fetus, it extends into the umbilical cord. [WP,unvetted].

name: obsolete supraoccipital
description: Median, unpaired bone that can form the dorsal margin of the foramen magnum.

name: skeletal muscle tissue
description: Muscle tissue that consists primarily of skeletal muscle fibers.

name: supinator process
description: A bony process that corresponds to the attachment site for the forelimb supinator muscles in tetrapods, distal to the deltopectoral crest and anterior to the radial condyle.

name: embryonic tagma
description: Any tagma (UBERON:6000002) that is part of some embryo (UBERON:6000052).

name: sternal head of coracoid
description: Medial end of the coracoid, which is synchondrotically fused to the epicoracoid cartilage.

name: neurogenic placode
description: Cranial ectodermal placode with potential to develop into a component of the nervous system, such as nerves or ganglia.

name: nail of manual digit 5
description: A nail that is part of a manual digit 5.

name: tubotympanic recess epithelium
description: The dorsal portion of the embryonic first endodermal pharyngeal pouch; it develops into the middle ear cavity.

name: pharyngobranchial 3 tooth plate
description: Pharyngeal tooth plate that lies ventral to pharyngobranchial 3 bone.

name: zygomatic ramus of squamosal
description: Ramus (process) that projects anteriorly from the dorsal body of the squamosal and forms part of the posterior margin of the orbit.

name: cardiac muscle tissue of right auricle
description: A cardiac muscle tissue that is part of a right atrium auricular region.

name: sublingual ventral ossification
description: Sublingual that is the ventral element paired with the sublingual dorsal ossification.

name: circulatory system
description: organ system that passes nutrients (such as amino acids and electrolytes), gases, hormones, blood cells, etc. to and from cells in the body to help fight diseases and help stabilize body temperature and pH to maintain homeostasis[WP].

name: epidermis gland
description: A gland that is part of a epidermis.

name: lower inner quadrant of breast
description: The quarter of the breast which is inferior and medial.

name: lamina propria of prostatic urethra
description: A lamina propria that is part of a prostatic urethra.

name: epibranchial cartilage
description: Pharyngeal arch cartilage that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with ceratobranchial cartilage or bone.

name: vomeronasal cartilage
description: The vomeronasal cartilage (or Jacobson's cartilage) is a narrow strip of cartilage, low on the medial wall of the nasal cavity. It lies between the cartilaginous nasal septum and the vomer. The cartilage lies below, but is not connected to, the rudimentary vomeronasal organ of Jacobson[WP].

name: endomeninx
description: The innermost layer of the mesenchymal capsule that surrounds the developing brain, primarily of neural crest origin. The endomeninx forms the leptomeninx.

name: right lung alveolus
description: An alveolus that is part of a right lung [Automatically generated definition].

name: obsolete middle temporal area
description: The term "middle temporal visual area" was first used by Allman and Kaas (1971) for a region of the owl monkey brain located on the "caudal third of the middle temporal gyrus." Functionally, it contains "a complete representation of the contralateral half of the visual field... This representation of the visual field (MT) corresponds to a histologically distinct area adjacent and rostral to area 19... The horizontal meridian divides MT into a lateral portion representing the upper visual quadrant and a medial portion representing the lower quadrant. The center of gaze is represented in the caudal portion of MT bordering area 19."

name: carpus cartilage element
description: A cartilaginous condensation that has the potential to develop into a carpal bone.

name: adult segment
description: Segment of the adult.

name: thoracic rib cage
description: Subdivision of skeletal system that consists of all ribs in an organism connected to the sternum and the vertebrae. Some vertebrates have abdominal ribs (gastrialia), not connected to the vertebrate - these are not considered part of the rib case.

name: hepatic diverticulum
description: An out-pocket of thickened ventral foregut epithelium adjacent to the developing heart. Constitutes the first morphological sign of the embryonic liver. The anterior portion of the hepatic diverticulum gives rise to the liver and intrahepatic biliary tree, while the posterior portion forms the gall bladder and extrahepatic bile ducts.

name: metanephric glomerulus
description: glomerulus of the mature vertebrate kidney, or metanephros.

name: epithelium of nasopharynx
description: An epithelium that is part of a nasopharynx [Automatically generated definition].

name: ciliary body
description: the thickened portion of the vascular tunic, which lies between the choroid and the iris, composed of ciliary muscle and ciliary processes

name: roof plate of medulla oblongata
description: A roof plate that is part of a medulla oblongata [Automatically generated definition].

name: stapedius muscle
description: The muscle that stabilizes the stapes bone. The stapedius emerges from a pinpoint foramen in the apex of the pyramidal eminence (a hollow, cone-shaped prominence in the posterior wall of the tympanic cavity), and inserts into the neck of the stapes. [WP,unvetted].

name: manual autopod pad
description: A autopod pad that is part of a manus.

name: open tracheal system trachea
description: A respiratory airway that is part of an open tracheal system.

name: epithelium of crypt of Lieberkuhn of large intestine
ural centrum 4
description: A vertebral centrum that is located immediately posterior to ural centrum 3 (polyural terminology) and may fuse to ural centrum 3 early in ontogeny. Ural centrum 4 articulates with hypural 4 ventrally. Ural centrum 4 is an unpaired median bone.

name: oral opening
description: The orifice that connects the mouth to the exterior of the body.

name: nasal cavity mucosa
description: The mucous membrane that lines the nasal cavity[MP].

name: renal parenchyma
description: The functional tissue of the kidney, consisting of the nephrons.

name: endotheliochorial placenta
description: A placenta in which the only maternal layer retained is the uterine endothelium.

name: mesotarsal joint
description: An ankle joint that passes between the proximal and distal tarsals.

name: limb skeleton subdivision
description: Skeletal subdivision that is a segment of the limb skeleton.

name: pallium
description: Dorsal part (roof region) of the telencephalon[GO].

name: transverse process of neural arch 3
description: Endochondral bone that is the anterodorsally oriented process of the third neural arch.

name: clitoral smooth muscle
description: A smooth muscle tissue that is part of a clitoris.

name: hemal postzygapophysis
description: Paired, ventromedially directed processes on the posterior ends of the centra, ligamentously joined to the hemal postzygapophyses of the immediately posterior vertebra. The most posterior caudal vertebrae lack hemal postzygapophyses.

name: annelid peristomium
description: The peristomium is the second body segment in an annelid worm's body in the anterior end. It is directly behind the prostomium and contains the mouth, tentacular cirri, and sometimes feeding palps, which may instead occur on the prostomium. If an eversible pharynx is present, it is contained in this segment as well, and can fill up to 20 segments when inverted, depending on the species.

name: hippocampus stratum lacunosum
description: A thin stratum in the hippocampus that is immediately deep to the molecular layer, and is superficial to the stratum radiatum.

name: thoracic vein
description: A vein that is part of a thorax [Automatically generated definition].

name: coracoclavicular ligament
description: Any ligament that connects the coracoid process with the clavicle

name: stylocone
description: Cusp found on a platform that is buccaal and mesial to the meta and paracones. Modified from Kermack 1967. Molar evolution in Mesozoic mammals

name: foramen secundum
description: A foramen in the septum secundum.

name: capsule
description: A cover or envelope partly or wholly surrounding a structure. Examples: egg shell, articular capsules, renal capsules[WP].

name: pectoral appendage apical ectodermal ridge
description: An apical ectodermal ridge that is part of a pectoral appendage bud.

name: lobar bronchus of right lung caudal lobe
description: A lobar bronchus that is part of a lower lobe of right lung [Automatically generated definition].

name: vesical vein
description: A tributary of the iliac vein that drains the urinary bladder.

name: mandibular process mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a mandibular prominence.

name: pharyngeal apophysis
description: Ventral process on the neurocranium for the articulation of upper pharyngeal bones. It is variably composed of the parasphenoid, basioccipital, and prootic depending on the species. From: Greenwood, PH (1978). A review of the pharyngeal hypophysis and its significance in the classification of African cichlid fishes. Bull. Br. Mus. Nat. Hist. (Zool.) 33: 297-323.

name: neural fold hinge point
description: The median hinge point extends for the entire length of the neural tube, and the lateral hinge points do not form in the spinal cord region of the neural tube[GO].

name: hyponychium
description: Epithelium located beneath the nail plate at the junction between the free edge and the skin of the fingertip. It forms a seal that protects the nail bed.

name: liver perisinusoidal space
description: the extravascular space in the liver between the parenchymal cells and a sinusoid that contains the blood plasma

name: right part of face
description: Subdivision of the head consisting of the right half of the face, vertically divided.

name: metatarsus region
description: A metapodium region that is part of a pes.

name: trabecula carnea
description: the supporting bundles of muscular fibers lining the walls of the ventricles of the heart

name: quadrate-articular joint
description: A skeletal joint that connects quadrate and articular bones.

name: macula densa
description: The macula densa is an area of specialized cells in the distal tubule that makes contact with the vascular pole of the glomerulus[GO].

name: oronasal membrane
description: The oronasal membrane separates the oral cavity and nasal cavity.

name: obsolete regional part of hippocampus proper
medial accessory inferior olivary nucleus
description: The inferior olivary nucleus that lies between the primary olivary nucleus and the pyramid, and forms a curved lamina, the concavity of which is directed laterally

name: cloacal gland
description: A gland that is part of a cloaca.

name: bony nodule of terminal phalanx of hind digit
description: Endochondral element distal to terminal phalanx of hind digit.

name: obsolete predominantly gray regional part of occipital lobe
ora serrata of retina
description: The ora serrata is the serrated junction between the retina and the ciliary body. This junction marks the transition from the simple non-photosensitive area of the retina to the complex, multi-layered photosensitive region. In animals in which the region does not have a serrated appearance, it is called the ora ciliaris retinae.

name: embryonic/larval head sensillum
description: Any sensillum (UBERON:6007152) that is part of some larval head (UBERON:6001730).

name: coeliaco-mesenteric artery
description: This artery has many branches which supply blood to various organs in the viscus.

name: anal fin pterygiophore
description: A range of twelve to fourteen rod-like internal median skeletal support structures of the anal fin, comprised of both bone and cartilage and found between vertebrae 14 and 21.

name: sciatic nerve
description: A large nerve that supplies nearly the whole of the skin of the leg, the muscles of the back of the thigh, and those of the leg and foot. It begins in the lower back and runs through the buttock and down the lower limb.

name: epibranchial 5 cartilage
description: Epibranchial cartilage that is bilaterally paired and located at the articulation of epibranchial 4 cartilage or bone and the posterior tip of ceratobranchial 4 cartilage or bone.

name: ramus muscularis of glossopharyngeus nerve
description: Branchiomotor branch of the glossopharyngeus nerve innervating the m. subarcuales rectus I.

name: pericardial parietal mesothelium
description: A parietal mesothelium that is part of a pericardium.

name: pole of lens
description: A central point or region on the anterior or posterior surface of the lens

name: ovarian ligament
description: A fibrous ligament that connects the ovary to the lateral surface of the uterus.

name: post-hyoid pharyngeal arch skeleton
description: The part of the pharyngeal arch skeleton that excludes the skeleton of arches 1 and 2.

name: nucleus of midbrain tegmentum
description: A nucleus of brain that spans a midbrain tegmentum.

name: metacarpus region
description: A metapodium region that is part of a manus.

name: lateral palpebral artery
description: The lateral palpebral arteries are small arteries which supply the eyelid.

name: eye muscle
description: A muscle that is part of the eye region.

name: radial nerve
description: A nerve that supplies the upper limb, including the triceps brachii muscle of the arm, as well as all 12 muscles in the posterior osteofascial compartment of the forearm, as well as the associated joints and overlying skin.

name: subcallosal area
description: The subcallosal area (parolfactory area of Broca, area parolfactoria) is a small triangular field on the medial surface of the hemisphere in front of the subcallosal gyrus, from which it is separated by the posterior parolfactory sulcus; it is continuous below with the olfactory trigone, and above and in front with the cingulate gyrus; it is limited anteriorly by the anterior parolfactory sulcus. [WP,unvetted].

name: integumentary papilla
description: Odontogenic papilla that is located in the integument.

name: skeletal muscle tissue of mylohyoid
description: A portion of skeletal muscle tissue that is part of a mylohyoid [Automatically generated definition].

name: proximal phalanx of manual digit 2
description: A proximal phalanx that is part of a hand digit 2 [Automatically generated definition].

name: popliteal lymph node
description: the lymph nodes which drain the legs; contained in the popliteal fossa

name: hemisphere part of cerebellar anterior lobe
description: A multi-tissue structure that is part of a anterior lobe of cerebellum and is part of a cerebellar hemisphere.

name: pulmonary collagen fibril
description: The connective tissue bundles in the extracellular matrix of pulmonary tissue that are composed of collagen, and play a role in tissue strength and elasticity

name: external anal sphincter
description: The Sphincter ani externus (external anal sphincter) is a flat plane of muscular fibers, elliptical in shape and intimately adherent to the integument surrounding the margin of the anus. [WP,unvetted].

name: neurula stage
description: Staged defined by the formation of a tube from the flat layer of ectodermal cells known as the neural plate. This will give rise to the central nervous system.

name: labial region
description: The region of an anatomical structure, such as a tooth or jaw bone, facing the lips.[PHENOSCAPE:WD]

name: 1st arch maxillary mesenchyme from neural crest
description: Mesenchyme that develops_from a neural crest and is part of a 1st arch maxillary mesenchyme.

name: neural spine 1
description: Neural spine that is associated with the first vertebra.

name: skin of thorax
description: A zone of skin that is part of a thorax [Automatically generated definition].

name: cuboidal epithelium
description: An epithelium consisting of cuboidal epithelial cells.

name: caudate lobe hepatic sinusoid
description: A hepatic sinusoid that is part of a caudate lobe of liver.

name: urohyal
description: Tendon bone that forms in the tendon of the sternohyoid muscles ventral to the anterior end of copula 1. The urohyal associates by ligaments to the ventral hypohyals or it articulates with the ventral hypohyals. The urohyal is an unpaired bone.

name: rostrolateral thalamic nucleus of Butler & Saidel
non-keratinized stratified squamous epithelium
description: Stratified squamous epithelium is a stratified squamous epithelium, the cells of which synthesizes but does not accumulate keratin. Examples: epithelium of vagina, epithelium of wall of esophagus.

name: posterior nasal barbel
description: Barbel that is attached to the anterior rim of the posterior nostril. Posterior nasal barbel is paired.

name: trabecula carnea of left ventricle
description: A trabecula carnea that is part of a heart left ventricle.

name: future pterygopalatine ganglion
description: A ganglion that has the potential to develop into a pterygopalatine ganglion.

name: palatine bone horizontal plate
description: The part of the palatine bone that forms the posterior part (approximately one third) of the bony palate.(Stedmans)

name: pancreas right lobe
description: A pancreatic lobule that is in_the_right_side_of a exocrine pancreas.

name: rostral middle frontal gyrus
description: Component of the middle frontal gyrus The rostral boundary is the first appearance of the superior frontal sulcus whereas the caudal boundary is the middle frontal gyrus. The medial and lateral boundaries are the superior frontal sulcus and the inferior frontal sulcus respectively (Christine Fennema-Notestine).

name: limb muscle
description: Any muscle organ that is part of a limb [Automatically generated definition].

name: vagina sebaceous gland
description: A sebaceous gland that is part of a vagina [Automatically generated definition].

name: mucosa of male urethra
description: A mucosa that is part of a male urethra [Automatically generated definition].

name: left renal cortex interstitium
description: A renal cortex interstitium that is part of a left kidney.

name: adrenal gland capsule
description: the thick capsule of dense irregular connective tissue that surrounds each adrenal gland and contains scattered elastic fibers; the capsule contains a rich plexus of blood vessels (mainly small arteries) and numerous nerve fibers; some blood vessels and nerves enter the substance of the gland in the trabeculae that extend inward from the capsule and then leave the trabeculae to enter the cortex.

name: cavernous sinus
description: The cavernous sinus (or lateral sellar compartment), within the human head, is a large collection of thin-walled veins creating a cavity bordered by the temporal bone of the skull and the sphenoid bone, lateral to the sella turcica.

name: terminal branch of ophthalmic artery
description: The two terminal branches of the ophthalmic artery in humans are the dorsal nasal artery and the supratrochlear artery

name: right lung alveolar duct
description: An alveolar duct that is part of a right lung [Automatically generated definition].

name: hindlimb
description: A (free) limb that is connected to a pelvic girdle region. The extent of this structure includes autopod, stylopod and zeugopod regions when present, but excludes the pelvic girdle and its parts.

name: inner canthus of right eye
description: A inner canthus that is part of a right eye.

name: jejunal mucosa
description: A mucosa that is part of a jejunum [Automatically generated definition].

name: secretion of crop
description: Nutritional fluid secreted by the crop in some species[Kardong]

name: obsolete regional part of central nervous system
thyroid follicular lumen
description: A follicular lumen is the closed cavity within a follicle of the thyroid gland. It is surrounded by follicular cells and filled with colloid, a concentrated solution of thyroglobulin

name: manual minor digit (Aves) plus metapodial segment
description: A subdivision of the autopod consisting of manual minor digit (Aves) plus the region incorporating a single metapodial element. These segments are typically repeated along the pre-axiom to post-axial axis.

name: jugulohyoideus muscle
description: runs from the processus jugularis to the os stylohyoideum; innervated with the ramus jugulohyoideus from the nervus facialis

name: interarcual cartilage
description: Pharyngeal arch cartilage located between uncinate process of epibranchial 1 and pharyngobranchial 2.

name: epaxial region somite 16
description: Somite-derived body wall muscle present dorsal to the horizontal myoseptum. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: right posterior cardinal vein
description: A posterior cardinal vein that is in_the_right_side_of a multicellular organism.

name: obsolete iridophore
description: A pigment cell derived from the neural crest. The cell contains flat light-reflecting platelets, probably of guanine, in stacks called reflecting platets or iridisomes. The color-generating components produce a silver, gold, or iridescent color.

name: hypaxial region somite 21
description: Somite-derived body wall muscle present ventral to the horizontal myoseptum. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: pedal digit 7 plus metapodial segment
description: A subdivision of the autopod consisting of pedal digit 7 plus the region incorporating a single metapodial element. These segments are typically repeated along the pre-axiom to post-axial axis.

name: spinal cord ventral commissure
description: The band of nerve fibers which cross the midline of the spinal cord ventral to the central canal and posterior grey commissure[MP]. The anterior (or ventral) white commissure, also known as the alba anterior medullae spinalis, is a bundle of nerve fibers which cross the midline of the spinal cord just anterior to the gray commissure. A N4 fibers and C fibers carrying pain sensation in the spinothalamic tract contribute to this commissure, as do fibers of the anterior corticospinal tract, which carry motor signals from the primary motor cortex[WP].

name: pelvic fin basipterygial radial
description: Pelvic fin radial that is an endochondral fused radials or pterygiophores at the base of the pelvic fin.

name: webbed interdigital region between pedal digits
description: A webbed interdigital region that is part of a pes.

name: lower jaw molar epithelium
description: A dental epithelium that is part of a lower jaw molar.

name: sulcus limitans of neural tube
description: A longitudinal groove in the neural tube wall that divides the neural tube into dorsal (alar) and ventral (basal) halves (dorsal receives input from sensory neurons, ventral effects motor functions); stretches from the mesencephalon caudad[TMD].

name: intestine smooth muscle
description: A portion of smooth muscle tissue that is part of a intestine [Automatically generated definition].

name: white matter lamina of cerebellum
description: The white laminae of cerebellum is subdivision of the cerebellar cortex comprised of myelinated axons lying deep to the granule cell layer of the cerebellar cortex.

name: tailgut
description: The extension of the hindgut of the primitive digestive tube of the embryo, caudal to the location of the anal opening

name: serosa of urinary bladder
description: A serous membrane that is part of a urinary bladder [Automatically generated definition].

name: primary palate mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a developing primary palate.

name: callosal sulcus
description: The callosal sulcus is a sulcus in the brain between the cingulate gyrus and corpus callosum, below the longitudinal cerebral fissure. [WP,unvetted].

name: skin of head
description: A zone of skin that is part of a head [Automatically generated definition].

name: hilum of dentate nucleus
description: The mouth of the flasklike dentate nucleus of the cerebellum, directed inward (rostromedial), and giving exit to many of the fibers that compose the superior cerebellar peduncle or brachium conjunctivum.

name: arciferal girdle
description: Pectoral girdle in which the epicoracoid cartilages are elaborated into posteriorly directed epicoracoid horns. Most arciferal pectoral girdles are characterized by fusion of the epicoracoid cartilages in the interclavicle region. Posterior to the clavicles, the epicoracoids usually are free and overlapping.

name: fin web
description: Membrane that connects the lepidotrichia or ceratotrichia of a fin.

name: incisor tusk
description: An incisor tooth that protrudes beyond the mouth.

name: inferior vesical artery
description: An artery that supplies blood to the lower urinary bladder.

name: smooth muscle tissue
description: Muscle tissue which is unstriated, composed primarily of smooth muscle fibers surrounded by a reticulum of collagen and elastic fibers. Smooth muscle differs from striated muscle in the much higher actin/myosin ratio, the absence of conspicuous sarcomeres and the ability to contract to a much smaller fraction of its resting length[GO].

name: epipodial facet
description: Facets for the articulation of the epipodial (zeugopodial) elements.

name: obsolete regional part of lumbar spinal cord
subscapular fossa
description: A marked depression on the medial side of the scapula blade, often opposite the glenoid region.

name: obsolete regional part of cerebral cortex
description: A regional part of brain that is part of a cerebral cortex [Automatically generated definition].

name: margo fenestralis
description: Anterior margin of the coracoid, which forms the posterior edge of the pectoral fenestra.

name: corpuscle of de Quatrefage
description: A specialised sensory organ located in the subepidermal connective tissue at the rostral end of late larval and adult amphioxus. They consist of between 1 and 4 nerve cells with axons, each with 2 cilia, surrounded by up to 7 sheath cells. The cilia extend into a protrusion of the basal lamina which surrounds each corpuscle. The axonal process contributes to the rostral nerve.

name: nail of pedal digit 1
description: A nail that is part of a pedal digit 1.

name: pharyngobranchial 3 tooth
description: Tooth that is part of the pharyngobranchial 3 tooth plate.

name: scrotal sweat
description: Any portion of sweat that is produced by a sweat gland of the scrotum.

name: myotome somite 14
description: Portion of the somite giving rise to body wall muscle masses. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: ventral thoracic disc
description: Imaginal disc that is a precursor of ventral thoracic structures of the adult.

name: infraorbital 9
description: Infraorbital that is the ninth bone of the infraorbital series.

name: epibranchial 1 cartilage
description: Epibranchial cartilage that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with ceratobranchial 1 cartilage or bone.

name: geniculate ganglion
description: the group of sensory neuron cell bodies associated with the facial nerve (seventh cranial nerve)

name: appendage girdle region
description: An organism subdivision that encompasses the region containing the pectoral or pelvic girdle. Note that this includes both the skeletal elements and associated tissues (integument, muscle, etc).

name: dental plaque
description: A soft, thin film of food debris, mucin, and dead epithelial cells deposited on the teeth, providing the medium for the growth of various bacteria. The main inorganic components are calcium and phosphorus, with small amounts of magnesium, potassium, and sodium; the organic matrix consists of polysaccharides, proteins, carbohydrates, lipids, and other components. Plaque plays an important etiologic role in the development of dental caries and periodontal and gingival diseases and provides the base for the development of materia alba; calcified plaque forms dental calculus.

name: ectomeninx
description: The outermost layer of the mesenchymal capsule that surrounds the developing brain, of mixed paraxial mesoderm and neural crest origin. The ectomeninx forms the dura mater (both inner layer and outer chondrogenic layer).

name: left lung alveolus
description: An alveolus that is part of a left lung [Automatically generated definition].

name: gastro-splenic ligament
description: peritoneum connecting the greater curvature of stomach with the hilum of the spleen[umich]. part of the greater omentum; derived from the dorsal mesogastrium in the embryo.

name: carpus pre-cartilage condensation
description: A pre-cartilage condensation that has the potential to develop into a carpal bone.

name: insect adult head
description: Head of the adult organism.

name: interdigital region between pedal digits 1 and 2
description: An interdigital region that adjacent_to a pedal digit 1 and adjacent_to a pedal digit 2.

name: neck of rib
description: The neck of the rib is the flattened portion which extends lateralward from the head; it is about 2.5 cm. long, and is placed in front of the transverse process of the lower of the two vertebrC& with which the head articulates. Its anterior surface is flat and smooth, its posterior rough for the attachment of the ligament of the neck, and perforated by numerous foramina. Of its two borders the superior presents a rough crest (crista colli costE) for the attachment of the anterior costotransverse ligament; its inferior border is rounded. On the posterior surface at the junction of the neck and body, and nearer the lower than the upper border, is an eminencebthe tubercle; it consists of an articular and a non-articular portion. The articular portion, the lower and more medial of the two, presents a small, oval surface for articulation with the end of the transverse process of the lower of the two vertebrC& to which the head is connected. The non-articular portion is a rough elevation, and affords attachment to the ligament of the tubercle. The tubercle is much more prominent in the upper than in the lower ribs.

name: hepatopancreatic ampulla
description: A dilation of the duodenal papilla that is the opening of the juncture of the common bile duct and the main pancreatic duct.

name: paraxial mesoderm
description: The paraxial mesoderm is the mesoderm located bilaterally adjacent to the notochord and neural tube[GO]

name: distal tarsal cartilage
description: A distal tarsal endochondral element that is composed primarily of cartilage tissue.

name: metanephric collecting duct
description: A collecting duct of renal tubule that is part of a metanephros [Automatically generated definition].

name: epithelium of oropharynx
description: An epithelium that is part of a oropharynx [Automatically generated definition].

name: mesoderm blood island
description: A blood island that is part of a mesoderm.

name: corona of glans penis
description: The circumference of the base of the glans forms a rounded projecting border, the corona of the glans penis, overhanging a deep retroglandular sulcus, behind which is the neck of the penis.

name: pedal autopod pad
description: A autopod pad that is part of a pes.

name: obsolete regional part of corticomedial nuclear complex
secretion of Harderian gland
description: A merocrine secretion that is produced by a Harderian gland, containing lipids

name: obsolete olfactory bulb main of rodent
sagittal crest
description: A ridge of bone running lengthwise along the midline of the top of the skull of many mammalian and reptilian skulls and serves as an attachment site for the temporailis muscle[WP,modified].

name: ural vertebra
description: Vertebra that is incomplete or rudimentary and may bear a rudimentary neural arch and sometimes a rudimentary spine or the neural arch and spine are completely absent. Ural vertebrae are one of the last bony elements of the vertebral column, usually smaller than the preural centra. Ural vertebrae are numbered beginning from anterior (1) to posterior (2, 3, 4, etc.). Ural vertebra is an unpaired median bone.

name: oral cavity
description: Anatomical cavity at the start of the digestive tract that that is enclosed by the mouth. The boundaries and contents vary depending on the species. In vertebrates, the boundaries are the oral opening, the cheeks, the palate and (if present) the palatoglossal arch - if this is not present then the mouth and pharynx form the oropharyngeal cavity. The buccal cavity contains the teeth, tongue and palate (when present)

name: right pulmonary vein
description: Vein that drains right lung and returns blood to the heart.

name: secretion of lacrimal gland
description: Aqueous substance secreted by the lacrimal gland.

name: hemochorial placenta
description: A placenta in which no maternal layers are retained.

name: tooth bud
description: A knoblike tooth primordium that develops into the mature tooth and consists of enamel organ, dental papilla, and dental sac enclosing them.

name: obsolete optic nerve head
description: Portion of cranial nerve II where large fasicles of axons from the optic fiber layer come together prior to leaving the eye.

name: vertebral arch of axis
description: A neural arch that is part of a vertebral bone 2.

name: mesonephric nephron progenitor
description: Cluster of cells comprising a portion of tissue which gives rise to new mesonephric nephrons. The cluster contains self-renewing stem cells.

name: rectosigmoid junction
description: An anatomical junction that is between the sigmoid colon and rectum.

name: foramen lacerum
description: A triangular hole in the base of the skull located at the base of the medial pterygoid plate.

name: hippocampus stratum oriens
description: Layer that is part of the CA fields of the hippocampus consisting of a narrow relatively cell free layer located deep to the pyramidal cell layer extending through areas CA1, CA2 and CA3. (adapted from Paxinos The rat central nervous system, 2nd ed, Academic Press, San Diego, 1995)

name: deferent duct vein
description: A vein that is part of a vas deferens [Automatically generated definition].

name: pectoral fin distal radial cartilage 2
description: pectoral fin distal radial 2 element that is composed of cartilage tissue.

name: mandibular symphyseal tooth
description: Tooth of the lower jaw that is adjacent to the mandibular symphysis

name: liver primordium
description: A small endodermal thickening in the foregut adjacent to the transverse septum. Invaginates forming the hepatic diverticulum.

name: pelvic appendage apical ectodermal ridge
description: An apical ectodermal ridge that is part of a pelvic appendage bud.

name: anterior abdominal wall muscle
description: Any skeletal muscle organ that is part of a anterior abdominal wall. Examples: the obliques, pyramidalis and transversus abdominus

name: ala of nose
description: The lateral surface parts of the external nose, inferiorly, surrounding the naris[EoM].

name: telencephalic ventricle
description: A brain ventricle that is part of a telencephalon. In mammals and species with an evaginated telencephalon, this is one of a pair of lateral structures, one in each hemisphere

name: somatic motor system
description: The neural tissue involved in the transmission of motor signals

name: skin of snout
description: A zone of skin that is part of the snout.

name: wing
description: Appendage that is shaped in order to produce lift for flight through the air.

name: imaginal disc-derived wing
description: A flight organ of the adult external thorax that is derived from a dorsal mesothoracic disc.

name: corpus luteum
description: A transient endocrine gland that develops from the postovulatory or atretic follicles and secretes progesterone; it is thought to be related to egg retention[PMID].

name: joint connecting upper and lower jaws
description: Synovial joint that articulates bones of upper and lower jaw.

name: corpus callosum
description: White matter structure containing massive numbers of commissural fibers connecting cortical areas in the two cerebral hemispheres.it is subdivided into a genu, a rostrum, a body, and a splenium. (MM)

name: epithelium of foregut-midgut junction
description: An epithelium that is part of a foregut-midgut junction.

name: urodeal gland
description: A gland that is part of a urodeum.

name: retroperitoneal lymph node
description: A lymph node located in the retroperitoneal space.

name: obsolete predominantly gray regional part of anterior hypothalamic region
obsolete anal fin lepidotrichium
description: Lepidotrichium which is part of the anal fin.

name: plantar metatarsal artery
description: The plantar metatarsal arteries (digital branches) are four in number, and run forward between the metatarsal bones and in contact with the Interossei. Each divides into a pair of plantar digital arteries which supply the adjacent sides of the toes. Near their points of division each sends upward an anterior perforating branch to join the corresponding dorsal metatarsal artery. The first plantar metatarsal artery (arteria princeps hallucis) springs from the junction between the lateral plantar and deep plantar arteries and sends a digital branch to the medial side of the first toe. The digital branch for the lateral side of the fifth toe arise from the lateral plantar artery near the base of the fifth metatarsal bone.

name: hepatic sinusoid of left of lobe of liver
description: A hepatic sinusoid that is part of a left lobe of liver.

name: epibranchial 4 bone
description: Epibranchial bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with ceratobranchial 4 cartilage or bone and medially with pharyngobranchial cartilage or bone.

name: circumflex branch of left coronary artery
description: Branch of left coronary artery which runs perpendicular to the anterior interventricular branch of the left coronary artery on the left side of the interventricular sulcus and supplies the left side of the heart.

name: reticulorumen
description: The first chamber in the alimentary canal of a ruminant stomach, composed of the rumen and reticulum.

name: mesothelium of serous pericardium
description: A mesothelium that is part of a serous pericardium.

name: supcapsular region of anterior region of lens
lower back
description: Subdivision of abdominal segment of trunk which in humans is demarcated from the front of the abdomen by the posterior surface of the anterior layer of the thoracolumbar fascia and the anterior surface of the lumbar vertebral column; together with the front of the abdomen, it constitutes the abdomen[Modified from FMA].

name: cranial suspensory ligament
description: Connects the cranial tip of the future gonad to the dorsocranial abdominal cavity.

name: nucleus of midbrain reticular formation
description: A nucleus of midbrain tegmentum that is part of a midbrain reticular formation.

name: thoracic vertebra 5
description: The fifth thoracic vertebra counting from the top down. Note that members of this class are not necessarily homologous[ncit,modified].

name: tunica media of artery
description: A tunica media that is part of a artery.

name: tarsal region
description: mesopodial segment of the pes, including the tarsal skeleton and associated tissues.

name: medial palpebral artery
description: The medial palpebral arteries (internal palpebral arteries) are arteries of the head. They are two in number, superior and inferior, arise from the ophthalmic, opposite the pulley of the Obliquus superior.

name: axillary nerve
description: The axillary nerve is a nerve of the human body, that comes off the posterior cord of the brachial plexus at the level of the axilla (armpit) and carries nerve fibers from C5 and C6. The axillary nerve travels through the quadrangular space with the posterior circumflex humeral artery and vein. [WP,unvetted].

name: anatomical wall
description: Organ component adjacent to an organ cavity and which consists of a maximal aggregate of organ component layers.

name: skeletal muscle tissue of orbicularis oculi
description: A portion of skeletal muscle tissue that is part of a orbicularis oculi [Automatically generated definition].

name: cochlear nucleus
description: Any of the nuclei of the cochlear nuclear complex.

name: molariform tooth
description: A molar or premolar

name: suprarostral cartilage
description: Larval upper jaws articulate with trabecular horns.

name: proximal phalanx of manual digit 3
description: A proximal phalanx that is part of a hand digit 3 [Automatically generated definition].

name: popliteal vein
description: The popliteal vein course runs alongside the popliteal artery but carries the blood from the knee joint and muscles in the thigh and calf back to the heart. Its origin is defined by the junction of the posterior tibial vein and anterior tibial vein. It drains the peroneal vein before reaching the knee joint and turns into the femoral vein when leaving the adductor canal (also known as Hunter's canal). The popliteal artery extends from the femoral artery behind the popliteal fossa which is the space behind the knee. [WP,unvetted].

name: hemisphere part of cerebellar posterior lobe
description: A multi-tissue structure that is part of a cerebellar hemisphere and is part of a posterior lobe of cerebellum.

name: bone collagen fibril
description: The connective tissue bundles in the extracellular matrix of bone tissue that are composed of collagen, and play a role in tissue strength and elasticity

name: obturator externus
description: An adductor muscle that attaches to the femur and the pelvis. In humans, the obturator externus muscle is a flat, triangular muscle, which covers the outer surface of the anterior wall of the pelvis. It is sometimes considered part of the medial compartment of thigh, and sometimes considered part of the gluteal region. [WP,generalized].

name: organogenesis stage
description: A stage at which the ectoderm, endoderm, and mesoderm develop into the internal organs of the organism.

name: posterolingual region
description: The region of an anatomical structure, such as a tooth or jaw bone, oriented posteriorly and facing the lips.[PHENOSCAPE:WD]

name: 2nd arch mesenchyme from neural crest
description: Mesenchyme that develops_from a neural crest and is part of a 2nd arch mesenchyme.

name: neural spine 2
description: Neural spine that is associated with the second vertebra.

name: skin of limb
description: A zone of skin that is part of a limb [Automatically generated definition].

name: quadrate lobe hepatic sinusoid
description: A hepatic sinusoid that is part of a quadrate lobe of liver.

name: subdivision of conjunctiva
description: One of the three major regions of the conjunctiva.

name: anterior nasal barbel
description: Barbel that is associated with the anterior nostril. Anterior nasal barbel is paired.

name: femur cartilage element
description: A femur endochondral element that is composed primarily of cartilage tissue.

name: thymic artery
description: A vein that supplies blood to the thymus.

name: forelimb muscle
description: Any muscle organ that is part of a forelimb.

name: mucosa of female urethra
description: A mucosa that is part of a female urethra [Automatically generated definition].

name: ambient gyrus
description: a rostral part of the parahippocampal gyrus.

name: right renal cortex interstitium
description: A renal cortex interstitium that is part of a right kidney.

name: zona glomerulosa of adrenal gland
description: the narrow subcapsular outer zone of the adrenal cortex where aldosterone is produced

name: splenic vein
description: A vein arising from the splenic trabecular vein in the hilum of the spleen that drains into the portal vein.

name: zygomatico-orbital artery
description: The middle temporal artery occasionally gives off a zygomatico-orbital branch, which runs along the upper border of the zygomatic arch, between the two layers of the temporal fascia, to the lateral angle of the orbit. This branch, which may arise directly from the superficial temporal artery, supplies the Orbicularis oculi, and anastomoses with the lacrimal and palpebral branches of the ophthalmic artery.

name: cartilago orbitalis
description: Lateral wall of chondrocranial braincase between lamina orbitonasalis and pila metoptica.

name: left lung alveolar duct
description: An alveolar duct that is part of a left lung [Automatically generated definition].

name: mesonephric late distal segment
description: The site of bicarbonate resorption in the adult kidney. It is equivalent to the convoluted distal segment of metanephric nephrons. [Xenbase]

name: visual system
description: The sensory system subserving the sense of vision.

name: rostral portion of the medial accessory olive
sequential hermaphroditic organism
description: Hermaphroditic organism that produces gametes first of one sex, and then later of the other sex.

name: layer of microvilli
description: A layer of microvilli, Thin cylindrical membrane-covered projections on the surface of an animal cell containing a core bundle of actin filaments[GO,modified]

name: dilatator laryngis
description: Involved in the movement of the arytenoid cartilages.

name: cervical gland
description: mucus-secreting glands in the mucosa of the uterine cervix

name: inner medulla vasa recta descending limb
occipitofrontalis muscle
description: The occipitofrontalis or epicranius is a muscle which covers parts of the skull. It consists of two parts or bellies: The occipital belly, near the occipital bone, and the frontal belly, near the frontal bone.

name: myotome somite 10
description: Portion of the somite giving rise to body wall muscle masses. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: obsolete melanocyte
description: A pigment cell derived from the neural crest. Contains melanin-filled pigment granules, which gives a brown to black appearance.

name: pedal digit 8 plus metapodial segment
description: A subdivision of the autopod consisting of pedal digit 8 plus the region incorporating a single metapodial element. These segments are typically repeated along the pre-axiom to post-axial axis.

name: functional part of brain
description: A brain region defined by functional criteria, e.g. auditory cortex, rather than by structural or histological criteria.

name: head kidney
description: Teleost head kidney consists of fused bilateral lobes located in the anterior part of the kidney. It is analogous to the mammalian bone marrow and the primary site of definitive hematopoiesis[ZFA,modified].

name: trigeminothalamic tract
description: The trigeminothalamic tract is one of the major routes of nociceptive and temperature signaling from the face

name: middle phalanx of digit 4
description: A middle phalanx that is part of a digit 4 [Automatically generated definition].

name: right lung accessory lobe epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a right lung accessory lobe.

name: dorsal motor nucleus of vagus nerve
description: A cranial nerve nucleus for the vagus nerve in the medulla that lies under the floor of the fourth ventricle. It mostly serves parasympathetic vagal functions in the gastrointestinal tract, lungs, and other thoracic and abdominal vagal innervations. The cell bodies for the preganglionic parasympathetic vagal neurons that innervate the heart reside in the nucleus ambiguus.[WP,unvetted].

name: superior mesenteric ganglion
description: A ganglion in the upper part of the superior mesenteric plexus that is the synapsing point for one of the pre- and post-synaptic nerves of the sympathetic division of the autonomous nervous system.

name: stomach smooth muscle
description: A portion of smooth muscle tissue that is part of a stomach [Automatically generated definition].

name: thoracic division of spinal cord central canal
description: Part of spinal cord central canal contained in the thoracic spinal cord. It is continuous rostrally with the cervical spinal cord central canal and caudally with the lumbar spinal cord central canal.

name: anterior definitive endoderm
description: The mesendoderm which first migrates from the node and which gives rise to the gut

name: lamina propria of urinary bladder
description: A lamina propria that is part of a urinary bladder [Automatically generated definition].

name: obsolete central nervous system cranial ganglion
longitudinal fissure
description: The deep groove which separates the two hemispheres of the vertebrate brain. The falx cerebri, a dural brain covering, lies within the medial longitudinal fissure. [WP,unvetted].

name: platypus crural gland
description: A kidney-shaped alveolar glands located in the upper thigh connected by a thin-walled duct to a calcaneus spur, or calcar, on each hind limb.

name: skin of trunk
description: A zone of skin that is part of a trunk [Automatically generated definition].

name: firmisternal girdle
description: Pectoral girdle that lacks epicoracoid horns. The sternum is fused to the pectoral arch, and the epicoracoid cartilages of each half of the girdle are fused to one another. The midzonal length of the girdle is shorter than that of an arciferal girdle, but pre- and postzonal elements tend to be longer.

name: posterior dorsal fin basal cartilage (elasmobranchs)
description: The large cartilage of the posterior dorsal fin, on which the radials articulate distally.

name: canine tusk
description: An cuspid tooth that protrudes beyond the mouth.

name: superior vesical artery
description: An artery that supplies blood to the upper urinary bladder.

name: mesothelium
description: Simple squamous epithelium of mesodermal origin which lines serous membranes. Examples: mesothelium of pleura, mesothelium of peritoneum[FMA]. Wikipedia: The mesothelium is a membrane that forms the lining of several body cavities: the pleura (thoracal cavity), peritoneum (abdominal cavity including the mesentery) and pericardium (heart sac). Mesothelial tissue also surrounds the male internal reproductive organs (the tunica vaginalis testis) and covers the internal reproductive organs of women (the tunica serosa uteri).

name: suture
description: Line of junction between two parts immovably connected. Modified from Henderson's Dictionary of Biological Terms.

name: supraacetabular buttress
description: A bony protuberance dorsal to the acetabulum on the ilium, confluent with the supraacetabular crest (when present). Acts as a bone brace to prevent excessive femoral abduction and the origin site for part of the M. iliofemoralis.

name: caudal fin ventral procurrent ray
description: Caudal procurrent ray that forms part of the anterior ventral series of lepidotrichia of the caudal fin that may be associated with a neural spine or a epural or an uroneural (dorsal series) and with a hemal spine of a preural vertebra (ventral series). A caudal procurrent ray is an unpaired median bone.

name: margo posterior
description: Posterior margin of the coracoid.

name: obsolete predominantly gray regional part of habenula
nail of pedal digit 2
description: A nail that is part of a pedal digit 2.

name: upper pharyngeal 4 tooth plate
description: Pharyngeal tooth plate that lies ventral to pharyngobranchial 4, and located anterior to upper pharyngeal 5 tooth plate.

name: costal diaphragm
description: The domain of the diaphragm that is a thin domed sheet of muscle composed of a radial array of myofibers extending laterally from the ribs and medially to a central tendon.

name: paraumbilical vein
description: The small superficial veins that arise from the cutaneous veins, and run from the umbilicus along the round ligament of the liver; these terminate as accessory portal veins in the liver.

name: scrotal sweat gland
description: Any sweat gland that is part of a scrotum.

name: infraorbital 10
description: Infraorbital that is the tenth bone of the infraorbital series.

name: prothoracic leg disc
description: Imaginal disc of the ventral prothoracic segment. Precursor of structures of the adult ventral prothorax including the prothoracic (1st) leg.

name: olfactory pit
description: An indentation of the olfactory placode which ends when the pits hollows out to form the nasopharynx[GO].

name: fourth ventricle choroid plexus stroma
description: A choroid plexus stroma that is part of a fourth ventricle.

name: epibranchial 3 cartilage
description: Epibranchial cartilage that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with ceratobranchial 3 cartilage or bone.

name: Brodmann (1909) area 7
description: Brodmann area 7 is one of Brodmann's cytologically defined regions of the brain. It is involved in locating objects in space. It serves as a point of convergence between vision and proprioception to determine where objects are in relation to parts of the body.

name: thoracic sympathetic nerve trunk
description: A sympathetic nerve trunk that is part of a thorax [Automatically generated definition].

name: tarsus endochondral element
