description: A tarsus bone or its cartilage or pre-cartilage precursor.

name: lieno-renal ligament
description: peritoneum that attaches the spleen to the posterior abdominal wall over the left kidney. develops from the dorsal mesogastrium of the embryo[umich]

name: rhombic lip
description: the posterior section of the developing metencephalon recognized transiently within the vertebrate embryo; the rhombic lip extends posteriorly from the roof of the fourth ventricle to dorsal neuroepithelial cell and can be divided into eight structural units based on rhombomeres 1-8 (r1-r8), recognized at early stages of hindbrain development; producing granule cells and five brainstem nuclei, the rhombic lip plays an important role in developing a complex cerebellar neural system

name: neck nerve
description: A nerve that is part of a neck [Automatically generated definition].

name: exocrine gland of integumental system
description: An exocrine gland that is part of a integumental system.

name: white matter of temporal lobe
description: A white matter of cerebral lobe that is part of a temporal lobe.

name: duodenal papilla
description: One of the two small elevations on the mucosa of the duodenum, the major at the entrance of the conjoined pancreatic and common bile ducts and the minor at the entrance of the accessory pancreatic duct.

name: epibranchial placode
description: Focal thickenings of the embryonic ectoderm that form immediately dorsal and caudal of the clefts between the pharyngeal arches and that produce the neuroblasts that migrate and condense to form the distal cranial ganglia.

name: distal tarsal bone pre-cartilage condensation
description: A distal tarsal endochondral element that is composed primarily of a pre-cartilage condensation.

name: metanephric juxtaglomerular apparatus
description: juxtaglomerular apparatus of the mature vertebrate kidney, or metanephros.

name: presubiculum
description: A modified six-layered cortex between the subiculum and the main part of the parahippocampal gyrus.

name: stratum argenteum of choroid
description: A silver reflective layer in the outer choroid, adjacent to the sclera, frequently present in fish larvae but not as frequent in adults.

name: obsolete regional part of vestibular ganglion
digit plus metapodial segment
description: A subdivision of the autopod consisting of digit plus the region incorporating a single metapodial element. These segments are typically repeated along the pre-axiom to post-axial axis.

name: digitopodium region
description: A segment of the autopod consisting of both acropodial region and metapodial region, but excluding the mesopodial/basopodial region.

name: substantia propria of cornea
description: the lamellated connective tissue of the cornea between the Bowman and Descemet membranes

name: skull
description: Anatomical structure that is part of the head consisting entirely of cranium and mandible[WP].

name: mucosa
description: A lining of mostly endodermal origin, covered in epithelium, which is involved in absorption and secretion. They line various body cavities that are exposed to the external environment and internal organs. It is at several places continuous with skin: at the nostrils, the lips, the ears, the genital area, and the anus. The sticky, thick fluid secreted by the mucous membranes and gland is termed mucus. The term mucous membrane refers to where they are found in the body and not every mucous membrane secretes mucus[WP]

name: pineal recess of third ventricle
description: The diverticulum of the thin roof of the dorsocaudal third ventricle that projects into the stalk of the pineal gland.

name: ural vertebra 1
description: Ural vertebra that is located directly posterior to preural centrum 1. It may bear a rudimentary neural arch and sometimes a rudimentary spine or the neural arch and spine are completely absent and it may articulate or fuse with hypural 1 (polyural terminology). Ural vertebra 1 is an unpaired median bone.

name: sagittal keel
description: The Sagittal keel (torus) is a thickening of bone on part or all of the midline of the frontal bone, or parietal bones where they meet along the sagittal suture, or on both bones..

name: proximal-distal subdivision of colon
description: A section dividing a colon along a proximal-distal axis.

name: gingiva
description: The fibrous investing tissue, covered by keratinized epithelium, that immediately surrounds a tooth and is contiguous with its periodontal ligament and with the mucosal tissues of the mouth[Glossary of Periodontal Terms 2001].

name: obsolete caudal fin skeleton
description: Median fin skeleton supporting the caudal fin.

name: submocosal esophageal gland
description: One of the racemose glands in the walls of the esophagus that in humans are small and serve principally to lubricate the food but in some birds secrete a milky fluid on which the young are fed.

name: iliac cartilage element
description: A iliac endochondral element that is composed primarily of cartilage tissue.

name: basioccipital-exoccipital joint
description: Joint that articulates the basioccipital and exoccipital. Basioccipital-exoccipital joint is paired.

name: paired limb/fin segment
description: An appendage segment that is part of a limb/fin.

name: anatomical surface region
description: Material anatomical entity that forms the outermost boundary of an anatomical structure.

name: hilum of inferior olivary complex
description: The white core of the inferior olivary nucleus of the medulla oblongata, most prominent medially.

name: maxillary recess
description: A hollow space in the skull of carnivores, which do not exhibit a maxillary sinus.

name: hippocampus stratum radiatum
description: The layer located immediately above the pyramidal cell layer in CA2 and CA1 and superficial to the stratum lucidum in CA3. Suprapyramidal region in which CA3 to CA3 associational connections and CA3 to CA1 Schaffer collateral connections are located.

name: spleen germinal center
description: A germinal center that is part of the spleen. The spleen germinal center is located in a secondary B follicle in the white pulp of the spleen.

name: erector spinae muscle group
description: A bundle of muscles and tendons that is paired and runs more or less vertically. It extends throughout the lumbar, thoracic and cervical regions, and lies in the groove to the side of the vertebral column.

name: slow muscle tissue
description: The darker-colored muscle tissue of some mammals, composed of slow twitch muscle fibers.

name: third ventricle
description: Part of the ventricular system of the brain, forming a single large cavity in the midline of the diencephalon; it is continuous with the lateral ventricles through the interventricular foramen and the fourth ventricle through the cerebral aqueduct. (Maryann Martone)

name: placenta labyrinth
description: The placental layers where embryonic blood vessels are surrounded by trophoblast cells and maternal blood

name: tip of snout
description: Subdivision of the head consisting of the pointed or rounded end or extremity of the snout.

name: subcostal vein
description: A vein that runs along the bottom of the lowest rib. Each subcostal vein gives off a posterior (dorsal) branch which has a similar distribution to the posterior ramus of an intercostal artery. [WP,modified].

name: axillary vein
description: Vein that drains the axilla

name: endochondral bone
description: Replacement bone that forms within cartilage.

name: nematode larva
description: A multicellular organism that existence_starts_and_ends_during a nematode larval stage.

name: retrorubral area of midbrain reticular nucleus
description: The term retrorubral area of the midbrain reticular nucleus refers to a region of the rat brain caudal and dorsal to the ventral tegmental area. It is one of three parts of the midbrain reticular nucleus; the other two are the magnocellular part of the midbrain reticular nucleus and the parvicellular part of the midbrain reticular nucleus (Swanson-2004). BrainInfo distinguishes between the Retrorubral area of the midbrain reticular formation and the retrorubral nucleus.

name: endometrial stroma
description: The layer of connective tissue comprised of the endometrial lining of the uterus which fluctuates in thickness throughout the menstrual cycle.

name: accessory XI nerve spinal component
description: The spinal root of accessory nerve (or part) is firm in texture, and its fibers arise from the motor cells in the lateral part of the anterior column of the gray substance of the medulla spinalis as low as the fifth cervical nerve. Passing through the lateral funiculus of the medulla spinalis, they emerge on its surface and unite to form a single trunk, which ascends between the ligamentum denticulatum and the posterior roots of the spinal nerves; enters the skull through the foramen magnum, and is then directed to the jugular foramen, through which it passes, lying in the same sheath of dura mater as the vagus, but separated from it by a fold of the arachnoid. In the jugular foramen, it receives one or two filaments from the cranial part of the nerve, or else joins it for a short distance and then separates from it again. As its exit from the jugular foramen, it runs backward in front of the internal jugular vein in 66.6 per cent. of cases, and behind in it 33.3 per cent. The nerve then descends obliquely behind the Digastricus and Stylohyoideus to the upper part of the Sternocleidomastoideus; it pierces this muscle, and courses obliquely across the posterior triangle of the neck, to end in the deep surface of the Trapezius. As it traverses the Sternocleidomastoideus it gives several filaments to the muscle, and joins with branches from the second cervical nerve. In the posterior triangle it unites with the second and third cervical nerves, while beneath the Trapezius it forms a plexus with the third and fourth cervical nerves, and from this plexus fibers are distributed to the muscle.

name: keratin-based acellular structure
description: Acellular anatomical structure whose predominant constituent is keratin.

name: hepatic sinusoid of right of lobe of liver
description: A hepatic sinusoid that is part of a right lobe of liver.

name: epibranchial 2 bone
description: Epibranchial bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with ceratobranchial 2 cartilage or bone and medially with pharyngobranchial cartilage or bone.

name: otic opercular element
description: Round, flat bone or cartilage that lies in the fenestra ovalis and articulates with the columella.

name: otic operculum
description: Plate of cartilage occluding fenestra ovalis.

name: rugal fold of vagina
description: A rugal fold that is part of a vagina.

name: rumen
description: The first compartment of the ruminant stomach. It lies on the left side of the body, occupying the whole of the left side of the abdomen and even stretching across the median plane of the body to the right side. It is capacious, divided into an upper and a lower sac, each of which has a blind sac at its posterior extremity.

name: supcapsular region of posterior region of lens
deep temporal artery
description: The deep temporal arteries, two in number, anterior and posterior, ascend between the Temporalis and the pericranium. They supply the muscle, and anastomose with the middle temporal artery. The anterior communicates with the lacrimal artery by means of small branches which perforate the zygomatic bone and great wing of the sphenoid.

name: cerebellar peduncle
description: any of the three large paired bundles of nerve fibers that connect the cerebellum to the brain stem

name: rectovesical pouch
description: Between the rectum and the bladder the peritoneal cavity forms, in the male, a pouch, the rectovesical excavation (or rectovesical pouch), the bottom of which is slightly below the level of the upper ends of the vesiculae seminalesbi. e. , about 7.5 cm. from the orifice of the anus. its lowest part membranous partition called Rectoprostatic fascia. The corresponding structure in women is the rectouterine pouch.

name: thoracic vertebra 6
description: The sixth thoracic vertebra counting from the top down. Note that members of this class are not necessarily homologous[ncit,modified].

name: neurula embryo
description: An embryo at the neurula stage.

name: inferior cerebellar vein
description: The inferior cerebellar veins are of large size, end in the transverse, superior petrosal, and occipital sinuses. [WP,unvetted].

name: ulnar nerve
description: A nerve which runs near the ulna bone.

name: obsolete lobe parts of cerebral cortex
dental epithelium
description: Epithelium that is part of a developing tooth or dental organ.

name: anatomical structure
description: Material anatomical entity that is a single connected structure with inherent 3D shape generated by coordinated expression of the organism's own genome.

name: oral part of ventral lateral nucleus
skeletal muscle tissue of masseter
description: A portion of skeletal muscle tissue that is part of a masseter [Automatically generated definition].

name: inferior vestibular nucleus
description: The inferior vestibular nucleus is the vestibular nucleus which lies near the fourth ventricle. [WP,unvetted].

name: obsolete predominantly gray ventral regional part of thalamus
epiglottic vallecula
description: A depression in front of the epiglottis, in which food is temporarily gathered as the animal chews.

name: enteric nerve
description: the neurons that innervate the esophagus, stomach, small and large bowel

name: anterior tibial vein
description: A vein of the lower limb that carries blood from the anterior compartment of the leg to the popliteal vein which is forms when it joins with the posterior tibial vein. Like most deep veins, the anterior tibial vein is accompanied by an artery of the same name, the anterior tibial artery, along its course. [WP,unvetted].

name: white matter of medulla oblongata
description: A white matter that is part of a medulla oblongata.

name: tendon collagen fibril
description: The connective tissue bundles in the extracellular matrix of tendon tissue that are composed of collagen, and play a role in tissue strength and elasticity

name: iliacus muscle
description: The iliacus is a flat, triangular muscle, which fills the iliac fossa. [WP,unvetted].

name: juvenile stage
description: The stage of being no more dependent of the nest and/or from caregivers for subsistence while having not reach sexual maturity.

name: pre-enameloid
description: Odontoid tissue that is avascular non-mineralized matrix that is deposited by odontoblasts and ameloblasts that are excluded from the matrix.

name: udder
description: A large pendulous organ consisting of two or more mammary glands enclosed in a common envelope and each provided with a single nipple.

name: primary somatosensory cortex
description: (Chapin & Lin, 1984, rat): the region considered as the SI cortex is not a cytoarchitecturally homogeneous structure but consists instead of a patchwork array of areas containing dense aggregations of layer IV granule cells, surrounded by granule-cell-sparse regions. As was shown by Welker (b71,b76), and in our own mapping studies (see Fig. 3), this discontinuous pattern of granular, or koniocortical, zones contains within itself a map of the ratbs cutaneous periphery. There are clear subtypes within this cytoarchitectural subregion, notably including the bgranular aggregateb type of cytoarchitecture characteristic of the paw, limb, and mystacial vibrissae areas, and the bbarrel-fieldb type (originally described by Woolsey and Van der Loos, b70) seen in the nose and perioral regions. In the mouse, but not the rat, such barrels also cover the whole whisker representation (Welker and Woolsey, b74).

name: radial element
description: Radial elements are the internal skeletal supports of the median and paired fins.

name: 3rd arch mesenchyme from neural crest
description: Mesenchyme that develops_from a neural crest and is part of a 3rd arch mesenchyme.

name: neural spine 3
description: Neural spine that is associated with the third vertebra.

name: cerebellar glomerulus
description: An intertwined cluster of nerve fibers surrounded by glia where mossy fibers from the pontine nuclei in the white matter synapse with granule cell axons, Golgi cell axons and unipolar brush interneuron axons

name: bulbar conjunctiva
description: The conjunctiva covering the anterior surface of the sclera and the surface epithelium of the cornea.

name: maxillary barbel
description: Barbel that is attached to the distal end of the maxilla and that originates on the side of the mouth. Maxillary barbel is paired.

name: metanephric short nephron
description: Short nephrons are associated with mid-cortical and superficial glomeruli, are situated entirely in the outer medulla, and have no thin ascending limb[GO].

name: amiculum
description: a dense surrounding coat of white fibers, as the sheath of the inferior olive and of the dentate nucleus.

name: anatomical line
description: Non-material anatomical entity of one dimension, which forms a boundary of an anatomical surface or is a modulation of an anatomical surface.

name: superficial cervical thymus
description: A cervical thymus that is located directly beneath the skin.

name: hindlimb muscle
description: Any muscle organ that is part of a hindlimb [Automatically generated definition].

name: CA2 stratum lacunosum moleculare
description: Part of stratum lacunosum-moleculare lying in area CA2, superficial to the CA2 stratum radiatum, that is continuous with the stratum lacunosum-moleculare in areas CA3 and CA1

name: skin sebaceous gland
description: A holocrine gland of the dermis that secretes sebum into hair follicles.

name: body of corpus callosum
description: An area within the corpus callosum, a white matter structure within the cleft that separates the left and right cerebral hemispheres in the mammalian brain, between the genu (anterior region) and the splenium (posterior region).

name: mucosa of prostatic urethra
description: A mucosa that is part of a prostatic urethra [Automatically generated definition].

name: head of rib
description: The head of the rib is the end of a rib closest to the vertebral column, with which it articulates with.

name: uterus
description: the female muscular organ of gestation in which the developing embryo or fetus is nourished until birth

name: left renal medulla interstitium
description: A renal medulla interstitium that is part of a left kidney.

name: zona fasciculata of adrenal gland
description: the wide middle zone of the adrenal cortex that produces cortisol (hydrocortisone)

name: neural tissue
description: Portion of tissue in the nervous system which consists of neurons and glial cells, and may also contain parts of the vasculature.

name: ophthalmotemporal branch of external ophthalmic artery
sympathetic nerve plexus
description: A nerve plexus that is part of a sympathetic nervous system.

name: right lung bronchiole
description: A bronchiole that is part of a right lung [Automatically generated definition].

name: intercostal vein
description: The intercostal veins are a group of veins which drain the area between the ribs.

name: vestibulo-auditory system
description: Sensory system responsible for the perception of spatial orientation and auditory stimuli.

name: auditory system
description: is the sensory system for the sense of hearing.

name: pelvic cartilage
description: Cartilage element associated with the pelvic fin in aulopiform fishes.

name: median fin radial element
description: Radial element that is part of a median fin.

name: brush border layer
description: The microvilli-covered surface of simple cuboidal epithelium and simple columnar epithelium cells found in certain locations of the body. Found in small intestine and kidney

name: constrictor laryngis anterior
description: Involved in the movement of the arytenoid cartilages.

name: cervical mucosa
description: Lining of the head of the uterus (cervix); contains large branched glands; does not undergo sloughing.

name: occipitalis
description: A belly of the occipitofrontalis muscle that is near the occipital bone

name: dorsal marginal zone
description: Marginal zone that is a key embryonic tissue region of the early gastrula stage embryo and that houses the Spemann-Mangold organizer.

name: myotome somite 13
description: Portion of the somite giving rise to body wall muscle masses. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: dopaminergic cell groups
description: collections of neurons in the central nervous system that have been demonstrated by histochemical fluorescence to contain the neurotransmitter dopamine ( Fuxe-1970 )

name: association cortex
description: Region of the cerebral cortex that integrates diverse sensory or motor information for purposeful action.

name: pons reticulospinal tract
description: Axon tract that carries efferent (outgoing) action potentials from the cell body in the pons towards target cells in the spinal cord.

name: innermost intercostal muscle
description: The Innermost intercostal muscle is a layer of intercostal muscle beneath the intercostal nerves and internal intercostal muscles. These are divided into transversus thoracis anteriorly, lateral muscle slips laterally and subcostalis posteriorly.

name: middle phalanx of digit 5
description: A middle phalanx that is part of a digit 5 [Automatically generated definition].

name: lens vesicle epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a lens vesicle.

name: hypoglossal nucleus
description: Nucleus forming a longitudinal cell column in the medulla, close beneath the floor of the 4th ventricle, containing motor neurons that innervate the muscles of the tongue (Brodal, Neurological Anatomy, 3rd ed., 1981, pg 453)

name: parieto-occipital sulcus
description: Only a small part of the Parietooccipital Fissure (or parieto-occipital sulcus) is seen on the lateral surface of the hemisphere, its chief part being on the medial surface. The lateral part of the parietooccipital fissure (Fig. 726) is situated about 5 cm. in front of the occipital pole of the hemisphere, and measures about 1.25 cm. in length. The medial part of the parietooccipital fissure (Fig. 727) runs downward and forward as a deep cleft on the medial surface of the hemisphere, and joins the calcarine fissure below and behind the posterior end of the corpus callosum. In most cases it contains a submerged gyrus. [WP,unvetted].

name: vagina smooth muscle
description: A portion of smooth muscle tissue that is part of a vagina [Automatically generated definition].

name: cervical division of cord spinal central canal
description: Part of central canal contained within the cervical spinal cord. It is continuous caudally with the thoracic spinal cord central canal and rostrally with the fourth ventricle of the brain via the obex

name: basal cistern
description: The enclosed space where the arachnoid membrane stretches between the two temporal lobes and encloses the cerebral peduncles including the structures contained in the interpeduncular fossa

name: wall of intestine
description: An anatomical wall that is part of a intestine [Automatically generated definition].

name: upper jaw incisor odontogenic papilla
description: An odontogenic papilla that is part of a upper jaw incisor.

name: olfactory trigone
description: A small triangular area in front of the anterior perforated substance. Its apex, directed forward, occupies the posterior part of the olfactory sulcus, and is brought into view by throwing back the olfactory tract (adapted from Wikipedia)

name: basal scute
description: A scute parte of the basal surface of the fin in Sarcopterygian fish

name: pseudofirmisternal girdle
description: Modified arciferal pectoral girdle in which the fusion of the epicoracoid cartilages in the interclavicle region is extended posteriorly. Thus, the cartilages no longer overlap freely, and functionally a partially firmisternal condition is created.

name: anterior dorsal fin basal cartilage (elasmobranchs)
description: The large cartilage of the anterior dorsal fin, on which the radials articulate distally.

name: iliolumbar artery
description: The iliolumbar artery is a branch of the posterior trunk of the internal iliac artery. [WP,unvetted].

name: dorsum
description: A major subdivision of an organism that is the entire part of the organism dorsal to a horizontal plane and bounded on one side by the same transverse plane. In vertebrares this includes the vertebral column..

name: fibula facet of femur
description: Facet on the femur for the fibula.

name: interhyal bone
description: Replacement bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates dorsally with the hyosymplectic cartilage or the articulation of the hyomandibula and symplectic.

name: pterosphenoid-orbitosphenoid joint
description: Joint that articulates the pterosphenoid and orbitosphenoid. Pterosphenoid-orbitosphenoid joint is paired.

name: margo anterior of scapula
description: Anterior margin of the scapula.

name: bladder lumen
description: A anatomical space that is enclosed by a urinary bladder.

name: upper pharyngeal 4 tooth
description: Tooth that is attached to the upper pharyngeal 4 tooth plate.

name: scapula cartilage element
description: A scapula endochondral element that is composed primarily of cartilage tissue.

name: obsolete predominantly gray regional part of hypothalamus
caval sphincter
description: A striated muscle sphincter that is an extension of the diaphragm and surrounds the vena cava.

name: secondary dentition
description: The teeth of adulthood that either replace or are added to the complement of deciduous teeth. (Boucher's Clinical Dental Terminology, 4th ed)

name: infraorbital 11
description: Infraorbital that is the eleventh bone of the infraorbital series.

name: outer renal medulla peritubular capillary
description: A peritubular capillary that is part of a outer medulla of kidney.

name: median dorsal digital artery for digit 1
cardiac muscle of left atrium
description: A portion of cardiac muscle tissue that is part of a left atrium [Automatically generated definition].

name: reticular membrane of spiral organ
description: A reticular lamina of epithelium that is part of a spiral organ of cochlea.

name: vasculature of retina
description: A vasculature that is part of a retina [Automatically generated definition].

name: exoccipital endochondral element
description: A exoccipital bone or its cartilage or pre-cartilage precursor.

name: costo-cervical trunk
description: The costocervical trunk arises from the upper and back part of the subclavian artery, behind the scalenus anterior on the right side, and medial to that muscle on the left side. Passing backward, it splits into the deep cervical artery and the supreme intercostal artery (or the Highest intercostal artery), which descends behind the pleura in front of the necks of the first and second ribs, and anastomoses with the first aortic intercostal (3rd posterior intercostal artery). As it crosses the neck of the first rib it lies medial to the anterior division of the first thoracic nerve, and lateral to the first thoracic ganglion of the sympathetic trunk. In the first intercostal space, it gives off a branch which is distributed in a manner similar to the distribution of the aortic intercostals. The branch for the second intercostal space usually joins with one from the highest aortic intercostal artery. This branch is not constant, but is more commonly found on the right side; when absent, its place is supplied by an intercostal branch from the aorta. Each intercostal gives off a posterior branch which goes to the posterior vertebral muscles, and sends a small spinal branch through the corresponding intervertebral foramen to the medulla spinalis and its membranes. [WP,unvetted].

name: cervical sinus of His
description: A temporary depression caudal to the second pharyngeal arch, containing the succeeding pharyngeal arches; it is overgrown by the second pharyngeal arch and closes off as the cervical vesicle. This sinus is bounded in front by the hyoid arch, and behind by the thoracic wall.

name: leg nerve
description: A nerve that is part of a leg [Automatically generated definition].

name: adult head segment
description: Segment of the adult head.

name: white matter of occipital lobe
description: A white matter of cerebral lobe that is part of a occipital lobe.

name: metaphysis of tibia
description: A metaphysis that is part of a tibia.

name: obsolete cell part
description: Anatomical structure that is a direct part of the cell.

name: sphincter of hepatopancreatic ampulla
description: muscular valve that controls the flow of digestive juices (bile and pancreatic juice) through the ampulla of Vater into the second part of the duodenum. Relaxed by the hormone Cholecystokinin (CCK) via vasoactive intestinal polypeptide (VIP).[WP].

name: central cardiac conduction system
description: Cardiac conduction system, characterized by slow impulse propagation and prolonged refractory periods.

name: floor plate
description: The specialized glial structure (non-neuronal cells) situated at the ventral midline of the embryonic neural tube; this structure spans the anteroposterior axis from the midbrain to the tail regions, separating the left and right basal plates of the developing neural tube, and serves as an organizer to ventralize tissues in the embryo as well as to guide neuronal positioning and differentiation along the dorsoventral axis of the neural tube.

name: pronephric glomerulus
description: The glomus forms from the splanchnic intermediate mesoderm and is the vascularized filtration unit, filtering the blood before it enters the tubules. The glomus is external to the nephron and extends over more than one body segment.

name: Ammon's horn
description: A part of the brain consisting of a three layered cortex located in the forebrain bordering the medial surface of the lateral ventricle. The term hippocampus is often used synonymously with hippocampal formation which consists of the hippocampus proper or Cornu Ammonis, the dentate gyrus and the subiculum.

name: choroidal gland
description: A gland that is part of a optic choroid.

name: manual digitopodium region
description: A digitopodium region that is part of a manus[Obol]. This includes the fingers and metacarpal region, but excludes the carpal region.

name: ciliary epithelium
description: A double layer covering the ciliary body that produces aqueous humor.

name: floor plate of neural tube
description: A floor plate that is part of a neural tube [Automatically generated definition].

name: myocardium of anterior wall of left ventricle
myelin
description: A dielectric (electrically insulating) material consisting of protein and fat that forms a layer, the myelin sheath, usually around only the axon of a neuron. Myelin is about 40 % water; the dry mass of myelin is about 70 - 85 % lipids and about 15 - 30 % proteins. Some of the proteins that make up myelin are myelin basic protein (MBP), myelin oligodendrocyte glycoprotein (MOG), and proteolipid protein (PLP). The primary lipid of myelin is a glycolipid called galactocerebroside (GalC). The intertwining hydrocarbon chains of sphingomyelin serve to strengthen the myelin sheath.

name: lacrimal gland bud
description: the single bud-like invagination of the conjunctival fornix epithelium at the temporal aspect of the eye that signals lacrimal gland formation (Int Rev Cytol. 1996;168:1-80. Cell biology of the harderian gland)

name: caudal principal ray set
description: Anatomical cluster including all segmented-and-branched rays plus one unbranched but segmented ray located at the leading margin in each lobe of the caudal fin (Hubbs and Lagler, 1947) and that associates with endoskeletal elements such as hypurals and hemal spines of preural centra 1 and 2 (Arratia, 2008). Caudal principal rays are counted from the dorsalmost one ventrally. Caudal principal rays are unpaired median bones.

name: major salivary gland
description: One of the three largest glands of the oral cavity that secrete most of the saliva, including the parotid, submandibular, and sublingual glands.

name: manual digit 6 digitopodial skeleton
description: A subdivision of the skeleton of the autopod consisting of the phalanges of manual digit 6 plus the associated metapodial element.

name: columnella
description: A central anatomical feature of a coiled snail shell or gastropod shell. It is often only clearly visible as a structure when the shell is broken, or sliced in half vertically, or in an X-ray.

name: dilatator fossa
description: Fossa located on the neurocranium that is formed from portions of the sphenotic, frontal and pterotic bones.

name: tympanic nerve
description: The tympanic nerve (nerve of Jacobson) is a branch of the glossopharyngeal nerve found near the ear.

name: anterior ethmoidal foramen
description: The anterior ethmoidal foramen, situated about the middle of the lateral margin of the olfactory groove, transmits the anterior ethmoidal vessels and the anterior ethmoidal nerve; the nerve runs in a groove along the lateral edge of the cribriform plate to the slit-like opening above mentioned.

name: spinal cord dorsal column
description: the wedge-shaped fiber bundle of white matter in the dorsomedial side of the spinal cord that is made up of the fasciculus gracilis and fasciculus cuneatus; it is part of the ascending posterior column-medial lemniscus pathway that is important for well-localized fine touch and conscious proprioception

name: haversian canal
description: Haversian canals are a series of tubes around narrow channels formed by lamellae. This is the region of bone called compact bone. Osteons are arranged in parallel to the long axis of the bone. The Haversian canals surround blood vessels and nerve cells throughout the bone and communicate with osteocytes in lacunae (spaces within the dense bone matrix that contain the living bone cells) through canaliculi. This unique arrangement is conducive to mineral salt deposits and storage which gives bone tissue its strength.

name: crus commune
description: A region formed by non-ampulated ends of posterior and superior semicircular canals of vestibular apparatus in inner ear.

name: obsolete muscle of body wall
description: Any muscle organ that is part of a body wall [Automatically generated definition].

name: presumptive retinal pigmented epithelium
description: Portion of tissue that is the outer layer of the optic cup and will become the retinal pigmented epithelium.

name: bulbus cordis myocardium
description: A myocardium that is part of a bulbus cordis [Automatically generated definition].

name: muscle of posterior compartment of hindlimb stylopod
description: Any of the posterior thigh muscles. [WP,modified].

name: margo choanalis
description: Margin between the prechoanal and postchoanal process. It bounds the fenestra endochoanalis.

name: fast muscle tissue
description: The paler-colored muscle tissue of some mammals, composed of fast twitch muscle fibers.

name: optic recess of third ventricle
description: Recess in third ventricle lying in front of the optic chiasm at the base of the lamina terminalis

name: tip of external ear
description: Subdivision of the head consisting of the pointed or rounded end or extremity of the external ear.

name: brain ventricle/choroid plexus
description: The brain ventricles or their associated choroid plexuses

name: intramembranous bone
description: Bone tissue forms directly within mesenchyme, and does not replace other tissues[TAO]. Intramembranous ossification is the formation of bone in which osteoblasts secrete a collagen-proteoglycan matrix that binds calcium salts and becomes calcified[GO]. Intramembranous ossification is the way flat bones and the shell of a turtle are formed[GO]. Unlike endochondral ossification, cartilage is not present during intramembranous ossification[WP].

name: procoelous
description: Holochordal vertebral centra that are concave anteriorly and convex posteriorly; they bear a condyle on the posterior end for the articulation with the posterior adjacent vertebral centrum, forming a ball-and-socket joint that allows extensive motion in most directions.

name: border of sublaminar layers S4 and S5
description: The intersection of sublaminar layers S4 and S5.

name: anterior division of bed nuclei of stria terminalis
description: One of two divisions of the nuclei of stria terminalis based on topology, connectivity and multiple stains in the rat ( Swanson-2004 ) and the mouse ( Dong-2004 ). The other division consists of the posterior nuclei of stria terminalis. The anterior division includes the anterolateral area of stria terminalis, anteromedial area of stria terminalis, oval nucleus of stria terminalis, juxtacapsular nucleus of stria terminalis, rhomboid nucleus of stria terminalis, dorsomedial nucleus of stria terminalis, fusiform nucleus of stria terminalis, ventral nucleus of stria terminalis, and the magnocellular nucleus of stria terminalis

name: lamina propria of bronchus
description: A lamina propria that is part of a bronchus [Automatically generated definition].

name: chorda tympani branch of facial nerve
description: The chorda tympani is a nerve that branches from the facial nerve (cranial nerve VII) inside the facial canal, just before the facial nerve exits the skull via the stylomastoid foramen. Chorda tympani is a branch of the facial nerve (the seventh cranial nerve) that serves the taste buds in the front of the tongue, runs through the middle ear, and carries taste messages to the brain. The chorda tympani is part of one of three cranial nerves that are involved in taste. The taste system involves a complicated feedback loop, with each nerve acting to inhibit the signals of other nerves. The chorda tympani appears to exert a particularly strong inhibitory influence on other taste nerves, as well as on pain fibers in the tongue. When the chorda tympani is damaged, its inhibitory function is disrupted, leading to less inhibited activity in the other nerves.

name: obsolete predominantly white regional part of septum pellucidum
parietal of mesothelium of pericardio-peritoneal canal
obsolete regional part of cervical spinal cord
chitin-based acellular structure
description: Acellular anatomical structure whose predominant constituent is chitin.

name: obturator internus
description: The obturator internus muscle originates on the medial surface of the obturator membrane, the ischium near the membrane, and the rim of the pubis. It exits the pelvic cavity through the lesser sciatic foramen. The obturator internus is situated partly within the lesser pelvis, and partly at the back of the hip-joint. It functions to help laterally rotate extended thigh and abduct flexed thigh, as well as to steady the femoral head in the acetabulum.

name: epibranchial 3 bone
description: Epibranchial bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with ceratobranchial 3 cartilage or bone and medially with pharyngobranchial cartilage or bone.

name: M. coracobrachialis longus
description: Muscle which originates as a long belly from the dorsal coracoid near the sternum and inserts on the shaft of the humerus.

name: transverse palatine fold
description: Any of the the series of transverse folds (ridges) of the mucosa located on the anterior third part of the secondary (hard) palate of most mammalian species.

name: ruminant stomach
description: The ruminants' stomach consists of four compartments: rumen, reticulum, omasum and abomasum. The first three compartments comprise the forestomach (proventriculus). They are lined with nonglandular membrane. The fourth compartment, the abomasum comprises the true stomach of the ruminants. It is lined with glandular mucous membrane. The rumen lies on the left of the abdominal cavity, the reticulum cranially and the omasum on the right. The abomasum lies ventrally, its proximal end lies ventral to the rumen, reticulum and omasum

name: systemic venous system
description: The part of the venous system that drains the general body tissues[Kardong]

name: thoracic vertebra 7
description: The seventh thoracic vertebra counting from the top down. Note that members of this class are not necessarily homologous[ncit,modified].

name: proisocortex
description: The part of the neocortex hich mainly consists of parts of cingulate, parahippocampal and temporopolar cortice. As distinct from isocortex (typical neocortex) which contains other regions.

name: entire sense organ system
description: Sum of all sensory systems in an organism.

name: temporal vein
description: Any of the veins draining the temporal region.

name: prosomere
description: A neuromere that is part of the presumptive forebrain

name: pectoral muscle
description: Muscles of the upper chest. The term may refer to one of two muscles, the pectoralis major and pectoralis minor. The former is a thick muscle in the anterior portion of the chest. Its action involves flexion, medial rotation, and adduction of the humerus. The latter is a thin muscle located beneath the pectoralis major. Its action involves lowering the scapula and raising the ribs.

name: pontine tegmentum
description: Dorsal portion of the pons, containing cranial nervee nuclei, ascending and descending tracts and reticular nuclei. It is continuous with the reticular formation of the medulla (Carpenter, A Core Text of Neuroanatomy, 3rd ed, 1985, pg 133).

name: paraventricular nucleus of the hypothalamus magnocellular division - anterior magnocellular part
organ
description: Anatomical structure that performs a specific function or group of functions [WP].

name: Purkinje cell layer of cerebellar cortex
description: The Purkinje cell layer lies just underneath the molecular layer of the cerebellar cortex. It contains the neuronal cell bodies of the Purkinje cells that are arranged side by side in a single layer. Candelabrum interneurons are vertically oriented between the Purkinje cells. Purkinje neurons are inhibitory and provide the output of the cerebellar cortex through axons that project into the white matter. Extensive dendritic trees from the Purkinje cells extend upward in a single plane into the molecular layer where they synapse with parallel fibers of granule cells.

name: skeletal muscle tissue of temporalis
description: A portion of skeletal muscle tissue that is part of a temporalis [Automatically generated definition].

name: medial vestibular nucleus
description: The medial vestibular nucleus is one of the vestibular nuclei. It is located in the medulla oblongata. Lateral vestibulo-spinal tract (lateral vestibular nucleus 'Deiters')- via ventrolateral medulla and spinal cord to ventral funiculus (lumbo-sacral segments). Ipsilaterally for posture Medial vestibulo-spinal tract (medial, lateral, inferior, vestibular nuclei), bilateral projection via descending medial longitudinal fasciculus to cervical segments. DESCENDING MLF. Bilaterally for head/neck/eye movements [WP,unvetted].

name: vallecula of cerebellum
description: On the upper surface of the cerebellum the vermis is elevated above the level of the hemispheres, but on the under surface it is sunk almost out of sight in the bottom of a deep depression between them; this depression is called the vallecula of the cerebellum, and lodges the posterior part of the medulla oblongata.

name: posterior tibial vein
description: A vein of the lower limb carries blood from the posterior compartment and plantar surface of the foot to the popliteal vein which it forms when it joins with the anterior tibial vein. Like most deep veins, the posterior tibial vein is accompanied by an artery of the same name, the posterior tibial artery, along its course. [WP,unvetted].

name: corneal stroma collagen fibril
description: The connective tissue bundles in the extracellular matrix of corneal stroma that are composed of collagen, and play a role in tissue strength and elasticity

name: post-juvenile adult stage
description: The stage of being a sexually mature adult animal.

name: zygomatic plate
description: In rodent anatomy, the zygomatic plate is a bony plate derived from the flattened front part of the zygomatic arch (cheekbone). At the back, it connects to the front (maxillary) root of the zygomatic arch, and at the top it is connected to the rest of the skull via the antorbital bridge. It is part of the maxillary bone, or upper jaw, which also contains the upper cheekteeth. Primitively, rodents have a nearly horizontal zygomatic plate. In association with specializations in zygomasseteric system, several distinct morphologies have developed across the order. The term is also used for an analogous structure in some South American typotheres, including Pseudotypotherium and Medistylus.

name: secondary somatosensory cortex
description: the area of the upper bank of the lateral sulcus that is involved in somatic sensation

name: 4th arch mesenchyme from neural crest
description: Mesenchyme that develops_from a neural crest and is part of a 4th arch mesenchyme.

name: supraneural 1 bone
description: Supraneural bone located dorsal to vertebra 1.

name: ventral lateral line
description: ventral sensory canal line in fish, ventral to dorsal lateral lane

name: muscle structure
description: Muscle structures are contractile cells, tissues or organs that are found in multicellular organisms[GO].

name: conjunctival fornix
description: The space formed by the junction of the bulbar and palpebral portions of the conjunctiva, that of the upper lid being the superior conjunctival fornix (fornix conjunctivae superior) and that of the lower lid, the inferior conjunctival fornix (fornix conjunctivae inferior); the fornix is loose and flexible, allowing the free movement of the lids and eyeball.

name: inter-basipterygium joint
description: Joint that articulates the left and right basipterygium cartilage or bone. Inter-basipterygium joint is unpaired.

name: pectinate line
description: The pectinate line (anocutaneous line, dentate line, anorectal junction) is a line which divides the upper 2/3rds and lower 1/3rd of the anal canal. Developmentally, this line represents the hindgut-proctodeum junction. It is an important anatomical landmark, and several distinctions can be made based upon the location of a structure relative to this line:

name: metanephric short descending thin limb
description: The metanephric short descending thin limb is the descending thin limb of a short nephron in the metanephros that has a squamous epithelial morphology[GO].

name: proximal head of humerus
description: Hemispherical structure on proximal epiphysis of humerus that articulates with glenoid cavity[WP,modified].

name: deep cervical thymus
description: A cervical thymus that is located deep in the ventral cervical region, superficial to hyoid, sternomastoid, and depressor neck muscles.

name: ventral funiculus of spinal cord
description: The white substance of the spinal cord lying on either side between the ventral median fissure and the ventral roots of the spinal nerves.

name: hindlimb joint
description: A limb joint that is part of a hindlimb [Automatically generated definition].

name: manual digit muscle
description: Any muscle organ that is part of a finger [Automatically generated definition].

name: abdominal mammary gland
description: A lactiferous gland that is part of the abdominal region [Automatically generated definition].

name: mucosa of intermediate urethra
description: A mucosa that is part of a membranous urethra [Automatically generated definition].

name: obsolete predominantly gray part of Intralaminar nuclear group
zona reticularis of adrenal gland
description: the inner zone of the adrenal cortex that produces the enzymes that convert pregnenolone, a 21-carbon steroid, to 19-carbon steroids

name: splanchnic nerve
description: The major nerves supplying sympathetic innervation to the abdomen, including the greater, lesser, and lowest (or smallest) splanchnic nerves that are formed by preganglionic fibers from the spinal cord which pass through the paravertebral ganglia and then to the celiac ganglia and plexuses and the lumbar splanchnic nerves carry fibers which pass through the lumbar paravertebral ganglia to the mesenteric and hypogastric ganglia.

name: Ongur, Price, and Ferry (2003) area Iapm
stomodeum
description: Anterior part of the embryonic digestive tract that develops into a mouth. The stomodeum includes as parts an invagination of the ectoderm and the stomodeal cavity.

name: subserosal plexus
description: The subserous part of the enteric plexus of autonomic nerves

name: left lung bronchiole
description: A bronchiole that is part of a left lung [Automatically generated definition].

name: intercostal space
description: A space in the rib cage between two successive ribs.

name: plane of autotomy bisecting intervertebral joint
description: A plane of autotomy that divides an appendage in the space between vertebrae.

name: spleen
description: the organ that functions to filter blood and to store red corpuscles and platelets

name: white matter of the cerebellar cortex
description: White matter that lies deep to the granular cell layer of the cerebellar cortex. It contains afferents to the cerebellar cortex and axons that run between the cerebellar cortex and the deep cerebellar nuclei.

name: striated border microvillus layer
description: A microvillus layer that is striated and found in the intestine.

name: dorsal tooth row
description: Tooth row that is the dorsalmost row of teeth on ceratobranchial 5 bone.

name: capillary layer of choroid
description: The capillary lamina of choroid or choriocapillaris is a layer of capillaries that is immediately adjacent to Bruch's membrane in the choroid.

name: ectocervix
description: The part of the cervix uteri that protrudes into the vagina and is lined with stratified squamous epithelium.

name: pars superior ear
description: The dorsal part of the ear. Comprises the three semicircular canals, which connect to the utricle.

name: cleidooccipital muscle
description: A muscle organ that attaches_to a clavicle and attaches_to a occipital bone.

name: myotome somite 17
description: Portion of the somite giving rise to body wall muscle masses. immel et al, 1995.

name: pectoral fin ray 4
description: Pectoral fin lepidotrichium that, in a linear sequence, is the fourth most anterior pectoral ray that it is usually branched and segmented.

name: trunk ganglion
description: Ganglion which is located in the trunk.

name: medulla reticulospinal tract
description: Axon tract that carries efferent (outgoing) action potentials from the cell body in the medulla towards target cells in the spinal cord[GO].

name: subcostal muscle
description: The Subcostales (Infracostales) consist of muscular and aponeurotic fasciculi, which are usually well-developed only in the lower part of the thorax; each originates from the inner surface of one rib, and is inserted into the inner surface of the second or third rib above, near its angle. Their fibers run in the same direction as those of the Intercostales interni.

name: crus commune epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a crus commune.

name: inferior salivatory nucleus
description: In the brain, the inferior salivatory nucleus is a cluster of neurons controlling the parasympathetic input to the parotid gland. It is one of the components of the glossopharyngeal nerve. [WP,unvetted].

name: bone tissue of epiphysis
description: A portion of bone tissue that is part of a epiphysis [Automatically generated definition].

name: muscular coat of vas deferens
description: A muscular coat that is part of a vas deferens [Automatically generated definition].

name: lumbar division of spinal cord central canal
description: Part of central canal lying within the lumbar spinal cord. It is continuous rostrally with the central canal of the thoracic spinal cord and caudally with the central canal of the sacral spinal cord.

name: pontine cistern
description: The space located on lateral aspects of the pons at the junction with the celebellum

name: pancreatic acinus
description: The secretory units of the exocrine pancreas, where fluid containing digestive enzymes is produced; consists of a group of secretory cells surrounding a luminal space that connects to the pancreatic duct.

name: lower jaw incisor odontogenic papilla
description: An odontogenic papilla that is part of a lower jaw incisor.

name: paired limb/fin skeleton
description: The collection of all skeletal elements in an individual limb or fin.

name: pleural fluid
description: Transudate contained in the pleural cavity.

name: hindlimb interepipodial space
description: The space between the bones of the tibia and the fibula.

name: transversus epibranchialis 2
description: Dorsal gill-arch muscle connecting right and left epibranchial 2s. Springer and Johnson (2015)

name: pseudoarciferal girdle
description: Modified firmisternal pectoral girdle in which the epicoracoid cartilages are partly free and overlapping; however, the epicoracoids are fused to one another and the sternum postermodially.

name: antorbital cartilage
description: Cartilage element on the neurocranium of sawsharks and batoids, separate cartilages attached to the sides of the nasal capsules that support the sides or front of the head. [Compagno, L.J.V. Sharks of the world. An annotated and illustrated catalogue of shark species known to date. Volume 2. Bullhead, mackerel and carpet sharks (Heterodontiformes, Lamniformes and Orectolobiformes). FAO Species Catalogue for Fishery Purposes. No. 1, Vol. 2. Rome, FAO. 2001. 269p. ISBN 92-5-104543-7]

name: obturator artery
description: The obturator artery passes antero-inferiorly (forwards and downwards) on the lateral wall of the pelvis, to the upper part of the obturator foramen, and, escaping from the pelvic cavity through the obturator canal, it divides into both an anterior and a posterior branch. [WP,unvetted].

name: superior mesenteric vein
description: In anatomy, the superior mesenteric vein (SMV) is a blood vessel that drains blood from the small intestine. At its termination behind the neck of the pancreas, the SMV combines with the splenic vein to form the hepatic portal vein. The SMV lies to the right of the similarly named artery, the superior mesenteric artery, which originates from the abdominal aorta. [WP,unvetted].

name: tibial facet of femur
description: Facet on the femur for the tibia.

name: pancreatic lobule
description: A dense accumulation of exocrine glands in the pancreas often surrounding islets of Langerhans.

name: parasphenoid-basioccipital joint
description: Joint that articulates the parasphenoid and basioccipital. Parasphenoid-basioccipital joint is unpaired.

name: margo clavicularis
description: Inferior margin of the pars acromialis of the scapula, which articulates with the clavicule.

name: lumen of oropharynx
description: A anatomical space that is enclosed by a oropharynx.

name: upper pharyngeal 5 tooth plate
description: Pharyngeal toothplate that lies ventral to pharyngobranchial 4, and located posterior to upper pharyngeal 4 tooth plate.

name: scapula pre-cartilage condensation
description: A scapula endochondral element that is composed primarily of a pre-cartilage condensation.

name: ventral ramus of spinal nerve
description: Branch of spinal nerve that innervates the hypaxial muscles

name: sphincter colli superficialis muscle
description: The sphincter colli superficialis is composed of transverse muscle fibers, and covers the entire area between the lower jaw and chest. The muscle is used to tighten the skin on the underside of the throat.

name: infraorbital 1
description: Infraorbital in fishes that is the first (anteriormost) bone of the infraorbital series.

name: secondary tooth
description: A tooth that forms after a primary tooth

name: mucosa of ascending colon
description: A mucosa that is part of an ascending colon [Automatically generated definition].

name: infraorbital 12
description: Infraorbital that is the twelfth bone of the infraorbital series.

name: lateral dorsal digital artery for digit 5
cardiac muscle of right ventricle
description: A portion of cardiac muscle tissue that is part of a right ventricle [Automatically generated definition].

name: peritoneal mesentery
description: Mesentery that is located in the peritoneum.

name: actinopterygian parietal bone
description: Dermal bone that covers the otic region and may articulate with its antimere medially, with the frontal bone anteriorly, the pterotic laterally, the supraoccipital medio-posteriorly, and the epiotic and extrascapula latero-posteriorly. The parietal is a paired bone.[TAO]

name: digit 3 digitopodial skeleton
description: A subdivision of the skeleton of the autopod consisting of the phalanges of digit 3 plus the associated metapodial element.

name: femur endochondral element
description: A femur bone or its cartilage or pre-cartilage precursor.

name: naso-frontal vein
description: The nasofrontal vein is a vein in the eye which drains to the superior ophthalmic vein.

name: obsolete predominantly gray regional part of ventral posterolateral nucleus
cloacal membrane
description: The membrane that covers the embryonic cloaca, formed by the union of proctodeal (anal pit) ectoderm and cloacal endoderm, with no intervening mesoderm; the urorectal septum joins the cloacal membrane and divides it into an anal membrane and a urogenital membrane; the point where the urorectal septum intersects the cloacal membrane is the future site of the perineal body; proliferation of mesoderm and ectoderm around the cloacal membrane produces primordial tissues of the external genitalia in both sexes: the genital tubercle, genital folds, and genital swellings.

name: chest nerve
description: A nerve that is part of a chest [Automatically generated definition].

name: white matter of limbic lobe
description: A white matter of cerebral lobe that is part of a limbic lobe.

name: metaphysis of radius
description: A metaphysis that is part of a radius bone.

name: compound organ component
description: Multi-tissue structure that is part of a compound organ.

name: anal sphincter
description: A sphincter muscle that is part of a anal region.

name: peripheral cardiac conduction system
description: Portion of the cardiac conduction system, with rapid impulse propagation.

name: obsolete vitreous
description: Portion of organism substance that is a gelatinous extracellular matrix structure that fills the vitreous cavity of the eye.

name: distal tarsal bone 1 cartilage
description: A distal tarsal bone 1 endochondral element that is composed primarily of cartilage tissue.

name: epithelium of respiratory bronchiole
description: An epithelium that is part of a respiratory bronchiole [Automatically generated definition].

name: pedal digitopodium region
description: A digitopodium region that is part of a pes[Obol]. This includes the toes and metatarsal region, but excludes the tarsals region.

name: iris stroma
description: The delicate vascular connective tissue that lies between the anterior surface of the iris and the pars iridica retinae.

name: floor plate of midbrain
description: A floor plate that is part of a midbrain [Automatically generated definition].

name: myocardium of anterior wall of right ventricle
intestinal bulb epithelium
description: Intestinal epithelium which lines the lumen of the intestinal bulb.

name: strand of tylotrich hair
description: a single large hair, surrounded by neurovascular tissue at the level of the sebaceous gland, with a hair follicle innervated by a hair-tylotrich neuron (CL:1001436), a rapidly acting mechanoreceptor.

name: caudal procurrent ray set
description: An anatomical cluster of short rays, shorter than the principal ones, which form the anterior dorsal and ventral series of lepidotrichia of the caudal fin that may be associated with neural spines, epurals and uroneurals (dorsal series) and haemal spines of preural vertebrae (ventral series) (Arratia, 2008). The anteriormost procurrent rays are commonly unsegmented, but the posteriormost ones are usually segmented. The procurrent rays are numbered from caudal to rostral direction. The caudal procurrent ray series is an unpaired median series.

name: renal straight tubule
description: Any region of a nephron tubule that is straight. Examples: distal convoluted tubule, proximal convoluted tuble.

name: manual digit 7 digitopodial skeleton
description: A subdivision of the skeleton of the autopod consisting of the phalanges of manual digit 7 plus the associated metapodial element.

name: prezygapophysis of thoracic vertebra
description: A prezygapophysis that is part of a thoracic vertebra.

name: epaxial region somite 1
description: Somite-derived body wall muscle present dorsal to the horizontal myoseptum. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: columnella muscle
description: The muscle of the central column or axis of a spiral univalve shell.

name: entorhinal cortex layer 1
description: Layer of the entorhinal cortex that is most superficial, continuous with layer 1 of adjacent neocortex and the molecular layer of the subiculum, lying deep to the pial layer and superficial to layer 2. It is relatively acellular consisting mostly of fibers running transversely relative to the cortical surface (Adapted from Paxinos, G. The rat central nervous system, 2nd ed, Academic Press, San Diego, 1995, pg. 474)

name: anatomical point
description: Non-material anatomical entity of zero dimension, which forms a boundary of an anatomical line or surface.

name: coelomic fluid
description: A bodily fluid that is located in the coelom.

name: ventrolateral sulcus of medulla oblongata
description: A longitudinal sulcus on the anterior surface of the medulla oblongata, lateral to the pyramid, from which emerge the fibers of the hypoglossal nerve.

name: epaxial region somite 11
description: Somite-derived body wall muscle present dorsal to the horizontal myoseptum. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: posterior ethmoidal foramen
description: The posterior ethmoidal foramen opens at the back part of this margin under cover of the projecting lamina of the sphenoid, and transmits the posterior ethmoidal vessels and nerve.

name: spinal cord lateral column
description: the region of white matter of the spinal cord that is located between the dorsal and ventral spinal roots

name: adrenal/interrenal gland
description: This gland can either be a discrete structure located bilaterally above each kidney, or a cluster of cells in the head kidney that perform the functions of the adrenal gland. In either case, this organ consists of two cells types, aminergic chromaffin cells and steroidogenic cortical cells[GO]

name: dorsal mesocardium
description: The part of the mesocardium dorsal to the embryonic heart; it breaks down to form the transverse sinus of the pericardium.

name: axial muscle
description: One of the skeletal muscles of the head and neck, spine, and ribs.

name: obsolete genital lymph node
description: The term tonsillar node can be inaccurate or ambiguous

name: presumptive neural retina
description: Portion of tissue that is the inner layer of the optic cup and will become the neural retina.

name: cuneocerebellar tract
description: White matter tract that originates from the cuneate and external cuneate nuclei. It relays ascending spinal fibers in the dorsal funiculus and conveys information from forelimbs to the cerebellum.

name: female inguinal ring
description: A inguinal ring that is part of a female reproductive system.

name: metanephric renal pelvis
description: A renal pelvis that is part of a metanephros.

name: crista vomeri
description: Ridge on the dorsal surface of the vomer that runs from the anterior to the postchoanal processes of the vomer; it takes part in the fixation of the bone to the lateral margin of the solum nasi.

name: lumen of digestive tract
description: An anatomical space that surrounded_by a digestive tract.

name: choroid plexus of third ventricle
description: Part of choroid plexus contained in the third ventricle

name: sheath of Schwann
description: The outermost nucleated cytoplasmic layer of Schwann cells that surrounds the axon of the neuron. It forms the outermost layer of the nerve fiber in the peripheral nervous system. The neurolemma is underlain by the basal lamina (referred to as the medullary sheath in the included illustrations. In CNS, axons are myelinated by oligodendrocytes, thus lack neurolemma.

name: prepectoral spine
description: Spine located anterior to the pectoral fin

name: blood-air barrier
description: The membrane between the capillary blood and alveolar air, comprised of the alveolar epithelium and the capillary epithelium and their adherent basement membranes and epithelial cell cytoplasm

name: cluster of hairs
description: A small collection or tuft of hairs.

name: haltere
description: The capitate stalk on both sides of the thorax having developed from the dorsal metathoracic wing-buds, it is freely movable and capable of vibration, representing the hind wing of Diptera; used for flight balance.

name: periosteum
description: the thick fibrous membrane that closely invests the entire surface of a bone except the articular cartilage at synovial joints

name: opisthocoelous
description: Ectochordal or stegochordal vertebral centra that are convex anteriorly and concave posteriorly; they bear a condyle on the anterior end for the articulation with the posterior adjacent vertebral centrum, forming a ball-and-socket joint that allows extensive motion in most directions.

name: border of sublaminar layers S2 and S3
description: The intersection of sublaminar layers S2 and S3.

name: epithelium of lobar bronchus
description: The tissue made up of epithelial cells that lines the inside of the lobar bronchus.

name: obsolete migratory slow muscle precursor cell
description: Cells that initially are located adjacent to the spinal cord and notochord along that migrate from their initial medial position radially through the myotome to the lateral surface of the somites.

name: superficial vein
description: Any of the veins carrying deoxygenated blood from the subcutaneous tissue layers.

name: small cardiac vein
description: A vein running parallel to the right coronary artery in the coronary sulcus that drains into the right extremity of the coronary sinus.

name: obsolete predominantly white regional part of cerebral peduncle
uterovesical pouch
description: The peritoneum over the rectum and the bladder is continued over the intestinal surface and fundus of the uterus on to its vesical surface, which it covers as far as the junction of the body and cervix uteri, and then to the bladder, forming here a second, but shallower, pouch, the vesicouterine excavation (or uterovesical pouch). The vesicouterine excavation is close to the anterior fornix of the vagina.

name: superficial lymphatic vessel
description: The tubules that carry lymph throughout the body that are just beneath the surface of the skin.

name: maxillomandibular part of trigeminal ganglion complex
falx cerebelli
description: A small triangular process of dura matter beginning at the internal occipital crest just beneath the tentorium and projecting forward.

name: posterior external jugular vein
description: A vein that drains the superficial muscles and integument of the upper back portion of the neck into the external jugular vein.

name: surface of tongue
description: An anatomical surface that is part of a tongue.

name: venous system
description: The part of the cardiovascular system consisting of all venous vessels. In vertebrates with a double circulation, this can be divided into systemic and pulmonary portions.

name: Brodmann (1909) area 46
description: Brodmann area 46, or BA46, is part of the frontal cortex in the human brain. It is between BA10 and BA45. BA46 is known as middle frontal area 46. In the human it occupies approximately the middle third of the middle frontal gyrus and the most rostral portion of the inferior frontal gyrus. Brodmann area 46 roughly corresponds with the dorsolateral prefrontal cortex (DLPFC), although the borders of area 46 are based on cytoarchitecture rather than function. The DLPFC also encompasses part of granular frontal area 9, directly adjacent on the dorsal surface of the cortex. Cytoarchitecturally, BA46 is bounded dorsally by the granular frontal area 9, rostroventrally by the frontopolar area 10 and caudally by the triangular area 45 (Brodmann-1909). There is some discrepancy between the extent of BA8 (Brodmann-1905) and the same area as described by Walker (1940)

name: neural decussation
description: Nerve fibers crossing the midline of the neuraxis relative to their point of origin, on a course to from one level of the nervous system to another. (CUMBO, Heimer, L. The Human Brain, 2nd ed., 1995, pg 6)

name: thoracic vertebra 9
description: The ninth thoracic vertebra counting from the top down. Note that members of this class are not necessarily homologous[ncit,modified].

name: midbrain neuromere
description: A neuromere that is part of the presumptive midbrain

name: ascending aorta
description: The ascending aorta is the portion of the aorta in a two-pass circulatory system that lies between the heart and the arch of aorta[GO]. A portion of the aorta commencing at the upper part of the base of the left ventricle, on a level with the lower border of the third costal cartilage behind the left half of the sternum; it passes obliquely upward, forward, and to the right, in the direction of the heart's axis, as high as the upper border of the second right costal cartilage, describing a slight curve in its course, and being situated, about 6 cm behind the posterior surface of the sternum. The total length is about 5 cm in length [Wikipedia]

name: principal part of ventral posteromedial nucleus
organ subunit
description: A part of an organ that constitutes a distinct modular sub-unit. In some cases, the organ may also contain other sub-units of identical or similar types, in other cases this may be a distinct entity.

name: skeletal muscle tissue of levator palpebrae superioris
description: A portion of skeletal muscle tissue that is part of a levator palpebrae superioris [Automatically generated definition].

name: tongue
description: A muscular organ in the floor of the mouth.

name: cricopharyngeal ligament
description: Laryngeal ligament that connects the cricoid cartilage to the pharynx[WP,modified]

name: small saphenous vein
description: The small saphenous vein (also lesser saphenous vein), is a relatively large vein of the superficial posterior leg. [WP,unvetted].

name: condylar joint
description: In a condyloid joint (condyloid articulation, ellipsoidal joint) an ovoid articular surface, or condyle, is received into an elliptical cavity. This permits movement in two planes, allowing flexion, extension, adduction, abduction, and circumduction.

name: lung connective tissue
description: the connective tissue located between the respiratory (airway and alveolar) epithelium, the capillary endothelium and pleural mesothelium; it contains basement membrane composed of collagen, elastin, proteoglycans, and fibronectin

name: rete mirabile
description: A rete mirabile (Latin for 'wonderful net'; plural retia mirabilia) is a complex of arteries and veins lying very close to each other, found in some vertebrates. The rete mirabile utilizes countercurrent blood flow within the net (blood flowing in opposite directions. ) It exchanges heat, ions, or gases between vessel walls so that the two bloodstreams within the rete maintain a gradient with respect to temperature, or concentration of gases or solutes.

name: gastropod albumen gland
description: The posterior oviduct opens into the large white albumen gland which adds a layer of albumen to the zygote before it reaches the egg capsule gland.

name: 6th arch mesenchyme from neural crest
description: Mesenchyme that develops_from a neural crest and is part of a 6th arch mesenchyme.

name: supraneural 1 cartilage
description: Postcranial axial cartilage located dorsal to vertebra 1.

name: thalamic glomerulus
description: Synaptic structure found in thalamic relay nuclei consising of a complex of afferent terminals, relay cell dendrites, interneuron dendrites and other processes. These complexes are surrounded by astrocytic processes.

name: ventral supracondylar tubercle
description: tubercle on the distal humerus for the origin of the Lig. collaterale ventral of the elbow joint. Modified from Baumel et al. 1993

name: os opticus
description: Scleral element located at the posterior pole of the scleral cartilage surrounding the foramen through which the optic nerve fibers pass. the internal architecture of this bone reveals a cancellous marrow cavity with fatty tissue.

name: mantle
description: A fold or lobe or pair of lobes of the body wall of a mollusk or brachiopod that in shell-bearing forms lines the shell and bears shell-secreting glands.

name: epineural
description: Some or all epineural bones ossify free from the neural arches in most teleosts. In some lower teleosts, e.g., Leptolepis, Hiodon, elopiforms and albuliforms, ossification proceeds from the attachment point of the ligament to the arch, and the epineural is a process of the neural arch. In many lower teleosts epineurals are forked proximally.

name: acetabular rim
description: A prominent unever rim that bounds the acetabulum, serving as the attachment for the acetabular labrum, which reduces its opening, and deepens the surface for formation of the hip joint.

name: thyroid vein
description: A vein that drains a thyroid gland.

name: substantia gelatinosa
description: Gelatinous-appearing material in the dorsal horn of the spinal cord, consisting chiefly of Golgi type II neurons and some larger nerve cells, corresponding to Rexed lamina II.

name: autopod joint
description: A limb joint that is part of an autopod [Automatically generated definition].

name: post-anal tail muscle
description: A muscle organ that attaches to a tail vertebra [Automatically generated definition].

name: respiratory system capillary endothelium
description: An endothelium of capillary that is part of a respiratory system [Automatically generated definition].

name: mucosa of lacrimal sac
description: A mucosa that is part of a lacrimal sac [Automatically generated definition].

name: olfactory gland
description: Bowman's glands (aka olfactory glands, glands of Bowman) are situated in the olfactory mucosa, beneath the olfactory epithelium, in the lamina propria, a connective tissue also containing fibroblasts, blood vessels, and bundles of fine axons from the olfactory neurons. The structure of the Bowman's glands consists of an acinus in the lamina propria and a secretory duct going out through the olfactory epithelium. Electron microscopy studies show that Bowman's glands contain cells with large secretory vesicles. Bowman's glands might secrete proteins such as Lysozyme, amylase and IgA similarly to serous glands. The exact composition of the secretions from Bowman's glands is unclear, but there is evidence that Bowman's glands do not produce odorant binding protein[WP].

name: obsolete predominantly gray regional part of midline nuclear group
inferior suprarenal artery
description: Each renal artery gives off some small inferior suprarenal branches to the suprarenal gland, the ureter, and the surrounding cellular tissue and muscles. [WP,unvetted].

name: recurrent laryngeal nerve
description: A branch of the vagus nerve that supplies motor function and sensation to the larynx (voice box). It travels within the endoneurium. It is the nerve of the 6th Branchial Arch.

name: subserosa
description: A layer of tissue between the muscularis and serosa.

name: posterior intercostal vein
description: The posterior intercostal veins are veins that drain the intercostal spaces posteriorly. They run with their corresponding posterior intercostal artery on the underside of the rib, the vein superior to the artery. Each vein also gives off a dorsal branch that drains blood from the muscles of the back. There are eleven posterior intercostal veins on each side. Their patterns are variable, but they are commonly arranged as: The 1st posterior intercostal vein, supreme intercostal vein, drains into the brachiocephalic vein or the vertebral vein. The 2nd and 3rd (and often 4th) posterior intercostal veins drain into the superior intercostal vein. The remaining posterior intercostal veins drain into the azygos vein on the right, or the hemiazygos vein on the left.

name: obsolete regional part of thoracic spinal cord white matter
liver
description: An exocrine gland which secretes bile and functions in metabolism of protein and carbohydrate and fat, synthesizes substances involved in the clotting of the blood, synthesizes vitamin A, detoxifies poisonous substances, stores glycogen, and breaks down worn-out erythrocytes[GO].

name: extrinsic post-anal tail muscle
description: A post-anal tail that attaches outside the tail.

name: gastralium
description: Dermal element that arises via intramembranous ossification and are developmentally distinct from true ribs that articulate with the vertebral column.

name: tooth 1V
description: Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is the anteriormost tooth in the ventral tooth row.

name: short microvillus layer
description: A layer of microvilli covering lymphocytes.

name: M. extensor digitorum communis longus
description: It arises on the lateral epicondyle of the humerus by two heads: the lateral one arises by a thin tendon in common with the m.extensor carpi ulnaris with fibers proximally fused. The internal one arises by a short tendon in common with proximally fused fibers of the m. extensor carpi radialis. It divides distally in two heads: the external head inserts with a long and thin tendon on the metacarpal V, at the same point of insertion of the m. abductor brevis dorsalis digiti V; the internal one inserts by a thin tendon on the proximal region of the metacarpal IV, between the m. extensor brevis superficialis digiti IV and the m. extensor brevis medius digiti IV (Pristimantis bogotensis).

name: obsolete regional part of a lobe of the cerebellum
intervertebral disk of third cervical vertebra
description: A intervertebral disk that connects a mammalian cervical vertebra 3 and connects a mammalian cervical vertebra 4.

name: sternooccipital muscle
description: A muscle organ that has_muscle_insertion a occipital bone and has_muscle_origin a sternum.

name: myotome somite 2
description: Portion of the somite giving rise to body wall muscle masses. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: sputum
description: Matter ejected from the lungs, bronchi, and trachea, through the mouth.

name: nociceptor
description: Peripheral receptors for pain. Nociceptors include receptors which are sensitive to painful mechanical stimuli, extreme heat or cold, and chemical stimuli. All nociceptors are free nerve endings.

name: neural keel
description: An intermediate stage (between the neural plate and neural rod) during the early segmentation period in the morphogenesis of the central nervous system primordium; the keel is roughly triangular shaped in cross section.

name: obsolete leg joint
