description: Joint in the leg. For example the knee, which separates the leg tibia and femur

name: secondary palatal shelf epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a secondary palatal shelf.

name: interpolar part of spinal trigeminal nucleus
bone tissue of distal epiphysis
description: A portion of bone tissue that is part of a distal epiphysis [Automatically generated definition].

name: femoral ridge
description: Low crest that arises just behind the acetabular head and extends distally for about one-third the length of the femoral shaft.

name: interlobar duct
description: A duct that is located between lobes, within conspicuous, thick connective tissue septa that separate lobes. All interlobar ducts are excretory.

name: respiratory system smooth muscle
description: A portion of smooth muscle tissue that is part of a respiratory system [Automatically generated definition].

name: forelimb skeleton
description: The collection of all skeletal elements in a free forelimb region. Excludes the pectoral girdle

name: cerebellomedullary cistern
description: The largest of the subarachnoid cisterns between the cerebellum and the medulla oblongata; it is divided into a posterior cerebellomedullary cistern located between the cerebellum and the posterior surface of the medulla (also called cisterna magna), and a lateral cerebellomedullary cistern located between the cerebellum and the lateral aspect of the medulla.

name: upper jaw incisor epithelium
description: A dental epithelium that is part of a upper jaw incisor.

name: terminal nerve
description: The terminal nerve, located anterior to cranial nerve I, is comprised of a group of cells with somata adjacent to the olfactory bulb and processes that extend anteriorly to the olfactory epithelium and posteriorly to the telencephalon. In teleost fish an additional group of axons extends along the optic tract and delivers putative neuromodulators to the retina. It is thought to develop from cranial neural crest.

name: stylopod
description: The proximal free limb segment. Includes as parts the stylopod skeleton.

name: stylopodial skeleton
description: Proximal element of a free limb skeleton consisting of the femur and humerus in the forelimb stylopodium and hindlimb stylopodium respectively[VSAO, modified].

name: urine
description: Excretion that is the output of a kidney

name: lateral plate
description: Body plates on the lateral sides of the body that occur as single bilateral rows and their number is highly heritable. Bell and Richkind (1981)

name: medial lemniscus of medulla
description: Part of medial lemniscus located within the medulla

name: inscriptional rib
description: Three pairs of cartilaginous elements posterior to the sternum that lie in the myosepta of the ventral trunk musculature.

name: supraneural element
description: Endochondral element that is median and located in the dorsal skeletogenous septum between the cranium and the dorsal fin.

name: duct of major vestibular gland
description: One of a pair of ducts leading from the Bartholin's glands to the surface of the vulva

name: collection of feathers
description: An anatomical cluster that consists of feathers.

name: superior gluteal artery
description: The superior gluteal artery (gluteal artery) is the largest branch of the internal iliac artery, and appears to be the continuation of the posterior division of that vessel. It is a short artery which runs backward between the lumbosacral trunk and the first sacral nerve, and, passing out of the pelvis above the upper border of the Piriformis, immediately divides into a superficial and a deep branch. Within the pelvis it gives off a few branches to the Iliacus, Piriformis, and Obturator internus, and just previous to quitting that cavity, a nutrient artery which enters the ilium. [WP,unvetted].

name: ectopterygoid bone
description: A palatal bone which -- like many palatal bones -- may originally have developed as a dermal bone replacing part of the palatoquadrate, the primitive upper jaw. Like the palatine (also called dermopalatine), the ectopterygoid replaces the middle part of the autopalatine. It may be serially homologous with the palatine(s), but is somewhat specialized, being the last (most posterior in palatal view) of the series and bordering the fossa for the jaw muscles. In a typical tetrapod it abuts the palatine anteriorly, the maxilla laterally, the pterygoid or the fossa mandubuaris medially, and the fossa posteriorly

name: common iliac vein
description: A vein that drains the pelvis and lower limbs into the inferior vena cava.

name: musculotendinous bundle
description: A collection of muscle and tendinous tissue.

name: ganglion of ciliary nerve
description: Any parasympathetic ganglion that extends fibers into the short ciliary nerve. Includes both the main and acccessory ciliary ganglia

name: premaxillary tooth row
description: Tooth row that is on the premaxilla.

name: upper pharyngeal 5 tooth
description: Tooth that is attached to the upper pharyngeal 5 tooth plate.

name: quadrate ventral process
description: Process that is the ventral, posteriorly-oriented bony extension of the quadrate.

name: sphincter colli profundus muscle
description: The sphincter colli profundus lies below the platysma in the area of the parotid gland (gland regions).

name: unerupted tooth
description: A normal developing tooth which has not yet perforated the oral mucosa or one that fails to erupt in the normal sequence or time interval expected for the type of tooth in a given gender, age, or population group.

name: mucosa of transverse colon
description: A mucosa that is part of a transverse colon [Automatically generated definition].

name: genital disc
description: Imaginal disc that gives rise to the internal and external genitalia, analia and adult hind gut (Cohen, 1993).

name: infraorbital 5
description: Infraorbital that is the fifth bone of the infraorbital series.

name: right subhepatic recess
description: The hepatorenal recess or subhepatic recess is the space that separates the liver from the right kidney. As a potential space, the recess is not filled with fluid under normal conditions. However, fluid can collect in this space in circumstances where the abdomen fills with fluid, such as hemoperitoneum. This fluid may be seen on ultrasound or computed tomography (CT scan).

name: cardiac muscle of left ventricle
description: A portion of cardiac muscle tissue that is part of a left ventricle [Automatically generated definition].

name: external nose
description: External part of the nose containing the external nares.

name: posterior fornix of vagina
description: The vaginal fornix that is behind the cervix. It is close to the recto-uterine pouch.

name: digit 4 digitopodial skeleton
description: A subdivision of the skeleton of the autopod consisting of the phalanges of digit 4 plus the associated metapodial element.

name: humerus endochondral element
description: A humerus bone or its cartilage or pre-cartilage precursor.

name: arm nerve
description: A nerve that is part of an arm [Automatically generated definition].

name: diaphysis of metacarpal bone
description: A diaphysis that is part of a metacarpal bone.

name: abdominal internal oblique muscle
description: The lateral abdominal wall muscle that is deep to the external oblique and superficial to the transversus.

name: yolk sac endoderm
description: The portion of the yolk sac that is derived from endoderm and lines the yolk sac.

name: simple organ
description: Multi-tissue structure that is not part of a compound organ.

name: gluteal muscle
description: On of the muscles that make up the buttocks: the gluteus maximus muscle, gluteus medius muscle and gluteus minimus muscle.

name: urethral sphincter
description: A sphincter muscle surrounding the urethra.

name: fulcrum
description: Dermal bone that is typically associated with a fin. Arratia, G. 2009. Identifying patterns of diversity of the actinopterygian fulcra. Acta Zoologica (Stockholm) 90 (Suppl. 1): 220-235.

name: distal tarsal bone 1 pre-cartilage condensation
description: A distal tarsal bone 1 endochondral element that is composed primarily of a pre-cartilage condensation.

name: cartilage of bronchus
description: The hyaline cartilaginous structures that support the bronchi, present as irregular rings in the larger bronchi (and not as regular as in the trachea), and as small plates and islands in the smaller bronchi; as the branching continues through the bronchial tree, the amount of hyaline cartilage in the walls decreases until it is absent in the smallest bronchioles[MP].

name: adnexa of uterus
description: The fallopian tubes and ovaries.

name: floor plate of telencephalon
description: A floor plate that is part of a telencephalon [Automatically generated definition].

name: calcaneum cartilage element
description: A calcaneum endochondral element that is composed primarily of cartilage tissue.

name: entire myelin sheath
description: The insulating envelope that surrounds nerve fibers or axons.

name: secretion of nictitans gland
description: A secretion that is produced by a nictitans gland, containing glycoprotein

name: pseudourostyle
description: An elongate lateral process ventrally placed to the proximal region of the pleurostyle. The pseudourostyle is paired.

name: trochophore stage
description: A larval stage of a trochozoan in which the organism is in free-swimming planktonic form with several bands of cilia[WP,modified].

name: manual digit 8 digitopodial skeleton
description: A subdivision of the skeleton of the autopod consisting of the phalanges of manual digit 8 plus the associated metapodial element.

name: postzygapophysis of lumbar vertebra
description: An postzygapophysis that is part of a lumbar vertebra.

name: epaxial region somite 12
description: Somite-derived body wall muscle present dorsal to the horizontal myoseptum. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: rumen epithelium
description: The rumen epithelium is the tissue which lines the largest of the four fore stomachs in the ruminant animal -cows and sheep. Rumen epithelial cells are important because they are responsible for the absorption of nutrients from the rumen into the blood.

name: entorhinal cortex layer 2
description: Layer of the entorhinal cortex lying superficial to layer 3 and deep to layer 1. It is characterized by medium-to large sized stellate cells that are grouped into prominent clusters, particularly in the rostral entorhinal cortex (Adapted from Paxinos, G. The rat central nervous system, 2nd ed, Academic Press, San Diego, 1995, pg. 474)

name: protandrous hermaphroditic organism
description: Sequential hermaphroditic organism that produces gametes first of the male sex, and then later of the female sex.

name: autopodial skeleton
description: The collection of all skeletal elements in an autopodium region.

name: anatomical surface
description: A two dimensional anatomical structure that is the boundary between an anatomical structure and an anatomical substance, an anatomical space or the organism's environment. Examples include the surface of your skin, the surface of the lining of your gut; the surface of the endothelium of you aorta that is in contact with blood.n

name: secondary prosencephalon
description: The most anterior region of the forebrain including both the telencephalon and the hypothalamus in the prosomeric model

name: pars endotympanica
description: This is present in the cat and forms the large medial part of the Bulla tympanica. It is not to be regarded as a part of the pars tympanica, which ossifies directly from connective tissue, whereas the Pars endotympanica is preformed in cartilage. The Septum bullae in the cat is formed by the Pars tympanica as well as by the Pars endotympanica(NOMINA ANATOMICA VETERINARIA (2005)).

name: lymph node of head
description: A lymph node that is part of a head.

name: spinal cord ventral column
description: the area of white matter of the spinal cord located on either side of the ventral (anterior) medial fissure

name: prepyriform area
description: Prepyriform area (or prepiriform cortex) is a portion of the rhinencephalon consisting of paleocortex. Some sources state that it is part of the primary olfactory cortex.

name: cervical mammary gland
description: A mammary gland that is part of a cervical region.

name: swim bladder bud
description: Embryonic structure that forms from the anterior gut epithelium at the level of the second somite that then matures to form the swim bladder.

name: dorsal mesogastrium
description: The portion of mesentery attached to the greater curvature of the stomach is named the dorsal mesentery (or dorsal mesogastrium, when referring to the portion at the stomach), and the part which suspends the colon is termed the mesocolon. The dorsal mesogastrium develops into the greater omentum.

name: ectepicondylar foramen
description: Formen present on the ectepicondyle of the humerus.

name: skeletal muscle tissue of trunk
description: A portion of skeletal muscle tissue in the trunk.

name: embryonic antennal segment
description: Any antennal segment (UBERON:6000009) that is part of some embryonic head (UBERON:6000155).

name: lens vesicle
description: Portion of tissue that gives rise to the lens.

name: lymphoid system
description: The lymphatic system in vertebrates is a network of conduits that carry a clear fluid called lymph. It also includes the lymphoid tissue through which the lymph travels. Lymphoid tissue is found in many organs, particularly the lymph nodes, and in the lymphoid follicles associated with the digestive system such as the tonsils. The system also includes all the structures dedicated to the circulation and production of lymphocytes, which includes the spleen, thymus, bone marrow and the lymphoid tissue associated with the digestive system[WP].

name: processus posterior of parasphenoid
description: Posterior projection of the median part of the parsphenoid, which may extend over the posterior margins of the subotic alae.

name: midbrain cerebral aqueduct
description: Part of ventricular system of brain consisting of a narrow channel in the midbrain connecting the third and fourth ventricles. (Maryann Martone)

name: processus ascendens plectri
description: Cartilaginous or ligamentous connection between the pars externa plectri and the crista parotica.

name: prepelvic fin spine
description: Spine located anterior to the pelvic fin and posterior to the pectoral fin.

name: sensory system
description: Anatomical system that overlaps the nervous system and is responsible for receiving and processing sensory information.

name: tubal tonsil
description: The lymph tissue associated with the pharyngeal opening of the auditory tube

name: top of head
description: The top of the head.

name: pons
description: The part of the central nervous system lying between the medulla oblongata and the midbrain, ventral to the cerebellum.

name: epiphyseal plate
description: A hyaline cartilage plate in the metaphysis at each end of a long bone. The plate is found in children and adolescents; in adults, who have stopped growing, the plate is replaced by an epiphyseal line.

name: epichordal
description: Vertebral centrum that originates from ossification of the dorsal portion of the perichordal tube; the resulting element tends to be depressed in cross section.

name: body of uterus
description: The part of the uterus above the isthmus and below the orifices of the uterine tubes.

name: obsolete caudal fin lepidotrichium
description: Lepidotrichium which is part of the caudal fin.

name: deep vasculature
description: The part of the circulatory system that lies deep beneath the subcutaneous tissue layers away from the surface of the skin.

name: parhypural
description: Haemal spine of last hemal arch that is pierced by the haemal canal through which the caudal vessels pass or haemal arch of preural centrum 1. Its distal part commonly supports lepidotrichia. The parhypural is an unpaired median haemal spine.

name: conotruncus
description: The distal portion of Bulbus cordis that forms an outflow channel and gives rise to the proximal conus cordis.

name: collar nerve cord
description: A nerve tract found in marine worms that is located in the collar body region (three body regions in marine worms: proboscis, collar (extending into tentacle-fringed arms) and trunk)

name: palmar branch of median nerve
description: The palmar branch of the median nerve is a branch of the median nerve which arises at the lower part of the forearm and innervates skin of proximal central palm and thenar eminence.

name: nephron tubule epithelium
description: the cellular avascular layer of the renal tubule luminar surfaces

name: thoracic vertebra 10
description: The tenth thoracic vertebra counting from the top down. Note that members of this class are not necessarily homologous[ncit,modified].

name: obsolete body cavity or lining
description: Either a cavity lining or the space it encloses.

name: central retinal vein
description: The central retinal vein (retinal vein) is a short vein that runs through the optic nerve and drains blood from the capillaries of the retina into the larger veins outside the eye. The anatomy of the veins of the orbit of the eye varies between individuals, and in some the central retinal vein drains into the superior ophthalmic vein, and in some it drains directly into the cavernous sinus. [WP,unvetted].

name: exocuticle
description: The outer layer of the procuticle of certain crustaceans and arthropods, which contains cuticulin, chitin, and phenolic substances that are oxidized to produce the dark pigment of the cuticle;nThe hard and usually darkened layer of the cuticle lying between the endocuticle and epicuticle.

name: spinal neuromere
description: A neuromere that is part of the presumptive spinal cord

name: muscle of pelvic girdle
description: Any muscle organ that is part of a pelvic girdle [Automatically generated definition].

name: central artery
description: Arteries that irrigate the forebrain and midbrain Isogai et al. 2001.

name: brachium of inferior colliculus
description: The Brachium of inferior colliculus (or inferior brachium) carries auditory afferent fibers from the inferior colliculus of the mesencephalon to the medial geniculate nucleus. [WP,unvetted].

name: organ part
description: A multicellular structure that is a part of an organ.

name: skeletal muscle tissue of trapezius
description: A portion of skeletal muscle tissue that is part of a trapezius [Automatically generated definition].

name: sphenoidal sinus
description: One of the paired paranasal sinuses, located in the body of the sphenoid bone and communicating with the highest meatus of the nasal cavity on the same side[MESH]. The sphenoidal sinuses (or sphenoid) contained within the body of the sphenoid vary in size and shape; owing to the lateral displacement of the intervening septum they are rarely symmetrical. The following are their average measurements: vertical height, 2.2 cm. ; transverse breadth, 2 cm. ; antero-posterior depth, 2.2 cm. [WP,unvetted].

name: thyroepiglottic ligament
description: Laryngeal ligament that connects the epiglottis to the thyroid cartilage[WP,modified]

name: lateral marginal vein
description: a continuation of the Dorsal venous arch of the foot and is the origin of the short saphenous vein

name: lung epithelium
description: The epithelial layer of the lung.

name: parotoid gland
description: The parotoid gland (alternatively, paratoid gland) is an external skin gland on the back, neck, and shoulder of toads and some frogs and salamanders. It secretes a milky alkaloid substance to deter predators. The substance produced acts as a neurotoxin. Parotoid glands are sometimes said to be wart-like in appearance, though warts are abnormal growths caused by viral infections while parotoid glands are normal, healthy parts of the animals that bear them. The vague similarity in appearance, however, is the reason behind the mistaken belief that touching a toad causes warts.

name: gastropod genital pore
description: A small opening on the side of the head in some gastropods through which the penis is protruded.

name: mesenchyme from rhombencephalic neural crest
description: Mesenchyme that develops_from a rhombencephalon neural crest.

name: line of Schwalbe
description: The thickened peripheral margin of the vitreous membrane of the cornea.

name: dorsal supracondylar tubercle
description: tubercle on the dorsal border of the distal humerus, a short distance from the dorsal epicondyle, for the origin of the m extensor carpe radialis modifeid from Baumel et al. 1993

name: palpebral bone
description: An ossified element investing the upper eyelid.

name: pelvic fin radial bone
description: pelvic fin radial element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: obturator foramen
description: The obturator foramen is the hole created by the ischium and pubis bones of the pelvis through which nerves and muscles pass.

name: cervical thymic artery
description: An artery that supplies a cervical thymus.

name: main bronchus
description: One of two branches of the trachea.

name: neural tube lumen
description: An anatomical space that surrounded_by a neural tube.

name: upper jaw molar
description: A molar tooth that is part of a upper jaw [Automatically generated definition].

name: mucosa of nasal septum
description: A mucosa that is part of a nasal septum [Automatically generated definition].

name: tectorial membrane of cochlea
description: The overlaying membrane of the cochlear duct, an extracellular matrix of the inner ear that contacts the stereocilia bundles of specialized sensory hair cells; sound induces movement of these hair cells relative to the tectorial membrane, deflects the stereocilia, and leads to fluctuations in hair cell membrane potential, transducing sound into electrical signals[MP,modified]

name: spinal cord sulcus limitans
description: A sulcus limitans of neural tube that is part of a future spinal cord.

name: phrenic artery
description: An artery that supplies the diaphragm

name: lamella alaris
description: Dorsal plate of the squamosal.

name: retromolar triangle
description: The small area behind the wisdom teeth

name: tail somite
description: A somite that is part of a tail.

name: small intestine
description: Subdivision of digestive tract that connects the stomach to the large intestine and is where much of the digestion and absorption of food takes place (with the exception of ruminants). The mammalian small intestine is long and coiled and can be differentiated histologically into: duodenum, jejunem, ileum[WP,cjm,Kardong].

name: spinalis caudalis muscle
description: A muscle that originates via thin tendons from the proximal and dorsal aspects of the neural spines and inserts via fleshy fibers onto the lateral aspect of the base of the neural arch

name: alular digit digitopodial skeleton
description: A subdivision of the skeleton of the autopod consisting of the phalanges of alular digit plus the associated metapodial element.

name: synchronous hermaphroditic organism
description: Hermaphroditic organism that produces both male and female gametes at the same time.

name: pulmonary alveolar parenchyma
description: The distinguishing cell types of the lung alveolar tissue, including pulmonary epithelial cells (pneumocytes), alveolar capillary endothelial cells, interstitial cells (fibroblasts) and alveolar macrophages

name: intestinal brush border layer
description: A brush border layer that is part of a intestine.

name: tooth 5V
description: Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is the posteriormost tooth in the ventral tooth row.

name: subarticular sesamoid
description: Is an endochondral structure located on the ventral to the junction between, in the hand, the metacarpal and most proximal phalanx of the digit and between phalanges, and in the foot between the metatarsal and most proximal phalanx of the digit and between phalanges. Typically subarticular sesamoids are found with the subarticular tubercles.

name: intervertebral disk of fourth cervical vertebra
description: A intervertebral disk that connects a mammalian cervical vertebra 4 and connects a mammalian cervical vertebra 5.

name: myotome somite 22
description: Portion of the somite giving rise to body wall muscle masses. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: lepidosteoid scale
description: Multi-layer ganoid scale composed of ganoine and cellular bone.

name: pudendal artery
description: Either the internal or external pudendal arteries.

name: rectouterine fold
description: These folds of the rectouterine excavation are named the sacrogenital or rectouterine folds. They contain a considerable amount of fibrous tissue and non-striped muscular fibers which are attached to the front of the sacrum and constitute the uterosacral ligaments.

name: distal interphalangeal joint of manual digit 4
internal genitalia
description: The internal genitalia are the internal sex organs such as the uterine tube, the uterus and the vagina in female mammals, and the testis, seminal vesicle, ejaculatory duct and prostate in male mammals

name: sural artery
description: The sural arteries (inferior muscular arteries) are two large branches, which are distributed to the Gastrocnemius, Soleus, and Plantaris. The term applies to any of four or five arteries arising from the popliteal artery, with distribution to the muscles and integument of the calf, and with anastomoses to the posterior tibial, medial and lateral inferior genicular arteries. [WP,unvetted].

name: cuneate fasciculus of spinal cord
description: An axon tract in the spinal cord which primarily transmits information from the forelimb and trunk. It is part of the posterior column-medial lemniscus pathway.

name: primary palate epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a primary palate.

name: bone tissue of proximal epiphysis
description: A portion of bone tissue that is part of a proximal epiphysis [Automatically generated definition].

name: preoccipital notch
description: Small indentation on the inferior surface of the cerebral cortex at the border of the occiptal and parietal lobes. It is considered as a landmark because the occipital lobe is located just behind the line that connects that notch with the parietoccipital sulcus (adapted from Wikipedia).

name: obsolete trochlear groove of femur
description: Canal on the posteroventral surface of the femoral head, which articulates with the ischial process on the rim of the acetabulum.

name: gastrointestinal system smooth muscle
description: A portion of smooth muscle tissue that is part of a digestive system [Automatically generated definition].

name: trabecula of spleen
description: A trabecula that is part of a spleen.

name: trigeminal nucleus
description: A nucleus of brain that is part of a trigeminal nuclear complex.

name: obsolete regional part of lateral ventricle
zeugopodial skeleton
description: Section of the forelimb skeleton located between the stylopodium and the autopodium.

name: sweat
description: Secretion produced by a sweat gland.

name: acrodin
description: Odontoid tissue forming a cap on teeth found in teeth of actinopterygian fishes.

name: viper venom
description: Venoms from snakes of the viperid family. They tend to be less toxic than elapid or hydrophid venoms and act mainly on the vascular system, interfering with coagulation and capillary membrane integrity and are highly cytotoxic. They contain large amounts of several enzymes, other factors, and some toxins.

name: regional part of cerebellar cortex
description: A regional part of brain that is part of a cerebellar cortex [Automatically generated definition].

name: duct of bulbourethral gland
description: A duct that is part of a bulbo-urethral gland.

name: supraoccipital crest
description: Process that is part of the supraoccipital. It is a posteriorly directed and unpaired median projection off the posterior margin of the supraoccipital bone.

name: external iliac vein
description: A large vein that connects the femoral vein to the common iliac vein. Their origin is at the inferior margin of the inguinal ligaments and they terminate when they join the internal iliac veins (to form the common iliac veins). Both external iliac veins are accompanied along their course by external iliac arteries. [WP,modified].

name: velum feeding organ
description: The locomotory and feeding organ, found in the larval veliger stage of bivalves.

name: splenial bone
description: The splenial is a small bone in the lower jaw of reptiles, amphibians and birds, usually located on the lingual side (closest to the tongue) between the angular and suprangular.

name: epipleural
description: Epipleurals lie below the horizontal septum and are posteroventrally directed. There are ossified epipleurals in certain ostariophysans. In many lower elopocephalan teleosts including ostariophysans the epipleural bones develop an anterodorsal branch so that they are forked proximally.

name: seminal clot
description: A portion of semen in a coagulated state.

name: lateral line
description: The lateral line consists of small sensory patches (neuromasts) located superficially on the skin or just under the skin in fluid-filled canals on the head and body of all fishes and most amphibians. The lateral line develops from cranial ectodermal placodes situated behind the ear and between the eye and ear.

name: upper pharyngeal tooth plate
description: Pharyngeal tooth plate that lies ventral to pharyngobranchials 3 and 4.

name: spleen primordium
description: A dense syncitial-like mesenchymal thickening in the dorsal mesogastrium[ISBN]. the embryonic connective tissue made up of loosely aggregated mesenchymal cells, supported by interlaminar jelly, that gives rise to the developing spleen[MP].

name: apical region of left ventricle
description: Region around the apex of the cardiac left ventricle located at the bottom of the left ventricle inferior to both the mitral and aortic valve.

name: mammary lobe
description: A cluster of mammary gland lobules. In humans this is a distinct lobe and located in the breast region.

name: deep facial vein
description: The anterior facial vein receives a branch of considerable size, the deep facial vein, from the pterygoid venous plexus.

name: umbilical vein endothelium
description: An endothelium that is part of a umbilical vein.

name: mucosa of descending colon
description: A mucosa that is part of a descending colon [Automatically generated definition].

name: male genital disc
description: Genital disc that gives rise to the penis and external genitalia, sperm pump, ejaculatory duct, paragonia and vas deferens, anal plates and adult hindgut (Cohen, 1993).

name: cardiac muscle tissue of interventricular septum
description: A portion of cardiac muscle tissue that is part of an interventricular septum [Automatically generated definition].

name: girdle bone/zone
description: A bone that is part of a appendage girdle region.

name: obsolete predominantly gray midline regional part of thalamus
anterior fornix of vagina
description: The vaginal fornix that is front of the cervix. It is close to the vesico-uterine pouch.

name: orbital cavity
description: Anatomical cavity bounded by the orbital region of the cranium and forming the location of some or all of the eye.

name: heart elastic tissue
description: The type of heart connective tissue found in the endocardial layer that consists mainly of elastic fibers.

name: digit 5 digitopodial skeleton
description: A subdivision of the skeleton of the autopod consisting of the phalanges of digit 5 plus the associated metapodial element.

name: iliac endochondral element
description: A iliac bone or its cartilage or pre-cartilage precursor.

name: tapetum
description: Light reflecting layer found in a variety of different types of eye.

name: wrist nerve
description: A nerve that is part of a wrist [Automatically generated definition].

name: distal epiphysis of metacarpal bone
description: A distal epiphysis that is part of a metacarpal bone.

name: neurocranium
description: Subdivision of skeletal system that surrounds and protects the brain. Includes the skull base, sensory capsules and the central part of the skull roof.

name: endoderm of foregut
description: An endoderm that is part of a foregut [Automatically generated definition].

name: testis
description: A gonad of a male animal. A gonad produces and releases sperm.

name: joint of rib
description: Any joint that connects a rib to another structure (or another rib). Examples: costochondral, costovertebral, interchondral, sternocostal joints.

name: internal urethral sphincter
description: A urethral sphincter muscle which constricts the internal urethral orifice. It is the junction of the urethra with the urinary bladder. The muscle is made of smooth muscle, so therefore it is under involuntary control. It is kept tonically contracted by the sympathetic nervous system and during micturition, is relaxed via the parasympathetic nervous system. This is the primary muscle for preventing the release of urine[WP].

name: epaxial basal fulcrum
description: Basal fulcrum that is positioned at the dorsal or anterodorsal margin of the caudal fin. Arratia, G. 2009. Identifying patterns of diversity of the actinopterygian fulcra. Acta Zoologica (Stockholm) 90 (Suppl. 1): 220-235.

name: submucosa of bronchus
description: A submucosa that is part of a bronchus [Automatically generated definition].

name: epaxial region somite 10
description: Somite-derived body wall muscle present dorsal to the horizontal myoseptum. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: floor plate of diencephalon
description: A floor plate that is part of a diencephalon [Automatically generated definition].

name: oral frenulum
description: A small fold of mucous membrane in the mouth, connecting either the tongue or the lip to the mouth mucosa.

name: clavicle cartilage element
description: A cartilaginous condensation that has the potential to develop into a clavicle.

name: ophthalmic nerve
description: The sensory nerve subdivision of the trigeminal nerve that transmits sensory information from the orbit and its contents, the nasal cavity and the skin of the nose and forehead.

name: tear film
description: An aqueous substance that covers the anterior surface of the eyeball, keeping the cornea wet.

name: pharyngeal membrane of 1st arch
description: A pharyngeal membrane that separates the first pharyngeal cleft from the first pharyngeal pouch.

name: stegural
description: Modified neural arch, probably of ural centrum 4, formed by a bony base that may extend along the dorso-lateral surfaces of ural centra and preural centra 1 or 2 and by a well-developed antero-dorsal membranous projection that extends lateral to the base of epural(s) and anterior toward the neural arches and/or spines of preural centra 1 or 2 (Arratia and Schultze, 1992). The stegural is a paired bone.

name: pedal digit 6 digitopodial skeleton
description: A subdivision of the skeleton of the autopod consisting of the phalanges of pedal digit 6 plus the associated metapodial element.

name: postzygapophysis of cervical vertebra
description: An postzygapophysis that is part of a cervical vertebra.

name: epaxial region somite 15
description: Somite-derived body wall muscle present dorsal to the horizontal myoseptum. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: feather calamus
description: The short, hollow, tubular, unpigmented end of the mature feather inserted into the feather follicle and thus present below the skin level.

name: pubic cartilage element
description: A pubic endochondral element that is composed primarily of cartilage tissue.

name: ungulate coronary band
description: A region of the pododerm above the hoof where hair growth ends.

name: inguinal part of abdomen
description: The external junctural region between the lower part of the abdomen and the thigh.

name: puparium
description: A chitin-based cuticular shell derived from the cuticle of the final larval instar that surrounds the pupal form of the organism

name: facial lymph node
description: Any of the lymph nodes that are part of a face.

name: olfactory bulb external plexiform layer
description: Cytoarchitectural part of the olfactory bulb, lying superior to the mitral cell layer and inferior to the glomerular layer. The EPL is mostly neuropil composed almost entirely of mitral and tulfted cell dendrites and granule cell dendrites and their synaptic inputs.

name: oral part of spinal trigeminal nucleus
epicercal tail
description: Tail fin in which the the caudal part of the notochord tapers posterodorsally. Based on Pradel et al. 2007

name: bladder organ
description: A membranous sac in animals that serves as the receptacle of a liquid or contains gas.

name: corneal primordium
description: Portion of tissue that is part of the eye and gives rise to the mature, fully layered cornea.

name: cuneate fasciculus of medulla
description: Part of cuneate fasciculus found in the medulla

name: intestine secretion
description: Clear to pale yellow watery secretions from the glands lining the small intestine walls. Secretion is stimulated by the mechanical pressure of partly digested food in the intestine.

name: gustatory system
description: The sensory system for the sense of taste.

name: prepectoral space
description: A triangular, anteroventrally facing area developed between the preaxial margin of the humerus and the proximal limb of the ventral humeral ridge. Based on Callier et al. 2009

name: obsolete predominantly gray regional part of dentate nucleus
internal sense organ
description: Sense organ that is internal to the animal - i.e. having no part that is part of the cuticle.

name: basicranium
description: The base of skull is the most inferior area of the skull, composed of the endocranium and lower parts of the skull roof.

name: perichordal
description: Vertebral centrum that originates from ossification of the entire perichordal tube; the resulting element is cylindrical in cross section and may have an open (notochord retained) or solid center.

name: digestive tract diverticulum
description: Branch or outpocketing of the digestive tract.

name: obsolete pectoral fin lepidotrichium
description: Lepidotrichium which is part of the pectoral fin, forming the pectoral fin skeleton and articulating with the pectoral radials. A pectoral lepidotrichium is composed of two hemitrichia that surround bundles of actinotrichia distally.

name: tooth row
description: Anatomical cluster consisting of adjacent teeth constituting a row.

name: accessory olfactory bulb internal plexiform layer
epithelial furrow
description: A region of an epithelium that folds inwards from the epithelial plane to form a furrow.

name: deep vein
description: A blood vessel carrying deoxygenated blood far beneath the skin usually accompanying an artery.

name: chorionic specialization
description: Specialized structure of the chorion of the egg.

name: process of vertebra
description: A process projection from a part of the vertebra such as centrum or arches. Examples: transverse process, diapophyses, parapophyses, and zygapophyses (both the cranial zygapophyses and the caudal zygapophyses).

name: enteropneust proboscis
description: Anteriormost of the three body regions of an enteropneust.

name: interphalangeal joint of pes
description: The interphalangeal articulations of the foot (articulations of the phalanges) are ginglymoid joints, and each has a plantar and two collateral ligaments. The arrangement of these ligaments is similar to that in the metatarsophalangeal articulations: the Extensor tendons supply the places of dorsal ligaments.

name: gland of anal canal
description: A gland that is part of an anal canal [Automatically generated definition].

name: endometrium epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of an endometrium [Automatically generated definition].

name: ossified ligament
description: Sesamoid that develops within a ligament, distal to an articulation or joint.

name: thoracic vertebra 11
description: The eleventh thoracic vertebra counting from the top down. Note that members of this class are not necessarily homologous[ncit,modified].

name: lacrimal drainage system
description: A collection of channels that connects the conjunctival sac with the nasal cavity, encompassing the lacrimal ducts, the lacrimal sac and the naso-lacrimal duct.

name: masseteric vein
description: A plexiform vein accompanying the masseteric artery that empty into the pterygoid venous plexus.

name: endocuticle
description: The inner layer of the procuticle in certain crustaceans and arthropods, which is almost entirely composed of protein and chitin.

name: cell group
description: A group of cells that may not be contained within macroscopic anatomical boundaries, e.g., A9 dopaminergic cell group; massa intercalata of the amygdala (CUMBO)

name: muscle of pes
description: Any muscle organ that is part of a pes [Automatically generated definition].

name: cerebellar central artery
description: Extend upward from the PCS, branch to provide an arterial feed to the hindbrain, then drain back down into the PHBC Isogai et al. 2001.

name: epithelium of trachea
description: the epithelial lining of the trachea which contains numerous ciliated cells

name: pedal digit 4 metatarsal cartilage element
description: A pedal digit metatarsal cartilage element that is part of a pedal digit 4 mesenchyme.

name: respiratory tract
description: Anatomical structure that is part of the respiratory system. In mammals consists of upper and lower tracts

name: cranial synchondrosis
description: The cartilaginous joints of the skull; these include sphenoethmoidal synchondrosis, sphenooccipital synchondrosis, sphenopetrosal synchondrosis, petrooccipital synchondrosis, anterior intraoccipital synchondrosis and posterior intraoccipital synchondrosis.

name: vestibular ligament
description: The vestibular fold is a fibroelastic band which passes from the ventral margin of the cuneiform cartilage to the cranial dorsal surface of the thyroid cartilage. It forms the support for the free edge of the vestibular fold.

name: lumen of laryngopharynx
description: A anatomical space that is enclosed by a hypopharynx.

name: dorsal metatarsal vein
description: The dorsal metatarsal veins are veins which drain the metatarsus of the foot. [WP,unvetted].

name: midcarpal joint
description: An intercarpal that connects a proximal and distal carpal bone

name: lung saccule
description: Primitive gas exchange portion of the lung composed of type I and type II cells[GO].

name: myotome somite 7
description: Portion of the somite giving rise to body wall muscle masses. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: visceral hump
description: Mollusks have three distinct divisions of their body. The head contains the sensory equipment (eyes, antennae, etc) and the primitive brain. The visceral hump, which is the main body, contains most of the organs, including a complete digestive and excretory tract as well as the reproductive organs. The visceral hump also includes the two external flaps of tissue, which are known as the mantle.

name: 1st arch mesenchyme from neural crest
description: Mesenchyme that develops_from a neural crest and is part of a 1st arch mesenchyme.

name: tibialis
description: Either of two muscles of the calf of the leg.

name: yolk sac blood island
description: masses of developing blood cells attached to endothelium in the yolk sac

name: caudal zone of median tuberal portion of hypothalamus
imaginal precursor
description: Structure that proliferates to produce a larval imaginal disc and which gives rise to adult tissues (Bate and Martinez Arias, 1991).

name: vidian canal
description: canal for the vidian nerve

name: trichome
description: Non-innervated projection of the cuticle around an actin-rich cellular process of an underlying epidermal cell.

name: embryonic cement gland
description: A simple mucus-secreting structure that is positioned at the front of the embryo, attaches the newly hatched embryo to a support before the hatchling can swim well or feed, and marks the anterior-most dorsal ectoderm[XAO].

name: mesonephric juxtaglomerular apparatus
description: The juxtaglomerular apparatus lies adjacent to the glomerulus and regulates kidney function by maintaining the blood flow to the kidney and the filtration rate[GO].

name: periosteum of long bone
description: A periosteum that is part of a long bone.

name: petrosal foramen
description: A foramen of skull that is part of a petrosal bone.

name: metanephric glomerular capillary
description: This process pertains to the initial formation of a structure from unspecified parts[GO].

name: reticular tissue
description: Loose connective tissue which consists of an irregular network of cells and reticular fibers and is spatially associated with myeloid and lymphoid cells. Examples: stroma of bone marrow, stroma of spleen, stroma of lymph node.[FMA]

name: lobar bronchus
description: The lobar bronchus is the major airway within the respiratory tree that starts by division of the principal bronchi on both sides and ends at the point of its own subdivision into tertiary or segmental bronchi[GO].

name: lower jaw molar
description: A molar tooth that is part of a lower jaw [Automatically generated definition].

name: autonomic nervous system
description: The autonomic nervous system is composed of neurons that are not under conscious control, and is comprised of two antagonistic components, the sympathetic and parasympathetic nervous systems. The autonomic nervous system regulates key functions including the activity of the cardiac (heart) muscle, smooth muscles (e.g. of the gut), and glands[GO].

name: mucosa of palate
description: A mucosa that is part of a palate [Automatically generated definition].

name: proximal phalanx of manus
description: A proximal phalanx that is part of a finger [Automatically generated definition].

name: pila antoptica
description: A strut of cartilage  extending dorsally from the basal plate and with other similar cartilages forming the sides of the brain case. The pila antoptica is posterior to pila metoptica together with which it may enclose the foramen for the ocular motor nerve and opthalmica magna artery.

name: ventral midline
description: In protostomes (such as insects, snails and worms) as well as deuterostomes (vertebrates), the midline is an embryonic region that functions in patterning of the adjacent nervous tissue. The ventral midline in insects is a cell population extending along the ventral surface of the embryo and is the region from which cells detach to form the ventrally located nerve cords. In vertebrates, the midline is originally located dorsally. During development, it folds inwards and becomes the ventral part of the dorsally located neural tube and is then called the ventral midline, or floor plate.

name: obsolete regional part of inner ear
main ciliary ganglion
description: A parasympathetic ganglion located in the posterior orbit that contains preganglionic nerves and postganglionic neurons of the oculomotor nerve, connects to the Edinger-Westphal nucleus via the oculomotor nerve and the eye muscles via the short ciliary nerve.

name: descending branch of the vagus nerve
description: Major branch of the vagus supplying parasympathetic innervation to viscera.

name: muscle spindle
description: The sensory organs in muscle that are involved in the stretch reflex.

name: pharyngeal muscle
description: A muscle that acts on the pharynx[WP, vetted].

name: muscle layer of jejunum
description: A muscular coat that is part of a jejunum.

name: laryngeal joint
description: A skeletal joint that connects a laryngeal cartilage.

name: pronephric proximal straight tubule
description: A proximal straight tubule that is part of a pronephros.

name: pair of nares
description: Pair of nostrils.

name: ramus lateral
description: Ventral division of the trunk of the PLLN, this prominent ramus extends over the lateral trunk and caudal musculature innervating the lateral line of neuromasts.

name: manual major digit (Aves) digitopodial skeleton
description: A subdivision of the skeleton of the autopod consisting of the phalanges of manual major digit (Aves) plus the associated metapodial element.

name: proximal convoluted tubule brush border
description: A brush border layer that is part of a proximal tubule in the kidney.

name: tooth 4V
description: Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is posterior to tooth 3V and anterior to tooth 5V in the ventral tooth row.

name: obsolete embryonic hypochord
description: A transient rod-like structure ventral to the notochord in salamander embryos. Derived from endoderm.

name: preputial space
description: space between the prepuce and glans penis or clitoris

name: intervertebral disk of fifth cervical vertebra
description: A intervertebral disk that connects a mammalian cervical vertebra 5 and connects a mammalian cervical vertebra 6.

name: myotome somite 25
description: Portion of the somite giving rise to body wall muscle masses. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: ganoid scale
description: Thick, rhomboid-shaped integumentary skeletal element composed of multiple tissues including ganoine and bone.

name: pineal corpora arenacea
description: A calcified structure of brain that is part of a pineal body.

name: distal interphalangeal joint of manural digit 5
external genitalia
description: The external genitalia are the outer sex organs, such as the penis or vulva in mammals

name: popliteus muscle
description: The popliteus muscle in the leg is used to unlock the knee by laterally rotating the femur on the tibia during a closed chain movement (such as one with the foot in contact with the ground). [WP,unvetted].

name: periosteum of epiphysis
description: A periosteum that is part of a epiphysis [Automatically generated definition].

name: foveal depression
description: Ovoid roughened pit situated on the dorsal and anteroventral surface of the acetabular head wherein the ligaments attaching the bone to the acetabulum are inserted.

name: kidney pelvis smooth muscle
description: the smooth muscle tissue surrounding the urothelium of the kidney pelvis

name: manus
description: distal segment of the fore limb, including carpal region, metacarpal region and digits.

name: skeleton of manus
description: Subdivision of skeleton that is the collection of all skeletal elements in a manus, which is the distal section of the anterior forelimb skeleton consisting of the mesopodium, the metapodium and the acropodium (e.g. including the wrist, palm, and fingers)[Phenoscape].

name: splenic cord
description: A structure found in the red pulp of the spleen between the sinusoids, consisting of fibrils and connective tissue cells with a large population of monocytes and macrophages. These cords contain half of the human body's monocytes as a reserve so that after tissue injury these monocytes can move in and aid locally sourced monocytes in wound healing. Erythrocytes pass through the cords of Billroth before entering the sinusoids. The passage into the sinusoids may be seen as a bottleneck, where erythrocytes need to be flexible in order to pass through. In disorders of erythrocyte shape and/or flexibility, such as hereditary spherocytosis, erythrocytes fail to pass through and get phagocytosed, causing extravascular hemolysis.

name: gustatory epithelium
description: A sensory epithelium that is part of a gustatory system.

name: cell condensation
description: Anatomical structure that is an aggregation of similar cells from which cartilages and bones form, and from which chondrogenesis and osteogenesis are initiated during repair and/or regeneration. (Hall and Miyake 1995).

name: process 2
description: Process on the humerus of basal tetrapods, anterior to the entepicondyle and associated with subscapularis muscle (based on Coates 1996)

name: supraneural 1 element
description: Postcranial axial skeletal element located dorsal to vertebra 1.

name: angular/surangular bone
description: Bone formed from the fusion of angular and surangular bones. Found in snakes

name: ceratobranchial 4 bone distal cartilage
description: Pharyngeal cartilage that is part of and at the distal end of ceratobranchial 4 bone, and that usually articulates with epibranchial 4 element. Ceratobranchial 4 distal cartilage is paired.

name: bony fin ray
description: Fin ray that is composed of bone tissue.

name: skin mucus
description: A mucous secretion that is produced by glands in the epidermis.

name: autopalatine-vomer joint
description: Joint that articulates autopalatine and vomer bones. Autopalatine-vomer joint is paired.

name: internal iliac vein
description: A vein that begins near the upper part of the greater sciatic foramen, passes upward behind and slightly medial to the hypogastric artery and, at the brim of the pelvis, joins with the external iliac to form the common iliac vein. [WP,unvetted].

name: obsolete proboscis
description: 1: The trunk of an elephant; also: any long flexible snout. 2: Any of various elongated or extensible tubular processes as the sucking organ of a butterfly of the oral region of an invertebrate.

name: surangular bone
description: The surangular is a dermal bone of the lower jaw. It typically covers much of the dorsal and lateral surface of the posterior jaw and variably extends onto the medial (inside) surface. The surangular articulates with and supports the articular, which forms the jaw joint with the quadrate in most vertebrates, and is in turn supported by the angular. More distally, the surangular bridges the mandibular fenestra, if one is present. It may also bear a raised dorsal coronoid process, an important attachment site for the mandibular adductors. At its distal (or rostral) end, the surangular meets the dentary, the main tooth-bearing bone of the lower jaw in most vertebrates.

name: telencephalic song nucleus HVC
description: A nucleus in the brain of songbirds located in the caudal nidopallium, projecting to the song motor pathway via the robust nucleus of the arcopallium and to the Anterior Forebrain Pathway via the basal ganglia nucleus Area X.

name: posterior lateral line nerve
description: Cranial nerve which enters the brain between cranial nerves VIII and IX; contains afferents and sensory efferents to the posterior lateral line ganglion and middle ganglion. Fibers from the posterior lateral line ganglion innervate the occipital dorsal lateral line and trunk lateral lines.

name: C8 segment of cervical spinal cord
upper pharyngeal tooth
description: Tooth that is attached to the upper pharyngeal tooth plate.

name: stapes pre-cartilage condensation
description: A stapes endochondral element that is composed primarily of a pre-cartilage condensation.

name: lateral ethmoid bone
description: Endochondral bone that separates the olfactory region from the orbit, extends medially to meet its fellow medially below the frontal bones and is bordered by the mesethmoid anteriorly. It may articulate with the autopalatine and infraorbital 1 laterally. The lateral ethmoid is paired.

name: umbilical artery endothelium
description: An endothelium that is part of a umbilical artery.

name: mucosa of sigmoid colon
description: A mucosa that is part of a sigmoid colon [Automatically generated definition].

name: neck of talus
description: The neck of talus is directed forward and medialward, and comprises the constricted portion of the bone between the body and the oval head. Its upper and medial surfaces are rough, for the attachment of ligaments; its lateral surface is concave and is continuous below with the deep groove for the interosseous talocalcaneal ligament.

name: stapedial artery
description: A small artery that passes through the ring of the stapes; while the stapedial artery is a temporary artery thought to disappear at late embryonic stage in humans, the mouse stapedial artery is complete by E13 and persists into adulthood[MP].

name: spinal cord arachnoid mater
description: An arachnoid mater that is part of a spinal cord [Automatically generated definition].

name: skeletal muscle tissue of pharynx
description: A portion of skeletal muscle tissue that is part of a pharynx [Automatically generated definition].

name: pectoral girdle bone
description: A bone that is part of a pectoral girdle region.

name: tapetum lucidum of camera-type eye
description: A layer of tissue in the eye of many vertebrate animals, that lies immediately behind or sometimes within the retina. It reflects visible light back through the retina, increasing the light available to the photoreceptors

name: respiratory system elastic tissue
description: An elastic tissue that is part of a respiratory system [Automatically generated definition].

name: pubic endochondral element
description: A pubic bone or its cartilage or pre-cartilage precursor.

name: forestomach-glandular stomach junction
description: the distinct low fold of tissue that separates the non-glandular area of the stomach (forestomach) from the glandular stomach; the limiting ridge extends circumferentially from the large curvature of the stomach to the small curvature, just below the esophagus; at the esophagus, the course of the limiting ridge bends into a U-shape and almost surrounds the esophageal opening

name: pedal digit nerve
description: A nerve that is part of a toe [Automatically generated definition].

name: integumentary system layer
description: A organ component layer that is part of a integumental system.

name: endoderm of midgut
description: An endoderm that is part of a midgut [Automatically generated definition].

name: female reproductive system
description: The organs and associated structures associated with bearing offspring in a female animal.

name: interchondral joint
description: Interchondral Articulations (articulations of the cartilages of the ribs with each other). The contiguous borders of the sixth, seventh, and eighth, and sometimes those of the ninth and tenth, costal cartilages articulate with each other by small, smooth, oblong facets. Each articulation is enclosed in a thin articular capsule, lined by synovial membrane and strengthened laterally and medially by ligamentous fibers which pass from one cartilage to the other. Sometimes the fifth costal cartilages, more rarely the ninth and tenth, articulate by their lower borders with the adjoining cartilages by small oval facets; more frequently the connection is by a few ligamentous fibers.

name: middle mesencephalic central artery
description: Project rostrally and dorsally from the AMCtA to to irrigate the midportion of the midbrain Isogai et al. 2001.

name: hypaxial basal fulcrum
description: Basal fulcrum that is positioned at the anteroventral margin of the caudal fin. Arratia, G. 2009. Identifying patterns of diversity of the actinopterygian fulcra. Acta Zoologica (Stockholm) 90 (Suppl. 1): 220-235.

name: distal tarsal bone 2 cartilage
description: A distal tarsal bone 2 endochondral element that is composed primarily of cartilage tissue.

name: deep cervical artery
description: The deep cervical artery (Profunda cervicalis) is an artery of the neck.

name: terminal bronchiole epithelium
description: An epithelium that lines a terminal bronchiole.

name: mucosa of lip
description: A mucosa that is part of a lip region [Automatically generated definition].

name: fringe on postaxial edge of toe V
clavicle pre-cartilage condensation
description: A pre-cartilage condensation that has the potential to develop into a clavicle.

name: limbic system
description: A set of midline structures surrounding the brainstem of the mammalian brain, originally described anatomically, e.g., hippocampal formation, amygdala, hypothalamus, cingulate cortex. Although the original designation was anatomical, the limbic system has come to be associated with the system in the brain subserving emotional functions. As such, it is very poorly defined and doesn't correspond closely to the anatomical meaning any longer. [BirnLex].

name: basal ventral medial nucleus of thalamus
preural centrum 1 + ural centrum 1 + ural centrum 2
description: Urostyle that is the result of fusion of preural centrum 1 with ural centra 1 and 2.

name: sulcus ampullaris
description: The groove on the external surface of the ampulla of each semicircular duct where the nerve enters the ampullary crest.

name: postzygapophysis of thoracic vertebra
description: An postzygapophysis that is part of a thoracic vertebra.

name: obsolete regional part of organ cavity
obsolete carotid
description: Either of two arteries which carry blood to the head.

name: epaxial region somite 18
description: Somite-derived body wall muscle present dorsal to the horizontal myoseptum. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: feather vane
description: The portion of the feather that extends to either side of the rachis and is composed of the barbs and their associated structures

name: girdle skeleton
description: The subdivision of the skeleton of either the pectoral or pelvic girdle.

name: plantar part of pes
description: The sole is the bottom of the foot.

name: lateral posterior nucleus of thalamus
description: The lateral posterior nucleus is a nucleus of the thalamus. It acts in concert with the pulvinar.

name: pupal case
description: Any acellular shell or covering that surrounds the pupal form of an insect

name: olfactory bulb glomerular layer
description: The glomerular layer is the most superficial layer, consisting of mitral cell dendritic arborizations (glomeruli), olfactory nerve fibers, and periglomerular cells. Periglomerular cells contact multiple mitral cell dendrites within the glomeruli and provide lateral inhibition of neighboring glomeruli while allowing excitation of a specific mitral cell dendritic tree. Each mitral cell is contacted by at least 1000 olfactory nerve fibers[BTO]. Portion of tissue which is located in between the primary olfactory fiber layer and the external cellular layer of the olfactory bulb[ZFA].

name: juxtarestiform body
description: Fibers interconnecting the cerebellum and vestibular nuclei, traveling medial to the restiform body (inferior cerebellar peduncle) (Nolte, The Human Brain, 6th ed., pg 497)

name: mesoderm-derived structure
description: An anatomical structure that develops (entirely or partially) from the mesoderm.

name: epichordal lepidotrichium
description: Caudal fin lepidotrichium located upon or above the notochord.

name: embryonic gnathal segment
description: Any gnathal segment (UBERON:6000011) that is part of some embryonic head (UBERON:6000155).

name: superficial parotid lymph node
description: A parotid lymph node that is located superficially.

name: vagal neural crest
description: Vagal neural crest is adjacent to the first seven somites gives rise to both ganglionic and ectomesenchymal derivatives[ZFA].

name: decussation of medial lemniscus
description: The sensory decussation or decussation of the lemniscus is a decussation or cross over of axons from the gracile nucleus and cuneate nucleus. The fibres of this decussation are called the internal arcuate fibres and are found at the superior aspect of the closed medulla superior to the motor decussation. It is part of the second neuron in the Posterior column-medial lemniscus pathway. [WP,unvetted].

name: capitulum of radius
description: Lateral portion of the proximal (upper) articular surface of the radius that consists of an eminence with a rounded apex.

name: condyle of femur
description: A condyle that is part of a distal epiphysis of femur.

name: filiform papilla
description: The filiform papillae are thin, long 'V'-shaped cones that don't contain taste buds but are the most numerous. These papillae are mechanical and not involved in gustation covering most of the dorsum (upper surface). They are small and arranged in lines parallel to the V-shaped row of circumvallate papillae, except at the tip of the tongue where they are aligned transversely. Projecting from their apices are numerous filamentous processes, or secondary papillae. These are of a whitish tint, owing to the thickness and density of the epithelium of which they are composed. This epithelium has undergone a peculiar modification as the cells have become cornified and elongated into dense, imbricated, brush-like processes. They contain also a number of elastic fibers, which render them firmer and more elastic than the papillae of mucous membrane generally. The larger and longer papillae of this group are sometimes termed papillae conicae. Fungiform papillae are found dispersed throughout the filiform papillae. [WP,unvetted].

name: hyoid plate
description: Azygous or paired bone that occurs on the ventral surface of the hyoid plate.

name: muscularis mucosae of small intestine
description: A muscularis mucosa that is part of a small intestine.

name: obsolete photoreceptor
description: Can refer to a light sensitive organ, a photoreceptor cell or a photoreceptor protein. This class was made obsolete because it was ambiguous

name: otolith organ
description: the crystalline particles composed of calcium carbonate and a protein which adhere to the gelatinous membrane of the maculae of the utricle and saccule (otolithic membrane)

name: heterocoelous
description: Vertebral centrum that bears saddle-shaped articular surfaces at both ends, having a convexity in the right-left axis and a concavity in the dorsoventral axis. This morphology allows great lateral and vertical flexion.

name: echinoderm gastric caecum
description: non-contractile pouch that is connected to the anterior stomach through a slit-like opening. This pouch is also well-connected to the haemal system through numerous haemal ducts within its connective tissue layer.

name: posterior division of bed nuclei of stria terminalis
description: One of two divisions of the nuclei of stria terminalis based on topology, connectivity and multiple stains in the rat ( Swanson-2004 ) and the mouse ( Dong-2004 ). The other division consists of the anterior nuclei of stria terminalis. The posterior division includes the principal nucleus of stria terminalis, interfascicular nucleus of stria terminalis, transverse nucleus of stria terminalis, premedullary nucleus of stria terminalis, dorsal nucleus of stria terminalis, the strial extension of stria terminalis, and the cell sparse zone of stria terminalis.

name: mesenchyme
description: Portion of tissue consisting of loosely organized undifferentiated mesodermal cells that give rise to such structures as connective tissues, blood, lymphatics, bone, and cartilage[XAO]. A mesh-like cell arrangement, less compact than an epithelium[ZFA]. The part of the embryonic mesoderm, consisting of loosely packed, unspecialized cells set in a gelatinous ground substance, from which connective tissue, bone, cartilage, and the circulatory and lymphatic systems develop[BTO].

name: obsolete pelvic fin lepidotrichium
description: Lepidotrichium which is part of the pelvic fin.

name: recessus marsupiatus of premaxilla
description: Is a recess on the surface of the premaxilla near to the base of the pars facialis.

name: set of lower jaw teeth
description: A tooth row that is part of a skeleton of lower jaw.

name: left cardiac chamber
description: Any chamber of the left side of the heart

name: root of optic nerve
description: A nerve root that extends_fibers_into a nerve connecting eye with brain.

name: maxilla ascending process
description: Process that is the upper portion of the maxilla that rests on the posterior surface of the lateral portion of the premaxilla.

name: transverse fold of rectum
description: One of the semi-lunar transverse folds of the rectal wall that protrude into the anal canal.

name: enteropneust collar
description: Middle of the three body regions of an enteropneust.

name: interphalangeal joint of manus
description: The interphalangeal articulations of hand are hinge-joints of the phalanges of the hand. There are two sets (except in the thumb): 'proximal interphalangeal joints' (PIP), those between the first (also called proximal) and second (intermediate) phalanges 'distal interphalangeal joints' (DIP), those between the second and third (distal) phalanges A similar group of articulations also function in the toes.

name: larval head
description: Any head that is part of some larva.

name: cartilaginous neurocranium
description: The primitive cartilagionous skeletal structure of the fetal skull that grows to envelop the rapidly growing embyonic brain. In humans, the chondrocranium begins forming at 28 days from mesenchymal condensations and is fully formed between week 7 and 9 of fetal development. While the majority of the chondrocranium is succeeded by the bony skull in most higher vertebrates, some components do persist into adulthood.[1] In Cartilagious fishes and Agnathans, the chondrocranium persist throughout life.[2] Embryologically, the chondrocranium represent the basal cranial structure, and lay the base for the formation of the endocranium in higher vertebrates[WP].

name: obsolete phragma
description: The lamella that serves as the site of attachment of the longitudinal flight muscle [HAO].

name: male prepuce epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a prepuce of penis [Automatically generated definition].

name: retromolar space
description: The retromolar space or retromolar gap is a space at the rear of a mandible, between the back of the last molar and the anterior edge of the ascending ramus where it crosses the alveolar margin.[WP]

name: thoracic vertebra 12
description: The twelfth thoracic vertebra counting from the top down. Note that members of this class are not necessarily homologous[ncit,modified].

name: cortex
description: Outermost layer of an organ[WP].

name: trigeminal ganglion
description: The cranial ganglion that is associated with and extends fibers into the trigeminal nerve.

name: liver reticuloendothelial system
description: A reticuloendothelial system that is part of a liver.

name: muscle of arm
description: A muscle organ that is part of an arm [Automatically generated definition].

name: opercular artery
description: The opercular artery arises from the hyoid stump on the first aortic arch, then follows the lateral margin of the operculum (gill covering) ventrally to reconnect into the proximal part of the first aortic arch. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: cingulate cortex
description: The cingulate cortex is a part of the brain situated in the medial aspect of the cortex. It is extended from the corpus callosum below to the cingulate sulcus above, at least anteriorly. [WP,unvetted].

name: epithelium of small intestine
description: An epithelium that is part of a small intestine [Automatically generated definition].

name: predorsal vertebra
description: Vertebra that is positioned between the vertebra immediately anterior to the first dorsal-fin pterygiophore to the anteriormost vertebra.

name: pedal digit 5 metatarsal cartilage element
description: A pedal digit metatarsal cartilage element that is part of a pedal digit 5 mesenchyme.

name: fully formed stage
description: The stage of development at which the animal is fully formed, including immaturity and maturity. Includes both sexually immature stage, and adult stage.

name: respiratory tube
description: A tube in the respiratory system. Examples: bronchus, bronchiole, trachea.

name: lumbar dorsal root ganglion
description: The group of nerve cell bodies located on the dorsal spinal roots within the vertebral column at the level of the lumbar vertebrae.

name: dorsal thoracic segment of trunk
description: Subdivision of thorax, which in humans is the posterior part of the thorax and is demarcated from the chest by the external surface of the posterolateral part of the rib cage and the anterior surface of the thoracic vertebral column; together with the chest, it constitutes the thorax.

name: renal cortex interstitium
description: A compartment of the renal cortex situated between basement membranes of epithelia and vessels that contains two contiguous cellular networks in mutual contact, one formed by interstitial fibroblasts, the other by dendritic cells.

name: sallet
description: A unit of the tectoral membrane that is shaped like string of flat, pearls. Modified from Manley, Fey and Popper 2008

name: lower central incisor tooth
description: A incisor tooth that is in_the_central_side_of a dentition and is part of a lower jaw region.

name: obsolete predominantly gray regional part of pulvinar
metanephric comma-shaped body
description: The metanephric comma-shaped body is the precursor structure to the metanephric S-shaped body that contributes to the morphogenesis of a nephron in the metanephros[GO].

name: meninx
description: Membrane organ that surrounds the brain and the spinal cord.

name: sternal end of clavicle
description: Medial end of the clavicle, which usually lies on the ventral side of the epicoracoid cartilage, just posterior to the epicoracoid bridge.

name: obsolete predominantly gray regional part of lateral nuclear group
segmental bronchus
description: The tertiary bronchi (also known as the segmental bronchi) arise from the secondary bronchi. The respiratory epithelium lining their lumen is surrounded by a layer of smooth muscle. This layer is composed of two ribbons of smooth muscle that spiral in opposite directions. The smooth muscle layer is surrounded by irregular plates of hyaline cartilage which help maintain the patency of the airway. Each of the tertiary bronchi serves a specific bronchopulmonary segment. There are 10 tertiary bronchi in the right lung, and eight in the left. The tertiary bronchi get smaller and divide into primary bronchioles. [WP,unvetted].

name: paranasal commissure
description: Cartilaginous bridge that extends posteriorly to the anterolateral corner of the posterior nasal wall.

name: upper eyelid epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of an upper eyelid [Automatically generated definition].

name: synovial bursa
description: A small fluid-filled sac lined by synovial membrane with an inner capillary layer of slimy fluid. It provides a cushion between bones and tendons and/or muscles around a joint. This helps to reduce friction between the bones and allows free movement. Bursae are filled with synovial fluid and are found around most major joints of the body.

name: clitoris
description: the small, erectile body located at the anterior end of the vulva

name: tubercle of rib
description: The tubercle of a rib is an eminence on the posterior surface, at the junction of the neck and body of the rib, and nearer the lower than the upper border. It consists of an articular and a non-articular portion. The articular portion, the lower and more medial of the two, presents a small, oval surface for articulation with the end of the transverse process of the lower of the two vertebrae to which the head is connected. The non-articular portion is a rough elevation, and affords attachment to the ligament of the tubercle. The tubercle is much more prominent in the upper than in the lower ribs[WP].

name: pila metoptica
description: A strut of cartilage  extending dorsally from the basal plate and with other similar cartilages forming the sides of the brain case. The pila metoptica is anterior to pila antoptica together with which it may enclose the foramen for the ocular motor nerve and opthalmica magna artery. Anterior to the pila antoptica is the pila preoptica (another pillar of cartilage) between these two cartilages emerges the optic and trochlear nerves.

name: lumen of central canal of spinal cord
description: A cerebrospinal fluid-filled space that runs longitudinally through the length of the entire spinal cord. The central canal is contiguous with the ventricular system of the brain. The central canal represents the adult remainder of the neural tube.

name: submandibular ganglion
description: the ganglion associated with the lingual nerve that provides postsynaptic fibers to the submandibular and sublingual glands

name: ramus muscularis of vagus nerve
description: Motor nervous branch of the vagus innervating m. subarcualis rectus I.

name: Pacinian corpuscle
description: Any of the rapidly adapting mechanoreceptors found in subcutaneous tissue beneath both hairy and glabrous skin, and which normally contain an afferent nerve fiber surrounded by a capsule with multiple concentric layers.

name: ventral nerve cord
description: The pair of closely united ventral longitudinal nerves with their segmental ganglia that is characteristic of many elongate invertebrates (as earthworms)[BTO]. A large process bundle that runs along the vental mid-line extending from the ventral region of the nerve ring[WB]. The ventral cord is one of the distinguishing traits of the central nervous system of all arthropods (such as insects, crustaceans and arachnids) as well as many other invertebrates, such as the annelid worms[GO].

name: cricothyroid joint
description: The cricoarytenoid articulation (or joint) is a joint connecting the cricoid cartilage and the thyroid cartilage.

name: spinal nerve root
description: The paired bundles of nerve fibers entering and leaving the spinal cord at each segment. The dorsal and ventral nerve roots join to form the mixed segmental spinal nerves. The dorsal roots are generally afferent, formed by the central projections of the spinal (dorsal root) ganglia sensory cells, and the ventral roots efferent, comprising the axons of spinal motor and autonomic preganglionic neurons. There are, however, some exceptions to this afferent/efferent rule.

name: extensor caudae medialis muscle
description: A muscle that originates via thin tendons from the distal and dorsal aspects of the neural spines. The tendons course proximomedially to distolaterally and give rise to fleshy fibers that insert onto the lateral aspect of the neural arches of each of the vertebrae it crosses. The m. extensor caudae medialis is a continuation of m. semispinalis dorsi into the tail.

name: manual minor digit (Aves) digitopodial skeleton
description: A subdivision of the skeleton of the autopod consisting of the phalanges of manual minor digit (Aves) plus the associated metapodial element.

name: tooth 2V
description: Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is posterior to tooth 1V and anterior to tooth 3V in the ventral tooth row.

name: intervertebral disk of sixth cervical vertebra
description: A intervertebral disk that connects a mammalian cervical vertebra 6 and connects a mammalian cervical vertebra 7.

name: pedal digit 7 digitopodial skeleton
description: A subdivision of the skeleton of the autopod consisting of the phalanges of pedal digit 7 plus the associated metapodial element.

name: myotome somite 28
description: Portion of the somite giving rise to body wall muscle masses. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: vacuolated notochordal tissue
description: Connective tissue that is matrix-poor with large number of vacuolated cells.

name: dorsal fin middle radial cartilage
description: dorsal fin middle radial element that is composed of cartilage tissue.

name: choroid plexus corpora arenacea
description: A calcified structure of brain that is part of a choroid plexus.

name: female inguinal canal
description: An inguinal canal that is part of a female organism. Conveys the round ligament + the ilioinguinal nerve.[WP,unvetted].
