name: distal interphalangeal joint of pedal digit 2
hemopoietic organ
description: Organ that is part of the hematopoietic system.

name: flexor hallucis longus
description: A deep muscle of the posterior compartment of the hindlimb that is innervated by the tibial nerve, arises from the fibula and insets in the distal phalanx of pedal digit 1.

name: fasciculus of spinal cord
description: A fascicle that is part of a spinal cord.

name: ganoine
description: Odontogenic tissue that is hypermineralized acellular, noncollagenous, covered by an epidermis and often deposited in multiple layers.

name: distal epiphysis of humerus
description: A distal epiphysis that is part of a humerus [Automatically generated definition].

name: urinary bladder smooth muscle
description: A portion of smooth muscle tissue that is part of a urinary bladder [Automatically generated definition].

name: chest
description: Subdivision of trunk proper, which is demarcated from the neck by the plane of the superior thoracic aperture and from the abdomen internally by the inferior surface of the diaphragm and externally by the costal margin and associated with the thoracic vertebral column and ribcage and from the back of the thorax by the external surface of the posterolateral part of the rib cage, the anterior surface of the thoracic vertebral column and the posterior axillary lines; together with the abdomen and the perineum, it constitutes the trunk proper[FMA].

name: sacral division of spinal cord central canal
description: Part of spinal cord central canal contained in the sacral spinal cord. It is continuous rostrally with the spinal cord central canal of the lumbar cord.

name: femoral nerve
description: The femoral nerve, the largest branch of the lumbar plexus, arises from the ventral divisions of the second, third, and fourth lumbar nerves. It descends through the fibers of the Psoas major, emerging from the muscle at the lower part of its lateral border, and passes down between it and the Iliacus, behind the iliac fascia; it then runs beneath the inguinal ligament, into the thigh, and splits into an anterior and a posterior division. Under the inguinal ligament, it is separated from the femoral artery by a portion of the Psoas major. [WP,unvetted].

name: peripheral nervous system
description: A major division of the nervous system that contains nerves which connect the central nervous system (CNS) with sensory organs, other organs, muscles, blood vessels and glands.

name: supraneural 2 element
description: Postcranial axial skeletal element located dorsal to vertebra 2.

name: compressor glandulae muscle
description: A prominent compressor muscle found in poisonous snakes that originates in the lower jaw, sweeps around the venom gland, and inserted on the gland's surface. The muscles acts to squeeze the gland and release venom.

name: ceratobranchial 5 bone distal cartilage
description: Pharyngeal cartilage that is part of and at the distal end of ceratobranchial 5 bone. Ceratobranchial 5 bone distal cartilage is paired.

name: facet
description: A small smooth area on a bone or other firm structure.  A worn spot on a tooth, produced by chewing or grinding.

name: supravaginal part of cervix
description: Supravaginal portion of cervix: the part of the cervix uteri that does not protrude into the vagina.

name: prearticular bone
description: Osseous element of intramembranous origin that extends along the lingual margin of Meckel's cartilage.

name: tail vasculature
description: A vasculature that is part of a post-anal tail.

name: Brodmann (1909) area 5
description: Brodmann area 5 is one of Brodmann's cytologically defined regions of the brain. It is involved in somatosensory processing and association.

name: caudal vertebra endochondral element
description: Any vertebra endochondral element that is part of the caudal region of the vertebral column (tail or coccyx).

name: transudate
description: Any bodily fluid that has passed through a membrane such as the capillary wall, as a result of unbalanced hydrostatic and osmotic forces

name: mucosa of fundus of stomach
description: A mucosa that is part of a fundus of stomach [Automatically generated definition].

name: neck of tooth
description: The slightly constricted part of a tooth, between the crown and the root.

name: female genital disc
description: Genital disc that gives rise to the vagina and vaginal plates, uterus, parovaria, spermatheca, seminal recepticle, oviducts, female analia and hindgut. (Cohen, 1993).

name: forebrain dura mater
description: A dura mater that is part of a forebrain.

name: dorsal fin proximal radial bone 3
description: dorsal fin proximal radial 3 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: posterior transverse temporal area 42
description: A subdivision of the cytoarchitecturally defined temporal region of cerebral cortex. It is located in the bank of the lateral sulcus on the dorsal surface of the temporal lobe. Cytoarchitecturally it is bounded medially by the anterior transverse temporal area 41(H) and laterally by the superior temporal area 22 (Brodmann-1909). Adapted from Brain Info

name: nematode pharynx
description: The feeding organ, a neuro-muscular pump in the head of the animal, used to ingest food, bacteria suspended in liquid, filter them out, grind them up and transport posteriorly into the instestine.

name: parietal organ
description: A part of the epithalamus present in some animal species. The eye may be photoreceptive and is usually associated with the pineal gland, regulating circadian rhythmicity and hormone production for thermoregulation. The parietal eye is a part of the epithalamus, which can be divided into two major parts; the epiphysis (the pineal organ, or pineal gland if mostly endocrine) and the parietal organ (often called the parietal eye, or third eye if it is photoreceptive). It arises as an anterior evagination of the pineal organ or as a separate outgrowth of the roof of the diencephalon. In some species, it protrudes through the skull.[4] The parietal eye uses a different biochemical method of detecting light than rod cells or cone cells in a normal vertebrate eye[WP].

name: ischial endochondral element
description: A ischial bone or its cartilage or pre-cartilage precursor.

name: major duodenal papilla
description: The common bile duct and the pancreatic duct together perforate the medial side of the second portion of the duodenum obliquely, some 7 to 10 cm below the pylorus, forming a structure called the major duodenal papilla. The accessory pancreatic duct sometimes pierces it about 2 cm above and slightly in front of these.

name: shoulder nerve
description: A nerve that is part of a shoulder [Automatically generated definition].

name: arterial blood
description: A blood that is part of a artery.

name: organism subdivision
description: Anatomical structure which is a subdivision of a whole organism, consisting of components of multiple anatomical systems, largely surrounded by a contiguous region of integument.

name: obsolete peripheral nerve
description: A cable-like bundle of peripheral axons (the long, slender projections of neurons). A nerve provides a common pathway for the electrochemical nerve impulses that are transmitted along each of the axons. Nerves are found only in the peripheral nervous system. In the central nervous system, the analogous structures are known as tracts[WP].

name: posterior mesencephalic central artery
description: Project dorsally from BCA to irrigate the caudal part of midbrain Isogai et al. 2001.

name: fish scute
description: Dermal bone that is an unpaired, scale-like structure. Arratia, G. 2009. Identifying patterns of diversity of the actinopterygian fulcra. Acta Zoologica (Stockholm) 90 (Suppl. 1): 220-235.

name: distal tarsal bone 2 pre-cartilage condensation
description: A distal tarsal bone 2 endochondral element that is composed primarily of a pre-cartilage condensation.

name: ascending cervical artery
description: The ascending cervical artery is a small branch which arises from the inferior thyroid artery as that vessel is passing behind the carotid sheath; it runs up on the anterior tubercles of the transverse processes of the cervical vertebrC& in the interval between the Scalenus anterior and Longus capitis. To the muscles of the neck it gives twigs which anastomose with branches of the vertebral, and it sends one or two spinal branches into the vertebral canal through the intervertebral foramina to be distributed to the medulla spinalis and its membranes, and to the bodies of the vertebrC&, in the same manner as the spinal branches from the vertebral. It anastomoses with the ascending pharyngeal and occipital arteries.

name: white pulp of spleen
description: the parenchymatous tissue of the spleen that surrounds splenic blood vessels, consists of compact masses of lymphatic cells and is where foreign material removed from the blood is used to initiate an immune reaction that results in the production of antibodies

name: renal pelvis/ureter
description: The upper tract of the renal system. The renal pelvis is the large cavity in the middle of each kidney. Urine drains from each kidney through a long tube called the ureter, into the bladder, where it is stored until it is passed from the body through the urethra.

name: pharyngeal membrane of 2nd arch
description: A pharyngeal membrane that separates the second pharyngeal cleft from the second pharyngeal pouch.

name: lymph node germinal center
description: A germinal center that is located in a lymph node

name: abductor hallucis muscle
description: The Abductor hallucis lies along the medial border of the pes and covers the origins of the plantar vessels and nerves. It arises from the medial process of the tuberosity of the calcaneus, from the laciniate ligament, from the plantar aponeurosis, and from the intermuscular septum between it and the Flexor digitorum brevis. The fibers end in a tendon, which is inserted, together with the medial tendon of the Flexor hallucis brevis, into the tibial side of the base of the first phalanx of the great toe.

name: obsolete external carotid
description: An artery which supplies blood to the muscles of the tongue and floor of the mouth via four major branches.

name: epaxial region somite 20
description: Somite-derived body wall muscle present dorsal to the horizontal myoseptum. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: feather rachis
description: The long solid, tubular extension of the calamus above the skin. The rachis contains pith, which is composed of air-filled keratinised epithelial cells surrounded by a solid keratinised outer cortex.

name: cerebellum vermis lobule
description: The region of a cerebellar lobule that resides in the central section of the cerebellum between the two hemispheres.

name: pelvic appendage field
description: A limb/fin field that has the potential to develop into a pelvic appendage bud mesenchyme.

name: heel skin
description: A zone of skin that is part of a heel.

name: olfactory bulb granule cell layer
description: The granule cell layer contains multiple small round neurons that lack axons. Long dendritic processes of the neurons reach the more superficial layers and inhibit mitral cells and tufted cells. Small distal processes make contacts with the exiting mitral cell axons.

name: ectoderm-derived structure
description: An anatomical structure that develops (entirely or partially) from the ectoderm.

name: ischiopubic ramus
description: The ischiopubic ramus is a compound structure consisting of the following two structures: from the pubis, the inferior pubic ramus from the ischium, the inferior ramus of the ischium It serves as part of the origin for the Obturator internus muscle. It also marks a vertex of the anal triangle and the urogenital triangle. The fascia of Colles is attached to its margin.

name: fundus of stomach
description: The fundus is the portion of the stomach that lies above the cardiac notch, and contains the fundic glands[GO, Kardong].

name: zona arcuata of basilar membrane of cochlea
description: The inner part of the basilar membrane of the cochlea that supports the spiral organ of Corti.

name: ectocondylar tubercle
description: Posteriorly projecting bony tubercle that is located proximal to the lateral condyle of the femur.

name: dorsal pancreatic duct
description: A pancreatic duct that develops from the dorsal pancreatic bud.

name: obsolete capitulum radii
description: Small eminence on the distal articular head of the radius.

name: foliate papilla
description: Any of the papillae located on the sides of the tongue

name: dento-alveolar joint
description: A joint that binds the teeth to the alveolar ridge.

name: prepubic process
description: Elongate process forming the anteriormost part of the pubis.

name: otolithic part of statoconial membrane
description: The layer of the statoconial membrane that is composed of otoliths

name: acoelous
description: Vertebral centrum with flat ends. Between successive vertebrae there is a fibrocartilaginous intervertebral body with a gel-like core, the nucleus pulposus, which is derived from the embryonic notochord. Acoelous vertebrae seem especially suited to receive and distribute compressive forces within the vertebral column.

name: lateral line ganglion
description: Ganglion that develops from a cranial ectodermal placode and contains sensory neurons that innervate a lateral line.

name: right cardiac chamber
description: Any chamber of the right side of the heart

name: lateral ethmoid palatine process
description: Lateral bony projection proximal to lateral ethmoid-palatine joint, and located anterior to orbital region and posterior to olfactory region.

name: trigeminal sensory nucleus
description: The sensory trigeminal nerve nuclei are the largest of the cranial nerve nuclei, and extend through the whole of the midbrain, pons and medulla. The nucleus is divided into three parts, from rostral to caudal (top to bottom in humans): * The mesencephalic nucleus * The chief sensory nucleus (or pontine nucleus or main sensory nucleus or primary nucleus) * The spinal trigeminal nucleus[WP].

name: cartilaginous neural arch
description: One of the cartilaginous structures surrounding the embryonic spinal cord, formed by the dorsal growth of the dorsolateral arcualia; it is the primordium of the vertebral arch.

name: enteropneust trunk
description: Posteriormost of the three body regions of an enteropneust.

name: interphalangeal joint of manual digit 1
description: An interphalangeal joint of manus that is part of a manual digit 1.

name: larval ocular segment
description: Any ocular segment (UBERON:6000005) that is part of some larval head (UBERON:6001730).

name: lateral occipital cortex
description: Component of the occipital lobe. The rostral and caudal boundaries of the lateral occipital cortex were the superior parietal gyrus and as the last visible portion of occipital cortex respectively. The medial and lateral boundaries were the cuneus/pericalcarine cortex and the inferior temporal/inferior parietal gyri respectively (Christine Fennema-Notestine).

name: seminiferous tubule epithelium
description: the stratified epithelial lining of the seminiferous tubules, consisting of the developing spermatozoa and the supporting Sertoli cells, which are tall, columnar type cells that line the tubule

name: upper esophagus
description: The upper one third of esophagus in which the muscle layer is composed of muscle cells of the striated type.

name: endolymph
description: Transudate contained within the membranous labyrinth.[FMA]

name: occipital bone
description: the bone at the lower, posterior part of the skull

name: centrale (fore)
description: Rectangular cartilage or bone between the distal basal commune and the proximal intermedium.

name: lateral vaginal canal
description: One of two lateral tracts connecting a uterus to a common median tract separated from the median vagina via ureters which prevent their fusion. Found in marsupials

name: commissure of inferior colliculus
description: A commissure that is part of a inferior colliculus [Automatically generated definition].

name: thalamic reticular nucleus
description: The thalamic reticular nucleus is part of the ventral thalamus that forms a capsule around the thalamus laterally. It is separated from the thalamus by the external medullary lamina. Reticular cells are GABAergic, and have discoid dendritic arbors in the plane of the nucleus. Thalamic Reticular Nucleus is variously abbreviated TRN, RTN, NRT, and RT. [WP,unvetted].

name: branched caudal fin ray
description: Caudal fin lepidotrichium that is distally branched.

name: pedal digit 1 mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a developing pedal digit 1.

name: obsolete embryo stage part
description: A stage that is part of the embryo stage.

name: taste bud
description: A specialized receptor organ that is a collection of cells spanning the gustatory epithelium.

name: Peyer's patch follicle
description: A lymphoid follicle that is part of a Peyer's patch.

name: kinethmoid cartilage
description: Cranial cartilage which is a small median cartilage located between the premaxillae and anterodorsal to the ethmoid.

name: lung bud
description: Structure derived from foregut that becomes a lung[GO].

name: areolar sweat gland
description: Any sweat gland that is part of an areola

name: zygomaticus muscle
description: One of: zygomaticus major, zygomaticus minor

name: pedal ganglion
description: The pedal ganglia mainly are necessary for coordination of locomotion of a snail.

name: juxtamedullary cortex
description: The part of the renal cortex nearest to the medulla.

name: stomach glandular region mucosa
description: stomach mucosa that is lined with glandular epithelium and part of a stomach glandular region.

name: placental labyrinth vasculature
description: blood vessels of the layer of the placenta where embryonic and maternal blood vessels interdigitate

name: lower lateral incisor tooth
description: A incisor tooth that is in_the_lateral_side_of a dentition and is part of a lower jaw region.

name: mesonephric nephron
description: A nephron that is part of a mesonephros.

name: metanephric nephron tubule
description: A metanephric nephron tubule is an epithelial tube that is part of the metanephric nephron, the functional part of the metanephros[GO].

name: pia mater
description: The innermost layer of the leptomeninges, consisting of a delicate membrane closely covering the surface of the brain and spinal cord,and lying under the arachnoid membrane. The pia, unlike the arachnoid, extends into the sulci in gyrencephalic animals.

name: entepicondyle of humerus
description: A bony projection on the distal epiphysis of the humerus that is the attachment site for the flexor muscles of the manus. This condyle faces posteriorly (for sprawling tetrapods) or medially (for erect tetrapods).

name: Brodmann (1909) area 11
description: Brodmann area 11 is one of Brodmann's cytologically defined regions of the brain. It is involved in planning, reasoning, and decision making.

name: bronchus
description: the upper conducting airways of the lung; these airways arise from the terminus of the trachea

name: lower eyelid epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a lower eyelid [Automatically generated definition].

name: fascia lata
description: The deep fascia of the thigh. [WP,unvetted].

name: vertebra
description: The ossified form of a vertebral element, a skeletal element that forms around the notochord and is part of the vertebral column.

name: costal cartilage
description: the nonvascular, resilient, flexible hyaline connective tissue that connects the end of a true rib to the sternum or the end of a false rib with the with the lower border of the costal cartilage above it

name: sulcus limitans of fourth ventricle
description: In the floor of the fourth ventricle, the sulcus limitans separates the cranial nerve motor nuclei (medial) from the sensory nuclei (lateral). In the superior part of the rhomboid fossa, it corresponds with the lateral limit of the fossa and presents a bluish-gray area, the locus ceruleus (which owes its color to an underlying patch of deeply pigmented nerve cells, termed the substantia ferruginea). [WP]

name: prenasal (amphibians)
description: A dermal bone that forms anterior to the premaxillae between the maxillae and articulates with the nasals posteriorly.

name: cricoarytenoid joint
description: The cricoarytenoid articulation (or joint) is a joint connecting the cricoid cartilage and the arytenoid cartilage.

name: lumbar nerve
description: The lumbar nerves are the five spinal nerves emerging from the lumbar vertebrae. They are divided into posterior and anterior divisions.

name: extensor caudae lateralis muscle
description: A muscle that originates via a robust tendon from a tuberosity on the cranial aspect of the iliac crest and via fleshy fibers from the caudoventral aspect of the pelvis, the lateral aspects of the transverse processes of Ca2-8 or 9, and the horizontal intramuscular septum.

name: alveolar pore
description: The openings in the alveolar septum that permit air flow between adjacent alveoli

name: tooth 3V
description: Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is posterior to tooth 2V and anterior to tooth 4V in the ventral tooth row.

name: obsolete leydig cells
description: A type of mucus and/or fluid secreting cell in larvae.

name: anatomical cluster
description: Anatomical group that has its parts adjacent to one another.

name: stratum intermedium of tooth
description: The stratum intermedium in a developing tooth is a layer of two or three cells between the inner enamel epithelium and the newly forming cells of the stellate reticulum. It first appears during the early bell stage of tooth development, at around the 14th week of intrauterine life (in humans). The stratum intermedium has a notably high alkaline phosphatase activity. This layer, along with the inner enamel epithelium, is responsible for the tooth enamel formation. It is a part of the dental (enamel) organ.

name: intervertebral disk of seventh cervical vertebra
description: A intervertebral disk that connects a thoracic vertebra and connects a mammalian cervical vertebra 7.

name: pedal digit 8 digitopodial skeleton
description: A subdivision of the skeleton of the autopod consisting of the phalanges of pedal digit 8 plus the associated metapodial element.

name: lamina densa of glomerular basement membrane
description: Middle layer of the glomerular basement membrane.

name: internal pudendal artery
description: The internal pudendal artery is an artery that branches off the internal iliac artery, providing blood to the external genitalia. The internal pudendal artery is the terminal branch of the anterior trunk of the internal iliac artery. It is smaller in the female than in the male.

name: bony projection
description: Anatomical projection that is composed of bone tissue.

name: extraembryonic umbilical vein
description: Extraembryonic part of the vein passing through the umbilical cord to the fetus and returning the purified and nutrient blood from the placenta.

name: anal fin middle radial cartilage
description: anal fin middle radial element that is composed of cartilage tissue.

name: xenarthrale
description: A supplementary intervertebral articulation found in xenarthrans characterized by two sets of zygapophyseal facets in the postdiaphragmatic vertebrae, one medial and one lateral to the met apophysis

name: male inguinal canal
description: An inguinal canal that is part of a male organism. Conveys the spermatic cord and its coverings + the ilioinguinal nerve.[WP,unvetted].

name: aorta smooth muscle tissue
description: the nonstriated, involuntary muscle tissue located in the wall of the aorta

name: auditory cortex
description: The part of the brain that is the ultimate target of afferent auditory information.

name: anterior transverse temporal area 41
description: A subdivision of the cytoarchitecturally defined temporal region of cerebral cortex. It occupies the anterior transverse temporal gyrus (H) in the bank of the lateral sulcus on the dorsal surface of the temporal lobe. Cytoarchitecturally it is bounded medially by the parainsular area 52 (H) and laterally by the posterior transverse temporal area 42 (H) (Brodmann-1909). Adapted from Brain Info

name: fasciculus of brain
description: A fascicle that is part of a brain.

name: limiting layer of elasmoid scale
description: Hypermineralized tissue lacking collagen (except Sharpey's fibres), developing in close proximity to the basal cells of the overlying epithelium.

name: future glans clitoris
description: A future glans that is part of a female genital tubercle.

name: distal epiphysis of tibia
description: A distal epiphysis that is part of a tibia [Automatically generated definition].

name: central retinal artery
description: The central retinal artery (retinal artery) branches off the ophthalmic artery, running inferior to the optic nerve within its dural sheath to the eyeball. [WP,unvetted].

name: trochanteric crest
description: Paired ridges on the ventral surface of the femoral shaft that run toward the femoral trochanter; the posterior crest is less developed.

name: urinary bladder trigone smooth muscle
description: A portion of smooth muscle tissue that is part of a trigone of urinary bladder [Automatically generated definition].

name: obsolete predominantly gray regional part of hippocampal formation
pyramidal layer of CA1
description: CA1 part of stratum pyramidale hippocampi

name: peritoneal fluid
description: Transudate contained in the peritoneal cavity.

name: parasympathetic nervous system
description: The parasympathetic nervous system is one of the two divisions of the vertebrate autonomic nervous system. Parasympathetic nerves emerge cranially as pre ganglionic fibers from oculomotor, facial, glossopharyngeal and vagus and from the sacral region of the spinal cord. Most neurons are cholinergic and responses are mediated by muscarinic receptors. The parasympathetic system innervates, for example: salivary glands, thoracic and abdominal viscera, bladder and genitalia[GO].

name: dentate gyrus polymorphic layer
description: A cellular layer of the dentate gyrus enclosed by the granule cell layer. A number of cell types are located in the polymorphic layer but the most prominent is the mossy cell.

name: pre-dentine
description: Odontogenic tissue that is collagen-rich and characteristic of vertebrate teeth and tooth-like structures (e.g., odontodes) deposited by preodontoblasts and odontoblasts that are typically excluded from the matrix.

name: supraneural 3 element
description: Postcranial axial skeletal element located dorsal to vertebrae 3 and 4.

name: eyelid mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a developing eyelid.

name: hypobranchial 1 bone distal cartilage
description: Pharyngeal cartilage that is part of and at the distal end of hypobranchial 1 bone, and that usually articulates with ceratobranchial 1 element. Hypobranchial 1 bone distal cartilage is paired.

name: posterior ramus of cleithrum
description: Laminar subdivision of the cleithrum that extends along the ventral (lateral) midbody of the suprascapula.

name: inner lining mucosa of the abomasum
description: The inner mucosa of the fourth stomach chamber of a ruminant produces rennet.

name: non-neurogenic ectodermal placode
description: Ectodermal placode that does not develop into a component of the nervous system.

name: vaginal vein
description: One the veins that drains the vaginal venous plexus, into the hypogastric veins. [WP,modified].

name: epithelial lining fluid
description: Epithelial lining fluid forms a thin fluid layer that covers the mucosa of the alveoli, the small airways, and the large airways.

name: mesencephalic vein
description: One of the several veins that drain the mesencephalon; the posterior ones are tributaries to the great cerebral vein; the lateral ones are tributaries to the basal vein. The main veins are: pontomesencephalic vein [TA] (vena pontomesencephalica [TA]), interpeduncular veins [TA] (venae interpedunculares [TA]), intercollicular vein [TA] (vena intercollicularis [TA]), and lateral mesencephalic vein [TA] (vena mesencephalica lateralis [TA])[MedLex]. The major vein of the midbrain, which crosses the midbrain medially to meet it's partner the mesencephalic artery[XAO].

name: Brodmann (1909) area 6
description: Brodmann area 6, or BA6, is part of the frontal cortex in the human brain. Situated just anterior to the primary motor cortex, it is composed of the premotor cortex and, medially, the supplementary motor area, or SMA. This large area of the frontal cortex is believed to play a role in the planning of complex, coordinated movements. Brodmann area 6 is also called agranular frontal area 6 in humans because it lacks an internal granular cortical layer (layer IV). It is a subdivision of the cytoarchitecturally defined precentral region of cerebral cortex. In the human brain, it is located on the portions of the precentral gyrus that are not occupied by the gigantopyramidal area 4; furthermore, BA6 extends onto the caudal portions of the superior frontal and middle frontal gyri. It extends from the cingulate sulcus on the medial aspect of the hemisphere to the lateral sulcus on the lateral aspect. It is bounded rostrally by the granular frontal region and caudally by the gigantopyramidal area 4 (Brodmann, 1909).

name: sesamoid bone of pes
description: A sesamoid bone that is part of a pes.

name: subcardinal vein
description: A vein in the mammalian embryo or the adult of some lower vertebrates that is located on each side of the abdominal region ventromedial to the mesonephros and that in mammals participates in the formation of the inferior vena cava and the renal vein

name: esophagogastric junction mucosa
description: mucosa from the lowest portion of the esophagus, just proximal to the stomach.

name: transverse process of cervical vertebra
description: A transverse process that is part of a cervical vertebra

name: mucosa of body of stomach
description: A mucosa that is part of a body of stomach [Automatically generated definition].

name: communicating artery
description: An artery that connects two larger arteries.

name: midbrain dura mater
description: A dura mater that is part of a midbrain [Automatically generated definition].

name: anal fin distal radial cartilage
description: anal fin distal radial element that is composed of cartilage tissue.

name: subbrachial nucleus
description: A group of cells ventral to the nucleus of brachium of inferior colliculus in the mouse (Paxinos-2001).

name: dorsal fin proximal radial bone 4
description: dorsal fin proximal radial 4 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: smooth muscle of eye
description: any of the striated muscles that move the eye and include: superior rectus, inferior rectus, medial rectus, lateral rectus, superior oblique, inferior oblique, retractor bulbi

name: nucleus of dorsal thalamus
description: A nucleus of brain that is part of a dorsal thalamus.

name: cardiovascular system elastic tissue
description: An elastic tissue that is part of a circulatory system [Automatically generated definition].

name: obsolete regional part of entorhinal cortex
scapula endochondral element
description: A scapula bone or its cartilage or pre-cartilage precursor.

name: minor duodenal papilla
description: The minor duodenal papilla is the opening of the accessory pancreatic duct into the duodenum. It is sometimes absent, and often nonfunctional.

name: eyelid nerve
description: A nerve that innervates an eyelid.

name: obsolete primordial germ cell
description: Primitive cell type that is involved in the reproduction of the organism beginning with the sexual differentiation of the gonads at NF stage 52. In males specifically, it migrates from the genital ridge cortical region into the medullary tissue, where it forms spermatogonia. In females it is embedded in the cortical region and multiplies as oogonia.

name: intervillus pockets
description: A portion of tissue formed between the base of the intestinal villi that is part of the intestinal epithelium where intestinal stem cells are located. In the intestine no crypts are present, but, the regions between the villi, the intervillus pockets, have a crypt-like function. Cells are produced in the intervillus pockets and shed from the villus tips.

name: venous blood
description: A blood that is part of a vein.

name: acellular anatomical structure
description: Anatomical structure that consists of cell parts and cell substances and together does not constitute a cell or a tissue.

name: oviducal vein
description: Vein which collects blood from the oviduct.

name: radius pre-cartilage condensation
description: A pre-cartilage condensation that has the potential to develop into a radius bone.

name: pharyngeal membrane of 3rd arch
description: A pharyngeal membrane that separates the third pharyngeal cleft from the third pharyngeal pouch.

name: jaw mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a developing jaw [Automatically generated definition].

name: hindlimb bone
description: A bone that is part of a hindlimb region. Examples: any pes phalanx, femur. Counter-examples: ischium, pubis (they are part of the pelvic girdle)

name: abductor pollicis brevis muscle
description: The abductor pollicis brevis is a muscle in the manus that functions as an abductor of the thumb.

name: right lung accessory lobe segmental bronchus
description: A segmental bronchus that is part of a right lung accessory lobe.

name: obsolete internal carotid
description: An artery which supplies the upper jaw and cranium.

name: epaxial region somite 23
description: Somite-derived body wall muscle present dorsal to the horizontal myoseptum. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: mouth mucosa
description: A mucous membrane that lines the mouth.

name: fin field
description: A limb/fin field that has_potential_to_developmentally_contribute_to a paired fin bud.

name: muscle layer of ileum
description: A muscular coat that is part of a ileum.

name: posterior hypothalamic region
description: The part of the hypothalamus posterior to the middle region consisting of several nuclei including the medial mamillary nucleus, lateral mamillary nucleus, and posterior hypothalamic nucleus (posterior hypothalamic area). The posterior hypothalamic area is concerned with control of sympathetic responses and is sensitive to conditions of decreasing temperature and controls the mechanisms for the conservation and increased production of heat.

name: dentatothalamic tract
description: The dentatothalamic tract (or dentatorubrothalamic tract) is a tract which connects the dentate nucleus and the thalamus. [WP,unvetted].

name: genitourinary system
description: Anatomical system that has as its parts the organs concerned with the production and excretion of urine and those concerned with reproduction.

name: body of stomach
description: The body of stomach is the part of the stomach that lies between the fundus above and the pyloric antrum below; its boundaries are poorly defined[GO].

name: densocellular part of medial dorsal nucleus
capitulum ulnae
description: Small eminence on the distal articular head of the ulna.

name: duodenal gland
description: A compound tubular submucosal gland found in that portion of the duodenum which is above the hepatopancreatic sphincter (Sphincter of Oddi). The main function of these glands is to produce a mucus-rich alkaline secretion (containing bicarbonate)[WP].

name: male pubococcygeus muscle
description: A pubococcygeus muscle that is part of a male organism.

name: presupracleithrum
description: An skeletal element of the upper pectoral girdle overlapped by the opercular and posttemporal bones.

name: caudal principal ray 18
description: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 17.

name: amphicoelous
description: Ectochordal, biconcave or terminally flat vertebral centrum. This design seems to allow limited motion in most directions. An intervertebral body (which may or may not be independent from the adjacent centra) fills the cavity between successive centra. The intervertebral body usually is formed by soft material that may be derived, at least in part, from the embryonic notochord.

name: cavum septum pellucidum
description: A space enclosed within the laminae of the septum pelludicum, the membranous partition that seperates the frontal horns of the ventricle. contains cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) that filters from the ventricles through the septal laminae. bounded anteriorly by the genu of the corpus callosum; superiorly by the body of the corpus callosum; posteriorly by the anterior limb and pillars of the fornix; inferiorly by the anterior commissure and the rostrum of the corpus callosum; and laterally by the leaflets of the septum pellucidum.

name: obsolete lepidotrichium
description: Dermal bone that is rod-like, formed and usually contained in a fin membrane, and jointed to or adjacent to distal radials. Lepidotrichia are formed from paired hemitrichia surrounding actinotrichia. There are usually two more lepidotrichia than distal radials.

name: trigeminal nerve root
description: A nerve root that extends_fibers_into a trigeminal nerve.

name: obsolete developing epithelial placode
description: OBSOLETE: A domain of columnar epithelium in an embryo that represents the early stage of the development of the epithelial component of a new anatomical structure.

name: future forebrain
description: A presumptive structure that has the potential to develop into a forebrain.

name: interphalangeal joint of pedal digit 1
description: An interphalangeal joint of pes that is part of a pedal digit 1.

name: larval head segment
description: Any segment that is part of some larval head.

name: endochondral bone tissue
description: Replacement bone tissue that forms within cartilage[VSAO, modified].

name: nucleus proprius of spinal cord
description: The Nucleus proprius is a layer of the spinal cord adjacent to the substantia gelatinosa. Nucleus proprius constitutes the bulk of the dorsal horn and receives inputs from the dorsal root ganglions that carry sensory information, such as light touch, as well as pain and temperature information. Cells in this nucleus project to deeper laminae of the spinal cord, to the posterior column nuclei, and to other supraspinal relay centers including the midbrain, thalamus, and hypothalamus. Rexed laminae III, IV, and V make up the nucleus propius Nucleus proprius (NP), along with nucleus dorsalis (ND) are involved in sensing fine touch and proprioception.

name: posterior column of fornix
description: Part of fornix adjacent to the fimbria comprising flattened bands of fibers that extend from the fimbria, running underneath the corpus callosum

name: submucosa of rectum
description: The submucous layer of the wall of the rectum.

name: upper respiratory tract epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a upper respiratory tract [Automatically generated definition].

name: lower esophagus
description: The lower one third of the esophagus in which the muscle layer is composed of muscle cells predominantly of the smooth type.

name: radius endochondral element
description: The major preaxial endrochondral skeletal element in the anterior zeugopod.

name: blood vessel endothelium
description: An endothelium that lines the blood vasculature. Other endothelia may line lymph vessels, the heart

name: utricle of membranous labyrinth
description: the larger of the two otolith organs in the vestibule

name: appendix testis
description: The appendix testis is a vestigial remnant of the Mullerian duct, present on the upper pole of the testis and attached to the tunica vaginalis. It is present about 90% of the time.

name: sphenoid bone
description: An unpaired bone situated at the base of the skull in front of the temporal bone and basilar part of the occipital bone. The sphenoid bone is one of the seven bones that articulate to form the orbit. Its shape somewhat resembles that of a butterfly or bat with its wings extended.

name: axial musculature
description: Musculature of the head and neck, spine, and ribs.

name: myoepithelium
description: An epithelium consisting of myopethelial cells, which are contractile cells resembling smooth muscle cells that are present in glands, notably the mammary gland, and aid in secretion. This cell has long weaving dendritic processes containing myofilament[CL].

name: anterior quadratocranial commissure
description: Cartilage that bridges palatoquadrate to ethmoid region.

name: median vaginal canal
description: A median canal in the reproductive system of marsupials that connects the uteri to a common tract, joining with the two lateral vaginas. Connects the uterine openings directly with the urogenital sinus

name: stria terminalis
description: White matter structure in the brain consisting of fibers running along the lateral margin of the ventricular surface of the thalamus. The stria terminalis covers the thalamostriate vein, marking a line of separation between the thalamus and the caudate nucleus as seen upon gross dissection of the ventricles of the brain, viewed from the superior aspect. The stria terminalis extends from the region of the interventricular foramen to the temporal horn of the lateral ventricle, carrying fibers from the amygdala to the septal, hypothalamic, and thalamic areas of the brain. It also carries fibers projecting from these areas back to the amygdala. (Wikipedia:Stria_terminalis)

name: habenula
description: A segment of the epithalamus that has as its parts the habenular nuclei and the habenular commissure[FMA,modified].

name: nuchal plate series
description: Anatomical cluster that consists of more than one type of nuchal plate in an individual.

name: embryo stage
description: A life cycle stage that starts with fertilization and ends with the fully formed embryo.

name: nasopharynx
description: the section of the pharynx that lies above the soft palate

name: Peyer's patch T cell area
description: The Peyer's patch area normally occupied by T lymphocytes

name: preural 2 vertebra
description: Vertebra anterior to preural centrum 1; sometimes termed the 'antepenultimate' vertebra. Mabee and Bird, 2001.

name: cotylephore
description: Multi-tissue structure that is a transient outgrowth of tissue on skin brooding fish that acts as an attachment site for embryos.

name: cell layer
description: Portion of tissue, that consists of single layer of cells connected to each other by cell junctions. Examples: layer of glial cells; epithelium.

name: hindbrain commissure
description: Any commissure within the hindbrain.

name: infraorbital lateral line neuromast
description: Neuromast that is part of the infraorbital lateral line. Kimmel et al, 1995. (Also see Anatomical Atlas entry for lateral line by T. Whitfield.)

name: claustrum cartilage
description: Postcranial axial cartilage and Weberian ossicle that is located dorsal to the scaphium. The claustrum cartilage is bilaterally paired.

name: peritubular capillary
description: the tiny blood vessels that receive blood from the efferent arterioles of the glomerulus, and interact with superficial cortical nephrons allowing reabsorption and secretion between blood and the inner lumen of the nephron; peritubular capillaries are situated around the tubule and are at low pressure

name: vestibular epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a vestibular labyrinth.

name: molar tooth 1
description: The molar tooth of the upper or lower jaw that is phylogenetically number 1

name: descending thin limb
description: The descending thin limb is a part of the loop of Henle situated just after the proximal straight tubule (S3). It extends to the tip of the loop of Henle[GO].

name: median lingual swelling
description: During the third week of embryological development there appears, immediately behind the ventral ends of the two halves of the mandibular arch, a rounded swelling named the tuberculum impar, which was described by His as undergoing enlargement to form the buccal part of the tongue. More recent researches, however, show that this part of the tongue is mainly, if not entirely, developed from a pair of lateral swellings which rise from the inner surface of the mandibular arch and meet in the middle line. The site of their meeting remains post-embryonically as the median sulcus of the tongue. The tuberculum impar is said to form the central part of the tongue immediately in front of the foramen cecum, but Hammar insists that it is purely a transitory structure and forms no part of the adult tongue[WP, Gray's].

name: interfrontal bone
description: A bone between the frontal bones in the skull; an extra bony plate within the anterior fontanelle that is not usually present

name: upper central incisor tooth
description: A incisor tooth that is in_the_central_side_of a dentition and is part of a upper jaw region.

name: mesonephric mesenchyme
description: Mesonephric mesenchyme is the tissue made up of loosely connected mesenchymal cells in the mesonephros[GO].

name: metanephric renal vesicle
description: The renal vesicle is the primordial structure of the metanephric nephron epithelium, and is formed by the condensation of mesenchymal cells[GO].

name: arachnoid mater
description: A think avascular meningeal layer, between the pia mater and the dural mater. It is separated from the pia mater by the subarachnoid space.

name: infra-orbital nerve
description: A branch of the maxillary nerve that enters the infraorbital canal and innervates the lower eyelid, upper lip, the nasal vestibule, the upper incisors, canines, premolars, upper gums, lower eyelid and conjunctiva, and part of the nose.

name: ectepicondyle of humerus
description: A bony projection on the distal epiphysis of the humerus that is the attachment site for the extensor muscles of the distal parts of the forelimb. In humans, this is known as the lateral epicondyle, but the position varies across tetrapods.

name: bronchiole
description: the conducting airway of the lungs found terminal to the bronchi; these structures contain neither cartilage nor mucous-secreting glands; the epithelium of the bronchioles becomes thinner with each branching

name: thymus epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a thymus, forming a supporting framework[MP,modified].

name: retroambiguus nucleus
description: The term retroambiguus nucleus refers to a group of neurons in the medulla at the caudal end of the nucleus ambiguus, from which the cranial part of the accessory nerve originates ( Crosby-1962 ).

name: cervical vertebra
description: A vertebra that is located in the cervical region of the vertebral column.

name: obsolete predominantly gray regional part of ventral anterior nucleus
true rib
description: A rib that is ventrally connected to the sternum.

name: posterior commissure
description: Rounded band of white fibers crossing the middle line on the dorsal aspect of the upper end of the cerebral aqueduct. It is important in the bilateral pupillary light reflex. Its fibers acquire their medullary sheaths early, but their connections have not been definitely determined. Most of them have their origin in a nucleus, the nucleus of the posterior commissure (nucleus of Darkschewitsch), which lies in the central gray substance of the upper end of the cerebral aqueduct, in front of the nucleus of the oculomotor nerve. Some are probably derived from the posterior part of the thalamus and from the superior colliculus, whereas others are believed to be continued downward into the medial longitudinal fasciculus. The posterior commissure interconnects the pretectal nuclei, mediating the consensual pupillary light reflex[WP]. Diencephalic tract which is located in the vicinity of the dorsal diencephalon and mesencephalon and connects the pretectal nuclei. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain[ZFA].

name: immature macula
description: An otic sensory epithelium that will develop into the mature macula.

name: stifle joint
description: A complex joint in the hind limbs of quadruped mammals such as the sheep, horse or dog. It is the equivalent joint to the human knee. It is often the largest synovial joint in the body.

name: pectoral appendage cartilage tissue
description: A cartilage tissue that is part of a pectoral appendage.

name: sacral nerve
description: The five sacral nerves emerge from the sacrum. Although the vertebral components of the sacrum are fused into a single bone, the sacral vertebrae are still used to number the sacral nerves. Posteriorly, they emerge from the posterior sacral foramina, and form the posterior branches of sacral nerves. Anteriorly, they emerge from the anterior sacral foramina, and contribute to the sacral plexus (S1-S4) and coccygeal plexus.

name: obsolete dorsoventral diencephalic tract
description: A tract originating in the epiphysis and fasiculating with the tract of the postoptic commissure. Ross et al, 1992.

name: ramus ventral
description: This ramus leaves the postotic ganglionic complex together with the third branchial ramus of X. This ramule innervates the ventral line of neuromasts.

name: pulmonary acinus
description: The part of the airway consisting of a respiratory bronchiole and all of its branches

name: tooth 1MD
description: Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is the anteriormost tooth in the mediodorsal tooth row.

name: obsolete dorsal ramus of occulomotor nerve
description: Innervates m. rectus superior (m. dorsal rectus).

name: axochord
description: A medial muscle found in the ventral midline of annelid embryos

name: intervertebral disk of axis
description: A intervertebral disk that connects a vertebral bone 2 and connects a mammalian cervical vertebra 3.

name: musculature of limb
description: Any collection of muscles that is part of a limb [Automatically generated definition].

name: lamina rara interna
description: Layer of the glomerular basement membrane adjacent to the glomerular capillary.

name: polypteroid scale
description: Multi-tissue structure composed of ganoine, dentine, elasmodine and cellular bone.

name: deep external pudendal artery
description: The deep external pudendal artery (deep external pudic artery), more deeply seated than the superficial external pudendal artery, passes medialward across the Pectineus and the Adductor longus muscles; it is covered by the fascia lata, which it pierces at the medial side of the thigh, and is distributed, in the male, to the integument of the scrotum and perineum, in the female to the labium majus; its branches anastomose with the scrotal (or labial) branches of the perineal artery.

name: entotympanic bone
description: Entotympanics are independent elements present in the auditory bullae of various eutherians

name: hemomonochorial placental membrane
description: A placental membrane that consists of a single layer of syncytiotrophoblast at term.

name: distal interphalangeal joint of pedal digit 4
prostate glandular acinus
description: A saclike structure of the prostate gland, comprised of at least three cell layers: an innermost layer of secretory columnar luminal epithelium, a middle layer of squamous basal epithelium that also contains neuroendocrine cells, transit amplifying cells, and stem cells, and an outer layer of smooth muscle intermixed with other stromal cells

name: axillary artery
description: Artery that supplies the axilla

name: thoracic spinal cord dorsal column
description: A subdivision of spinal cord dorsal column that is part of a thoracic spinal cord.

name: vasodentine
description: Dentine tissue that lacks dentine tubules and that is penetrated by blood capillaries.

name: embryonic urethral groove
description: The precursor of the urethra

name: distal epiphysis of femur
description: A distal epiphysis that is part of a femur [Automatically generated definition].

name: coronary artery
description: An artery that supplies the myocardium.

name: obsolete regional part of stratum lacunosum moleculare
intercalated duct
description: A small duct which drains individual secretory units. These are usually inconspicuous, lined by a simple epithelium consisting of low cuboidal cells.

name: arrector pili muscle of vibrissa
description: An arrector muscle of hair that is part of a vibrissa hair.

name: skeleton of pes
description: Subdivision of skeleton that is the collection of all skeletal elements in a pes, which is the distal section of the posterior hindlimb skeleton consisting of the mesopodium, the metapodium and the acropodium (e.g. including the ankle, sole, and toes)[Phenoscape].

name: pyramidal layer of CA2
description: Part of pyramidal cell layer in area CA2, lying superficial to the CA2 stratum oriens, and deep to the stratum radiatum of CA2, continuous with the pyramidal cell layers of CA1 and CA3

name: acetabular part of hip bone
description: The acetabulum is a concave surface of the pelvis. The head of the femur meets with the pelvis at the acetabulum, forming the hip joint. There are three bones of the os coxae (hip bone) that come together to form the acetabulum. Contributing a little more than two-fifths of the structure is the ischium, which provides lower and side boundaries to the acetabulum. The ilium forms the upper boundary, providing a little less than two-fifths of the structure of the acetabulum. The rest is formed by the pubis, near the midline. It is bounded by a prominent uneven rim, which is thick and strong above, and serves for the attachment of the acetabular labrum, which reduces its opening, and deepens the surface for formation of the hip joint. At the lower part of the acetabulum is the acetabular notch, which is continuous with a circular depression, the acetabular fossa, at the bottom of the cavity of the acetabulum. The rest of the acetabulum is formed by a curved, crescent-moon shaped surface, the lunate surface, where the joint is made with the head of the femur. Its counterpart in the pectoral girdle is the glenoid fossa.[WP,unvetted].

name: somatic nervous system
description: Part of peripheral nervous system that includes the somatic parts of the cranial and spinal nerves and their ganglia and the peripheral sensory receptors.

name: pre-enamel
description: Odontogenic tissue that is avascular non-mineralized matrix that is deposited by preameloblast and ameloblasts that are excluded from the matrix.

name: supraneural 4 element
description: Supraneural element dorsal to neural spine 4.

name: presumptive arista
description: Region of the antennal disc that will develop into the arista.

name: hypobranchial 2 bone distal cartilage
description: Pharyngeal cartilage that is part of and at the distal end of hypobranchial 2 bone, and that usually articulates with ceratobranchial 2 element. Hypobranchial 2 bone distal cartilage is paired.

name: chorionic mesenchyme
description: A mesenchyme that is part of a chorion.

name: parietomastoid suture
description: unites the mastoid process of the temporal with the region of the mastoid angle of the parietal[WP:Squamosal_suture].

name: pectoral fin spine
description: Pectoral-fin lepidotrichium 1 with mostly co-ossified and unsegmented hemitrichia that form a stiff and usually thick shaft and enlarged basal processes that moveably articulate with the pectoral girdle. The pectoral fin spine may also result from the fusion of several lepidotrichia that form a stiff shaft.

name: promontory of tympanic cavity
description: The promontory of the tympanic cavity, better known as the cochlear promontory is a rounded hollow prominence, formed by the projection outward of the first turn of the cochlea. It is placed between the fenestrae, and is furrowed on its surface by small grooves, for the lodgement of branches of the tympanic plexus. A minute spicule of bone frequently connects the promontory to the pyramidal eminence.

name: frontoparietal bone
description: An anuran dermal bone that usually is paired and roofs the braincase.

name: irregular bone
description: The irregular bones are bones which, from their peculiar form, cannot be grouped as long bone, short bone, flat bone or sesamoid bone. Irregular bones serve various purposes in the body, such as protection of nervous tissue, affording multiple anchor points for skeletal muscle attachment (as with the sacrum), and maintaining pharynx and trachea support, and tongue attachment (such as the hyoid bone). They consist of cancellous tissue enclosed within a thin layer of compact bone. The irregular bones are: the vertebrC&, sacrum, coccyx, temporal, sphenoid, ethmoid, zygomatic, maxilla, mandible, palatine, inferior nasal concha, and hyoid.

name: sublingual gland primordium
description: A primordium that has the potential to develop into a sublingual gland.

name: flexor sesamoid
description: A sesamoid bone located near or in the flexor musculature of a joint.

name: mucosa of terminal bronchiole
description: A mucosa that is part of a terminal bronchiole [Automatically generated definition].

name: esophagogastric junction submucosa
description: submucosa from the lowest portion of the esophagus, just proximal to the stomach.

name: cervical rib
description: A rib that is attached to a cervical vertebra.

name: mucosa of cardia of stomach
description: A mucosa that is part of a cardia of stomach [Automatically generated definition].

name: alveolar system
description: System pertaining to a bronchus and alveoli.

name: iliocostalis thoracis muscle
description: The iliocostalis dorsi (musculus accessorius; iliocostalis thoracis) arises by flattened tendons from the upper borders of the angles of the lower six ribs medial to the tendons of insertion of the iliocostalis lumborum; these become muscular, and are inserted into the upper borders of the angles of the upper six ribs and into the back of the transverse process of the seventh cervical vertebra.

name: histoblast
description: A progenitor of the adult external abdomen.

name: lateral nucleus of trapezoid body
description: One of two potential parts of the trapezoid nucleus. Separated by an indistinct boundary, the other is the medial trapezoid nucleus ( Crosby-1962 ). The existence of the trapezoid nucleus in the human is disputed ( Bazwinsky-2003 )

name: telencephalon dura mater
description: A dura mater that is part of a telencephalon [Automatically generated definition].

name: dorsal fin proximal radial bone 5
description: dorsal fin proximal radial 5 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: smooth muscle of trachea
description: A portion of smooth muscle tissue that is part of a trachea [Automatically generated definition].

name: cerebellar nuclear complex
description: The gray matter nuclei located in the center of the cerebellum, embedded in the white matter, which receive inhibitory (GABAergic) inputs from Purkinje cells in the cerebellar cortex and excitatory (glutamatergic) inputs from mossy fiber pathways; all output fibers of the cerebellum originate from the these nuclei[MP]

name: obsolete regional part of superior temporal sulcus
nucleus of ventral thalamus
description: A nucleus of brain that is part of a ventral thalamus.

name: cartilaginous vertebral centrum
description: Cartilaginous form of a vertebral centrum, a skeletal element that functionally replaces the notochord[VSAP,modified].

name: blood vessel elastic tissue
description: Elastic tissue layer that lines a blood vessel layer.

name: alisphenoid endochondral element
description: A alisphenoid bone or its cartilage or pre-cartilage precursor.

name: iris nerve
description: Any nerve that innervates the iris.

name: capillary blood
description: A blood that is part of a capillary.

name: enteric nervous system
description: The enteric nervous system is composed of two ganglionated neural plexuses in the gut wall which form one of the three major divisions of the autonomic nervous system. The enteric nervous system innervates the gastrointestinal tract, the pancreas, and the gall bladder. It contains sensory neurons, interneurons, and motor neurons. Thus the circuitry can autonomously sense the tension and the chemical environment in the gut and regulate blood vessel tone, motility, secretions, and fluid transport. The system is itself governed by the central nervous system and receives both parasympathetic and sympathetic innervation[GO].

name: distal tarsal bone 3 cartilage
description: A distal tarsal bone 3 endochondral element that is composed primarily of cartilage tissue.

name: transverse cervical artery
description: The transverse cervical artery (transverse artery of neck, transversa colli artery) is a branch of the thyrocervical trunk, running at a higher level than the suprascapular artery.

name: depressor supercilii
description: The Depressor Supercilii is an eye muscle of the human body. The nature of this muscle is in some dispute. Few printed anatomies include it (Netter, et al. ) and many authorities consider it to be part of the orbicularis oculi muscle . On the other hand, many dermatologists, ophthalmologists and plastic surgeons hold that the depressor supercilli is a distinct muscle and has a definite, individual effect on the movement of the eybrow and skin of the glabella.

name: superior rectal artery
description: The superior rectal artery (superior hemorrhoidal artery) is an artery that descends into the pelvis to supply blood to the rectum.

name: ulna pre-cartilage condensation
description: A pre-cartilage condensation that has the potential to develop into a ulna.

name: pharyngeal membrane of 4th arch
description: A pharyngeal membrane that separates the fourth pharyngeal cleft from the fourth pharyngeal pouch.

name: outer renal medulla loop of Henle
right lung upper lobe bronchiole
description: A bronchiole that is part of a upper lobe of right lung.

name: paired limb/fin field
description: A ring of cells capable of forming a limb or paired fin[Gilbert,modified].

name: palmar/plantar sweat gland
description: A sweat gland that is part of the skin of the palmar part of the manus or plantar part of the pes

name: zygosphene
description: An articular process on anterior surface of neural arch of vertebrae which fits into zygantrum. Modified from Henderson's dictionary of Biological terms 12th Edition.

name: middle temporal gyrus
description: Component of the temporal lobe, lateral aspect. The rostral boundary is the rostral extent of the superior temporal sulcus whereas the caudal boundary is the temporo-occipital incisure on the cortical surface. The superior temporal sulcus is the medial boundary and the inferior temporal sulcus is the lateral boundary (Christine Fennema-Notestine).

name: heel
description: The part of the foot that is the projection of the calcaneus.

name: orbital sulcus
description: The inferior or orbital surface of the frontal lobe is concave, and rests on the orbital plate of the frontal bone. It is divided into four orbital gyri by a well-marked H-shaped orbital sulcus

name: anterior ramus of cleithrum
description: Subdivision of the cleithrum that extends along the anterior edge of the suprascapula.

name: myocardial layer
description: Any of the layers of the myocardium. Example: compact layer, trabecular layer.

name: tunica vaginalis testis
description: the outer coelomic epithelial covering of the testis; a sac of serous tissue covering the testis and the epididymis within which the testis can move about; it covers the tunica albuginea

name: superior ischial ramus
description: The superior ramus of the ischium (descending ramus) projects downward and backward from the body and presents for examination three surfaces: external, internal, and posterior. The external surface is quadrilateral in shape. It is bounded above by a groove which lodges the tendon of the Obturator externus; below, it is continuous with the inferior ramus; in front it is limited by the posterior margin of the obturator foramen; behind, a prominent margin separates it from the posterior surface. In front of this margin the surface gives origin to the Quadratus femoris, and anterior to this to some of the fibers of origin of the Obturator externus; the lower part of the surface gives origin to part of the Adductor magnus. The internal surface forms part of the bony wall of the lesser pelvis. In front it is limited by the posterior margin of the obturator foramen. Below, it is bounded by a sharp ridge which gives attachment to a falciform prolongation of the sacrotuberous ligament, and, more anteriorly, gives origin to the Transversus perinC&i and Ischiocavernosus. Posteriorly the ramus forms a large swelling, the tuberosity of the ischium

name: cardia of stomach
description: The part of the stomach attached to the esophagus. The cardia begins immediately distal to the z-line of the gastroeosphageal junction, where the squamous epithelium of the esophagus gives way to the columnar epithelium of the gastrointestinal tract[WP]

name: macula lutea proper
description: The part of the macula lutea that excludes the fovea.

name: embryonic labial segment
description: Any labial segment (UBERON:6000014) that is part of some embryonic head (UBERON:6000155).

name: dorsal longitudinal fasciculus of medulla
description: Part of dorsal longitudinal fasciculus located in the medulla

name: sphincter pupillae
description: A sphincter muscle that is part of the iris.

name: mesethmoid-vomer joint
description: Joint that articulates the mesethmoid and vomer. Mesethmoid-vomer joint is unpaired.

name: pars reuniens
description: Area of fusion of the ceratohyals.

name: intestinal villus
description: the tiny hair-like projections that protrude from the inside of the small intestine that contain blood vessels that capture digested nutrients that are absorbed through the intestinal wall; the villi increase the absorptive surface area of the small intestine by approximately 30-fold

name: female pubococcygeus muscle
description: Pubovaginalis in the female is the equivalent of levator prostatae in the male.

name: strand of hair
description: A filament, mostly protein, that grows from follicles found in the dermis[WP].

name: pteroid
description: Slender bone connected to the carpus in pterosaurs. The bone, which may have pointed forward, supports the propatagium, a membrane located between the carpus and pectoral region.

name: caudal principal ray 19
description: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 18.

name: ectochordal
description: Spool-shaped vertebral centrum with an open center in which the notochord lies.

name: mesonephric distal tubule
description: The mesonephric distal tubule is a mesonephric nephron tubule that begins at the macula densa and extends to the mesonephric connecting tubule

name: caudal scute
description: Scute that is a median bony plate forming anterior to procurrent caudal fin rays.

name: hemal arch
description: A vertebral arch that is attached to the ventral surface or the vertebral centrum and encloses and protects the caudal artery and vein ventrally.

name: endothelium of main bronchus
description: An endothelium that is part of a main bronchus [Automatically generated definition].

name: accessory nerve cord of dorsal region
description: Any longitudinally extending condensed cluster of neurons and processes that runs along the dorsal mid-line of the animal that is not the most prominent nerve cord.

name: interphalangeal joint of pedal digit 2
description: An interphalangeal joint of pes that is part of a pedal digit 2.

name: submucosa of common hepatic duct
description: A submucosa that is part of a common hepatic duct [Automatically generated definition].

name: larval procephalic segment
description: Any procephalic segment (UBERON:6000007) that is part of some larval head (UBERON:6001730).

name: intramembranous bone tissue
description: Bone tissue that forms directly within mesenchyme, and does not replace other tissues[TAO]. Intramembranous ossification is the formation of bone in which osteoblasts secrete a collagen-proteoglycan matrix that binds calcium salts and becomes calcified[GO]. Intramembranous ossification is the way flat bones and the shell of a turtle are formed[GO]. Unlike endochondral ossification, cartilage is not present during intramembranous ossification[WP].

name: auditory hillocks, pharyngeal arch 1 derived
description: A collection of protruberances derived from pharyngeal arch 1 that develop into the tragus, crus of the helix, and helix.

name: submucosa of colon
description: A submucosa that is part of a colon [Automatically generated definition].

name: basal regeneration epithelium of regenerating fin/limb
description: Layer of the wound epidermis that surrounds the blastema in the fin or limb[ZFA,modified].

name: adductor magnus
description: An adductor muscle that attaches to the pelvic bone and the femur. In humans, the adductor magnus is a large triangular muscle, situated on the medial side of the thigh. The portion which arises from the ischiopubic ramus (a small part of the inferior ramus of the pubis, and the inferior ramus of the ischium) is called the 'adductor magnesius portion', and the portion arising from the tuberosity of the ischium is called the 'hamstring portion'. The hamstring portion is not considered part of the hamstring group of muscles, but it is adjacent to it.[WP,generalized].

name: lower respiratory tract epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a lower respiratory tract [Automatically generated definition].

name: middle part of esophagus
description: The middle one third of the esophagus in which the muscle layer is composed of muscle cells of the striated and smooth types.

name: radius-ulna endochondral element
description: A radius-ulna bone or its cartilage or pre-cartilage precursor.

name: renal afferent arteriole
description: the blood vessels that branch from the kidney interlobular artery, convey blood to the glomerular capillaries, and play an important role in the regulation of blood pressure as a part of the tubuloglomerular feedback mechanism

name: saccule of membranous labyrinth
description: the smaller of the two otolith organs in the vestibule

name: temporal bone
description: the large, irregular bone located at the base and side of the skull; consists of three parts at birth: squamous, tympanic, and petrous

name: main body axis
description: A principle subdivision of an organism that includes all structures along the primary axis, typically the anterior-posterior axis, from head to tail, including structures of the body proper where present (for example, ribs), but excluding appendages.

name: male mammary gland duct
description: A mammary gland duct that is part of a male organism. This structure typically regresses.

name: coelom
description: The aggregate of the coelemic cavity lumen plus the membranes that line the lumen.

name: dorsal longitudinal anastomotic vessel
description: Trunk vessel that connects to the primitive hindbrain channel and the basilar artery at the caudal end of the medulla oblongata. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: stomach lumen
description: The anatomical space that is enclosed by a stomach.

name: bone of appendage girdle complex
description: A bone that is part of an appendage girdle complex (i.e. any bone in a limb, fin or girdle).

name: limb bone
description: A bone that is part of a limb [Automatically generated definition].

name: pineal body
description: A midline, cone like structure located in the dorso-caudal roof of the 3rd ventricle, attached by peduncles to the habenular and posterior commissures. The stalk contains nerve fibers, blood vessels, connective tissue and parenchymal cells (Paxinos, The Rat Central Nervous System, 2nd ed, pg 399).

name: manual digit 1 mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a developing manual digit 1.

name: metacestode
description: The larval (metacestode) stage of the tapeworm Echinococcus multilocularis.

name: caterpillar stage
description: The larval stage of members of the order Lepidoptera.

name: zoea stage
description: A crustacean larval stage characterised by the use of the thoracic appendages for swimming.

name: larval stage
description: A distinct juvenile stage many animals undergo before metamorphosis into adults. Animals with indirect development such as insects, amphibians, or cnidarians typically have a larval phase of their life cycle.

name: veliger stage
description: The characteristic larval stage of the gastropod, bivalve and scaphopod taxonomic classes. It is produced following either the embryonic or trochophore larval stage of development

name: oropharynx
description: the portion of the pharynx that lies between the soft palate and the upper edge of the epiglottis

name: proximal segment of rib
description: The segment of the rib that connects to a vertebra[MP]. a small part of the rib composed of the head, neck, tuberculum and a short proximal part of the body[PMID]

name: obsolete musculus rectus medialis
description: Cranial nerve III innervated; medial in the rectus group.

name: venous sinus cavity
description: An enlarged chamber in the blood sinus capable of accumulating a large volume of blood.

name: sphenotic
description: Endochondral bone that sutures with the pterosphenoid anteriorly, the prootic ventrally, the frontal bone dorso-medially, and the pterotic dorso-posteriorly. Occasionally the sphenotic sutures with the parietal bone. The sphenotic separates the orbital from the otic region. The sphenotic bears a large antero-lateral or lateral or ventro-lateral process that borders the postero-dorsal margin of the orbit. The sphenotic is a paired bone.

name: opercular lateral line neuromast
description: Neuromast that is part of the opercular lateral line. Kimmel et al, 1995. (Also see Anatomical Atlas entry for lateral line by T. Whitfield.)

name: commissura rostral, pars dorsalis
description: Part of the anterior commissure which is located immediately ventral to the supracommissural nucleus of area ventralis telencephali.

name: nail bed
description: Region of skin beneath the nail plate[WP].

name: molar tooth 3
description: The molar tooth of the upper or lower jaw that is phylogenetically number 3

name: renal connecting tubule
description: The connecting tubule is a tubular segment of the nephron; it connects the distal convoluted tubule to the collecting duct[GO].

name: lateral lingual swelling
description: During the third week there appears, immediately behind the ventral ends of the two halves of the mandibular arch, a rounded swelling named the tuberculum impar, which was described by His as undergoing enlargement to form the buccal part of the tongue. More recent researches, however, show that this part of the tongue is mainly, if not entirely, developed from a pair of lateral swellings (or distal tongue bud) which rise from the inner surface of the mandibular arch and meet in the middle line.

name: placenta junctional zone
description: Fetally derived placental region that separates the maternal uterine tissue from the placenta labyrinth

name: upper lateral incisor tooth
description: A incisor tooth that is in_the_lateral_side_of a dentition and is part of a upper jaw region.

name: mesonephric macula densa
description: The mesonephric macula densa is an area of specialized cells in the distal tubule of the mesonephros that makes contact with the vascular pole of the glomerulus[GO].

name: metanephric S-shaped body
description: The metanephric S-shaped body is the successor of the metanephric comma-shaped body that contributes to the morphogenesis of a nephron in the metanephros[GO].

name: dura mater
description: Thick, fibrous meningeal covering surrounding the brain and spinal cord. It is the outermost of the three meningeal coverings. It consists of two layers: the periosteal dura linking the inner surface of the skull and the meningeal dura that lies above the arachnoid dural membrane. The meningeal layer draws away from the periosteal layer and certain locations to form the dural reflections.

name: septum semicircularium anterior
description: The anterior connective tissue partition between walls of otic capsule around which the membranous semicircular canals pass.

name: terminal bronchiole
description: the last conducting structure of non-respiratory bronchioles; after this point, the airways have alveoli in their walls

name: thyroid artery
description: A artery that supplies a thyroid gland.

name: obsolete regional Parts of the Interpositus Nucleus
lumbar vertebra
description: Large vertebra of the movable part of the vertebral column, characterized by the absence of the foramen transversarium within the transverse process, and by the absence of facets on the sides of the body.

name: cardiac mesenchyme
description: The embryonic connective tissue made up of loosely aggregated mesenchymal cells, supported by interlaminar jelly, that gives rise to the developing cardiac structures

name: false rib
description: A rib that is not directly ventrally connected to the sternum.

name: obsolete regional part orbital frontal cortex
lamina inferior
description: Lateral expansion of the crista intermedia that serves as the floor of the cavum medium.

name: gray matter of telencephalon
description: A portion of gray matter that is part of a telencephalon.

name: xiphisternal joint
description: The xiphisternal joint (or xiphisternal synchondrosis) is a location near the bottom of the sternum, where the body of the sternum and the xiphoid process.

name: adult protocerebrum
description: Protocerebrum of the adult brain.

name: superior thoracic artery
description: The superior thoracic artery (highest thoracic artery) is a small vessel normally arising from the first division of the axillary artery, but may arise from the thoracoacromial artery, itself a branch of the second division of the axillary artery. Running forward and medialward along the upper border of the pectoralis minor, the superior thoracic artery passes between it and the pectoralis major to the side of the chest. It supplies branches to the first and second intercostal spaces as well as to the superior portion of serratus anterior. It anastomoses with the internal mammary and intercostal arteries.

name: pelvic appendage cartilage tissue
description: A cartilage tissue that is part of a pelvic appendage.

name: iliocaudalis muscle
description: A muscle that attaches to the iliac crest and to a caudal vertebra.

name: tooth 2MD
description: Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is posterior to tooth 1MD and anterior to tooth 3MD in the mediodorsal tooth row.

name: presumptive axochord
description: Contractile mesodermal midline cells in the ventral midline of annelid embryos that give rise to the axochord

name: intervertebral disk of atlas
description: A intervertebral disk that connects a vertebral bone 1 and connects a vertebral bone 2.

name: zonal layer of superior colliculus
description: A thin layer consisting of small myelinated axons together with marginal and horizontal cells.

name: outflow part of right atrium
description: Outflow part of atrium which consists of wall and cavity of the outflow part of right atrium and the tricuspid valve.[FMA]

name: lamina rara externa
