description: Layer of the glomerular basement membrane adjacent to the podocytes and capsular space.

name: parasphenoid flange
description: Lateral expansion of the parasphenoid. [PHENOSCAPE:BC]

name: superficial external pudendal artery
description: An artery that arises from the medial side of the femoral artery, close to the superficial epigastric artery and superficial iliac circumflex artery.

name: ovarian cortex
description: the layer of the ovarian stroma lying immediately beneath the tunica albuginea, composed of connective tissue cells and fibers, among which are scattered primary and secondary (antral) follicles in various stages of development; the cortex varies in thickness according to the age of the individual, becoming thinner with advancing years; included in the follicles are the cumulus oophorus, membrana granulosa (and the granulosa cells inside it), corona radiata, zona pellucida, and primary oocyte; the zona pellucida, theca of follicle, antrum and liquor folliculi are also contained in the follicle; also in the cortex is the corpus luteum derived from the follicles.

name: chorda tendinea of left ventricle
description: Chorda tendinea which is attached to the leaflet of mitral valve and is continuous with the endocardium of papillary muscle of left ventricle.

name: apical ectodermal ridge
description: multilayered ectodermal region at the distal tip of a limb or fin bud necessary for the proper development of the underlying mesenchyme[MP,modified]. Along with the zone of polarizing activity, it is a crucial organizing region during limb development[WP].

name: genioglossus muscle
description: Either of a pair of lingual muscles with origin in the mandible, with insertion to the lingual fascia below the mucous membrane and epiglottis, with nerve supply from the hypoglossal nerve, and whose action depresses and protrudes the tongue.

name: distal interphalangeal joint of pedal digit 5
thoraco-acromial artery
description: The thoracoacromial artery (acromiothoracic artery; thoracic axis) is a short trunk, which arises from the forepart of the axillary artery, its origin being generally overlapped by the upper edge of the Pectoralis minor. [WP,unvetted].

name: elasmodine
description: Odontogenic tissue that consists of multiple layers of collagen fibers organized in orthogonal or twisted arrangements.

name: distal epiphysis of radius
description: A distal epiphysis that is part of a radius [Automatically generated definition].

name: lacrimal artery
description: The lacrimal artery arises close to the optic foramen, and is one of the largest branches derived from the ophthalmic artery: not infrequently it is given off before the artery enters the orbit. It accompanies the lacrimal nerve along the upper border of the Lateral Rectus, supplies the lacrimal gland. [WP,unvetted].

name: intercalated duct of pancreas
description: A intercalated duct that is part of a pancreas.

name: lateral angle of scapula
description: An angle of the scapula that is broad and bears the glenoid cavity or fossa[WP,unvetted].

name: fibula
description: The major postaxial endochondral bone in the posterior zeugopod[Phenoscape].

name: jugular lymph sac
description: An embryonic lymph sac that forms at the junction of the future internal jugular/anterior cardinals and subclavian veins.

name: caudal octavolateralis nucleus
description: Hindbrain nucleus which is part of the medulla oblongata and is a mechanoreceptive area along with the medial octavolateralis nucleus. It is smaller than the medial octavolateralis nucleus and is located lateral to the facial and vagal lobes of the medulla oblongata. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

name: sympathetic nervous system
description: The sympathetic nervous system is one of the two divisions of the vertebrate autonomic nervous system (the other being the parasympathetic nervous system). The sympathetic preganglionic neurons have their cell bodies in the thoracic and lumbar regions of the spinal cord and connect to the paravertebral chain of sympathetic ganglia. Innervate heart and blood vessels, sweat glands, viscera and the adrenal medulla. Most sympathetic neurons, but not all, use noradrenaline as a post-ganglionic neurotransmitter [GO].

name: non-mineralized cartilage tissue
description: Cartilage tissue that is not mineralized.

name: supraneural 5 element
description: Supraneural element dorsal to neural spine 5.

name: epithelium of handplate
description: An epithelium that is part of a handplate.

name: epibranchial 3 bone uncinate process cartilage
description: Pharyngeal cartilage that is part of and at the distal end of epibranchial bone 3 uncinate process. epibranchial bone 3 uncinate process cartilage is paired.

name: adult cerebral ganglion
description: The pre-oral neuropils of the adult brain located above, around and partially below the esophagus, including the optic lobes. It excludes the gnathal ganglion. Developmentally, it comprises three fused neuromeres: protocerebrum, deutocerebrum, and tritocerebrum.

name: supraesophageal ganglion
description: The pre-oral neuropils of the brain located above and some of it below the esophagus, comprising three fused ganglia (protocerebrum, deutocerebrum, and tritocerebrum) in the head.

name: sphenofrontal suture
description: The Sphenofrontal suture is the cranial suture between the sphenoid bone and the frontal bone.

name: pelvic splint
description: Dermal bone that is located near the lateral margin of the pelvic fin, and lateral to pelvic-fin lepidotrichium 1.

name: type 3 adrenal tissue
description: Adrenal tissue found in archosaurs - tissue arranged in bands, alternating with interrenal cords (Yadav, 2008)

name: nictitating membrane
description: A fold of the mucous membrane of the conjunctiva in many animals. At rest, it is hidden in the medial canthus. It can extend to cover part or all of the cornea to help clean the cornea.

name: Brodmann (1909) area 30
description: Brodmann area 30, also known as agranular retrolimbic area 30, is a subdivision of the cytoarchitecturally defined retrosplenial region of the cerebral cortex. In the human it is located in the isthmus of cingulate gyrus. Cytoarchitecturally it is bounded internally by the granular retrolimbic area 29, dorsally by the ventral posterior cingulate area 23 and ventrolaterally by the ectorhinal area 36 (Brodmann-1909).

name: submandibular gland primordium
description: A primordium that has the potential to develop into a submandibular gland.

name: foramen for glossopharyngeal nerve
description: Foramen that allows the passge of the glossopharyngeal nerve (cranial nerve IX).

name: mucosa of respiratory bronchiole
description: A mucosa that is part of a respiratory bronchiole [Automatically generated definition].

name: central carpal bone
description: A small bone occasionally found at the dorsal aspect of the wrist between the scaphoid, capitate, and trapezoid; it is developed as an independent cartilage in early foetal life but usually becomes fused with the scaphoid; it occurs normally in most monkeys.

name: lumbar rib
description: A rib that is attached to a lumbar vertebra.

name: heart right ventricle
description: A cardiac ventricle that is in the right side of the heart.

name: mucosa of pyloric antrum
description: A mucosa that is part of a pyloric antrum [Automatically generated definition].

name: epigastric artery
description: An external iliac artery branch that supplies blood to the anterior abdominal wall.

name: diencephalon dura mater
description: A dura mater that is part of a diencephalon [Automatically generated definition].

name: dorsal fin proximal radial bone 6
description: dorsal fin proximal radial 6 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: mesothelium of pericardial cavity
description: A mesothelium that is part of a pericardium [Automatically generated definition].

name: anterior lobe of cerebellum
description: the region of the cerebellum that is anterior to the primary fissure

name: Meissner's corpuscle
description: A type of nerve ending in the skin that is responsible for sensitivity to light touch. In particular, they have highest sensitivity (lowest threshold) when sensing vibrations lower than 50 Hertz. They are rapidly adaptive receptors.

name: lung elastic tissue
description: Elastic tissue that is part of a lung [Automatically generated definition].

name: orbitosphenoid endochondral element
description: A orbitosphenoid bone or its cartilage or pre-cartilage precursor.

name: columnar epithelium
description: An epithelium that consists of columnar epithelial cells. Columnar epithelia are epithelial cells whose heights are at least four times their width. Columnar epithelia are divided into simple (or unilayered), and the rarer stratified (or multi-layered).[WP, modified]

name: nerve of trunk region
description: A nerve that is part of the trunk region of the body (not to be confused with a nerve trunk).

name: obsolete spermatozoon
description: A mature male germ cell that develops from a spermatid.

name: cervical os
description: One of two openings in the uterine cervix.

name: extraembryonic structure
description: A multicellular anatomical structure that is associated with an embryo and derived from the zygote from which it develops, but which does not contribute to the embryo proper or to structures that are part of the same organism after embryogenesis.

name: cortex of lymph node
description: Peripheral portion of the lymph node, underneath the capsule[WP].

name: retrocerebral complex
description: Corpora allata with Corpora cardiaca form the retrocerebral complex, a neurosecretory organ.

name: epaxial region somite 24
description: Somite-derived body wall muscle present dorsal to the horizontal myoseptum. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: radius-ulna cartilage element
description: A radius-ulna endochondral element that is composed primarily of cartilage tissue.

name: right lung accessory lobe bronchiole
description: A bronchiole that is part of a right lung accessory lobe.

name: cerebellum interpositus nucleus
description: The nucleus composed of the globose and emoliform nuclei of the cerebellum; in some mammalian species the globose nucleus is not distinguishable

name: limb field
description: A ring of cells capable of forming a limb.

name: sweat of palm
description: Sweat that is produced by the glands on the palmar and plantar surfaces.

name: obsolete humeral facet of the ulna
olfactory sulcus
description: The medial orbital gyrus presents a well-marked antero-posterior sulcus, the olfactory sulcus, for the olfactory tract. [WP,unvetted].

name: distal phalanx
description: Distal-most phalanx within a digit.

name: pelvic lymph node
description: Any lymph node within the abdominal pelvic region.

name: anomocoelous
description: Stegochordal slightly biconcave or flat terminally vertebral centrum. Each intervertebral cartilage is subdivided anteriorly and posteriorly, producing a free intervertebral element between adjacent vertebrae. This element subsequently ossifies and remains free.

name: myocardium trabecular layer
description: The layer of the myocardium composed of projections of contractile myocytes. The trabecular layer is bounded internally by the endocardium. In zebrafish, unlike the trabeculations of higher vertebrates, both atrial and ventricular trabeculae have more strut-like character, and are more uniform without apparent regional differences[ZFA].

name: obsolete regional part of middle frontal gyrus
inferior ischial ramus
description: The Inferior Ramus of the ischium (ascending ramus) is the thin, flattened part of the ischium, which ascends from the superior ramus, and joins the inferior ramus of the pubisbthe junction being indicated in the adult by a raised line. The outer surface is uneven for the origin of the obturator externus and some of the fibers of the adductor magnus; its inner surface forms part of the anterior wall of the pelvis. Its medial border is thick, rough, slightly everted, forms part of the outlet of the pelvis, and presents two ridges and an intervening space. The ridges are continuous with similar ones on the inferior ramus of the pubis: to the outer is attached the deep layer of the superficial perineal fascia (fascia of Colles), and to the inner the inferior fascia of the urogenital diaphragm. If these two ridges be traced downward, they will be found to join with each other just behind the point of origin of the transversus perinC&i; here the two layers of fascia are continuous behind the posterior border of the muscle. To the intervening space, just in front of the point of junction of the ridges, the transversus perinC&i is attached, and in front of this a portion of the crus penis vel clitoridis and the ischiocavernosus. Its lateral border is thin and sharp, and forms part of the medial margin of the obturator foramen.

name: lesser curvature of stomach
description: The lesser curvature of the stomach, extending between the cardiac and pyloric orifices, forms the right or posterior border of the stomach. It descends as a continuation of the right margin of the esophagus in front of the fibers of the right crus of the diaphragm, and then, turning to the right, it crosses the first lumbar vertebra and ends at the pylorus. Nearer its pyloric than its cardiac end is a well-marked notch, the incisura angularis, which varies somewhat in position with the state of distension of the viscus; it serves to separate the stomach into a right and a left portion. The lesser curvature gives attachment to the two layers of the hepatogastric ligament, and between these two layers are the left gastric artery and the right gastric branch of the hepatic artery. [WP,unvetted].

name: hyoid artery
description: The second arch becomes the hyoid artery, which is prominent in early development and normally persists as the caroticotympanic branch of the ICA[Padget]

name: obsolete regional part of lumbar spinal cord white matter
insect embryonic thorax
description: Any thorax (UBERON:6000015) that is part of some embryo (UBERON:6000052).

name: magnocellular part of medial dorsal nucleus
sulcus longitudinalis
description: In a fused radio-ulna, longitudinal furrow that demarcates the area of fusion of both elements. This sulcus is deep in the distal portion of the compound bone, but barely evident or absent at the proximal end.

name: medial condyle of femur
description: The medial condyle is one of the two projections on the lower extremity of femur. The medial condyle is larger than the lateral (outer) condyle due to more weight bearing caused by the center of gravity being medial to the knee. On the posterior surface of the condyle the linea aspera (a ridge running down the posterior shaft of the femur) turns into the medial supracondylar ridge. The outermost protrusion on the medial surface of the medial condyle is referred to as the 'medial epicondyle' and can be palpated by running fingers medially from the patella with the knee in flexion.

name: cornu mesial process
description: Bony projection that is mesially-directed and off the anteromedial corner of each mesethmoid cornu.

name: hyoglossal sinus
description: Is the space along the anterior edge of the hyoid plate between the hyale and through which passes the hyoglossus muscle as it passes dorsally into the tongue.

name: pancreatic tributary of splenic vein
description: The pancreatic veins consist of several small vessels which drain the body and tail of the pancreas, and open into the trunk of the great pancreatic vein. [WP,unvetted].

name: abductor pollicis, radioulna-prepollox
description: Originates on the distal radioulna and inserts on the palmar prepollex.

name: chordotonal organ
description: Chordotonal organs are arthropod sensory structures consisting of special sensilla called the scolopidia, which are mechano-transducers and respond mainly to stretch or flexion. In insects, they consist of bundles of internal sensilla, each of which has a cap cell, an enveloping cell and one or more sense cells. The distal end of the organ is usually attached to the cuticle of the body wall, marked by a pit, a thickened disc or a nodule of chitin, and the base of the organ is connected with the hypodermis, often by a special ligament.

name: pubic boot
description: Anteroposterior expansion of the distal region of the pubis.

name: somite 1
description: Undifferentiated mesodermal component of early trunk or tail segment or metamere, derived from paraxial mesoderm; forms the myotome, sclerotome and perhaps dermatome. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: Reissner's fiber
description: An acellular strand that runs from subcommissural organ caudally through the ventricular system and central canal to the ampulla caudalis. Develops from glycoproteins secreted into CSF.

name: vertebral element 5
description: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 4.

name: holochordal
description: Spool-shaped vertebral centrum with a solid center. All traces of the notochord dissapear.

name: endosteum
description: A thin layer of connective tissue that lines the surface of the bony tissue that forms the medullary cavity of long bones

name: right lung accessory lobe
description: A specialized lobe of the right lung that extends to the left side of the organism

name: basipterygoid process of parasphenoid
description: Process that is the paired process of the parasphenoid that articulates with the suspensorium.

name: epithelial sac
description: An epithelial tube that is open at one end only.

name: gall bladder primordium
description: A sac-like cavity ventral to the liver, lying in the sub-mesodermal space and closed by a thin sheet of ectodermal cells, from which the future gall bladder develops.

name: mesentery of stomach
description: The portion of the primitive mesentery that encloses the stomach; from its dorsal sheet, the greater omentum develops, and from its ventral sheet, the lesser omentum.

name: dura mater lymph vessel
description: Any lymph vessel that is located in the dura mater of the brain.

name: interphalangeal joint of pedal digit 3
description: An interphalangeal joint of pes that is part of a pedal digit 3.

name: submucosa of right hepatic duct
description: A submucosa that is part of a right hepatic duct [Automatically generated definition].

name: arista
description: Highly specialised, slender sixth segment of the antenna covered in bristle-like outgrowths known as laterals. It extends laterally from the dorsal region of the third segment of the antenna.

name: larval labral segment
description: Any labral segment (UBERON:6000008) that is part of some larval head (UBERON:6001730).

name: skeletal element
description: Organ consisting of skeletal tissue. Encompasses whole bones, fused bones, cartilaginious elements, teeth, dermal denticles.

name: arteriole
description: The smallest division of the artery located between the muscular arteries and the capillaries[GO].

name: auditory hillocks, pharyngeal arch 2 derived
description: A collection of protruberances derived from pharyngeal arch 2 that develop into the concha, antihelix and antitragus.

name: submucosa of duodenum
description: A submucosa that is part of a duodenum [Automatically generated definition].

name: obsolete gold iridophore
description: Iridescent iridophore containing gold reflecting platelets.

name: syncytiotrophoblast
description: extraembryonic cells of trophoblastic shell surrounding embryo, outside the cytotrophoblast layer, involved with implantation of the blastocyst by eroding extracellular matrix surrounding maternal endometrial cells at site of implantation, also contribute to villi. (dark staining, multinucleated).

name: larynx epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a larynx [Automatically generated definition].

name: gustatory gland
description: A serous salivary gland which resides adjacent to the moats surrounding the circumvallate papillae in the posterior one-third of the tongue, anterior to the terminal sulcus.

name: manual digit 1 epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a manual digit 1.

name: ulna endochondral element
description: Major postaxial endrochondral skeletal element in the anterior zeugopod.

name: air sac
description: Any of the membranous air-filled extensions of the lungs of birds, which increase the efficiency of gaseous exchange in the lungs

name: cochlear duct of membranous labyrinth
description: An endolymph filled cavity inside the cochlea, located in between the scala tympani and the scala vestibuli, separated by the basilar membrane and Reissner's membrane (the vestibular membrane) respectively. Houses the organ of Corti[WP].

name: scala media
description: the division of the spiral canal of the cochlea that contains the organ of Corti (the neuroepithelial receptor organ for hearing)

name: ethmoid bone
description: A bone in the skull that separates the nasal cavity from the brain. As such, it is located at the roof of the nose, between the two orbits. The cubical bone is lightweight due to a spongy construction. The ethmoid bone is one of the bones that makes up the orbit of the eye[WP]

name: body proper
description: The region of the organism associated with the visceral organs.

name: lung field
description: A specific region of the foregut into the area in which the lung will develop.

name: primary head sinus
description: Main route for venous drainage of the anterior and mid cerebral veins as well as portions of the primordial hindbrain channel. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: otocyst lumen
description: A anatomical cavity that is part of a ear vesicle.

name: bone of pectoral complex
description: A bone that is part of a pectoral complex. Examples: scapula, manus phalanx, any carpal bone, any bone of the pectoral fin.

name: forelimb bone
description: A bone that is part of a forelimb region. Examples: humerus, any of the phalanges. Counter-example: scapula (a bone of the pectoral girdle). Note that we consider the forelimb to end at the shoulder.

name: subthalamic nucleus
description: The subthalamic nucleus is the lens-shaped nucleus located in the ventral part of the subthalamus on the inner aspect of the internal capsule that is concerned with the integration of somatic motor function[GO].

name: ural centrum 1
description: A vertebral centrum that is immediately posterior to preural vertebra 1. Ural centrum 1 is an unpaired median bone.

name: manual digit 1 metacarpus pre-cartilage condensation
description: A manual digit metacarpus pre-cartilage condensation that is part of a manual digit 1 mesenchyme.

name: posterior lateral line neuromast
description: Neuromast that is part of the posterior lateral line. Kimmel et al, 1995. (Also see Anatomical Atlas entry for lateral line by T. Whitfield.)

name: post-embryonic notochord
description: A notochord that has persisted beyond the embryonic stage.

name: pterygoid bone
description: A bone which corresponds to the inner plate of the pterygoid process of the human skull, but which, in all vertebrates below mammals, is not connected with the posterior nares, but serves to connect the palatine bones with the point of suspension of the lower jaw

name: proprioceptive system
description: The sensory system for the sense of proprioception.

name: inferior endocardial cushion
description: The endocardial cushion that forms on the ventral surface of the AV canal.

name: blood sinus of vibrissa
description: The sinuses of Vibrissae are the walls of blood spaces surrounding the roots of vibrissae.

name: glabella skin
description: The zone of skin that overlaps with the glabella region.

name: nucleus of medial longitudinal fasciculus of medulla
greater sac cavity
description: The cavity in the abdomen that is inside the peritoneum but outside of the lesser sac. [WP,unvetted].

name: commissure of the secondary gustatory nuclei
sensory epithelium
description: Simple columnar epithelium made up of cells specialized to serve as sensory cells for the reception of external stimuli, as the sensory cells of the cochlea, vestibule, nasal mucosa, and tongue.

name: crustacean larval stage
description: The larval stage of a crustacean, the stages of which are separated my moults. Typically this goes through a nauplius - zoea - post-larval cycle.

name: frontal gyrus
description: A gyrus that is part of a frontal cortex.

name: nasal concha of ethmoid bone
description: One of the conchae of the ethmoid bone, which occupy the caudal part of the nasal fossae and form the lateral and superior portions of the turbinate bones in mammals[MP]. The ethmoturbinals are associated with the cribiform plate. They are covered with olfactory epithelium. Primarily, they serve to increase the surface area over which olfactory receptor neurons can come in contact with respiratory air. These olfactory receptor nerves then synapse with the mitral cells of the olfactory lobes through the cribiform plate in the manner described above[Palaeos]

name: rhombomere lateral wall
description: A neural tube lateral wall that is part of a rhombomere.

name: mesonephric glomerulus
description: The mesonephric glomerulus is a capillary tuft which forms a close network with the visceral epithelium (podocytes) and the mesangium to form the filtration barrier and is surrounded by Bowman's capsule in nephrons of the mature vertebrate kidney, or mesonephros[GO].

name: lateral line system
description: A line of sensory organs and associated structures along the sides of fish and amphibia that detect vibrations and pressure changes.

name: metanephric connecting tubule
description: The metanephric connecting tubule is a tubular segment of the metanephric nephron; it connects the distal convoluted tubule to the collecting duct in the metanephros[GO].

name: septum semicircularium laterale
description: The lateral connective tissue partition between walls of otic capsule around which the membranous semicircular canals pass.

name: respiratory bronchiole
description: A bronchiole that is the first segment of the respiratory zone.

name: ventral humeral ridge
description: A distinct bony ridge on ventralsurface of the humeral shaft that corresponds to the attachment site of the pectoralis muscle.

name: gonadal vein
description: In medicine, gonadal vein refers to the blood vessel that carrying blood away from the gonad (testis, ovary) toward the heart. Females : ovarian vein Males : testicular vein [WP,unvetted].

name: autopod bone
description: A bone that is part of a autopod region. Note that this incudes the carpal and tarsal bones.

name: paraventricular nucleus of the hypothalamus magnocellular division
pancreas mesenchyme
description: The embryonic connective tissue made up of loosely aggregated mesenchymal cells, supported by interlaminar jelly, that gives rise to the developing pancreas

name: floating rib
description: A rib that is not connected to sternum or sternal cartilage.

name: medulla oblongata sulcus limitans
description: A sulcus limitans of neural tube that is part of a future medulla oblongata.

name: obsolete regional part of oculomotor nuclear complex
cervical part of esophagus
description: Clinical esophageal segment composed of skeletal muscle. It corresponds to the superior part of the upper third topographic segment of the esophagus.

name: hemipenis transversus muscle
description: A muscle that overlies the hemipenis.

name: hypodermis skeletal muscle layer
description: Any skeletal muscle organ in the hypodermis / superficial fascia

name: tooth 1D
description: Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is the anteriormost tooth in the dorsal tooth row.

name: unencapsulated tactile receptor
description: Free nerve endings are widely distributed throughout the body, and are found as branches of unmyelinated, or lightly myelinated fibres grouped in bundles beneath the epithelium. As they penetrate the epithelium, they lose their myelin, and branch among the epithelial cells. Branches of one nerve may cover a wide area and overlap the territories of other nerves. The free nerve endings detect pain, touch, pressure and temperature, and are associated with C fibres.

name: suprabranchial fin
description: Paired fin that is a bilaterally paired anterior outgrowth located high on the side of the animal, not far behind the orbit, with the posterior extremity corresponding with the expected posterior end of the branchial region.

name: hyohyoideus
description: Is a hyoid muscle that inserts at the most anterior basibranchial and also at the posterior ends of the ceratohyals and functions in jaw closure.

name: trachea pre-cartilage rings
description: A pre-cartilage condensation that is part of a trachea.

name: hyaloid canal
description: A small transparent canal running through the vitreous body from the optical nerve disc to the lens. It is formed by an invagination of the hyaloid, a membrane which encloses the vitreous body[WP].

name: outflow part of left atrium
description: An outflow tract of atrium that is part of a left atrium.

name: saphenous vein
description: Either of two main superficial veins of the leg, one larger than the other, that begin at the foot.

name: left testis
description: A testis that is in the left side of the genitalia [Automatically generated definition].

name: ovarian medulla
description: highly vascular stroma found in the center of the ovary that forms from embryonic mesenchyme and contains blood vessels, lymphatic vessels, and nerves; this stroma forms the tissue of the hilum by which the ovarian ligament is attached, and through which the blood vessels enter; it does not contain any ovarian follicles.

name: marginal venous sinus
description: A paired dural venous sinus at the rim of the foramen magnum.

name: chorda tendinea of right ventricle
description: Chorda tendinea which is attached to the leaflet of tricuspid valve and is continuous with the endocardium of papillary muscle of right ventricle.

name: paired limb/fin bud
description: An outgrowth on the lateral trunk of the embryo that develops into a limb or paired fin. The limb/fin bud is divided into ectoderm and mesenchyme[cjm, modified from MP].

name: hyoglossus muscle
description: A muscle that attaches to the hyopid bone and to the tongue and is innervated by cranial nerve XII

name: obsolete predominantly gray regional part of cingulate gyrus
female organism
description: Gonochoristic organism that can produce female gametes.

name: lateral thoracic artery
description: A blood vessel that supplies oxygenated blood to the lateral structures of the thorax and breast. It originates from the axillary artery and follows the lower border of the Pectoralis minor muscle to the side of the chest, supplies the serratus ventralis muscle and the Pectoralis major muscle, and sends branches across the axilla to the axillary lymph nodes and Subscapularis muscle. It anastomoses with the internal thoracic artery, subscapular, and intercostal arteries, and with the pectoral branch of the thoracoacromial artery. In the female it supplies an external mammary branch which turns round the free edge of the Pectoralis major and supplies the breasts. [WP,unvetted].

name: non-mineralized hyaline cartilage tissue
description: Hyaline cartilage tissue that is not mineralized.

name: primordial vasculature
description: A portion of tissue that will develop into vasculature.

name: distal epiphysis of ulna
description: A distal epiphysis that is part of a ulna [Automatically generated definition].

name: dorsal nasal artery
description: The dorsal nasal artery (nasal artery) is an artery of the head. It is one of the two terminal branches of the ophthalmic artery. [WP,unvetted].

name: colorectal mucosa
description: A mucosa that is part of a colorectum.

name: melon organ
description: The melon is an ovoid-shaped, fatty organ found in the forehead of all toothed whales (odontocetes), including dolphins and porpoises (Cranford et al., 1996; Harper, C. J., et al., 2008) and believed to be used in echolocation

name: intercalated duct of salivary gland
description: The tiny tubules with a very thin epithelial layer in the salivary glands running from the salivary acini into the striated duct.

name: tarsal bone
description: A bone that is part of the tarsal skeleton. Examples: calcaneus, talus, centralia.

name: manual digit 1 plus metapodial segment
description: A subdivision of the autopod consisting of manual digit 1 plus the region incorporating a single metapodial element. These segments are typically repeated along the pre-axiom to post-axial axis.

name: zone of skin
description: Any portion of the organ that covers that body and consists of a layer of epidermis and a layer of dermis.

name: supraneural 6 element
description: Supraneural element dorsal to neural spine 6.

name: sulcus of brain
description: A depression or fissure in the surface of the brain. It surrounds the gyri, creating the characteristic appearance of the brain in humans and other large mammals.

name: extraembryonic membrane mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a extraembryonic membrane.

name: epibranchial 4 bone uncinate process cartilage
description: Pharyngeal cartilage that is part of and at the distal end of epibranchial bone 4 uncinate process. Epibranchial bone 4 uncinate process cartilage is paired.

name: sphenoparietal suture
description: The Sphenoparietal suture is the cranial suture between the sphenoid bone and the parietal bone.

name: dorsal fin spine 1
description: Dorsal-fin lepidotrichium 1 with co-ossified and unsegmented hemitrichia that form a stiff shaft and enlarged base that moveably articulates with first (anteriormost) dorsal-fin pterygiophore.

name: skin appendage placode
description: An ectodermal placode that gives rise to any of the cutaneous appendages that protrude from the skin epidermis (heair, feathers, epidermal scales).

name: scleral lamina cribrosa
description: The perforated part of the sclera through which pass the axons of the retinal ganglion cells.

name: gill raker
description: Dermal bone that is a projection present on the inner surface of a branchial arch.

name: type 4 adrenal tissue
description: In mammals, adrenal tissue has a cortex and medulla creating a composite adrenal gland (Kardong 2012)

name: Brodmann (1909) area 31
description: Brodmann area 31, also known as dorsal posterior cingulate area 31, is a subdivision of the cytoarchitecturally defined cingulate region of the cerebral cortex. In the human it occupies portions of the posterior cingulate gyrus and medial aspect of the parietal lobe. Approximate boundaries are the cingulate sulcus dorsally and the parieto-occipital sulcus caudally. It partially surrounds the subparietal sulcus, the ventral continuation of the cingulate sulcus in the parietal lobe. Cytoarchitecturally it is bounded rostrally by the ventral anterior cingulate area 24, ventrally by the ventral posterior cingulate area 23, dorsally by the gigantopyramidal area 4 and preparietal area 5 and caudally by the superior parietal area 7 (H) (Brodmann-1909).

name: fused sacrum
description: A collection of sacral vertebrae in the sacral region that are fused and part of the bony pelvis.

name: fourth phalanx
description: fourth most proximal phalanx in manual or pedal digits.

name: inner epithelial layer of tympanic membrane
description: A portion of the tympanic cavity epithelium which makes up the outer (cuticular) layer of the tympanic membrane

name: transverse process of lumbar vertebra
description: A transverse process that is part of a lumbar vertebra

name: cardiac atrium
description: Cardiac chamber in which blood enters the heart.

name: mucosa of pylorus
description: A mucosa that is part of a pylorus [Automatically generated definition].

name: hindbrain dura mater
description: A dura mater that is part of a hindbrain [Automatically generated definition].

name: dorsal fin proximal radial bone 7
description: dorsal fin proximal radial 7 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: mesothelium of diaphragm
description: A mesothelium that is part of a diaphragm [Automatically generated definition].

name: sensory receptor
description: A sensory nerve ending that responds to a stimulus in the internal or external environment of an organism. In response to stimuli the sensory receptor initiates sensory transduction by creating graded potentials or action potentials in the same cell or in an adjacent one.

name: bronchus elastic tissue
description: An elastic tissue that is part of a bronchus [Automatically generated definition].

name: meso-epithelium
description: Epithelium that derives from the mesoderm. [Automatically generated definition].

name: continuous capillary
description: Capillary that has endothelial cells that provide an uninterrupted lining, and only allow small molecules, like water and ions to diffuse through tight junctions which leave gaps of unjoined membrane which are called intercellular clefts.

name: internal cervical os
description: Opening of uterine cervix into the body of the uterus.

name: tissue
description: Multicellular anatomical structure that consists of many cells of one or a few types, arranged in an extracellular matrix such that their long-range organisation is at least partly a repetition of their short-range organisation.

name: medulla of lymph node
description: The mdeullary portion of the lymph node, which contains large blood vessels, sinuses and medullary cords that contain antibody-secreting plasma cells.

name: sclerotome somite 21
description: Medial ventral region of the somite that will form vertebral cartilages. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: gubernacular bulb
description: The caudal, swollen portion of the gubernaculum.

name: M. plantaris longus
description: Originates by two heads, one from the dorso-distal border of the aponeurosis covering the knee and the other from two tendinous branches along the medial border of the knee joint. Inserts by a thick, broad tendon to form the aponeurosis plantaris.

name: zygomaticus major muscle
description: Facial muscle attached to the modiolus, corner (angle) of the mouth, and zygomatic bone. See Diogo 2008; Diogo et al., 2009; Burrows et al.., 2011., also DuBrul, 1980.

name: primary olfactory cortex
description: A group of structures defined by connectivity, namely, structures that receive axons from the olfactory bulb. They include the anterior olfactory nucleus, the anterior perforated substance, the rostral part of the medial amygdaloid nucleus (anterior cortical nucleus of amygdala), and structures in the anterior part of the parahippocampal gyrus, namely, the prepyriform area, most of the periamygdaloid area, and the rostral part of the entorhinal area (Price-90). Note that some authors have regarded the olfactory bulb itself as the primary olfactory area and the areas to which it projects as secondary (Anthoney-94). In the mouse (Dong-2004) and the rat (Swanson-2004), olfactory areas include the olfactory bulb, accessory olfactory bulb, anterior olfactory nucleus, tenia tecta, prepyriform area, postpiriform transition area, piriform amygdaloid area, nucleus of lateral olfactory tract, and cortical amygdaloid area.

name: middle temporal artery
description: The middle temporal artery arises immediately above the zygomatic arch, and, perforating the temporal fascia, gives branches to the Temporalis, anastomosing with the deep temporal branches of the internal maxillary. It occasionally gives off a zygomaticoC6rbital branch, which runs along the upper border of the zygomatic arch, between the two layers of the temporal fascia, to the lateral angle of the orbit.

name: inferior petrosal sinus
description: The inferior petrosal sinus, within the human head, is an area beneath the brain, which allows blood veins to span the area, from the center of the head downward. It drains from the cavernous sinus (beneath the brain) to the sigmoid sinuses above the internal jugular vein.

name: tibia cartilage element
description: A cartilaginous condensation that has the potential to develop into a tibia.

name: anterior mediastinum
description: The anterior mediastinum exists only on the left side where the left pleura diverges from the mid-sternal line. It is narrow, above, but widens out a little below.

name: upper arm bone
description: A bone that is part of a forelimb stylopod [Automatically generated definition].

name: obsolete transitional epithelium
description: See urothelium.

name: tunica adventitia of blood vessel
description: The outermost layer of a blood vessel, composed mainly of fibrous tissue.

name: sweat of axilla
description: Sweat that is produced by the glands of the axilla.

name: CA3 stratum oriens
description: Part of stratum oriens lying in area CA3 deep to the CA3 pyramidal cell layer and continuous with stratum oriens of area CA2 and bounded by the dentate gyrus hilus.

name: anterior transverse temporal gyrus
description: The transverse temporal gyri (also called Heschl's gyri or Heschl's convolutions) are found in the area of primary auditory cortex in the superior temporal gyrus of the human brain, occupying Brodmann areas 41 and 42. It is the first cortical structure to process incoming auditory information. Anatomically, the transverse temporal gyri are distinct in that they run mediolaterally (towards the center of the brain) rather than dorsiventrally (front to back) as all other temporal lobe gyri run. The Heschl's gyri are named after Richard L. Heschl.

name: middle phalanx
description: A phalanx located between proximal and distal phalanges.

name: displasiocoelous
description: Vertebral column in which the first seven vertebrae have holochordal centra and the intervertebral cartilages are posteriorly subdivided in the procoelous manner. The eighth presacral vertebra has a holochordal centrum and the intervertebral cartilage is subdivided in the opisthocoelous manner. Thus, the first seven presacral vertebrae are concave anteriorly and convex posteriorly, whereas the eighth is biconcave.

name: cervical spinal cord dorsal horn
description: A dorsal horn of spinal cord that is part of a cervical spinal cord.

name: dorsal artery of penis
description: The Dorsal Artery of the Penis ascends between the crus penis and the pubic symphysis, and, piercing the inferior fascia of the urogenital diaphragm, passes between the two layers of the suspensory ligament of the penis, and runs forward on the dorsum of the penis to the glans, where it divides into two branches, which supply the glans and prepuce. On the penis, it lies between the dorsal nerve and deep dorsal vein, the former being on its lateral side. It supplies the integument and fibrous sheath of the corpus cavernosum penis, sending branches through the sheath to anastomose with the deep artery of the penis. [WP,unvetted].

name: greater curvature of stomach
description: The greater curvature of the stomach is directed mainly forward, and is four or five times as long as the lesser curvature. [WP,unvetted].

name: surangular pit line
description: ...a v-shaped pair of ridges, each carrying three or four smallpores Modified from Ahlberg et al. 2005

name: iliac artery
description: Any of the arteries that arise from a bifurcation of the aorta supplying the pelvic or abdomen. Examples: Common iliac artery, External iliac artery, Internal iliac artery

name: vestibular ganglion
description: The ganglion of the vestibular nerve. It contains the cell bodies of the bipolar primary afferent neurons whose peripheral processes form synaptic contact with hair cells of the vestibular sensory end organs[WP,unvetted]. Distributed to the maculae of the utricle and saccule and to the ampullary crests of the semicircular ducts. The vestibular fibers arise in bipolar cells in the vestibular ganglion in the internal acoustic meatus.

name: embryonic thoracic segment
description: Any segment (UBERON:6000003) that is part of some embryonic thorax (UBERON:6000166).

name: lateral ethmoid element
description: Endochondral element that separates the olfactory region from the orbit, extends medially to meet its fellow medially below the frontal bones and is bordered by the mesethmoid anteriorly. It may articulate with the autopalatine and infraorbital 1 laterally. The lateral ethmoid is paired.

name: lateral condyle of femur
description: The lateral condyle is one of the two projections on the lower extremity of femur. It is the more prominent and is the broader both in its antero-posterior and transverse diameters

name: infralabial gland
description: Oral gland in reptiles situated immediately below the lip.

name: inferior mesenteric vein
description: A blood vessel that drains blood from the large intestine that usually terminates when reaching the splenic vein, which goes on to form the portal vein with the superior mesenteric vein (SMV). Anatomical variations include the IMV draining into the confluence of the SMV and splenic vein and the IMV draining in the SMV. The IMV lies to the right of the similarly name artery, the inferior mesenteric artery, which originates from the abdominal aorta. [WP,unvetted].

name: pubic peduncle
description: Bony projection on the anterior portion of the ilium, anterior to the acetabulum that articulates with the pubis.

name: somite 5
description: Undifferentiated mesodermal component of early trunk or tail segment or metamere, derived from paraxial mesoderm; forms the myotome, sclerotome and perhaps dermatome. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: mesethmoid ventral diverging lamella
description: Bony projection that is the posterolaterally oriented projection on the ventral region of the mesethmoid. Mesethmoid ventral diverging lamellae are paired and posteriorly contact the lateral ethmoid bones.

name: ventral hypohyal bone
description: Replacement bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates with the ceratohyal bone posteriorly and the dorsal hypohyal bone dorsally.

name: mesonephric proximal tubule
description: The mesonephric proximal tubule extends from the capsule to the distal tubule

name: autopalatine-lateral ethmoid joint
description: Joint that articulates the autopalatine and lateral ethmoid and bones. Autopalatine-lateral ethmoid joint is paired.

name: musculature of hindlimb zeugopod
description: Any collection of muscles that is part of a hindlimb zeugopod.

name: mesentery of heart
description: A mesentery that surrounds the heart.

name: insect embryonic/larval nervous system
description: Nervous system of the embryo/larva.

name: outer root sheath companion layer
description: the innermost layer of the outer root sheath.

name: interphalangeal joint of pedal digit 4
description: An interphalangeal joint of pes that is part of a pedal digit 4.

name: submucosa of left hepatic duct
description: A submucosa that is part of a left hepatic duct [Automatically generated definition].

name: paraaortic lymph node
description: The paraaortic lymph nodes (also known as para-aortic, periaortic, and peri-aortic) are a group of lymph nodes that lie in front of the lumbar vertebral bodies near the aorta. These lymph nodes receive drainage from the lower gastrointestinal tract and the pelvic organs.

name: larval antennal segment
description: Any antennal segment (UBERON:6000009) that is part of some larval head (UBERON:6001730).

name: cranial bone
description: A bone that is part of a cranium.

name: blood vessel
description: A vessel through which blood circulates in the body.

name: lamina I of gray matter of spinal cord
description: Cytoarchitectural part of spinal cord gray matter

name: submucosa of jejunum
description: A submucosa that is part of a jejunum [Automatically generated definition].

name: obsolete silver iridophore
description: Iridescent iridophore containing silver reflecting platelets.

name: extensor digitorum brevis pes
description: A muscle on the upper surface of the foot that helps extend digits 2 through 4.

name: lacrimal gland epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a lacrimal gland [Automatically generated definition].

name: tibia endochondral element
description: The major preaxial endochondral element in the posterior zeugopod[Phenoscape].

name: semicircular duct
description: Any of the three loop-shaped membranous inner tubular parts of the semicircular canals that are about one-fourth the diameter of the corresponding outer bony canals, that communicate at each end with the utricle, and that have near one end an expanded ampulla containing an area of sensory epithelium

name: Nobelian rod
description: Either of a pair of cartilaginous rods that support the intromittent organ of male Ascaphus, and are attached to the posteroventral part of the pelvic girdle.

name: integumentary projection
description: Anatomical projection that is part of the integumentl system.

name: eccrine sweat gland
description: A merocrine, unbranched, unbranched, coiled, tubular gland sweat gland. In humans, distributed over almost all of the body surface, and promote cooling by evaporation of their secretion.

name: obsolete cytoarchitectural part of occipital lobe
posterior cerebral vein
description: Vein that drains the dorsal longitudinal vessel and the caudal portions of the venous capillary network of the medulla oblongata. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: pectoral flipper tubercle
description: A bump or swelling adorining the head and leading edge of a pectoral flipper, associated with the multiple joints and terminal phalanges as found in the multiple phalanges of the humpback whale

name: bone of pelvic complex
description: A bone that is part of a pelvic complex. Examples: pubis, ischium, fot phalanx, any tarsal bone, any bone of the pelvic fin or girdle.

name: zona incerta
description: The zona incerta is a horizontally elongated region of gray matter cells in the subthalamus below the thalamus. Its connections project extensively over the brain from the cerebral cortex down into the spinal cord. Its function is unknown though several have been proposed related to 'limbic-motor integration' such as controlling visceral activity and pain; gating sensory input and synchronizing cortical and subcortical brain rhythms. Its dysfunction may play a role in central pain syndrome. It is also been identified as a promising deep brain stimulation therapy target for treating Parkinsons Disease. Its existence was first described by Auguste Forel in 1877 as a 'region of which nothing certain can be said'. A hundred and thirty years later in 2007, Nadia Urbain and Martin Desch√™nes of Universit√© Laval noted that the 'zona incerta is among the least studied regions of the brain; its name does not even appear in the index of many textbooks. ' [WP,unvetted].

name: auditory fenestra
description: Opening in the neurocranium to allow communication between the swimbladder and the inner ear.

name: manual digit 2 metacarpus pre-cartilage condensation
description: A manual digit metacarpus pre-cartilage condensation that is part of a manual digit 2 mesenchyme.

name: nucleus of the medial longitudinal fasciculus synencephalon
vaginal fluid
description: Fluid that lines the vaginal walls that consists of multiple secretions that collect in the vagina from different glands.

name: posterior lateral line nerve (PLLN)
description: Sensory nerve of the posterior lateral line component. It develops from de postotic posterior placode. PLLN innervates the trunk lines of neuromasts.

name: superior endocardial cushion
description: The endocardial cushion that forms on the dorsal surface of the AV canal.

name: vibrissal follicle-sinus complex
description: A sensory receptor of the mammalian integument system that consist of a blood sinus plus follicle, and sometimes concentric rings of epidermal tissue.

name: ovipositor
description: Organ that functions in egg deposition.

name: glabella region
description: A region of the forehead corresponding to the space between the eyebrows and above the nose.

name: segment of manus
description: A segment of autopod that is part of a manus.

name: frontal suture
description: A suture that connects the two frontal bones of the skull.

name: crista ampullaris neuroepithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a crista ampullaris.

name: pelvic fin radial element
description: Pelvic fin radial elements are internal skeletal supports of the pelvic fin.

name: short descending thin limb
description: The short descending thin limb is the descending thin limb of a short nephron that has a squamous epithelial morphology[GO].

name: upper part of vagina
description: The upper third of the vagina.

name: molar tooth 2
description: The molar tooth of the upper or lower jaw that is phylogenetically number 2

name: mesonephric glomerulus vasculature
description: The mesonephric glomerulus vasculature is composed of the tubule structures that carry blood or lymph in the mesonephric glomerulus[GO].

name: germ ring
description: The thickend rim of the blastoderm evident during late blastula and gastrula stages[FishBase]. Embryonic structure which is a uniform thickened annulus at the blastoderm margin, consisting of two layers in addition to the EVL, the epiblast and the hypoblast. The germ ring is formed by the involution of the blastoderm back upon itself[ZFA]

name: exocrine gland
description: A gland that secretes products (excluding hormones and other chemical messengers) into ducts (duct glands) which lead directly into the external environment[WP]. Typical exocrine glands include sweat glands, salivary glands, mammary glands, stomach, liver, pancreas

name: septum semircularium posterior
description: The posterior connective tissue partition between walls of otic capsule around which the membranous semicircular canals pass.

name: splenic lymph node
description: The splenic lymph nodes (or pancreaticolienal) accompany the lienal (splenic) artery, and are situated in relation to the posterior surface and upper border of the pancreas; one or two members of this group are found in the gastrolienal ligament. Their afferents are derived from the stomach, spleen, and pancreas, their efferents join the celiac group of preaortic glands.

name: cultriform process
description: Process that extends anteriorly from the orbitotemporal region.

name: navicular bone of pes
description: the oval-shaped tarsal bone found between the talus and the 3 cuneiform bones

name: pedal centrale
description: A centrale found in the pes.

name: mesencephalic neural crest
description: A neural crest that has_potential_to_developmentally_contribute_to a midbrain.

name: levator claviculae muscle
description: A skeletal muscle in the posterior triangle of the neck. It originates on the transverse processes of the upper cervical vertebrae and is inserted in the lateral half of the clavicle

name: integumental system
description: Connected anatomical system that forms a barrier between an animal and its environment. In vertebrates, the integumental system consists of the epidermis, dermis plus associated glands and adnexa such as hair and scales. In invertebrates, the integumental system may include cuticle.

name: apical ectodermal ridge pelvic fin
description: Apical ectodermal ridge that is part of the pelvic fin.

name: metencephalon sulcus limitans
description: A sulcus limitans of neural tube that is part of a future metencephalon.

name: coronomeckelian
description: Tendon bone located on the median side of the lower jaw, dorsal to Meckel's cartilage and medial to the angular. The coronomeckelian forms as an ossification of the tendon of the adductor mandibulae muscle. The coronomeckelian is a paired bone.

name: cervical spinal cord ventral horn
description: A ventral horn of spinal cord that is part of a cervical spinal cord.

name: tunicate tunic
description: Outer covering of an animal typically consisting primarily of cellulose (tunicin) in addition to varying amounts of water, protein and carbohydrates. The tunicate is a characteristic feature of Tunicata

name: imaginal disc
description: one of the parts of a holometabolous insect larva that will become a portion of the outside of the adult insect during the pupal transformation.

name: obsolete immature hair cell anterior macula
transversus perinei muscle
description: A muscle in females that overlies the soft tissue related to the cloaca, where the hemipenes are located in males.

name: epidermal-dermal junction
description: The multi-layer basement membrane between the dermis and epidermis that serves to adhere the dermis and epidermis, provide mechanical support for the epidermis, and forms a barrier to cells and large molecules across the junction

name: dorsal adductor hyomandibulae
description: Is a hyoid muscle that attaches to the dorsomedial faces of the hyosymplectics.

name: upper esophageal sphincter
description: The upper esophageal sphincter (UES) (also called the Pharyngoesophageal sphincter) refers to the superior portion of the esophagus. Unlike the lower esophageal sphincter, it consists of striated muscle and is under conscious control. The primary muscle of the UES is the cricopharyngeus portion of the inferior pharyngeal constrictor. During swallowing the upper esophageal sphincter opens so the bolus can pass into the esophagus. A secondary role of the UES is to reduce backflow from the esophagus into the pharynx.

name: olfactory placode
description: A thick plate of cells derived from the neural ectoderm in the head region of the embryo that develops into the olfactory region of the nasal cavity.

name: conotruncal ridge
description: One of the pair of spiral mesenchymal swellings in the primordial ventricular outflow tract, that eventually fuse to form the conotruncal septum, dividing the subvalvular outflow tract and contributing to the membranous interventricular septum[MP]

name: pectoral appendage
description: Paired appendage that consists of the anterior appendicular skeleton and associated soft and hard tissues, but excludes the pectoral girdle and its associated soft and hard tissues.

name: right testis
description: A testis that is in the right side of the genitalia [Automatically generated definition].

name: parakeratinized epithelium
description: An epithelium that is characterized by incomplete keratinization of the cells in the stratum corneum. The cells are flattened and composed primarily of packed tonofilaments. However, the cells may retain remnants of nuclei and other organelles

name: splenium of the corpus callosum
description: The posterior end of the corpus callosum. It overlaps the tela chorioidea of the third ventricle and the mid-brain, and ends in a thick, convex, free border.

name: primitive marginal sinus
description: The primitive marginal sinuses (PMS) are embryonic sinuses forming the later superior sagittal sinus.

name: commissural leaflet of mitral valve
description: Leaflet of mitral valve which is attached to the commissural chorda tendinea of left ventricle.

name: caput epididymis
description: The head of the epididymis

name: styloglossus
description: The Styloglossus, the shortest and smallest of the three styloid muscles, arises from the anterior and lateral surfaces of the styloid process, near its apex, and from the stylomandibular ligament. Passing downward and forward between the internal and external carotid arteries, it divides upon the side of the tongue near its dorsal surface, blending with the fibers of the Longitudinalis inferior in front of the Hyoglossus; the other, oblique, overlaps the Hyoglossus and decussates with its fibers. [WP,unvetted].

name: male organism
description: Gonochoristic organism that can produce male gametes.

name: distal interphalangeal joint of digit 2
description: A distal interphalangeal joint that is part of a digit 2.

name: subscapular artery
description: The subscapular artery, the largest branch of the axillary artery, arises at the lower border of the Subscapularis, which it follows to the inferior angle of the scapula, where it anastomoses with the lateral thoracic and intercostal arteries and with the descending branch of the transverse cervical, and ends in the neighboring muscles. About 4 cm. from its origin it gives off two branches, first the scapular circumflex artery and then the thoracodorsal artery. [WP,unvetted].

name: obsolete predominantly gray part of corticomedial nuclear complex
groove for sigmoid sinus
description: Groove for Sigmoid Sinus is a groove in the posterior cranial fossa.

name: mineralized hyaline cartilage tissue
description: Hyaline cartilage tissue that is mineralized.

name: sensory ganglion
description: The clusters of neurons in the somatic peripheral nervous system which contain the cell bodies of sensory nerve axons, interneurons and non-neuronal supporting cells.

name: vaginal plate
description: The vaginal plate is a precursor to the inferior portion of the vagina. They form from sinovaginal bulbs.

name: intersegmental pulmonary vein
description: A vein receiving blood from adjacent bronchopulmonary segments; it emerges from the inferior margin of a segment to become a tributary of a branch of a pulmonary vein.

name: distal epiphysis of phalanx of manus
description: A distal epiphysis that is part of a phalanx of manus [Automatically generated definition].

name: anterior cerebral artery
description: One of a pair of arteries on the brain that supply oxygen to most medial portions of frontal lobes and superior medial parietal lobes. The 2 anterior cerebral arteries arise from the internal carotid artery and are part of the Circle of Willis.

name: parabronchus
description: tertiary bronchus in the avian lung.

name: palatine torus
description: A bony protuberance sometimes found on the hard palate at the junction of the intermaxillary suture and the transverse palatine suture.

name: metatarsal bone
description: The metatarsus or metatarsal bones are a group of five long bones in the pes located between the tarsal bones of the hind- and mid-pes and the phalanges of the toes. Lacking individual names, the metatarsal bones are numbered from the medial side (side of big toe): the first, second, third, fourth, and fifth metatarsal. The metatarsals are analogous to the metacarpal bones of the manus. [WP,unvetted].

name: hyoideomandibular nerve
description: Nerve that is a branch of cranial nerve VII that passes through or around the suspensorium to innervate muscles and sensory organs on or near pharyngeal arch 2.

name: strand of auchene hair
description: A truncal hair that has a single constriction and bend about midway along the hair shaft, and contains two or more air cells in the medulla

name: non-material anatomical boundary
description: A non-material anatomical entity of two dimensions. Anatomical boundaries are contiguous structures.

name: supraneural 7 element
description: Supraneural element dorsal to neural spine 7.

name: haemal node
description: A lymphoid organ found in various mammals and some birds.

name: maxillary process mesenchyme from neural crest
description: Mesenchyme that develops_from a neural crest and is part of a maxillary process mesenchyme.

name: sphenozygomatic suture
description: The Sphenozygomatic suture is the cranial suture between the sphenoid bone and the zygomatic bone.

name: alveolar mucosa
description: The mucous membrane apical to the attached gingiva.

name: apex of paracone
description: The highest elevation of the paracone on a molariform tooth.

name: plica semilunaris of conjunctiva
description: The plica semilunaris is a small fold of bulbar conjunctiva on the medial canthus of the eye. It is loose, so that eye movements are not restricted.

name: Brodmann (1909) area 33
description: Brodmann area 33, also known as pregenual area 33, is a subdivision of the cytoarchitecturally defined cingulate region of cerebral cortex. It is a narrow band located in the anterior cingulate gyrus adjacent to the supracallosal gyrus in the depth of the callosal sulcus, near the genu of the corpus callosum. Cytoarchitecturally it is bounded by the ventral anterior cingulate area 24 and the supracallosal gyrus (Brodmann-1909).

name: epidural space
description: The outermost part of the spinal canal. It is the space within the canal (formed by the surrounding vertebrae) lying outside the dura mater.

name: hyoid articular area
description: Area on the otic capsule for the articulation of the hyoid

name: mucosa of nasolacrimal duct
description: A mucosa that is part of a nasolacrimal duct [Automatically generated definition].

name: cardiac ventricle
description: Cardiac chamber through which blood leaves the heart.

name: mucosa of biliary tree
description: A mucosa that is part of a biliary tree [Automatically generated definition].

name: head connective tissue
description: A portion of connective tissue that is part of a head [Automatically generated definition].

name: dorsal fin proximal radial bone 8
description: dorsal fin proximal radial 8 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: atrioventricular valve
description: A cardial valve in the atrioventricular region that separates the atrium from the ventricle and prevent backflow from the ventricles into the atria during systole.

name: postsphenoidal bone
description: The posterior portion of the sphenoid bone developed in five separate parts consisting of a central basisphenoid, the two alisphenoids, and the two medial pterygoid laminae.

name: yolk
description: Nutrient store for embryonic development in the form of semicrystalline phospholipoprotein and contained within yolk granules. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: trachea elastic tissue
description: An elastic tissue that is part of a trachea [Automatically generated definition].

name: obsolete primary oogonium
description: A germ cell that is a primordial oocyte in a female and that develops into secondary oogonia by mitotic division.

name: anal membrane endodermal component
description: An endoderm that is part of a anal region.

name: serosa of fundus of stomach
description: A serous membrane that is part of a fundus of stomach.

name: cardiac nerve plexus
description: A plexus of nerves situated at the base of the heart that innervate the heart.

name: levator mandibulae externus
description: Responsible for the closing of the jaw.

name: obsolete superficial feature part of diencephalon
pearly penile papule
description: small saliences on the ridge of the glans of the male genital organs.

name: sclerotome somite 24
description: Medial ventral region of the somite that will form vertebral cartilages. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: bronchial tube
description: Either of the short tubes which bifurcate posteriorly from the trachea and lead into the lungs.

name: zygomaticus minor muscle
description: Facial muscle attached to the modiolus, corner (angle) of the mouth, and zygomatic bone. This muscle is ventral to the zygomaticus minor and dorsal to the platysma muscle. In many mammals this muscle also has an attachment to the cartilage of the external ear, in which case it is called the auriculolabialis inferior. See Diogo 2008; Diogo et al., 2009; Burrows et al.., 2011., also DuBrul, 1980.

name: temporal branch of lateral pretrosal artery
description: Part of lateral pretrosal artery which supplies blood to the eyelids.

name: medial arcuate ligament
description: The medial arcuate ligament (also medial lumbocostal arch) is tendinous fascia that arches over the psoas major muscle as it passes through the diaphragm.

name: middle mediastinum
description: The middle mediastinum is the broadest part of the interpleural space. It is made up of the pericardial sac and its contents.

name: hindlimb zeugopod bone
description: A bone that is part of a lower leg [Automatically generated definition].

name: endo-epithelium
description: Epithelium that derives from the endoderm. Examples: urothelium, transitional epithelium of ureter, epithelium of prostatic gland.[FMA]

name: CA1 alveus
description: CA1 portion of the alveus

name: proximal straight tubule
description: The proximal straight tubule is the part of the descending limb that extends from the proximal convoluted tubule to the descending thin tubule.

name: obsolete regional part of midbrain
description: A regional part of brain that is part of a midbrain [Automatically generated definition].

name: obsolete mode of ossification
description: The formation of bone or of a bony substanc, or the conversion of fibrous tissue or of cartilage into bone or a bony substance.

name: uterine fat pad
description: Encapsulated adipose tissue associated with the uterus

name: posterodorsal process of ilium
description: Anatomical project part of the blade of the ilium that projects posteriorly.

name: proximal phalanx
description: Proximal-most phalanx within a digit.

name: common iliac lymph node
description: The external iliac lymph nodes, from eight to ten in number, lie along the external iliac vessels. They are arranged in three groups, one on the lateral, another on the medial, and a third on the anterior aspect of the vessels; the third group is, however, sometimes absent. Their principal afferents are derived from the inguinal lymph nodes, the deep lymphatics of the abdominal wall below the umbilicus and of the adductor region of the thigh, and the lymphatics from the glans penis vel clitoridis, the membranous urethra, the prostate, the fundus of the urinary bladder, the cervix uteri, and upper part of the vagina.

name: paracentral sulcus
description: The paracentral sulcus is a sulcus of the brain. It forms the paracentral lobule's anterior border.

name: trabecular layer of ventricle
description: A myocardium trabecular layer that is part of a cardiac ventricle.

name: lesser sac
description: The lesser sac, also known as the omental bursa, is the cavity in the abdomen that is formed by the lesser and greater omentum. Usually found in mammals, it is connected with the greater sac via the epiploic foramen (also known as the Foramen of Winslow). [WP,unvetted].

name: acetabular fossa
description: The acetabular fossa is the roughened depression in the centre of the acetabulum, surrounded by the lunate acetabular surface and the acetabular notch. The acetabular fossa provides an insertion point for the teres ligaments that secure the femoral head.

name: hypoplastron
description: A paired plastron element that is in the posterior part of the plastron, anterior to the xiphiplastron and posterior to the hyoplastron

name: pyloric antrum
description: the area at the bottom of the stomach on the caudal side of the pyloric canal that contains gastrin-producing G cells, which stimulate acid production, and the luminal pH-sensitive population of somatostatin-producing D cells

name: superior part of vestibular ganglion
description: The part of the vestibular ganglion that receives fibers from the maculae of the utricle and the sacculae and the ampullae of the anterior and lateral semicircular ducts.

name: prepubic element
description: A small plate of cartilage synchondrotically united with the pubis. Modified from Baez and Harrison 2005.

name: embryonic prothoracic segment
description: Prothoracic segment of the embryo.

name: distal segment of caudal ray
description: Lepidotrichial segment that is part of the distal region of a caudal fin ray.

name: element Y of fore mesopodium
description: Oval carpal element that is located on the anteromedial side of the radiale and the anterolateral side of the ulnare. Anteriorly, it articulates with carpals 1 through 4 (or 2 through 5 according to some authors). It is also recognized as centrale by some authors. This element originates from one, two, or three condensation centers. Occasionally it may fuse to carpal 2(1), carpal 3(2), the ulnare, or other elements.

name: dorsolateral fasciculus of medulla
description: Part of Lissauer's tract located in the medulla

name: lateral epicondyle of femur
description: The lateral epicondyle of the femur, smaller and less prominent than the medial epicondyle, gives attachment to the fibular collateral ligament of the knee-joint. Directly below it is a small depression from which a smooth well-marked groove curves obliquely upward and backward to the posterior extremity of the condyle.

name: dorsal patch of Leydig's organ
description: The dosralmost of the two bodies of the elasmopbranch hemopoietic organ betweean the esophageal mucosa and muscularis

name: transcapular ligament
description: Ligament that is attached to supracleithrum and basioccipital.

name: jejunal vein
description: A tributary of the superior mesenteric vein that drains the jejunum.

name: chondroglossus muscle
description: The Chondroglossus is sometimes described as a part of the Hyoglossus, but is separated from it by fibers of the Genioglossus, which pass to the side of the pharynx. It is about 2 cm. long, and arises from the medial side and base of the lesser cornu and contiguous portion of the body of the hyoid bone, and passes directly upward to blend with the intrinsic muscular fibers of the tongue, between the Hyoglossus and Genioglossus.

name: opercle
description: Dermal bone that forms the postero-dorsal part of the opercular series. The opercle articulates with the hyomandibula antero-dorsally and with the subopercle ventrally. The opercle is a paired bone.

name: pubis-ischium contact
description: Contact zone between the pubis and the ischium.

name: pharyngobranchial 1 element
description: Most anterior pharyngobranchial element, located medial to the epibranchials.

name: urophysis
description: This is a neurosecretory organ rostral to the ampulla caudalis on the ventral surface of the distal end of the spinal cord. Receives axons from caudal neurosecretory nucleus, which contains Dahlgren cells that secrete urotensin I and II, implicated in osmotic regulation, cardiovascular function and reproduction[Butler].

name: somite 26
description: Undifferentiated mesodermal component of early trunk or tail segment or metamere, derived from paraxial mesoderm; forms the myotome, sclerotome and perhaps dermatome. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: posterior process of basipterygium
description: Process that is the posteriorly oriented, paired projection of the basipterygium.

name: mandibular lateral line neuromast
description: Neuromast that is part of the mandibular lateral line. Kimmel et al, 1995. (Also see Anatomical Atlas entry for lateral line by T. Whitfield.)

name: tarsal segment
description: A segment of the tarsus of the adult leg. The first tarsal segment, the metatarsus, is proximally connected to the tibia. Tarsal segments are covered in 8 longitudinal rows of bristles, with row 1 being the most ventral.

name: lobar bronchus alveolar system
description: The lobar bronchus alveolar system is where molecules of oxygen and carbon dioxide are passively exchanged, by diffusion, between the gaseous environment and the blood in the lobar bronchus

name: pharyngobranchial 2 bone uncinate process
description: Bony projection that is part of the pharyngobranchial 2 bone.

name: bone of tail
description: A bone that is part of a post-anal tail.

name: mesentery of oesophagus
description: A mesentery that is part of a esophagus [Automatically generated definition].

name: interphalangeal joint of pedal digit 5
description: An interphalangeal joint of pes that is part of a pedal digit 5.

name: submucosa of urinary bladder
description: The submucous layer of the wall of the urinary bladder.

name: connective tissue of prostate gland
description: A portion of connective tissue that is part of a prostate gland.

name: vomerine tooth
description: A tooth that is on the vomer.

name: capillary
description: Any of the smallest blood vessels connecting arterioles with venules.

name: eyelid blood vessel
description: A blood vessel that is part of a eyelid [Automatically generated definition].

name: muscular coat
description: A region of muscle in many organs in the vertebrate body, adjacent to the submucosa membrane. It is responsible for gut movement such as peristalsis.

name: serosa of rectum
description: A serous membrane that is part of a rectum [Automatically generated definition].

name: velar skeleton
description: Subdivision of skeleton that is part of the velum and consists of a complex arrangement of thin cartilage rods and arches

name: tapetum of corpus callosum
description: On either side of the corpus collosum, the fibers radiate in the white substance and pass to the various parts of the cerebral cortex; those curving forward from the genu into the frontal lobe constitute the forceps anterior, and those curving backward into the occipital lobe, the forceps posterior. Between these two parts is the main body of the fibers which constitute the tapetum and extend laterally on either side into the temporal lobe, and cover in the central part of the lateral ventricle. [Wikipedia via Greys]

name: terminal bronchus epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a terminal bronchus [Automatically generated definition].

name: dorsolateral motor nucleus of vagal nerve
description: Motor nucleus of vagal nerve that is located within the dorsolateral portion of rhomobomere 8.

name: hypaxial region somite 1
description: Somite-derived body wall muscle present ventral to the horizontal myoseptum. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: notochordal canal
description: A tubular passage that extends from the primitive pit into the head process during the early stages of embryonic development in mammals. It perforates the splanchnopleure layer so that the yolk sac and the amnion are connected temporarily.

name: blood nerve barrier
description: barrier between the perineurium of peripheral nerves and the vascular endothelium of endoneurial capillaries. The perineurium acts as a diffusion barrier, but ion permeability at the blood-nerve barrier is still higher than at the blood-brain barrier[GO].

name: gastric pit
description: Gastric pits are indentations in the stomach which denote entrances to the gastric glands. They are deeper in the pylorus than they are in the other parts of the stomach. The human stomach has several million of these pits.

name: obsolete cytoarchitectural part of frontal lobe
M. gracilis major
description: Originates by a broad tendon from the postero-ventral surface of the pelvic rim and inserts by two tendons. One broad tendon inserts on the knee aponeurosis, and in part on the ventro-medial surface of the tibiofibula. The other long tendon inserts on the posterior surface of the tibiofibula just below the proximal head.

name: meningeal cluster
description: The collection of all meningeal layers that line a central nervous system.

name: optic tract
description: Diencephalic white matter (tract) which is comprised of retinal ganglion cell axons after which they have passed through the optic chiasm[ZFA]. Predominantly white matter structure found in diencephalon consisting of fibers originating in the retina. The optic tract is considered to extend from the point of the optic chiasm and terminates largely, although not exclusively, in the lateral geniculate complex. Other fibers end in the superior colliculus and other structures in the diencephalon, midbrain and brainstem (MM)[NIF].

name: upper hypural set
description: Anatomical cluster including hypural 3 and more dorsal hypurals that supports the dorsal series of principal caudal lepidotrichia or rays.
