The upper hypural set articulates or fuses to ural centra 3, 4 or 5 (polyural terminology) or ural centrum 2 (diural terminology) depending on the teleost subgroup. The upper hypural set is composed of unpaired median bones.

name: manual digit 3 metacarpus pre-cartilage condensation
description: A manual digit metacarpus pre-cartilage condensation that is part of a manual digit 3 mesenchyme.

name: secretion of serous membrane
description: A transudate found in the serous sac.

name: subglottis
description: The lower portion of the larynx, extending from just beneath the vocal cords down to the top of the trachea.

name: saccus vasculosus
description: a circumventricular organ of the hypothalamus of many jawed fishes, protruding from the caudal infundibular wall. It is a vascularized neuroepithelium that consists of coronet cells, cerebrospinal fluid-contacting neurons and supporting cells.

name: scale radius
description: Erosion channel that radiates out from the growth center (focus) of the scale across and through the circuli.

name: buccal vestibule
description: The buccal vestibule is the space external to teeth and gums and internal to lips and cheeks. The proportion of its walls formed by the lips varies according to species depending upon their feeding action. The horse like most herbivores has a relatively small opening. PPP The buccal vestibule opens to the outside rostrally via a U shaped slit the oral fissure. PPP When the mouth is closed the buccal vestibule and the mouth cavity proper connect via spaces between and behind the teeth. These allow free communication between the two sides of the vestibule. PPP Several salivary ducts open into the dorso caudal part of the vestibule: PPP Parotid gland - opens into the cheek on the small parotid papilla, opposite to the caudal part of upper 4 th premolar teeth PPP Zygomatic gland - the main duct opens in the caudal part of the upper 1 st molar tooth on a small papilla near the vestibular fornix PPP Submucous glands - minimal in number, confined to the lower lip and adjacent part of the cheek. Secretion occurs through about 10 openings located near the fornix of the vestibule.

name: flexor hallucis brevis muscle
description: A muscle that originates from the cuboid bone and divides into two portions, which are inserted into the medial and lateral sides of the base of the first phalanx of the great toe, a sesamoid bone being present in each tendon at its insertion.

name: hepatic cord
description: A three-dimensional arrangement formed by plates of hepatocytes, usually one cell thick, that radiates from the center of the liver lobule; hepatic laminae are highly branched, irregular structures bordered by endothelial lined vascular spaces called hepatic sinusoids.

name: dorsal skin of finger
description: A dorsal skin of digit that is part of a manual digit.

name: lambdoid suture
description: the dense, fibrous connective tissue joint between the parietal bones and the occipital bone

name: thymus subcapsular epithelium
description: the epithelial cells lining the capsule and trabeculae of the thymus

name: internal female genitalia
description: The internal feminine genital organs, including the ovaries, uterine tubes, uterus, uterine cervix, and vagina.

name: mesonephric glomerular epithelium
description: A mesonephric glomerular visceral epithelial cell is a specialized epithelial cell that contains 'feet' that interdigitate with the 'feet' of other glomerular epithelial cells in the mesonephros[GO].

name: scale
description: A small rigid plate that grows out of an animal's skin to provide protection. In lepidopteran (butterfly and moth) species, scales are plates on the surface of the insect wing, and provide coloration. Scales are quite common and have evolved multiple times with varying structure and function.

name: bulbo-urethral gland
description: Any of the small paired racemose glands below the apex of the prostate in males, located posterolateral to the membranous portion of the urethra at the base of the penis, between the two layers of the fascia of the urogenital diaphragm, in the deep perineal pouch, and enclosed by transverse fibers of the sphincter urethrae membranaceae muscle; homologous to the greater vestibular (Bartholin's) glands in the female[MP]

name: subotic alae
description: Paired processes extending lateraly from the posterior body of the parasphenoid that, when present, support the otic capsules ventrally.

name: ectepicondylar flange
description: Flange present of the distal region of the humerus, associated with extensor musculature of forelimb.

name: scent gland
description: Scent glands are exocrine glands found in most mammals. They produce semi-viscous secretions which contain pheromones and other semiochemical compounds. These odor-messengers indicate information such as status, territory marking, mood, and sexual power. The odor may be subliminal-not consciously detectable. Though it is not their primary function, the salivary glands may also function as scent glands in some animals.

name: abdominal segment of trunk
description: The abdominal segment of the torso.

name: blubber
description: A thick layer of vascularized adipose tissue found under the skin of all cetaceans, pinnipeds and sirenians.

name: myelencephalon sulcus limitans
description: A sulcus limitans of neural tube that is part of a future myelencephalon.

name: sublingual
description: Endochondral bone that is the median element of the ventral hyoid arch, generally lying between the paired ventral hypohyals.

name: ramus superficial ophthalmic
description: Dorsal branch of ADLLN that innervates supraorbital line of neuromasts.

name: obsolete immature hair cell posterior macula
epiphyseal bar
description: Bilaterally paired medial bar of cartilage formed at midorbit through medial chondrification from triangles of cartilage that later form the junction of the taeniae marginales anterior, taeniae marginales posterior and the epiphyseal bar.

name: epigastrium
description: The upper central region of the abdomen between the costal margins and the subcostal plane.

name: coccygeal nerve
description: The coccygeal nerve is the spinal nerve that corresponds to the coccyx bone.

name: mandible coronoid process
description: A dorsal process on the lower jaw associated with muscle attachment. It may be formed by a separate coronoid bone or as a process of the dentary. In most living (and many extinct) mammals, the most dorsal of the three proximal processes of the jaw.

name: pillar of the anterior semicircular canal
pectoral appendage musculature
description: Any collection of muscles that is part of a pectoral appendage.

name: interdigital region
description: Anatomical region connecting two digits.

name: ear vesicle
description: An epithelial sac of invaginated ectoderm formed from the otic placode that gives rise to the structures of the inner ear[MP]

name: infundibulum of hair follicle
description: The portion of the hair follicle from the entrance of the sebaceous gland duct to the epidermal surface opening.

name: jugular vein
description: The jugular veins are veins that bring deoxygenated blood from the head back to the heart via the superior vena cava.

name: blastocele
description: fluid-filled central region of a blastocyst.

name: avascular GAG-rich matrix
description: Proteinaceous extracellular matrix that is avascular and consists primarily of glycosaminoglycans.

name: cardiovascular system
description: Anatomical system that has as its parts the heart and blood vessels.

name: lacrimal apparatus
description: A network of orbital structures of the eye that secrete and drain tears from the surface of the eyeball into the nasal cavity; these parts include the lacrimal glands, lacrimal lake, lacrimal ducts, lacrimal canals, lacrimal sacs, nasolacrimal ducts, and lacrimal puncta.

name: orthokeratinized epithelium
description: A keratinized epithelium in which the cells of the stratum corneum become very flat, loose their nuclei and cytoplasmic organelles and are now composed of densely packed tonofilaments cemented by filaggrin

name: sinus of von Szily
description: A circular gap in the iris near the pupil between the layers of the optic cup (von Szily, 1902)

name: anterior leaflet of mitral valve
description: Leaflet of mitral valve which is attached to the anterior head of the posterior papillary muscle of left ventricle through the chorda tendinea of the left ventricle.

name: corpus epididymis
description: The body of the epididymis

name: palatoglossus muscle
description: The palatoglossus, glossopalatinus, or palatoglossal muscle is a small fleshy fasciculus, narrower in the middle than at either end, forming, with the mucous membrane covering its surface, the glossopalatine arch. It arises from the anterior surface of the soft palate, where it is continuous with the muscle of the opposite side, and passing downward, forward, and lateralward in front of the palatine tonsil, is inserted into the side of the tongue, some of its fibers spreading over the dorsum, and others passing deeply into the substance of the organ to intermingle with the Transversus lingu√¶. [WP,unvetted].

name: surface structure
description: Anatomical structure that overlaps the outer epithelial layer and is adjacent to the space surrounding the organism.

name: endoneurial fluid
description: Fluid of the ganglia and peripheral nerves that lie outside the brain and spinal cord

name: brachial artery
description: The brachial artery is the major blood vessel of the (upper) arm. It is the continuation of the axillary artery beyond the lower margin of teres major muscle. It continues down the ventral surface of the arm until it reaches the cubital fossa at the elbow. It then divides into the radial and ulnar arteries which run down the forearm. In some individuals, the bifurcation occurs much earlier and the ulnar and radial arteries extend through the upper arm. The pulse of the brachial artery is palpable on the anterior aspect of the elbow, medial to the tendon of the biceps, and, with the use of a stethoscope and sphygmomanometer (blood pressure cuff) often used to measure the blood pressure. The brachial artery is closely related to the median nerve; in proximal regions, the median nerve is immediately lateral to the brachial artery. Distally, the median nerve crosses the medial side of the brachial artery and lies anterior to the elbow joint. [WP,unvetted].

name: anterior segment of eyeball
description: any of the parts of the eye that lie in front of, or ventral to, the lens (inclusive)

name: sinovaginal bulb
description: solid evaginations of the UG sinus that develops into a vaginal plate that which will will eventually canalize to form the inferior portion of the vagina.

name: right coronary artery
description: Coronary artery which runs along the right side of the heart and predominantly supplies the mycocardium of the right side of the heart[Wikipedia,modified]

name: popliteal area
description: A depression on the ventral side of the femur, at the knee joint, between the condyles.

name: lacrimal punctum
description: A minute orifice on the summit of the papillae lacrimales, which is the commencement point of the lacrimal canaliculi.

name: striated duct of salivary gland
description: gland duct which connects an intercalated duct to an interlobular duct in a salivary gland.

name: vitelline vein
description: the paired veins that carry blood from the yolk sac back to the embryo

name: phalanx of pes
description: A phalanx that is part of a hindlimb autopod[Automatically generated definition].

name: lateral fontanel of frontal
description: Fontanel within the frontal bone near the frontal-sphenotic joint. Lateral fontanel of frontal is paired.

name: bed nuclei of the stria terminalis oval nucleus
description: Part of bed nucleus of stria terminalis, comprising a distinct, large, egg-shaped collection of neurons that, together with the juxtacapsular (Ju) and rhomboid (Rh) nuclei, encompass the anterolateral area of the BST (Ju and Swanson, 1989)

name: strand of awl hair
description: A truncal hairs that is straight, but shorter than a guard hair, and contain two or more air cells in the medulla

name: endocrine pancreas
description: The part of the pancreas that is part of the endocrine system and is made up of islet cells, which produce insulin, glucagon and somatostatin.

name: maxillary process mesenchyme from head mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that develops_from a head mesenchyme from mesoderm and is part of a maxillary process mesenchyme.

name: occipitomastoid suture
description: The occipitomastoid suture is the cranial suture between the occipital bone and the mastoid portion of the temporal bone. It is continuous with the lambdoidal suture.

name: lumen of atrioventricular canal
description: A tube lumen that is part of a atrioventricular canal.

name: bulboid corpuscle
description: A receptor in the transitional zone between mucous membrane and skin.

name: cortical preplate
description: The layer of the developing cerebral cortex that is formed from the first cohort of neurons to migrate out of the cortical ventricular zone; split by the second wave into marginal zone and subplate.

name: caniniform region
description: The anterior region of the maxillary tooth row, if that tooth row contains teeth that are substantially over the premaxillary teeth (see Laurin and Reisz 1995)

name: Brodmann (1909) area 34
description: Brodmann area 34 is a part of the brain. It has been described as part of the entorhinal area. It has been described as part of the superior temporal gyrus.

name: acromioclavicular joint
description: Any joint connecting the acromonion of the scapula and clavicle.

name: pancreas head parenchyma
description: A parenchyma that is part of a head of pancreas [Automatically generated definition].

name: hypochordal radial
description: Caudal fin radial element located ventral to the notochord

name: mucosa of pharyngotympanic tube
description: A mucosa that is part of a pharyngotympanic tube [Automatically generated definition].

name: ampullary gland secretion
description: A bodily secretion that produced_by a ampullary gland.

name: ductus venosus
description: The vascular channel in the fetus passing through the liver and joining the umbilical vein with the inferior vena cava.

name: margo mandibularis of pterygoid
description: Ventrally directed margin that connects the anterior and posterior rami of the pterygoid.

name: abdomen connective tissue
description: A portion of connective tissue that is part of an abdomen [Automatically generated definition].

name: hippocampus fimbria
description: Regional part of fornix consisting of a prominent white matter structure adjacent to the hippocampus on the ventricular side continuous with the alveus. Near the splenium the fimbria separates from the hippocampus as the crus of the fornix. [adapted from Wikipedia] (MM: 2006-10-26).

name: tricuspid valve
description: An atrioventricular valve that is part of the outflow part of the right atrium.

name: dorsum of tongue
description: The superior surface of the tongue divided by the sulcus terminalis into an anterior two-thirds, the presulcal part (pars presulcalis). and a posterior one-third, the postsulcal part (pars postsulcalis).

name: obsolete regional part of nucleus accumbens
pineal complex
description: A cluster in the epithalamus that consists of the pineal body and any associated structures, such as the parapineal gland or the parietal organ. The complex is poorly developed in mammals.

name: cephalodorsosubpharyngeus
description: One of the principal muscles used in swallowing.

name: extremitas anterior
description: Large anterior outgrowth of the septomaxilla that is directed into the space between the alary cartilage and the lamina inferior.

name: aorta tunica media
description: The middle layer of the aorta wall, containing the smooth muscle layer and elastic fibers.

name: obsolete primary spermatogonium
description: A germ cell that is a primordial spermatocyte in a male and that develops into secondary spermatogonia by mitotic division.

name: lateral lingual swelling epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a lateral lingual swelling.

name: adventitia of esophagus
description: A adventitia that is part of a esophagus.

name: pulmonary nerve plexus
description: The pulmonary plexus is an autonomic plexus formed from pulmonary branches of vagus nerve and the sympathetic trunk that supplies the Bronchial tree. [WP,modified].

name: m. latissimus dorsi
description: Muscle which originates from the ventral surface of the dorsal fascia and inserts on the deltoid crest of the humerus.

name: sclerotome somite 27
description: Medial ventral region of the somite that will form vertebral cartilages. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: penile spine
description: Keratinized structures along the glans and/or shaft of their penis that may be involved in sexual selection.

name: obsolete predominantly gray regional part of epithalamus
olfactory cortex layer 3
description: Deepest layer of olfactory cortex

name: lateral arcuate ligament
description: The lateral arcuate ligament (also lateral lumbocostal arch) is a ligament under the diaphragm that arches across the upper part of the quadratus lumborum. It is traversed by the subcostal nerve, artery and vein.

name: posterior mediastinum
description: The posterior mediastinum is an irregular triangular space running parallel with the vertebral column.

name: midgut dorsal mesentery
description: A dorsal mesentery that is part of a midgut.

name: mesenchyme derived from head neural crest
description: Mesenchyme that develops_from a cranial neural crest.

name: hindlimb stylopod muscle
description: Any muscle organ that is part of a hindlimb stylopod (upper leg)[Automatically generated definition].

name: transitional epithelium of major calyx
description: An urothelium of ureter that is part of a mucosa of major calyx.

name: CA3 alveus
description: Part of alveus lying within hippocampal sector CA3

name: thick ascending limb of loop of Henle
description: the distal sub-portion of the ascending loop of Henle which is lined by simple cuboidal epithelium and enters the renal cortex to empty a hypotonic filtrate into the distal convoluted tubule

name: obsolete regional part of intermediate hypothalamic region
description: A regional part of brain that is part of a intermediate hypothalamic region [Automatically generated definition].

name: permanent cartilage
description: Chondrogenic element that is composed of cartilage that is not replaced.

name: proximal mesopodial bone
description: A proximal mesopodial endochondral element that is composed primarily of a bone tissue.

name: intercentrum
description: The anteriormost of the two possible elements found in the tetrapod centrum (when the centrum is not a single element).

name: olivocochlear bundle
description: A pathway that terminates on the hair cells of the cochlea or equivalent organ in the inner ear.

name: head external integument structure
description: Dermal, epidermal, glandular and pigment structures of the external head integument.

name: imbricate neural arch
description: Overlapping neural arches that obscure the spinal cord dorsally.

name: compact layer of ventricle
description: The outer layer the ventricular myocardium, muscle fibers are arranged in a compact form and involved the entire ventricle.

name: mesovarium
description: The mesentery that suspends the ovary from the dorsal wall of the coelom[VHOG].

name: acetabular notch
description: The acetabulum presents below a deep notch, the acetabular notch, which is continuous with a circular non-articular depression, the acetabular fossa, at the bottom of the cavity: this depression is perforated by numerous apertures, and lodges a mass of fat. The notch is converted into a foramen by the transverse ligament; through the foramen nutrient vessels and nerves enter the joint; the margins of the notch serve for the attachment of the ligament of the head of the femur.

name: xiphiplastron
description: A paired plastron element that is in the posterior part of the plastron, posterior to the hypoplastron

name: pylorus
description: the stomach tissue region surrounding and controlling the distal outlet of the stomach, which opens into the duodenum

name: parasymphysial plate
description: Bone, often with tooth attachments, on the lingual side of the anterior of the lower jaw.

name: sternal keel
description: The vertical plate of bone or cartilage attached to the median line of the sternum. Modified from Baumel et al. 1993

name: embryonic mesothoracic segment
description: Mesothoracic segment of the embryo.

name: epibranchial 4-upper pharyngeal toothplate joint
description: Joint that articulates the epibranchial 4 cartilage or bone and upper pharyngeal toothplate. Epibranchial 4-upper pharyngeal toothplate joint is paired.

name: nigrostriatal tract
description: The term nigrostriatal fibers refers to a dopaminergic fiber pathway connecting the substantia nigra with the striatum. It is not readily distinguished in myelin-stained cross-sections (Carpenter-83).

name: medial epicondyle of femur
description: The medial epicondyle of the femur is a bony protrusion located on the medial side of the bone's distal end. Located above the medial condyle, it bears an elevation, the adductor tubercle, which serves for the attachment of the superficial part, or 'tendinous insertion', of the adductor magnus. This tendinous part here forms an intermuscular septum which forms the medial separation between the thigh's flexors and extensors. Behind it, and proximally to the medial condyle is a rough impression which gives origin to the medial head of the Gastrocnemius.

name: obsolete predominantly Gray regional part of inferior parietal cortex
mucosa of dorsum of tongue
description: A mucosa that is part of a dorsum of tongue.

name: ossified transcapular ligament
description: Membrane bone that is fused to supracleithrum and is jointed to basioccipital and exoccipital.

name: ileal vein
description: The veins that drain blood from the ileum into the superior mesenteric vein.

name: adipose fin
description: A fin that is fleshy, lacks supporting rays, and is located posterior to the dorsal fin.

name: pharyngobranchial 2 element
description: Pharyngobranchial element, located medial to the epibranchials and posteriorly adjacent to pharyngobranchial 1 element.

name: scapular foramen
description: Foramen that is located in the scapula. The scapular foramen is paired and formed by a ring of bone.

name: renal sinus of right kidney
description: A renal sinus that is part of a right kidney.

name: interalveolar septum
description: A the thin septum that separates adjacent pulmonary alveoli, containing connective tissue constituents of the respiratory tissue and the capillary network of the blood supply of the lung.

name: proximal carpal bone pre-cartilage condensation
description: A proximal carpal endochondral element that is composed primarily of a pre-cartilage condensation.

name: humerus cartilage element
description: A humerus endochondral element that is composed primarily of cartilage tissue.

name: arm bone
description: A bone that is part of the region of the forelimb that includes the zeugopod and stylopod. Examples: patella, femur, tibia

name: deep cerebral vein
description: The deep cerebral veins are a group of veins in the head. This group includes the superior thalamostriate vein.

name: mesentery of midgut
description: A mesentery that is part of a midgut [Automatically generated definition].

name: interphalangeal joint of manual digit 2
description: An interphalangeal joint of manus that is part of a manual digit 2.

name: submucosa of trigone of urinary bladder
description: A submucosa that is part of a trigone of urinary bladder [Automatically generated definition].

name: larval gnathal segment
description: Any gnathal segment (UBERON:6000011) that is part of some larval head (UBERON:6001730).

name: subepithelial connective tissue of prostatic gland
bone of lower jaw
description: Any bone that is part of the lower jaw skeleton. This includes (when present): the dentary/mandible, the articular, the splenial, the suprangular

name: crypt of Lieberkuhn
description: the tubular intestinal glands found in the mucosal membranes

name: iris blood vessel
description: A blood vessel that is part of a iris [Automatically generated definition].

name: serosa of colon
description: A serous membrane that is part of a colon [Automatically generated definition].

name: kidney epithelium
description: the cellular avascular layer of the kidney luminar surfaces

name: cecal tonsil
description: A thickened round patch of lymphoid tissue located at the ileocecal junction adjacent to the sacculus rotundus.

name: dorsolateral septum
description: Portion of tissue that grows in from the dorsolateral wall of the otic vesicle, forming a dorsolateral partition between the developing anterior and posterior semicircular canals.

name: pedal digit 1 epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a pedal digit 1.

name: hypaxial region somite 12
description: Somite-derived body wall muscle present ventral to the horizontal myoseptum. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: fascia of Scarpa
description: The deep layer (fascia of Scarpa) is a layer of the anterior abdominal wall.

name: rostral blood island
description: Hematopoietic tissue derived from the cephalic mesoderm. Predominantly produces myeloid cells. de Jong and Zon 2005.

name: Brodmann area
description: A segmentation of the cerebral cortex on the basis of cytoarchitecture as described in Brodmann-1905, Brodmann-1909 and Brodmann-10. Maps for several species were presented. NeuroNames includes only areas in the human and in Old World monkeys. Of the latter, Brodmann studied representatives of several species including guenons (one Cercopithecus mona, one Cercocebus torquatus, and one Cercopithecus otherwise unspecified), which are all closely related African species, and one macaque (Macaca mulatta) an Asian species (Brodmann-1905). The legend to the summary map in Brodmann-1909 ascribes the areas simply to Cercopithecus. Brodmann referenced the areas by name and number. The same area number in humans and monkeys did not necessarily refer to topologically or cytoarchitecturally homologous structures. In NeuroNames the standard term for human areas consists of the English translation of Brodmann's Latin name followed by the number he assigned, e.g., agranular frontal area 6; the standard terms for monkey areas are in the format: area 6 of Brodmann-1909. He mapped a portion of areas limited to the banks of sulci, e.g., area 3 of Brodmann-1909 (Brodmann-1909) onto the adjacent, visible surface. This accounts for the fact that some areas appear larger on his surface map than on maps of other authors, e.g., area 3 of Vogts-1919. (Adapted from NeuroNames)

name: sacral vertebra pre-cartilage condensation
description: A sacral vertebra endochondral element that is composed primarily of a pre-cartilage condensation.

name: cervical thymus
description: A mature thymus that is entirely part of the cervical region.

name: habenular commissure
description: A brain commissure that is situated in front of the pineal gland and connects the habenular nucleus on one side of the diencephalon with that on the other side.

name: agranular insular cortex
description: Agranular region of the insular cortex

name: lower hypural set
description: Anatomical cluster including hypurals 1 and 2 that supports part of the ventral principal caudal lepidotrichia or rays and that separates from the dorsal hypural set through the hypural diastema. The lower hypural set articulates or fuses to ural centra 1 and 2 (polyural terminology) or ural centrum 1 (diural terminology) depending on the teleost subgroup. The lower hypural set is composed of unpaired median bones.

name: manual digit 4 metacarpus pre-cartilage condensation
description: A manual digit metacarpus pre-cartilage condensation that is part of a manual digit 4 mesenchyme.

name: parenchyma of mammary gland
description: Parenchymal tissue that consists of the alveoli, grape-like clusters where milk is stored, and branching ducts, which are tubular canals carrying gladular secretions.

name: obsolete musculus obliquus inferior
description: Cranial nerve III innverated; ventral in the obliquus group.

name: hypaxial region somite 11
description: Somite-derived body wall muscle present ventral to the horizontal myoseptum. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: tracheoesophageal fold
description: One of two longitudinal ridges that develop caudal to the pharynx and fuses to give rise to the tracheoesophageal septum.

name: morphological feature
description: A part of an organism or organ that is continuous with its surroundings and distinguished from its surroundings based on morphology.

name: inferior mesenteric ganglion
description: A ganglion located near where the inferior mesenteric artery branches from the abdominal aorta[WP].

name: dorsal skin of toe
description: A dorsal skin of digit that is part of a pedal digit.

name: obsolete embryonic cilium
description: OBSOLETE: the earliest cilia of the mouse embryo found on the cells of the embryonic node

name: inner ear epithelium
description: the epithelial cell layer containing the sensory hair cells and their associated sensory nerve terminals

name: saccule duct
description: The saccular portion of the utriculosaccular duct that normally extends from the sacculus to the endolymphatic duct

name: mesonephric comma-shaped body
description: The mesonephric comma-shaped body is the precursor structure to the mesonephric S-shaped body that contributes to the morphogenesis of a nephron in the mesonephros[GO].

name: obsolete median fin skeleton
description: Postcranial axial skeleton that is unpaired and located on the sagittal plane of the organism.

name: obsolete median fin skeleton
description: Postcranial axial skeleton that is unpaired and located on the sagittal plane of the organism.

name: carpal skeleton
description: Subdivision of skeleton that consists of the endochondral elements distal to the anterior limb/fin zeugopodial skeletal elements which constitute the proximal region of the anterior autopod skeleton[PHENOSCAPE:ad].

name: prostate gland
description: The prostate gland is a partly muscular, partly glandular body that is situated near the base of the mammalian male urethra and secretes an alkaline viscid fluid which is a major constituent of the ejaculatory fluid.

name: thyrohyoid muscle
description: The thyrohyoid muscle is a small, quadrilateral muscle appearing like an upward continuation of the Sternothyreoideus. It belongs to the infrahyoid muscles group. It arises from the oblique line on the lamina of the thyroid cartilage, and is inserted into the lower border of the greater cornu of the hyoid bone. [WP,unvetted].

name: flexor surface
description: Surface of a long bone that possess the flexor muscle attachment sites.

name: spermaceti
description: wax present in the head cavities of the sperm whale.

name: M. coccygeocutaneus
description: Originates from the posterior tip of the urostyle and inserts on the cloacal musculature and the overlying skin.

name: tunicate postabdomen
description: Basalmost subdivision of a tunicate containing the heart and reproductive organs

name: segment of antenna
description: Any appendage segment that is part of some antenna.

name: pecten oculi
description: A comb-like structure of blood vessels belonging to the choroid in the eye of a bird or reptile. It is non-sensory and is a pigmented structure that projects into the vitreous body from the point where the optic nerve enters the eyeball. The pecten is believed to both nourish the retina and control the pH of the vitreous body.

name: upper outer quadrant of breast
description: The quarter of the breast which is superior and lateral.

name: pillar of the lateral semicircular canal
interdigital region between manual digits
description: An interdigital region that is part of a manus.

name: midbrain-hindbrain boundary
description: The part of the brain that is the morphological boundary between the midbrain and hindbrain and that is the location of an organizing center which patterns the midbrain and hindbrain primordia of the neural plate.

name: bilaminar disc
description: A flattened, almost circular bilaminar plate of cells formed when the inner cell mass (aka embryoblast) forms two epithelial layers, each of a distinct lineage, separated by an extracellular basement membrane: the external (dorsal) layer is called the epiblast and the internal (ventral) layer is called the hypoblast (aka primitive endoderm); together, they compose the bilaminar embryonic disc.

name: lymph vasculature
description: A network of blunt ended vessels lacking direct connection to the blood vascular system. These vessels collect and drain fluids and macromolecules from interstitial spaces throughout the animal. They derive from a subpopulation of endothelial cells and have walls that are much thinner than the blood carrying vessels. Lymphatic vessels are usually classified as either superficial or deep.

name: dentine
description: Collagen-rich odontogenic tissue characteristic of teeth and tooth-like skeletal elements (e.g., odontodes); mature dentine is mineralized and develops from predentine tissue; often (but not always) tubular and acellular.

name: parakeratinized epithelium of gingiva
description: A parakeratinized epithelium that is part of a gingiva.

name: posterior leaflet of mitral valve
description: Leaflet of mitral valve which is attached to the posterior head of the lateral papillary muscle of left ventricle through the chorda tendinea of the left ventricle.

name: extrinsic muscle of tongue
description: A muscle organ that attaches the tongue to some other structure.

name: compound organ
description: Anatomical structure that has as its parts two or more multi-tissue structures of at least two different types and which through specific morphogenetic processes forms a single distinct structural unit demarcated by bona fide boundaries from other distinct anatomical structures of different types.

name: distal interphalangeal joint of digit 4
description: A distal interphalangeal joint that is part of a digit 4.

name: lumen of vagina
description: A organ cavity that is part of a vagina.

name: deep brachial artery
description: The arteria profunda brachii (also known as deep artery of the arm and the deep brachial artery) is a large vessel which arises from the medial and back part of the brachial, just below the lower border of the Teres major. [WP,unvetted].

name: infratemporal fossa
description: The infratemporal fossa is an irregularly shaped cavity, situated below and medial to the zygomatic arch. Boundaries defined by: anteriorly, by the infratemporal surface of the maxilla and the ridge which descends from its zygomatic process posteriorly, by the articular tubercle of the temporal and the spinal angularis of the sphenoid superiorly, by the greater wing of the sphenoid below the infratemporal crest, and by the under surface of the temporal squama, containing the foramen ovale, which transmits the mandibular branch of the trigeminal nerve, and the foramen spinosum, which transmits the middle meningeal artery inferiorly, by the medial pterygoid muscle attaching to the mandible medially, by the lateral pterygoid plate laterally, by the ramus of mandible, which contains the mandibular foramen, leading to the mandibular canal through which the inferior alveolar nerve passes. This also contains the lingula, a triangular piece of bone that overlies the mandibular foramen antero-medially. Finally, the mylohyoid groove descends obliquely transmitting the mylohyoid nerve the only motor branch of the anterior division of the trigeminal nerve.

name: posterior segment of eyeball
description: any of the parts of the eye that lie in back of, or dorsal to, the lens (but not inclusive)

name: left coronary artery
description: Coronary artery which runs along the left side of the heart and predominantly supplies the mycocardium of the left side of the heart[Wikipedia,modified]

name: hoof
description: The tip of a toe of an ungulate mammal, strengthened by a thick horny (keratin) covering. The hoof consists of a hard or rubbery sole, and a hard wall formed by a thick nail rolled around the tip of the toe. The weight of the animal is normally borne by both the sole and the edge of the hoof wall. Hooves grow continuously, and are constantly worn down by use.

name: midbrain basal plate
description: Portion of tissue that is dorsolateral to the floor plate and part of the midbrain.

name: epural
description: A free, modified neural spine of a preural or a ural vertebra that is placed between the last developed neural spine of a preural centrum and the dorsal axis (= anterior margin of first uroneural) of the caudal skeleton . An epural commonly supports one or more dorsal procurrent rays. An epural is an unpaired median perichondrally ossified bone.

name: cartilaginous projection
description: Anatomical projection that is composed of cartilage tissue.

name: pedal digit plus metapodial segment
description: A subdivision of the autopod consisting of pedal digit plus the region incorporating a single metapodial element. These segments are typically repeated along the pre-axiom to post-axial axis.

name: dentary foramen
description: Foramen located on the dentary for passage of the mandibular nerve.

name: strand of guard hair
description: A long, straight truncal hair that contains two air cells in the medulla[MP]. A strand of hair from the top layer consisting of longer, often coarser, straight shafts of hair that stick out through the underfur. This is usually the visible layer for most mammals and contains most of the pigmentation.

name: exocrine pancreas
description: The part of the pancreas that is part of the exocrine system and which produces and store zymogens of digestive enzymes, such as chymotrypsinogen and trypsinogen in the acinar cells [GO].

name: mandibular process mesenchyme from neural crest
description: Mesenchyme that develops_from a neural crest and is part of a mandibular process mesenchyme.

name: outer mental barbel
description: Mental barbel that originates on the chin, in a posterolateral position relative to the inner mental barbel.

name: DEL
description: A multilayer of deep cells of fairly uniform thickness that forms during early epiboly (at dome stage; upon conversion of the blastodisc to the blastoderm); during gastrulation the DEL (deep cell layer) gives rise to the epiblast and hypoblast. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: intergluteal cleft
description: The line that divided the gluteal regions of the body.

name: axial skeletal system
description: Subdivision of the skeletal system which consists of the axial skeleton plus associated joints.

name: encapsulated tactile receptor
description: A tacile mechanoreceptor that lacks a capsule.

name: yellow fibrocartilage
description: fibrocartilage containing bundles of yellow elastic fibers but with little or no white fibrous tissue.

name: postcingulum of deciduous premolar 5
description: A postcingulum found on deciduous premolar 5

name: adult central nervous system
description: Central nervous system of the adult.

name: perineal body
description: The perineal body (or central tendon of perineum) is a pyramidal fibromuscular mass in the middle line of the perineum at the junction between the urogenital triangle and the anal triangle . It is found in both males and females. In males, it is found between the bulb of penis and the anus; in females, is found between the vagina and anus, and about 1.25 cm in front of the latter. The perineal body is essential for the integrity of the pelvic floor, particularly in females. Its rupture during delivery leads to widening of the gap between the anterior free borders of levator ani muscle of both sides, thus predisposing the woman to prolapse of the uterus, rectum, or even the urinary bladder.

name: Brodmann (1909) area 37
description: Brodmann area 37, or BA37, is part of the temporal cortex in the human brain. This area is known as occipitotemporal area 37 (H). It is a subdivision of the cytoarchitecturally defined temporal region of cerebral cortex. It is located primarily in the caudal portions of the fusiform gyrus and inferior temporal gyrus on the mediobasal and lateral surfaces at the caudal extreme of the temporal lobe. Cytoarchitecturally it is bounded caudally by the peristriate Brodmann area 19, rostrally by the inferior temporal area 20 and middle temporal area 21 and dorsally on the lateral aspect of the hemisphere by the angular area 39 (H) (Brodmann-1909).

name: retroperitoneal space
description: Anatomical space in the abdominal cavity behind (retro) the peritoneum. It has no specific delineating anatomical structures. Organs are retroperitoneal if they only have peritoneum on their anterior side.

name: liver right lobe parenchyma
description: A parenchyma that is part of a right lobe of liver [Automatically generated definition].

name: caudal fin radial element
description: Radial element that is part of the caudal fin.

name: mucosa of ethmoidal sinus
description: A mucosa that is part of a ethmoid sinus [Automatically generated definition].

name: ventral root of spinal cord
description: The ventral roots contain efferent motor axons. Similar to the dorsal roots, the ventral roots continue out from the spinal column, and meet and mix with their corresponding dorsal nerve root at a point after the ganglion.

name: venous blood vessel
description: A blood vessel that carries blood from the capillaries toward the heart

name: heart left ventricle
description: A cardiac ventricle that is in the left side of the heart.

name: margo orbitalis of maxilla
description: Dorsal margin of the maxilla between the frontal and zygomatico-maxillary processes.

name: neck connective tissue
description: A portion of connective tissue that is part of a neck [Automatically generated definition].

name: mitral valve
description: An atrioventricular valve that is part of the outflow part of the left atrium.

name: levator bulbi
description: One of the principal muscles used in swallowing.

name: aorta tunica intima
description: The innermost layer of the aorta, containing the endothelium and an inner elastic membrane.

name: gland of nasal mucosa
description: The nasal glands are the seromucous glands in the respiratory region of the nasal mucous membrane. The three major types of nasal glands are anterior serous glands, seromucous glands, and Bowman glands.

name: obsolete secondary oogonium
description: A type of germ cell that results from the mitotic division of a primary oogonium.

name: mesenchyme of handplate
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a handplate.

name: basibranchial copula
description: Pharyngeal arch cartilage that is ventral, median, and associated with more than one pharyngeal arch in the pharyngeal arch 3-7 skeleton.

name: proximal epiphysis of tibia
description: A proximal epiphysis that is part of a tibia.

name: keratinized stratified squamous epithelium
description: Keratinized stratified squamous epithelium is a stratified squamous epithelium, the cells of which synthesize and accumulate keratin.

name: sclerotome somite 3
description: Medial ventral region of the somite that will form vertebral cartilages. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: mentalis muscle
description: A muscle of facial expression, innervated by the facial nerve, attached to the skin of the lower lip and inferior to the lower lip (in humans this region is called the chin or mental region), the orbicularis oris muscle, and the mandible in the symphyseal region. See Diogo et al., 2009; Burrows et al., 2011)

name: parotid gland intralobular duct
description: Any of the tubular canals of the parotid gland located within the parenchymal (secretory) tissue i.e. within lobules; both intercalated and striated (secretory) ducts are intralobular ducts.

name: superior nasal meatus
description: The superior meatus, the smallest of the three meatuses of the nose, occupies the middle third of the lateral wall of the nasal cavity. It lies between the superior nasal conchC& and middle nasal conchC&; the sphenopalatine foramen opens into it behind, and the posterior ethmoidal cells in front. The sphenoidal sinus opens into a recess, the sphenoethmoidal recess, which is placed above and behind the superior concha.

name: postganglionic sympathetic fiber
description: A noradrenergic or adrenergic axonal fiber projecting from a sympathetic ganglion to an effector organ

name: neural tube derived brain
description: A brain that develops_from a neural tube.

name: caecum dorsal mesentery
description: A dorsal mesentery that is part of a caecum.

name: mesenchyme derived from trunk neural crest
description: Mesenchyme that develops_from a trunk neural crest.

name: skin muscle
description: Any muscle organ that is part of a skin of body [Automatically generated definition].

name: distal convoluted tubule
description: The first segment of the nephron lying just downstream from the loop of Henle, immediately after the macula densa.

name: swim bladder tunica externa
description: Multi-tissue structure that is the external layer of the swim bladder that is covered by the peritoneum, and made of elastic fibres and ichthyocol (short needles of collagen).

name: intermediate acoustic stria
description: White matter structure containing axons arising from cochlear nuclear complex (Brodal, Neurological Anatomy, 3rd ed, 1985, pg 609)

name: obsolete opercle bone
description: Dermal bone that forms the postero-dorsal part of the opercular series. The opercle articulates with the hyomandibula antero-dorsally and with the subopercle ventrally. The opercle is a paired bone.

name: interscapular fat pad
description: Encapsulated adipose tissue located between the scapulae.

name: pleurocentrum
description: The posteriormost of the two possible elements found in the tetrapod centrum (when the centrum is not a single element).

name: ventral nuclear group
description: Nuclei in the ventral part of the thalamus, involved in modulating activity of dorsal thalamic nuclei.

name: non-imbricate neural arch
description: Neural arches that do not overlap, thus exposing the spinal cord dorsally.

name: substantia gelatinosa of cervical spinal cord dorsal horn
description: A substantia gelatinosa that is part of a cervical spinal cord dorsal horn.

name: optic vesicle
description: The optic vesicle is the evagination of neurectoderm that precedes formation of the optic cup[GO]. Portion of tissue that is comprised of neuroepitheium which has pinched off from the anterior neural keel and will form the optic cup[ZFA].

name: seminiferous tubule of testis
description: The tubules in the testes where spermatogenesis occurs.

name: feathered facial disc
description: A collection of feathers arranged in a concave pattern surrounding the eyes in some birds, particularly owls.

name: wall of stomach
description: the layered structure that makes up the stomach, typiclly consists of a serous coat, a muscular coat, a mucous membrane, and other tissue layers in between

name: vestibulocochlear ganglion
description: the group of neuron cell bodies associated with the eighth cranial nerve during embryogenesis; splits in later development to form the cochlear and vestibular ganglia

name: sucking disc
description: Distinctive first dorsal fin taking the form of a modified oval sucker-like organ with slat-like structures that open and close to create suction and take a firm hold against the skin of larger marine animals.

name: pelvic sucking disc
description: An adhesive disk modified from the pelvic fins in, for example, clingfishes (Gobiesocidae), gobies (Gobiidae) and snailfishes (Liparidae).

name: epibranchial 3-pharyngobranchial 3 joint
description: Joint that articulates the epibranchial 3 cartilage or bone and pharyngobranchial 3 cartilage or bone. Epibranchial 3-pharyngobranchial 3 joint is paired.

name: condyle of humerus
description: The distal end of the humerus, including the trochlea, capitulum and the olecranon, coronoid and radial fossae

name: echolocation organ
description: Any organ that plays a role in the process of echolocation.

name: lateral ethmoid-ectopterygoid ligament
description: Lateral ethmoid-ectopterygoid ligament is a ligament that connects the lateral ethmoid to the ectopterygoid.

name: middle colic vein
description: The middle colic vein drains the transverse colon. It is a tributary of the superior mesenteric vein, and follows the path of its corresponding artery, the middle colic artery. [WP,unvetted].

name: pharyngobranchial 3 element
description: Pharyngobranchial element, located medial to the epibranchials and posteriorly adjacent to pharyngobranchial 2 element.

name: renal sinus of left kidney
description: A renal sinus that is part of a left kidney.

name: antorbital
description: Dermal bone positioned as the first bone of the infraorbital series. The antorbital articulates with the lacrimal or infraorbital 1 anteroventrally and the supraorbital posterodorsally. The antorbital is a paired bone.

name: intersomitic vein
description: The vein that sprouts from the posterior cardinal vein, growing dorsally between the somites, and then joining, and draining the dorsal longitudinal anastomosing vessel.

name: alveolar wall
description: A wall that contains the alveoli

name: proximal tarsal endochondral element
description: A proximal mesopodial endochondral element that is part of a hindlimb.

name: humerus pre-cartilage condensation
description: A humerus endochondral element that is composed primarily of a pre-cartilage condensation.

name: shoulder bone
description: A bone that is connected via a shoulder joint (i.e. glenohumeral or acromioclavicular joints). The shoulder bones are the clavicle, scapula and humerus - but note that these are only considered to be shoulder bones when a true shoulder is present, as in most tetrapods.

name: cerebral blood vessel
description: A blood vessel that is part of a cerebellum.

name: submucosa of neck of urinary bladder
description: A submucosa that is part of a neck of urinary bladder [Automatically generated definition].

name: diaphysis
description: Subdivision of long bone which forms the part of the bone between the two epiphyses, excluding the metaphyses[FMA,modified].

name: crypt of Lieberkuhn of large intestine
description: A crypt of lieberkuhn that is part of a large intestine [Automatically generated definition].

name: lung blood vessel
description: A blood vessel that is part of a lung [Automatically generated definition].

name: shell of nucleus accumbens
description: Crescent shaped outer zone of the nucleus accumbens, defined by a combination of chemoarchitecture and afferent and efferent connections. The shell is distinguished from the more centrally located core through the notable reduction in staining for the calcium-binding protein calbindin D28K, which is dense in the core and virtually absent in the shell.

name: serosa of duodenum
description: A serous membrane that is part of a duodenum [Automatically generated definition].

name: mandibular nerve
description: The motor and sensory nerve subdivision of the trigeminal nerve that transmits sensory information from the auricle, the external acoustic meatus, tympanic membrane, temporal region, the cheek, the skin overlying the mandible, the anterior portion of the tongue, the floor of the mouth, lower teeth and gingiva and transmits motor information from the muscles of mastication, the mylohyoid muscle and digastric muscle and the muscles tensor tympani and tensor veli palatini.

name: lung endothelium
description: A blood vessel endothelium that is part of a lung [Automatically generated definition].

name: neck of radius
description: The narrow part of the shaft of the radius just below the head.

name: cervical vertebra endochondral element
description: A vertebral endochondral element in the cervical region of the vertebral column.

name: extravillous trophoblast
description: The outermost layer of trophoblast, produced by cytotrophoblast where there is direct contact with maternal decidua rather than blood. The EVT cells travel into the decidua, reacting with NK cells and invading maternal blood vessels feeding the placenta, softening the walls and replacing the lining with fetal tissue, a process called conversion.

name: M. gracilis minor
description: Originates from the pelvic rim just ventral to the anus and merges with M. gracilis major. M. gracilis minor also attaches to the skin.

name: sacral vertebra cartilage element
description: A sacral vertebra endochondral element that is composed primarily of cartilage tissue.

name: thoracic thymus
description: A mature thymus that is entirely part of thoracic region.

name: distal cartilage of posterior process of basipterygium
description: Process that is cartilaginous and arises from the distal margin or tip of posterior process of basipterygium and projects posteriorly.

name: manual digit 5 metacarpus pre-cartilage condensation
description: A manual digit metacarpus pre-cartilage condensation that is part of a manual digit 5 mesenchyme.

name: incudostapedial joint
description: the small synovial joint connecting the inclus and the stapes, located between the lenticular process on the long crus of the incus and the head of the stapes.

name: quadrato-orbital commissure
description: Cartilage that bridges palatoquadrate muscular process to dorsal orbitonasal plate.

name: hypaxial region somite 14
description: Somite-derived body wall muscle present ventral to the horizontal myoseptum. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: lumbar splanchnic nerve
description: The lumbar splanchnic nerves are splanchnic nerves that arise from the lumbar part of the sympathetic trunk and travel to an adjacent plexus near the aorta. They are originated from L1 and L2. These nerves contain preganglionic sympathetic and visceral afferent fibers. The site of synapse is found in the prevertebral ganglia and innervate the smooth muscle and glands of the pelvic viscera and hindgut.

name: tendon of biceps brachii
description: A tendon that attaches_to a biceps brachii.

name: excreted gas
description: Any gaseous product of an excretory process.

name: fetal membrane
description: The amnion and chorion which surround and protect a developing fetus.

name: obsolete postcommissural nucleus of V central entopeduncular nucleus
uterine artery
description: the branch of the internal iliac artery that supplies the uterus and the upper part of the vagina

name: spongiotrophoblast layer
description: The structure of the outer structural layer of the rodent placenta[MP].

name: pinna surface epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a pinna.

name: utricle duct
description: The utricular portion of the utriculosaccular duct that normally extends from the utriculus to the endolymphatic duct

name: mammillary peduncle
description: White matter bundle in the posterior hypothalamus containing ascending afferent fibers to the mammillary bodies from the ventral and dorsal tegmental nuclei (Brodal, Neurological Anatomy, 3rd ed., 1981, pg 671).

name: mesonephric nephron tubule
description: A mesonephric nephron tubule is an epithelial tube that is part of the mesonephric nephron, the functional part of the mesonephros[GO].

name: endocrine gland
description: Endocrine glands are glands of the endocrine system that secrete their products directly into the circulatory system rather than through a duct.[WP, modified].

name: skeletal support for eminentia olfactoria
description: Elevation of the dorsal surface of the solum nasi medial to the fenestra endochoanalis that provides support for the eminentia olfactoria.

name: intercostal muscle
description: the respiratory muscles that arise from the lower border of one rib and insert into the upper border of the adjoining rib

name: respiratory muscle
description: Muscle that is part of the respiratory system.

name: paries nasi
description: Paired, elongate, ventrolaterally-orieted cartilaginous structures that extend to the premaxilla-maxilla articulation.

name: lateral tuber of ulna
description: Projection on the lateral side of proximal part of the ulna[PHENOSCAPE:ni].

name: skin gland
description: A gland that is part of a skin of body [Automatically generated definition].

name: spermaceti organ
description: An organ that contains spermaceti.

name: endolymphatic space
description: endolymph-filled space contained by the membranous labyrinth.

name: anterior chamber swim bladder
description: The anterior compartment of the swim bladder is thought to have acoustic resonance properties that play a key role in audition. It is connected to the posterior chamber via the dusctus communicans. Finney et al, 2006.

name: ramus buccal
description: Ventral ramus of the ADLLN that innervates the infraorbital line of neuromasts.

name: superficial part of temporalis
description: The superficial temporalis muscle is a separable part of the temporalis muscle that attaches to the temporalis fascia

name: occipital arch cartilage
description: Cranial cartilage which is a paired anterodorsal projection of the posterior end of the parachordal cartilage. It lies lateral to the notochord, just anterior to the posterior tip of the otic capsule. The bilaterally paired occipital arch cartilages fuse anterodorsally to the posterior edges of the auditory capsules and meet medially as the tectum synoticum (by 12 dpf).

name: comb and wattle
description: A wattle is a fleshy dewlap or caruncle hanging from various parts of the head or neck in several groups of birds, goats and other animals. In some birds the caruncle is erectile tissue.

name: vertebra lamina
description: two broad plates directed dorsomedially from the pedicles; these fuse at the dorsal midline, and complete the dorsal wall of the vertebral foramen

name: musculature of perineum
description: Any collection of muscles that is part of a perineum [Automatically generated definition].

name: interdigital region between pedal digits
description: An interdigital region that is part of a pes.

name: ventricular zone
description: Proliferative region that is part of the ventricular system.

name: corpus cavernosum penis
description: One of the columns of erectile tissue forming the dorsum and sides of the penis.

name: post-embryonic stage
description: stage succeeding embryo, including mature structure

name: blood vasculature
description: A vascular network consisting of blood vessels.

name: enamel
description: A dentine-like hypermineralized substance that covers the tooth tip. Enamel's primary mineral is hydroxylapatite, which is a crystalline calcium phosphate. Unlike dentin and bone, enamel does not contain collagen. Instead, it has two unique classes of proteins called amelogenins and enamelins[WP].

name: enameloid
description: Skeletal tissue that is hypermineralized and aprismatic and deposited by a combination of ameloblasts and odontoblasts that are excluded from the matrix. Enameloid develops from pre-enameloid tissue.

name: strand of wool
description: A strand of pelage hair that is crimped and grows in clusters

name: cysticercus stage
description: The larval form of any of the Taenia tapeworms.

name: intrinsic muscle of tongue
description: The intrinsic tongue muscles are an integral part of the tongue and completely contained within the tongue that are innervated by Cranial Nerve XII.

name: endomysium
description: A layer of connective tissue that ensheaths a muscle fiber and is composed mostly from reticular fibers. It also contains capillaries, nerves and lymphatics. The term cardiac skeleton is sometimes considered synonymous with endomysium, but sometimes it refers to the combination of the endomysium and perimysium.

name: jugal point
description: The jugal point is the point at the anterior end of the upper border of the zygomatic arch where the masseteric and maxillary edges meet at an angle.

name: epithelium of lens
description: A layer of epithelial cells that is part of the eye.

name: male paramesonephric duct
description: A epithelial tube that develops from a Mullerian duct in a male. Later degenerates.

name: orbital region
description: The subdivision of the face that includes the eye (eyeball plus adnexa such as eyelids) and the orbit of the skull and associated parts of the face such as the eyebrows, if present

name: intersomitic vessel
description: One of the primary blood vessel sprouts that originate from the dorsal aorta and posterior cardinal vein and align dorsoventrally at the myotomal boundaries between somites.

name: middle cerebral artery
description: The middle cerebral artery (MCA) is one of the three major paired arteries that supplies blood to the cerebrum. The MCA arises from the internal carotid and continues into the lateral sulcus where it then branches and projects to many parts of the lateral cerebral cortex. It also supplies blood to the anterior temporal lobes and the insular cortices. The left and right MCAs rise from trifurcations of the internal carotid arteries and thus are connected to the anterior cerebral arteries and the posterior communicating arteries, which connect to the posterior cerebral arteries. The MCAs are not considered a part of the Circle of Willis. [WP,unvetted].

name: abdominal ganglion
description: A ganglion that is part of a abdominal segment of trunk.

name: abdominal ganglion of visceral hump
description: An unpaired knot of nerves in The visceral sacs that innervates the pallial organs as well as the inner organs.

name: midbrain neural tube
description: Portion of neural tube that gives rise to the midbrain.

name: ascending limb of ceratobranchial 5 bone
description: Process that is the dorsally directed portion of ceratobranchial 5 bone.

name: strand of zigzag hair
description: A truncal hair that has two or more sharp bends with diameter constrictions at the bends, and contain one air cell in the medulla.

name: compound eye
description: A light sensing organ composed of ommatidia

name: mandibular process mesenchyme from head mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that develops_from a head mesenchyme from mesoderm and is part of a mandibular process mesenchyme.

name: inner mental barbel
description: Mental barbel that originates on the chin, in an anteromedial position relative to the outer mental barbel. The inner mental barbel is nearer to the mandibular symphysis than is the outer mental barbel.

name: internal yolk syncytial layer
description: The portion of the YSL that lies deep to the blastoderm during epiboly. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: gluteal sulcus
description: A horizontal crease formed by the inferior aspect of the buttocks and the posterior upper leg.

name: hepatic duct
description: Any portion of the ducts that carry bile from the liver to the common bile duct. This may include both intrahapetic components (parts of left and right hepatic ducts) and extrahapetic components (common hepatic duct, plus hilar portion).

name: cranial neuron projection bundle
description: Any of the cranial nerves, or their central nervous system analogs (the optic tract, the epiphyseal tract). These analogs are not true nerves, and are instead evaginated sensory afferents emanating from the brain

name: posthypocrista of deciduous premolar 5
description: A posthypocrista found on deciduous premolar 5

name: adult brain
description: Brain of the adult.

name: septum of scrotum
description: an incomplete wall of connective tissue and nonstriated muscle (dartos fascia) dividing the scrotum into two sacs, each containing a testis.

name: longus colli muscle
description: The Longus colli muscle is a muscle of the human body. The Longus colli is situated on the anterior surface of the vertebral column, between the atlas and the third thoracic vertebra. It is broad in the middle, narrow and pointed at either end, and consists of three portions, a superior oblique, an inferior oblique, and a vertical. The superior oblique portion arises from the anterior tubercles of the transverse processes of the third, fourth, and fifth cervical vertebr√¶ and, ascending obliquely with a medial inclination, is inserted by a narrow tendon into the tubercle on the anterior arch of the atlas. The inferior oblique portion, the smallest part of the muscle, arises from the front of the bodies of the first two or three thoracic vertebr√¶; and, ascending obliquely in a lateral direction, is inserted into the anterior tubercles of the transverse processes of the fifth and sixth cervical vertebr√¶. The vertical portion arises, below, from the front of the bodies of the upper three thoracic and lower three cervical vertebr√¶, and is inserted into the front of the bodies of the second, third, and fourth cervical vertebr√¶. [WP,unvetted].

name: distal mesopodial endochondral element
description: An endochondral element in the distal portion of the mesopodial skeleton, between the central mesopodial skeleton and the metapodial skeleton

name: atlanto-axial joint
description: The Atlanto-axial joint is of a complicated nature, comprising no fewer than four distinct joints. There is a pivot articulation between the odontoid process of the axis and the ring formed by the anterior arch and the transverse ligament of the atlas.

name: liver left lobe parenchyma
description: A parenchyma that is part of a left lobe of liver [Automatically generated definition].

name: ilioischiadic foramen
description: Situated just caudal to the acetabulum, the foramen is bound dorsally by the illium and ventrally by the ischium. The foramen transmitts the ischiadic nerves and vessels (Baumel et al. 1993)

name: mucosa of hard palate
description: A mucosa that is part of a hard palate [Automatically generated definition].

name: dorsal root of spinal cord
description: The dorsal roots contain afferent sensory axons. The dorsal roots of each side continue outwards, along the way forming a dorsal root ganglion (also called a spinal ganglion).

name: pancreas primordium
description: embryonic structure that develops into pancreatic bud.

name: interatrial septum
description: A cardiac septum that divides the left and right atria of the heart.

name: margo orbitalis of pterygoid
description: Margin that connects the anterior and medial rami of the pterygoid.

name: obsolete pharyngeal nerve
description: OBSOLETE. Original definition: The pharyngeal nerve (pterygopalatine nerve) is a small branch arising from the posterior part of the pterygopalatine ganglion. It passes through the pharyngeal canal with the pharyngeal branch of the maxillary artery, and is distributed to the mucous membrane of the nasal part of the pharynx, behind the auditory tube. [WP,unvetted].

name: perineural vascular plexus
description: The capillary bed that initially surrounds the relative avascular brain and spinal cord; the perineural vascular plexus (PNVP) is the precursor to the blood brain barrier formed by angioblasts which migrate away from somites and is recruited to surround the neural tube in response to VEGF; vascularization of the brain and spinal cord occurs via angiogenesis as sprouting vessels from the PNVP invade the neuroepithelium and grow inward toward the ventricular lumen[MP].

name: obsolete subparabrachial nucleus
description: A cell group located ventral to the brachium conjunctivum in the general area where the medial and lateral parabrachial nuclei abut, shifting to the slightly more lateral position rostrally.

name: leg connective tissue
description: A portion of connective tissue that is part of a leg [Automatically generated definition].

name: efferent lymphatic vessel
description: Lymphatic vessel that exits the lymph node. The efferent lymphatic vessel commences from the lymph sinuses of the medullary portion of the lymph nodes and leave the lymph nodes either to veins or greater nodes. Efferent lymphatic vessels are also found in the thymus and spleen. This is in contrast to afferent lymphatic vessels, which are found only in lymph nodes.

name: hilus of dentate gyrus
description: Layer of the dentate gyrus lying deep to the granule cell layer, within the opening of the C or V formed by the granule cell layer characterized by loosely packed polymorphic cells

name: parapodium
description: either of a pair of fleshy lateral processes borne by most segments of a polychaete worm.

name: vertebral element 4
description: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 5.

name: ramules nasalis lateralis
description: First branch gives rise to two ramules that border the naris and innervate the surrounding tissue.

name: obsolete regional part of peripheral nervous system
epididymis epithelium
description: the layer of secretory cells which lines the epididymis

name: anterior copula
description: Copula that is ventral, median, and associated with pharyngeal arches 3-5.

name: sclerotome somite 5
description: Medial ventral region of the somite that will form vertebral cartilages. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: depressor anguli oris muscle
description: The Depressor anguli oris (Triangularis) arises from the oblique line of the mandible, whence its fibers converge, to be inserted, by a narrow fasciculus, into the angle of the mouth.

name: parotid gland intercalated duct
description: Any of the small intralobular tubular canal that leads directly from the serous acinus of the parotid gland to a striated (secretory) duct; in mouse, the intercalated ducts are short and narrow and are lined by low cuboidal epithelial cells with large central nuclei; they secrete bicarbonate ion into and absorb chloride ion from the acinar product.

name: distal radio-ulnar joint
description: The Distal Radioulnar Articulation (inferior radioulnar joint) is a pivot-joint formed between the head of the ulna and the ulnar notch on the distal radius.

name: radio-ulnar joint
description: A joint that connects the radius and the ulna. Examples: proximal and distal radio-ulnar joints

name: duct of epididymis
description: Any duct branching of of the main epididymis duct.

name: cartilaginous condensation
description: Cell condensation that is an aggregation of mesenchymal cells that are committed to differentiate into chondroblasts and chondrocytes.

name: orbitosphenoid cartilage element
description: A orbitosphenoid endochondral element that is composed primarily of cartilage tissue.

name: trabecula cranii
description: Paired thin medially aligned bar of cartilage that extends from the anterior end of the chondrocranium to just anterior to the anterior end of the notochord. The posterior ends of the trabeculae cranii are continuous with the parachordal cartilages, and they enclose the hypophyseal fenestra.

name: proximal epiphysis of fourth metatarsal bone
description: A proximal epiphysis that is part of a metatarsal bone of digit 4 [Automatically generated definition].

name: forelimb zeugopod muscle
description: Any muscle organ that is part of a forelimb zeugopod (lower arm)[Automatically generated definition].

name: cerebellum vermis lobule IX
description: The uvula (uvular lobe) forms a considerable portion of the inferior vermis; it is separated on either side from the tonsil by the sulcus valleculC&, at the bottom of which it is connected to the tonsil by a ridge of gray matter, indented on its surface by shallow furrows, and hence called the furrowed band.

name: outer medulla of kidney
description: The renal outer medulla is the region of the kidney that lies between the renal cortex and the renal inner medulla[GO].

name: swim bladder tunica interna
description: Multi-tissue structure that is the internal layer of the swim bladder and is comprised of thin endoderm and a smooth muscle layer called the muscularis mucosa with longitudinal and circular fibres with some collagen.

name: lateral lemniscus
description: A fiber bundle that runs through the medulla, pons and midbrain that arises in the cochlear nucleus and projects to various brainstem nuclei and ultimately the contralateral inferior colliculus of the midbrain. The brainstem nuclei include the superior olive, the medial nucleus of the trapezoid body, and the dorsal nucleus of the lateral lemniscus. Fibers leaving these brainstem nuclei ascending to the inferior colliculus rejoin the lateral lemniscus. In that sense, this is not a 'lemniscus' in the true sense of the word (second order, decussated sensory axons), as there is third (and out of the lateral superior olive, fourth) order information coming out of some of these brainstem nuclei. Adapted from Wikipedia.org (MM).

name: lateral process of malleus
description: A short projection from the base of the manubrium of the malleus, attached firmly to the drum membrane.

name: atlas intercentrum
description: The intercentrum unit of the atlas vertebra.

name: rostral ossicle
description: Ossicle that surrounds the sensory canals of the snout when passing from the ethmoidal commissure to the infraorbital series and have first been noticed by Nybelin [14] in Elops. From: Filleul and Lavou√©. (2001). Basal teleosts and the question of elopomorph monophyly. Morphological and molecular approaches. Comptes rendus de l'Acad√©mie des sciences. S√©rie III, Sciences de la vie. 324. 393-9. 10.1016/S0764-4469(00)01302-0.

name: systemic vein
description: Any vein within the general circulation that transports blood back to the right atrium of the heart.

name: spinotrapezius muscle
description: Spinotrapezius, also called thoracic trapezius, is the most posterior of the three trapezius muscles. It is triangular shaped. Posterior to the acromiotrapezius and overlaps latissimus dorsi on the front. Its origin is the neural spines of the thoracic vertebrae and its insertion is the scapular fascia. Its action is to draw the scapula to the dorsal and caudal regions.

name: pronator teres
description: The pronator teres is a muscle of the human body (located mainly in the forearm) that, along with the pronator quadratus, serves to pronate the forearm (turning it so the palm faces posteriorly). [WP,unvetted].

name: presacral shield
description: Dorsal, dermal plate of bone that overlies the presacral vertebrae. Such shield usually has irregular, sculptured surfaces, frequently is broadly expanded, and may be composed of several separate plates.

name: growth plate cartilage
description: cartilage that will provide a scaffold for mineralization of endochondral bones as they elongate or grow.

name: epithelium of vagina
description: The epithelial layer of the vagina.

name: obsolete predominantly gray regional part of anterior nuclear group
feathered ear tuft
description: A collection of feathers found on the heads of some owls.

name: wall of small intestine
description: An anatomical wall that is part of a small intestine [Automatically generated definition].

name: ventral cochlear nucleus
description: The ventral cochlear nucleus (or anterior, or accessory), placed between the two divisions of the cochlear nerve, is on the ventral aspect of the inferior peduncle. Composed of several regions of distinct cell types, this nucleus serves primarily as a relay station for ascending auditory information. Bushy cells in the anterior ventral cochlear nucleus (AVCN), which receive end bulbs of held from auditory nerve fibers, project to the superior olivary complex through the trapezoid body and intermediate acoustic stria. Other cell types project to the lateral lemniscus and the inferior colliculus directly. [WP,unvetted].

name: eyeball of camera-type eye
description: The core globe-shaped component of the camera-type eye.

name: epibranchial 3-pharyngobranchial 4 joint
description: Joint that articulates the epibranchial 3 cartilage or bone and pharyngobranchial 4 cartilage or bone. Epibranchial 3-pharyngobranchial 4 joint is paired.

name: condyle of tibia
description: One of the lateral or medial condyles of the tibia.

name: malleus cartilage element
description: A malleus endochondral element that is composed primarily of cartilage tissue.

name: bony shelf above orbit
description: The bony shelf above orbit is an anatomical cluster formed by the dorsolateral portions of the lateral ethmoid, frontal and sphenotic bones that forms the dorsal margin of the orbit.

name: ileocolic vein
description: The ileocolic vein is a vein which drains the ileum, colon, and cecum. [WP,unvetted].

name: pharyngobranchial 4 element
description: Most posterior pharyngobranchial element, located medial to the epibranchials.

name: coracoid foramen
description: Foramen that is located in the coracoid.

name: mesonephric sinus
description: A renal sinus that is part of a mesonephros.

name: alveolar smooth muscle
description: Alveolar smooth muscle is a type of non-striated muscle, found within the walls of the alveolus

name: proximal tarsal cartilage
description: A proximal tarsal endochondral element that is composed primarily of cartilage tissue.

name: iliac pre-cartilage condensation
description: A iliac endochondral element that is composed primarily of a pre-cartilage condensation.

name: pit
description: An roughly circular indentation in a surface.

name: submucosa of ileum
description: A submucosa that is part of a ileum [Automatically generated definition].

name: braincase and auditory apparatus
description: The part of the skull that encloses the brain and surrounds the inner ear.

name: corneal endothelium
description: A monolayer of specialized, flattened, mitochondria-rich cells that lines the posterior surface of the cornea and faces the anterior chamber of the eye[WP].

name: trunk blood vessel
description: A blood vessel that is part of a trunk [Automatically generated definition].

name: stomach primordium
description: A primordium that has the potential to develop into a stomach.

name: serosa of jejunum
description: A serous membrane that is part of a jejunum [Automatically generated definition].

name: dulla
description: A diverticulum on the lingual aspect of the soft palate of male dromedaries which may be inflated with air and be extruded from the oral cavity during rut.

name: hyale
description: Anterior-lateral projections from the corpus of the hyoid apparatus.

name: epidermal placode
description: Portion of tissue that is a thickening and reshaping of the epidermal basal stratum cells beneath which fibroblasts accumulate to form the scale primordium.

name: mesenchyme of tarsal region
description: Mesenchyme of the carpal region that contributes to the tarsal skeleton.

name: thoracic vertebra endochondral element
description: A vertebral endochondral element in the thoracic region of the vertebral column.

name: obsolete regional part of inferior frontal gyrus
hypaxial region somite 15
description: Somite-derived body wall muscle present ventral to the horizontal myoseptum. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: iliac spine
description: A bone spine that is part of a ilium.

name: M. semimembranosus
description: Originates on the ventro-lateral surface of the ischium below the anus and inserts on the ventro-medial aspect of the femur and the head of the tibiofibula by a stout tendon, which is formed by the ventral origin of the plantaris longus.
