name: superior cerebral vein
description: The Superior Cerebral Veins, eight to twelve in number, drain the superior, lateral, and medial surfaces of the hemispheres, and are mainly lodged in the sulci between the gyri, but some run across the gyri. They open into the superior sagittal sinus; the anterior veins runs nearly at right angles to the sinus; the posterior and larger veins are directed obliquely forward and open into the sinus in a direction more or less opposed to the current of the blood contained within it.

name: iliac blade
description: The extension of the ilium above the level of the acetabulum. Attachment site for both hindlimb and caudal musculature. Medially is the site of attachment of the sacral ribs, where these exist[PHENOSCAPE:ad].

name: thymoid
description: A thymus-like lympho-epithelial structures, in the tips of the gill filaments and the neighbouring secondary lamellae (both within the gill basket) of lamprey larvae.

name: incudomallear joint
description: the saddle-shaped synovial joint connecting the incus and the malleus.

name: rhombomere 5 lateral wall
description: A rhombomere lateral wall that is part of a rhombomere 5.

name: hypaxial region somite 17
description: Somite-derived body wall muscle present ventral to the horizontal myoseptum. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: sacral splanchnic nerve
description: A splanchnic nerve that connects the inferior hypogastric plexus to the sympathetic trunk in the pelvis.

name: gas excreted from digestive tract
description: Any excreted gas that is produced by the digestive tract.

name: extraembryonic membrane
description: Intrinsic membrane that arises from embryonic germ layers and grow to surround the developing embryo.

name: interventricular groove
description: Either of the anterior and posterior grooves on the surface of the heart that lie over the interventricular septum and join at the apex.

name: anterior ascending limb of lateral sulcus
nail bed of toe
description: A nail bed that is part of a pedal digit.

name: papillary muscle of heart
description: one of the group of myocardial bundles which terminate in the chordae tendineae that attach to the cusps of the atrioventricular valves; each ventricle has an anterior and a posterior papillary muscle; the right ventricle sometimes has a septal papillary muscle

name: germinal neuroepithelium
description: The single layer of epithelial cells that lines the early neural tube and develops into the nervous system and into the neural crest cells

name: prepollical element
description: Is a endochondral element that is part of the mesopodial skeleton and is contained within the prepollex which in some taxa appears as a pre-axial digit-like projection anterior to the first digit of the hand.

name: lateral sulcus
description: A sulcus that divides the frontal lobe and parietal lobe above from the temporal lobe below. It is in both hemispheres of the brain but is longer in the left hemisphere. The lateral sulcus is one of the earliest-developing sulci of the human brain. It first appears around the fourteenth gestational week[WP,modified].

name: female external urethral sphincter
description: The external sphincter muscle of female urethra is a muscle which controls urination.

name: anal column
description: One of a number of vertical folds, produced by an infolding of the mucous membrane and some of the muscular tissue in the upper half of the lumen of the anal canal[WP]

name: adrenal gland
description: Either of a pair of complex endocrine organs near the anterior medial border of the kidney consisting of a mesodermal cortex that produces glucocorticoid, mineralocorticoid, and androgenic hormones and an ectodermal medulla that produces epinephrine and norepinephrine[BTO].

name: latissimus dorsi muscle
description: The latissimus dorsi is the larger, flat, dorso-lateral muscle on the trunk, posterior to the arm, and partly covered by the trapezius on its median dorsal region. [WP,unvetted].

name: inner digits of foot
description: The medial most digits of the pes.

name: Eimer's organ
description: A sensory organ in which the epidermis is modified to form bulbous papillae. The organs are formed from a stack of epidermal cells, which is innervated by nerve processes from myelinated fibers in the dermis, which form terminal swellings just below the outer keratinized layer of epidermis. They contain a Merkel cell-neurite complex in the epidermis and a lamellated corpuscle in the dermal connective tissue.

name: supratemporal sensory canal
description: Sensory canal that crosses over the dorsal midline and in close proximity to the contralateral post-otic sensory canals. The supratemporal sensory canal is unpaired.

name: ambergris
description: A biliary secretion of the intestines of the sperm whale.

name: angular bone
description: Dermal bone that is located posterior to the dentary and lateral to the articular and retroarticular bones of the lower jaw. The angular forms the outer dermal sheet of the posterior part of the lower jaw. The angular bears a portion of the mandibular sensory canal. The angular is a paired bone.

name: obsolete predominantly gray regional part of intermediate hypothalamic region
posterior chamber swim bladder
description: The posterior compartment of the swim bladder plays a key role in buoyancy control. It is connected to the anterior chamber via the dusctus communicans. Finney et al, 2006.

name: deep part of temporalis
description: The deep temporalis muscle is a separable part of the temporalis muscle that that attaches to the bony wall of the braincase and is deep to the superficial temporalis.

name: migrating epithelium
description: An epithelium that extends its surface area by peripheral movement.

name: taenia marginalis anterior
description: Cartilage bar (bilaterally paired) that grows anteroventrally from the epiphyseal bar to join the anterolatera1 edge of the ethmoid plate.

name: supraclavicular lymph node
description: A lymph node which is located above the clavicle.

name: palmar digital vein
description: The palmar digital veins (or volar digital veins) on each finger are connected to the dorsal digital veins by oblique intercapitular veins. Some sources distinguish between the 'proper palmar digital veins', which are more distal, and the 'common palmar digital veins', which are more proximal.

name: proatlas
description: A small, paired bony element (more rarely, having fused parts) located between the skull and the atlas in tuataras, crocodiles, chameleons, and many fossil reptiles; it is uncommon in turtles and mammals (hedgehog). The proatlas apparently develops from the ossified neural part of the sclerotome. Externally it resembles the neural arch of the vertebra, since it articulates anteriorly with the lateral occipital bone and posteriorly with the anterior articular process of the atlas.

name: aorta wall
description: An anatomical wall that is part of an aorta, enclosing the luminal space.

name: musculature of forelimb zeugopod
description: Any collection of muscles that is part of a lower arm [Automatically generated definition].

name: epithelium of male urethra
description: A epithelium that is part of a male urethra.

name: webbed interdigital region
description: A membranous region of skin between the digits.

name: epithelium of carpal region
description: An epithelium that is part of a wrist [Automatically generated definition].

name: roof plate
description: A single row of glia at the dorsal midline of the developing neural tube along the entire anterior-posterior axis. This region provides inductive signals for the specification of neuronal cell types and of the specification of neural crest cells. The cells comprising the roof plate are the precursors to radial glial cells.

name: septum pellucidum
description: A triangular double membrane, consisting of glial cells and fibers (Heimer, 1996) separating the anterior horns of the lateral ventricles of the brain. It is situated in the median plane and bounded by the corpus callosum and the body and columns of the fornix.

name: left kidney
description: A kidney that is part of a left side of organism [Automatically generated definition].

name: cementum
description: Odontoid tissue that is deposited by cementoblasts onto dentine tissue and functions to attach teeth, odontodes and other odontogenic derivatives to bone tissue and the integument.

name: facial muscle
description: A muscle innervated by a facial nerve.

name: intervessel commissure
description: Vessels that travel between artery and veins or vein and vein in a single ray.

name: lateral accessory nucleus of optic tract
dorsal lateral plate region
description: Region located near the pronephros and pronephric ducts that is a site of hematopoiesis in the embryo.

name: duodenal mucosa
description: A mucosa that is part of a duodenum [Automatically generated definition].

name: smooth muscle endomysium
description: Reticular tissue which surrounds a smooth muscle cell.

name: posterior fontanelle
description: A gap between bones in the skull at the junction of the sagittal suture and lambdoidal suture.

name: anatomical point connecting sagittal and lambdoidal sutures
description: The occipital angle is rounded and corresponds with the point of meeting of the sagittal and lambdoidal sutures-a point which is termed the lambda (after the Greek letter of the same name); in the fetus this part of the skull is membranous, and is called the posterior fontanelle.

name: trochlea of humerus
description: The medial portion of the articular surface of the humerus is named the trochlea, and presents a deep depression between two well-marked borders; it is convex from before backward, concave from side to side, and occupies the anterior, lower, and posterior parts of the extremity. It is directly inferior to the most prominent anterior humeral fossia, the Coronoid fossia. It articulates with the ulna.

name: capsule of lens
description: the elastic, clear, membrane-like structure, that is outer most layer of the lens

name: paradidymis
description: A small collection of convoluted tubules, situated in front of the lower part of the cord above the head of the epididymis. These tubes are lined with columnar ciliated epithelium, and probably represent the remains of a part of the Wolffian body but are functionless and vestigial. The Wolffian body operates as a kidney (metanephros) in fishes and amphibians, but the corresponding tissue is co-opted to form parts of the male reproductive system in other classes of vertebrate. The paradidymis represents a remnant of an unused, atrophied part of the Wolffian body[WP,modified].

name: posterior communicating artery
description: One of a pair of right-sided and left-sided blood vessels in the circle of Willis. It connects the three cerebral arteries of the same side. Anteriorly, it is one portion of the terminal trifurcation of the internal carotid artery. The anterior cerebral artery and the middle cerebral artery are the other two branches of the trifurcation. Posteriorly, it communicates with the posterior cerebral artery.

name: CA1 stratum radiatum
description: Part of stratum radiatum lying in area CA1, superficial to the CA1 pyramidal cell layer and deep to the CA1 stratum lucidum-moleculare, continuous with the stratum radiatum of CA2 and bounded by the subiculum. It contains the Schaffer collateral projection from CA3.

name: ascending limb of ceratobranchial 5 cartilage
description: Process that is the dorsally directed portion of ceratobranchial 5 cartilage.

name: strand of duvet hair
description: A strand of hair from the fine underhair of the coat

name: camera-type eye
description: An organ of sight that includes the camera-type eyeball and supporting structures such as the lacrimal apparatus, the conjunctiva, the eyelid.

name: 1st arch maxillary mesenchyme from head mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that develops_from a head mesenchyme from mesoderm and is part of a 1st arch maxillary mesenchyme.

name: abdomen element
description: An organ or element that is in the abdomen. Examples: spleen, intestine, kidney, abdominal mammary gland.

name: epiphyseal tract
description: A cranial nerve fiber tract that innervates the parietal eye.

name: lumen of open tracheal system trachea
description: An anatomical space that surrounded_by a open tracheal system trachea.

name: egg tooth
description: A protuberence or true tooth that is used during hatching to break the eggshell.

name: deep dorsal vein of penis
description: The deep dorsal vein of the penis lies beneath the deep fascia of the penis; it receives the blood from the glans penis and corpora cavernosa penis and courses backward in the middle line between the dorsal arteries; near the root of the penis it passes between the two parts of the suspensory ligament and then through an aperture between the arcuate pubic ligament and the transverse ligament of the pelvis, and divides into two branches, which enter the pudendal plexus. The deep vein also communicates below the symphysis pubis with the internal pudendal vein.

name: metacarpophalangeal joint
description: The metacarpophalangeal joints (MCP) are of the condyloid kind, formed by the reception of the rounded heads of the metacarpal bones into shallow cavities on the proximal ends of the first phalanges, with the exception of that of the thumb, which presents more of the characters of a ginglymoid joint. Arthritis of the MCP is a distinguishing feature of Rheumatoid Arthritis, as opposed to the distal interphalangeal joint in osteoarthritis. [WP,unvetted].

name: pancreas body parenchyma
description: A parenchyma that is part of a body of pancreas [Automatically generated definition].

name: mucosa of vocal fold
description: A mucosa that is part of a vocal cord [Automatically generated definition].

name: celiac ganglion
description: The celiac ganglia are two large irregularly shaped masses of nerve tissue in the upper abdomen. Part of the sympathetic subdivision of the autonomic nervous system (ANS), the two celiac ganglia are the largest ganglia in the ANS, and they innervate most of the digestive tract. They have the appearance of lymph glands and are placed on either side of the midline in front of the crura of the diaphragm, close to the suprarenal glands (also called adrenal glands). The ganglion on the right side is placed behind the inferior vena cava. They are sometimes referred to as the semilunar ganglia or the solar ganglia. [WP,unvetted].

name: pancreatic epithelial bud
description: The embryonic pancreas develops from two separate anlagen in the foregut epithelium, one dorsal and two ventral pancreatic buds[PMID].

name: sinoatrial valve
description: A valve at the opening of the sinus venosus into the primordial atrium[TFD,modified]

name: margo orbitalis of squamosal
description: Anterior margin of the squamosal that takes part in the formation of the orbit.

name: thoracic ganglion
description: The thoracic ganglia are paravertebral ganglia. The thoracic portion of the sympathetic trunk typically has 12 thoracic ganglia. Emerging from the ganglia are thoracic splancic nerves (the cardiopulmonary, the greater, lesser, and least splanchic nerves) that help provide sympathetic innervation to abdominal structures. Also, the ganglia of the thoracic sympathetic trunk have both white and gray rami communicantes. The white rami carry sympathetic fibers arising in the spinal cord into the sympathetic trunk. [WP,unvetted].

name: hippocampus pyramidal layer
description: A cytoarchitectural term denoting the layer of the hippocampus in which pyramidal cells are predominant. Its location is superficial to the Stratum oriens; it is deep to the Stratum radiatum in area CA1 and area CA2 and deep to the Stratum lucidum in area CA3 (Stephan-75) (NeuroNames).

name: cortical arch of kidney
description: The portions of renal substance (cortex) intervening between the bases of the pyramids and the capsule of the kidney.

name: aortic valve
description: Cardiac valve which has as its parts the anterior, right posterior and left posterior cusps, attached to the fibrous ring of aortic valve.[FMA]

name: Merkel nerve ending
description: mechanoreceptors found in the skin and mucosa of vertebrates that provide touch information to the brain. The information they provide are those regarding pressure and texture. Each ending consists of a Merkel cell in close apposition with an enlarged nerve terminal

name: os suspensorium
description: Endochondral bone and Weberian ossicle that is an element of the fourth vertebra that curves ventrally around the anterior head of the swim bladder.

name: ramus nasalis medialis
description: First branch gives rise to two ramules that border the naris and innervate the surrounding tissue.

name: presumptive rhombomere 3
description: A presumptive structure that has the potential to develop into a rhombomere 3.

name: posterior copula
description: Copula that is ventral, median, and associated with branchial arches 4 and 5 (pharyngeal arches 6-7).

name: levator mandibulae longus
description: Responsible for the closing of the jaw.

name: frontoparietal fontanelle
description: Dorsal opening of the neurocranium.

name: sclerotome somite 8
description: Medial ventral region of the somite that will form vertebral cartilages. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: risorius muscle
description: Facial muscle that attaches to the fascia of the masseter muscle and the facia of the skin in the region of the corner (angle) of the mouth. Even in species in which this muscle is present, it is highly variable. A true risorius muscle may only be present in Hominins (humans and great apes). See Diogo 2008; Diogo et al., 2009; Burrows et al.., 2011., also DuBrul, 1980.

name: keratin-based scale
description: Fold or elevation of the epidermis rich in keratin proteins; possibly calcified but does not contain skeletal elements.

name: parotid gland striated duct
description: Any of the intralobular secretory duct of the parotid gland which connects an intercalated duct to an interlobular excretory duct; striated ducts are lined by cuboidal to columnar acidophilic cells and are so-named because of characteristic striations in the basal portions of the cells which are due to the alignment of mitochondria between deep infoldings of the basal cell membrane; the nucleus is in the central part of the cell above the striations; as they approach the excretory ducts, their diameter may exceed that of the acini; striated ducts reabsorb sodium and secrete potassium.

name: proximal radio-ulnar joint
description: The proximal radioulnar articulation (superior radioulnar joint) is a trochoid or pivot joint between the circumference of the head of the radius and the ring formed by the radial notch of the ulna and the annular ligament.

name: proximal epiphysis
description: An epiphysis that is on the proximal side of the bone.

name: foramina of scarpa
description: In the maxilla, occasionally two additional canals are present in the middle line of the palatine process; they are termed the foramina of Scarpa, and when present transmit the nasopalatine nerves, the left passing through the anterior, and the right through the posterior canal.

name: dorso-rostral cluster
description: Early-forming telencephalic neural cluster. Neurons of the dorso-rostral cluster (drc) extend axons to form the supra-optic tract (SOT) and the anterior commissure (AC). Ross et al., 1992.

name: lens vesicle cavity
description: An anatomical cavity that is part of a lens vesicle.

name: proximal epiphysis of fifth metatarsal bone
description: A proximal epiphysis that is part of a metatarsal bone of digit 5 [Automatically generated definition].

name: claustrum element
description: Postcranial axial skeletal element and Weberian ossicle that is located dorsal to the scaphium. The claustrum skeletal element is bilaterally paired.

name: forelimb stylopod muscle
description: Any muscle organ that is part of a forelimb stylopod (upper arm)[Automatically generated definition].

name: glenohumeral joint
description: The glenohumeral joint, commonly known as the shoulder joint, is a multiaxial synovial ball and socket joint and involves articulation between the glenoid fossa of the scapula (shoulder blade) and the head of the humerus (upper arm bone). [WP,unvetted].

name: inner medulla of kidney
description: Innermost region of the mammalian kidney.

name: dorsal hypothalamic area
description: A relatively small region of the hypothalamus located inferior to the hypothalamic sulcus.

name: anterior humeral ridge
description: Ridge or keel at the proximal end of the humerus. (see Laurin 1998)

name: ethmoid commissure
description: Sensory canal that traverses the rostral bone.

name: capillary bed
description: A localized group of blood capillaries.

name: nuchal line attachment site
description: Any of the four curved lines on the external surface of the occipital bone that serves as an attachment site for a muscle.

name: flexor carpi radialis muscle
description: A muscle of the forearm that acts to flex and abduct the manus. [WP,unvetted].

name: cartilago paraglenoidalis
description: Strip of cartilage that separates the coracoid from the scapula.

name: wall of large intestine
description: An anatomical wall that is part of a large intestine [Automatically generated definition].

name: dorsal cochlear nucleus
description: The dorsal cochlear nucleus (DCN, also known as the 'tuberculum acousticum'), is a cortex-like structure on the dorso-lateral surface of the brainstem. Along with the ventral cochlear nucleus, it forms the cochlear nucleus, where all auditory nerve fibers from the cochlea form their first synapses. [WP,unvetted].

name: inter-hypobranchial 3 joint
description: Joint that articulates the left and right hypobranchial 3 cartilages or bones. Inter-hypobranchial 3 joint is unpaired.

name: stapes cartilage element
description: A stapes endochondral element that is composed primarily of cartilage tissue.

name: interopercular-mandibular ligament
description: Interopercular-mandibular ligament is a ligament that connects the interopercle to an element of the lower jaw, typically the retroarticular.

name: obsolete basibranchial element
description: Endochondral element that is ventral, median, and associated with a single pharyngeal arch in the pharyngeal arch 3-7 skeleton.

name: ventral actinotrichium
description: Actinotrichium which is part of the ventral fin fold.

name: perihilar interstitium
description: the part of the renal interstitium surrounding the pelvis

name: auricular vein
description: Any vein serving the ear region

name: right lung accessory lobe lobar bronchus
description: The right lung accessory lobe lobar bronchus is the major airway within the right lung accessory lobe that starts at the division of the bronchus on the right side and ends at the point of its own subdivision into tertiary or segmental bronchi

name: proximal tarsal bone pre-cartilage condensation
description: A proximal tarsal endochondral element that is composed primarily of a pre-cartilage condensation.

name: incus pre-cartilage condensation
description: A incus endochondral element that is composed primarily of a pre-cartilage condensation.

name: trunk bone
description: A bone that is part of a trunk [Automatically generated definition].

name: statoconial membrane
description: An acellular membrane in the vestibular labyrinth that is composed of the otoconial layer, gelatinous layer, and a subcupular meshwork.

name: thoracic dorsal root ganglion
description: A dorsal root ganglion that is part of a thorax [Automatically generated definition].

name: nipple
description: Projection of skin containing the outlets for 15-20 lactiferous ducts arranged cylindrically around the tip.

name: submucosa of right main bronchus
description: A submucosa that is part of a right main bronchus [Automatically generated definition].

name: visceral endoderm
description: Visceral endoderm, a population of extraembyonic endoderm, is an extraembryonic tissue that functions in a regulatory capacity but does not contribute directly to the formation of any adult organs[PMID:15905405]. primitive endoderm-derived tissue which remains in contact with and surrounds the extra-embryonic ectoderm and the epiblast and provides signals for the differentiation and patterning of the epiblast; a small number of visceral endoderm cells also contribute to the endoderm of the embryonic gut[MP].

name: sphenoid bone pre-cartilage condensation
description: A sphenoid endochondral element that is composed primarily of a pre-cartilage condensation.

name: endothelium
description: A layer of epithelium that lines the heart, blood vessels (endothelium, vascular), lymph vessels (endothelium, lymphatic), and the serous cavities of the body[MESH]. Simple squamous epithelium which lines blood and lymphatic vessels and the heart[FMA]

name: middle suprarenal artery
description: The middle suprarenal arteries (middle capsular arteries; suprarenal arteries) are two small vessels which arise, one from either side of the abdominal aorta, opposite the superior mesenteric artery. They pass laterally and slightly upward, over the crura of the diaphragm, to the suprarenal glands, where they anastomose with suprarenal branches of the inferior phrenic and renal arteries. In the fetus these arteries are of large size.

name: ganglion of peripheral nervous system
description: A spatially aggregated collection of nerve cell bodies in the PNS, consisting of one or more subpopulations that share cell type, chemical phenotype, and connections. (CUMBO).

name: mediale
description: A recurrent variant of salamanders; a rhomboidal cartilage lying immediately postaxial from the centrale or centrale 1.

name: hump
description: A fatty deposit found on the back of camels.

name: maxillary nerve
description: The sensory nerve subdivision of the trigeminal nerve that transmits sensory information from the palate, upper teeth and gingiva, the skin between the palpebral fissure and the mouth, and from the nasal cavity and maxillary sinuses.

name: skeleton of pedal acropodium
description: The subdivision of the skeleton that consists of all the skeletal elements at the distalmost end of the pedal autopodium - i.e. the bones of the foot or their cartilaginous precursors[cjm].

name: lumbar vertebra endochondral element
description: A lumbar vertebra bone or its cartilage or pre-cartilage precursor.

name: obsolete regional part of solitary nucleus
hypaxial region somite 18
description: Somite-derived body wall muscle present ventral to the horizontal myoseptum. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: prostate epithelium
description: The prostate epithelium.

name: intermedium (fore)
description: Quadrangular cartilage or bone lying between the preaxial radiale and the postaxial ulnare in the proximal level of the mesopodium.

name: body of ilium
description: The body of ilium enters into the formation of the acetabulum, of which it forms rather less than two-fifths. Its external surface is partly articular, partly non-articular; the articular segment forms part of the lunate surface of the acetabulum, the non-articular portion contributes to the acetabular fossa. The internal surface of the body is part of the wall of the lesser pelvis and gives origin to some fibers of the Obturator internus. Below, it is continuous with the pelvic surfaces of the ischium and pubis, only a faint line indicating the place of union.

name: indifferent gonad
description: A gonad prior to differentiating into a definitive testis or ovary.

name: hypaxial region somite 16
description: Somite-derived body wall muscle present ventral to the horizontal myoseptum. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: joint of auditory ossicle
description: Any synovial joint that connects auditory ossicles.

name: rhombomere 5 roof plate
description: A rhombomere roof plate that is part of a rhombomere 5.

name: nursing stage
description: A mammalian developmental stage that covers the period from birth until weaning.

name: gas in respiratory system
description: Any portion of gas located in a part of the respiratory system.

name: fibular facet of the astragalus
description: Articular surface on the astragalus for the fibula.

name: jugular foramen
description: The jugular foramen is a large aperture in the base of the skull. It is located behind the carotid canal and is formed in front by the petrous portion of the temporal, and behind by the occipital; it is generally larger on the right than on the left side

name: long bone
description: Long bone is a limb bone that is subcylindrical and has a shaft with periosteum separating the ends of the bones. Long bones are present only in the limbs[VSAO:wd].

name: pedicel
description: Paired stalks located dorsolateral to the vertebral centrum that provide support to the lateral margins of the neural arch laminae.

name: ganglionic eminence
description: The transient proliferative population of neurons that expands exponentially during late prenatal development; it is a continuous germinal zone distinct from the ventricular zone that surrounds the brain ventricles[MP].

name: genu of corpus callosum
description: Part of corpus callosum comprising the "kneelike" anterior bend (adapted from Nolte, The Human Brain, 6th ed., 2009 pg 664)

name: anatomical entity
description: Biological entity that is either an individual member of a biological species or constitutes the structural organization of an individual member of a biological species.

name: prehallical element
description: Is a endochondral element that is part of the mesopodial skeleton and is contained within the prehallux which in some taxa appears as a pre-axial digit-like projection anterior to the first digit of the foot.

name: utricle valve
description: The utriculo-endolymphatic (UE) valve which is located in the antero-inferior wall of the utricle at the orifice of the utricular duct and serves to regulate endolymph volume in the endolymphatic sac, the utricle and the canals

name: rhombomere 3
description: the third transiently divided segment of the developing rhombencephalon; rhombomeres are lineage restricted, express different genes from one another, and adopt different developmental fates; rhombomeres are numbered in caudal to rostral order

name: trochlear nucleus
description: Nucleus in the midbrain at the level of the inferior colliculus near the midline, containing the motor neurons giving rise to the trochlear nerve, innervating the contralateral superior oblique extraocular muscle of the eye (Brodal, Neurological Anatomy, 3rd ed, 1981, pg. 533).

name: cranial placode
description: Ectodermal placode that develops in the head into a part of the sensory nervous system. With a few exceptions (lens, adenohypophyseal), cranial placodes are neurogenic.

name: sacral condyle
description: Anterior, paired convex facets for articulation with the cotyle(s) of the urostyle.

name: medullary ray
description: A renal, cortical lobule, consisting of the ascending or descending limbs of the loop of Henle or of the collecting tubules; medullary rays are regions where parallel arrays of straight tubules travel perpendicular to the capsule and extend from the cortex to the medulla.

name: lobe of liver
description: Traditional gross anatomy divided the liver into four lobes based on surface features. The falciform ligament is visible on the front (anterior side) of the liver. This divides the liver into a left anatomical lobe, and a right anatomical lobe.

name: postbranchial lamina
description: Medial facing projection or surface on the anterior ( cranial) region of the cleithrum that is often textured or denticled. This process has two primary functions: 1) its shape enhances the vertical strength of the cleithrum and 2) it forms the edge of the gill chamber and helps to direct water after it has passed over the gills (modified from Clack 2012)

name: rhinarium
description: Moist, hairless, crenelated area around nostrils of some mammals

name: branchiostegal ray 1
description: Branchiostegal ray that is the anterior-most ray in the adult.

name: metatarsophalangeal joint of pedal digit 1
description: A skeletal joint that connects a metatarsal bone and connects a distal phalanx of pedal digit 1.

name: suprazygomatic part of temporalis
description: The suprazygomatic part of the temporalis muscle is a separable part of the deep temporalis that attaches to the superior surface of the temporal root of the zygomatic arch.

name: pygostyle
description: Pygostyle refers to a number of the final few caudal vertebrae fused into a single ossification, supporting the tail feathers and musculature. In modern birds, the rectrices attach to these[WP].

name: pigment epithelium of eye
description: epithelial layer of the retina, ciliary body, or iris composed of cells containing pigment granules.

name: aorta tunica adventitia
description: the outermost layer of the aorta wall, containing connective tissue and collagen and elastic fibers

name: musculature of pes
description: Any collection of muscles that is part of a foot [Automatically generated definition].

name: lamina propria of fundus of stomach
description: A lamina propria that is part of a mucosa of fundus of stomach.

name: interdigital region between digits 1 and 2
description: An interdigital region that adjacent_to a digit 1 and adjacent_to a digit 2.

name: epithelium of hip
description: An epithelium that is part of a hip [Automatically generated definition].

name: palatocerebral artery
description: The PLA branches ventrally from the CrDI. It extends rostrally along the base of mid- and forebrain, then loops medially and links to the corresponding vessel from the other side of the embryo. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: Brodmann (1909) area 19
description: Brodmann area 19, or BA19, is part of the occipital lobe cortex in the human brain. Along with area 18, it comprises the extrastriate (or peristriate) cortex. In normally-sighted humans, extrastriate cortex is a visual association area, with feature-extracting, shape recognition, attentional, and multimodal integrating functions. This area is also known as peristriate area 19, and it refers to a subdivision of the cytoarchitecturally defined occipital region of cerebral cortex. In the human it is located in parts of the lingual gyrus, the cuneus, the lateral occipital gyrus (H) and the superior occipital gyrus (H) of the occipital lobe where it is bounded approximately by the parieto-occipital sulcus. Cytoarchitecturally it is bounded on one side by the parastriate area 18 which it surrounds. Rostrally it is bounded by the angular area 39 (H) and the occipitotemporal area 37 (H) (Brodmann-1909).

name: periderm
description: A temporary epithelium that derives from the outer layer of the ectdoerm and is shed once the inner layer differentiates to form a true epidermis.

name: annulus fibrosus disci intervertebralis
description: The ring of fibrocartilage and fibrous tissue forming the circumference of the intervertebral disc; surrounds the nucleus pulposus, which is prone to herniation when the annulus fibrosus is compromised.

name: paraventricular nucleus of hypothalamus
description: Nucleus in the anterior part of the hypothalamus. (MSH) * one of the magnocellular hypothalamic nuclei, an elongated plate of large, deeply staining cells located close to the third ventricle in the anterior hypothalamic area; major source of oxytocin and to a lesser extent, of antidiuretic hormone, neurohormones, which are carried to the neurohypophysis along the paraventriculohypophysial tract. (CSP)

name: membrane organ
description: Nonparenchymatous organ that primarily consists of dense connective tissue organized into a sheet which interconnects two or more organs, separates two or more body spaces from one another, or surrounds an organ or body part. Examples: interosseous membrane of forearm, obturator membrane, tympanic membrane, fibrous pericardium, fascia lata, dura mater. [FMA]

name: right kidney
description: A kidney that is part of a right side of organism [Automatically generated definition].

name: dental pulp
description: The part in the center of a tooth made up of living soft tissue and cells called odontoblasts[WP].

name: cocoon
description: A casing spun of silk by many moth caterpillars, and numerous other holometabolous insect larvae as a protective covering for the pupa[WP].

name: crustacean post-larval stage
description: A crustacean larval stage characterised by the use of abdominal appendages (pleopods) for propulsion.

name: orbicularis oculi muscle
description: A circumorbital muscle in the face that closes the eyelid[HP].

name: interray vessel
description: Vessels that travel between veins in adjacent rays.

name: medial accessory nucleus of optic tract
urostyle
description: In teleosts: Anatomical cluster that is the result of fusion of preural centrum 1 with one or more adjacent ural centra[AAO]; Rodlike caudal bony structure unique to anurans that lies within a compartment formed by the elongated, anteriorly oriented pelvic girdle. The urostyle is formed by the fusion of the coccyx and the hypochord[AAO].

name: cardiac endomysium
description: Reticular tissue which surrounds a cardiac myocyte.

name: periurethral tissue
description: Any portion of tissue that surrounds a urethra.

name: autonomic ganglion
description: ganglion that has dendrites that form a junction between autonomic nerves originating from the central nervous system and autonomic nerves innervating their target organs in the periphery. There are two subtypes, sympathetic ganglion and parasympathetic ganglion.

name: paroophoron
description: A collection of a few scattered rudimentary tubules child, situated in the broad ligament between the epoophoron and the uterus.

name: carotid body
description: A small epithelioid structure consisting of a small cluster of chemoreceptive and supporting cells located near the bifurcation of the common carotid artery that serves as a chemoreceptive organ that senses the pH, carbon dioxide, and oxygen concentrations in the blood and plays a crucial role in their homeostatic control.

name: larval chondrocranium
description: Cartilaginous larval skull.

name: extrascapula
description: Dermal canal-bearing bone placed at the dorso-posterior region of the skull roof, lying on the posterior region of the pterotic and parietals, or the pterotic and epioccipital, or on the pterotic, epioccipital and occipital bones.

name: pharyngobranchial tooth plate
description: Dermal bone of upper pharyngeal arches associated with pharyngobranchial bones or cartilages, usually bearing teeth.

name: brille
description: A layer of transparent, immovable disc-shaped skin or scale covering the eyes of some animals for protection, especially in animals without eyelids. The brille has evolved from a fusion of the upper and lower eyelids.

name: stratum lemnisci of superior colliculus
description: Composite layer of the superior colliculus lying deep to the stratum opticum, that can be further subdivided into fiber and cell rich layers (Brodal, Neurological Anatomy, 2nd ed., 1981, pg 544)

name: nasopharyngeal gland
description: A gland that is part of a nasopharynx.

name: 1st arch mandibular mesenchyme from head mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that develops_from a head mesenchyme from mesoderm and is part of a 1st arch mandibular mesenchyme.

name: honey
description: A sweet viscid material elaborated out of the nectar of flowers in the honey sac of various bees.

name: abdominal segment element
description: An organ or element that is part of the adbominal segment of the organism. This region can be further subdivided into the abdominal cavity and the pelvic region.

name: pineal tract
description: A cranial nerve fiber tract that innervates the pineal body.

name: lumen of trachea
description: An anatomical space that surrounded_by a trachea.

name: calcareous egg tooth
description: Tooth used to break the eggshell, that is shed soon after hatching. In lepidosaurs, a true tooth that is shed soon after hatching.

name: glenoid fossa
description: Anatomical cavity for the proximal articular surface of the proximal limb or fin element with the scapulocoracoid or equivalent structure.

name: telencephalon arachnoid mater
description: An arachnoid mater that is part of a telencephalon.

name: metatarsophalangeal joint
description: The metatarsophalangeal articulations are the joints between the metatarsal bones of the foot and the proximal bones of the toes . They are condyloid joints meaning an elliptical or rounded surface (of the metatarsal bones) come close to the shallow cavities (of the proximal phalanges). The ligaments are the plantar and two collateral.

name: pancreas tail parenchyma
description: A parenchyma that is part of a tail of pancreas [Automatically generated definition].

name: incisura fossa
description: The condyloid fossa on the cranial aspect of the Atlas my be perforated (foramen fossa) or have an open dorsal notch (Incisura fossa) in which the apex of the dens rides. (From Baumel et al. 1993)

name: mucosa of uterine tube
description: A mucosa that is part of a fallopian tube [Automatically generated definition].

name: posterior nuclear complex of thalamus
description: Part of thalamus comprising ill defined cellular groups in the caudal thalamus at the meso-diencephalic junction. It is not a homogeneous structure but consists of several distinct cellular groups, including the suprageniculate and limitans nuclei, the magnocellular division of the medial geniculate body, portions of the pulvinar nucleus and an area of mixed cell types intercalated between the ventroposterior nucleus and the nucleus lateral posterior (Brodal, Neurological Anatomy, 3rd ed., 1981, pg 97)

name: lentiform nucleus
description: The lentiform nucleus or lenticular nucleus comprises the putamen and the globus pallidus within the basal ganglia. It is a large, cone-shaped mass of gray matter just lateral to the internal capsule. [WP,unvetted].

name: dorsal pancreatic bud
description: pancreatic bud that gives rise to the accessory pancreatic duct.

name: atrioventricular canal
description: The part of the heart connecting the atrium to the cardiac ventricle[ZFA]. In the developing heart, the constriction between the atrium and ventricle constitutes the atrial canal, and indicates the site of the future atrioventricular valves[WP].

name: margo tympanicus of pterygoid
description: Margin that connects the posterior and medial rami of the pterygoid.

name: nerve of cervical vertebra
description: The cervical nerves are the spinal nerves from the cervical vertebrae. Although there are seven cervical vertebrae (C1-C7), there are eight cervical nerves (C1-C8). All nerves except C8 emerge above their corresponding vertebrae, while the C8 nerve emerges below the C7 vertebra. (In the other portions of the spine, the nerve emerges below the vertebra with the same name. Dorsal (posterior) distribution includes the greater occipital (C2) and third occipital (C3). Ventral (anterior) distribution includes the cervical plexus (C1-C4) and brachial plexus (C5-C8) [WP,unvetted].

name: midbrain tectum
description: Dorsal part of the midbrain, consisting of the superior and inferior colliculi and the pretectal nuclei (MM).

name: nephron tubule basement membrane
description: A basement membrane that is part of a nephron tubule.

name: pedal digit 1 digitopodial skeleton
description: A subdivision of the skeleton of the autopod consisting of the phalanges of pedal digit 1 plus the associated metapodial element.

name: urethra mesenchymal layer
description: A mesenchyme that is part of a urethra.

name: habenulo-interpeduncular tract
description: White matter tract containing fibers projecting from the habenular nuclei to the interpeduncular nucleus (Maryann Martone)

name: Ruffini nerve ending
description: An encapsulated nerve receptor present in subpapillary dermis and deep dermis of hairy and glabrous skin.

name: roofing cartilage
description: Cartilaginous larval structure dorsal to the four anterior-most vertebrae, which forms the connection between neural arches and supraneurals in the Weberian apparatus. Bird and Mabee, 2003.

name: rectus cervicis
description: Retracts the hyoid and, therefore, the tongue.

name: sacrococcygeal symphysis
description: The sacrococcygeal symphysis (sacrococcygeal articulation, articulation of the sacrum and coccyx) is an amphiarthrodial joint, formed between the oval surface at the apex of the sacrum, and the base of the coccyx. It is a slightly moveable joint which is frequently, partially or completely, obliterated in old age, homologous with the joints between the bodies of the vertebrae.

name: extrinsic extensor muscle of manus
description: The extrinsic extensor muscles of the hand are located in the back of the forearm and have long tendons connecting them to bones in the hand, where they exert their action.

name: trunk ectoderm
description: The region of the ectoderm posterior to the cephalic furrow.

name: presumptive rhombomere 4
description: A presumptive structure that has the potential to develop into a rhombomere 4.

name: maxillary process mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a maxillary prominence.

name: basibranchial 1 bone
description: Basibranchial bone that is ventral, median, and associated with branchial arch 1 (pharyngeal arch 3). Typically develops in the anterior copula cartilage.

name: proximal epiphysis of fibula
description: A proximal epiphysis that is part of a fibula.

name: aortic valve cusp
description: The three fibrous triangular components and associated flap of the aortic valve

name: ovisac
description: Part of the ovary consisting of a thin sheath of connective tissue enclosing the ovarian follicles.

name: cosmoid scale
description: Multi-tissue integumentary element composed of enamel or enameloid, dentine and lamellar bone, and characterized by pore-canal system.

name: parotid gland excretory duct
description: Any of the interlobular excretory ducts of the parotid gland which are found in the connective tissue septa and formed by the union of several intralobular striated (secretory) ducts; ultimately, the excretory ducts of the parotid gland coalesce and form a single main excretory duct (Stensen's duct) that opens into the oral cavity; excretory ducts do not change the secretory product.

name: skeleton of limb
description: The collection of all skeletal elements in an individual limb.

name: pulmonary surfactant
description: a substance formed by type II alveolar cells composed of surface-active lipoprotein complex (phospholipoprotein).

name: ventro-rostral cluster
description: Early-forming neural cluster located in the rostral diencephalon. At 19 h, axons arising from the vrc grow caudally to pioneer the tract of the postoptic commissure (TPOC). Ross et al., 1992.

name: 2nd arch mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a pharyngeal arch 2.

name: skeletal element projection
description: Anatomical projection that is composed of bone or cartilage tissue.

name: proximal epiphysis of distal phalanx of manual digit 2
description: A proximal epiphysis that is part of a distal phalanx of manual digit 2 [Automatically generated definition].

name: P1 area of pallium (Myxiniformes)
description: Most superficial of the areas of the pallium in the enlarged evaginated telencephalon of hagfishes.

name: hindlimb zeugopod muscle
description: Any muscle organ that is part of a hindlimb zeugopod (lower leg) [Automatically generated definition].

name: skin of prepuce of penis
description: the loose fold of skin that covers the penis

name: obsolete basihyal bone
description: Endochondral bone that is median and is the anterior-most bone of the ventral hyoid arch.

name: sinusoidal space
description: A anatomical space that is enclosed by a sinusoid.

name: incisor process
description: Process that is part of the mandible that is in close proximity to the incisor teeth.

name: lateral line scale 6
description: The sixth scale in the lateral line series.

name: soleal vein
description: A vein that drains the soleus

name: lateral superior olivary nucleus
description: One of two recognized nuclei comprising the superior olive. The lateral superior olivary nucleus is much less prominent in humans than in many rodents and carnivores. In the latter species, it is frequently described as S- or V-shaped.

name: highest nuchal line attachment site
description: Of the nuchal lines, the upper, often faintly marked, is named the highest nuchal line, but is sometimes referred to as the Mempin Line, and to it the galea aponeurotica is attached.

name: flexor carpi ulnaris muscle
description: The flexor carpi ulnaris muscle (FCU) is a muscle of the human forearm that acts to flex and adduct the manus. [WP,unvetted].

name: straight venules of kidney
description: The straight venules of kidney are branches from the plexuses at the apices of the medullary pyramids, formed by the terminations of the arteriae rectae. They run outward in a straight course between the tubes of the medullary substance, and joining, as above stated, the interlobular veins, form venous arcades; these in turn unite and form veins which pass along the sides of the pyramids. Contains fenestrated capillaries.

name: vaginal hymen
description: A membrane that surrounds or partially covers the vaginal opening.

name: carapace bone
description: Fused dorsal element constituting the carapace of a turtle shell.

name: basibranchial 1 cartilage
description: Pharyngeal arch cartilage that is ventral, median, and associated with branchial arch 1 (pharyngeal arch 3).

name: future tongue
description: A compound organ that has the potential to develop into a tongue.

name: palatine cartilage
description: Cartilage that is separate from and anterior to the pterygoquadrate cartilage.

name: basibranchial 1 element
description: Skeletal element that is median and associated with branchial arch 1.

name: anterior cranial fontanel
description: Fontanel that is located between the contralateral frontals and anterior to the epiphyseal bar.

name: part of afferent arteriole forming the juxtaglomerular complex
dorsal intercostal artery
description: The highest intercostal artery (supreme intercostal artery, superior intercostal artery) is an artery in the human body that usually gives rise to the first and second posterior intercostal arteries, which supply blood to their corresponding intercostal space. It usually arises from the costocervical trunk, which is a branch of the subclavian artery.

name: presumptive ectoderm
description: Presumptive structure of the blastula that will develop into ectoderm.

name: right lung accessory lobe lobar bronchus mesenchyme
description: The right lung accessory lobe lobar bronchus mesenchyme is a type of tissue made up of loosely-packed mesenchymal cells in the right lung accessory lobe lobar bronchus

name: descending trunk of arch of aorta
pedal digit 1 phalanx
description: A phalanx that is part of a foot digit 1 [Automatically generated definition].

name: adult muscle system
description: Muscle system of the adult.

name: meninx of midbrain
description: A meninx that is part of a midbrain [Automatically generated definition].

name: epithelium of bronchus
description: An epithelium that is part of a bronchus [Automatically generated definition].

name: submucosa of left main bronchus
description: A submucosa that is part of a left main bronchus [Automatically generated definition].

name: Ongur, Price, and Ferry (2003) area 10m
description: Area 10m is a cortical area in the frontal lobe defined on multiple architectonic criteria.

name: carpal pad
description: An autopod pad found in the carpal region of a manus. Used for additional traction when stopping or descending a slope in digitigrade species.

name: placenta
description: organ of metabolic interchange between fetus and mother, partly of embryonic origin and partly of maternal origin[GO]. The fetal portion of the placenta is known as the villous chorion. The maternal portion is known as the decidua basalis. The two portions are held together by anchoring villi that are anchored to the decidua basalis by the cytotrophoblastic shell.

name: forelimb blood vessel
description: A blood vessel that is part of a forelimb [Automatically generated definition].

name: Y-shaped fibrocartilage skeleton of ventral pouch
description: A Y-shaped fibrocartilage structure that lies in the substance of the muscular ventral pouch of rorqual whales.

name: ganglion of central nervous system
description: A ganglion that is part of a central nervous system [Automatically generated definition].

name: Rathkes pouch epithelium
description: A epithelial sac that is part of a Rathke's pouch.

name: lateral appendix
description: A small lateral diverticulum of the nasal cavity found in anuran larvae.

name: corpus cavernosum maxillaris
description: A bulbous ridge of highly vascularized tissue that runs along the center of the hard palate, expanding cranially to form two large lobes that terminate under the tip of the rostral palate, with another enlarged node at the caudal terminus.

name: tongue muscle
description: The muscular portion of the tongue.

name: small intestine smooth muscle circular layer
description: A circular muscle layer of muscular coat that is part of a small intestine smooth muscle.

name: hypaxial region somite 20
description: Somite-derived body wall muscle present ventral to the horizontal myoseptum. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: anterior inferior iliac spine
description: The anterior inferior iliac spine (AIIS) is a bony eminence on the anterior border of the hip bone, or, more precisely, the wing of the ilium (i.e. the upper lateral parts of the pelvis).

name: enteric plexus
description: A plexus of autonomic nerve fibers within the wall of the digestive tube, and made up of the submucosal, myenteric, and subserosal plexuses; it contains visceral afferent fibers, sympathetic postganglionic fibers, parasympathetic preganglionic and postganglionic fibers, and parasympathetic postganglionic cell bodies.

name: supratemporal commissure
description: Lateral line canal that that crosses the supratemporal region posterior to the openings of the endolymphatic ducts and connects the lateral canals of each side.

name: lymph node follicle
description: A lymphoid follicle that is part of a lymph node.

name: dorsal fin proximal radial bone
description: dorsal fin proximal radial element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: zona pectinata of basilar membrane of cochlea
description: The acellular membrane that forms the outer two thirds of the basilar membrane of the conchlea.

name: breast epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a breast.

name: rhombomere 6 floor plate
description: A rhombomere floor plate that is part of a rhombomere 6.

name: carbon dioxide in respiratory system
description: Any portion of gas located in a part of the respiratory system that is composed primarily of carbon dioxide.

name: ethomosphenoid region
description: Region consisitng of the ethmoid and sphenoid bones.

name: left thymus lobe
description: A thymus lobe that is in the left side of a thymus.

name: kidney pyramid
description: Kidney pyramids are the conical arrangements of tubules that constitute the renal medulla in a multi-lobed mammalian kidney; they contain the loops of Henle and the medullary collecting ducts.

name: digit 1 plus metapodial segment
description: A subdivision of the autopod consisting of digit 1 plus the region incorporating a single metapodial element. These segments are typically repeated along the pre-axiom to post-axial axis.

name: stapes base
description: The flat portion of the stirrup of the ear that fits in the oval window between the middle and inner ear.

name: medial ganglionic eminence
description: A distinct elevation of a transient proliferating cell mass of the fetal subventricular zone; this mass contributes most of its cells to the neocortex; however, hippocampal neurons, thalamus, septum and olfactory bulb neurons are also partly derived from the MGE.

name: flocculus
description: the small lobe of the cerebellum at the posterior border of the middle cerebellar peduncle anterior to the biventer lobule that receives input from the inferior and medial vestibular nuclei and sends fibers back to the vestibular nuclei, and processes and integrates these signals to allow for the constant maintenance of balance

name: urostyle cotyle
description: Anterior, single or paired concave facets for articulation with the sacral condyle(s).

name: ural centrum 2
description: A vertebral centrum that is located immediately posterior to ural centrum 1. Ural centrum 2 is an unpaired median bone.

name: right lobe of liver
description: The right lobe is much larger than the left; the proportion between them being as six to one. It occupies the right hypochondrium, and is separated from the left lobe on its upper surface by the falciform ligament; on its under and posterior surfaces by the left sagittal fossa; and in front by the umbilical notch. It is of a somewhat quadrilateral form, its under and posterior surfaces being marked by three foss√¶: the porta and the foss√¶ for the gall-bladder and inferior vena cava, which separate its left part into two smaller lobes; the quadrate and caudate lobes. [WP,unvetted].

name: obsolete infraglenoid buttress
description: An anatomical projection venteral to the glenoid fossa on the scapulocoracoid that abuts on the cliethrum.

name: bulge
description: expanded and swollen region of a surface that is otherwise relatively flat

name: multicellular anatomical structure
description: An anatomical structure that has more than one cell as a part.

name: ectopterygoid tooth
description: Tooth that is attached to the ectopterygoid bone.

name: tympanosquamosal
description: Central, funnel-shaped, ossified portion of the tympanic annulus fused to the squamosal bone.

name: pectoral fin endoskeletal disc
description: A plate-like chondrogenic condensation within the pectoral fin, which subdivides into individual radials by decomposition of extracellular matrix in the inter-radial mesenchyme (Grandel and Schulte-Merker, 1998).

name: inferior horn of the lateral ventricle
description: The part of the lateral ventricle extending downward and anteriorly in the temporal lobe.

name: pars reflexa of masseter
description: The pars reflexa is a separable part of the superficial masseter muscle that attaches to the medial surface of the mandible.

name: obsolete forerunner cell group
description: A group of cells that migrate at the leading edge of shield during gastrulation but do not involute. At the end of gastrulation, forerunner cells migrate deep into the embryo and organize to form Kuppfer's vesicle. Cooper and D'Amico, 1996.

name: skin mucous gland
description: A mucous gland that is part of the skin.

name: paraventricular nucleus of the hypothalamus magnocellular division - posterior magnocellular part
uropygial gland
description: A large gland at the base of a bird's tail dorsal to the cloaca at the end of the pygostyle that secretes an oil used in preening. It opens through a caudally directed nipple.

name: muscular coat of seminal vesicle
description: A muscular coat that is part of a seminal vesicle [Automatically generated definition].

name: bed nucleus of stria terminalis
description: A brain structure in the forebrain wrapped around the stria terminalis. It's largest extent can be found around the crossing of the anterior commissure[INCF].

name: musculature of manus
description: Any collection of muscles that is part of a manus [Automatically generated definition].

name: lumen of duodenum
description: A anatomical space that is part of a duodenum.

name: epithelium of knee
description: An epithelium that is part of a knee [Automatically generated definition].

name: communicating vessel palatocerebral artery
description: Connect the palatocerebral artery with the prosencephalic artery. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: Brodmann (1909) area 20
description: Brodmann area 20, or BA20, is part of the temporal cortex in the human brain. The region encompasses most of the ventral temporal cortex, a region believed to play a part in high-level visual processing and recognition memory. This area is also known as inferior temporal area 20, and it refers to a subdivision of the cytoarchitecturally defined temporal region of cerebral cortex. In the human it corresponds approximately to the inferior temporal gyrus. Cytoarchitecturally it is bounded medially by the ectorhinal area 36 (H), laterally by the middle temporal area 21, rostrally by the temporopolar area 38 (H) and caudally by the occipitotemporal area 37 (H) (Brodmann-1909).

name: pre-chordal neural plate
description: The portion of neural plate anterior to the mid-hindbrain junction.

name: conceptus
description: The embryo and its adnexa (appendages or adjunct parts) or associated membranes (i.e. the products of conception) The conceptus includes all structures that develop from the zygote, both embryonic and extraembryonic. It includes the embryo as well as the embryonic part of the placenta and its associated membranes - amnion, chorion (gestational sac), and yolk sac[WP].

name: lateral preoptic nucleus
description: The lateral preoptic nucleus is lateral to the medial preoptic nucleus. It also mediates non-REM sleep onset.[WP,unvetted].

name: cardiac neural crest
description: portion of neural crest that develops from the dorsal neural tube. It overlaps the vagal neural crest and migrates to populate the pharyngeal arches 3, 4 and 6 (producing structures in the head) and to the heart, forming connective tissue that separates the great vessels of the heart. [Wikipedia]

name: distal part of styloid process of temporal bone
description: A segment in the hyoidean arch between the epihyal and tympanohyal[biology-online]. The interhyal is a small rod-like element that connects the ventral and dorsal parts of the hyoid arch. It articulates laterally with the posterior end of the epihyal and medially at the cartilaginous junction between the hyomandibula and the symplectic. It remains cartilaginous in adult zebrafish and other cypriniforms[ZFA].

name: megalopa stage
description: The crustacean post-larval stage of a crab

name: olfactory nerve
description: Nerve that carries information from the olfactory epithelium to the olfactory bulb[Butler and Hodos].

name: Meckel's cartilage
description: Meckel's cartilage is the bilaterally paired, rod-like, cartilaginous ventral component of the lower jar, or ventral mandibular arch. It is typically resorbed in adults.

name: skeletal muscle endomysium
description: Reticular tissue which surrounds a skeletal muscle cell.

name: obelion
description: The point of the sagittal suture which is on a level with the parietal foramina.

name: sympathetic ganglion
description: A ganglion of the sympathetic nervous system. Examples: paravertebral and the prevertebral ganglia, which include the sympathetic chain ganglia, the superior, middle, and inferior cervical ganglia, and the aorticorenal, celiac, and stellate ganglia

name: manual digit 1 digitopodial skeleton
description: A subdivision of the skeleton of the autopod consisting of the phalanges of manual digit 1 plus the associated metapodial element.

name: centrum semiovale
description: The semioval center is the white matter found underneath the grey matter on the surface of the cerebrum. The term is synonymous with cerebral white matter. The white matter, located in each hemisphere between the cerebral cortex and nuclei, as a whole has a semioval shape. It consists of cortical projection fibers, association fibers and cortical fibers.

name: scleral cartilage
description: Circular cartilage ringing the posterior portion of the eye in the sclera. Supports the eye.

name: spine appendage
description: A hard, thorny or needle-like structure which occurs on various animals. Animals such as porcupines and sea urchins grow spines as a self-defense mechanism. Spines are often formed of keratin. Other animals with spines are hedgehogs, spiny mice and at least two ornithischian dinosaurs.

name: endometrium luminal epithelium
description: A luminal layer of epithelium that is part of a endometrium epithelium.

name: ceratobranchial bone
description: Endochondral bone that is bilaterally paired and forms part of the ventral branchial arches.

name: pharyngobranchial 4 tooth plate
description: Pharyngeal tooth plate that lies ventral to pharyngobranchial 4.

name: clasper
description: A male anatomical structure found some groups of animals, used in mating. Male cartilaginous fish have claspers formed from the posterior portion of their pelvic fin which serve as intromittent organs used to channel semen into the female's cloaca during mating. The act of mating in some fish including sharks usually includes one of the claspers raised to allow water into the siphon through a specific orifice. The clasper is then inserted into the vagina, where it opens like an umbrella to anchor its position. The siphon then begins to contract expelling water and sperm. Male chimaeras have cephalic claspers on their heads, which are thought to aid in holding the female during mating

name: layer of superior colliculus
description: The microstructure of the optic tectum / superior colliculus varies across species. As a general rule, there is always a clear distinction between superficial layers, which receive input primarily from the visual system and show primarily visual responses, and deeper layers, which receive many types of input and project to numerous motor-related brain areas. The distinction between these two zones is so clear and consistent that some anatomists have suggested that they should be considered separate brain structures. In mammals, neuroanatomists conventionally identify seven layers[WP].

name: penile bulb artery
description: A short vessel of large caliber which arises from the internal pudendal between the two layers of fascia of the urogenital diaphragm; it passes medialward, pierces the inferior fascia of the urogenital diaphragm, and gives off branches which ramify in the bulb of the urethra and in the posterior part of the corpus spongiosum. It gives off a small branch to the bulbo-urethral gland.

name: root of abducens nerve
description: Nerve fibers arising from motor neurons in the abducens nucleus that are contained within the pontine tegmentum

name: regurgitated substance
description: A bodily fluid consisting of the contents of the digestive tract expulsed through the anterior portion of the digestive tract.

name: dorsal region element
description: An organ or element that part of the dorsum of the organism. Examples: spinal cord, vertebrae, muscles of back.

name: rostral epiphyseal tract
description: The more rostral of the two branches of the epiphyseal tract.

name: uterus or analog
description: A subdivision of a the reproductive tract in a female organism that is the site of embryo development.

name: epidermal egg tooth
description: Epidermal outgrowth that facilitates breaking of the eggshell in archosaurs and monotremes.

name: protocerebrum
description: The most anterior of the segmental subdivisions of the insect CNS; thought to represent the first pre-oral segment of the brain. The protocerebrum comprises many discrete neuropil regions including the central body complex and mushroom bodies.

name: interphalangeal joint
description: A joint that connects one phalanx to another along a proximodistal axis.

name: cerebral hemisphere gray matter
description: A gray matter that is part of a cerebral hemisphere.

name: abdominal wall
description: The tissues that surround the organs that are present within the abdominal cavity. The abdominal wall tissue is composed of layers of fat, parietal peritoneum, fascia, and muscles.

name: upper leg epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a hindlimb stylopod [Automatically generated definition].

name: inferior cervical ganglion
description: The inferior cervical ganglion is situated between the base of the transverse process of the last cervical vertebra and the neck of the first rib, on the medial side of the costocervical artery. Its form is irregular; it is larger in size than the middle cervical ganglion, and is frequently fused with the first thoracic ganglion. [WP,unvetted].

name: interpterygoid region
description: The region on the palate corresponding to the location of the pterygoid bone, if present and between the palatine bones and the parasphenoid if not.

name: mucosa of infundibulum of uterine tube
description: A mucosa that is part of a uterine tube infundibulum [Automatically generated definition].

name: olfactory bulb
description: A bulbous anterior projection of the olfactory lobe that is the place of termination of the olfactory nerves and is especially well developed in lower vertebrates (as fishes)[BTO].

name: ventral pancreatic bud
description: pancreatic bud that gives rise to the major pancreatic duct.

name: lateral thoracic vein
description: The lateral thoracic vein is a tributary of the axillary vein. It runs with the lateral thoracic artery and drains the serratus ventralis muscle and the Pectoralis major muscle. Normally, the thoracoepigastric vein exists between this vein and superficial epigastric vein (a tributary of femoral vein), to act as a shunt for blood if the portal system (through the liver) develops hypertension or a blockage. [WP,unvetted].

name: coracobrachialis muscle
description: The Coracobrachialis is the smallest of the three muscles that attach to the coracoid process of the scapula. (The other two muscles are pectoralis minor and biceps brachii. ) It is situated at the upper and medial part of the arm. It is perforated by and innervated by the musculocutaneous nerve. [WP,unvetted].

name: pharyngeal arch derived gill
description: A gill that develops_from a pharyngeal gill precursor.

name: processus zygomatico-maxillaris
description: Posterodorsal extension of the maxilla by which it establishes contact with the squamosal.

name: bronchus basement membrane
description: A basement membrane that is part of a bronchus.

name: obsolete regional part of autonomic nervous system
pedal digit 2 digitopodial skeleton
description: A subdivision of the skeleton of the autopod consisting of the phalanges of pedal digit 2 plus the associated metapodial element.

name: subcommissural organ
description: The subcommissural organ is a circumventricular organ consisting of ependymal cells which secrete SCO-spondin[WP,partially vetted].

name: occipito-petrosal
description: Fusion of the occipital segment or occipital ring and otic capsule (Francis, 1934).

name: madreporite
description: The madreporite is an opening used to filter water into the water vascular system of echinoderms. It is visible as a small red or yellow button-like structure, looking like a small wart, on the aboral surface of the central disk of a sea star. Close up, it is visibly structured, resembling a 'madrepore' colony. From this, it derives its name. The water vascular system of the sea star consists of a series of seawater-filled ducts that function in locomotion and feeding and respiration. Its main parts are the madreporite, the stone canal, the ring canal, the radial canals, the lateral canals, and the tube feet. The sieve-like madreporite allows entry of seawater into the stone canal, which connects to the ring canal around the mouth. Five or more radial canals extend from the ring canal, one in each arm above the ambulacral groove. From the radial canals extend many lateral canals, each of which leads to a tube foot. Each tube foot is a closed cylinder with muscular walls, having a sucker at the outer end and a bulb-like ampulla at its inner end within the body cavity.

name: antler velvet
description: highly vascular skin called velvet that covers the antler whilst it grows, supplying oxygen and nutrients to the growing bone.

name: posterior paraventricular nucleus of thalamus
description: The posterior of the two nuclei paraventriculares thalami.

name: muscle layer of small intestine
description: A muscle layer that is part of a small intestine.

name: pelvic fin distal radial cartilage
description: Pelvic fin distal radial element that is composed of cartilage tissue

name: aryepiglotticus muscle
description: The aryepiglotticus is a muscle of the larynx running in the aryepiglottic fold from the arytenoid cartilage to the epiglottis.

name: right ear
description: The organ of hearing located on the right side of the head.

name: presumptive rhombomere 5
description: A presumptive structure that has the potential to develop into a rhombomere 5.

name: basibranchial 2 bone
description: Basibranchial bone that is ventral, median, and associated with branchial arch 2 (pharyngeal arch 4). Typically develops in the anterior copula cartilage.

name: inner cell mass derived hypoblast
description: A thin monolayer of small cuboidal cells that make up the lower layer of the bilaminar embryonic disc, beneath the epiblast.

name: aortic valve anulus
description: The fibrous ring of the aortic valve that attaches the cusps of aortic valve to the wall of left ventricle, and which consists of portions of the fibrous scallops of the posterior, right anterior and left anterior cusps

name: obsolete predominantly gray regional part of medullary raphe nuclear complex
presumptive embryonic/larval tracheal system
description: The sum of all the structures in the embryo that will develop into the embryonic/larval tracheal system. This corresponds to the tracheal primordia and their component tracheal branch primordia along with primordia of the spiracles.

name: anterior temporal artery
description: A branch of the middle cerebral artery that supplies blood to the anterior part of the temporal lobe.

name: excretory duct of salivary gland
description: Any of the interlobular excretory ducts of a salivary gland which are found in the connective tissue septa and formed by the union of several intralobular striated (secretory) ducts[MP,generalized].

name: epiphysis of humerus
description: An epiphysis that is part of a humerus [Automatically generated definition].

name: stomach non-glandular region
description: A region of the stomach is lined with non-glandular epithelium. Examples of a stomach non-glandular region are found in rodents.

name: murine forestomach
description: A distinct rodent non-glandular region of the stomach which is demarcated from the glandular stomach by the limiting ridge (margo plicatus).

name: pre-cartilage condensation
description: A delimited region of dense mesenchyme within looser mesenchyme whose cells are committed to become chondroblasts.

name: ventro-caudal cluster
description: Early-forming neural cluster of the ventral midbrain. At 16 h, axons of the vcc grow caudally to pioneer the medial longitudinal fasciculus (MLF), which is part of the larger ventral longitudinal tract (VLT). Later, neurons from this cluster project axons rostrally into the tract of the post-optic commissure (TPOC). Ross et al., 1992.

name: obsolete astragalus-calcaneum unit
description: Anatomical cluster that is an osteological unit consisting of the astragalus and calcaneum.

name: proximal epiphysis of distal phalanx of manual digit 3
description: A proximal epiphysis that is part of a distal phalanx of manual digit 3 [Automatically generated definition].

name: branched pelvic fin ray
description: Pelvic fin lepidotrichium that is distally branched and segmented.

name: P2 area of pallium (Myxiniformes)
description: Area directly deep to the P1 area of pallium in hagfishes.

name: upper leg blood vessel
description: A blood vessel that is part of a hindlimb stylopod [Automatically generated definition].

name: vaginal venous plexus
description: The vaginal plexuses are placed at the sides of the vagina; they communicate with the uterine, vesical, and hemorrhoidal plexuses, and are drained by the vaginal veins, one on either side, into the hypogastric veins. [WP,unvetted].

name: Hadjikhani et al. (1998) visuotopic partition scheme region
myometrium
description: the smooth muscle coat of the uterus, which forms the main mass of the organ and surrounds and supports the endometrium

name: granular layer of cerebellar cortex
description: The granular layer is the innermost layer of the cerebellar cortex. This layer contains densely packed small neurons, mostly granule cells. Some Golgi cells are found at the outer border. Granule neurons send parallel fibers to the upper molecular layer, where they synapse with Purkinje cell dendrites. Mossy fibers from the pontine nuclei in the white matter synapse with granule cell axons, Golgi cell axons and unipolar brush interneuron axons at cerebellar glomeruli in the granule cell layer.

name: sallet sensory system
description: Ciliary restraint system in the inner ear that uses sallets instead of the tectorial membrane.

name: premaxillary tooth 2
description: Premaxillary tooth that is the second tooth in a premaxillary tooth series, and positioned adjacent to the symphyseal tooth.

name: gastrocnemius vein
description: A vein that drains the gastrocnemius

name: epibranchial arborescent organ
description: Anatomical cluster that is an outgrowth of the soft tissue around the dorsolateral corner of a branchial arch that is internally supported by a core of rigid cartilage-like tissue. Epibranchial arborescent organ is paired.

name: body external integument structure
description: Dermal, epidermal, glandular and pigment structures of the body integument.

name: superior nuchal line attachment site
description: Of the nuchal lines, the one below the highest nuchal line is the superior nuchal line. To it is attached the Occipitalis muscle, the Splenius capitis muscle, the trapezius muscle, and the Sternocleidomastoid muscle.

name: flexor digitorum profundus
description: A muscle in the forearm that flexes the manual digits[WP,modified].

name: white adipose tissue
description: Connective tissue consisting of fat-storing cells and arranged in lobular groups or along minor blood vessels[MP,modified]

name: obsolete regional part of cochlear canal
peripheral plate of carapace
description: One of a series of bones around the edge of the carapace.

name: chondral bone
description: Replacement bone that forms within or surrounding a cartilaginous skeletal element.

name: stroma of thyroid gland
description: The connective tissue that supports the lobules and follicles of the thyroid gland.

name: basibranchial 4 cartilage
description: Pharyngeal arch cartilage that is ventral, median, and associated with branchial arch 4 (pharyngeal arch 6).

name: pterygoquadrate cartilage
description: pterygoquadrate cartilage - cartilage that is separate from and posterior to the palatine cartilage.

name: basibranchial 2 element
description: Skeletal element that is median and associated with branchial arch 2.

name: main bronchus connective tissue
description: A portion of connective tissue that is part of a main bronchus [Automatically generated definition].

name: pectoral fin proximal radial cartilage 1
description: pectoral fin proximal radial 1 element that is composed of cartilage tissue.
