The lateral line system is stimulated by local water displacements and vibrations, and detects propulsion of the fish through the water, as well as facilitating shoaling, prey capture, and predator and obstacle avoidance. (See Anatomical Atlas entry for lateral line by T. Whitfield.)

name: basibranchial 5 element
description: Skeletal element that is median and associated with branchial arch 5.

name: bed nucleus of the accessory olfactory tract
description: a group of cells near the surface of the brain between the supraoptic nucleus and the cortical amygdalar nucleus in the rat ( Swanson-1998 ) and the mouse ( Paxinos-2001 ). It is one of five subdivisions of the medial amygdalar nucleus.

name: strand of vibrissa hair
description: A specialized hair usually employed for tactile sensation. Vibrissae hair grow around the nostrils, above the lips, and on other parts of the face of most mammals, and all primates except humans. vibrissae are different from other hairs because they are implanted in a special hair follicle incorporating a capsule of blood called a blood sinus and heavily innervated by sensory nerves[WP].

name: thoracic cavity connective tissue
description: A portion of connective tissue that is part of a thoracic cavity [Automatically generated definition].

name: posterior superior alveolar nerve
description: The posterior superior alveolar branches (posterior superior dental branches) arise from the trunk of the maxillary nerve just before it enters the infraorbital groove; they are generally two in number, but sometimes arise by a single trunk. They descend on the tuberosity of the maxilla and give off several twigs to the gums and neighboring parts of the mucous membrane of the cheek. They then enter the posterior alveolar canals on the infratemporal surface of the maxilla, and, passing from behind forward in the substance of the bone, communicate with the middle superior alveolar nerve, and give off branches to the lining membrane of the maxillary sinus and gingival and dental branches to each molar tooth from a superior dental plexus; these branches enter the apical foramina at the roots of the teeth. The posterior superior alveolar nerve innervates the second and third maxillary molars, and two of the three roots of the maxillary first molar (all but the mesiobuccal root). When giving a Posterior Superior Alveolar nerve block, it will anesthetize the mesialbuccal root of the maxillary first molar approximately 72% of the time.

name: metanephric long descending thin limb bend
description: The metanephric long descending thin limb bend is a part of the descending thin limb of a long nephron that lies beyond the prebend segment in the metanephros[GO].

name: pectoral fin proximal radial cartilage 4
description: pectoral fin proximal radial 4 element that is composed of cartilage tissue.

name: tectum synoticum
description: Unpaired thin dorsal sheet of cartilage that partially covers the posterior chondrocranium.

name: prostate bud
description: A region of the fetal urogenital sinus epithelium destined to become the prostate[GO].

name: obsolete predominantly gray part of posterior nuclear complex
postductal region of aortic arch
description: Area of aorta distal to the ductus arteriosus.

name: kidney arterial blood vessel
description: An arterial blood vessel that is part of a kidney [Automatically generated definition].

name: distal carpal bone 2 cartilage
description: A distal carpal bone 2 endochondral element that is composed primarily of cartilage tissue.

name: ureteric segment of renal artery
description: The ureteral branches of renal artery are small branches which supply the ureter.

name: nerve root
description: A continuation of the neuron projection bundle component of a nerve inside, crossing or immediately outside the central nervous system.

name: medial preoptic nucleus
description: The medial preoptic nucleus is bounded laterally by the lateral preoptic nucleus, and medially by the preoptic periventricular nucleus. It releases gonadotropin-releasing hormone, controls copulation in males, and is larger in males than in females.[WP,unvetted].

name: chyme
description: A semifluid mass of partly digested food expelled by the stomach into the duodenum.

name: infundibulum of gallbladder
description: The tapering portion of the gall bladder that narrows to form the neck and cystic duct.

name: acropodium region
description: The segment of the autopod that is distal to the metapodial region and consists of the digits.

name: thoracic cavity blood vessel
description: A blood vessel that is part of a thoracic cavity [Automatically generated definition].

name: posterior recess
description: Posterior protrusion of the third ventricle.

name: granular gland
description: A gland that contains toxic secretions within the lumen. In frogs and salamanders, this is the larger of the two types of gland, the other being the mucuous gland[Kardong]

name: cricopharyngeus muscle
description: The cricopharyngeus is a pharyngeal arch 4/6 muscle that participates in oral/pharyngeal behaviors and is innervated by the pharyngeal plexus and the recurrent laryngeal n. (from Vagus, CN X), and is an integral part of the pharyngeal tube, and attaches to the cricoid cartilage and the midline raphe. It acts as a sphincter between the pharynx and esophagus.

name: rhombomere 7 lateral wall
description: A rhombomere lateral wall that is part of a rhombomere 7.

name: ventricular septum intermedium
description: Endocardial cushions project into the atrial canal, and, meeting in the middle line, unite to form the septum intermedium which divides the canal into two channels, the future right and left atrioventricular orifices[Gray's via WP].

name: tubercle
description: A round nodule, small eminence, or warty outgrowth found on bones, skin, or within the lungs in tuberculosis. They are also found on the leading edge of Humpback Whale's flippers, improving fluid flow over the flipper's surface[WP].

name: left gastric artery
description: An artery that arises from the celiac artery and supplies the stomach.

name: pyloric region epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a pylorus.

name: infraspinous process
description: Process on infraspinous (region below the spine) of scapula.

name: pars cylindriformis ilei
description: Elongate, cylindrical structure on the ventral side of the shaft of the ilium that extends through its entire length.

name: outer medullary collecting duct
description: The outer medullary collecting duct is the portion of the collecting duct that lies in the renal outer medulla

name: oculomotor division of oculomotor nuclear complex
description: A division of oculomotor nuclear complex that exists in organisms with electric organs which is responsible for eye movements.

name: serosa of intestine
description: A serous membrane that is part of a wall of intestine [Automatically generated definition].

name: lunate sulcus
description: The lunate sulcus is a structure in the occipital lobe. It is not present in all individuals.

name: vertebral arch joint
description: A synovial joint between the prezygapophysis of one vertebra and the postzygapophysis of the vertebra directly above it. There are two facet joints in each spinal motion segment[WP].

name: facial modiolus
description: A chiasma of facial muscles held together by fibrous tissue, located lateral and slightly superior to each angle of the mouth. It is important in moving the mouth, facial expression and in dentistry. It derives its motor nerve supply from the facial nerve, and its blood supply from labial branches of the facial artery. It is contributed to by the following muscles: orbicularis oris, buccinator, levator anguli oris, depressor anguli oris, zygomaticus major, risorius quadratus labii superioris, quadratus labii inferioris.

name: Koller's sickle
description: A local thickening of cells that acts as a margin separating sheets of cells from posterior margin of avian blastoderms from hypoblasts as they migrate anteriorly to push primary hypoblast cells anteriorly to form a secondary hypoblast known as the endoblast

name: caudal principal ray
description: Caudal fin lepidotrichium that is adjacent to a branched ray. Caudal principal rays may be segmented but unbranched and the main element forming the dorsal or ventral leading margin of the caudal fin or a ray that may be only segmented-and-branched and forms part of the middle-posterior region of the fin. A caudal principal ray is an unpaired median bone.

name: hypohyal element
description: The hypohyal is a ventral element of the hyoid arch which links the ceratohyal and the basihyal.

name: lobe of thyroid gland
description: A lobe of tissue that is part of a thyroid gland.

name: preoperculo-mandibular sensory canal
description: Sensory canal lateral or ventral to and in close proximity to the otic and post-otic sensory canals at their union. The preoperculo-mandibular sensory canal is bilaterally paired and associated with the preopercle, angular and dentary bones.

name: nucleus lentiformis mesencephali (Aves)
description: A pretectal nucleus in Aves that receives heavy retinal input and is hypothesized to be homologous to the nucleus of the optic tract of Mammals.

name: pharyngobranchial 4 bone
description: Most posterior pharyngobranchial bone, located medial to the epibranchials.

name: orbital fissure
description: Either of two openings transmitting nerves and blood vessels to or from the orbit.

name: rhinosphenoid
description: An endochondral bone which is located anterior to the orbitosphenoid and medial to the paired lateral ethmoid. Rhinosphenoid is a median bone.

name: esophagus secretion
description: A secretion that is part of a esophagus [Automatically generated definition].

name: inferior rectus extraocular muscle
description: A muscle in the orbit that depresses, adducts, and helps extort (rotate laterally) the eye. The inferior rectus muscle is the only muscle that is capable of depressing the pupil when it is in a fully abducted position.

name: subparafascicular nucleus
description: The term subparafascicular nucleus refers to a cell group located ventral to the parafascicular nucleus in the thalamus. Identified by internal structure, it is present in the human ( Mai-1997 ), the macaque ( Paxinos-2009a ), the rat ( Swanson-1998 ), and the mouse ( Hof-2000 ).

name: dorsal digital artery of manus
description: Dorsal digital arteries arise from the bifurcation of dorsal metacarpal arteries. They travel along the sides and dorsal aspects of the phalanges of the middle finger, ring finger, and little finger. They communicate with the proper palmar digital arteries. They run with the dorsal digital nerves of ulnar nerve and dorsal digital nerves of radial nerve.

name: epithelium of sublingual gland
description: An epithelium that is part of a sublingual gland [Automatically generated definition].

name: inner canthus of left eye
description: A inner canthus that is part of a left eye.

name: pedal digit 2 phalanx endochondral element
description: A pedal digit 2 phalanx bone or its cartilage or pre-cartilage precursor.

name: phrenic nerve
description: A nerve that arises from the caudal cervical nerves and is primarily the motor nerve of the diaphragm but also sends sensory fibers to the pericardium.

name: hindlimb bud mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a hindlimb bud.

name: pelvic appendage bud mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a pelvic appendage bud.

name: palate bone
description: Any bone that is part of a palate.

name: epithelium of lower jaw
description: An epithelium that is part of a lower jaw [Automatically generated definition].

name: prefrontal cortex
description: The anterior part of the frontal lobes of the brain, lying in front of the motor and premotor areas.nnThis brain region has been implicated in planning complex cognitive behaviors, personality expression, decision making and moderating correct social behavior. The basic activity of this brain region is considered to be orchestration of thoughts and actions in accordance with internal goals.nnThe most typical psychological term for functions carried out by the pre-frontal cortex area is executive function. Executive function relates to abilities to differentiate among conflicting thoughts, determine good and bad, better and best, same and different, future consequences of current activities, working toward a defined goal, prediction of outcomes, expectation based on actions, and social 'control' (the ability to suppress urges that, if not suppressed, could lead to socially-unacceptable outcomes).nnMany authors have indicated an integral link between a person's personality and the functions of the prefrontal cortex. - definition adapted from Wikipedia

name: basitrabecular process
description: A process of the otic capsule that will bridge to the palatoquadrate basal process.

name: median palatocerebral vein
description: Drains the PLA loop proceeds straight caudally along the cranial midline just above the pharynx, just below the diencephalon. Forms a 'T' with the palatocerebral veins. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: right subcardinal vein
description: A subcardinal vein that is in_the_right_side_of a multicellular organism.

name: ventromedial nucleus of hypothalamus
description: The ventromedial nucleus (sometimes referred to as the ventromedial hypothalamus) is a nucleus of the hypothalamus. [WP,unvetted].

name: dorsal fin pterygiophore 1
description: Dorsal fin pterygiophore that is the anteriormost pterygiophore of the dorsal fin.

name: vagus nerve
description: Cranial nerve that branches into the lateral (to body sense organs) and the intestino-accessorial (to the skin, muscles of shoulder, hyoid, larynx, gut, lungs, and heart).

name: omphalopleure
description: A fetal membrane, part of the yolk sac, that appears during some placentation processes.

name: magnocellular layer of dorsal nucleus of lateral geniculate body
pancreatic juice
description: Pancreatic juice is slightly alkaline and contains numerous enzymes and inactive enzyme precursors including alpha-amylase, chymotrypsinogen, lipase, procarboxypeptidase, proelastase, prophospholipase A2, ribonuclease, and trypsinogen. Its high concentration of bicarbonate ions helps to neutralize the acid from the stomach.

name: anterior swim bladder bud
description: Portion of tissue that forms from the swim bladder epithelium at the anterior end of the swim bladder.

name: upper back skin
description: A zone of skin that is part of a dorsal thoracic segment of trunk.

name: pelvic fin middle radial bone
description: Pelvic fin radial in the middle of the pelvic fin.

name: webbed autopod
description: An autopod region that has_part a webbed interdigital region.

name: cardiopharyngeal field
description: An region of the mesoderm that includes anterior lateral mesoderm of the first heart field plus contiguous pharyngeal mesoderm that gives rise to second-heart-field-derived regions of the heart and branchiomeric muscles.

name: echinopluteus larval stage
description: Larval stage in echinoderms characterized by a planktonic and feeding larval form that possesses limb-like outgrowths bearing ciliated bands.

name: M. glutaeus magnus
description: Originates from the superior process of the ilium and inserts on the aponeuronis of the M. cruralis.

name: middle white layer of superior colliculus
malleus processus brevis
description: The projection extending from the base of the manubrium of the malleus which contacts the upper part of the tympanic membrane where the tympanic cavity makes a deep pocket (epitympanic pocket) surrounding the cartilaginous nodule[MP].

name: thoracic cavity element
description: An organ or element that is in the thoracic cavity. Examples: lung, heart, longus colli.

name: pharyngotympanic tube
description: Organ with organ cavity which connects the cavity of the middle ear to the cavity of the pharynx. Examples: There are only two pharyngotympanic tubes, the right and the left pharyngotympanic tubes.[FMA]

name: pararenal fat
description: The paranephric body (or paranephric fat or pararenal fat) is collection of adipose tissue located superficial to the renal fascia. The perirenal fat, or adipose capsule of kidney, is deep to the renal fascia but superficial to the renal capsule.

name: tuber cinereum
description: Part of hypothalamus consisting of hollow eminence of gray matter situated between the mammilary bodies and the optic chiasm visible on the basal surface of the brain (adapted from Wikipedia)

name: lower leg epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a lower leg [Automatically generated definition].

name: lens fiber
description: A region of the lens consisting of packed elongated enucleate cells packed with crystallin

name: olfactory organ
description: An organ that houses olfactory neurons and is responsible for the sense of smell. Examples include the vertebrate nose and the Drosophila dorsal organ.

name: hemolymph
description: Blood analogue used by all arthropods and most mollusks that have an open circulatory system. In these animals there is no distinction between blood and interstitial fluid. The liquid fills all of the interior (the hemocoel) of the body and surrounds all cells.

name: digestive system duct
description: A duct that is part of a digestive system [Automatically generated definition].

name: m. oblique internus
description: A muscular sheet in which the fibers run in right angles to those of the m. oblique externus, slanting downward anteriorly. This is one of three sheets composing the flank musculature.

name: labial segment
description: Most posterior of the gnathal segments. In the adult it bears a pair of fused appendages, the labia, and its ectodermal invaginations give rise to the salivary glands.

name: gular region
description: Surface structure that extends from the chin covering pharynx and larynx.

name: mesangium
description: inner layer of the glomerulus, within the basement membrane surrounding the glomerular capillaries.

name: obsolete regional part of midbrain reticular formation
basal vein
description: The basal vein is formed at the anterior perforated substance by the union of (a) a small anterior cerebral vein which accompanies the anterior cerebral artery and supplies the medial surface of the frontal lobe by the fronto-basal vein. (b) the deep middle cerebral vein (deep Sylvian vein), which receives tributaries from the insula and neighboring gyri, and runs in the lower part of the lateral cerebral fissure, and (c) the inferior striate veins, which leave the corpus striatum through the anterior perforated substance. The basal vein passes backward around the cerebral peduncle, and ends in the internal cerebral vein; it receives tributaries from the interpeduncular fossa, the inferior horn of the lateral ventricle, the hippocampal gyrus, and the mid-brain.

name: subarcualis rectus I
description: Deep, visceral muscle associated with tongue movement.

name: carpometacarpus
description: The carpometacarpus is the fusion of the carpal and metacarpal bone, essentially a single fused bone between the wrist and the knuckles. It is a smallish bone in most birds, generally flattened and with a large hole in the middle. In flightless birds, however, its shape may be slightly different, or it might be absent entirely.

name: preethmoid bone
description: Small rounded to egg-shaped cartilage bone that sits in an anterolateral depression on the prevomer. Articulates with the autopalatine in all cypriniforms.

name: presumptive rhombomere 2
description: A presumptive structure that has the potential to develop into a rhombomere 2.

name: intramuscular adipose tissue
description: Adipose tissue which is located throughout skeletal muscle and is responsible for the marbling seen in certain cuts of beef. In humans, excess accumulation of intramuscular fat is associated with insulin resistance and type 2 diabetes.

name: mitral valve anulus
description: The fibrous ring of the mitral valve that attaches the cusps of mitral valve to the heart, and which consists of portions of the fibrous scallops of the anterior and posterior cusps

name: secondary cartilage tissue
description: Cartilage tissue that is part of the exoskeleton, deposited adjacent to bone after bone formation.

name: hyperpallium
description: A pallial structure unique to avians.

name: digital vein
description: Any vein containing deoxygenated blood that is located in a finger or toe.

name: distal epiphysis of distal phalanx of manual digit 1
description: A distal epiphysis that is part of a distal phalanx of manual digit 1.

name: epiphysis of ulna
description: An epiphysis that is part of an ulna [Automatically generated definition].

name: mammalian cervical vertebra 4
description: The fourth of the seven cervical vertebrae[ncit,modified].

name: second phalanx
description: Second most proximal phalanx in manual or pedal digits.

name: hypothenar eminence
description: Hypothenar refers to a group of three muscles of the palm that control the motion of the little finger. The three muscles are: Abductor digiti minimi Flexor digiti minimi Opponens digiti minimi

name: proximal epiphysis of middle phalanx of manual digit 3
description: A proximal epiphysis that is part of a middle phalanx of manual digit 3 [Automatically generated definition].

name: left pulmonary artery
description: The pulmonary artery that supplies the left lung.

name: Wulst
description: A nuclear complex in the avian telecephalon dorsal to the DVR. The Wulst has telencephalic circuitry similar to the DVR.

name: calcaneofibular ligament
description: A skeletal ligament that connects the fibula to the calcaneus

name: deltoid
description: A muscle of shoulder which attaches to the scapula, clavicle and humerus.[FMA,generalized]

name: median raphe nucleus
description: The median raphe nucleus (or superior central nucleus) is composed of polygonal, fusiform and pyriform neurons and exists rostral to the nucleus raphe pontis. One trait of the MRN is its inhibition by lysergic acid diethylamide and psilocin, two serotonin antagonist hallucinogens. The inactivation of the nucleus centralis superior via LSD produces a dose dependent inactivation in the MRN, but not in the raphe pallidus[WP,unvetted].

name: remex feather
description: A flight feather located on the posterior side of the wing

name: tendon
description: Dense regular connective tissue that connects muscle to bone[VSAO].

name: dentary tooth 3
description: Dentary tooth that is the third tooth in a dentary tooth series, and positioned adjacent to the symphyseal tooth.

name: endoskeleton
description: Skeletal subdivision that undergoes indirect development and includes elements that develop as a replacement or substitution of other elements or tissues.

name: gill raker row
description: Anatomical cluster that consists of adjacent gill rakers constituting a row and is part of a ceratobranchial or epibranchial element of the branchial arches. Gill raker row is paired.

name: abductor pollicis longus
description: The Abductor pollicis longus lies immediately below the Supinator and is sometimes united with it. [WP,unvetted].

name: male urethral gland
description: any of the numerous small mucous-secreting glands located in the wall of the penile urethra

name: acinus of sebaceous gland
description: An acinus that is part of a sebaceous gland.

name: pectoral fin distal radial cartilage 3
description: pectoral fin distal radial 3 element that is composed of cartilage tissue.

name: parametrial fat pad
description: encapsulated adipose tissue associated with the extension of the subserous coat of the uterus laterally between the layers of the broad ligament

name: trachealis
description: A smooth muscle tissue that bridges the gap between free ends of C-shaped cartilages at the posterior border of the trachea, adjacent to the esophagus. A primary function of the trachealis is to constrict the windpipe, allowing for higher velocity of air in the windpipe during coughing[WP, modified].

name: pore
description: An anatomical space that is an opening, usually at the end of a canal or duct, on the surface of the integument or the lining of an internal anatomical space.

name: supraneural 2 cartilage
description: Postcranial axial cartilage located dorsal to vertebra 2.

name: precerebral fontanelle
description: The lack of chondrification of the anterior wall of the cranial cavity in front of the pineal foramen.....(Hanken and Hall)

name: posterior neuropore
description: The neuropore at the posterior (caudal) end of the neural tube.

name: excretory tube
description: A tube that is part of a excretory system.

name: pelvis connective tissue
description: A portion of connective tissue that is part of a pelvis [Automatically generated definition].

name: metanephric macula densa
description: The metanephric macula densa is an area of specialized cells in the distal tubule of the metanephros that makes contact with the vascular pole of the glomerulus[GO].

name: pulmonary part of lymphatic system
description: An organ system subdivision that is the part of the lymphoid system that includes the pulmonary lymphatic vessels.

name: gracile nucleus
description: Nucleus in the caudal medulla that receive projections primarily from ipsilateral dorsal root ganglion cells via the posterior column of the spinal cord

name: mandibular symphysis
description: A cartilaginous joint that connects left and right mandibles/dentary bones. Mandibular symphysis is unpaired[TAO,modified].

name: cloacal mucosa
description: A mucosa that is part of a cloaca [Automatically generated definition].

name: juxtaductal region of aortic arch
description: Area of aorta at the area of insertion to the ductus arteriosus.

name: metacarpal bone of digit 1
description: A metacarpal bone that distally_connected_to a proximal phalanx of manual digit 1.

name: perirhinal cortex of rodent of Burwell et al 1995
description: Cortical region surrounding the posterior rhinal sulcus in the rat, encompassing areas 35 and 36 in the rat. Rostraly, it abuts the posterior insular cortex

name: distal carpal bone 2 pre-cartilage condensation
description: A distal carpal bone 2 endochondral element that is composed primarily of a pre-cartilage condensation.

name: respiratory system artery
description: An artery that is part of a respiratory system [Automatically generated definition].

name: macula of saccule of membranous labyrinth
description: the oval neuroepithelial sensory receptor in the anterior wall of the saccule; hair cells of the neuroepithelium support the statoconial membrane and have terminal arborizations of vestibular nerve fibers around their bodies

name: dorsal nerve root of cervical spinal cord
description: A dorsal root of spinal cord that overlaps a cervical spinal cord.

name: obsolete predominantly gray regional part of pontine tegmentum
striated muscle tissue
description: Muscle tissue that contains fibers that are divided by transverse bands into striations.

name: chyle
description: Chyle is a bodily fluid consisting of a milky fluid consisting of lymph and emulsified fats; formed in the small intestine during digestion of ingested fats.

name: manual acropodium region
description: The segment of the manus that is distal to the metacarpal region and consists of the manual digits (fingers).

name: obsolete gastrula cell
description: A cell of the embryo in the early stage following the blastula, characterized by morphogenetic cell movements, cell differentiation, and the formation of the three germ layers.

name: basioccipital pre-cartilage condensation
description: A basioccipital endochondral element that is composed primarily of a pre-cartilage condensation.

name: mesenchyme of interdigital region of manus
description: An interdigital region mesenchyme that is part of a manus.

name: interincisive suture
description: median palatine suture of the palatine processes of the maxillary bones, and the median suture of the palatine bones

name: tunica adventitia of artery
description: A tunica adventitia that is part of a artery.

name: oropharyngeal papilla
description: Odontogenic papilla located along the jaws or pharyngeal skeleton.

name: rhombomere 7 roof plate
description: A rhombomere roof plate that is part of a rhombomere 7.

name: deciduous tooth
description: One of the first set of teeth in the growth development of humans and many other mammals[WP].

name: proximal phalanx of manual digit 4
description: A proximal phalanx that is part of a hand digit 4 [Automatically generated definition].

name: arch of atlas
description: A vertebral arch that is part of the first cervical vertebra

name: placentome of cotyledonary placenta
description: An anatomical group consisting of a placental caruncle and a placental cotyldeon, a placental unit in some mammals such as ruminants.

name: precentral fissure of cerebellum
description: Fissure between cerebellar lobules I and II.

name: hepatic artery
description: An artery that supplies the liver.

name: anterior chamber epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a anterior chamber of eyeball.

name: intercondylar fossa
description: The deep fossa between the femoral condyles in which the cruciate ligaments are attached. From Medilexicon.com

name: mesial region
description: The region of an anatomical structure, such as a tooth or jaw bone, facing the midline of the jaw.[PHENOSCAPE:WD]

name: obsolete regional part of medullary raphe nuclear complex
description: A regional part of brain that is part of a medullary raphe nuclear complex [Automatically generated definition].

name: crista ischii
description: Crest on the posterior side of the ischium, which may also extend to the posteroventral aspect of pubis.

name: inner medullary collecting duct
description: The inner medullary collecting duct is the portion of the collecting duct that lies in the renal inner medulla

name: subscapular vein
description: a vein formed by the confluence of the thoracodorsal and circumflex scapular veins and accompanying the subscapular artery to drain into the axillary vein.

name: electromotor division of oculomotor nuclear complex
description: A division of oculomotor nuclear complex that exists in organisms with electric organs which has axons terminating in the electric organs.

name: canal of Schlemm
description: The vascular structure encircling the anterior chamber of the eye, through which the aqueous humor is returned to the blood circulation

name: internal anal sphincter
description: the smooth muscle ring, formed by an increase of the circular muscle fibers of the rectum, situated at the upper end of the anal canal, internal to the outer voluntary external anal sphincter

name: lateral occipital sulcus
description: In the occipital lobe, the lateral occipital sulcus extends from behind forward, and divides the lateral surface of the occipital lobe into a superior and an inferior gyrus, which are continuous in front with the parietal and temporal lobes. [WP,unvetted].

name: skin of back
description: A zone of skin that is part of a back [Automatically generated definition].

name: embryonic autopod plate
description: The distal elements of the developing limb of vertebrates that will give rise to the autopod (e.g. manus, pes, paw)

name: secondary heart field
description: A specific region of the lateral mesoderm that will form the majority of the mesodermal component of the right ventricle, arterial pole (outflow tract) and venous pole (inflow tract).

name: pectoral fin radial bone
description: pectoral fin radial element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: basihyal element
description: Skeletal element that is median and is the anterior-most element of the ventral hyoid arch.

name: right lobe of thyroid gland
description: A lobe of thyroid gland that is in the right side of a thyroid gland.

name: preopercular sensory canal
description: Sensory canal lateral or ventral to and in close proximity with the otic and post-otic sensory canals at their union, and anteroventrally with the mandibular sensory canal. The preopercular sensory canal is bilaterally paired and associated with the preopercle bone.

name: placental labyrinth villous
description: The vascularized and branched structures arising from the rodent trophoblast-derived epithelium that allow an increase its surface area for the efficient exchange of nutrients and wastes between the maternal and fetal circulation

name: pericardial fat
description: The sum of epicardial and paracardial fat deposits.

name: metatarsophalangeal joint of pedal digit 3
description: A skeletal joint that connects a metatarsal bone and connects a distal phalanx of pedal digit 3.

name: labial disc
description: Imaginal disc that, in the adult, gives rise to the proboscis, including the prementum, prestomal cavity, labellum, labellar cap and pseudotrachea (Cohen, 1993).

name: pancreas secretion
description: A secretion that is part of a pancreas [Automatically generated definition].

name: superior rectus extraocular muscle
description: The superior rectus muscle is a muscle in the orbit. It is one of the extraocular muscles. It is innervated by the superior division of the oculomotor nerve (Cranial Nerve III). In the primary position (looking straight ahead), the superior rectus muscle's primary function is elevation, although it also contributes to intorsion and adduction.

name: epithelium of endolymphatic duct
description: An epithelium that is part of a endolymphatic duct [Automatically generated definition].

name: connecting stalk vasculature
description: A vasculature that is part of a connecting stalk.

name: antihelix
description: On the pinna, a curved prominence of cartilage, parallel with and in front of the helix, is called the antihelix, also known as the anthelix; this divides above into two crura, the crura antihelicis, between which is a triangular depression, the fossa triangularis.

name: pedal digit 3 phalanx endochondral element
description: A pedal digit 3 phalanx bone or its cartilage or pre-cartilage precursor.

name: outer medulla vasa recta descending limb
dentate gyrus of hippocampal formation
description: Part of the hippocampal formation forming a 'V' or 'U' shaped structure with the opening bounded by hippocampal area CA3. It consists of 3 layers from superficial to deep: molecular, granule cell and polymorphic or hilar layer.

name: pectoral fin bud mesenchyme
description: Mesechyme that is part of a pectoral fin bud.

name: pectoral appendage bud mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a pectoral appendage bud.

name: forelimb bud mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a forelimb bud.

name: lumen of jejunum
description: A anatomical space that is part of a jejunum.

name: vestibule of nasal cavity
description: A tube leading from the external naris to the nasal cavity.

name: villosities
description: Small hair or nipple like projection on the integument.

name: palatocerebral vein
description: Vein that drains the median palatocerebral vein into the optic vein. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: craniocervical region vein
description: A vein that is part of a craniocervical region.

name: ventromedial opening of posttemporal fossa
description: A third opening of the posttemporal fossa posteriorly located relative to the fossa. It is bordered completely by the epiocciptial, or by both the epioccipital and exoccipital.

name: obsolete xanthophore
description: A pigment cell derived from the neural crest. Contains cartenoid pigments in structures called pterinosomes or xanthosomes. This gives an appearance ranging from a golden yellow to orange and red.

name: bilaminar omphalopleure
description: A non-vascular omphalopleure that supports uptake and metabolism of nutrients.

name: odontoids
description: Toothlike processes found on the mandible of some anurans; can be formed by dentary or dentary + mentomeckelian bones; odontoids lack enamel and dentine present in true teeth.

name: parvocellular layer of dorsal nucleus of lateral geniculate body
aortic body
description: one of several small clusters of chemoreceptors, baroreceptors, and supporting cells located along the aortic arch.

name: webbed manus
description: A manus that has_part a webbed interdigital region.

name: oral siphon muscle
description: A muscle that is part of an oral siphon

name: echinopluteus larva
description: A planktonic and feeding larval form that possesses limb-like outgrowths bearing ciliated bands.

name: superior orbital fissure
description: The orbital fissure that is situated superiorly between the greater wing and the lesser wing of the sphenoid bone

name: olfactory cortex layer 1
description: Surface layer of the olfactory cortex that contains dendrites, fiber systems and a small number of neurons. It has been divided into a superficial part and a deep part.

name: pars distalis of adenohypophysis
description: The distal part of adenohypophysis: the part that makes up the main body of the gland.

name: middle gray layer of superior colliculus
malleus neck
description: The narrow contracted section of the malleus located between the head and the manubrium[MP].

name: pelvic region element
description: An organ or element that is part of the pelvic region. Examples: reproductive organs (in some organisms), urinary bladder, bones of the pelvis.

name: bile duct
description: Any of the ducts that form the biliary tree, carrying bile from the liver to the small intestine.

name: suprasphenoid
description: Endochondral ossification of the dorsomedial portion of the braincase.

name: dorsal ramus of spinal nerve
description: Branch of spinal nerve that innervates the epaxial muscles

name: obsolete predominantly gray medial regional part of thalamus
acrocoracoid process
description: Anatomical process located in the proximal region of the coracoid in avian theropods, that is hook-shaped. [NI]

name: perirenal fat
description: The adipose capsule of kidney (or perinephric fat or perirenal fat) is a structure between the renal fascia and renal capsule, and may be regarded as a part of the latter. A different structure, the pararenal fat, is the adipose tissue superficial to the renal fascia.

name: obsolete regional part of cochlear nuclear complex
description: A regional part of brain that is part of a cochlear nuclear complex [Automatically generated definition].

name: nail of pedal digit 3
description: A nail that is part of a pedal digit 3.

name: ulnare
description: The postaxial bone of the proximal carpal region. Found in close approximation to the ulna, often in articulation[PHENOSCAPE:ad].

name: pupillary membrane
description: The pupillary membrane in mammals exists in the fetus as a source of blood supply for the lens. It normally atrophies from the time of birth to the age of four to eight weeks.

name: head of radius
description: The head of the radius has a cylindrical form, and on its upper surface is a shallow cup or fovea for articulation with the capitulum (or capitellum) of the humerus. The circumference of the head is smooth; it is broad medially where it articulates with the radial notch of the ulna, narrow in the rest of its extent, which is embraced by the annular ligament. The deepest point in the fovea is not axi-symmetric with the long axis of the radius, creating a cam effect during pronation and supination[WP].

name: digestive tract epithelium
description: An epithelium that lines the lumen of the digestive tract.

name: insect thorax
description: The main middle section of the insect body comprising three thoracic rings: the pro-, the meso- and the metathoraces which are more or less well fused and cask-like sometimes having on the upper lateral part one of two pairs of wings, while on the ventrolateral part each thoracic ring bears a pair of legs.

name: surface of prostate
description: The external portion of the prostate including the anterior, inferolateral, lateral and posterior surfaces.

name: paired fin lepidotrichium
description: Lepidotrichium that is part of a paired fin.

name: Sylvian cistern
description: The subarachnoid space associated with the lateral cerebral sulcus (Sylvian fissure); contains the M1 segment of the middle cerebral artery and the origin of lenticulostriate arteries, and proximal parts of the middle cerebral artery

name: epibranchial 2 cartilage
description: Epibranchial cartilage that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with ceratobranchial 2 cartilage or bone.

name: posterolateral supplementary element
description: A muscle slip arising from the ventral surface of the mandible by means of the ligament near the site of mandibular articulation. The fibers pass anteromedially and attach upon the ventral surfaces of the principal element of the m. intermandibularis (Tyler, 1971).

name: hinge joint
description: A joint that allows motion around an axis.

name: lumen of epithelial sac
description: The space within an epithelial sphere.

name: presumptive pronephric mesoderm
description: A presumptive structure that has the potential to develop into a pronephric mesoderm.

name: precordial region
description: A subdivision of the trunk that is comprised of the epigastrium and the anterior lower thorax.

name: mitral valve cusp
description: The two fibrous components and associated flaps of the mitral valve

name: dense mesenchyme tissue
description: Mesenchyme with little extracellular matrix.

name: posterior horn lateral ventricle
description: Part of the lateral ventricle that extends posteriorly into the occipital lobe.

name: forelimb digital vein
description: A digital vein that is part of a forelimb.

name: distal epiphysis of distal phalanx of manual digit 2
description: A distal epiphysis that is part of a distal phalanx of manual digit 2.

name: epiphysis of phalanx of manus
description: An epiphysis that is part of a phalanx of a manus [Automatically generated definition].

name: male breast
description: A breast that is part of a male organism.

name: arthropod sternum
description: ventral portion of a segment of an arthropod thorax or abdomen. In insects, the sterna are usually single, large sclerites, and external. However, they can sometimes be divided in two or more, in which case the subunits are called sternites, and may also be modified on the terminal abdominal segments so as to form part of the functional genitalia, in which case they are frequently reduced in size and development, and may become internalized and/or membranous.

name: ligamentous replacement element
description: Replacement element that forms as a replacement of a ligament.

name: mammalian cervical vertebra 5
description: The fifth of the seven cervical vertebrae[ncit,modified].

name: parasternal process
description: Posterior projection of the interclavicle that extends betwen and sometimes beyond the clavicles. [AD]

name: proximal epiphysis of middle phalanx of manual digit 4
description: A proximal epiphysis that is part of a middle phalanx of manual digit 4 [Automatically generated definition].

name: facial vein
description: The anterior facial vein (facial vein) commences at the side of the root of the nose, and is a direct continuation of the angular vein where it also receives a small nasal branch. It lies behind the facial artery and follows a less tortuous course. It receives blood from the external palatine vein before it either joins the anterior branch of the retromandibular vein to form the common facial vein, or drains directly into the internal jugular vein. [WP,unvetted].

name: Westoll line
description: More or less concentric lines of discontinuity in the cosmine of Dipnoi, probably due to cyclic resorption and redeposition during growth occurring on the bases of individual scales and also as large structures between headshield plates.[Fishbase]

name: medial ligament of ankle joint
description: A skeletal ligament that connects a tibia and connects a tarsal skeleton.

name: infraspinatus muscle
description: The infraspinatus muscle is a thick triangular muscle, which occupies the chief part of the infraspinatous fossa. The infraspinatus is a muscle of the rotator cuff. [WP,unvetted].

name: dorsal longitudinal fasciculus of midbrain
description: Part of dorsal longitudinal fasciculus located in the midbrain tegmentum

name: atlanto-occipital joint
description: The Atlanto-occipital joint (articulation between the atlas and the occipital bone) consists of a pair of condyloid joints. The atlanto-occipital joint is a synovial joint. The ligaments connecting the bones are: Two Articular capsules; Posterior atlanto√∂ccipital membrane; Anterior atlanto√∂ccipital membrane; Lateral atlanto√∂ccipital

name: primary remex feather
description: A remex feather that is connected to the manus

name: dorsal root ganglion
description: Sensory ganglia located on the dorsal spinal roots within the vertebral column. The spinal ganglion cells are pseudounipolar. The single primary branch bifurcates sending a peripheral process to carry sensory information from the periphery and a central branch which relays that information to the spinal cord or brain. (MSH) * ganglion found on the posterior root of each spinal nerve, composed of the unipolar nerve cell bodies of the sensory neurons of the nerve. (CSP)

name: thenar muscle
description: Any of the muscles of the thenar eminence, a raised fleshy area on the palm of the hand near the base of the thumb.

name: fused hypural 1 and 2
description: Single hypural element formed from the fusion of hypural 1 and 2.

name: endochondral element
description: A skeletal element that has the potential to participate in endochondral ossification, and may participate in intramembranous ossification.

name: acinus of parotid gland
description: An acinus that is part of a parotid gland.

name: omental fat pad
description: encapsulated adipose tissue associated with the fold of peritoneal tissue that extends from the stomach to the posterior abdominal wall after associating with the transverse colon

name: interthalamic adhesion
description: The medial surface of the thalamus constitutes the upper part of the lateral wall of the third ventricle, and is connected to the corresponding surface of the opposite thalamus by a flattened gray band, the Interthalamic adhesion (massa intermedia, middle commissure, gray commissure). In non-human mammals it is a large structure. In humans this mass averages about 1 cm in length in its antero-posterior diameter. It sometimes consists of two parts and occasionally is absent. The interthalamic adhesion is found in 70-80% of humans. It is present more often in females and larger than in males by an average of 53 percent. . When absent in development, no noticeable deficit has been observed. It contains nerve cells and nerve fibers; a few of the latter may cross the middle line, but most of them pass toward the middle line and then curve lateralward on the same side.

name: torus pylorus
description: A fleshy protuberance at the pylorus of some species such as ruminants and pigs, that projects into the lumen of the pyloric canal

name: caudal fin actinotrichium
description: Actinotrichium that is part of the caudal fin skeleton.

name: prismatic cartilage
description: cartilage arranged into tesserae, blocks of calcified cartilage that fit together as tiles on a floor form a mosaic. Found only in chondrichthyans. Reference: A. Peter Klimley. 2013. The Biology of Sharks and Rays. University of Chicago Press.

name: pes connective tissue
description: A portion of connective tissue that is part of a foot [Automatically generated definition].

name: metanephric prebend segment
description: The metanephric prebend segment is a part of the metanephric descending thin limb that lies before the bend and exhibits permeabilities characteristic of the ascending limb, especially negligible water permeability[GO].

name: pulmonary lymphatic vessel
description: A lymphatic vessel that is part of a lung.

name: area postrema
description: A small, rounded eminence on each side of the fourth ventricle, which receives nerve fibers from the solitary nucleus , spinal cord, and adjacent areas of the medulla. The area postrema lies outside the blood-brain barrier and its functions include acting as an emetic chemoreceptor.

name: medial umbilical ligament
description: The medial umbilical ligament is a paired structure found in human anatomy. It is on the deep surface of the anterior abdominal wall, and is covered by the medial umbilical folds.

name: forelimb stylopod
description: The part of the forelimb between pectoral region and the elbow, corresponding to the humerus.

name: mucus body coating
description: A coating of mucus that is produced by the skin and covers all or most of the body of an animal.

name: metacarpal bone of digit 2
description: A metacarpal bone that distally_connected_to a proximal phalanx of manual digit 2.

name: cartilaginous joint
description: Nonsynovial joint in which the articulating bones or cartilages are connected by cartilage. Examples: Spheno-occipital synchondrosis, first sternocostal joint, pubic symphysis.[FMA]

name: endoderm of foregut-midgut junction
description: An endoderm that is part of a foregut-midgut junction.

name: cerebellum
description: Part of the metencephalon that lies in the posterior cranial fossa behind the brain stem. It is concerned with the coordination of movement[MESH]. A large dorsally projecting part of the brain concerned especially with the coordination of muscles and the maintenance of bodily equilibrium, situated between the brain stem and the back of the cerebrum , and formed in humans of two lateral lobes and a median lobe[BTO]. Brain structure derived from the anterior hindbrain, and perhaps including posterior midbrain. The cerebellum plays a role in somatic motor function, the control of muscle tone, and balance[ZFA].

name: inferior prenasal cartilage
description: Elongate cartilage that extends anteroventrally from the solum nasi to abut the ventral portion of the posterior aspect of the alary process of the premaxilla. It was first described by Wiedersheim in 1876.

name: mucus
description: Mucus is a bodily fluid consisting of a slippery secretion of the lining of the mucous membranes in the body. It is a viscous colloid containing antiseptic enzymes (such as lysozyme) and immunoglobulins. Mucus is produced by goblet cells in the mucous membranes that cover the surfaces of the membranes. It is made up of mucins and inorganic salts suspended in water.

name: pedal acropodium region
description: The segment of the pes that is distal to the metatarsal region and consists of the pedal digits (toes).

name: obsolete blastoderm cell
description: An undifferentiated cell produced by early cleavages of the fertilized egg (zygote).

name: craniofacial suture
description: Any suture between cranial and/or facial bones.

name: mesenchyme of interdigital region of pes
description: An interdigital region mesenchyme that is part of a pes.

name: vestibular canal
description: The division of the spiral canal of the cochlea lying above the spiral lamina and the vestibular membrane.

name: tusk
description: A calcareous tooth that is elongated and protrudes from the mouth.

name: palatomaxillary suture
description: line of union, in the floor of the orbit, between the orbital process of the palatine bone and the orbital surface of the maxilla.

name: tunica adventitia of vein
description: A tunica adventitia that is part of a vein.

name: acellular membrane
description: A acellular anatomical structure that is the bounding layer of a anatomical structure.

name: rhombomere 8 floor plate
description: A rhombomere floor plate that is part of a rhombomere 8.

name: primary dentition
description: The set of teeth first in order or time of development that will be replaced by permanent dentition upon their loss.

name: proximal phalanx of manual digit 5
description: A proximal phalanx that is part of a hand digit 5 [Automatically generated definition].

name: pelvic fin distal radial cartilage 2
description: pelvic fin distal radial 2 element that is composed of cartilage tissue.

name: obsolete predominantly gray anterior regional part of thalamus
X bone
description: The x bone is a detached neural spine anterior to the neural spine of preural centrum 2.

name: dorsal hypothalamic nucleus
description: A nerve cell nucleus situated in the dorsal portion of the intermediate hypothalamic region.

name: gluteus maximus
description: The largest and most superficial of the three gluteal muscles [WP,unvetted].

name: anterior tubercle of transverse process of cervical vertebra
description: The anterior arch forms about one-fifth of the ring: its anterior surface is convex, and presents at its center the anterior tubercle for the attachment of the Longus colli muscles.

name: placental caruncle
description: An oval or round thickening in the uterine mucosa resulting from proliferation of subepithelial connective tissue, in the maternal side of the placentome.

name: splenic artery
description: An artery that supplies the spleen.

name: right lung cranial lobe epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a upper lobe of right lung.

name: obsolete predominantly gray regional part of thalamus
intermediate spine
description: Spine ventrally located on the body and not part of the pectoral, pelvic or anal fins.

name: obsolete regional part of medulla oblongata
description: A regional part of brain that is part of a medulla oblongata [Automatically generated definition].

name: spina pelvis posterior
description: Small, rounded process on the anterodorsal margin of the ischium, just posterior to the area of articulation with the ilium.

name: extraembryonic vascular system
description: A vascular system that overlaps a umbilical cord and is part of a entire extraembryonic component.

name: long descending thin limb bend
description: The long descending thin limb bend is a part of the descending thin limb of a long nephron that lies beyond the prebend segment

name: pectoral girdle region
description: An organism subdivision that includes the pectoral girdle skeleton and associated soft tissue. Note that this includes both the skeletal elements and associated tissues (integument, muscle, etc). Examples: There are only two instances in an organism, right and left pectoral girdle regions.

name: limb of internal capsule of telencephalon
intralingual sulcus
description: A groove located within the boundaries of the lingual gyrus in the human. Identified by dissection, it is oriented parallel to the inferior margin of the occipital lobe ( Ono-1990; Duvernoy-1992 ).

name: adductor pollicis muscle of prepollex
description: Originates from the distal carpal 5-4-3 and inserts on the palmar prepollex.

name: head of pancreas
description: The head of pancreas is a portion of the pancreas that is lodged within the curve of the duodenum, and is flattened anteriorly (from before). The other parts of the pancreas are the body and the tail. Its upper border is overlapped by the superior part of the duodenum and its lower overlaps the horizontal part; its right and left borders overlap in front, and insinuate themselves behind, the descending and ascending parts of the duodenum respectively. [WP,unvetted].

name: male bulbospongiosus muscle
description: A bulbospongiosus muscle that is part of a male reproductive system.

name: conducting tissue of heart
description: Any portion of cardiac muscle tissue that is part of the conducting system of heart or the Purkinje fibers.

name: pectoral fin proximal radial bone
description: pectoral fin proximal radial element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: basihyal cartilage
description: Pharyngeal arch cartilage that is median and is the anterior-most cartilage of the ventral hyoid arch.

name: mandibular sensory canal
description: Sensory canal anterior and ventral to and in close proximity with the preoperculo-mandibular sensory canal. The mandible sensory canal is bilaterally paired and associated with the angular and dentary bones.

name: subpretectal complex of Aves
description: A nuclear complex in the ventral pretectal region.

name: placenta intervillous maternal lacunae
description: The spaces of the placenta occupied by maternal blood, into which the fetal labyrinth villi project

name: otic pit
description: the pair of depressions of thickened otic placode epithelium, that further develops into the otic vesicles

name: paracardial fat
description: Fat deposits in the mediastinum outside the parietal pericardium .

name: right renal medulla interstitium
description: A renal medulla interstitium that is part of a right kidney.

name: ocular adnexa
description: The parts of the orbital region that are outside of the the eyeball, including the lacrimal apparatus, the extraocular muscles and the eyelids, eyelashes, eyebrows and the conjunctiva

name: clypeo-labral disc
description: Imaginal disc that in the adults gives rise to the labrum, anterior and posterior cibarial plates, fish trap bristles, epipharyngeal sclerite and clypeus (Cohen, 1993).

name: prostate gland secretion
description: A bodily secretion that is produced by the prostate gland.

name: obsolete basipterygium cartilage
description: basipterygium element that is composed of cartilage tissue.

name: epithelium of ductus reuniens
description: An epithelium that is part of a ductus reuniens [Automatically generated definition].

name: adipose tissue of abdominal region
description: Adipose tissue that is located in the abdominal region. This includes any subcutaneous fat, visceral fat or encapsulated adipose tissue depots.

name: antitragus
description: The antitragus is a feature of human ear anatomy. It is a small tubercle that points anteriorly. It is separated from the tragus by the intertragic notch.

name: peripheral region of retina
description: Anatomical region comprising the peripheral part of the retina.

name: obsolete predominantly gray regional part of amygdala
pedal digit 4 phalanx endochondral element
description: A pedal digit 4 phalanx bone or its cartilage or pre-cartilage precursor.

name: choroid plexus
description: A network formed by blood vessels and the tela choroidea which secretes CSF into the ventricular spaces.

name: mesenchyme of mandible
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a developing mandible [Automatically generated definition].

name: tooth of palatine bone
description: A tooth that is attached to a palatine bone.

name: obsolete CiD
description: A interneuron of the spinal cord with an ipsilateral axon that extends ventral to the Mauthner axon then turns dorsally and caudally and sometimes has a minor ascending branch.

name: epithelium of superior semicircular canal
description: An epithelium that is part of an anterior semicircular canal [Automatically generated definition].

name: quadratoethmoid process
description: Process that projects from anterior margin of commissure as site of attachment for quadratoethmoid ligament.

name: limb paddle
description: A transient developing limb structure that develops from the limb bud; it is a dorsoventral flattening of the limb bud structure and develops into the foot plate

name: alary cartilage
description: Paired, cup-shaped cartilage that are dorsal to the septomaxillae and anterior to the oblique cartilage. The anterior, convex face of each alary cartilage is synchondrotically fused to the superior prenasal cartilage and the ventral edge is fused to the superior margin of the crista intermedia.

name: entire embryonic mesenchyme
description: Sum total of mesenchyme in the embryo.

name: bony plate series
description: Anatomical cluster that consists of more than one bony plate in an individual.

name: radiale
description: Endochondral proximal carpal bone articulating with the radius.

name: obsolete podocyte
description: Cell type that is a component of the glomus.

name: trilaminar omphalopleure
description: A vascular omphalopleure that is important for respiration.

name: gut wall
description: The wall of the digestive tract. This encompasses all parts of the digestive tract with the exception of the lumen (cavity).

name: jugular body
description: A nonchromaffin paraganglion located in the wall of the jugular bulb.

name: subbrachial nucleus of mouse of Franklin and Paxinos 2008
webbed pes
description: A pes that has_part a webbed interdigital region.

name: CA3 stratum lacunosum moleculare
description: Part of stratum lacunosum-moleculare in area CA3. It is bounded by the stratum lacunosum-moleculare of CA2 and CA1. It is bounded superficially by the pial surface and deep by the CA3 stratum radiatum. It is continuous with the stratum lacunosum-moleculare of CA2.

name: tentorial sinus
description: An unpaired venous dural sinus that receives blood from the superior cerebellar veins and inferior sagittal sinus and drains into the confluence of sinuses.

name: olfactory cortex layer 2
description: Middle layer of olfactory cortex lying deep to layer 1 and superficial to layer 3, characterized by a compact layer of cell bodies. It can be divided into a superficial part and a deep part.

name: CA2 stratum radiatum
description: Part of stratum radiatum in area CA2, lying superficial to the pyramidal cell layer and deep to CA2 stratum lacunosum-moleculare, continuous with the stratum radiatum of CA1 and CA3.

name: vascular cord
description: The vascular cord is the primordial vasculature that will develop into blood vessels by the process of tubulogenesis[GO]. The vascular cord is composed of angioblast or vascular endothelial cells in a solid linear mass called a cord. The cord then undergoes tubulogenesis to form the lumen of the vessels[ZFA].

name: deep gray layer of superior colliculus
Rathke's pouch
description: A pouch of ectoderm that grows out from the upper surface of the embryonic stomodeum and gives rise to the anterior and intermediate lobes of the pituitary gland[MP]. In embryogenesis, Rathke's pouch is a depression in the roof of the developing mouth in front of the buccopharyngeal membrane. It gives rise to the anterior pituitary (adenohypophysis), a part of the endocrine system[WP].

name: talus
description: A proximal tarsal bone resulting from fusion of intermedium and fibulare.

name: accessory lacrimal gland
description: Serous gland with distended lumen. It includes the gland of Krause in the lacrimal sac and the gland of Wolfring on the inner surface of the upper eyelid. (NCI)

name: aponeurosis palmaris
description: The palmar aponeurosis is a fibrotendinous complex that functions as the tendinous extension of the palmaris longus, when present, and as a strong stabilizing structure for the palmar skin of the hand. It has five longitudinal slips that project into the base of each digit and a deeper transverse portion that crosses the palm at the proximal end of the metacarpals bones (from Wikipedia).

name: sublingual ganglion
description: the small parasympathetic ganglion found anterior to the submandibular gland that provides postsynaptic fibers to the sublingual gland

name: preoptic periventricular nucleus
description: The preoptic periventricular nucleus is located along the midline and is medial to the medial preoptic nucleus.[WP,unvetted].

name: nail of pedal digit 4
description: A nail that is part of a pedal digit 4.

name: dorsal anterior lateral line nerve
description: Nerve fibers originating from the dorsal anterior lateral line ganglion. These rami innervate the otic, supraorbital, and infraorbital neuromasts.

name: preorbital process of the pars facialis of the maxilla
adipose tissue
description: Portion of connective tissue composed of adipocytes enmeshed in areolar tissue

name: thoracic segment
description: Any segment (UBERON:6000003) that is part of some thorax (UBERON:6000015).

name: obsolete joint connecting hardened body parts
dorsolateral prefrontal cortex
description: The dorsolateral prefrontal cortex (DL-PFC or DLPFC), according to a more restricted definition, is roughly equivalent to Brodmann areas 9 and 46.[1] According to a broader definition DL-PFC consists of the lateral portions of Brodmann areas 9 - 12, of areas 45, 46, and the superior part of area 47.[2] These regions mainly receive their blood supply from the middle cerebral artery. With respect to neurotransmitter systems, there is evidence that dopamine plays a particularly important role in DL-PFC.[2]DL-PFC is connected to the orbitofrontal cortex, and to a variety of brain areas, which include the thalamus, parts of the basal ganglia (the dorsal caudate nucleus), the hippocampus, and primary and secondary association areas of neocortex, including posterior temporal, parietal, and occipital areas

name: facial skeleton
description: Subdivision of skull that consists of the facial bones.

name: epibranchial 4 cartilage
description: Epibranchial cartilage that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with ceratobranchial 4 cartilage or bone.

name: pseudodentary
description: Compound bone of adult Gymnophiona, consisting of dentary, coronoid and mentomeckelian.

name: apical supplementary element
description: A muscle slip arising from the lingual surface of the mandible on each side of the m. submentalis. The fibers pass posteromedially and attach upon the median raphe of the principal element (Tyler, 1971).

name: deep middle cerebral vein
description: The blood vessel that receives deoxygenated blood from the insula and gyri and drains into the basal vein of Rosenthal deep in the lateral sulcus.

name: iliocostalis lumborum
description: The iliocostalis lumborum (iliocostalis muscle; sacrolumbalis muscle) is inserted, by six or seven flattened tendons, into the inferior borders of the angles of the lower six or seven ribs.

name: kinethmoid bone
description: Sesamoid bone located in the premaxillary-ethmoid ligament, between the mesethmoid and the premaxilla. The kinethmoid is an unpaired median bone.

name: pronephric proximal convoluted tubule
description: A proximal convoluted tubule that is part of a pronephros.

name: adult procephalic segment
description: Any procephalic segment (UBERON:6000007) that is part of some adult head (UBERON:6003007).

name: interdigital region between pedal digits 2 and 3
description: An interdigital region that adjacent_to a pedal digit 2 and adjacent_to a pedal digit 3.

name: tricuspid valve anulus
description: The fibrous ring of the tricuspid valve that attaches the cusps of tricuspid valve to the heart, and which consists of portions of the fibrous scallops of the anterior cusp (infundibular cusp), the posterior cusp (marginal cusp), and the septal cusp (medial cusp)

name: mineralized cartilage tissue
description: Cartilage tissue that is mineralized.

name: hindlimb digital vein
description: A digital vein that is part of a hindlimb [Automatically generated definition].

name: distal epiphysis of distal phalanx of manual digit 3
description: A distal epiphysis that is part of a distal phalanx of manual digit 3.

name: epiphysis of fibula
description: An epiphysis that is part of a fibula [Automatically generated definition].

name: arthropod tibia
description: A section of the arthropod leg.

name: simian shelf
description: A bony buttress on the inner surface of the foremost part of the ape mandible, functioning to reinforce the mandible.

name: pair of lungs
description: The pair of anatomical structures comprised of a left lung and right lung.

name: mammalian cervical vertebra 6
description: The sixth of the seven cervical vertebrae[ncit,modified].

name: minor salivary gland
description: One of the smaller, largely mucus-secreting, exocrine glands of the oral cavity, consisting of the labial, buccal, molar, lingual, and palatine glands[MP].

name: pectoral articular facet
description: Facet of scapulocoracoid with which the pectoral fin radial(s) articulates. Facet of scapulocoracoid with which the pectoral fin radial(s) articulates. Based on Goujet and Young (1995). [PHENOSCAPE:pm]

name: proximal epiphysis of middle phalanx of manual digit 5
description: A proximal epiphysis that is part of a middle phalanx of manual digit 5 [Automatically generated definition].

name: supraorbital vein
description: The supraorbital vein begins on the forehead where it communicates with the frontal branch of the superficial temporal vein. It runs downward superficial to the Frontalis muscle, and joins the frontal vein at the medial angle of the orbit to form the angular vein. Previous to its junction with the frontal vein, it sends through the supraorbital notch into the orbit a branch which communicates with the ophthalmic vein; as this vessel passes through the notch, it receives the frontal diploic vein through a foramen at the bottom of the notch. The areas drained by this vessel are the forehead, eyebrow and upper eyelid. [WP,unvetted].

name: epichordal radial
description: Radial found above the vertebral column.[PHENOSCAPE:AD]

name: epiphysis of phalanx of pes
description: An epiphysis that is part of a phalanx of a pes [Automatically generated definition].

name: teres major muscle
description: Teres major is a muscle of the upper limb and one of six scapulohumeral muscles. It is a thick but somewhat flattened muscle. [WP,unvetted].

name: cloacal sphincter
description: A sphincter muscle that is part of a cloaca.

name: supraauricular point
description: A craniometric point on the posterior root of the zygomatic process of the temporal bone directly above the auricular point.

name: secondary remex feather
description: A remex feather that is connected to the ulna.

name: inter-coracoid joint
description: Joint between the right and left coracoid bones of the pectoral girdle.

name: tarsus pre-cartilage condensation
description: A pre-cartilage condensation that has the potential to develop into a tarsal bone.

name: ganglion
description: A biological tissue mass, most commonly a mass of nerve cell bodies.

name: nail
description: A horn-like keratin structure covering the dorsal aspect of the terminal phalanges of fingers and toes[WP].

name: lateral occipital foramen
description: Foramen that has the exoccipital as the anterior and dorsal rim. The occipital forms the anterior rim during early development. [database_cross_reference: GOC:cvs][database_cross_reference: ORCiD:0000-0002-2244-7917][database_cross_reference: ZFIN:ZDB-PUB-961014-192]

name: dermal skeleton
description: Skeletal subdivision that undergoes direct development and includes elements that either develop in association with the basement membrane of the ectoderm or are homologous with such elements; includes dermatocranium, components of the appendicular skeleton, teeth and tooth-like elements of the oropharynx, and integumentary elements.

name: brachiocephalic artery
description: the short first aortic arch branch and divides into the right subclavian artery and the right common carotid artery

name: protuberance
description: A roughly circular bulge in a surface.

name: obsolete nucleus motorius of nervi vagi
barrel cortex
description: One of the discrete functional units of the somatosensory cortex that processes tactile information derived from the vibrissae.

name: hypoglossal canal
description: The hypoglossal canal is a bony canal in the occipital bone of the skull.

name: ampullary organ
description: Organ that consists of receptor cells located within an epidermal invagination and functions as an electroreceptor.

name: quadrate condyle
description: The convex articular surface on the qudrate, part of the craniomandibular joint.

name: digit 6 digitopodial skeleton
description: A subdivision of the skeleton of the autopod consisting of the phalanges of digit 6 plus the associated metapodial element.

name: ankle connective tissue
description: A portion of connective tissue that is part of an ankle [Automatically generated definition].

name: metanephric proximal convoluted tubule
description: The metanephric proximal convoluted tubule is the most proximal portion of the metanephric proximal tubule and extends from the metanephric glomerular capsule to the metanephric proximal straight tubule[GO].

name: inferior cerebellar peduncle
description: Regional part of medullary white matter (according to Neuronames) primarily found at the level of the open medulla, consisting of a large bundle of fibers projecting to and projecting from the cerebellum. The icp is continuous with the dorsal spinocerebellar tract and also contains a large number of fibers originating in the inferior olivary complex (MM).

name: submucosa of cloaca
description: A submucosa that is part of a cloaca [Automatically generated definition].

name: mucus cocoon
description: A mucous covering produced nocturnally by some fish that is used to envelope the whole animal.

name: metacarpal bone of digit 3
description: A metacarpal bone that distally_connected_to a proximal phalanx of manual digit 3[Automatically generated definition].

name: centro-posterior medial synaptic neuropil domain
description: A synaptic neuropil domain of the larval brain located posterior to the medial lobe of the mushroom body. It is separated from the centro-lateral compartment by the peduncle, and from the centro-posterior intermediate compartment by the antenno-cerebral tract to which it is connected via a branch.

name: macula of utricle of membranous labyrinth
description: the neuroepithelial sensory receptor in the inferolateral wall of the utricle; hair cells of the neuroepithelium support the statoconial membrane and have terminal arborizations of vestibular nerve fibers around their bodies; normally sensitive to linear acceleration in the longitudinal axis of the body and to gravitational influences

name: distal segment of digit
description: A segment of a digit containing the distal phalanx, and overlapping the distal interphalangeal joint[CJM]. The digit tip is derived from multiple and distinct embryonic origins, and includes the distal bone with associated marrow cavity and haematopoietic cells, ventral (flexor) and dorsal (extensor) tendons, sweat glands with myoepithelial and luminal secreting cells and associated neurons for innervation, dermis with resident melanocytes and dendritic cells, mesenchyme with resident fibroblasts, skin epidermis with hair follicles, a nail organ composed of six specific parts (the root, nail bed, nail plate, eponychium (cuticle), perionychium and hyponychium).

name: substantia nigra
description: Predominantly gray matter midbrain structure lying dorsal to the crus cerebri and ventral to the midbrain tegmentum. It is divided into a dorsal, cellularly compact region known as the pars compacta and a more ventrally located, containing more loosely packed cells, the pars reticulata. The most lateral region of the reticulata is identified as the pars lateralis (MM).

name: venous dural sinus
description: A venous channel found between layers of dura mater in the brain. Receives blood from internal and external veins of the brain, receive cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) from the subarachnoid space, and ultimately empty into the internal jugular vein.

name: interstitial fluid
description: Interstitial fluid is a bodily fluid consisting of a solution which bathes and surrounds the cells of multicellular animals. It is the main component of the extracellular fluid, which also includes plasma and transcellular fluid.

name: digitopodium bone
description: A bone that is part of a the digitopodium skeleton - i.e. the acropodial skeleton or the metapodial skeleton.

name: obsolete ectodermal cell
description: A cell of the outer of the three germ layers of the embryo.

name: capsular process
description: Narrow process of the skeletal support that projects forward.

name: facial suture
description: Any suture between facial bones.

name: left lung associated mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a developing left lung.

name: ectoplacental cavity
description: closed space within the ectoplacental cone, formed by the fusion of the parts of the amniotic fold that separate it from the amniotic cavity[MP]. a developmental cavity that exists in some mammals and is derived by division of the proamniotic space; it is further removed from the embryo than the amniotic cavity in some mammals

name: palatoethmoidal suture
description: A line of junction of the orbital process of the palatine bone and the orbital plate of the ethmoid.

name: tunica intima of vein
description: A tunica intima that is part of a vein.

name: dorsal fin proximal radial element
description: Rod-like internal median skeletal support elements of the dorsal fin, which articulate with the distal radial elements.

name: hair inner root sheath
description: A multilayered tube composed of terminally differentiated hair follicle keratinocytes that is surrounded by the outer root sheath; the layers of the inner root sheath include the companion layer, Henle's layer, Huxley's layer and the inner root sheath cuticle[MP].

name: opercular part of inferior frontal gyrus
description: Component of the inferior frontal gyrus.defined as the first gyrus from the precentral gyrus.

name: rhombomere 8 lateral wall
description: A rhombomere lateral wall that is part of a rhombomere 8.

name: cingulum of lower jaw molar
description: A ridge that girdles the base of a lower molar tooth

name: proximal phalanx of pedal digit 1
description: A proximal phalanx that is part of a pedal digit 1 [Automatically generated definition].

name: pelvic fin distal radial cartilage 3
description: pelvic fin distal radial 3 element that is composed of cartilage tissue.

name: obsolete regional part of cervical spinal cord gray matter
Y bone
description: The y bone is a detached neural spine anterior to the haemal spines of preural centrum 2.

name: gluteus medius
description: One of three gluteal muscles, is a broad, thick, radiating muscle, situated on the outer surface of the pelvis. Its posterior third is covered by the gluteus maximus, its anterior two-thirds by the gluteal aponeurosis, which separates it from the superficial fascia and integument. [WP,unvetted].

name: posterior tubercle of transverse process of cervical vertebra
description: The posterior arch of a cervical vertebra forms about two-fifths of the circumference of the ring: it ends behind in the posterior tubercle, which is the rudiment of a spinous process and gives origin to the Recti capitis posteriores minores. The diminutive size of this process prevents any interference with the movements between the atlas and the skull.

name: obsolete predominantly white regional part of superior olivary complex
endostylar duct
description: A duct in ammocetes (larval lamprey) that is reputed to connect the endostylar lumen to the pharyngeal lumen. Resembles the thyroglossal duct.

name: manual digit 2 plus metapodial segment
description: A subdivision of the autopod consisting of manual digit 2 plus the region incorporating a single metapodial element. These segments are typically repeated along the pre-axiom to post-axial axis.

name: inferior pancreaticoduodenal artery
description: The inferior pancreaticoduodenal artery is a branch of the superior mesenteric artery or from its first intestinal branch, opposite the upper border of the inferior part of the duodenum.
