description: The muscles that move the eye. Included in this group are the medial rectus, lateral rectus, superior rectus, inferior rectus, inferior oblique, superior oblique, musculus orbitalis, and levator palpebrae superioris.

name: respiratory system connective tissue
description: A portion of connective tissue that is part of a respiratory system [Automatically generated definition].

name: obsolete regional part of lateral amygdaloid nucleus
mesentery of hindgut
description: A mesentery that is part of a hindgut [Automatically generated definition].

name: intestinal-cloacal junction
description: The juncture where the intestine empties into the cloaca.

name: distal visceral endoderm
description: precursors of the anterior visceral endoderm that arises at the distal tip of the embryo[MP]

name: pes nerve
description: A nerve that is part of a foot [Automatically generated definition].

name: central nervous system white matter layer
description: A layer of of the central nervous system that is composed of white matter.

name: common crus of semicircular duct
description: A nonampullary end of the superior or posterior semicircular ducts.

name: simple cuboidal epithelium
description: Unilaminar epithelium that consists of a single layer of cuboidal cells.

name: pulmonary artery
description: An artery that carries deoxygenated blood from heart to the lungs. They are the only arteries (other than umbilical arteries in the fetus) that carry deoxygenated blood..

name: submucosa of ascending colon
description: A submucosa that is part of an ascending colon [Automatically generated definition].

name: posterior mesenteric artery
description: Unpaired artery departing from dorsal aorta that typically supplies the large intestine

name: fused metatarsal bones 3 and 4
description: An element formed from the fusion of metatarsal 3 and metatarsal 4.

name: distal tarsal bone 5 pre-cartilage condensation
description: A distal tarsal bone 5 endochondral element that is composed primarily of a pre-cartilage condensation.

name: mesosalpinx
description: The mesosalpinx is part of the lining of the abdominal cavity in higher vertebrates, specifically the portion of the broad ligament that stretches from the uterine tube to the level of the ovary.

name: semen
description: Organism substance that is composed of sperm cells suspended in seminal fluid.

name: splenius capitis
description: A muscle that arises from the lower half of the ligamentum nuch√¶, from the spinous process of the seventh cervical vertebra, and from the spinous processes of the upper three or four thoracic vertebr√¶ and inserts the mastoid process of the temporal bone, and into the rough surface on the occipital bone just below the lateral third of the superior nuchal line[WP,modified].

name: obsolete regional part of parietal lobe
skin of front of neck
description: A skin of neck that is part of a throat.

name: lower eyelid nerve
description: A nerve that innervates a lower eyelid.

name: manual digit 4 phalanx cartilage element
description: A cartilage element that is part of a manual digit 4 mesenchyme.

name: obsolete predominantly gray regional part of posterior hypothalamic region
clavicle bone primordium
description: A primordium that develops into a clavicle bone.

name: pennaceous feather
description: Pennaceous feathers are also known as contour feathers. This type of feather is present in most modern birds, and has been shown in some species of maniraptoran dinosaurs. Pennaceous feathers have a central shaft (or rachis) with vanes spreading to either side. These vanes are composed of a high number of flattened barbs, that are connected to one another with barbules. The barbules are tiny strands that criss-cross on the flattened side s of the barbs. This forms a kind of miniature velcro-like mesh that holds all the barbs together, stabilizing the vanes. Flight feathers (remiges and rectrices) are specialized types of pennaceous feathers, adapted for high loadings and often strongly asymmetric for improved flight performance[WP].

name: dentate gyrus granule cell layer outer blade
prechordal mesoderm
description: the area of axial mesoderm that develops into the prechordal plate

name: myotome somite 19
description: Portion of the somite giving rise to body wall muscle masses. Kimmel et al, 1995.>

name: trigeminal neural crest
description: Cranial neural crest which gives rise to the trigeminal ganglion.

name: olfactory glomerulus
description: One of the small globular masses of dense neuropil in the olfactory bulb, containing the first synapse in the olfactory pathway[BTO].

name: cerebellar layer
description: A cortical cell layer of the cerebellum. Examples: the granular (inner+outer) layer, molecular layer, Purkinje cell layer, and the ventricular layer of the embryo.

name: external soft tissue zone
description: A region or zone on the surface of an organism that encompasses skin and any adnexa, down through muscles and bounded by underlying skeletal support structures.

name: lens anterior epithelium
description: A layer of cuboidal epithelial cells bounded anteriorly by the capsule of the lens and posteriorly by the lens cortex.

name: insect embryonic abdominal segment
description: Metameric subdivision of the embryonic abdomen.

name: coronary sinus
description: the short trunk that recieves most of the cardiac veins carrying the blood from the myocardium and delivers it to the right atrium, with the sinoatrial connection occurring between the inferior vena cava and the atrioventricular orifice

name: gracile fasciculus of medulla
description: Part of gracile fasiculus located in the medulla

name: medial condyle of tibia
description: The medial condyle is the medial portion of the upper extremity of tibia. It is the site of insertion for the Semimembranosus muscle[WP].

name: medial globus pallidus
description: The more medial segment of the globus pallidus.

name: quadratus lumborum
description: An abdominal muscle that inserts on the last rib and transverse processes of lumbar vertebrae. It is irregular and quadrilateral in shape, and broader below than above.

name: obsolete predominantly gray regional part of ventral nuclear group
saliva-secreting gland
description: saliva-secreting exocrine glands of the oral cavity[GO]

name: scapular process
description: The dorsal extension of the scapulocoracoid above the level of the glenoid region in basal gnathostomes. Modified from Brazeau 2009.

name: metathalamus
description: The metathalamus is a composite structure of the thalamus, consisting of the medial geniculate nucleus and the lateral geniculate nucleus. [WP,unvetted].

name: cranial lymph vasculature
description: A lymph vasculature that is part of a head.

name: eye epithelium
description: A epithelium that is part of a camera-type eye.

name: sacral lymph node
description: A lymph node located in the sacral region.

name: Hatschek's pit
description: A deep ciliated fossa on the dorsal midline of the buccal cavity (the region of the gut behind the mouth). Among other things, it secrets mucus which entraps food particles from the water[WP].

name: ventral tubercle of humerus
description: The greater tubercle of the humerus is situated lateral to the head of the humerus and posteriolateral to the lesser tubercle. Its upper surface is rounded and marked by three flat impressions. the highest of these gives ('superior facet') insertion to the Supraspinatus the middle ('middle facet') to the Infraspinatus. the lowest one ('inferior facet'), and the body of the bone for about 2.5 cm. below it, to the Teres minor. The lateral surface of the greater tubercle is convex, rough, and continuous with the lateral surface of the body. Between the greater tubercle and the lesser tubercle is the intertubercular sulcus (bicipital groove).

name: anterior inferior cerebellar artery
description: A basilar artery branch that supplies the anterior portion of the inferior surface of the cerebellum.

name: magnocellular superficial pretectal nucleus
description: A nucleus that is part of the superficial pretectum and is characterized by large widely scattered cells.

name: facial neural crest
description: Cranial neural crest that is part of the facial region.

name: wall of ureter
description: An anatomical wall that is part of a ureter.

name: obsolete regional part of neuraxis cavity
mesethmoid bone
description: An ossified mesethmoid element

name: dorsal fin middle radial bone
description: dorsal fin middle radial element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: ductus communicans
description: The constriction between the anterior and posterior chambers of the swim bladder. There does not appear to be an identifiable sphincter in the ductus, and therefore other musculature may regulate its opening. Finney et al, 2006.

name: cervical region of vertebral column
description: That portion of the spine comprising the cervical vertebrae. The neck area of the spine.

name: interphalangeal joint of manual digit 5
description: An interphalangeal joint of manus that is part of a manual digit 5.

name: larval labial segment
description: Any labial segment (UBERON:6000014) that is part of some larval head (UBERON:6001730).

name: mucoid tissue
description: Loose connective tissue, the intercellular matrix of which consists predominantly of mucoid ground substance. Examples: Mucoid tissue of umbilical cord, mucoid tissue of vitreous body, mucoid tissue of nucleus pulposus.

name: posterior nasal aperture
description: Opening/conduit between the nasal cavity and the nasopharynx[AAO] The choanae are separated by the vomer[WP].

name: median palatine suture
description: the line of junction between the horizontal parts of the palatine bones that extends from both sides of the skull to form the posterior part of the hard palate.

name: lateral ocellus
description: The ocellus that is paired[HAO]. The number, form, and function of the dorsal ocelli varies markedly throughout insect orders. They tend to be larger and more strongly expressed in flying insects (particularly bees, wasps, dragonflies and locusts), where they are typically found as a triplet. Two lateral ocelli are directed to the left and right of the head respectively, while a central (median) ocellus is directed frontally. In some terrestrial insects (e.g. some ants and cockroaches), only two lateral ocelli are present: the median ocellus is absent. Note that the unfortunately labelled 'lateral ocelli' here refers to the sideways facing position of the ocelli, which are of the dorsal type. They should not be confused with the lateral ocelli of some insect larvae (see stemmata)[Wikipedia].

name: extrahepatic bile duct epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a extrahepatic bile duct [Automatically generated definition].

name: crypt of Lieberkuhn of ileum
description: An intestinal crypt that is located in the ileum.

name: infraorbital artery
description: The infraorbital artery is an artery in the head that runs in the maxilla, emerging through the infraorbital foramen, just under the orbit of the eye. [WP,unvetted].

name: ductus reuniens
description: The canalis reuniens of Hansen is part of the human inner ear. It connects the lower part of the saccule to the ductus cochlearis near its vestibular extremity.

name: optic vein
description: Vein that connects to the hyaloid vein that drains the eye. External to eye. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: distal cartilage of internal anterior process of basipterygium
description: Process that is cartilaginous and arises from the distal tip of internal anterior process of basipterygium.

name: manual digit 2 metacarpus cartilage element
description: A manual digit metacarpus cartilage element that is part of a manual digit 2 mesenchyme.

name: external ectoderm
description: The surface (external) layer of ectoderm which begins to proliferate shortly after separation from the neuroectoderm.

name: submandibular gland
description: Either of the paired compound tubuloalveolar (aka tubuloacinar) major salivary glands composed of both serous and mucous secretory cells and situated beneath the mandible.

name: lymph node primary follicle
description: An unstimulated network of follicular dendritic cells and small resting B cells in the lymph node cortex.

name: hypaxial region somite 2
description: Somite-derived body wall muscle present ventral to the horizontal myoseptum. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: adductor longus
description: An adductor muscle that attaches to the hip and femur. In humans, it is a part of the adductor group of the thigh, that as the name suggests adducts the thigh. The adductor longus muscle forms the medial wall of the femoral triangle[WP, generalized].

name: mesorchium
description: The testes, at an early period of fetal life, are placed at the back part of the abdominal cavity, behind the peritoneum, and each is attached by a peritoneal fold, the mesorchium, to the mesonephros.

name: pouch scale
description: Scale that forms part of the posterior border of the caudal-fin organ. Pouch scales are usually hypertrophied.

name: ventral commissural nucleus of spinal cord
description: The term commissural nucleus of the spinal cord refers to a group of cells in the medial portion of the anterior gray column; it corresponds roughly to lamina VIII

name: upper lobe of lung
description: A lobe of the lung that is closest to the head.

name: anterior communicating artery
description: A blood vessel of the brain that connects the left and right anterior cerebral arteries. The anterior communicating artery connects the two anterior cerebral arteries across the commencement of the longitudinal fissure. Sometimes this vessel is wanting, the two arteries joining together to form a single trunk, which afterward divides; or it may be wholly, or partially, divided into two. Its length averages about 4 mm, but varies greatly. It gives off some of the anteromedial ganglionic vessels, but these are principally derived from the anterior cerebral artery. It is part of the cerebral arterial circle, also known as the circle of Willis.

name: round ligament of liver
description: A degenerative string of tissue that exists in the free edge of the falciform ligament of the liver. Anatomically, the round ligament divides the left part of the liver into medial and lateral sections. The round ligament represents the remnant of the fetal left umbilical vein. The round ligament therefore only exists in mammals. Prenatally and for a month or two after birth, the left umbilical vein is patent, subsequently degenerating to fibrous tissue, the round ligament. The umbilical vein/round ligament inserts around the umbilicus and is an important landmark of the inner surface of the anterior abdominal wall[WP].

name: mesonephric renal vesicle
description: The renal vesicle is the primordial structure of the mesonephric nephron epithelium, and is formed by the condensation of mesenchymal cells[GO].

name: open tracheal system
description: An open tracheal system is a respiratory system, a branched network of epithelial tubes that supplies oxygen to target tissues via spiracles. An example of this is found in Drosophila melanogaster.

name: thymus
description: Anatomical structure of largely lymphoid tissue that functions in cell-mediated immunity by being the site where T cells develop.

name: obsolete regional part of cerebellar peduncular complex
areolar connective tissue
description: Loose connective tissue located at the outer and inner layers of organs. Examples: submucosal connective tissue, tunica adventitia of artery, papillary dermis, superficial fascia of dorsum of hand.

name: axilla skin
description: A zone of skin that is part of a axilla.

name: capsule of lymph node
description: Capsule surrounding lymph node composed of connective tissue with some plain muscle fibers.

name: spinal cord neural plate
description: A neural plate that develops_from a future spinal cord.

name: choroid plexus stroma
description: Stromal matrix surrounding blood vessels within the choroid plexus.

name: hippocampal formation
description: Hippocampus (proper) plus dentate gyrus and subiculum[definition derived from NIF comments and ontology alignment].

name: cerebellar hemisphere
description: A paired regions of the cerebellum that lie outside and lateral to the central vermis[MP]. The cerebellum consists of three parts, a median and two lateral, which are continuous with each other, and are substantially the same in structure. The median portion is constricted, and is called the vermis, from its annulated appearance which it owes to the transverse ridges and furrows upon it; the lateral expanded portions are named the hemispheres. The lateral hemisphere is considered the portion of the cerebellum to develop most recently. [WP,unvetted].

name: bursal follicle
description: Follicle within the plicae of bursa of Fabricius.

name: stratum granulosum of epidermis
description: the layer of flattened cells containing basophilic granules of keratohyalin and lying just above the stratum spinosum (spiny layer) of the epidermis

name: basibranchial II
description: Unpaired medial element that articulates with the anterior basibrachial I (if present).

name: intermetacarpal joint
description: A skeletal joint that connects two adjacent metacarpals[FMA,modified].

name: root of sacral nerve
description: A spinal nerve root that is part of a sacral nerve.

name: umbilical smooth muscle
description: A smooth muscle tissue that is part of a umbilical cord.

name: spinal cord commissure
description: The nerve fiber tracts that span the midline of the spinal cord

name: blastema of regenerating digit tip
description: A blastema that is part of a distal segment of digit.

name: egg capsule
description: Protective membranes that surround amphibian embryos.

name: base of prostate
description: The uppermost part of the prostate gland adjacent to the bladder wall.

name: endocardium of left auricle
description: An endocardium that is part of a left atrium auricular region.

name: dorsolateral prefrontal cortex layer 3
description: Layer 3 of dorsolateral prefrontal cortex lying deep to the layer 2 and cytoarchitectonically defined by numerous small pyramidal neurons.

name: pelvic appendage skeleton
description: The collection of all skeletal elements in a pelvic appendage region.

name: chordo neural hinge
description: Portion of tissue that is posterior to the developing notochord during tail bud extension.

name: tunnel of Corti
description: A triangular, fluid-filled space normally found between the inner and outer rows of supporting pillar cells in the organ of Corti.

name: epithelial tube open at both ends
description: An epithelial tube open at both ends that allows fluid flow.

name: duplex uterus
description: The duplex uterus is doubled, and is found in monotremes, marsupials, elephants and rodents

name: external thoracic vein
description: extension of the long thoracic vein that collects blood from the mammary glands

name: lumen of hindgut
description: An anatomical cavity that surrounded_by a hindgut.

name: prostate gland dorsolateral lobe
description: the rodent prostate lobe that lies in the triangular area between urethra and seminal vesicle

name: tooth whorl
description: A spirally arranged cluster of teeth

name: thoracic spinal cord lateral column
description: A subdivision of spinal cord lateral column that is part of a thoracic spinal cord.

name: lateral amygdaloid nucleus
description: The sensory interface of the amygdala where plasticity is mediated (Phelps & LeDoux, 2005, http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/ 16242399).

name: proximal epiphysis of phalanx of manus
description: A proximal epiphysis that is part of a phalanx of manus [Automatically generated definition].

name: dorsal ventricular ridge of pallium
description: A large expansion of the lateral wall of the telencephalon, located in the pallium. Found in reptiles and birds

name: spleen smooth muscle
description: A portion of smooth muscle tissue that is part of a spleen [Automatically generated definition].

name: distal tarsal bone 2
description: Endochondral tarsal bone articulating with centralia and metatarsal 2.

name: CA1 stratum lacunosum moleculare
description: Part of stratum lacunosum-moleculare lying in area CA1, superficial to CA1 stratum radiatum and bounded by the pial surface, continuous with stratum lacunosum-moleculare of CA2 and the subiculum stratum moleculare

name: lower jaw opening
description: An anatomical space that is part of a bone of lower jaw.

name: intestinal epithelium
description: Epithelial layer that lines the intestine.

name: sense organ
description: An organ that is capable of transducing sensory stimulus to the nervous system.

name: basale commune (tarsal)
description: Amalgamation of distal tarsals 1 and 2.

name: parvicellular part of ventral anterior nucleus
precaudal vertebra endochondral element
description: Vertebral elements lacking hemal spines (Weitzman, 1962), refers generally to the anterior vertebral region bounding the abdominal cavity. Alternate but not quite synonymous terms are abdominal or trunk vertebrae, which bear parapophyses and ribs. In many actinopterygians dorsal to the posterior abdominal cavity there are transitional vertebrae lacking ribs but also without hemal spines or sometimes even enclosed hemal arches. The primary definition would identify these vertebrae as precaudal.(Bird and Mabee, 2003)

name: left posterior cardinal vein
description: A posterior cardinal vein that is in_the_left_side_of a multicellular organism.

name: parapophysis 4
description: Parapophysis that is the lateral projection from the fourth centrum. Parapophysis 4 is bilaterally paired.

name: lumbrical muscle of pes
description: The lumbricals are four small skeletal muscles, accessory to the tendons of the flexor digitorum longus and numbered from the medial side of the pes; they arise from these tendons, as far back as their angles of division, each springing from two tendons, except the first.

name: eyebrow
description: The eyebrow is an area of thick, delicate hairs above the eye that follows the shape of the lower margin of the brow ridges. Their main function is to protect the eye, but they are also important to human communication and facial expression. It is not uncommon for people to modify their eyebrows by means of hair addition or removal, make up, or piercings.

name: ceratohyal foramen
description: Foramen in the anterior ceratohyal for passage of the hyoidean artery.

name: dense connective tissue
description: Dense connective tissue is mainly composed of collagen type I. Crowded between the collagen fibers are rows of fibroblasts, fiber-forming cells, that manufacture the fibers. Dense connective tissue forms strong, rope-like structures such as tendons and ligaments. Tendons attach skeletal muscles to bones; ligaments connect bones to bones at joints. Ligaments are more stretchy and contain more elastic fibers than tendons. Dense connective tissue also make up the lower layers of the skin (dermis), where it is arranged in sheets

name: lobe of prostate
description: A portion of a prostate that forms a lobe.

name: inter-ventral hypohyal joint
description: Joint that articulates the contralateral ventral hypohyal bones or the contralateral ceratobranchial cartilages. Inter-ventral hypohyal joint is paired.

name: fundic gastric gland
description: The fundus glands (or fundic glands, or gastric glands) are found in the body and fundus of the stomach. They are simple tubes, two or more of which open into a single duct.

name: pars flaccida of tympanic membrane
description: A small, triangular, flaccid portion of the tympanic membrane, or eardrum, lying above the malleolar folds, attached directly to the petrous bone at the notch of Rivinus.

name: renal fascia
description: A fascial pouch derived from extraperitoneal connective tissue that contains the kidneys, the suprarenal glands, the renal vessels and perirenal fat

name: epigastric vein
description: A vein that drains the anterior abdominal wall.

name: trachea connective tissue
description: A portion of connective tissue that is part of a trachea.

name: mesentery of rectum
description: A mesentery that is part of a rectum [Automatically generated definition].

name: esophageal-pneumatic duct sphincter
description: Sphincter at the junction of the esophagus and pneumatic duct.

name: epipharyngeal sclerite
description: Unpaired sclerite to which the median tooth (labrum) posteriorly merges, and bears the cuticular pores of the labral sense organ.

name: marginal zone of embryo
description: Belt-like region of presumptive mesoderm at the equator of the late blastula.

name: perianal sebaceous gland
description: A holocrine gland that is part of the pilosebaceous unit of a hair located in the area around the anus.

name: ankle nerve
description: A nerve that is part of an ankle [Automatically generated definition].

name: hyomandibula-opercle joint
description: Synovial joint that articulates the hyomandibula and the opercle.

name: digestive system element
description: Any of the organs or elements that are part of the digestive system. Examples: tongue, esophagus, spleen, crop, lunge feeding organ, tooth elements.

name: simple columnar epithelium
description: Unilaminar epithelium, which consists of a single layer of columnar cells. Examples: ciliated columnar epithelium, gastric epithelium, microvillus columnar epithelium.[FMA]

name: superior hypogastric nerve plexus
description: The superior hypogastric plexus (in older texts, hypogastric plexus or presacral nerve) is a plexus of nerves situated on the vertebral bodies below the bifurcation of the aorta. [WP,unvetted].

name: swim bladder artery
description: An elaborate set of vessels that branche off caudally from the anterior mesenteric artery just after the dorsal aorta. The SBA vascular loops are located on the ventral side of the swim bladder. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: koniocortex
description: Regions of the cerebal cortex characterized by a particularly well-developed inner granular layer (layer 4); this type of cerebral cortex is represented by the primary sensory Brodmann area 17 of the visual cortex, Brodmann areas 1-3 of the somatic sensory cortex, and Brodmann area 41 of the auditory cortex.

name: lamina terminalis of cerebral hemisphere
description: The remnant of the lamina terminalis in the developed brain.

name: broad ligament of uterus
description: A broad fold of peritoneum that extends from the side of the uterus to the wall of the pelvis.

name: blood plasma
description: The liquid component of blood, in which erythrocytes are suspended.

name: fin fold pectoral fin bud
description: Fin fold of the pectoral fin bud, resulting from mesenchyme migration into the apical fold.

name: skin of forelimb wing
description: A zone of skin that is part of a forelimb wing.

name: upper eyelid nerve
description: A nerve that innervates an upper eyelid.

name: obsolete peripheral nucleus of ventral telencephalon
description: Telencephalic nucleus which has migrated away from the ependyma and consists of the central, lateral nuclei and the dorsal and ventral entopeduncular nuclei. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

name: manual digit 5 phalanx cartilage element
description: A cartilage element that is part of a manual digit 5 mesenchyme.

name: capillary system of liver
description: The smallest of the blood vessels, parts of the microcirculation, of the liver.

name: superficial cervical fascia
description: Superficial cervical fascia is a thin layer of subcutaneous connective tissue that lies between the dermis of the skin and the deep cervical fascia. It contains the platysma, cutaneous nerves, blood, and lymphatic vessels. It also contains a varying amount of fat, which is its distinguishing characteristic.

name: tunica intima of artery
description: A tunica intima that is part of a artery.

name: myotome somite 21
description: Portion of the somite giving rise to body wall muscle masses. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: gonad primordium
description: Portion of tissue that gives rise to the immature gonad.

name: photoreceptor array
description: An array of photoreceptors and any supporting cells found in an eye.

name: pretectal nucleus
description: A neural nucleus of the pretectal area (between dorsal thalamus and optic tectum) that receives afferents primarily from the retina and the optic tectum and are involved in modulating motor behavior in response to visual input.

name: mesentery of small intestine
description: The peritoneum responsible for connecting the jejunum and ileum (parts of the small intestine) to the back wall of the abdomen. Between the two sheets of peritoneum are blood vessels, lymph vessels, and nerves. This allows these parts of the small intestine to move relatively freely within the abdominopelvic cavity. The brain, however, cannot map sensation accurately, so sensation is usually referred to the midline, an example of referred pain[WP].

name: parvicellular part of medial dorsal nucleus
lateral condyle of tibia
description: The lateral condyle is the lateral portion of the upper extremity of tibia. It serves as the insertion for the Biceps femoris muscle[WP].

name: proximal phalanx of digit 1
description: A proximal phalanx that is part of a autopod digit 1 [Automatically generated definition].

name: cerebellum intermediate zone
description: The paired regions of the cerebellar hemisphere that lie adjacent to the vermis and are between the vermis and lateral regions of the hemispheres; it receives input from the corticopontocerebellar fibers that originate from the motor cortex, and also receives sensory feedback from the muscles; these signals are integrated by this region, to coordinate muscle activity with motor inputs

name: transversus abdominis muscle
description: The lateral abdominal wall muscle that is deep to the internal oblique.

name: midgut
description: Middle subdivision of a digestive tract[CJM]. In vertebrates: The middle part of the alimentary canal from the stomach, or entrance of the bile duct, to, or including, the large intestine[GO].

name: sternal trabecula
description: Anatomical projections that are  elongate processes in the mid and posterior regions of the sternum.

name: cleidocephalicus muscle
description: The cleidomastoideus is a thick, strap-like muscle that together with the cleidocervicalis forms the proximal part of the brachiocephalicus. It lies beneath the cleidocervicalis. Its origin is the clavicular tendon with its insertion being at the mastoid process of the temporal bone. It is distinctly narrow and is united with the cleidocervicalis and cleidobrachialis by the clavicular tendon. Together with the other two components of the brachiocephalicus muscle, its primary function is to advance the free limb, however, it can also act as an shoulder extensor. Acting bilaterally, it fixes and depresses the neck, while by its unilateral action, it allows the head and neck to be drawn to the side. Its blood supply is the inferior cervical, carotid and vertebral arteries and its nerve supply is the spinal accessory, cervical and axillary nerves.

name: limb segment
description: A major subdivision of a mature or developing limb, including both skeletal elements (or the mesenchyme that gives rise to the skeletal elements) and associated tissues, such as muscle, connective tissue, integument. Examples: autopod region, zeugopod region, stylopod region, metapodial region, arm region. Excludes the limb girdles.

name: Hatschek's nephridium
description: An unpaired kidney whose duct opens into the anterior pharynx. It can be seen as a deep ciliated fossa on the dorsal midline of the buccal cavity (mouth). Among other things, it secrets mucus which entraps food particles from the water[WP].

name: cutaneous trunci muscle
description: Lying just below the skin, cutaneus trunci is one of very few cutaneus muscles. It composes of a thin sheets of muscle that spred over the body in the superficial fasciae. Their role is to twich the skin to rid of pests etc. Cuteneus muscles are found in all domestic species.

name: parvocellular superficial pretectal nucleus
description: A nucleus that is part of the superficial pretectum and is characterized by small cells.

name: kidney corticomedullary boundary
description: The region demarcating the renal medulla from the surrounding cortex; end-stage renal failure may be associated with loss of the normal corticomedullary boundary

name: sclerite
description: A region of integument whose external cuticular part is a hard, sclerotized plate.

name: anal fin middle radial bone
description: anal fin middle radial element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: thoracic region of vertebral column
description: That part of the spine comprising the thoracic vertebrae.

name: levator scapulae muscle
description: An axial muscle that originates in the cervical vertebraae inserts on the scapula.

name: mastoid lymph node
description: The mastoid lymph nodes (retroauricular lymph nodes, posterior auricular glands), usually two in number, are situated on the mastoid insertion of the Sternocleidomastoideus, beneath the Auricularis posterior. Their afferent vessels drain the posterior part of the temporoparietal region, the upper part of the cranial surface of the auricula or pinna, and the back of the external acoustic meatus; their efferents pass to the superior deep cervical glands.

name: larval thorax
description: Any thorax (UBERON:6000015) that is part of some larva (UBERON:6001727).

name: eyelid tarsus
description: The tarsi (tarsal plates) are two comparatively thick, elongated plates of dense connective tissue, about 2.5 cm. in length; one is found in each eyelid, and contributes to its form and support. They directly abut the lid margins.

name: supracardinal vein
description: Either of two veins in the mammalian embryo and various adult lower vertebrate forms located in the thoracic and abdominal regions dorsolateral to and on either side of the descending aorta and giving rise to the azygos and hemiazygos veins and a part of the inferior vena cava[MW]. These veins drain the body wall via the segmental intercostal veins, thus taking over the function of the posterior cardinals[ISBN]

name: intrahepatic bile duct epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a intrahepatic bile duct [Automatically generated definition].

name: obsolete regional part of calcarine sulcus
crypt of Lieberkuhn of duodenum
description: An intestinal crypt that is located in the duodenum.

name: sacral vertebra endochondral element
description: A vertebra endochondral element that is part of the sacral region of the vertebral column.

name: liver lobule
description: the polygonal structure of the liver that consists of hepatocytes radiating outward from a hepatic vein

name: vestibular labyrinth
description: The part of the membranous labyrinth that includes the utricle and saccule lodged within the vestibule and the semicircular ducts lodged eccentrically in the corresponding canals.

name: auditory ossicle bone
description: One of 3 small bones contained within the middle ear space and serve to transmit sounds from the air to the fluid-filled labyrinth. The absence of the auditory ossicles would constitute a moderate-to-severe hearing loss. The term 'ossicles' literally means 'tiny bones' and commonly refers to the auditory ossicles, though the term may refer to any small bone throughout the body. [WP,unvetted].

name: mammary gland alveolus
description: A sac-like structure that is found in the mature gland[GO].

name: M. ileo-fibularis
description: Originates from the ventral border of the ala ossis ilei just posterior to the origin of M. glutaeus maximus. Insterts in the aponeurosis covering the knee joint.

name: milk
description: An emulsion of fat globules within a fluid that is secreted by the mammary gland during lactation.

name: middle anterior process of basipterygium
description: Process that is bony and arises from anterior margin of basipterygium between internal anterior process of basipterygium and external anterior process of basipterygium. Middle anterior process of basipterygium projects anteriorly or anteromedially.

name: manual digit 3 metacarpus cartilage element
description: A manual digit metacarpus cartilage element that is part of a manual digit 3 mesenchyme.

name: mixed endoderm/mesoderm-derived structure
description: An anatomical structure that develops from the endoderm and the mesoderm.

name: appendicocostalis muscle
description: One of of three muscles associated with the uncinate processes.

name: larynx
description: A continuation of the pharynx that is involved in breathing, sound production, and protecting the trachea against food aspiration.

name: afferent lymphatic vessel
description: Lymphatic vessel that enters the lymph node. The afferent lymph vessels enter at all parts of the periphery of the lymph node, and after branching and forming a dense plexus in the substance of the capsule, open into the lymph sinuses of the cortical part. In doing this they lose all their coats except their endothelial lining, which is continuous with a layer of similar cells lining the lymph paths

name: hypaxial region somite 22
description: Somite-derived body wall muscle present ventral to the horizontal myoseptum. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: tendon sheath
description: A layer of membrane around a tendon. It has 2 layers: synovial sheath + fibrous tendon sheath

name: olivary body
description: prominent oval structure in the medulla oblongata, present in pairs, the lower portion of the brainstem. They contain the olivary nuclei

name: margin of eyelid
description: the confluence of the mucosal surface of the conjunctiva, the edge of the orbicularis, and the cutaneous epithelium.

name: lower lobe of lung
description: The bottom most subdivision of either the right or left lung.

name: lower back muscle
description: A muscle of back that is part of a lower back.

name: anal fin distal radial bone
description: anal fin distal radial element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: upper secondary canine tooth
description: A secondary canine tooth that is part of a upper jaw region.

name: ventricular system of central nervous system
description: A set of structures containing cerebrospinal fluid in the brain. It is continuous with the central canal of the spinal cord[WP].

name: metacercaria
description: A tailless encysted late larva of a trematode parasite that is usually the form which is infective for the definitive host.

name: cerebellum fissure
description: One of a set of deep furrows which divide the lobules of the cerebellum. Examples: postcentral, primary and secondary furrows

name: round ligament of uterus
description: The round ligament of the uterus originates at the uterine horns, in the parametrium. It leaves the pelvis via the deep inguinal ring, passes through the inguinal canal and continues on to the labia majora where its fibers spread and mix with the tissue of the mons pubis[WP]. A fibromuscular band that attaches to the uterus and then passes along the broad ligament, out through the inguinal ring, and into the labium majus[MESH].

name: mesonephric S-shaped body
description: The mesonephric S-shaped body is the successor of the mesonephric comma-shaped body that contributes to the morphogenesis of a nephron in the mesonephros[GO].

name: reproductive structure
description: Any anatomical structure that is part of the reproductive system.

name: bone marrow
description: the soft tissue that fills the cavities of bones

name: trabecula of lymph node
description: Membranous process coming from capsule of lymph node[WP].

name: gonad mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a developing gonad [Automatically generated definition].

name: mouth floor
description: The ventral area of the mouth. In organisms with a tongue, this is the area under the ventral surface of the tongue[ncit, modified].

name: tonsil capsule
description: A capsule that is part of a tonsil [Automatically generated definition].

name: fourth ventricle
description: Part of the ventricular system of the brain, forming a single large irregularly shaped cavity located on the midline of the rhombencephalon, between the medulla, pons and the isthmus ventrally and the cerebellum dorsally. It is continuous with the cerebral aqueduct anteriorally and the central canal of the spinal cord posteriorly. It communicates with the subarachnoid space through its lateral and median apertures.

name: dorsal thoracic nucleus
description: Two column-shaped nuclear masses formed by large cells. Clarke's nuclei are located in the regions dorsolateral to the central canal in the thoratic and upper lumbar segments.

name: plectral apparatus
description: Complex sound-conducting anatomical structure.

name: cardiac jelly
description: Portion of extracellular matrix between the myocardium and the endocardium. The cardiac jelly plays a central role in the septation of the heart and comprises most of the thickness of the heart wall at early stages, but disappears as the heart differentiates.

name: branchiostegal ray 3
description: Branchiostegal ray that is the third anterior-most ray in the adult.

name: stomach
description: An expanded region of the vertebrate alimentary tract that serves as a food storage compartment and digestive organ. A stomach is lined, in whole or in part by a glandular epithelium.

name: intercarpal joint
description: A skeletal joint that connects two carpal bones.

name: root of coccygeal nerve
description: A spinal nerve root that is part of a coccygeal nerve.

name: osteoid
description: Bone tissue that is an unmineralized bone matrix deposited by osteoblasts prior to the mineralization of bone tissue.

name: obsolete mucous surface cell
description: Type of mucous-producing cell that appears in early larval stages and persists after metamorphosis.

name: upper uroneural
description: Uroneurals that form the uppermost three uroneural series that overlap, and lie at an angle to, longer anterior ones. [http://hdl.handle.net/2246/1224]

name: endocardium of right auricle
description: An endocardium that is part of a right atrium auricular region.

name: dorsolateral prefrontal cortex layer 4
description: Layer 4 of dorsolateral prefrontal cortex lying deep to the external pyramidal layer and cytoarchitectonically defined by presence of small cells.

name: crista of ampulla of anterior semicircular duct of membranous laybrinth
description: A crista ampullaris neuroepithelium that is part of a anterior semicircular duct.

name: mandibular neural crest
description: Cranial neural crest that migrates into the mandibular arch.

name: blood-inner ear barrier
description: The function of the group of barriers and transport systems which regulate the transport of various substances from blood to inner ear tissue and maintain the microhomeostasis and functional integrity of the inner ear; the endothelial cells of the inner ear blood capillaries, linked to each other by tight junctions, represent the main component of the blood-inner ear barrier

name: arborizing epithelial duct system
description: A collection of connected epithelial tubes with a single portal.

name: bipartite uterus
description: The bipartite uterus is y-shaped externally and divided internally (ungulates, carnivores)

name: deep fibular nerve
description: A branch of the common peroneal nerve. It innervates the ankle and toes.

name: inferior thyroid artery
description: One of the three branches of the thyroid axis that supplies the thyroid gland and branches to form the ascending cervical, esophageal, inferior laryngeal, muscular and tracheal arteries.

name: ectoplacental cone
description: thickened trophoblast of the blastocyst in rodents that becomes the fetal portion of the placenta

name: parasymphisial tooth whorl
description: A tooth whorl located at or near the mandibular symphysis.

name: glomerular epithelium
description: The glomerular epithelium is an epithelial tissue that covers the outer surfaces of the glomerulus. The glomerular epithelium consists of both parietal and visceral epithelium. Metanephric glomerular parietal epithelial cells are specialized epithelial cells that form tight junctions as a barrier to protein transport. A metanephric glomerular visceral epithelial cell is a specialized epithelial cell that contains 'feet' that interdigitate with the 'feet' of other glomerular epithelial cells in the metanephros.

name: sacral spinal cord lateral column
description: A subdivision of spinal cord lateral column that is part of a sacral spinal cord.

name: vesicular appendage of epoophoron
description: In connection with the fimbriae of the uterine tube, or with the broad ligament close to them, there are frequently one or more small pedunculated vesicles. These are termed the vesicular appendages of the epoophoron.

name: proximal epiphysis of metatarsal bone
description: A proximal epiphysis that is part of a metatarsal bone [Automatically generated definition].

name: muscle organ
description: Organ consisting of a tissue made up of various elongated cells that are specialized to contract and thus to produce movement and mechanical work[GO].

name: actinopterygian pyloric caecum
description: A finger-like out-pocketing of the intestine where it meets the end of the stomach (pylorus). Also spelled cecum (ceca). Serves to aid digestion.

name: cornual diverticulum
description: An extension of the frontal sinus into the horn

name: allocortex
description: One of two types of cerebral cortex defined on the basis of cytoarchitecture and fetal development. The other is neocortex. Allocortex does not pass through a prenatal phase of six-layered structure and has three or four layers in the mature brain ( Schiebler-1999 ). Allocortex has three subtypes: paleocortex, archicortex and periallocortex. This definition differs from that in some older sources, which excluded the olfactory bulb and the accessory olfactory bulb ( Carpenter-1983 ).

name: small intestine smooth muscle
description: A portion of smooth muscle tissue that is part of a small intestine [Automatically generated definition].

name: distal tarsal bone 3
description: Endochondral tarsal bone articulating with centralia and metatarsal 3.

name: upper jaw opening
description: An anatomical space that is part of a bone of upper jaw.

name: epithelium of large intestine
description: An epithelium that is part of a large intestine [Automatically generated definition].

name: cutaneous appendage
description: Anatomical projection that protrudes from the skin. Examples: hair, nail, feather, claw, hoof, horn, wattle, spur, beak, antler, bristle and some scales.

name: parvocellular part of red nucleus
description: The parvocellular red nucleus (RNp) is located in the rostral midbrain and is involved in motor coordination. Together with the magnocellular red nucleus, it makes up the red nucleus.

name: bone of upper jaw
description: Any bone that is part of the upper jaw skeleton. This includes (when present): the maxilla, the quadrate (in some species).

name: precaudal vertebra cartilage element
description: Vertebral cartilage elements lacking hemal spines (Weitzman, 1962), refers generally to the anterior vertebral region bounding the abdominal cavity. Alternate but not quite synonymous terms are abdominal or trunk vertebrae, which bear parapophyses and ribs. In many actinopterygians dorsal to the posterior abdominal cavity there are transitional vertebrae lacking ribs but also without hemal spines or sometimes even enclosed hemal arches. The primary definition would identify these vertebrae as precaudal.(Bird and Mabee, 2003)

name: left subcardinal vein
description: A subcardinal vein that is in_the_left_side_of a multicellular organism.

name: intercostal ligament
description: Ligament that connects one rib to another.

name: collection of hairs
description: An anatomical cluster that composed_primarily_of a strand of hair.

name: epibranchial 2 bone uncinate process
description: Epibranchial uncinate process that is part of epibranchial 2 bone.

name: nucleus incertus
description: Distinct cell group in caudoventral regions of the pontine periventricular gray, adjacent to the ventromedial border of the caudal dorsal tegmental nucleus.

name: hypobranchial bone
description: Replacement bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates medially with a median skeletal element and laterally with a ceratobranchial cartilage or bone.

name: arytenoid swellings
description: paired primordial elevations, on either side of the embryonic larynx, within which the arytenoid cartilages are formed

name: dorsal hypohyal-urohyal joint
description: Joint that articulates the dorsal hypohyal and urohyal bones. Dorsal hypohyal-urohyal joint is paired.

name: food storage organ
description: An organ of the digestive tract that is capable of retaining and storing food

name: infraorbital margin
description: The infraorbital margin is the lower margin of the orbita.

name: olfactory tract linking bulb to ipsilateral ventral telencephalon
skin scent gland
description: A scent gland that is part of the skin

name: chest connective tissue
description: A portion of connective tissue that is part of a chest [Automatically generated definition].

name: long descending thin limb
description: The long descending limb starts in the inner stripe of the outer medulla and extends into the inner medulla[GO].

name: mesentery of colon
description: A mesentery that is part of a colon [Automatically generated definition].

name: lower part of vagina
description: The lower third of the vagina.

name: centrale endochondral element
description: Endochondral element located between the proximal and distal rows of carpals or tarsals and thus representing the central carpals or tarsals[PHENOSCAPE].

name: mammary fat pad
description: encapsulated adipose tissue associated with the mammary gland

name: digit nerve of manus
description: A nerve that is part of a finger [Automatically generated definition].

name: pterotic fossa
description: Fossa on the pterotic where the hyomandibula articulates.

name: epicanthal fold
description: A fold of skin of the upper eyelid that partially covers the inner corner of the eye.

name: multilaminar epithelium
description: Epithelium which consists of more than one layer of epithelial cells that may or may not be in contact with a basement membrane. Examples: keratinized stratified squamous epithelium, ciliated stratified columnar epithelium.[FMA]

name: inferior hypogastric nerve plexus
description: The inferior hypogastric plexus (pelvic plexus in some texts) is a plexus of nerves that supplies the viscera of the pelvic cavity. The inferior hypogastric plexus is a paired structure, with each situated on the side of the rectum in the male, and at the sides of the rectum and vagina in the female. [WP,unvetted].

name: obsolete neocortical column
description: A group of neurons in the cortex of the brain which can be successively penetrated by a probe inserted perpendicularly to the cortical surface, and which have nearly identical receptive fields.

name: ovarian bursa
description: A pouch formed by the mesosalpinx and the mesovarium that encloses the infundibulum of the uterine tube and the ovary

name: obsolete mesorchium
description: A thin membrane which attaches the testes to the kidneys and supports the efferent ductules from the testes to the kidneys.

name: pectoral fin fold
description: The functional webs of the paired fins. They arise as a consequence of apical fold (AER) expansion and of migration of the distal mesenchyme. The fin folds are delimited by a dorsal and a ventral striated epidermis. The cells of the epidermal basal stratum are positioned on a basement membrane. Directly beneath the basement membrane of each side there is an array of actinotrichs, fibers of the extracellular matrix which act as supportive elements of the larval fin folds.

name: patagium
description: A membranous extension of skin that forms the wing material in animals such as bats. It typically comprises a number of patagial segments, stretching from the side of the body between the forelimb digits and sometimes the hindlimbs.

name: 3rd arch mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a pharyngeal arch 3.

name: retractor penis magnus muscle
description: A tube-like muscle attaches to the distal tip of the hemipenis and inserts onto the transverse processes of a caudal vertebra.

name: parafibula
description: third bone of the lower leg, normally restricted to the area of the knee, in multuberculates, monotremes and some therians

name: facio-acoustic neural crest
description: Cranial neural crest that gives rise to the facio-acoustic ganglion.

name: obsolete regional part of forebrain
description: A regional part of brain that is part of a forebrain [Automatically generated definition].

name: transparent eye structure
description: A transparent structure that is part of a visual sense organ, the function of which is to direct or focus light onto a photoreceptor array.

name: tongue taste bud
description: A taste bud that is located on the tongue, situated on a gustatory papilla.

name: portal lobule
description: The triangular region on the periphery of the liver lobules that contain a bile duct and a terminal branch of the hepatic artery and portal vein, and may also include a lymphatic vessel.

name: meckelian bone
description: The ossification of the Meckel's cartilage.

name: mesenteric artery
description: Arteries which arise from the abdominal aorta and distribute to most of the intestines.

name: body of lateral ventricle
description: Part of lateral ventricle consisting of the central portion that lies dorsally, bounded by the thalamus on the ventral side (Adapted from Heimer, 1996)

name: cranial sensory ganglion
description: The ganglion found on the root of each cranial nerve, containing the cell bodies of afferent (sensory) neurons.

name: dorsal lateral geniculate nucleus
description: The main division of the lateral geniculate body; consists of two magnocellular layers [TA] (strata magnocellularia [TA]) and four parvocellular layers [TA] (strata parvocellularia [TA]) and serves as a processing station in the major pathway from the retina to the cerebral cortex, receiving fibers from the optic tract and giving rise to the geniculocalcarine radiation to the visual cortex in the occipital lobe.

name: bronchial process
description: Paired processes that extend posteroventrally from the anterolateral margins of the cricoid ring.

name: proximal phalanx of digit 2
description: A proximal phalanx that is part of a autopod digit 2 [Automatically generated definition].

name: right ureter
description: An ureter that is part of a right side of organism [Automatically generated definition].

name: supraacetabular crest
description: Anatomical projection (crest) located dorsaly to the acetabulum.

name: posterior nucleus of hypothalamus
description: The posterior nucleus of the hypothalamus is one of the many nuclei that make up the hypothalamic region of the brain. Its function is thermoregulation (heating) of the body. Damage or destruction of this nucleus causes hypothermia.

name: tibial crest
description: Ridge that arises from the dorso-masial side of the extensor surface of the tibia. It receives the insertion of the tendon of the extensor ilio-tibialis muscle.

name: posterior cranial fontanel
description: Fontanel that is located posterior to the epiphyseal bar, and typically located between the contralateral frontals and parietals (if present) and bordered posteriorly by the supraoccipital.

name: haemal arch lamina
description: Paired plates that form the haemal arch. The lateral margin of each lamina is firmly attached to the ventral surface of the caudal vertebral centrum and the medial end fuses to the medial end of the opposite lamina.

name: lamina propria of large intestine
description: A lamina propria that is part of a large intestine.

name: epithelial mesenchymal boundary of regenerating fin/limb
description: A epithelial-mesenchymal boundary that is part of a regenerating fin/limb.

name: caudal pretectal nucleus
description: Diencephalic nucleus that is part of the superficial pretectum and is rostrally contiguous with the magnocellular superficial pretectal nucleus. Cells of the caudal pretectal nucleus are slightly smaller and less orderly around a central neuropil than those of the magnocellular superficial pretectal nucleus. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

name: retrotrapezoid nucleus
description: The loose collection of neurons that reside in the rostral medulla close to the medullary surface, ventral and immediately caudal of nVII, that are crucial for CO2 sensing in the brain

name: tergite
description: The dorsal plate (sclerite) of an adult abdominal segment.

name: sphenotic spine
description: Process of the sphenotic. The process may project antero-laterally or laterally or ventro-laterally and it has different development in different fish groups. The sphenotic spine is paired.

name: infundibular recess of 3rd ventricle
description: A funnel-shaped diverticulum that extends downward from the anterior aspect of the floor of the third ventricle into the infundibulum of the hypophysis; the embryonic structure gives rise the neural component of the pituitary (pas nervosa).

name: lumbar region of vertebral column
description: Subdivision of vertebral column that corresponds to the lumbar subdivision of the body, containing the lumbar vertebrae.

name: ball
description: The anterior round region of the yolk cell present after the yolk extension forms during the segmentation period. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: deep parotid lymph node
description: The deep parotid lymph nodes are lymph nodes found below the parotid gland. The afferents of the subparotid glands drain the nasal part of the pharynx and the posterior parts of the nasal cavities. Their efferents pass to the superior deep cervical glands.

name: larval thoracic segment
description: Any segment (UBERON:6000003) that is part of some larval thorax (UBERON:6001741).

name: superior eyelid tarsus
description: An eyelid tarsus that is part of a upper eyelid [Automatically generated definition].

name: posterior vena cava
description: A vein that carries deoxygenated blood from the lower half of the body into the right atrium of the heart.

name: crypt of Lieberkuhn of jejunum
description: An intestinal crypt that is located in the jejunum.

name: tibiotarsus endochondral element
description: A tibiotarsus bone or its cartilage or pre-cartilage precursor.

name: esophagus muscularis mucosa
description: A muscularis mucosa that is part of a esophagus.

name: scala vestibuli
description: the division of the spiral canal of the cochlea lying on the apical side of the spiral lamina and vestibular membrane

name: stapes bone
description: The stapes or stirrup is the stirrup-shaped small bone or ossicle in the middle ear which is attached to the incus laterally and to the fenestra ovalis, the 'oval window' medially. The oval window is adjacent to the vestibule of the inner ear. The stapes is the smallest and lightest bone in the human body. The stapes transmits the sound vibrations from the incus to the membrane of the inner ear inside the fenestra ovalis. The stapes is also stabilized by the stapedius muscle, which is innervated by the facial nerve. In non-mammalian vertebrates, the bone homologous to the stapes is usually called the columella; however, in reptiles, either term may be used[WP,unvetted].

name: obsolete midbrain interneuron
description: CNS interneurons located in the midbrain.

name: posterior superior iliac spine
description: The posterior border of the ala, shorter than the anterior, also presents two projections separated by a notch, the posterior superior iliac spine and the posterior inferior iliac spine. The posterior superior iliac spine serves for the attachment of the oblique portion of the posterior sacroiliac ligaments and the Multifidus.

name: ventral intermediate nucleus of thalamus
description: A nucleus medially located within the ventral nuclei of the thalamus.

name: parachordal vessel
description: Vessels run longitudinally along the horizontal myoseptum. These vessels are not functional until after lumenization which occurs near 4 dpf. Isogai et al. 2003.

name: anterior commissure anterior part
description: The horseshoe-shaped tract that connects the two olfactory bulbs.

name: colostrum
description: The thin, yellow, serous fluid secreted by the mammary glands during pregnancy and immediately postpartum before lactation begins. It consists of immunologically active substances, white blood cells, water, protein, fat, and carbohydrates.

name: distal cartilage of middle anterior process of basipterygium
description: Process that is cartilaginous and arises from the distal tip of middle anterior process of basipterygium.

name: manual digit 4 metacarpus cartilage element
description: A manual digit metacarpus cartilage element that is part of a manual digit 4 mesenchyme.

name: mixed ectoderm/mesoderm/endoderm-derived structure
description: An anatomical structure that develops from the ectoderm, mesoderm and endoderm.

name: perinatal stage
description: The period spanning the range immediately before and after birth

name: obsolete predominantly gray regional part of tectum
zone of basilar membrane of cochlea
temporal part of superior longitudinal fasciculus
hypaxial region somite 25
description: Somite-derived body wall muscle present ventral to the horizontal myoseptum. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: vein of vestibular aqueduct
description: A vein that leaves the vestibule through an individual bone canal running parallel to the vestibular aqueduct up to the dura of the posterior side of the petrosa in the area of the endolymphatic sac. It then opens in the inferior petrosal sinus or the jugular bulb. The vein receives other branches from the bone, dura and sac.

name: amnion
description: the thin innermost layer of the extraembryonic membranes that contains the amniotic fluid; the membrane forms a closed sac in which the embryo and later, the fetus, is suspended and protected

name: tendon of triceps brachii
description: A tendon that attaches_to a triceps brachii.

name: pelvic fin actinotrichium
description: Actinotrichium that is part of the pelvic fin.

name: nuptial tubercle
description: Surface structure that is a small protuberance on the surface of the body. Nuptial tubercles primarily function to facilitate contact between individuals for breeding.

name: uncus of parahippocampal gyrus
description: The anterior extremity of the Parahippocampal gyrus is recurved in the form of a hook, the uncus, which is separated from the apex of the temporal lobe by a slight fissure, the incisura temporalis. Although superficially continuous with the hippocampal gyrus, the uncus forms morphologically a part of the rhinencephalon. The term uncus was coined by Felix Vicq dbAzyr (1748b1794).

name: upper back muscle
description: A muscle of back that is part of a dorsal thoracic segment of trunk.

name: tracheal pit
description: Deep and narrow pit formed by the invagination of a tracheal placode in a late extended germ band embryo. Invagination of the placode begins during stage 11. Branches begin to bud from the pit during stage 11, with a dorsal and ventral stem being apparent by mid-stage 12. The pit closes over during stage 13. There are 10 pairs of tracheal pits - one pair in each tracheal metamere (each segment from T2 to A8). Pits are located in the central one third of each parasegment, with the most anterior in parasegment 4 and the most posterior in parasegment 14.

name: lower secondary canine tooth
description: A secondary canine tooth that is part of a lower jaw region.

name: primordial ovarian follicle
description: primordial follicles are indiscernible to the naked eye and develop to primary, secondary, and finally mature vesicular follicles

name: mammary bud
description: A bulb of epithelial cells that forms from the mammary placode that develops into the mammary gland.

name: epithelial fold
description: An epithelial sheet bent on a linear axis.

name: tonsil
description: either of the two small almond-shaped masses of lymph tissue found on either side of the oropharynx

name: nose skin
description: A zone of skin that is part of a external nose.

name: adenohypophysis
description: The glandular, anterior lobe of the pituitary gland. The anterior pituitary regulates several physiological processes including stress, growth, and reproduction[WP]. The anterior lobe of the hypophysis (pituitary gland). This lobe contains cells that produce prolactin, growth hormone, thyroid-stimulating hormone, follicle-stimulating hormone and proopiomelanocortin[ZFA].

name: uncondensed odontogenic mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme enclosed by a dental organ that gives rise to an odontogenic papilla.

name: right atrium valve
description: A valve that is part of a right atrium [Automatically generated definition].

name: hepatobiliary system
description: The part of the digestive system that contains the liver and the biliary system

name: uterine horn
description: either one of the pair of tubular extensions from the uterine body where the uterus and the uterine tubes meet; uterine horns are anterior Mullerian duct-derived structures

name: 1st arch mandibular mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a 1st arch mandibular component.

name: left atrioventricular canal
description: An atrioventricular canal that is in the left side of a atrioventricular region.

name: branchiostegal ray 2
description: Branchiostegal ray that is the second anterior-most ray in the adult.

name: cardial valve
description: A membranous fold of the heart that prevents reflux of fluid

name: hyoid arch neural crest
description: Population of cranial neural crest that give rise to hyoid arch elements.

name: parachordal cartilage
description: Chondrocranium chondrification center that fuses with cartilages derived from sclerotome region of occipital somites forming occipital bone, hypoglossal canals and foramen magnum.

name: left putamen
description: A putamen that is part of a left cerebral hemisphere.

name: obsolete ciliary cell
description: A type of cell that develops in embryos and functions in embryonic movements.

name: predorsal scale
description: Scale that is part of row along the midline between the dorsal fin and the back of the skull. In counting, all scales crossing the midline are included. (Fishbase)

name: dorsolateral prefrontal cortex layer 5
description: Layer 5 of dorsolateral prefrontal cortex lying deep to the internal granule cell layer 4 and cytoarchitectonically divisible into layers 5a and 5b. Layer 5a is characterized by the predominance of large pyramidal cell bodies. Layer 5b is pale in comparison.

name: crista of ampulla of posterior semicircular duct of membranous laybrinth
description: A crista ampullaris neuroepithelium that is part of a posterior semicircular duct.

name: cardiac muscle tissue of atrium
description: A portion of cardiac muscle tissue that is part of an atrium [Automatically generated definition].

name: hyoid neural crest
description: Cranial neural crest that migrates into the hyoid arch.

name: posterior cerebellomedullary cistern
description: A space between the cerebellum and the dorsal surface of the medulla[MP]. The cisterna magna (or cerebellomedullary cistern) is one of three principal openings in the subarachnoid space between the arachnoid and pia mater layers of the meninges surrounding the brain. The openings are collectively referred to as cisterns. The cisterna magna is located between the cerebellum and the dorsal surface of the medulla oblongata. Cerebrospinal fluid produced in the fourth ventricle drains into the cisterna magna via the lateral apertures and median aperture. The two other principal cisterns are the pontine cistern located between the pons and the medulla, and the interpeduncular cistern located between the cerebral peduncles. Cerebral spinal fluid can also be obtained by puncture of the cisterna magna (cistern puncture).

name: epithelial plexus
description: A complex of interlinking epithelial tubules.

name: bicornuate uterus
description: The bicornate uterus is y-shaped but has no internal partition (some ungulates, whales)

name: copepodite stage
description: A development stage of copepods which follows the nauplius stage. It is segmented with more than 3 pairs of appendages

name: vitelline blood vessel
description: blood vessel that is connected to the yolk sac.

name: levator labii superioris
description: The levator labii superioris (or quadratus labii superioris) is a broad sheet, the origin of which extends from the side of the nose to the zygomatic bone. Its medial fibers form the angular head, which arises by a pointed extremity from the upper part of the frontal process of the maxilla and passing obliquely downward and lateralward divides into two slips. One of these is inserted into the greater alar cartilage and skin of the nose; the other is prolonged into the lateral part of the upper lip, blending with the infraorbital head and with the Orbicularis oris. The intermediate portion or infraorbital head arises from the lower margin of the orbit immediately above the infraorbital foramen, some of its fibers being attached to the maxilla, others to the zygomatic bone. Its fibers converge, to be inserted into the muscular substance of the upper lip between the angular head and the Caninus. The lateral fibers, forming the zygomatic head, arise from the malar surface of the zygomatic bone immediately behind the zygomaticomaxillary suture and pass downward and medialward to the upper lip. [WP,unvetted].

name: Helicoprion tooth whorl
description: A tooth whorl found in extinct holocephalids, in which the teeth in the center of the spiral are smallest and oldest, probably occupying the entire mandibular arch.

name: glomerular endothelium
description: The glomerular endothelium is an epithelial tissue that covers the internal surfaces of the glomerulus

name: cervical spinal cord lateral column
description: A subdivision of spinal cord lateral column that is part of a cervical spinal cord.

name: obsolete terminally differentiated osteoblast
description: Osteoblast that is terminally differentiated, located adjacent to acellular or cellular bone tissue within periosteum, and is capable of mineralizing the matrix.

name: lateral part of basal amygdaloid nucleus
proximal epiphysis of metacarpal bone
description: A proximal epiphysis that is part of a metacarpal bone [Automatically generated definition].

name: thoracic duct
description: A major lymphatic vessel that drains lymph from the lower body, left appendage, and left thorax into the junction of the left jugular and subclavian veins.

name: procumbent dorsal fin spine
description: Fin spine that precedes the dorsal fin, oriented anteriorly towards the head of the fish.

name: venom gland duct
description: A duct that is part of a venom gland.

name: mammary gland luminal epithelium
description: The inner cell layer of the mammary epithelium bilayer that lines the luminal surface of mammary gland ducts and alveoli; luminal cells have only limited contact with the underlying basement membrane and surrounding connective tissue; they are secretory epithelial cells characterized by the expression of the receptors for systemic hormones, i.e. estrogens, progesterone and prolactin.

name: cuboid bone
description: A tarsal bone that is formed from distal tarsals 4 and 5. [WP,modified].

name: utriculosaccular duct
description: A duct connecting the the utricle to the saccule in the membranous labyrinth of the ear.

name: portal triad
description: A multi-organ-part structure that consists of three vessels of the portal lobule including the bile duct, a terminal branch of the hepatic artery and portal vein, and may also include a lymphatic vessel

name: feather
description: one of the epidermal growths that form the distinctive outer covering, or plumage, on birds. Feathers are formed in tiny follicles in the epidermis, or outer skin layer, that produce keratin proteins.

name: vein of abdomen
description: A vein that is part of a abdomen.

name: 1st arch mesenchyme from head mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that develops_from a head mesenchyme from mesoderm and is part of a 1st arch mesenchyme.

name: brachialis muscle
description: The brachialis (brachialis anticus) is a muscle in the upper arm that flexes the elbow joint. It lies just deep of the biceps brachii, and is a synergist that assists the biceps brachii in flexing at the elbow. It makes up part of the floor of the region known as the cubital fossa. [WP,unvetted].

name: collection of hair on face
description: A collection of hairs that is part of a face.

name: epibranchial 1 bone uncinate process
description: Epibranchial uncinate process that is part of epibranchial 1 bone.

name: levator operculi
description: Hyoid muscle that originates at the ventrolateral margin of the pterotic and inserts in the dorsomesial edge of the opercle. The levator operculi is responible for jaw depression, its force of contraction is transmitted through the opercular series and the interoperculo-mandibular ligament to the lower jaw.

name: hypural
description: Laterally flattened haemal spine of an ural vertebra that lacks its arch and supports a few principal caudal lepidotrichia distally. A hypural may articulate or fuse with its ural centrum proximally or may lie ventral to the notochord. A hypural is an unpaired median bone that ossifies perichondrally. (Modified from Monod, 1968 and Arratia and Schultze, 1992).

name: ventral hypohyal-urohyal joint
description: Joint that articulates the ventral hypohyal and urohyal bones. Ventral hypohyal-urohyal joint is paired.

name: interpterygoid vacuity
description: Open space between on the palate between the pteryogoid bone and the parasphenoid

name: orbital margin
description: the mostly sharp edge of the orbital opening that is the peripheral border of the base of the pyramidal orbit.

name: mesocoracoid bone
description: Endochondral bone that articulates laterally with the medial surface of the cleithrum and ventro-medially with the scapula and coracoid. Meoscoracoid bone is a small, arch-like bone that develops from the mesocoracoid cartilage. Mesocoracoid bone is paired.

name: ligament of middle ear
description: A ligament that is part of a middle ear.

name: renal convoluted tubule
description: Any region of a nephron tubule that is convoluted. Examples: distal convoluted tubule, proximal convoluted tuble.

name: interdigital gland
description: A skin gland found in the interdigital region of some mammals

name: vasa hyaloidea propria
description: The vasa hyaloidea propria and tunica vasculosa lentis are small branches of the hyaloid artery which fill the primary vitreous

name: arm connective tissue
description: A portion of connective tissue that is part of an arm [Automatically generated definition].

name: early distal convoluted tubule
description: The early distal convoluted tubule contains DCT cells and is vasopressin-insensitive[GO].

name: mesentery of duodenum
description: A mesentery that is part of a duodenum [Automatically generated definition].

name: parabigeminal nucleus
description: Cholinergic cell group that is located ventral to the brachium of the inferior colliculus (in rat) and has reciprocal connectivity with the superior colliculus (Adapted from Paxinos, The rat central nervous system, 2nd ed, 1995, pg 865

name: paired fin radial element
description: Radial element that is part of a paired fin.

name: fenestra endochoanalis
description: Opening on the ventral aspect of the nasal capsule. It contains the apertura nasalis interna.

name: distal carpal endochondral element
description: A distal mesopodial endochondral element that is part of a forelimb.

name: femoral fat pad
description: encapsulated adipose tissue associated with the femur

name: manus nerve
description: A nerve that is part of a manus [Automatically generated definition].

name: erector muscle
description: Muscle that moves parts of the body in a superior direction to an erect position. Antagonistic to depressor muscle.

name: frontal process of maxilla
description: A plate of bone from the maxilla that that projects upward, medialward, and backward, by the side of the nose, forming part of its lateral boundary[WP,modified].

name: simple squamous epithelium
description: Unilaminar epithelium which consists of a single layer of squamous cells. Examples: pulmonary alveolar epithelium, endothelium.[FMA]

name: kidney capsule
description: the tough fibrous layer surrounding the kidney which is covered in a thick layer of perirenal adipose tissue that functions to provide some protection from trauma and damage

name: scolex
description: The anterior organ of a tapeworm used for attachment to the host intestine.

name: navicular bursa
description: A fluid-filled sac that lies between the navicular bone and the deep digital flexor muscle

name: basal process of palatoquadrate
description: Process that extends medially from the ventromedial corner of the palatoquadrate cartilage and articulates or fuses to the anterior wall of the otic capsule via the basitrabecular process.

name: 4th arch mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a pharyngeal arch 4.

name: paraglossale
description: An arrowhead-shaped bone in the avian hyoid apparatus which forms the base of the tongue

name: adventitia
description: An outermost connective tissue covering of an organ, vessel, or other structure[WP].

name: caudal part of ventral posterolateral nucleus of thalamus
gustatory epithelium of tongue
description: A gustatory epithelium that is part of a tongue.

name: hepatic acinus
description: The functional unit of the liver, consisting of a mass of hepatocytes from adjacent liver lobules aligned around the hepatic arterioles and portal venules just as they anastomose into sinusoids.

name: mesenteric vein
description: A vein that returns blood from the intestines.

name: ventral nucleus of trapezoid body
description: A small nucleus of the periolivary complex located laterally to the MNTB, and ventral to the MSO.

name: fin spine
description: A spine that is part of some fin.

name: primary chorionic villus
description: A chorionic villus that is a solid outgrowth of the cytotrophoblast that protrudes into the syncytiotrophoblast.

name: anterior cartilage of palatine
description: anterior cartilage of palatine - cartilage that caps the anterior end of the autopalatine bone. It is typically present in adults.

name: proximal phalanx of digit 3
description: A proximal phalanx that is part of a autopod digit 3 [Automatically generated definition].

name: cerebellar plate
description: The embryonic pseudostratified epithelium of the fourth cerebellar ventricle that eventually forms the vermis and ventral neuroepithelium

name: left ureter
description: An ureter that is part of a left side of organism [Automatically generated definition].

name: neural glomerulus
