description: The middle of the face including the nose and its associated bony structures[MW].

name: choroidal artery
description: One of two arteries (anterior and posterior choroidal artery) that supply blood to the choroid plexus, optic tract, hippocampus, globus pallidus, and other various brain regions.

name: distal phalanx of pedal digit 2
description: A distal phalanx that is part of a foot digit 2 [Automatically generated definition].

name: right common carotid artery plus branches
description: The rightmost of the two common carotid arteries, originating from in the neck from the brachiocephalic trunk.

name: pair of dorsal aortae
description: the paired arterial structures of the embryo that supplies each developing somite via efferent segmental arteries; the dorsal aortae articulate with the umbilical arteries, which return mixed blood to the villi of the chorion for reoxygenation

name: acinus of salivary gland
description: An acinus that is part of a salivary gland.

name: deep femoral artery
description: The profunda femoris artery (also known as the deep femoral artery, or the deep artery of the thigh) is a branch of the femoral artery that, as its name suggests, travels more deeply (posteriorly) than the rest of the femoral artery. [WP,unvetted].

name: obsolete regional part of suprachiasmatic nucleus
obsolete cytoarchitectural part of cerebral cortex
temporal fenestra
description: One of two bilaterally symmetrical holes (fenestrae) in the temporal bone.

name: carapace scute
description: A scute that is part of a carapace.

name: peritoneal cavity
description: Anatomical cavity bounded by visceral and parietal peritoneum

name: tectorial restraint system
description: Tectorial restraint system is a type of ciliary restraint system for hair cells in the inner ear.  In tectorial restraint systems, the tectorial membrane restrains the cilia of the hair cells by attaching either directly to ciliary tufts or indirectly through various kinds of fibrous structure (simple fibers, fibrous strands, finger-like processes, tectorial plates). [Phylogenetic Relationships of the Lizard Families: Essays Commemorating Charles L. Camp. 1988. Eds. R Estes, GK Pregill. Stanford University Press]

name: head sensory canal system
description: Lateral line system on head and pectoral girdle.

name: ulnar artery
description: The ulnar artery is the main blood vessel, with oxygenated blood, of the medial aspect of the forearm. It arises from the brachial artery and terminates in the superficial palmar arch, which joins with the superficial branch of the radial artery. It is palpable on the anterior and medial aspect of the wrist. Along its course, it is accompanied by a similarly named vein or veins, the ulnar vein or ulnar veins. The ulnar artery, the larger of the two terminal branches of the brachial, begins a little below the bend of the elbow in the cubital fossa, and, passing obliquely downward, reaches the ulnar side of the forearm at a point about midway between the elbow and the wrist. It then runs along the ulnar border to the wrist, crosses the transverse carpal ligament on the radial side of the pisiform bone, and immediately beyond this bone divides into two branches, which enter into the formation of the superficial and deep volar arches. [WP,unvetted].

name: transverse radial
description: Endochondral bone, which may be ossified or not in adults, located immediately anteriorly to the pterygiophore series of the anal fin. The structure is usually cylindrical, and its plane of symmetry is transverse to that of pterygiophores and fin rays.

name: primary somatosensory area barrel field layer 2/3
preopercle
description: Dermal bone that is part of the opercular series and bears the preopercular sensory canal. The preopercle is a paired bone and typically L-shaped, with the horizontal limb overlying the interopercle and the vertical limb overlying the opercle.

name: occipital artery foramen
description: Foramina that allow passage of occipital arteries.

name: yolk syncytial layer
description: Peripheral layer of the yolk cell including nuclei and non-yolky cytoplasm. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: superficial ophthalmic nerve foramen
description: Foramen through which the superficial ophthalmic nerve passes.

name: femoral canal
description: The compartment of the femoral sheath that contains efferent lymphatic vessels and a lymph node embedded in a small amount of areolar tissue. It is conical in shape and is about 2 cm long. The femoral canal is bordered: Anteriorly by the inguinal ligament Posteriorly by the pectineal ligament Medially by the lacunar ligament Laterally by the femoral vein It contains the lymph nodes of Cloquet or Rosenmuller. It should not be confused with the nearby adductor canal.

name: thoracic cavity artery
description: An artery that is part of a thoracic cavity[cjm].

name: mucosa of common hepatic duct
description: A mucosa that is part of a common hepatic duct [Automatically generated definition].

name: lamina VI of gray matter of spinal cord
description: Spinal lamina VI is a lamina of the spinal cord. It is also known as the base of the posterior horn.

name: distal late tubule
description: Portion of the renal tubule which is just posterior to the distal early tubule.

name: gland of integumental system
description: A gland that is part of a integumental system [Automatically generated definition].

name: perifoveal part of retina
description: The outermost region surrounding the fovea centralis

name: bronchial artery
description: A systemic artery that supplies the lung with with oxygenated blood.

name: autopod hair
description: A strand of hair that is part of a autopod region.

name: obsolete cartilage bridge of nasal skeleton
tail blood vessel
description: A blood vessel that is part of a tail [Automatically generated definition].

name: outer fin tissue
description: Part of the fin consisting of flattened epidermal cells elevated into a keel-like structure.

name: endohypothalamic tract
description: CNS white matter, axonal tract interconnecting catecholaminergic cell groups in the posterior tuberculum and hypothalamus.

name: stem of Y-shaped fibrocartilage skeleton of ventral pouch
limb bone pre-cartilage condensation
description: A skeletal element that is part of a limb and composed of pre-cartilage tissue.

name: meniscus
description: crescent-shaped fibrocartilaginous structure present in the knee, acromioclavicular, sternoclavicular, and temporomandibular joints[2] that, in contrast to articular disks, only partly divides a joint cavity.[3] A small meniscus also occurs in the radio-carpal joint.

name: rib endochondral element
description: A rib bone or its cartilage or pre-cartilage precursor.

name: obsolete predominantly gray regional part of septal nuclear complex
orbicularis oris muscle
description: The orbicularis oris is a superficial facial muscle with fibers that encircle the opening of the oral cavity that attaches to the maxilla, mandible, skin and modiolus, and that participates in oral/pharyngeal behaviors, and is innervated by the facial nerve (CN VII).

name: rib 8
description: The eighth rib counting from the top of the rib cage down. Note that members of this class are not necessarily homologous[ncit,modified].

name: epibranchial ganglion
description: Cranial ganglion which develops from an epibranchial placode.

name: zygomatic process of frontal bone
description: The part of the zygomatic process consisting of the frontal bone[WP]

name: obsolete mitochondrial aggregate
description: A large distinctive organelle aggregate comprised of mitochondria found in developing oocytes of many species. From Pepling et al. 2007.

name: sclerotome somite 20
description: Medial ventral region of the somite that will form vertebral cartilages. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: helicis major
description: The Helicis major is a narrow vertical band situated upon the anterior margin of the helix. It arises below, from the spina helicis, and is inserted into the anterior border of the helix, just where it is about to curve backward.

name: transverse foramen of axis
description: A transverse foramen that is part of a vertebral bone 2.

name: ultimobranchial body epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a ultimobranchial body.

name: acinus of olfactory gland
description: A acinus that is part of a olfactory gland.

name: podocyte slit junction
description: The gaps between the interdigitated foot processes of the podocyte

name: medulla oblongata anterior median fissure
description: The longitudinal groove in the midline of the anterior aspect of the medulla oblongata

name: perineal nerve
description: A nerve arising from the pudendal nerve that supplies the perineum.

name: pars glenoidalis of scapula
description: Concave structure (posteromedial head) that forms the posterior head of the ventral margin of the scapula. The pars glenoidalis articulates with the humerus, and comprises the dorsal portion of the glenoid fossa.

name: male anatomical structure
description: A part of the body present only in males.

name: scalenus posterior
description: The Scalenus posterior (Scalenus posticus), the smallest and most deeply seated of the three Scaleni, arises, by two or three separate tendons, from the posterior tubercles of the transverse processes of the lower two or three cervical vertebr√¶, and is inserted by a thin tendon into the outer surface of the second rib, behind the attachment of the serratus ventralis. It is occasionally blended with the Scalenus medius. [WP,unvetted].

name: supraglenoid foramen
description: Foramen that perforates supraglenoid buttress.

name: sulcus articularis medialis
description: In a zygapophysis that has ridges and sulci, the medial canal between the carina medialis and the carina proximalis.

name: ventral ramus of squamosal
description: Longest of the three squamosal rami; it invests the dorsolateral margin of the palatoquadrate. The distal end of the ventral ramus invests the quadrate and articulates with the quadratojugal.

name: distal interphalangeal joint
description: An inter-phalangeal joint that connects a distal phalanx to either a medial or proximal phalanx.

name: laryngeal nerve
description: Any nerve that innervates the larynx.

name: nerve to stylopharyngeus from glossopharyngeal nerve
description: The stylopharyngeal branch of glossopharyngeal nerve is distributed to the Stylopharyngeus.

name: ceratobranchial cartilage
description: Pharyngeal arch cartilage that forms the largest skeletal element of the ventral branchial arches.

name: craniocervical region
description: The anteriormost subdivision of the body that includes the head, jaws, pharyngeal region and the neck (if present). In vertebrates this is the subdivision that includes the cervical vertebrae.

name: nucleus of medulla oblongata
description: A neural nucleus that is part of a medulla oblongata.

name: lymph node endothelium
description: An endothelium that is part of a lymph node [Automatically generated definition].

name: skeletal muscle tissue of quadriceps femoris
description: A portion of skeletal muscle tissue that is part of a quadriceps femoris [Automatically generated definition].

name: interdigital region between manual digits 1 and 2
description: An interdigital region that adjacent_to a manual digit 1 and adjacent_to a manual digit 2.

name: epithelium of utricle
description: An epithelium that is part of a utricle of membranous labyrinth [Automatically generated definition].

name: right lung lobar bronchus mesenchyme
description: The right lung lobar bronchus mesenchyme is a type of tissue made up of loosely-packed mesenchymal cells in the right lung lobar bronchus

name: ciliary marginal zone
description: Region at the periphery of the retina where retinal stem cells are located. After 60 hpf, the CMZ is the source of most retinal growth.[Wehman et al, 2005]

name: piriform cortex
description: the subdivision of the laminated olfactory cortex with only three main layers that receive monosynaptic input from the olfactory bulb via the lateral olfactory tract; it is located bilaterally in the ventrolateral forebrain and is commonly divided into anterior and posterior regions

name: presacral rib
description: Rib located anterior to the sacral region. [PHENOSCAPE:NI]

name: right eye
description: An eye that is part of a right side of organism [Automatically generated definition].

name: maxillary sinus
description: One of the paired paranasal sinuses, located in the body of the maxilla, communicating with the middle meatus of the nasal cavity.

name: vertebral vein
description: The vertebral vein is formed in the suboccipital triangle, from numerous small tributaries which spring from the internal vertebral venous plexuses and issue from the vertebral canal above the posterior arch of the atlas. They unite with small veins from the deep muscles at the upper part of the back of the neck, and form a vessel which enters the foramen in the transverse process of the atlas, and descends, forming a dense plexus around the vertebral artery, in the canal formed by the foramina transversaria of the cervical vertebrae. This plexus ends in a single trunk, which emerges from the foramen transversarium of the sixth cervical vertebra, and opens at the root of the neck into the back part of the innominate vein near its origin, its mouth being guarded by a pair of valves. On the right side, it crosses the first part of the subclavian artery. [WP,unvetted].

name: ileal mucosa
description: A mucosa that is part of a ileum [Automatically generated definition].

name: vertebral element 10
description: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 9.

name: theca cell layer
description: A layer of the ovarian follicle that consists of theca cells.

name: left uterine horn
description: An uterine horn that is in the left side of a uterus.

name: lumbosacral nerve plexus
description: An arrangement of nerve fibers, running from the spine that travels to the pelvic appendage where it innervates skin and muscle.

name: hepatic portal vein
description: A portal vein that transports nutrients from the digestive tract to the liver[Kardong].

name: snake venom gland
description: The venom gland of snakes is in actual fact a modified salivary gland and is linked to the groove in the fangs by a duct.

name: diffuse placenta
description: A placenta in which the chorionic sac meets the uterine endometrium over its entire surface. The villi of the chorion are distributed evenly throughout the surface of the chorion, and they extend into processes in the uterine endometrium.

name: acetabular labrum
description: A ring of cartilage that surrounds the acetabulum[WP,unvetted].

name: hypobranchial artery
description: A pair of HA are connect one to each AA1. They run rostromedially until at the extreme rostro-ventral midline the two vessels merge and then run straight caudally along the ventral midline until they reach the cranial end of the ventral aorta (VA). There, the single HA passes just dorsal to the rostral end of the VA and then immediately splits again into a pair of HA. The paired HA continue caudally just to either side of the ventral midline. The HA provide blood supply to the ventral branchial region and the heart.sogai et al. 2001.

name: pharyngeal gill
description: A gill that develops in the walls of the pharynx along a series of gill slits opening to the exterior. In fish, the gills are located on both sides of the pharynx.

name: hypaxial region somite 4
description: Somite-derived body wall muscle present ventral to the horizontal myoseptum. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: intermediate layer of superior colliculus
description: A layer of superior colliculus that lies between the superficial layer and the deep layer.

name: otic capsule pre-cartilage condensation
description: A otic capsule endochondral element that is composed primarily of a pre-cartilage condensation.

name: common penile artery
description: The artery that serves blood to the penis. It subdivides into three arteries, the bulbourethral artery, the dorsal artery of the penis and the cavernosal artery.

name: cervical sympathetic nerve trunk
description: The cervical ganglia are paravertebral ganglia of the sympathetic nervous system. These emerging postganglionic nerves synapse with preganglionic nerves from the thoracic spinal cord. They consist of three paravertebral ganglia: superior cervical ganglion middle cervical ganglion inferior cervical ganglion. The inferior ganglion may be fused with the first thoracic ganglion to form a single structure, the stellate ganglion. Nerves emerging from cervical sympathetic ganglia contribute to the cardiac plexus, among other things.

name: root of cranial nerve
description: The initial segment of a cranial nerve, leaving the central nervous system.

name: premolar 1 hypoconoid
description: Hypoconid found on the first premolar tooth.

name: CA2 field of hippocampus
description: Part of hippocampus proper bounded by areas CA3 and CA1, characterized by a narrow layer of large pyramidal cells, similar in size to CA3 pyramidal cells, but which lack the mossy fiber input from the dentate gyrus (adapted from Paxinos, G. The rat central nervous system, 2nd ed, Academic Press, San Diego, 1995, pg. 460)

name: cartilaginous otic capsule
description: A otic capsule endochondral element that is composed primarily of cartilage tissue.

name: optic eminence ectoderm
description: An ectoderm that is part of a optic eminence [Automatically generated definition].

name: medial cotyla
description: The medialmost of the cotyla of the lower jaw, for articulation with the cranium.

name: hemolymphoid system gland
description: A gland that is part of a hemolymphoid system [Automatically generated definition].

name: medial pterygoid muscle
description: The medial pterygoid is a pharyngeal arch 1 muscle that participates in oral/pharyngeal behaviors and is innervated by the nerve to the medial pterygoid and attaches to the cranial base and the medial side of the mandibular angle.

name: cranial cartilage
description: A cartilage element that is part of the cranial skeleton.

name: dewlap
description: A longitudinal flap of skin that hangs beneath the lower jaw or neck.

name: skin of body
description: The organ covering the body that consists of the dermis and epidermis.

name: median prenasal process
description: Anterior projection of the septum nasi that protrudes through the anterior nasal wall.

name: antenna
description: The paired, usually multiple jointed, sensory organs articulating on the procephalic region of the head capsule; its highly versatile sensory structures are capable to detect the various environmental stimuli. In the context of Drosophila refers to they are the most anterior segmented sensory appendage of the head.

name: zygomatic arch
description: the bony arch in vertebrates that extends along the side or front of the skull beneath the eye socket and is formed by the temporal process of the zygomatic bone and the zygomatic process of the temporal bone

name: metanephric smooth muscle tissue
description: Any smooth muscle tissue that is part of a metanephros.

name: muscle of back
description: Any muscle organ that is part of a back [Automatically generated definition].

name: midbrain nucleus
description: Nucleus located in the midbrain.

name: plume
description: Vascularized tip of their free end of a tubeworm which is an organ for exchanging compounds with the environment.

name: locus ceruleus
description: The locus ceruleus is a dense cluster of neurons within the dorsorostral pons. This nucleus is the major location of neurons that release norepinephrine throughout the brain, and is responsible for physiological responses to stress and panic[GO]. Bluish region in the superior angle of the fourth ventricle floor, corresponding to melanin-like pigmented nerve cells which lie lateral to the ponto-mesencephalic central gray (griseum centrale). It is also known as nucleus pigmentosus pontis[GAID].

name: obsolete portion of cell substance
description: Portion of organism substance located within a cell.

name: enclosed anatomical space
description: An anatomical space with no opening to another space or to the exterior.

name: m. intertransversarius capitus superior
description: Involved in the movement of the head.

name: external sensillum
description: Sensillum which is embedded in the body wall and has a specific cuticular structure involved in the transduction of some sensory signal as a part.

name: endocardium of right ventricle
description: Any endocardium that is part of the right ventricle of the heart.

name: obsolete predominantly gray regional part of parietal lobe
calcarine artery
description: An artery that branches from the medial occipital artery that aligns with the calcarine sulcus.

name: vascular element of left lung
description: A vascular plexus that is part of a left lung.

name: hypobranchial 1 bone
description: Hypobranchial bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates with a median skeletal element medially and with a ceratobranchial 1 element laterally. Develops in hypobranchial 1 cartilage.

name: upper limb segment
description: A limb segment that is part of a forelimb.

name: medial circumflex femoral vein
description: A circumflex femoral vein that accompanies the medial circumflex femoral artery.

name: stria vascularis vasculature
description: blood vessels supplying the stria vascularis in the cochlea of the inner ear.
